INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bonnet', '[\'bɑːnət]', 'n.软帽；无边帽；引擎罩；烟囱罩；壁炉罩；辅助帆 vt.给 ... 戴帽子；给 ... 装罩子', '1. The bonnet was swayed on her head. 那顶小圆软帽歪戴在她的头上。 2. The little girl wears a red bonnet. 那小女孩戴着一顶小红帽。 3. The poke of her black bonnet hide her face from him. 她那黑色帽子的前沿遮住了她的脸，使他看不见。 4. She experienced more trouble while trying to open the bonnet of the car. 她设法把汽车引擎罩打开时碰到了麻烦。', '过去式: bonneted 过去分词: bonneted 现在分词: bonneting 第三人称单数: bonnets');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('optimum', '[\'ɑːptɪməm]', 'adj.最佳的；最适宜的 n.最适宜', '1. The market offers optimum condition for sale. 市场为销售提供了最佳条件。 2. You have established the optimum price. 你已制定了最佳价格。 3. The optimum starting age is ten. 最佳起始年龄是10岁。 4. Now your advice is very optimum. 现在你的建议是很适宜的。 5. Strive for optimum, not maximum, performance. 不求最多、最花哨，只求最适宜。', '名词复数: optima');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('shred', '[ʃred]', 'v.撕成碎片 n.碎布条；细片；少许', '1. I was shredding top-secret documents at that time. 我当时正把机密文件切碎。 2. They send a pile of old invoice to be shred. 他们将一堆旧发票送去切成碎条。 3. We haven\'t got a shred of evidence. 我们没有丝毫证据。', '名词: shredder 过去式: shredded/shred 过去分词: shredded/shred 现在分词: shredding 第三人称单数: shreds');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inordinate', '[ɪn\'ɔːrdɪnət]', 'adj.过度的；非常的；无法无天的', '1. She had an inordinate fondness for junk food. 她喜欢吃零食到了无节制的程度。 2. They spent an inordinate amount of time and money on the production. 他们在生产上投入了过多的时间和资金。 3. The girl has inordinate passion for music. 这个女孩过分喜爱音乐。 4. A winner must be firm and posess strong stamina and inordinate courage. 成功者是需要坚韧的毅力和非凡的勇气的。', '副词: inordinately 名词: inordinacy');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('colossal', '[kə\'lɑːsl]', 'adj. 巨大的； <口>异常的', '1. This is indeed a colossal success. 这确实是个巨大的成功。 2. But to go back to the old ways would be a colossal mistake. 但是，回到老路上将是一个巨大的错误。', '副词: colossally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('progenitor', '[proʊ\'dʒenɪtər]', 'n.祖先；先驱', '1. It is said that our progenitors are monkeys. 据说我们的祖先是猴子。 2. He was the progenitor of a distinguished family. 他是一家名门望族的始祖。 3. Marx is the progenitor of Communism. 马克思是共产主义的创始人。 4. Schoenberg was a progenitor of modern music. 勋伯格是一位现代音乐的先驱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inborn', '[ˌɪn\'bɔːrn]', 'adj.天生的；生来的', '1. Confidence is built, not inborn. 信心是建立起来的，不是天生的。 2. A woman is an inborn guardian of \"home\". 一个女人天生就是一个“家”的守候者。 3. Birds have an inborn ability to fly. 鸟生来就会飞。 4. He has a certain inborn genius that can\'t be taught or learned. 他具有的一些与生俱来的天才我永远无法通过教或者学去获得。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('coltish', '[\'koʊltɪʃ]', 'adj.活泼的；小马(似)的；轻佻的，不受拘束的', '1. Modern toilet sanitation is better, the position is so coltish. 现代化厕所卫生较好，所以位置不受拘束。 2. Jo, fifteen, was tall, thin, and coltish, and gloried in an unconcealed scorn of polite conventions. 乔，十五岁，是个瘦高个活泼的姑娘，她毫不掩饰对斯文习俗的蔑视，并以此自豪。 3. Jo,fifteen,was tall,thin,and coltish,and gloried in an unconcealed scorn of polite conventions. 15岁的乔是个高瘦活泼女孩，得意于对传统礼仪的蔑视； 4. Jo, fifteen, was tall, thin, and coltish , and gloried in an unconcealed scorn of polite conventions. 乔,十五岁,是个瘦高个活泼的姑娘,她毫不掩饰对斯文习俗的蔑视,并以此自豪。', '副词: coltishly 名词: coltishness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dissident', '[\'dɪsɪdənt]', 'adj.有异议的；不同意的 n.意见不同的人；持不同政见者', '1. There were many dissident elements in the population. 人民间尚存有许多意见不合的分子。 2. The dissident was cast out from his country. 这位持不同政见者被驱逐出境。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mundane', '[mʌn\'deɪn]', 'adj.平凡的；世俗的；世界的', '1. I lead a pretty mundane life; nothing interesting ever happens to me. 我生活平凡 2. Even the most mundane things can become objects of beauty in French eyes. 即使是最平凡的事物，在法国人的眼中也是美丽的。 3. The book is full of complicated and sometimes mundane details. 书中充满了复杂,有时甚至是世俗的细节。 4. Each one is contained in a spherical shell surrounded by layers of elemental matter that mark the boundary between mundane space and the unlimited spiritual world. 每个宇宙被物质元素构成的壳所包裹着，这些层层的壳就是物质世界与无限的灵性世界的分界。', '副词: mundanely 名词: mundaneness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dilapidate', '[də\'læpəˌdeɪt]', 'v.(使)荒废；(使)毁坏', '1. Second, they may indulge in it, thus dilapidate their study, which isn\'t rare. 其次，他们会沉迷其中以致荒废了学习，这是不罕见。', '名词: dilapidation 过去式: dilapidated 过去分词: dilapidated 现在分词: dilapidating 第三人称单数: dilapidates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('refractory', '[rɪ\'fræktəri]', 'adj.不听话的；执拗的；难治疗的；免疫的；耐火的 n.倔强的人；耐火材料', '1. Despite very good hospice palliative care, some terminally ill patients still continue to experience intolerable, unrelieved pain and suffering from refractory symptoms. 尽管有很好的安宁缓和疗护，有一些末期病人仍会经历难以忍受无法缓解的疼痛与其他难治疗的症状。 2. Refractory children, lunatics, and criminals may require authority, and may need to be forced to obey. 对倔强的儿童，精神病人以及犯罪的人，需要使用权力，或者需要强迫服从。 3. Top quality basic and non-basic refractory products. 高质量的碱性和非碱性的耐火材料制品。 4. Taphole Mrx is a functional refractory material that used for the blast furnace. 高炉出铁口用炮泥是功能性耐火材料。', '副词: refractorily 名词: refractoriness 名词复数: refractories');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('constitutional', '[ˌkɒnstə\'tjuːʃənəl]', 'adj.宪法的；合乎宪法的；体质的；组成的 n.散步保健', '1. They have made the constitutional reform. 他们已经做了宪法的修改。 2. The United Kingdom is a constitutional monarchy. 英国是君主立宪国。 3. They claimed that the new law was not constitutional. 他们声称这项新法律不符合宪法。 4. It is not constitutional to censor the press. 审查新闻是违反宪法的。 5. He takes a constitutional every morning. 他每天早上都要散步健身。', '副词: constitutionally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('beholder', '[bɪ\'hoʊldər]', 'n.旁观者', '1. When is death our lone beholder? 我们孤独的旁观者什么时候死去？ 2. Macao\'s appeal is very much in the eyes of the beholder. 在旁观者眼中，澳门非常有吸引力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('circumlocution', '[ˌsɜːrkəmlə\'kjuːʃn]', 'n.迂回累赘的陈述；遁词', '1. He is a master at circumlocution. 他讲话很会兜圈子。 2. This sort of ritual circumlocution is common to many parts of mathematics. 这种繁冗的遁辞常见于数学的许多部分分式中。 3. The sort of circumlocution is required in nearly every use of a method that returns null in place of a zero length array. 类遁辞在几乎在零的长度列阵位置退回零位对方法的每个用途需要。', '形容词: circumlocutory 副词: circumlocutorily');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scabrous', '[\'skeɪbrəs]', 'adj.粗糙的；困难的；猥亵的', '1. It differs in the smaller size of all parts and rufous scabrous tomentum. 它在全株各部分较小和红棕色的粗糙的绒毛层的方面不同。', '副词: scabrously 名词: scabrousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('visceral', '[\'vɪsərəl]', 'adj.发自肺腑的；内脏的', '1. Such a visceral reaction could only come from a woman who still cares. 这样发自内心的激烈反应只可能来自仍然关心的女人。 2. There are visceral and parietal peritonea. 有内脏与腔壁的腹膜。 3. So, we really should try to get rid of the excess visceral fat cells. 因此，我们确实应该清除过剩的内脏脂肪细胞。', '副词: viscerally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('oasis', '[oʊ\'eɪsɪs]', 'n.绿洲；宜人之地', '1. This desert of unattractiveness has its oasis . 在这一片枯燥无味的沙漠上，也有一座绿洲。 2. They stopped for the night at an oasis. 他们在沙漠中的绿洲停下来过夜。 3. Borne on the back of the ship of the desert, we reached the oasis at sunset. 我们骑着骆驼，在太阳落山时到达了这块绿洲。 4. The study is an oasis of calm in a noisy household. 在喧闹的家中，书房可谓宁静之一隅。', '名词复数: oases');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sacrilege', '[\'sækrəlɪdʒ]', 'n.亵渎圣物；悖理逆天的行为', '1. It is a sacrilege to steal a crucifix from an altar. 从圣坛窃取耶稣受难像是亵渎神灵的行为。 2. By doing so, she would risk committing a sacrilege. 这样一来她就会冒亵渎神明的危险。 3. She regarded the damage done to the painting as sacrilege. 她认为毁坏了那幅画是大逆不道的事.', '名词: sacrilegist');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('preposterous', '[prɪ\'pɑːstərəs]', 'adj.荒谬的；可笑的', '1. That\'s a preposterous accusation! 那样的指责简直荒谬可笑！ 2. The result is preposterous. 结果很可笑。', '副词: preposterously 名词: preposterousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wobble', '[\'wɑːbl]', 'n.摆动；动摇；不稳定 vi.摇晃；游移不定 vt.使摇晃；使动摇', '1. In other cases, evidence leads to the conclusion that planets must be causing the wobble. 在另一些情况下，由这些证据可得出行星必定要引起摆动的结论。 2. I experienced the most complex and indelible time in my life, including sorrow, happy, defection, wobble and reverie. 我经历了我一生中最复杂也是最难忘的时光,包含了悲伤,快乐,背叛,动摇和幻想的时光。 3. But the stockmarket wobble raises concerns. 然而股市的波动还是引起了人们的关注。 4. I wobble uncertainly for a couple of paces. 我踉跄了几步。 5. Don\'t wobble the desk when I\'m writing. 我写字时你不要摇动桌子。', '名词: wobbler');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('epoch', '[\'epək]', 'n. 时期； 时代； 新纪元； 划时代的大事； <地质>世', '1. Ice age refers to the latest glacial epoch. 冰河时期指的是最近的一个冰川时期。 2. The Revolution had many of these men, proportioned to the epoch. 革命时期有过许多那样的人，都和那时代相称。 3. Einstein\'s theory marked a new epoch in history. 爱因斯坦的理论标志著历史上一个新时代的开始。 4. The epoch of revolution creates great figures. 革命时代造就伟大的人物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dilate', '[daɪ\'leɪt]', 'v.使扩大；扩大；膨胀；详述', '1. Sometimes, I feel I need to dilate my pupils to remain attentive. 有时,我觉得需要扩大瞳孔才能精神集中。 2. The horse dilated its nostrils. 那匹马张大它的鼻孔。 3. The cat dilated its eyes in the darkness. 猫在黑暗中睁大眼睛。 4. The balloon will dilate with air. 气球充气将会膨胀。', '形容词: dilatable 副词: dilatably 名词: dilatability 过去式: dilated 过去分词: dilated 现在分词: dilating 第三人称单数: dilates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('redundancy', '[rɪ\'dʌndənsi]', 'n.冗余；多余信息；备份；裁员', '1. The takeover cause250 redundancy. 接管移交造成250人的裁员。 2. He put all his redundancy money into a shop. 他把所有剩余资金都投入了一家商店。 3. But if the trail of predecessor is long, redundancy can be well hidden. 但是如果前导的联接链很长，那么这种多余就常常隐藏起来。 4. The threat of redundancy was suddenly removed. 裁员的危险顿时消除了。', '名词复数: redundancies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('celestial', '[sə\'lestʃl]', 'adj.天上的；非凡的 n.天神 Celestial. adj.中国的；中国人的 n.中国人', '1. The rosy light yet beamed like a celestial dawn. 玫瑰色的红光依然象天上的朝霞一样绚丽。 2. She is a celestial bodhisattva and an ascended master. 她是天上的菩萨和已提升的大师。 3. And if living in the lower celestial and Brahma realms, their heads are always turned towards the higher planes of those worlds. 虽然他们还在低层的天神界以及梵天界，从那时起，就会转生较高级的天神界以及梵天界。', '副词: celestially');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('brochure', '[broʊ\'ʃʊr]', 'n.小册子，资料手册', '1. I\'ll send you a brochure. 我给你一份小册子。 2. The computer\'s features are detailed in our brochure. 该计算机的特点在我们的小册子中有详细介绍。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('commingle', '[kə\'mɪŋɡl]', 'v.混合；掺和', '1. Ground waters originating in different beds commingle. 来源于不同层位的地下水相互混合。 2. Chinese managers have less trouble accepting that personal feelings and business decisions can commingle. 中国经理人更容易接受把个人的感受与商业决策相混合。', '过去式: commingled 过去分词: commingled 现在分词: commingling 第三人称单数: commingles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('perfidy', '[\'pɜːrfədi]', 'n.不诚实；不忠；背信弃义', '1. All his usual formalities of perfidy were observed with scrupulous technique. 他所有形式的狡诈与不忠都被极其审慎地记录下来。', '名词复数: perfidies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('impose', '[ɪm\'poʊz]', 'v.强加；课征；强迫；征收(税款)', '1. I don\'t want to impose on you by staying too long. 我不想打扰你,不多耽搁了。 2. Do not try to impose your belief upon others. 别试图把你的信仰强加在别人头上。 3. We could not impose our own standards on others. 我们不能把我们的标准强加于他人。 4. He helped the Mongols impose taxes, interceding with the Khan to prevent reprisals when rebellions broke out. 因害怕在诺夫哥罗德人造反时遭到报复，他协助蒙古人征敛赋税。', '名词: imposer 过去式: imposed 过去分词: imposed 现在分词: imposing 第三人称单数: imposes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bifurcate', '[\'baɪfərkeɪt]', 'v.(使)分叉 adj.分叉的；分成两支的', '1. Drainage was to the north and individual channels bifurcate in that direction. 整个水系向北排水，各个河道朝该方向分叉。', '副词: bifurcately 名词: bifurcation 过去式: bifurcated 过去分词: bifurcated 现在分词: bifurcating 第三人称单数: bifurcates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('disavow', '[ˌdɪsə\'vaʊ]', 'v.否认；不赞成', '1. I disavow all responsibility for you. 我不承认对你有任何责任。 2. She disavows any part (ie says she was not involved) in the plot. 她否认参与了这一密谋。', '形容词: disavowable 名词: disavowal 过去式: disavowed 过去分词: disavowed 现在分词: disavowing 第三人称单数: disavows');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('insolence', '[\'ɪnsələns]', 'n.傲慢；无礼', '1. His overbearing insolence angered everyone. 他的傲慢无礼激起了大家的愤怒。 2. Your insolence shall be the death of your people. 是你的傲慢造成了你的人民死亡。 3. His insolence is more than I can stand. 我受不了他的无礼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dissuade', '[dɪ\'sweɪd]', 'v.劝阻', '1. My teacher dissuade me from accepting the job. 老师劝我不要接受这份工作。 2. They try to dissuade her to do that. 他们极力阻止她那样做。', '名词: dissuader 过去式: dissuaded 过去分词: dissuaded 现在分词: dissuading 第三人称单数: dissuades');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('exposition', '[ˌekspə\'zɪʃn]', 'n.博览会；展览会；说明', '1. They are going to hold an international exposition. 他们打算召开一次国际博览会。 2. So the West Lake Exposition has a long history. 那西湖博览会已有很长的历史了。 3. He entered a landscape painting in the Exposition. 他把一幅风景画送展览会展出。 4. The World Exposition is not the same as a trade fair, in which mainly governments and international organizations participate. 世博会不同于贸易展览会，贸易展览会主要是由政府和国际组织参加的。', '形容词: expositive 名词: expositor');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('exultant', '[ɪɡ\'zʌltənt]', 'adj.非常高兴的；欢腾的', '1. Intense and especially ecstatic or exultant happiness. 欢欣，喜悦，高兴强烈的喜悦，尤指狂喜或欢腾的喜悦', '副词: exultantly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('aversion', '[ə\'vɜːrʒn]', 'n.嫌恶；憎恨', '1. Girls generally have an aversion to snakes. 姑娘们通常对蛇很嫌恶。 2. Do you feel any aversion to hard study? 你嫌恶努力学习吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('complementary', '[ˌkɑːmplɪ\'mentri]', 'adj.补充的；互补的', '1. His personality is complementary to hers. 他的个性与她的相反相成。 2. The two viewpoints are complementary and both approaches are of interest. 这两种方法是互为补充的而且都是有价值的。 3. Red and green are complementary colors. 红色和绿色是互补色。 4. Our two countries are mutually complementary in economy. 我们两国的经济是互补的。', '副词: complementarily 名词: complementariness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('floodgate', '[\'flʌdɡeɪt]', 'n.泄水闸门；防洪闸门；(怒气等的)制约；大量', '1. The floodgate is closed to control the flow of water. 为了控制水流，防洪闸门关闭了。 2. However, to my amazement, this award seemed to open a floodgate of money. 但出乎我意料的是，这个奖项为我打开了一扇喷涌金钱的闸门。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ramble', '[\'ræmbl]', 'vi.漫步；漫谈；漫游；蔓延 n.【C】漫步；闲谈；漫游；漫笔', '1. I like rambling around in the country. 我喜欢在乡间漫步。 2. The old man rambled about the past. 老者在聊过去的事情。 3. Speakers who ramble are almost inevitably bores. 信口开河的演说家几乎是不可避免地要讨人嫌恶。 4. The clouds ramble in the sky everyday. 云彩每天都在天空中游走。 5. We went for a ramble through the woods. 我们散步穿过树林。', '过去式: rambled 过去分词: rambled 现在分词: rambling 第三人称单数: rambles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('concussion', '[kən\'kʌʃn]', 'n.脑震荡；震动', '1. She suffers from brain concussion. 她得了脑震荡。 2. He was taken to hospital with concussion. 他因脑震荡被送进医院。', '形容词: concussive 副词: concussively');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('straightforward', '[ˌstreɪt\'fɔːrwərd]', 'adj.易懂的；笔直的；坦率的', '1. The instructions are reasonably straightforward. 用法说明还算简单易懂。 2. I wonder if the literature can be put in straightforward Chinese. 我不知道那些说明书能不能译成简明易懂的中文。 3. This book presents an up-to-date, straightforward course for students. 这本书为学生提供了一本最新式的、简明易懂的教程。 4. They took a straightforward route to the lake. 他们走了一条笔直通向湖的路。', '副词: straightforwardly 名词: straightforwardness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ameliorate', '[ə\'miːliəreɪt]', 'vt.使改善；使变好 vi.改善；变好', '1. Everyone wishes to ameliorate his own condition . 改善自己境况的愿望人皆有之。 2. He works hard to ameliorate his family\'s poor circumstances. 他努力地工作以改善家庭的穷困。 3. It is not clear what can be done to ameliorate the situation. 不清楚我们能做些什么来改变这个情况。 4. Self-talk can thus ameliorate our status. 因此，与自己对话可以改善我们的现状。', '过去式: ameliorated 过去分词: ameliorated 现在分词: ameliorating 第三人称单数: ameliorates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gnawing', '[\'nɔːɪŋ]', 'adj.咬的；痛苦的；折磨人的 动词gnaw的现在分词形式.', '1. After three days, we felt the gnawing pains of hunger. 三天后，我们感到了饥肠绞痛。 2. I\'ve had gnawing doubts about this project for some time. 这个项目已经困扰我一段时间了。 3. At night gnawing pain pierces my bones. 夜间痛苦刺透我骨。 4. From the ground had risen a gnawing frost that chilled him to the bone. 地面上升起一股刺骨的寒气，使他冷彻骨髓。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vicissitudinous', '[vɪsɪsɪ\'tjuːdɪnəs]', 'adj.有变化的；变迁的；有盛衰的', '1. This article finds the developmental and vicissitudinous law, and realizes the inevitability of development. 找到了油画“角色”发展变迁的规律，并认识到发展的必然性。 2. In the meantime, the metope that finds a sitting room to do not let a person too too drab, made wall of one side vicissitudinous again. 同时，为了不让人感觉到客厅的墙面太过单调，又做了一面有变化的墙。 3. So when one investigates the style of legal English, he is to take the vicissitudinous history of Great Britain into account. 所以，当我们要考察法律英语的风格时，我们必须把大不列颠岛曲折的历史考虑进去。 4. A Primary Study on the Vicissitudinous Machanism of the Social-Cultural Environment in the Tourist Destinations 旅游地社会文化环境变迁机制试研究', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('winkle', '[\'wɪŋkl]', 'v.挑出；剔出；设法搞到；把...驱逐出去 n.滨螺；玉黍螺', '1. You can use the toothpick to winkle the shellfish out of its shell. 你可以用牙签把贝肉从贝壳中挖出来。 2. I managed to winkle the truth out of him. 我设法从他那里探到了真相。 3. They managed to winkle out the spy. 他们设法找出了这个间碟。 4. The waiter winkled the beggar out of the restaurant. 侍者把乞丐赶出饭店。', '过去式: winkled 过去分词: winkled 现在分词: winkling 第三人称单数: winkles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fleece', '[fliːs]', 'n.羊毛；一次剪得的羊毛；羊毛状物 v.欺诈', '1. These sheep have fine thick fleeces. 这些绵羊的毛又细又厚。 2. The sheep\'s fleece was white as snow. 羊毛是雪白的。 3. Let man wear the fell of the lion, woman the fleece of the sheep. 让男人穿狮皮,女人穿羊毛。 4. They fleeced us at that hotel. 那家旅馆敲了我们一笔钱。', '名词: fleecer 过去式: fleeced 过去分词: fleeced 现在分词: fleecing 第三人称单数: fleeces');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('coward', '[\'kaʊərd]', 'n.懦夫 adj.胆小的 Coward. n.科沃德(姓氏)', '1. Only a coward gives in to his fate. 只有懦夫向命运屈服。 2. He is a coward by his own admission. 他自己承认是个胆小鬼。 3. There is a coward silence when the stern principal come in. 严厉的校长走进来时,大家胆怯得不敢出声。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('condemn', '[kən\'dem]', 'vt.谴责；判刑', '1. We must not condemn her on pure supposition. 我们不能单凭猜测就谴责她。 2. We condemn all sorts of slanders. 我们谴责一切诽谤中伤的言论。 3. Most people are willing to condemn violence. 大部分的人极力谴责暴力。 4. The criminal was condemned to death. 这个罪犯被判死刑。', '形容词: condemnable 名词: condemner 过去式: condemned 过去分词: condemned 现在分词: condemning 第三人称单数: condemns');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('indecipherable', '[ˌɪndɪ\'saɪfrəbl]', 'adj.辨读不出的；无法破译的；无法解释的', '1. His signature is indecipherable. 他的签字无法辨认。 2. As a rule, computer languages are indecipherable to the average person. 通常电脑语言是一般人无法解读的。 3. The coded message was indecipherable. 这份用密码写的消息译不出来。 4. Traditional economy theory is indecipherable to this. 传统经济理论对此无法解释。', '副词: indecipherably 名词: indecipherability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('abuse', '[ə\'bjuːs]', 'n.滥用；恶习 vt.滥用；辱骂；虐待', '1. The government has set up a working party to look into the problem of drug abuse. 政府已成立工作组调查滥用毒品问题。 2. His political reputation was tainted by his abuse of the power. 他因滥用职权而破坏了政治声誉。 3. He greeted me with a stream of abuse. 他见到我就连声辱骂。 4. It\'s easy to abuse one\'s power. 人容易滥用权力。', '名词: abuser 过去式: abused 过去分词: abused 现在分词: abusing 第三人称单数: abuses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('solemn', '[\'sɑːləm]', 'adj.庄严的；严肃的；隆重的', '1. The ceremony proceeded in a solemn atmosphere. 仪式在庄严的气氛中进行。 2. They watched the solemn ceremony. 他们观看那庄严的仪式。 3. He looked at her with a solemn expression. 他表情严肃地望着她。 4. Her solemn face told them that the news was bad. 她严肃的表情告诉他们那是坏消息。', '副词: solemnly 名词: solemnness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('luscious', '[\'lʌʃəs]', 'adj.甘美的；浓厚的；官能的；性感的', '1. I like the luscious taste of ripe peaches. 我喜欢熟桃的香甜味。 2. The pineapple was very luscious. 菠萝很可口。 3. The dancers bathed in luscious strains. 跳舞者沉浸在悦耳的乐曲中。 4. She is a luscious blonde. 她是个迷人的金发女郎。', '副词: lusciously 名词: lusciousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('illustrious', '[ɪ\'lʌstriəs]', 'adj.著名的；杰出的', '1. He studied painting under illustrious masters. 他在著名大师的指导下学画。 2. Don\'t pull your illustrious past on me. 别把你那辉煌的过去灌输给我啦。 3. Washington and Lincoln are illustrious Americans. 华盛顿和林肯都是杰出的美国人。 4. His illustrious accomplishments made him one of the greatest men in this century. 他的杰出成就使他成为本世纪最伟大的人物之一。', '副词: illustriously 名词: illustriousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lace', '[leɪs]', 'n.鞋带；饰带；花边；缎带 v.系带子；饰以花边；把酒搀入；<口>抨击', '1. He stopped to do up his shoe lace. 他停下来把鞋带系上。 2. My shoe lace keeps coming undone. 我的鞋带老是松开。 3. My daughter wears a dress embellished with lace and ribbons today. 今天我女儿穿了一件有花边和饰带的连衣裙。 4. She wears a dress with delicate lace. 她穿了一件带有精致花边的裙子。 5. If you don\'t lace up your shoes, you\'ll trip over. 如果你不系好鞋带，你会被绊倒的。', '形容词: laceless 名词: lacer 过去式: laced 过去分词: laced 现在分词: lacing 第三人称单数: laces');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scamper', '[\'skæmpər]', 'n.蹦跳；奔跑 v.蹦跳', '1. The children were scampering around the garden. 孩子们在花园里嬉戏奔跑。 2. She loves to scamper through the woods of the forest. 她喜欢在森林里的树林中穿梭嬉戏.', '过去式: scampered 过去分词: scampered 现在分词: scampering 第三人称单数: scampers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cant', '[kænt]', 'n.倾斜；斜面；斜角；伪善之言；黑话 v.(使)倾斜；伪善地说；说术语 adj.倾斜的', '1. The ship took on a dangerous cant to port. 船只出现向左舷危险倾斜。 2. There has been a great deal of politician\'s cant. 说了一大堆政客惯用的言不由衷的话。 3. The Prefect was fond of the cant of diplomacy. 这位警察局长很爱好外交辞令。', '副词: cantingly 名词: cantingness 过去式: canted 过去分词: canted 现在分词: canting 第三人称单数: cants');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('embellish', '[ɪm\'belɪʃ]', 'v.美化、装饰或修饰；渲染或添枝加叶', '1. We embellish our room with new rug, lamp, and picture. 我们以新地毯，灯和图画布置我们的房间。 2. My daughter wears a dress embellished with lace and ribbons today. 今天我女儿穿了一件有花边和饰带的连衣裙。 3. Nothing can embellish a beautiful face more than a narrow band drawn over the brow. 除了一条横束额上的细带而外，没有别的东西能把美丽的面庞衬托得更好的了。 4. He often embellishes the tales of his travels. 他常给他的旅游趣闻添枝加叶。', '名词: embellisher 过去式: embellished 过去分词: embellished 现在分词: embellishing 第三人称单数: embellishes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('statutory', '[\'stætʃətɔːri]', 'adj.法定的；法令的；触犯法令的', '1. There\'s no question of bypassing a statutory procedure. 法定程序是回避不了的。 2. This guarantee does not affect your statutory rights. 这项保证不会影响你的法定权利。 3. No one can excess the statutory juristiction. 任何人都不得超越法令的管辖权。 4. In short, both the statutory context and the policy choices presented in this area are atypical. 总之，这方面法令的内容和政策的选择都不是典型的。', '副词: statutorily');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('coruscate', '[\'kɔːrəskeɪt]', 'vi.闪亮；闪光', '1. What kind of mood can let person mind coruscate? 什么样心情可以让人精神焕发? 2. Will old building is redesigned decorate, let its coruscate give luster. 房子的空间重新设计装修好之后，接下来就是房间内部的色彩和摆设了。 3. The clean and elegant color and structure coruscate the unique expressive force and permanent life. 清雅的色彩与结构,在纷繁的世界里,焕发出独特的表现力和持久的生命力。 4. Efficacy: Reject oil and coruscate full luster; an effective cleansing mask makes your skin fresh, transparent and comfortable. 功效：拒绝油光，焕发肌肤净透光采；一款带来深层洁净的卓效面膜，让你的肌肤前所未有的清澈、透明，感觉无比清爽、舒适。', '名词: coruscation 过去式: coruscated 过去分词: coruscated 现在分词: coruscating 第三人称单数: coruscates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('slosh', '[slɑːʃ]', 'v.泼溅；搅动；在泥中荡；(液体)晃动作响 n.雪泥；泼溅声', '1. To remove bacteria, slosh hot water around your mouth with your cheek muscles. 把热水放在口中，用你的两颊的肌肉进行搅动，可除去细菌。 2. Wrongly applied credit can slosh around, drive up costs and create excess capacity. 错误提供的贷款会搅动市场，抬高成本并制造过剩产能。', '形容词: sloshy 过去式: sloshed 过去分词: sloshed 现在分词: sloshing 第三人称单数: sloshes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('arid', '[\'ærɪd]', 'adj.干燥的；不毛的；枯燥的；无趣的；没有生气的', '1. The broom grows down the arid sandhill. 金雀草蔓延在干燥的沙丘下。 2. It is difficult to grow fruit in arid desert areas. 在干燥的沙漠地带栽培水果很困难。 3. How can people make a living in this arid area? 这片不毛之地上的人们怎么谋生呢？ 4. The audience soon grew tired of his arid speech. 没多久听众对他枯燥无味的演说就感到厌腻了。', '名词: aridity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('spat', '[spæt]', 'n.小争吵；轻打声；<口> 轻拍 n.鞋罩 n.贝卵；蚝卵；蚝仔 v.轻轻拍打；发生小争吵 动词spit的过去式和过去分词', '1. Her parents always have spats. 她的父母经常有些小的口角。 2. There is only a spat between the brother and sister. 那只是兄妹间的小吵小闹。 3. He took one sip of the wine and spat it out. 他抿了一口酒，又吐了出来。 4. She spat at his face in contempt. 她吐口水在他的脸上，以此表示对他的蔑视。', '名词复数: spat 过去式: spatted 过去分词: spatted 现在分词: spatting 第三人称单数: spats');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('disaster', '[dɪ\'zæstər]', 'n.灾难', '1. They had led the country into economic disaster. 他们把国家带入了经济灾难中。 2. The disaster caused him to waver in his faith. 这件灾难使他对信仰发生了动摇。 3. He spoke darkly of possible future disaster. 他悲观地说将来可能大难临头。 4. We are all pervaded with a sense of disaster. 我们普遍有大祸降临的感觉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('penetration', '[ˌpenɪ\'treɪʃn]', 'n.侵入；渗透；突破；洞察力', '1. Penetration by foreign capitalism accelerated this process. 外国资本主义的侵入，促进了这种发展。 2. We don\'t have one hundred percent market penetration. 但我们的市场渗透率并没有达到百分之百。 3. The material has good penetration and good water-resistance. 这种材料具有高度的渗透力及良好的防水性能。 4. The German penetration of the Allied lines was a damning commentary on the supposed (invulnerability) of the Maginot Line. 马奇诺防线据说是固若金汤这一点，已被德军突破盟军防线这件事驳得体无完肤了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('benign', '[bɪ\'naɪn]', 'adj.仁慈的；温和的；良性的', '1. My mother\'s character is very benign. 我母亲非常慈祥。 2. The heat, the bureaucracy, the confusion and complications of his job, had reduced him in seven years to a blob of benign jelly. 炎热的天气，官僚政治和他工作的错综复杂和混乱，在七个年头里已使他变成一个仁慈的和稀泥老手。 3. The benign weather brought North America a bumper crop. 温和的气候给北美带来大丰收。 4. After tests the tumor was found to be benign. 检测发现肿瘤是良性的。', '副词: benignly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('derogate', '[\'derəɡeɪt]', 'v.贬低；诽谤；减损', '1. People often derogate what they don\'t understand. 人们常诋毁他们不懂的东西。 2. Such behavior will derogate from your image. 这样的行为将损及你的形象。', '名词: derogation 过去式: derogated 过去分词: derogated 现在分词: derogating 第三人称单数: derogates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('funereal', '[fju\'nɪriəl]', 'adj.适合葬礼的；悲哀的；送葬的', '1. The mood of the music was almost funereal. 音乐的调子几乎像哀乐。 2. He was walking at a funereal pace. 他迈着悲伤的步伐慢慢地走着。', '副词: funereally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('verisimilitude', '[ˌverɪsɪ\'mɪlɪtuːd]', 'n.逼真；逼真的事物', '1. These flower illustrations show the artist\'s concern for verisimilitude. 这些花卉插图表明这个画家很注重写实。', '形容词: verisimilitudinous');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('trend', '[trend]', 'n.趋势；倾向；方位 vi.倾向；转向', '1. The trend of prices is still upward. 物价仍有上涨趋势。 2. The youth like to follow the latest trends in fashion. 年轻人喜好追求最新的流行款式。 3. This quartet represents a major new trend in modern music. 这首四重奏的曲子反映了现代音乐中一种主要的新趋向。 4. The event changed the trend of public opinion. 这件事改变了舆论的趋向。 5. The prices of houses are trending upwards. 房价趋于上涨。', '过去式: trended 过去分词: trended 现在分词: trending 第三人称单数: trends');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bombast', '[\'bɑːmbæst]', 'n.浮夸的言语；高调', '1. His speech was full of bombast. 他的讲演通篇是夸夸其谈。', '形容词: bombastic 副词: bombastically 名词: bombaster');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('outskirts', '[\'aʊtskɜːrts]', 'n.郊区 名词outskirt的复数.', '1. We live on the outskirts of the city. 我们住在这个城市的郊区。 2. The hotel is situated in the outskirts of the city. 这个酒店位于城市的郊区。 3. You may as well take a brief look at the outskirts and the city along the way. 大家不妨欣赏一下沿途郊区和市区的景色。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('leverage', '[\'levərɪdʒ]', 'n.杠杆；杠杆作用；举债经营 v.举债经营；补充(金钱等)；对…产生影响', '1. We can lift extremely heavy things by leverage. 通过杠杆，我们可以提起极其沉重的东西。 2. In the market economy system, we should give full play to the leverage of price. 在市场经济体制下,我们应充分发挥价格的杠杆作用。 3. Our enterprise is different from its counterparts: we grow and flourish by leverage. 我们企业与其他同类企业不一样,我们是通过举债经营才得以成长发达的。 4. With such a small amount of capital in hand, we have no other choice but leverage this company. 我们手上的资金太少了,不得不使这家公司举债经营。', '过去式: leveraged 过去分词: leveraged 现在分词: leveraging 第三人称单数: leverages');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tragedy', '[\'trædʒədi]', 'n.悲剧；灾难；惨事', '1. Tragedy is in store for that poor girl from the beginning. 从一开始，那个女孩的悲剧就是不可避免的。 2. Shakespeare\'s Hamlet is a very famous tragedy. 莎士比亚的《哈姆雷特》是一部十分著名的悲剧。 3. It was not long before tragedy struck again. 没多久，灾难又再次降临。 4. This recent tragedy has put the manufacturersof the drug squarely in the dock. 新近发生的这一悲惨事件使药品厂商受到指控。', '名词复数: tragedies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wallop', '[\'wɑːləp]', 'v.重击；猛打；蹒跚；滚沸 n.猛击；痛击', '1. She walloped the ball (for) miles. 她把球打出很远很远。 2. My father used to wallop me if I told lies. 以前我要是说谎，我父亲就狠狠揍我。 3. He crashed down on the floor with a wallop. 他砰的一声倒在地板上了。 4. My mother gave me such a wallop when she eventually found me. 妈妈最后找到我时狠狠揍了我一顿。', '名词: walloper 过去式: walloped 过去分词: walloped 现在分词: walloping 第三人称单数: wallops');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('transparent', '[træns\'pærənt]', 'adj.透明的；明显的；清晰的', '1. Plain glass is transparent. 普通的白玻璃是透明的。 2. The insect\'s wings are almost transparent. 这昆虫的翅膀几乎是透明的。 3. It was transparent that her pride was hurt. 很显然，她的自尊心受到了伤害。 4. Your words are a transparent lie. 你所说的明显是谎言。', '副词: transparently 名词: transparentness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unearth', '[ʌn\'ɜːrθ]', 'v.发掘；掘出；发现并披露', '1. You will unearth a whole new history. 你们将会挖掘出一个完整的新历史。 2. They will unearth the buried treasure here. 他们将在这儿挖掘地下宝藏。 3. You may also unearth an ugly side of their personalities. 你会突然发现他们个性中让人讨厌的一面。 4. I\'ve asked Shirley to see what she can unearth on them. 我已经让雪莉去调查他们的情况了。', '过去式: unearthed 过去分词: unearthed 现在分词: unearthing 第三人称单数: unearths');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('taper', '[\'teɪpər]', 'n.小蜡烛；蜡芯；尖锥形；渐弱 v.逐渐变小；逐渐消失 adj.尖细的；划分等级的', '1. They had red tapers on the table at Christmastime. 在圣诞节期间他们在桌子上点红色的细蜡烛。 2. Financial aids generally taper off after the first year of college. 助学金通常在大学一年级之后逐渐减少。 3. Taper the plug off a bit with the chisel so that it will fit into the hole. 用凿子把塞子的一头削掉一点，使它能塞进洞里。 4. The storm is beginning to taper off now. 风暴现在逐渐减弱了。', '副词: taperingly 过去式: tapered 过去分词: tapered 现在分词: tapering 第三人称单数: tapers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('preempt', '[priː\'empt]', 'v.以优先购买权获得；先占；(桥牌中)先发制人地叫牌；优先；取代', '1. The council found that their traffic plans had been preempted by a government decision. 市议会发现他们的交通规划已因政府先行作了决定而无法推行。', '形容词: preemptory 异体字: pre-empt 名词: preemptor 过去式: preempted 过去分词: preempted 现在分词: preempting 第三人称单数: preempts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('latency', '[\'leɪtənsi]', 'n.潜伏；潜伏期；延迟', '1. The virus remains latent in the body for many years. 病毒在体内潜伏数年。 2. These occur after a variable latency period. 这些变数发生后潜伏期。 3. Six studies gave results for malignant brain tumours in that latency group. 有六个研究在潜伏期的族群当中发现恶性脑瘤。 4. This article will help students understand the factors that increase network latency. 这篇文章将帮助学生了解增加网路延迟的因素。', '名词复数: latencies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('abundance', '[ə\'bʌndəns]', 'n.丰富；充裕', '1. At the party there is food and drink in abundance. 宴会中有丰富的食物和饮料。 2. This country has an abundance of natural resources. 这个国家拥有丰富的天然资源。 3. There was an abundance of corn last year. 去年玉米丰收。 4. Carpets are available in abundance. 可供地毯货源充足。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('guillotine', '[\'ɡɪlətiːn]', 'n.断头台；切纸机；<英>截止辩论的时限 v.斩决；<英>停止对…的辩论而进行表决', '1. The guillotine will soon strike off his dead. 他就要上断头台了。 2. Within twenty-four hours he died on the guillotine. 不出24小时,他就死在断头台上。 3. Not many French people are in favour of using the guillotine. 没有多少法国人赞成使用断头台。 4. Cutter is mainly divided into mechanical paper cutting machine and hydraulic guillotine. 切纸机主要分为机械切纸机和液压切纸机。 5. Many members of the aristocracy were guillotined in France during the Revolution. 大革命时期法国许多贵族被送上断头台。', '过去式: guillotined 过去分词: guillotined 现在分词: guillotining 第三人称单数: guillotines');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flay', '[fleɪ]', 'v.剥皮；去皮；抢夺；痛责', '1. A good shepherd must fleece his sheep but not flay them. 好牧人只剪羊毛，不剥羊皮。（不要杀鸡取卵） 2. He was going to flay that stranger with every trick known to the law. 他要用法律上所有的招数来痛斥那个陌生人。', '名词: flayer 过去式: flayed 过去分词: flayed 现在分词: flaying 第三人称单数: flays');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('garish', '[\'ɡerɪʃ]', 'adj.过分装饰的；炫耀的；俗气的；耀眼的', '1. It\'s a little too garish for my taste. 对于我的品位来说，这个有点过于装饰了。 2. They climbed the garish purple-carpeted stairs. 他们爬上了铺着华丽的紫色地毯的梯子。 3. It\'s just a store in a garish shopping center. 这不过是一家俗气的购物中心旁边的一家小店。', '副词: garishly 名词: garishness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gardenia', '[ɡɑːr\'diːniə]', 'n.栀子花；栀子', '1. On muggy summer night, gardenia brought about memories in the South. 闷热的夏夜，栀子花带来关于南方的回忆。 2. The writer alwalys received a gardenia every day in summer from child to adult. 作者从小到大每到夏天每天都会收到一支栀子花。 3. The stability of gardenia red pigment was studied in this essay. 本文对栀子红色素的稳定性做了研究。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('actuate', '[\'æktʃueɪt]', 'vt.促使；开动（机器等）', '1. He was actuated solely by greed. 他完全是受了贪欲的驱使。', '名词: actuation 过去式: actuated 过去分词: actuated 现在分词: actuating 第三人称单数: actuates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fast', '[fæst]', 'adj.快的；迅速的；紧的；牢固的；放荡的 adv.快速地；紧紧地；放荡地；深深地 n.斋戒；禁食；系泊用具 v.斋戒；禁食', '1. I like fast music. 我喜欢节奏快的音乐。 2. The star was whipped into a fast car and driven off. 那个明星迅速上了一辆汽车疾驶而去。 3. The post is fast in the ground. 那柱子牢牢地埋在地里. 4. He led a fast life. 他过着放荡的生活。 5. He ran fast enough to catch the thief. 他跑得飞快，足以抓住那小偷。 6. The priest had only water and bread during his three week fast. 牧师在三个星期的斋戒期间只进食水和面包。 7. They have to fast from dawn to dusk. 他们一整天都得禁食。', '比较级: faster 最高级: fastest 过去式: fasted 过去分词: fasted 现在分词: fasting 第三人称单数: fasts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('blossom', '[\'blɑːsəm]', 'n.花；开花；全盛期 vi.开花；成长', '1. The sunshine will bring out the blossom. 阳光将使花朵开放。 2. The tree was covered with beautiful pink blossom. 这树开满了美丽的粉红色的花。 3. The apple trees are in blossom. 苹果树正在开花。 4. There are many pear trees covered in blossom. 那里有许多开满花的梨树。 5. The apple trees are blossoming. 苹果树正在开花。', '形容词: blossomy 过去式: blossomed 过去分词: blossomed 现在分词: blossoming 第三人称单数: blossoms');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lubricate', '[\'luːbrɪkeɪt]', 'v.润滑；加润滑剂', '1. My throat needs lubricating. 我需要润润嗓子了。 2. We find it necessary to lubricate machines. 我们认为给机器加润滑油是必要的。 3. If you never bother to lubricate your engine, of course it will seize up. 如果你老是怕麻烦，不给发动机添加润滑油，发动机当然会失灵卡住啦。', '形容词: lubricative 名词: lubrication 过去式: lubricated 过去分词: lubricated 现在分词: lubricating 第三人称单数: lubricates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('muck', '[mʌk]', 'n.垃圾；粪肥；污物；淤泥 v.施肥；弄脏；弄糟', '1. The last book he wrote was sheer muck. 他写的最后一本书全是无价值的东西。 2. Money is like muck,not good except it be spread. 金钱好比粪肥,撒在大地上才有用。 3. I\'ll have to scrub off all the oil muck. 我得把这些油污都擦洗掉。 4. There was muck everywhere. 到处都是淤泥。 5. The farmers muck their orchards each year. 农夫们每年为果园施肥。', '形容词: mucky 副词: muckily 过去式: mucked 过去分词: mucked 现在分词: mucking 第三人称单数: mucks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('shoddy', '[\'ʃɑːdi]', 'adj.劣质的 n.软再生毛(织物)；劣质品', '1. His essay was a pretty shoddy piece of work. 他写的文章很蹩脚。 2. Our new washing machine keeps breaking down, and it\'s entirely due to shoddy workmanship. 我们的新洗衣机老出毛病', '副词: shoddily 比较级: shoddier 最高级: shoddiest 名词: shoddiness 名词复数: shoddies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cornet', '[\'kɔːrnɪt]', 'n.短号；(盛冰淇淋的)圆锥形蛋卷', '1. He played the cornet in the school band. 他在学校乐队吹奏短号。 2. I saw a small boy licking an ice-cream cornet. 我看到一个小孩在吃冰淇淋蛋卷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nucleus', '[\'nuːkliəs]', 'n.核；核心；细胞核；原子核', '1. A nucleus can have only one Y-chromosome. 一个核可以仅有一个Y染色体。 2. These council will form the nucleus of a future regime. 这些委员会将成为一个未来政权的核心。 3. These paintings will form the nucleus of a new collection. 这些油画将是新收藏品的核心。 4. These 1000 books will form the nucleus of the new school library. 这一千本书将构成学校新图书馆藏书的基础。', '名词复数: nuclei');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inflammation', '[ˌɪnflə\'meɪʃn]', 'n.发炎；炎症；燃烧；激动', '1. He has an inflammation of the lungs. 他得了肺炎。 2. Many babies develop a mild inflammation in the eyes a few days after birth. 许多婴孩出生几天以后眼睛会有轻微的发炎。 3. Inflammation plays a major role in these processes. 炎症在以上过程中起了重要的作用。 4. The submucosa shows intense inflammation. 黏膜下层有严重的炎症。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cue', '[kjuː]', 'n.暗示；提示；信号；（台球的）球杆 vt.给 ... 提示；把 ... 插入演出', '1. When I nod my head, that\'s your cue to interrupt the meeting. 我一点头，就是暗示你把会议中断。 2. The actor picked up his cue with effect. 演员对他所得到的提示迅速地作出了反应，效果良好。 3. The horses reacted as if on cue. 马像得了信号一样地起了反应。 4. Can you cue me when you want me to begin speaking? 你要我开始讲话时能给我暗示一下吗?', '过去式: cued 过去分词: cued 现在分词: cuing 第三人称单数: cues');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('legitimate', '[lɪ\'dʒɪtɪmət]', 'adj.合法的；世袭的；婚生的；正当的；合理的 vt.使合法；授权；宣布 ... 为合法', '1. I\'m not sure that his business is strictly legitimate. 我说不好他的生意是否全部合法。 2. He is a legitimate heir to the throne. 他是王位的合法继承人。 3. a legitimate son. 婚生子 4. Politicians are legitimate targets for satire. 政治家理所当然是讽刺的靶子。 5. Distributed Denial of Service, which depletes the network\'s resource and denies service to legitimate users, is one of the hardest security problems in the Internet. 分布式拒绝服务攻击，目的在于耗尽网络资源从而使合法用户的服务请求被拒绝，是最难解决的网络安全问题之一。', '副词: legitimately 名词: legitimateness 过去式: legitimated 过去分词: legitimated 现在分词: legitimating 第三人称单数: legitimates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incessant', '[ɪn\'sesnt]', 'adj.不断的；无尽的', '1. The incessant barking of the dog annoyed me. 不断的狗叫声让我苦恼。 2. We felt put out by the guest\'s incessant requests. 客人不断的要求令我们觉得受打扰。', '副词: incessantly 名词: incessancy');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('homogeneity', '[ˌhɑːmədʒə\'niːəti]', 'n.同种；同质；同次性', '1. There is a remarkable homogeneity between the two companies. 那两家公司极为相似。 2. It must take place at one single time to ensure the homogeneity of the juice. 采摘必须一次完成，这样才能保证果汁的同一性。', '名词复数: homogeneities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('zoom', '[zuːm]', 'v.急速上升；嗡嗡作响；（镜头）拉近（拉远） n.急速上升；嗡嗡声；(摄影)变焦', '1. Overnight trading caused share prices to zoom up. 一夜的交投使股票价格直线上升。 2. We heard a jet plane zooming overhead. 我们听见喷射机在头上嗡嗡作响。 3. If you zoom out at this point, we shall get a view of the whole square. 如果你在此地把镜头推远，我们将看到整个广场。 4. The airplane\' s zoom carried it above the clouds. 飞机的陡直上升使它飞到云层之上。', '过去式: zoomed 过去分词: zoomed 现在分词: zooming 第三人称单数: zooms');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('crepuscular', '[krɪ\'pʌskjələr]', 'adj.微光的；黄昏的；拂晓的', '1. Bats are crepuscular creatures. 蝙蝠是在黎明或黄昏时分活动的动物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('coffer', '[\'kɔːfər]', 'n.保险箱；（建筑物的）镶板；防水堰 （复数）coffers: 金库. v.放入保险箱；用平顶镶板装饰', '1. Years passed, happy years when the roses bloomed and the copper coffer grew. 几年过去了，幸福的几年过去了，这几年玫瑰开放，铜保险箱在变大。', '过去式: coffered 过去分词: coffered 现在分词: coffering 第三人称单数: coffers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('accomplice', '[ə\'kɑːmplɪs]', 'n.共犯；同谋；帮凶', '1. The man was suspected as an accomplice. 那个人被怀疑为共犯。 2. In the accomplice, abettors\' problems attract scholars most.So far, some problems of abettors are not solved, and fail to come to any agreement. 在共犯中，教唆犯的问题更是受到学者们的关注，但是关于教唆犯的一些问题至今没有解决，莫衷一是。 3. He is suspected as an accomplice. 他有同谋嫌疑。 4. He was shortly to be tried at Aix with his accomplice. 不久他就得在艾克斯和他的同谋女犯一同受审。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('thorny', '[\'θɔːrni]', 'adj.多刺的；棘手的；痛苦的', '1. Cacti are thorny. 仙人掌多刺。 2. We are discussing a thorny matter. 我们在讨论一个棘手的问题。 3. Race relations in the US continue to be a thorny problem. 美国的种族关系一直是棘手的问题。 4. Mr Armytage had to endure the sufferings of the thorny crown made by himself. 阿米塔奇先生不得不忍受自找的痛苦的折磨。', '副词: thornily 比较级: thornier 最高级: thorniest 名词: thorniness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('combustible', '[kəm\'bʌstəbl]', 'adj.易燃的；燃烧性的；易激动的 n.燃质物；可燃物', '1. Petrol is highly combustible. 汽油极易燃。 2. It was surrounded with heaps of combustible materials. 它周围是一堆堆易燃物资。 3. He has a combustible temperament. 他易冲动。 4. We must keep these combustibles away from the fire. 我们必须使这些易燃物远离火焰。', '副词: combustibly 名词: combustibility');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('shroud', '[ʃraʊd]', 'n.寿衣；裹尸布；覆盖物 v.用某物覆盖或遮蔽某物', '1. There are no pockets in a shroud. 寿衣没有口袋。 2. With my thread and needle, I’ll make the shroud. 用我的针和线，我将为他做寿衣。 3. The doctor wanted us to use the sheet for a shroud. 医生想让我们用床单当裹尸布。 4. A shroud of secrecy surrounds the plan. 这个计划神秘莫测。 5. The whole jail was shrouded in darkness. 整座监狱笼罩在黑暗之中。', '过去式: shrouded 过去分词: shrouded 现在分词: shrouding 第三人称单数: shrouds');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cubicle', '[\'kjuːbɪkl]', 'n.小室', '1. A technical sergeant hunches in a cubicle. 一位技术军士在一间小屋里弯腰坐着。 2. She studies in a cubicle in the school library. 她在学校图书馆的小自习室里学习。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stale', '[steɪl]', 'adj.不新鲜的；陈腐的；厌倦的 v.变得不新鲜；腐坏；(动物)撒尿 n.(动物的)尿', '1. His hunger makes his stale bread go down. 饥饿使他把这不新鲜的面包吞了下去。 2. He always bought two loaves of stale bread. 他总是要买两个不新鲜的面包。 3. The males think the females have talent for telling stale tales. 男人认为女人有讲陈腐故事的才能。 4. After ten years in the job, she felt stale and needed a change. 在那个岗位干了十年之后，她觉得腻了，需要换换工作。 5. The pleasure I get from playing guitar never stales. 我对吉它一直兴味盎然。', '副词: stalely 比较级: staler 最高级: stalest 名词: staleness 过去式: staled 过去分词: staled 现在分词: staling 第三人称单数: stales');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('jovial', '[\'dʒoʊviəl]', 'adj.快活的；高兴的；愉快的', '1. He is a friendly jovial fellow. 他是个和蔼而快乐的人。 2. Tom\'s jovial manner is one of his characters. 汤姆快活的态度是他的个性之一。 3. Mike\'s jovial face seemed to sag. 迈克那张高兴的脸似乎一沉。 4. I was in a jovial mood yesterday. 我昨天心情很愉快。', '副词: jovially 名词: joviality');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('quill', '[kwɪl]', 'n.羽茎；大翎毛；鹅毛笔；（豪猪等动物的)刺；纬管 v.用刺刺；把(线等）绕在纬管上；打褶皱', '1. The duke wrote a letter with a quill pen. 公爵用一根羽毛笔写信。 2. Hermione sighed and laid down her quill. 赫敏叹着气放下羽毛笔。 3. There are porcupine quills on the wayside vender. 路边小贩有豪猪刺。 4. The quill is designed to rest within the shuttle. 纬管的设计是应能使其安放在梭子之中。', '过去式: quilled 过去分词: quilled 现在分词: quilling 第三人称单数: quills');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('exorcise', '[\'eksɔːˌsaɪz]', 'v.驱赶；驱邪', '1. But there are proven ways to exorcise the curse. 已经有可靠的办法来解咒了。 2. He could not exorcise the memory of his past misdeeds. 他无法忘记自己过去的罪行。 3. A priest exorcized the ghost from the house. 教士将鬼从房屋中驱走。', '名词: exorciser 过去式: exorcised 过去分词: exorcised 现在分词: exorcising 第三人称单数: exorcises');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('denounce', '[dɪ\'naʊns]', 'v.谴责；告发；通告废除', '1. The minister\'s action was denounced in the newspaper. 部长的行为受到报界的指责。 2. American trade policies have been denounced by some European governments. 一些欧洲政府指责美国的贸易政策。 3. They denounced him to the police as a criminal. 他们向警方告发他是罪犯。 4. Somebody denounced him to the military police as a spy. 有人向宪兵队告发他为间谍。', '名词: denouncement 过去式: denounced 过去分词: denounced 现在分词: denouncing 第三人称单数: denounces');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('voracious', '[və\'reɪʃəs]', 'adj.狼吞虎咽的；贪婪的；贪吃的；求知欲强的', '1. After swimming, I find that I have a voracious appetite. 游完泳后,我发现我的食欲大增。 2. They are aggressively territorial and voracious to fault. 好斗与贪婪也是它们的弱点。 3. Kids can have voracious appetites. 小孩会很贪吃。 4. He was a voracious reader of the translations of Eastern religious works. 他如饥似渴地阅读东方宗教著作的译本。', '副词: voraciously 名词: voracity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('heir', '[er]', 'n.继承人', '1. Tilda seems to be his only heir. 迪儿特似乎是他唯一的继承人。 2. The young heir played away the whole of the estate. 那个年轻的继承人把全部遗产都赌输了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('impression', '[ɪm\'preʃn]', 'n.印象；感觉；模仿 n.印迹；印刷', '1. Her gentleness has given me a deep impression. 她的亲切给我留下了很深的印象。 2. I am surprised you\'ve got an unfavorable impression of him. 我很惊讶你对他印象不佳。 3. I had the impression that your boy hates school. 我感觉你的孩子不喜欢去上学。 4. The students did some marvellous impressions of the teachers at the end-of-term party. 在期末联欢会上,学生惟妙惟肖地模仿起了教师。 5. The well-printed book has a sharp, clean impression. 印刷良好的书籍有明显而清楚的印痕。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('seam', '[siːm]', 'n.缝；接缝 vt.缝合；接合；使有纹 vi.有裂缝', '1. We can mend a seam but not a big hole. 我们可以缝好脱线处，但不是补大洞。 2. The seam of her skirt ripped. 她的裙子的接缝裂开了。 3. You should seam up the shirt without using sewing-machine. 你不要用机器去缝制这件衬衣。 4. She seamed two pieces of carpet together. 她将两块地毯缝在一起。 5. The fields dried and seamed in the heat. 农田在高温下干裂。', '名词: seamer 过去式: seamed 过去分词: seamed 现在分词: seaming 第三人称单数: seams');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rookie', '[\'rʊki]', 'n.新手', '1. I was a rookie in my office last year. 去年我在办公室里还是新手一名。 2. These rookie cops don\'t know anything yet. 这些新警察什么都还不懂。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('granary', '[\'ɡrænəri]', 'n.谷仓；谷物仓；谷产丰富的地区', '1. That remote barren land has blossomed into rich granaries. 过去的穷乡僻壤变成了富饶的谷仓。 2. But now they have been adapted for use as storehouses or granaries. 不过现在它们已经被改建，用作库房或粮仓了。 3. The Northeast is the granary of the country. 东北是祖国的粮仓。 4. The Midwest is often called the granary of the US. 美国中西部地区常被喻为美国的粮仓。', '名词复数: granaries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('practitioner', '[præk\'tɪʃənər]', 'n.从业者；实践者', '1. He is an unqualified practitioner of law. 他是个无资格的律师。 2. A batch of moneybags will appear again in practitioner of domestic network game. 国内网络游戏从业者中又将出现一批富翁。 3. Socrates was the greatest practitioner of this analytical search for fundamental assumptions. 苏格拉底是这种以理性分析法探求基本假设的最伟大的实践者。 4. In Qing Dynasty Government, Li Hongzhang is the main leader and practitioner of the construction of coast defense. 李鸿章是清政府海防建设的主要领导人和实践者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('subscribe', '[səb\'skraɪb]', 'vt.订阅；签名；支持；捐赠；同意', '1. I subscribe to\" Reader\'s Digest\" magazine. 我订了《读者文摘》杂志。 2. They refused to subscribe to the agreement. 他们拒绝在协议上签字。 3. Do you subscribe to her pessimistic view of the state of the economy? 你是否同意她对经济状况所持的悲观看法？ 4. We subscribe to an animal protection society. 我们定期捐款给一个动物保护基金会。', '名词: subscriber 过去式: subscribed 过去分词: subscribed 现在分词: subscribing 第三人称单数: subscribes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('verified', '[\'verəˌfaɪd]', 'adj.经证实的 动词verify的过去式和过去分词.', '1. My fears were verified by subsequent events. 后来的事件证明了我的虑并没有错。 2. The bank refused to cash the check until the signature was verified. 银行直到签字得到了确认才兑现了这张支票 3. The truth verified the allegations. 事实证明了这些说法。 4. The computer verified whether the data was loaded correctly. 计算机查实数据输入是否正确。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('transaction', '[træn\'zækʃn]', 'n.交易；办理；处理；事务 （复）transactions: 学报；会报.', '1. Had you not helped us, we should have canceled this transaction. 假如没有你的帮助，这笔生意早就告吹了。 2. His failure in this transaction was due to nothing else than his own carelessness. 他在这笔交易中的失利完全是由于他自己的粗心大意。 3. Payments by cheque easily outnumbered cash transactions. 用支票付款在数量上大大超过现金交易。 4. They charge a fixed rate for each transaction. 他们对办理的每项业务收取一定的费用。', '形容词: transactional');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('strangulation', '[ˌstræŋɡju\'leɪʃn]', 'n.扼杀；勒死', '1. It\'s the strangulation of the human spirit. 这是对人类精神的扼杀。 2. He died of slow strangulation. 他因慢慢窒息而死。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('empyreal', '[ˌempaɪ\'riːəl]', 'adj.最高天的；九天的；崇高的', '1. After unanimous agreement within the Circle of the Empyreal council, The Sagittarius Science Directorate is founded within Centaurus space. 在崇高界委员会的一致同意后，半人马座科学董事会建在半人马星座空间内。 2. The model that finishs continuously continuously is most simple, have quite go up continuously empyreal feel directly. 直下直下的造型最为简单，颇有直上九天的径直感。 3. Mandatory Biogen treatment is introduced into Centaurus interstellar society and welcomed by the majority of citizens within Circle of the Empyreal sovereign space. 强制性的酵母促生物原（生命素）被引入半人马座星际社会，并受到崇高界大部分人们的欢迎。 4. Circle of the Empyreal sovereignty now spans 20 star systems within 100 light years of New Delta with a total population of 16.5 billion Centaurus citizens. 崇高界政权在在一百光年之内，扩展了20个行星系统，半人马星座居民的总数达到163亿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('indoctrinate', '[ɪn\'dɑːktrɪneɪt]', 'v.灌输；教导', '1. The writer wants to indoctrinate the readers with the idea. 作者想把这种想法灌输给读者。 2. The coach tried to indoctrinate the players with the teamwork of attack 教练试图使他的队员充分熟悉进攻的配合。', '名词: indoctrination 过去式: indoctrinated 过去分词: indoctrinated 现在分词: indoctrinating 第三人称单数: indoctrinates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('absolute', '[\'æbsəluːt]', 'adj.绝对的；确实的；专制的；完全的；独立的；无限制的 n.绝对的事物', '1. There is no absolute standard for beauty. 美是没有绝对的标准的。 2. Motion is absolute, while stillness is relative. 运动是绝对的，而静止是相对的。 3. There is no absolute freedom in the world. 世上没有绝对的自由。 4. The police have absolute proof of his guilt. 警方有他犯罪的确凿证据。', '名词: absoluteness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('increment', '[\'ɪŋkrəmənt]', 'n.增量；增加；增值；增额', '1. Every time the file is filled, it increases its size by the growth increment. 每次填充文件时,其大小均按此增量来增长。 2. Your salary will be $12000 a year, withannual increments of 500. 你的年薪为12000美元,每年增加500美元。 3. In the new stage, factors of urban land value increment have new characteristics. 在新的经济、社会背景下，城市土地增值的影响因素呈现新的特点。 4. She receives a salary increment each year. 她每年得到加薪。', '形容词: incremental 副词: incrementally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('torpedo', '[tɔːr\'piːdoʊ]', 'n.鱼雷 v.用鱼雷破坏；破坏政策或事情等', '1. The ship was attacked by torpedo. 那条船遭到鱼雷的攻击。 2. The torpedo homed in on its target. 鱼雷射向目标。 3. The ship was sunk by an enemy torpedo. 这艘船被敌人的鱼雷击沉了。 4. He was accused of trying to torpedo the talks. 他被指责试图破坏会谈。', '名词复数: torpedoes 过去式: torpedoed 过去分词: torpedoed 现在分词: torpedoing 第三人称单数: torpedoes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('seditious', '[sɪ\'dɪʃəs]', 'adj.煽动性的', '1. He distributed a seditious pamphlet called The Rights of Man. 他散发了名叫《人的权利》的带有煽动性的小册子。', '副词: seditiously 名词: seditiousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('marital', '[\'mærɪtl]', 'adj.婚姻的', '1. We don\'t know her marital status, whether or not she has children. 我们不清楚她的婚姻状况,也不知道她是否有孩子。 2. We can define marital felicity accurately. 我们能够给美满婚姻下个准确定义。 3. He is faced with the fact of an irremediable marital breakdown. 他面临着不可挽救的婚姻破裂的事实。 4. He did not appear to have any financial or marital problems. 他看起来没有任何经济或婚姻问题。', '副词: maritally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('allegiance', '[ə\'liːdʒəns]', 'n.忠诚；效忠', '1. The judge received their oath of allegiance. 法官听取了他们的忠诚誓言。 2. Private members keep up their outward allegiance to the parties they belong to. 议员们对各自所属的党派保持表面上的忠诚。 3. His allegiance has never been questioned. 他的忠心是毫无疑问的。 4. The soldiers swore allegiance to their motherland. 士兵们宣誓效忠于他们的祖国。', '形容词: allegiant');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('addict', '[\'ædɪkt]', 'vt.沉溺；使 ... 上瘾 n.耽溺者；上瘾者', '1. The young generation should addict themselves to science. 年轻的一代应该酷爱科学。 2. His tastes addict him to the study of antiquity. 嗜好使他沉迷于研究古代的事物。 3. He was addicted to cocaine. 他吸可卡因上瘾。 4. He is turning into an internet addict. 他快变成网虫了。', '形容词: addictive 过去式: addicted 过去分词: addicted 现在分词: addicting 第三人称单数: addicts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('viscous', '[\'vɪskəs]', 'adj.粘的；粘性的', '1. The monomer, or base epoxy, is a light amber fluid which is usually quite viscous. 单体或碱性环氧树脂，是一种淡琥珀色的液体，通常都是很粘的。', '副词: viscously 名词: viscousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rebarbative', '[rɪ\'bɑːrbətɪv]', 'adj.厌烦的；令人讨厌的；难看的', '1. He became rebarbative and prickly and spiteful. 他变得令人讨厌，容易发怒，而且满怀恶意。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('decoy', '[\'diːkɔɪ]', 'n.（诱捕鸟兽的）动物；诱饵 v.引诱', '1. This is just a motherfucking decoy. 这只是个该死的诱饵。 2. He succeeded in decoying the ducks toward his blind. 他成功地把野鸭引诱到他的隐藏处。 3. He was decoyed by a false message into enemy territory. 他被假情报诱骗进入敌区。', '名词: decoyer 过去式: decoyed 过去分词: decoyed 现在分词: decoying 第三人称单数: decoys');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('providential', '[ˌprɑːvɪ\'denʃl]', 'adj.幸运的；神助的', '1. Their departure just before the floods was providential. 他们恰在发洪水之前离开，走得真是时候。 2. This was providential rest and shelter until the moon rose. 在月亮上来之前，这是一个幸运的休憩与隐蔽之所。 3. Your rheumatism can hardly be reckoned among providential visitations. 神的造访也很难让你的风湿病康复。 4. I escaped by a most providential circumstance, which seems a very simple one. 我是靠了老天爷保佑才幸免于难的，而且情况倒似乎十分简单。', '副词: providentially');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sedulous', '[\'sedʒələs]', 'adj.勤勉的；勤苦工作的；聚精凝神的', '1. Self-discipline required a sedulous work. 需要作出艰苦努力的自我约束 2. Slef-discipline required a sedulous work. 需要作出艰苦努力的自我约束。 3. There are many sedulous staffs worked at different post! 在各个部门，我们都有如此没计辛劳的员工奋战在第一线！ 4. Not be sedulous because of this element decorate ahead of schedule.Ms. 并不是因为这个因素而刻意提前装修。', '副词: sedulously 名词: sedulousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ethnic', '[\'eθnɪk]', 'adj.种族的；民族的；有民族特色的 n.少数民族的一员', '1. Canada is a multicultural country. Regardless of your ethnic origin, you will feel at home in Canada; 加拿大是一个多元文化国家,无论你为何种族,在加拿大你都会感到安适; 2. Along the way, tourists can see the Tujia ethnic minorities tilling the land. 沿着这条路,旅游者可以看到土家族的人在耕地。 3. That\'s why you can find almost every kind of ethnic food in America. 那也就是为什么在美国你几乎可以看到所有不同民族的食物。 4. Now all the 55 ethnic minorities have their own college students,and some even are master\'s and doctor\'s degree holders. 目前，55个少数民族都有了本民族的大学生，有的还有了硕士生和博士生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('offset', '[\'ɔːfset]', 'vt.抵消；弥补；用平版印刷 vi.形成分支 n.补偿；平版印刷；支派；弯管；[计]偏移量', '1. The pay raise will be offset by inflation. 增加的工资会被通货膨胀所抵销。 2. Higher mortgage rates are partly offset by increased tax allowances. 抵押款提高了，其中一部分可由免税额增加而抵消。 3. Hedge can help them offset inventory loss when commodity price fall. 在商品价格下跌时,套期保值能够帮助他们抵补存货价跌的损失。 4. He raised his prices to offset the increased cost of materials. 他提高售价以补偿材料增加的成本。 5. Offset requirements also vary between these areas. 补偿要求在这些地区也各有不同。', '过去式: offset 过去分词: offset 现在分词: offsetting 第三人称单数: offsets');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('counterbalance', '[ˌkaʊntər\'bæləns]', 'n.平衡；平衡力 v.抵销；使平衡', '1. The two weights counterbalance each other. 那两个秤锤互成平衡。 2. His wife\'s calm nature act as a counterbalance to his excitability. 他妻子生性从容不迫，这对他的易冲动的个性起著平衡作用。 3. He took two days off to counterbalance the overtime the week before. 他休了两天假以抵消前星期加的班。 4. The boy\'s earnest effort counterbalance his slowness at learning. 这孩子孜孜不倦的努力抵消了他学习的迟钝。', '过去式: counterbalanced 过去分词: counterbalanced 现在分词: counterbalancing 第三人称单数: counterbalances');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inhale', '[ɪn\'heɪl]', 'v.吸入；吸气；吞咽', '1. Do you inhale when you smoke? 你抽烟时是否把烟吸入肺里？ 2. We inhale oxygen and exhale carbon dioxide. 我们吸入的是氧气，呼出的是二氧化碳。 3. He inhaled deeply. 他深深地吸了口气。 4. Follow me please, inhale! exhale! 跟我做,吸气! 呼气！', '过去式: inhaled 过去分词: inhaled 现在分词: inhaling 第三人称单数: inhales');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nightmare', '[\'naɪtˌmeə]', 'n.恶梦；使人极其痛苦的事情或经历；梦魇', '1. The nightmare gave her the creeps. 那场恶梦使她不寒而栗。 2. Will I wake up from this nightmare? 我会从这个恶梦中醒来吗? 3. The holocaust survivors have lived a nightmare. 大屠杀幸存者经历了一场噩梦。 4. Losing a child is most people\'s worst nightmare. 对于大多数人来说，丧子之痛是最可怕的梦魇。', '形容词: nightmarish 副词: nightmarishly 名词: nightmarishness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unify', '[\'juːnɪfaɪ]', 'vt.使统一、使成为一体', '1. The new leader hopes to unify the country. 新领袖希望把国家统一起来。 2. England and Scotland do not have a unified legal system. 英格兰和苏格兰法制不统一.', '形容词: unifiable 名词: unification 过去式: unified 过去分词: unified 现在分词: unifying 第三人称单数: unifies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cooperative', '[koʊ\'ɑːpərətɪv]', 'adj.合作的；协作的 n.合作社', '1. We found him friendly and cooperative. 我们感到他是友好的，乐于合作的。 2. They are trying to adopt a more cooperative posture. 他们正试图采取更为合作的态度。 3. The management would like to thank the staff for being so cooperative. 资方要感谢全体员工的通力合作。 4. The school was very cooperative when we made a film there. 我们到该校拍摄影片时，获得校方的大力协助。 5. They decided to set up a cooperative. 他们决定开办一家合作社。', '副词: cooperatively 名词: cooperativeness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('insufficient', '[ˌɪnsə\'fɪʃnt]', 'adj.不足的', '1. The food was insufficient for our needs. 食物不够我们的需要。 2. I felt my knowledge was insufficient. 我感到知识不足。 3. There is insufficient light for reading. 这里光线不足,不适合阅读。 4. His children were dwarfed by insufficient food. 他的儿女因营养不良而发育不全。', '副词: insufficiently');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('worship', '[\'wɜːrʃɪp]', 'n.崇拜；爱慕；做礼拜 vi.做礼拜 vt.崇拜；爱慕', '1. He deserves all the praise and worship. 他值得我们一切的赞美和崇拜。 2. She scorn the girls who worship football stars. 她看不起那些崇拜足球明星的女孩子。 3. She was blind to the silent worship in his eyes. 她没有发觉他眼里流露出的无声的敬慕之情。 4. This is the church where we used to worship. 这就是那座我们过去常做礼拜的教堂。 5. This is the church where we used to worship. 这就是那座我们过去常做礼拜的教堂。 6. The boy worshipped his father. 这小孩崇拜他的父亲。', '名词: worshiper 过去式: worshiped/worshipped 过去分词: worshiped/worshipped 现在分词: worshiping/worshipping 第三人称单数: worships/worships');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tumble', '[\'tʌmbl]', 'v.暴跌；倒塌；跌倒；翻滚；弄乱；明白；突然发现 n.暴跌；跌跤；混乱', '1. Share prices tumbled on the stock-market. 股市上股票价格暴跌。 2. Stock market price tumble after rumor of a rise in interest rate. 谣传利率上升之後，股票市场价格猛跌。 3. That old building could tumble down at any time. 那座古老的楼房随时可能倒塌。 4. It only needed a push and the whole building will come tumble down. 只要稍稍一推，那整幢房子就会倒塌下来。 5. Stock prices took a tumble in the afternoon. 股票价格下午猛跌。', '过去式: tumbled 过去分词: tumbled 现在分词: tumbling 第三人称单数: tumbles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('renown', '[rɪ\'naʊn]', 'n.名望；声誉 vt.使有名望', '1. He is an artist of great renown. 他是一位极有名望的艺术家。 2. His renown as a reporter spread throughout the country. 他作为一名记者的名望在全国都传开了。 3. He is an artist of great renown. 他是一位极有名望的艺术家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pitfall', '[\'pɪtfɔːl]', 'n.陷阱；隐患；想不到的困难', '1. The wolf was caught in a pitfall. 那只狼是利用陷阱捉到的。 2. There are many pitfalls for teenagers today. 对现今的青少年来说,到处有许多陷阱。 3. We need to be alert to potential pitfalls. 我们需要警惕可能出现的隐患。 4. Life is full of snares and pitfalls and no one is proof against them all. 生活充满了诱惑和风险,没有人能挡得住的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('marionette', '[ˌmæriə\'net]', 'n.牵线木偶', '1. Marionette was also one of the art forms first created by Chinese. 提线木偶也是中国人首先发明的艺术形式之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('spike', '[spaɪk]', 'n.长钉；尖状物；钉鞋；峰值；穗；穗状花；【排球】扣球 v.以大钉钉牢；使 ... 失效；用尖物刺伤；【排球】扣球', '1. There are many sharp spikes on the railings in the park. 公园的栏杆上有很多尖头。 2. In that case, the price spike would be something like a dead-cat bounce. 在那种情况下，股价峰值可能会像死猫诈尸一样反弹。 3. Here is effective rice spike number. 这是水稻有效稻穗数。 4. They\'ll do anything to spike the guns of the opposition. 他们会使出各种手段来挫败对手。', '形容词: spiked 过去式: spiked 过去分词: spiked 现在分词: spiking 第三人称单数: spikes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('auger', '[\'ɔːɡər]', 'n.螺丝钻；钻孔机', '1. The function of an auger is to bore holes. 麻花钻的功用是钻孔。 2. Then I felt the numbing pain of the auger bit crushing my back. 然后，钻孔机钻头压断了我的后背，我痛的几乎麻木了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('maternal', '[mə\'tɜːrnl]', 'adj.母亲的；母系的；母方的；母性的', '1. She feels very maternal towards him. 她对他充满母爱。 2. Maternal age affects the baby\'s survival rate. 母亲的年龄影响婴儿的成活率。 3. My maternal grandfather is coming. 我的外祖父要来了。 4. On the maternal side his inheritance was a happy one. 他从母方接受的遗传是良好的。', '副词: maternally 名词: maternalism');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('honorarium', '[ˌɑːnə\'reriəm]', 'n.（自愿赠予的）酬劳金或谢礼', '1. There will be an honorarium for you to cover your phone and time. 将会有包括你的电话和时间的你一个报酬。 2. Travel and hotel costs as well as an honorarium will be provided. 我们提供旅费和住宿费以及酬金。', '名词复数: honorariums');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('amenity', '[ə\'menəti]', 'n.适意；舒适；便利设施 （复）amenities：礼仪；礼节.', '1. He immediately noticed the amenity of his new surroundings. 他立刻觉察到了新环境的宜人之处。 2. People who retire to the country often miss the amenity of a town. 退居到乡村的人们时常怀念城市舒适的生活。 3. A sauna in the hotel would be a useful amenity. 旅馆中的芬兰蒸汽浴室倒是个有益的好设施。', '名词复数: amenities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unscathed', '[ʌn\'skeɪðd]', 'adj.没有受伤的；未受损害', '1. The hostages emerged from their ordeal unscathed. 人质经受磨难而平安生还。 2. He walked away from the accident completely unscathed. 他安然无恙地从事故现场走开了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('offend', '[ə\'fend]', 'vt.冒犯；犯罪 vi.违反；令人不适', '1. I didn\'t mean to offend you. 我不是故意冒犯你。 2. We were careful not to offend his nibs. 我们小心翼翼不敢冒犯这位要人。 3. You would be wise enough not to offend him. 你最好是不去冒犯他。 4. He did not offend against the law . 他没犯法。 5. We mustn\'t offend against their customs. 我们不能违反他们的风俗。', '过去式: offended 过去分词: offended 现在分词: offending 第三人称单数: offends');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('peripatetic', '[ˌperipə\'tetɪk]', 'n.巡行者；巡游 adj.巡游的；兼职的 Peripatetic. n.亚里士多德信徒 adj.亚里士多德学派的', '1. Peripatetic music teachers visit the school regularly. 兼职音乐教师定期到校授课。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flicker', '[\'flɪkər]', 'n.闪烁；闪光；颤动 v.闪动；闪烁；摇动', '1. She is read by the flicker light of the candle. 她借著闪烁的烛光读书。 2. Watch the flames flicker in the room. 注视着火焰在屋里闪烁。 3. But the tiny flicker of Gryffindor boldness wasn\'t entirely quenched. 但是，格兰芬多的胆大冒失的微小闪光并没有完全熄灭。 4. Now as Peter\'s eyes discovered the bandaid on his neck, the telltale flicker of anger appeared. 现在彼得一看到他脖子上的绷带，那怒火的隐蔽闪光就出现了。 5. Perhaps there\'s a brief flicker in some toolbar button which, when investigated, reveals a crash. 可能在工具条的一个短暂的闪动，经过调查后，揭示了一个失效错误。', '过去式: flickered 过去分词: flickered 现在分词: flickering 第三人称单数: flickers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('doctrine', '[\'dɑːktrɪn]', 'n.学说；教义；主义；（政府政策的）正式声明', '1. This is the doctrine of the nominalist party. 这是唯名主义学派的学说。 2. Christian and Muslim doctrines are very different. 基督教教义和穆斯林教义极为不同。 3. He was impelled to proclaim his doctrine. 他不得不宣扬他的教义。 4. He preached a doctrine which was new to him. 他对教义的解释一改旧貌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cleaver', '[\'kliːvər]', 'n.切肉刀；屠刀', '1. In fact, a cleaver is a class of ax. 实际上，切肉刀也是斧子的一种。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('quack', '[kwæk]', 'n.(鸭子)嘎嘎叫声；庸医；冒充内行的人 v.嘎嘎地叫；大声闲谈；冒充内行 adj.骗人的', '1. A duck\'s quack doesn\'t echo and no one knows the reason. 鸭子呱呱叫是不会产生回音的 2. She discovered that the man was a quack. 她发现那人是个庸医。 3. The quack was stormed with questions. 江湖骗子受到了猛烈的质问。 4. He landed among the tame ducks, and began to waddle around and quack merrily. 他落在了家鸭群中,开始四处踱来踱去,欢叫个不停,还吃起了地上的谷物。 5. He was told that it\'s a quack medicine. 他被告知这是假药。', '形容词: quacky 副词: quackishly 名词: quackery 过去式: quacked 过去分词: quacked 现在分词: quacking 第三人称单数: quacks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('glossy', '[\'ɡlɑːsi]', 'adj.光滑的；有光泽的', '1. He tickled gently at its glossy carapace, but the stubborn beetle would not budge. 他轻轻地搔着甲虫光滑的壳，但这只固执的甲虫就是不动。 2. In order to give chewing gum balls a glossy surface, they are treated with Bees or Carnauba wax in appropriate implements. 为了使某些口香糖有一个光滑的外壳，通常制造商会用适当的设备处理蜂蜜或巴西棕榈蜡。 3. Tufted evergreen perennial herb having spikes of tiny white flowers and glossy green round to heart-shaped leaves that become coppery to maroon or purplish in fall. 多年生常绿簇生草本植物，有白色小花穗，圆形或心形有光泽的绿叶，秋天从古铜色变成褐紫红色或紫色。', '副词: glossily 比较级: glossier 最高级: glossiest 名词: glossiness 名词复数: glossies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('restraint', '[rɪ\'streɪnt]', 'n.克制；抑制；束缚', '1. The police appealed to the crowd for restraint. 警方呼吁群众保持克制。 2. Nobody could count on his restraint or rationality. 谁也不能指望他会克制或讲道理的态度。 3. There is still need for profit restraint. 现在仍有必要限制利润。 4. His rage was beyond restraint. 他怒不可遏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nova', '[\'noʊvə]', 'n.新星', '1. Therefore, the broadcasting station has become a media market dazzling nova. 于是，广播电台成了媒体市场的一颗耀眼新星。 2. The nova phenomenon generally occurs in a binary system that has as one member a very hot white dwarf. 新星这种现象一般发生在双星系统中，其中一颗子星是非常热的白矮星。', '名词复数: novae');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('consonant', '[\'kɑːnsənənt]', 'n.辅音 adj.一致的；符合的；辅音的', '1. She asked me to pronounce each vowel and consonant clearly. 她叫我把每个元音和辅音都清晰地发出来。 2. Many letters in the alphabet such as b, c, d, etc are consonants. 字母表中的许多字母像b，c，d，等等都是辅音字母。 3. His view on the issue is consonant with mine. 他对这个问题的看法和我是一致的。 4. The quality of this suit is not quite consonant with its price . 这套衣服的质量与价钱不太相符。', '副词: consonantly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fag', '[fæɡ]', 'n.(尤英）苦工；苦差事 n.公校中为高年级男生服务的低年级男生 n.香烟 vi.做苦工；为（高年级生）服务 vt.使劳累；使疲倦', '1. It\'s too much of a fag. 那是叫人受不了的苦工。 2. It\'s too much (of a) fag. 这工作真叫人吃不消。 3. Running soon fags me out. 我很快就跑累了。 4. I\'ve got to tidy my room. What a fag! 我得整理自己的房间。真是累人的事。', '过去式: fagged 过去分词: fagged 现在分词: fagging 第三人称单数: fags');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('groan', '[ɡroʊn]', 'v.呻吟；抱怨；发嘎吱声；受重压 n.呻吟；呻吟声', '1. The girl groaned in pain. 那女孩在痛苦中呻吟。 2. He was heard to groan. 有人听见他在呻吟。 3. Don\'t moan and groan because of a little setback. 不要受了一点挫折就唉声叹气。 4. The roof creaked and groaned under the weight of the snow. 屋顶被积雪压得发出吱吱嘎嘎的声响。 5. The wounded man uttered a groan. 那个受伤的人发出呻吟。', '副词: groaningly 名词: groaner 过去式: groaned 过去分词: groaned 现在分词: groaning 第三人称单数: groans');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stench', '[stentʃ]', 'n.臭气；恶臭', '1. The stench of treachery hung in the air. 到处都是可耻的叛变的气息。 2. The stench of the rotton fish is fearful. 烂鱼的臭味太难闻了。 3. The stench of the battlefield spread for miles around. 战场上的臭气在周围绵延好几里。 4. The cans in the school had an awful stench. 学校的公共厕所发出一股恶臭。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rendition', '[ren\'dɪʃn]', 'n.演奏；解释；翻译；投降', '1. She gave a splendid rendition of the song. 这首歌她唱得动听极了。 2. Mother and I are especially fond of the Tchaikovsky Concerto, and your rendition of it was simply superb. 妈妈和我特别喜欢柴可夫斯基的小协奏曲，您把那支曲子演奏得好极了！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('confer', '[kən\'fɜːr]', 'v.商讨；授予，赐予', '1. I must confer with my lawyer before I decide. 我必须先同我的律师商量一下才能做出决定。 2. I will confer with him on the subject. 我将和他商议这件事。 3. The Queen conferred knighthood on several distinguished men. 女王将爵士头衔授予几位杰出人士。 4. The university confers master degree on her. 学校授予她硕士学位。', '形容词: conferrable 名词: conferment 过去式: conferred 过去分词: conferred 现在分词: conferring 第三人称单数: confers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unproductive', '[ˌʌnprə\'dʌktɪv]', 'adj.不生产的；非生产性的；没有收获的；徒劳的', '1. One quarter of the country is reckoned as unproductive. 这个国家有四分之一被认为是不毛之地。 2. We have reduced the unproductive spending. 我们已削减了非生产性开支。 3. I\'ve had a very unproductive day. 我这一天什么事都没干成。 4. It is unproductive self-punishment. 自我惩罚是徒劳的。', '副词: unproductively 名词: unproductiveness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('infelicitous', '[ˌɪnfə\'lɪsətəs]', 'adj.不妥当的；不幸的', '1. This infelicitous term partly refers to offering consumers a discount to build their own furniture. 这个不太恰当的词汇，部分意思是指向顾客提供折扣，由他们自己组装家具。 2. Chinese people generally chase for double gifts, because odd number is seemed to be infelicitous. 中国人一般讲究礼品成双，因为奇数被视为不吉利。 3. the infelicitous typesetting was due to illegible copy. 错误的排版是因为原稿潦草难认。 4. an infelicitous remark; infelicitous phrasing; the infelicitous typesetting was due to illegible copy. 不恰当的评论；不贴切的措辞；错误的排版是因为原稿潦草难认。', '副词: infelicitously');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cuddle', '[\'kʌdl]', 'vt.怀抱；拥抱 vi.拥抱；依偎 n.搂抱；拥抱', '1. The little girl cuddled her pet cat. 这个小女孩搂抱着她的宠物猫。 2. My mother gave me a cuddle before I went to bed. 我上床睡觉前妈妈拥抱了我。 3. Cuddle on the sofa and watch a movie. 在沙发上一边互相拥抱一边看电影。 4. I love to snuggle and cuddle with you. 我喜欢偎依着你、拥抱着你。 5. My lovely daughter came to her father for a cuddle. 我可爱的小女儿走到她父亲那，要他抱抱她。', '形容词: cuddlesome 过去式: cuddled 过去分词: cuddled 现在分词: cuddling 第三人称单数: cuddles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tribute', '[\'trɪbjuːt]', 'n.贡品；称赞；敬意；礼物', '1. The victorious nations are demanding tribute from their former enemies. 战胜国要求战败国向其进奉贡品。 2. Many Greek cities had to send yearly tribute to Athens. 许多希腊城市不得不每年向雅典进贡。 3. The musician gave full tribute to his former teacher. 这位音乐家盛赞了他过去的老师。 4. He paid tribute to the way the country had forged national unity. 他称赞这个国家加强民族团结的方式。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('customary', '[\'kʌstəmeri]', 'adj.习惯的；惯例的', '1. That\'s his customary shortcoming. 那是他一个习惯的毛病。 2. Obviously, this has gone beyond their customary limits. 显然，这已经超出了置业习惯的限制。 3. He refused to have his portrait conventionalized into the customary smooth beauty of the pharaoh god. 他不让他的画像具有惯例的法老神的那种传统的温和的美。 4. In addition, the personal right of copyright can be restricted by the laws related, the customs, especially the professional customary practices. 此外，著作人身权还要受到相关法律和习惯，尤其是行业惯例的限制。', '副词: customarily 名词: customariness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('converse', '[kən\'vɜːrs]', 'n.相反的事物；逆命题 adj.相反的；逆向的；倒的 v.交谈；谈话 n.谈话', '1. He says she is satisfied, but I believe the converse to be true: she is very dissatisfied. 他说她已心满意足了，不过我认为实际情况相反: 她很不满意。 2. I believe the converse of what you are saying. 我相信的和你说的正相反。 3. It is possible, of course, that the converse of this theory may also be true. 当然该原理的逆命题也有可能成立。 4. This statement is converse to that one. 这个声明和那个相反。 5. Would you give me half an hour to converse with you? 我想跟你谈谈，半小时就行。 6. It is a pleasure to converse with her. 和她谈话是一种乐趣。', '副词: conversely 过去式: conversed 过去分词: conversed 现在分词: conversing 第三人称单数: converses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('equity', '[\'ekwəti]', 'n.公平；公正 n.衡平法；权益；产权；(无固定利息的)股票', '1. The equity of the referee\'s decision was accepted by everyone. 大家都同意裁判员的公正裁判. 2. They shared the work of the house with perfect equity. 他们很公平地分担屋内的工作。 3. He seeks after equity all life long. 他一生都在追求公正。 4. The judge has become a model of justice and equity. 这位法官已经成了公正正义的楷模。 5. This became the characteristic idea of classical equity. 这成了典型的衡平法所具备的特殊观念。', '名词复数: equities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('earthly', '[\'ɜːrθli]', 'adj.地球的；俗世的；可能的', '1. You have reached the apex of earthly honour. 你已经达到世界上荣誉的顶点。 2. In this earthly life nothing is perfect. 在我们现世的生活中，没有什么是完美无缺的。 3. We are bankrupt of earthly treasures. 我们失去了尘世间的所有珍宝。 4. They have not an earthly chance to win. 他们根本没有希望得胜。', '名词: earthliness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('compulsory', '[kəm\'pʌlsəri]', 'adj.强制的；势在必行的；义务的', '1. Attendance at evening prayers is not compulsory. 参加晚祷并非硬性规定。 2. I think it is compulsory. 我认为这是非做不可的。 3. The car insurance is compulsory. 这项汽车保险是强制性的。 4. I think it is compulsory to look over the house. 我认为检查这栋房子势在必行。', '副词: compulsorily 名词: compulsoriness 名词复数: compulsories');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tongs', '[tɔːŋz]', 'n.钳子；夹具 名词tong的复数形式.', '1. She uses tongs to add coals to the fire. 她用火钳往炉火中添煤。 2. Our team went like hammer and tongs in the piano-smashing contest and easily own first prize. 我们队在钢琴演奏大赛中劲头十足，轻而易举地赢得了一等奖。 3. But the point of design is the design of the tongs. 而设计的重点是夹具的设计。 4. In the aspects of tongs choosing, specialized tongs are used. 在夹具方面选用专用夹具。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rote', '[roʊt]', 'n.死记硬背；机械的做法 adj.死记硬背的；机械的', '1. He has conned the poems by rote. 他已经把这诗歌背下来了。 2. He used to learn everything by rote. 他过去总是死记硬背。 3. He can say the whole of the English Bible by rote. 他能把整本英语《圣经》硬背出来。 4. She imitated her teacher by rote. 她机械地模仿她的老师。 5. Learning by rote is discouraged in this school. 这所学校不鼓励死记硬背的学习方式。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('grave', '[ɡreiv]', 'n.坟墓；死亡 adj.严肃的；严重的；庄重的 v.雕刻；铭记；', '1. She laid the bouquet on the newly turfed grave. 她把那束花放置在新铺上草皮的坟墓上。 2. You are just digging your own grave if you go on smoking so heavily. 你继续这样过度吸烟，就是在自掘坟墓。 3. His face was grave when I told him my decision. 当我告诉他我的决定时，他的脸色很严肃。 4. The situation poses a grave threat to world peace. 这局势对世界和平构成了严重的威胁。', '副词: gravely 比较级: graver 最高级: gravest 名词: graveness 过去式: graved 过去分词: graven/graved 现在分词: graving 第三人称单数: graves');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stockade', '[stɑː\'keɪd]', 'n.栅栏；围栏 v.(用围栏)围', '1. The sheep were surrounded by stockade. 羊被栅栏圈着。 2. The lambs were kept in the stockade. 小羊羔被放在围栏里养着。', '过去式: stockaded 过去分词: stockaded 现在分词: stockading 第三人称单数: stockades');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('closure', '[\'kloʊʒər]', 'n.关闭；关口；讨论终结；终结', '1. Lack of money forced the closure of the company. 公司因缺钱而被迫关闭。 2. The strike forced the closure of the factory. 罢工迫使该厂关闭。 3. The closure of the large factory made many workers live in idleness. 那家大工厂倒闭，使许多工人失业。 4. The closure of the car factory had a knock-on effect on the tyre manufacturers. 汽车厂关闭后,轮胎制造商受到间接的影响。', '过去式: closured 过去分词: closured 现在分词: closuring 第三人称单数: closures');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('detonate', '[\'detəneɪt]', 'v.使爆炸；使爆裂；爆炸；发爆炸声', '1. An engineer tried to detonate the mine. 一名工程师试图引爆地雷。 2. The bomb failed to detonate. 炸弹没爆炸。', '形容词: detonatable 过去式: detonated 过去分词: detonated 现在分词: detonating 第三人称单数: detonates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('plebeian', '[plə\'biːən]', 'adj.平民的；粗俗的 n.平民；粗俗的人', '1. He was born of plebeian origins. 他出身平民。 2. The plebeian education in Tang dynasty is characterized by popularity, synthesis, and usefulness. 唐代的平民教育具有通俗性、综合性、实用性的特点。 3. This book has plebeian tastes. 这本书有庸俗的味道。 4. Some mass media tend to please people of plebeian tastes. 有些媒体有讨好低俗品味者的倾向。', '副词: plebeianly 名词: plebeianism');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fell', '[fel]', 'vt.砍伐；击倒 n.丘原；沼泽地 adj.凶残的；毁灭性的 动词fall的过去式.', '1. The lumberman will fell these great trees. 这位伐木工将砍伐掉这些大树。 2. He felled his enemy with a single blow. 他一拳将他的敌人打倒了。 3. This is the famous Lakeland Fells. 这就是著名的莱克兰荒野。 4. The wind and rain beat down on me, and I fell down several times, but finally I arrived at a long, low house, standing rather isolated in the middle of the moor. 风裹着雨打在我的身上，我跌倒了好几次，但终于还是走到了一幢孤零零立在沼泽地中间的长长的矮房子前。 5. He was struck by a fell blow to the head. 他的头部受到了重击。 6. The girl lost her balance and fell off the balance beam. 小女孩失去了平衡，从平衡木上摔了下来。', '形容词: fellable 名词: fellness 过去式: felled 过去分词: felled 现在分词: felling 第三人称单数: fells');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('spire', '[\'spaɪər]', 'n.(教堂的)尖塔；尖顶；螺旋 v.给 ... 装尖顶；塔状矗立', '1. We could see the spire of the church in the distance. 我们可以看到远处教堂的尖塔。 2. It\'s a magnificent view of the spires of the city. 这是全城建筑物尖顶尽收眼底的美景。 3. Some new buildings spired in the city. 城市中又耸立起了几座新楼。', '过去式: spired 过去分词: spired 现在分词: spiring 第三人称单数: spires');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rove', '[roʊv]', 'v.漂泊；流浪；环顾；把线穿过孔 n.徘徊；流浪；粗纺线 动词reeve的过去式和过去分词.', '1. He loved to rove the green hills and clear waters. 他喜欢漫游于山青水秀之乡。 2. I rove to search for the value of my life. 流浪只是在寻找生命的价。 3. He rove about his student. 他扫了他的学生一眼。 4. His eyes roved around the room. 他的眼睛扫视着房间的每个角落。', '过去式: roved 过去分词: roved 现在分词: roving 第三人称单数: roves');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('culinary', '[\'kʌlɪneri]', 'adj.厨房的；烹调的', '1. I was shocked by his culinary arts. 我对他的厨艺叹为观止。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mortify', '[\'mɔːrtɪfaɪ]', 'v. 使 ... 受辱； 抑制', '1. The knowledge of future evils mortified the present felicities. 对未来苦难的了解压抑了目前的喜悦。 2. He felt mortified for his mistake. 他对自己的过失深感羞愧。', '过去式: mortified 过去分词: mortified 现在分词: mortifying 第三人称单数: mortifies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pusillanimous', '[ˌpjuːsɪ\'lænɪməs]', 'adj.懦弱的；胆小的', '1. \"Pusillanimous?\" Martin protested. “娇小姐？”马丁抗议。 2. The Song of McGillicudie the Pusillanimous... 按歌曲查看音乐。 3. The state or quality of being pusillanimous; cowardice. 胆小，懦弱怯懦的状态或品质；胆小 4. The pusillanimous man would not defend his own family. 软弱无力的人不会保卫他自己的家。', '副词: pusillanimously');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ooze', '[uːz]', 'v.（使）渗出；泄漏；流露 n.软泥；渗出物', '1. Black oil was oozing out of the engine. 发动机渗出了黑油。 2. Blood was still oozing from the wound. 伤口仍在渗血。 3. The wound was oozing pus. 伤口在流脓. 4. She was simply oozing (with) charm. 她浑身散发着魅力。', '过去式: oozed 过去分词: oozed 现在分词: oozing 第三人称单数: oozes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('apropos', '[ˌæprə\'poʊ]', 'prep.关于 adj.恰当的；适宜的', '1. Apropos our date for lunch, I can\'t go. 关于我们的午餐约会，我不能去 2. Apropos tomorrow\'s event, I\'ll see how I feel. 关于明天的活动,那就看我感觉如何了。 3. I thought he spoke very apropos. 我认为他说得很中肯。 4. His suggestion is very much apropos. 他的建议非常适当。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('aromatic', '[ˌærə\'mætɪk]', 'adj.芳香的 n.芳香植物；芳香族化合物', '1. It is light, ,fruity aromatic and a perfect choice for ending a meal. 它是口感轻淡，圆润，芳香的，用于结束一顿饭完美的选择。 2. The dried aromatic inner bark of certain tropical Asian trees in the genus Cinnamomum,especially C. verum and C. loureirii,often ground and used as a spice. 桂皮，一种樟属的亚洲热带树木的芳香的干燥内层树皮，特别是正肉桂和劳木罗肉桂，常磨成粉做香料。 3. Aromatic plants are often used in cooking. 烹调中常使用芳香植物。 4. Sage is an aromatic plant in the lamiaceae family cultivated particularly in southern Europe. 鼠尾草是一种唇形科芳香植物，尤其种植于南欧。', '副词: aromatically 名词: aromaticness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bonhomie', '[ˌbɑːnə\'miː]', 'n.好性情；温和；和蔼', '1. Yet beneath the enforced bonhomie, abiding issues remain. 在强制的温和之下，旧有的问题依旧存在。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('membrane', '[\'membreɪn]', 'n.【C】薄膜；膜状物', '1. A plastic membrane serves as selective diffusion barrier. 一层塑料薄膜起着选择性渗透屏障的作用。 2. A vibrating membrane in the ear helps to convey sounds to the brain. 耳膜的振动帮助声音传送到大脑。 3. Such membrane lipids are amphiphatic molecules. 这种膜的类脂是一种有两种亲和性的分子。', '形容词: membranal');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('souvenir', '[ˌsuːvə\'nɪr]', 'n.纪念品', '1. Can you mail this souvenir to America for me? 您能帮我把这件纪念品邮到美国吗? 2. I bought this bag as a souvenir of my visit to London. 我买了这个袋子作为访问伦敦的纪念品。 3. My favorite souvenir is my key chain from China. 我最喜欢的纪念品是在中国买的钥匙链。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('apposite', '[\'æpəzɪt]', 'adj.适当的；恰切的', '1. His answer was apposite. 他的回答是得当的。 2. According to the appropriate appraisal ,he apportioned them apposite work. 根据恰当的鉴定，他分配给他们适当的工作。 3. What he said is apposite to the case. 他所说的是切合实情的。 4. This is a very apposite comparison. 这是一个非常妥帖的比喻。', '副词: appositely 名词: appositeness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('errand', '[\'erənd]', 'n.差使；差事；跑腿', '1. It was not an errand that much pleased the doctor. 这种差使医生可不大喜欢干。 2. I have to go an errand for him now. 我现在得去听他的差遣。 3. I\'ve got a few errands to do in the town. 我有几件事要进城办。 4. You must do the two errands this week. 你必须在一周内完成这两项任务。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('adduce', '[ə\'duːs]', 'v.引证；举出', '1. You must adduce a lot of examples to support your argument. 你必须引用许多例证来证明你的观点。 2. When you adduce evidence of this nature, you must be sure of your sources. 在你提供实质性的证据时,你必须确知它的来源。 3. I could adduce several reasons for his strange behaviour. 对他的奇怪行为，我能提出几点原因。', '形容词: adduceable 过去式: adduced 过去分词: adduced 现在分词: adducing 第三人称单数: adduces');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('satirize', '[\'sætəraɪz]', 'v.讽刺', '1. His cartoons pitlessly satirize the top politicians nowadays. 他的漫画无情地讽刺了当今的政界要人。', '过去式: satirized 过去分词: satirized 现在分词: satirizing 第三人称单数: satirizes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('brassy', '[\'bræsi]', 'adj.似黄铜的；厚脸皮的', '1. Brassy enough to call herself girl. 还有脸说自己是女孩子。 2. Then the colorist gave me Brassy Brigitte instead of Harlow Honey. 可是,那里的染发师把我的头发染成了深黄铜色而不是浅蜜糖色。 3. From the telescreen a brassy female voice was squalling a patriotic song. 电幕上一个低沉的女人声音在唱一支爱国歌曲。 4. A buffet of wind made him stagger and he saw that he was out in the open, on rock, under a brassy sky. 一阵风吹得他踉踉跄跄，他看到自己已经到了开阔地，在黄铜色的天穹之下，在山岩之上。', '副词: brassily 比较级: brassier 最高级: brassiest 名词: brassiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('epitaph', '[\'epɪtæf]', 'n.墓志铭', '1. He tried to read the epitaph on the monument. 他试图读出墓碑上的铭文。 2. He wanted these lines as his epitaph. 他想把这些文字作为他的墓志铭。', '形容词: epitaphic');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('divagate', '[\'daɪvəˌgeɪt]', 'vi.(文章或谈话)离题；漂泊', '1. Please don\'t divagate from what we\'re discussing about! We don\'t need your political opinions. 请别从我们所讨论的事岔开话题，我们不需要你政治上的意见。 2. Divagate from （文章或谈话）离题', '名词: divagation 过去式: divagated 过去分词: divagated 现在分词: divagating 第三人称单数: divagates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('imposture', '[ɪm\'pɑːstʃər]', 'n.冒名顶替；欺骗', '1. Soiled by her imposture she remains silent. 她背着冒名顶替者的黑锅却一直沉默。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('conformist', '[kən\'fɔːmɪst]', 'n.遵奉者 adj.因循守旧的', '1. She\'s too much of a conformist to wear silly clothes. 她很古板，不穿那些奇装异服。 2. No one can possibly achieve any real and lasting success by being a conformist. 没有人能够因为随大流而实现真正和持久的成功。 3. Boys tend to be less conformist than girls. 男孩往往没有女孩那么循规蹈矩。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('suborn', '[sə\'bɔːrn]', 'vt.教唆；收买；贿赂；教唆某人作伪证', '1. If he thinks that he can suborn me, he is grievously in error. 如果他认为可以收买我，那他就大错特错了。 2. He tried to suborn the police. 他企图贿赂警方。', '名词: subornation 过去式: suborned 过去分词: suborned 现在分词: suborning 第三人称单数: suborns');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('supersede', '[ˌsuːpər\'siːd]', 'vt.取代；接替；废弃', '1. Will factory workers be entirely superseded by machines one day? 工人将来能完全由机器取代吗? 2. Motorways have largely superseded ordinary roads for long-distance travel. 高速公路多已取代了普通公路。 3. The use of robots will someday supersede manual labor. 机器人的使用有一天会取代人力。 4. Any one could supersede you as manager in my office. 我办公室中的任何一个人都可以接替你的经理职务。', '名词: superseder 过去式: superseded 过去分词: superseded 现在分词: superseding 第三人称单数: supersedes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('chaffing', '[\'tʃæfɪŋ]', 'adj.嘲弄的；玩笑的 动词chaff的现在分词形式.', '1. They chaffed him about his love-life. 他们拿他的爱情生活开玩笑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ignoble', '[ɪɡ\'noʊbl]', 'adj.平民的；卑贱的；卑鄙的；不光彩的', '1. Some very great men have come from ignoble families. 有些伟人出身低微。 2. He is an ignoble man. 他是一个卑鄙的小人。 3. He has achieved whatever work it was in him to do, the fear of death is somewhat abject and ignoble. 完成了他份内要做的所有工作，怕死就有点儿卑鄙和不光彩了。', '副词: ignobly 名词: ignobility');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gluttonous', '[\'ɡlʌtənəs]', 'adj.暴食的；贪吃的；饕餮的', '1. Ve never met a man as gluttonous as him. 我从来没有见过像他那样贪吃的人。 2. Among the guests there was a gluttonous man whose eyes stared at a plate full of walnuts and ate all of them. 客人中有个贪吃的人，眼盯着满满的一碟核桃，全吃光了。', '副词: gluttonously');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('introspective', '[ˌɪntrə\'spektɪv]', 'adj.反省的；内省的', '1. This forces me to look \"inside\" myself and become introspective. 这迫使我往自己“内心”看并变得自省。 2. There were a lot of family problems and Jim became increasingly introspective. 由于出现了很多家庭问题，吉姆变得越来越爱内省了。 3. He allowed his works to express an introspective consciousness of individual isolation. 他使自己的作品表现了孤独的个人内省的意识。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('virtuoso', '[ˌvɜːrtʃu\'oʊsoʊ]', 'n.艺术能手；演艺精湛的人', '1. In the world of car salesmen, Golomb is a virtuoso. 在同行当中，格鲁姆是一位汽车销售艺术家。 2. He is a virtuoso at every endeacour. 他是个非常努力的艺术品鉴赏家. 3. Leslie Lemke is a musical virtuoso. 莱姆克是位音乐演奏名家。', '形容词: virtuosic 副词: virtuosically 名词复数: virtuosos');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unanimous', '[ju\'nænɪməs]', 'adj.全体一致的；一致同意的', '1. The Chinese are unanimous in their condemnation. 全中国人民一致提出谴责。 2. Politicians from all parties were completely unanimous in condemning his action. 所有党派的政治家们都一致谴责他的行为。 3. He was elected with unanimous approval. 他以全体一致同意而中选。 4. The committee were unanimous that the application should be turned down. 委员会一致同意拒绝这项申请。', '副词: unanimously 名词: unanimousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lug', '[lʌɡ]', 'n. 柄； 突出部； 螺帽 n. (英）耳朵 <俚>笨蛋 vt. 拖； 拉； 用力拖动', '1. The striker has a lug that interacts with the sear and is used to hold the striker in the cocked position. 下手帮手有一个与柄互动的那枯萎的而且用来在被耸立的位置中捉住下手帮手。 2. I had to lug my bags up to the fourth floor. 我只得费劲地把我的几个包拖上五楼。 3. At nine his father, a naturalist who had started a reptile park on the Queensland coast, taught him to stalk crocs at night and lug them out of the water. 在他九岁那年，他的父亲，一名自然学家，在昆士兰州海岸开设了一家爬虫类公园，教他在夜里追踪鳄鱼的踪迹，并将它们拖出水面。 4. It is such a shame to use such a fine beast to lug salt. 这么好的马，用它拉沉重的盐太可惜了。', '过去式: lugged 过去分词: lugged 现在分词: lugging 第三人称单数: lugs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('coeval', '[koʊ\'iːvl]', 'adj.同时代 n.同时代的人', '1. Of equal age, duration, or period; coeval. 同年代的年龄、期间或时期相同的；同年代的 2. Of equal age, duration, or period;coeval. 同年代的年龄、期间或时期相同的； 3. Contemporary: Belonging to the same time; coeval. 同时的；同年代的。 4. Analysis has proved that this document is coeval with that one. 这份文件经分析证明与那一份是同一个时代的。', '副词: coevally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('attain', '[ə\'teɪn]', 'v.实现；获得；达到', '1. We can attain whatever goal we set in our mind. 我们设定了什么目标，就能实现什么目标。 2. We should be able to attain that goal. 我们应该能够实现这个目标。 3. The country attained its independence in 1972. 这个国家在1972年获得了独立。 4. They\'re sure to attain emancipation in the end. 他们最后一定能获得解放。', '形容词: attainable 名词: attainability 过去式: attained 过去分词: attained 现在分词: attaining 第三人称单数: attains');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dune', '[duːn]', 'n.沙丘', '1. There are lots of dunes in the desert. 沙漠里有许多沙丘。 2. The little dune is formed with loose dry sand by wind. 这个小沙丘是由风吹来的干沙子形成的。 3. By dusk they finally found the two men on top of a high dune. 黄昏时候,他们终于在一个高高的沙丘顶上发现了那两个人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('albino', '[æl\'baɪnoʊ]', 'n.白化病者；白化变种 adj.白化的', '1. In April 2005, a female albino cobra laid 20 eggs. 2005年4月，一只患白化病的雌眼镜蛇产下20个卵。 2. This humpback mother whale still loves her freaky albino baby. 驼背鲸妈妈仍然爱着她的白化病宝宝。 3. I ended up living with this albino guy who was cleaning windshields. 最后我和患白化症的男人同居。他为港务局的人清洗车窗。', '名词复数: albinos');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bide', '[baɪd]', 'v.等待；忍耐；停留', '1. If we bide our time the chance will come. 只要我们等待时机，总会有希望的。 2. We\'ll have to bide our time until the rain stops. 我们必须等到雨停。', '过去式: bided/bode 过去分词: bided 现在分词: biding 第三人称单数: bides');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('regulate', '[\'reɡjuleɪt]', 'vt.调整；校准；管理；控制', '1. Specification could be regulated as buyer\'s request. 指标可根据客户要求进行调整。 2. Regretfully, we can\'t regulate the irregular liner on the gulf. 遗憾的是我们不能调整海湾上不定期的班船。 3. Your watch is always slow; it needs to be regulated. 你的手表总是慢，需要校准一下。 4. Accidents sometimes happen even in the best regulated families. 即便是在管理最好的家庭，事故有时也会发生的。', '形容词: regulative 过去式: regulated 过去分词: regulated 现在分词: regulating 第三人称单数: regulates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('foible', '[\'fɔɪbl]', 'n.小缺点；小毛病', '1. Lazy is one of the foible in humanity. 人性的弱点之一是懒惰。 2. My grandfather always carries his watch in his pocket, it\'s a foible of his. 我的祖父总是把手表放在口袋里，这是他的一种怪习性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('arrogant', '[\'ærəɡənt]', 'adj.傲慢的；自大的', '1. One should never be arrogant even when he is at his best. 一个人在最得意时也不应傲慢。 2. Well as he does in study, he is not arrogant. 虽然他功课很好，却一点都不傲慢。 3. It\'s arrogant of you to say that. 你竟然那样说，未免太自大了。 4. He is an arrogant man. 他是一个自高自大的人。', '副词: arrogantly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lusty', '[\'lʌsti]', 'adj.健壮的；精力充沛的；贪欲的；欢乐的', '1. He has a strong and lusty son. 他有一个体格健壮精力充沛的儿子。 2. On the benches in his shop were the lusty and valiant young men. 他店内凳子上坐的都是一些强壮骠悍的小伙子。 3. A lusty lady loved a lawyer and longed to lure him from his laboratory. 一位妖媚的小姐爱上了一个律师，渴望能诱使他远离他的实验室。 4. Mary is a lusty singer and a devastating take-off artist. 玛丽是一个活泼的歌唱演员，也是一个极善挖苦模仿别人的人。', '副词: lustily 比较级: lustier 最高级: lustiest 名词: lustiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tan', '[tæn]', 'n.棕褐色；黝黑 v.晒黑；鞣(革)；<俚>痛打 adj.棕褐色的', '1. I bought a pair of tan leather shoes the other day. 前几天我买了双棕褐色的皮鞋。 2. It took me all summer to get this tan. 我花了整个夏天才晒出这样的棕褐色。 3. My tan\'s beginning to fade. 我晒黑的肤色逐渐变浅了。 4. The skin of your cheeks will tan. 你双颊的皮肤将被晒得黝黑. 5. These shoes are tan, not dark brown. 这些鞋是棕黄色的，不是深褐色的。', '形容词: tannish 比较级: tanner 最高级: tannest 过去式: tanned 过去分词: tanned 现在分词: tanning 第三人称单数: tans');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('banter', '[\'bæntər]', 'n.轻松说笑 v.戏弄；开玩笑', '1. He senses the truth beneath her banter. 他辨出这玩笑话里有真意在。 2. The students exchanged banter with each other. 同学们互相开玩笑。 3. It is rude to banter a man out of his senses. 戏弄他人而使其失去理性是无礼的。 4. I do not banter you, I am in earnest. 我没有同你开玩笑，我是认真的。', '副词: banteringly 名词: banterer 过去式: bantered 过去分词: bantered 现在分词: bantering 第三人称单数: banters');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('institute', '[\'ɪnstɪtuːt]', 'n.学院；学会；协会 vt.开始；制定；创立', '1. New methods of teaching foreign languages are adopted in this institute. 该学院采用新的外语教学法。 2. Integrity and professionalism are the two main corporate values of the Institute. 诚信和专业精神是学会的两个主要机构价值观。 3. The UK\'s Securities & Investment Institute provides education and qualifications for many of these staff. 英国证券与投资协会为许多这样的员工提供培训和资格证书。 4. The police instituted an inquiry into the cause of the accident. 警方开始调查事故的原因。', '名词: instituter 过去式: instituted 过去分词: instituted 现在分词: instituting 第三人称单数: institutes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('clause', '[klɔːz]', 'n.条款；[语]从句', '1. There is a contentious clause in the treaty. 这条约中有一条有争议的条款。 2. A penalty clause was written into the contract. 在合同中写入了一项罚款条款。 3. Please pay attention to this clause in the sentence. 请注意看句中的这个从句。 4. This is an attributive clause. 这是一个定语从句。', '形容词: clausal');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('acquainted', '[ə\'kweɪntɪd]', 'adj.熟悉的；认识的；了解的；有知识的 动词acquaint的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. Are you acquainted with him? 你跟他熟吗? 2. I am acquainted with her. 我认识她。 3. We\'ll talk further after you are acquainted with the possibilities for our product sales. 等你们全面了解我们产品销售的可能性之后，我们再进一步细谈。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incandescence', '[ˌɪnkæn\'desns]', 'n.白热光；白热化', '1. A fine wire is heated electrically to incandescence in an electric lamp. 灯丝在电灯中电加时成白炽状态。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('utensil', '[juː\'tensl]', 'n.【C】器具；用具', '1. This store sells cooking utensils. 这商店出售炊具。 2. Teachers use chalk as a writing utensil. 老师们把粉笔当成了一个书写器具了。 3. The cooking utensil were frozen up in the ice. 炊具都给冻在冰里了。 4. I have to buy some kitchen utensils before starting cooking. 开始做饭前，我还得去买些厨房用具。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('poise', '[pɔɪz]', 'n.平衡；姿态；镇静 v.使 ... 平衡；保持 ... 姿势；做准备；盘旋', '1. Good poise is important for a dancer. 保持良好的平衡对舞蹈演员非常重要。 2. He discovers true poise and equilibrium. 他明白了什么是真正的平静和平衡。 3. We admired the graceful poise of the dancer. 我们很欣赏那位舞蹈演员的优美舞姿。 4. She was a beautiful girl with the grace and poise of a natural model. 她是一个美丽的姑娘，有着模特儿的那种优雅姿态。 5. He poised the glass on the shelf. 他把玻璃杯稳稳地放在架子上。', '过去式: poised 过去分词: poised 现在分词: poising 第三人称单数: poises');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('integrity', '[ɪn\'teɡrəti]', 'n.完整；完善；正直；诚实', '1. We must respect each other\'s territorial integrity. 我们应当尊重彼此的领土完整。 2. We all have an interest in maintaining the integrity of the ecosystem. 维持生态系统的完整是我们共同的利益。 3. One of the most important features of the steel cables is their structural integrity. 钢索最重要的特点之一，是结构的完善性。 4. My husband is a man of the highest integrity. 我丈夫是个非常正直的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('overhaul', '[\'oʊvərhɔːl]', 'vt.翻修；仔细检查；革新；赶上 n.彻底检查；全面检修', '1. You should overhaul your car engine. 你应检修你的汽车发动机。 2. The engines were overhauled completely before our departure. 在我们出发之前马达都彻底检修过。 3. There have already been several attempts to overhaul the system. 已有多次尝试彻底改革。 4. The fast cruiser soon overhauled the old cargo boat. 快速巡逻艇迅即赶上那艘旧货船。 5. I\'ve taken my typewriter in for an overhaul. 我已把打字机拿去彻底检修了。', '名词: overhauler 过去式: overhauled 过去分词: overhauled 现在分词: overhauling 第三人称单数: overhauls');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rive', '[raɪv]', 'v.撕开；使沮丧', '1. Double charge will rive a connon. 加倍填药，炸裂炮膛。', '过去式: rived 过去分词: riven/rived 现在分词: riving 第三人称单数: rives');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('renounce', '[rɪ\'naʊns]', 'v.声明放弃；与...断绝关系', '1. He renounced his claim to the property. 他放弃了对财产的要求。 2. The barrister entirely renounce his right to object to a juror. 这位律师完全放弃了反对陪审团成员的权力。 3. It was painful for him to renounce his son. 宣布与儿子脱离关系对他来说是很痛苦的。 4. He renounced his religion and became a Muslim. 他宣布脱离他原来的宗教而成为了一名穆斯林教徒。', '名词: renouncement 过去式: renounced 过去分词: renounced 现在分词: renouncing 第三人称单数: renounces');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('harrow', '[\'hæroʊ]', 'n.耙 vt.耙掘；伤害；使苦恼', '1. The farmer\'s harrow was broken during his working. 农夫正在劳动的时候，耙子断了。 2. I\'ll take the iron harrow to the field. 今天下地干活要用上铁耙了。 3. He is removing weeds with a harrow in the rice field. 他正在用耥耙给稻田除去杂草。 4. This ground harrows well. 这块地很好耙。', '名词: harrower 过去式: harrowed 过去分词: harrowed 现在分词: harrowing 第三人称单数: harrows');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('horrendous', '[hɔː\'rendəs]', 'adj.可怕的；令人震惊的', '1. Many people witnessed the horrendous massacre. 许多人目击到该次令人不寒而栗的大屠杀。 2. He decucted that only one person was capable of committing such a horrendous crime. 他推断出只有一个人能够犯下如此可怕的案子。 3. That colour scheme is horrendous. 那样的色彩设计真让人吃惊.', '副词: horrendously');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('riven', '[\'rɪvn]', 'adj.分裂的；撕裂的 动词rive的过去分词形式.', '1. The family was riven by ancient feuds. 这个家族是由于世代结仇而分裂的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('denunciation', '[dɪˌnʌnsi\'eɪʃn]', 'n.谴责', '1. We were amazed to hear the witness\'s denunciation of the accused. 听了证人对被告的指责,我们大为惊异。 2. All parties joined in bitter denunciation of the terrorists. 所有党派同仇敌忾地痛斥恐怖主义者。', '形容词: denunciative');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('yielding', '[\'jiːldɪŋ]', 'adj.柔软的；听从的；生产的', '1. She sank onto the yielding cushions of the couch. 她沉坐在柔软的沙发垫上。 2. She is rarely yielding on such an issue. 在这类问题上她是很少让步的。 3. The identification of high yielding seeds is not so difficult. 高产量的种子的鉴别没有那么困难。 4. Nitrogen is the most important nutrient for high yielding cultivation of rice plant. 氮是水稻高产栽培中最重要的养分。', '副词: yieldingly 名词: yieldingness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('graduated', '[\'ɡrædʒueɪtɪd]', 'adj.刻度的；(税)累进的；分等级的 动词graduate的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. The graduated rotary shaft makes it easy to grind at any angle. 具有刻度的旋转轴,可随意转换任何角度。 2. This ruler is graduated in centimeters. 这把尺的刻度是厘米。 3. In a graduated tax scheme the more one earns, the more one pays. 按照累进税制，收入多者多纳税。 4. He graduated from a school of crafts and arts. 他毕业于一所工艺美术学校。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fulminate', '[\'fʊlmɪneɪt]', 'v.大声呵斥；强烈谴责；使爆发 n.雷酸盐；雷粉', '1. The newspapers fulminate against the crime. 报纸严厉谴责这个罪行。', '形容词: fulminatory 名词: fulmination 过去式: fulminated 过去分词: fulminated 现在分词: fulminating 第三人称单数: fulminates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('endorse', '[ɪn\'dɔːrs]', 'vt.赞同；支持；背书于', '1. I am afraid I can\'t endorse your opinion. 很抱歉，我不赞成你的意见。 2. I fully endorse their approach. 我完全赞同他们的工作方针。 3. I would like to endorse any choice you make. 我愿意认可你做出的任何选择。 4. He\'s had his license endorsed for dangerous driving. 他的驾驶执照上载有危险驾驶记录。', '形容词: endorsable 异体字: indorse 名词: endorser 过去式: endorsed 过去分词: endorsed 现在分词: endorsing 第三人称单数: endorses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bilingual', '[ˌbaɪ\'lɪŋɡwəl]', 'adj.双语的', '1. Today I would like to try writing a bilingual blog. 今天,我想试着写一篇双语的博客。 2. The course requires you to be bilingual. 这门课程要求修学者懂两门外语。 3. He is virtually bilingual in Spanish and Portuguese. 他实际上讲西班牙语和葡萄牙语两种语言。', '副词: bilingually 名词: bilingualism');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cower', '[\'kaʊər]', 'v.畏缩；退缩；抖缩', '1. The dog cowered (down) under the table. 那只狗吓得蜷伏在桌子底下。 2. In face of difficulties, we should not cower but meet them bravely. 面临困难时我们不应该退缩，而应该勇敢地面对。 3. He cowered away/back as she raised her hand to hit him. 她扬手打他,他立即退缩开[向后退缩]。', '过去式: cowered 过去分词: cowered 现在分词: cowering 第三人称单数: cowers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tempo', '[\'tempoʊ]', 'n.拍子；节奏；速率', '1. We play the music of Mozart at the slow tempo. 我们以慢速演奏了莫扎特的音乐。 2. Don\'t let the other team dictate the tempo of the game. 别让对方球队控制比赛的节奏。 3. We should keep pace with the swift tempo of the day. 我们应跟上时代的飞速步伐。 4. All this was comparatively slow until, with the coming of science, the tempo was suddenly raised. 所有这些发展都比较缓慢，直到出现了科学，其速度才突然加快。', '名词复数: tempos');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('forlorn', '[fər\'lɔːrn]', 'adj.孤独的；凄凉的；渺茫的', '1. She had a forlorn look on her face. 她脸上有一种孤独的神情。 2. She looked wretched and forlorn, despairing of the arrival of a friend who had promised to meet her. 她看上去又可怜又孤独，对于答应来看她的朋友的到来已不抱希望。 3. The house stood forlorn and empty. 房子被弃置了，空无一物。 4. He made his final forlorn attempt. 他做了最后一次几乎无望的努力。', '副词: forlornly 名词: forlornness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('exult', '[ɪɡ\'zʌlt]', 'v.欢欣鼓舞；狂喜；欢跃', '1. Few people would not exult at the abolition of slavery. 奴隶制被废除了,人们无不为之欢欣鼓舞。 2. He did not exult over his rivals 他没有因为战胜了对手而兴高采烈。 3. The soldiers exulted at their victory. 战士们为取得胜利而欢跃。', '副词: exultingly 名词: exultance 过去式: exulted 过去分词: exulted 现在分词: exulting 第三人称单数: exults');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('huffish', '[\'hʌfɪʃ]', 'adj.生气的；不高兴的；发怒的；傲慢的', '1. He is certain breakneck, if he is huffish, may kill us. 他一定非常危险，假如他发怒的话，可能会将我们都杀了。 2. Is mood be agitated easy huffish how adjust and to how adjust and control? 情绪烦躁易发怒怎样调节和控制？ 3. To Fu child for, regular meeting causes not contented sensation, huffish even, resentment. 对妇子来说，常会引起不满足的感觉，甚至发怒、怨恨。 4. I stand in window cannot help laughing, fear C returning again huffish, had had one pile explains. 我站在窗口忍俊不禁，又恐C归来发怒，备好一大堆解释。', '副词: huffishly 名词: huffishness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('obstreperous', '[əb\'strepərəs]', 'adj.吵闹的；喧嚣的；难管束的', '1. He becomes obstreperous when he\'s had a few drinks. 他喝了些酒就爱撒酒疯。 2. He becomes obstreperous when he\'s had a few drink s. 他喝了些酒就爱撒酒疯. 3. In the class that day was an obstreperous man who was creating turmoil. 那天教室里有个任性的男人在捣乱。 4. The Master held up a hand for silence, and called the most obstreperous of the neophytes who had mocked forward, to where he and the end user sat. 无名师抚手不语;命这个嘲笑最终用户的新门徒前坐;坐到最终用户身边.', '副词: obstreperously 名词: obstreperousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('typhoon', '[taɪ\'fuːn]', 'n.台风', '1. The typhoon is gathering strength. 台风的风力正逐渐增强。 2. The typhoon hit the coastal area. 台风侵袭沿海地区。 3. The navy rescued forty people in the typhoon. 海军在台风天时救了四十个人。 4. The typhoon pulled up many trees by the roots. 台风把许多树连根拔了起来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('clash', '[klæʃ]', 'n.冲突；抵触；撞击声 vt.使…发出撞击声 vi.引起冲突', '1. A border clash between the two armies started the war. 双方军队在边境的冲突引发了战争。 2. In some ways,ours is a clash of cultures. 从某种意义上来说，我们的冲突是不同文化间的冲突。 3. The issue really boils down to a clash between left and right. 这场争论确实可归结为左派与右派之间的冲突。 4. His opinions clash against yours. 他的观点和你的相抵触。 5. She clashed these pans down on the floor. 她将这些盘子哗啦一声摔在地上。 6. The enemy armies clashed near the border. 敌军在边境附近发生冲突。', '过去式: clashed 过去分词: clashed 现在分词: clashing 第三人称单数: clashes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('antecedent', '[ˌæntɪ\'siːdnt]', 'n.前情；先行词；祖先 adj.在 ... 之前的；居先的', '1. This is an antecedent of the war. 这是战争的前因。 2. Something out mind always has antecedent. 意想不到的事情总是有其前因的。 3. The word \"man\" is the antecedent of \"who\" in \"the man who spoke\". \"man\"这个字是\"the man who spoke\"中\"who\"的先行词。 4. No one knew the antecedents of the mysterious stranger. 谁也不知道那个神秘陌生人的身世。 5. Those were events antecedent to the revolution. 这些都是革命前的事了。', '副词: antecedently');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('diffident', '[\'dɪfɪdənt]', 'adj.无自信的；客客气气的；羞怯的', '1. He was too diffident to express his opinion. 他太不自信，不敢发表自己的见解。 2. She is diffident about expressing her opinions. 她怯于表述自己的意见。 3. He has a politely diffident manner. 他的态度是客气中带有羞怯。', '副词: diffidently');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('trepidation', '[ˌtrepɪ\'deɪʃn]', 'n.恐惧；惊惶；忧虑；颤抖', '1. They kept dumb in fear and trepidation. 他们诚惶诚恐一言不发。 2. The threat of an epidemic caused great alarm and trepidation. 流行病猖獗因而人心惶惶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lasting', '[\'læstɪŋ]', 'adj.永久的；永恒的 动词last的现在分词.', '1. This agreement will pave the way for a lasting peace. 这个协议将为持久和平铺路。 2. I hope you will strike up a lasting friendship. 我希望你们将建立起永久的友谊。 3. Her face left a lasting impression on me. 她的脸让我留下了永恒的印象。 4. Nothing can break the lasting friendship between us. 没有任何东西能破坏我们的永恒友谊。', '副词: lastingly 名词: lastingness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('weary', '[\'wɪri]', 'adj.疲倦的；厌烦的 v.疲倦；厌烦；生厌', '1. After many hours in the saddle he was very weary. 骑马骑了几个小时后，他非常疲倦。 2. I feel weary after such a long journey. 经过这么长时间的旅行后，我觉得很累。 3. We all grew weary of his long-winded speech. 我们对他冗长的发言都感到很厌烦。 4. He began to be weary of the research work. 他开始对研究工作感到厌烦。 5. The long walk completely wearied us. 这麽长的路走得我们疲惫不堪。', '副词: wearily 比较级: wearier 最高级: weariest 名词: weariness 过去式: wearied 过去分词: wearied 现在分词: wearying 第三人称单数: wearies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('profuse', '[prə\'fjuːs]', 'adj.很多的；丰富的；慷慨的；浪费的', '1. He made profuse apologies. 他再三道歉。 2. There are profuse blossoms. 那儿有很多花朵。 3. Many hybrids are profuse and persistent with flowers. 许多杂种开花繁茂耐久。 4. The truth is, that nature, seldom profuse, and seldom niggardly, has distributed her gifts more equally than she is generally supposed to have done. 事实是,自然总是将天赋公平地分配给人们,比人们通常认为的还要不偏不倚,很少过分地慷慨,也很少吝啬。', '副词: profusely 名词: profuseness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('homograph', '[\'hɑːməɡræf]', 'n.同形异义字', '1. Homograph: when two word are identical in spelling. 同形异义：两个词拼写相同。 2. How can the Trust Center help protect me from homograph attacks? 信任中心如何帮助我抵御形似字攻击? 3. In semantics, Jianyu construction is of homograph, while SVOC is polysemantic. 在语义上，汉语兼语式是同形异义构块，而英语的SVOC是多义构块。 4. In more sophisticated homograph attacks, the Web address looks exactly like that of a legitimate Web site. 在大多数复杂的同形异义词攻击中,Web地址看上去确实像合法网站的Web地址。', '形容词: homographic');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scorch', '[skɔːrtʃ]', 'v.（使）烧焦；变焦；（使）枯萎 n.烧焦', '1. Jenny scorch her jacket carelessly while she is smoking her pipe. 珍妮抽烟斗时不小心把夹克烧焦。 2. Luckily, flashes of such strong radiation occur so far away they will not scorch our planet. 幸运的是，诸如这类的强辐射大发生离我们非常的遥远，他们不会烧焦我们的地球。 3. Jenny scorch her jacket carelessly while she is smoking her pipe. 珍妮抽烟斗时不小心把夹克烧焦。 4. Luckily, flashes of such strong radiation occur so far away they will not scorch our planet. 幸运的是，诸如这类的强辐射大发生离我们非常的遥远，他们不会烧焦我们的地球。', '副词: scorchingly 过去式: scorched 过去分词: scorched 现在分词: scorching 第三人称单数: scorches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('candidate', '[\'kændɪdət]', 'n.候选人；应试者', '1. There are three candidates for the vacancy. 这一空缺有三名候选人。 2. She had been nominated as candidate for the presidency. 她已被提名为总统候选人。 3. He made several favorable comments about their candidate. 他对他们的候选人发表了一些有利的评论。 4. Most candidates passed in grammar. 参加考试的人大多数语法及格。', '名词: candidacy');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('portray', '[pɔːr\'treɪ]', 'vt.描写；描绘；饰演', '1. It is difficult to portray feelings in words. 感情很难用言语来描写。 2. The book portrays the life of an actor. 这本书描述了一个演员的一生。 3. The picture portrays a beautiful sunset. 这幅画描绘了落日美景。 4. The actor is trying his best to portray the role of Hamlet. 这位演员尽力扮演哈姆雷特的角色。', '形容词: portrayable 名词: portrayer 过去式: portrayed 过去分词: portrayed 现在分词: portraying 第三人称单数: portrays');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('untold', '[ˌʌn\'toʊld]', 'adj.数不清的(没有说到的)', '1. Untold millions of believers have served him faithfully under despotic governments. 数不清的信徒是在暴虐专横的政府之下忠心地服事主。 2. She brought with her all other good things, untold riches in her hands. 的确，一切美物都伴她而来，在她手中握有数不清的财富。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('intentional', '[ɪn\'tenʃənl]', 'adj.存心的；故意的', '1. His insult was intentional. 他的侮辱是有意的。 2. If I hurt your feelings, it was not intentional . 我若伤了你的感情 3. The official reportedly said the collision did not appear to be intentional. 据报导，这位美军官员称碰撞看来不是故意的。', '副词: intentionally 名词: intentionality');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('encompass', '[ɪn\'kʌmpəs]', 'vt.围绕；包围；包括；完成', '1. The prison is encompassed by high walls. 监狱被高墙围绕着。 2. The voices of people and sounds of cars encompass his path. 他在路上听见四面八方都是人声车声。 3. The general arts at the university encompass a wide range of subjects. 大学文科包括的科目非常广泛。', '名词: encompassment 过去式: encompassed 过去分词: encompassed 现在分词: encompassing 第三人称单数: encompasses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('meander', '[mi\'ændər]', 'v.缓慢而弯曲地流动；漫步；闲聊 n.河流的曲折；漫步；迂回曲折的进程', '1. They tumble down mountainsides; they meander through flat farmlands. 它们滚滚冲下山脊，蜿蜒穿过平坦的农田。 2. I liked to meander through familiar streets. 我喜欢闲逛穿过熟悉的街道。 3. They usually meander down to the pub after work. 他们通常下班后漫步到那家小酒店去。 4. The discussion meandered (on) for hours. 讨论会漫无边际地进行了几小时。 5. Major changes in a river course result in both lateral shifts of the old meander belt and in the development of new belts. 河道中大的变动，造成老河曲带的侧向迁移和新河曲带的产生。', '形容词: meandrous 副词: meanderingly 名词: meanderer 过去式: meandered 过去分词: meandered 现在分词: meandering 第三人称单数: meanders');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tutor', '[\'tuːtər]', 'n.家庭教师；导师 v.指导；当家庭教师；当导师', '1. His parents employed a tutor to teach him Greek. 他父母雇佣了一位家庭教师来教他希腊语。 2. My tutor is an accomplished scholar. 我的导师是一位学识渊博的学者。 3. Most parents have no time to tutor their children. 大部分家长没有时间辅导孩子。 4. For extra money, she tutors on weekends. 为了多挣些钱，她在周末当家庭教师。', '过去式: tutored 过去分词: tutored 现在分词: tutoring 第三人称单数: tutors');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('disinfectant', '[ˌdɪsɪn\'fektənt]', 'adj.消毒的 n.消毒剂', '1. The nurse bathed the wound with disinfectant water. 护士用消毒水冲洗伤口。 2. Clean the infected area with disinfectant. 把受感染的部分用消毒剂消毒. 3. Dip your injured finger in the disinfectant to soak out the poison. 把你受伤的手指浸在消毒剂里，把毒浸泡出来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scald', '[skɔːld]', 'v.烫伤；用沸水烫洗；加热至接近沸点 n.烫伤；烫洗；(植物的)晒焦', '1. She was scalded when the boiler exploded. 锅炉爆炸时她被烫伤了。 2. Scald the needles to sterilize them. 用沸水烫洗一下这些针，消一下毒。 3. Scald the milk and then add it to the egg and sugar mixture. 把牛奶加热至沸点，然后再加加进鸡蛋和糖的混合液中。 4. It is an ointment for burns and scalds. 这是治疗烧伤和烫伤的药膏。', '过去式: scalded 过去分词: scalded 现在分词: scalding 第三人称单数: scalds');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('irradicable', '[ɪ\'rædɪkəbəl]', 'adj.不能根除的', '1. irradicable weeds;irradicable prejudices. 无法根除的杂草;根据蒂固的偏见 2. irradicable weeds; irradicable prejudices. 无法根除的杂草；根据蒂固的偏见', '副词: irradicably');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('filly', '[\'fɪli]', 'n.小牝马；小姑娘', '1. The filly has been raced twice this season . 这匹小牝马本季度曾两次参赛。', '名词复数: fillies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nuance', '[\'nuːɑːns]', 'n.细微差别', '1. He watched her face intently to catch every nuance of expression. 他认真地注视着她的脸，捕捉每一丝细微的表情变化。 2. He was aware of every nuance in her voice. 他了解她声音中的每个细微之处。 3. These users will easily learn each nuance of the applications they use. 这些用户会很快了解他们所使用程序的每一细微差别。', '形容词: nuanced');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('resourceful', '[rɪ\'sɔːrsfl]', 'adj.资源丰富的；足智多谋的', '1. Til is a resourceful textile material. 胡麻是一种资源丰富的纺织原料。 2. He is a keen and resourceful politician. 他是个头脑敏锐又足智多谋的政治家。 3. He\'s an old man who is intelligent and resourceful. 他是一位足智多谋的老叟。', '副词: resourcefully 名词: resourcefulness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unison', '[\'juːnɪsn]', 'n.(做事、说话)一起；一致行动；(歌唱或演奏)齐声', '1. They ran together, their legs moving in unison. 他们步调一致地一起跑。 2. The banks have acted in unison with the Building Societies in lowering interest rates. 银行降低了利率来配合房屋建筑协会的行动。 3. The last verse will be sung in unison. 歌词的最后部分要齐唱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vandalism', '[\'vændəlɪzəm]', 'n.【U】故意破坏公物（艺术或文化的等）的行为', '1. Vandalism used to be a rare occurrence here. 过去这里很少发生故意破坏公物的事。 2. The school suffered from widespread vandalism. 这所学校遭受广泛的野蛮破坏。 3. However, vandalism and theft are criminal offenses. 然而，故意破坏和偷窃是犯罪行为。', '形容词: vandalistic');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('deputy', '[\'depjuti]', 'n.代表；副手；议员', '1. My younger brother is my deputy during my absence. 我不在时，我弟弟代表我。 2. He is a deputy to the National People\'s Congress. 他是人民代表大会代表。 3. I must find someone to act as a deputy for me during my absence. 我必须找一个人，在我离开期间代理我的职务。 4. I am resigning as chairman and handing over to my deputy. 我现在辞去主席职位，交由我的副手接替。', '名词复数: deputies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('abet', '[ə\'bet]', 'v.煽动；教唆；怂恿', '1. It\'s illegal to aid and abet a thief. 伙同小偷作案是有罪的。 2. He wouldn\'t throw the stone if those boys did not abet him. 要不是那些男孩子怂恿他，他不会扔那块石头。 3. To tolerate evil is to abet it; coddling wrong only helps the devil. 纵容坏事即是怂恿；过分宽容就会助长坏人坏事。', '名词: abetment 过去式: abetted 过去分词: abetted 现在分词: abetting 第三人称单数: abets');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('excogitate', '[eks\'kɒdʒəˌteɪt]', 'vt.想出；设计', '1. But, japanese is to excogitate special chili to reduce weight food, be not thought like you, dry gnaw chili. 但是，日本人是研究出专门的辣椒减肥食品，并不是像你所想的，干啃辣椒。 2. He can not excogitate the stratagem himself,there must be some teach him to do like this. 他自己是想不出那个计谋的。一定是有人教他这么做的。 3. Algorithms in the program excogitate technology are recounted,a new algorithm of solving knapsack problem is expounded,it uses algorithms amalgamate. 介绍了程序设计技术中的几种算法 ,并利用算法间的混合提出了一种解决背包问题的新型算法 4. I wouldn\'t put the question to you for the world, and expose you to the inconvenience of having to excogitate an answer. 我决不会来问你这个问题，叫你不得不编造答案出尽洋相。', '形容词: excogitative 名词: excogitation 过去式: excogitated 过去分词: excogitated 现在分词: excogitating 第三人称单数: excogitates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lasso', '[\'læsoʊ]', 'n.套索(捕捉牛、马用) v.用套索捕捉', '1. He tried to throw a lasso but he got the rope all fouled up. 他想扔出个套索，却把绳子缠在一起了。 2. The cowboy captures a calf with a lasso and binds its feet. 牛仔用绳索捕获小牛并绑住它的腿。 3. Futuristic cowboy straddles a rocket attempting to lasso various robo-cattle. 未来派牛仔骑着火箭弹试图套住机器牛。', '名词: lassoer 名词复数: lassos 过去式: lassoed 过去分词: lassoed 现在分词: lassoing 第三人称单数: lassos/lassoes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('impede', '[ɪm\'piːd]', 'vt.妨碍；阻止', '1. The inflexibility of the country\'s labor market seriously impede its economic recovery. 该国劳工市场缺乏灵活性，这严重阻碍了它的经济恢复。 2. The development of the project was seriously impeded by a reduction in funds. 由于基金削减工程进度严重受阻。 3. He impedes me to do the job well. 他妨碍我把工作做好。 4. What impedes you to make progress? 什么事妨碍你取得进步？', '名词: impeder 过去式: impeded 过去分词: impeded 现在分词: impeding 第三人称单数: impedes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('abject', '[\'æbdʒekt]', 'adj.卑贱的；不幸的；可怜的', '1. She was not aware that the English habits of comfort attach an idea of abject misery to the idea of a barefootedtraveller. 她不了解英国人出于爱舒服的习惯总把一个赤脚的旅行者看成最可怜的人。', '副词: abjectly 名词: abjectness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dolt', '[doʊlt]', 'n.笨蛋；傻瓜；呆子', '1. The boy is a dolt,but we\'ll hammer these facts into his dull wits. 这个小男孩是个笨蛋，但我们要强行把这些事灌输进他那迟纯的头脑。 2. He\'s a first-class dolt who insists on doing things his way. 他是一等的傻瓜，坚持要以自己的方式做事情。', '形容词: doltish 副词: doltishly 名词: doltishness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mean', '[miːn]', 'v.意思是；打算；导致；意味 adj.低劣的；刻薄的；卑鄙的；出色的；吝啬的；平均的；中等的 n.平均值；平均数；中间；中庸', '1. What does this word mean? 这个单词是什么意思？ 2. I mean that\'s his own decision to resign or not. 我的意思是说辞不辞职是他自己的决定。 3. I mean to call on you tomorrow. 我打算明天看望你。 4. His father meant him to be an engineer. 他父亲打算让他当工程师。 5. Don\'t be so mean to your little brother! 别对你弟弟那麽刻薄！ 6. It is an estimate of the mean of the population. 这是对人口平均数的一个估计。', '副词: meanly 比较级: meaner 最高级: meanest 过去式: meant 过去分词: meant 现在分词: meaning 第三人称单数: means');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('milestone', '[\'maɪlstoʊn]', 'n.里程碑', '1. Type a name and date for the milestone. 键入里程碑的名称和日期。 2. Each birthday is a milestone we touch along life\'s way. 每个生日都是我们人生中的里程碑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('shale', '[ʃeɪl]', 'n.页岩；泥板岩', '1. The new process extracts oil from shale. 这一新过程可从页岩里提炼出石油。 2. Most of the rock in this mountain is shale. 这座山上大部分的岩石都是页岩。 3. It is the density data of the shale. 这是泥页岩密度数据。', '形容词: shaley');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dull', '[dʌl]', 'adj.呆滞的；钝的；迟钝的；无趣的；暗的 v.变钝；迟钝', '1. Jack had all work but no play, making him a dull boy. 杰克只学不玩,这使得他成为一个呆笨的孩子。 2. It\'s impossible to cut a pineapple with such a dull knife. 用一把这么钝的刀子切菠萝是不可能的。 3. The mind becomes dull if the body doesn\'t get on exercise. 要是身体得不到锻炼,头脑也会迟钝的。 4. This book is rather dull. 这本书很枯燥。 5. The heating was turned up high to dull his audience\'s senses. 暖气温度被调到很高，以至于听众的意识变得迟钝。', '形容词: dullish 副词: dully 比较级: duller 最高级: dullest 名词: dullness 过去式: dulled 过去分词: dulled 现在分词: dulling 第三人称单数: dulls');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mercantile', '[\'mɜːrkəntaɪl]', 'adj.贸易的；商业的', '1. San Francisco and New York are important mercantile ports in America. 旧金山和纽约是美国重要的贸易港口。 2. I\'ve never seen you since at that mercantile evening last year. 自从去年的商务晚会以后我就没有再碰见你了。 3. The mercantile exchange led the push into electronic trading in the early 1990’s. 在20世纪90年代前期，商业交易所就推动电子交易。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('endue', '[ɪn\'djuː]', 'vt.授与；赋与', '1. He prayed to God night and day to endue him with the spirit of holiness. 他日夜祈求上帝赋予他虔敬的心。', '异体字: indue 过去式: endued 过去分词: endued 现在分词: enduing 第三人称单数: endues');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('discriminate', '[dɪ\'skrɪmɪneɪt]', 'vt.区分；区别对待 vi.辨别；差别对待', '1. You must learn to discriminate fact from opinion. 你必须学会把事实和看法区分开。 2. Can you discriminate good books from bad? 你能区别好书与坏书吗？ 3. Death does not discriminate; it comes to everyone. 死亡对每个人都一视同仁，它会降临到每个人的身上。 4. He is able to discriminate good book from bad. 他具有区分优秀图书与低劣图书的能力。 5. You must learn to discriminate between things. 你必须学会区别事物。', '副词: discriminately 过去式: discriminated 过去分词: discriminated 现在分词: discriminating 第三人称单数: discriminates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gesticulate', '[dʒe\'stɪkjuleɪt]', 'v.用姿势(动作)示意；打手势', '1. He tried to gesticulate a message. 他试图用手势来传递信息。 2. He was gesticulating wildly at me, but I could not understand what he was trying to tell me. 他使劲向我做手势，可是我不明白他的意思。', '形容词: gesticulative 名词: gesticulator 过去式: gesticulated 过去分词: gesticulated 现在分词: gesticulating 第三人称单数: gesticulates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wiggle', '[\'wɪɡl]', 'v.扭动；摆动 n.扭动；蠕动；奶油青豆烧鱼', '1. Wombat wanted to wiggle along the ground. 毛鼻袋熊想在地面上扭动前进。 2. The baby was wiggling its toes. 那幼儿扭动著脚趾。 3. If you can\'t wiggle your toes, your shoes are too tight. 如果你不能摆动脚趾，鞋子就太紧了。 4. Wombat wanted to wiggle along the ground. 毛鼻袋熊想在地面上扭动前进。', '形容词: wiggly 过去式: wiggled 过去分词: wiggled 现在分词: wiggling 第三人称单数: wiggles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('habitable', '[\'hæbɪtəbl]', 'adj.可居住的；适于居住的', '1. It will take a lot of spit and polish to get this room habitable again. 要想使这间屋子能住人的话，那将要好好打扫一下。 2. The lowest habitable story of a building, usually below ground level. 建筑物最低的可居住楼层一般在地平面以下。 3. This house is too old to be habitable. 这间房子太旧了,不适合人居住。 4. If they melted,could Mars become a habitable place? 如果它们融化的话，火星能够成为一个可以居住的地方吗?', '副词: habitably 名词: habitability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stature', '[\'stætʃər]', 'n.身高；名望', '1. She was rather small in stature. 她身材矮小。 2. He is five feet five inches in stature/height. 他身高5英尺5英寸。 3. She had not yet grown to full stature. 她的个子还没有完全长到应有的高度。 4. He is a musician of world stature. 他是一个世界级的音乐家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('probity', '[\'proʊbəti]', 'n.诚实；廉洁；正直', '1. Jobbery crime is an extreme form of social corruption which has destoried the political probity and social justice. 职务犯罪是社会腐败的一种极端形式，它腐蚀政治清明，破坏经济发展，损害社会正义。 2. But there is scant risk of too much fiscal probity in Washington. 但在华盛顿再多财政廉洁也没有大风险。 3. The administrator gained much public praise because of his efficiency and probity. 这位行政官因其高效和廉洁而受到了人民的称赞。 4. Probity will command respect everywhere. 为人正直无论在哪里都会受人尊敬。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('castigate', '[\'kæstɪɡeɪt]', 'v.惩罚；严厉批评；谴责', '1. Reconnoitring and collecting evidence is the first step to castigate such crime. 侦查与取证是打击这种犯罪的第一步。 2. She could not find sufficient reproaches with which to castigate herself. 她找不出充分的理由非难自己。', '名词: castigation 过去式: castigated 过去分词: castigated 现在分词: castigating 第三人称单数: castigates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('juggernaut', '[\'dʒʌɡərnɔːt]', 'n. 摧毁一切的强大力量； <英>重型卡车', '1. The Juggernaut of war. 迷信战事而使人牺牲一切', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ferry', '[\'feri]', 'n.渡船；渡口 vt.摆渡；运输 vi.摆渡', '1. There\'s a good duty-free shop (ie one selling such goods) on the ferry. 渡船上有个挺不错的免税商店。 2. The sway of the ferry made him feel sick. 渡船摇摇晃晃，他感到恶心。 3. We crossed the river by ferry. 我们坐渡船过了河。 4. He went down to the ferry but found the boat on the other side. 他到了渡口，却发现渡船在对岸。 5. Two small boats ferry people back and forth. 两只小船往返为人摆渡。 6. The tourists ferried across to the opposite bank. 游客摆渡到对岸。', '名词复数: ferries 过去式: ferried 过去分词: ferried 现在分词: ferrying 第三人称单数: ferries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tarnish', '[\'tɑːrnɪʃ]', 'n.晦暗；污渍 v.沾污', '1. Moisture leads to the tarnish of the silverware. 湿气使得银器毫无光泽。 2. Check cutlery to make sure them free from tarnish and stain. 检查餐具的清洁,保证光亮无污渍。 3. The firm\'s good name was badly tarnished by the scandal. 这件丑事玷污了公司的好名声。 4. If news of this gets out, it will tarnish his image. 如果这消息传出去', '形容词: tarnishable 过去式: tarnished 过去分词: tarnished 现在分词: tarnishing 第三人称单数: tarnishes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('svelte', '[svelt]', 'adj.苗条的；文雅的；和蔼的', '1. All Americans crave to be svelte and rich. 所有的美国人都渴望身材苗条和富有。 2. A lady wears white yarn tippet, svelte coming from a distance. 远处还有一位身披白纱的贵妇，娉婷而来。', '副词: sveltely 比较级: svelter 最高级: sveltest 名词: svelteness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('filch', '[fɪltʃ]', 'v.偷(不贵重的东西)', '1. Who\'s filched my pencil? 谁把我的铅笔拿走了? 2. Oliver filched a packet of cigarettes from a well-dressed passenger. 奥立佛从一名衣冠楚楚的乘客身上偷得一包香烟。', '名词: filcher 过去式: filched 过去分词: filched 现在分词: filching 第三人称单数: filches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('referee', '[ˌrefə\'riː]', 'n.裁判员；仲裁人；鉴定人；证明人 v.裁判；仲裁', '1. The referee whistled and the game began. 裁判哨子一响，比赛开始了。 2. Does the referee have the power to send him off the field? 裁判员有权勒令他退场吗? 3. He was booked by the referee for foul play. 他因为动作犯规而被裁判记下姓名。 4. At the end of each match, players must maintain the final screens and receive confirmation from a referee. 在每个比赛结束的时候,运动员一定维持最后的荧屏而且受到来自一个仲裁人的证实。 5. Who\'s going to referee the basketball match? 谁将担任这场篮球赛的裁判?', '过去式: refereed 过去分词: refereed 现在分词: refereeing 第三人称单数: referees');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bower', '[\'baʊər]', 'n.树荫处(凉亭)；闺房', '1. There is a bower on the knoll. 小山上有一个凉亭。 2. He sat in the bower to have a rest. 他坐在凉亭里，休息一会儿。 3. Mrs Quilp was pining in her bower. 奎尔普太太正在她的闺房里度着愁苦的岁月。 4. Lucy arranged her bower and put on her best white frock. 露西整理好闺房,然后穿上她最好的白色连衣裙。', '形容词: bowery 过去式: bowered 过去分词: bowered 现在分词: bowering 第三人称单数: bowers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('grouse', '[ɡraʊs]', 'n.松鸡；牢骚 v.埋怨；发牢骚', '1. Grouse will soon be in season again. 捕猎松鸡的时期又快到了。 2. If you don\'t agree with me, please forget my grouse. 如果你的看法不同，请不必介意我的牢骚之言。 3. If you\'ve got any grouses, you\'d better tell me about them. 你若有什麽不满就跟我说. 4. Old Charlie would find something new to grouse about each day. 老查理每天总会找到新的抱怨的对象。', '名词: grouser 名词复数: grouse 过去式: groused 过去分词: groused 现在分词: grousing 第三人称单数: grouses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ecstasy', '[\'ekstəsi]', 'n.狂喜；入迷 Ecstasy. n.摇头丸', '1. Love brings ecstasy and relieves loneliness. 爱带来狂喜，减轻孤独。 2. Davidson\'s eyes shone with ecstasy. 戴维逊的双眼发出狂喜的光芒。 3. His ecstasy to the pop music is unbelievable. 他对流行音乐的入迷是令人难以置信的。 4. Tantra teaches that lovemaking between a man and woman, when entered into with awareness, is a gateway to both sexual and spiritual ecstasy. 坦陀罗教导男女之间的做爱，当进入知晓的时候，是性和精神入迷的道路。 5. The drug is commonly known as Ecstasy. 这种致幻药通常称作摇头丸。', '名词复数: ecstasies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('overturn', '[ˌoʊvər\'tɜːrn]', 'v.翻倒；推翻；颠覆 n.倾覆；打翻', '1. The boat overturned but didn\'t sank. 小船翻了，但没有沉。 2. The revolutionist planned to overturn this puppet regime. 革命者计划推翻傀儡政府。 3. Some high-ranking officers plotted to overturn the government. 有几名高级军官策划推翻政府。 4. The 21st century will overturn many of our basic assumptions about economic life. 21世纪将会颠覆很多我们关于经济生活的基础假设。 5. This is one of the important reasons for overturn of ro-ro ships. 这是许多滚装船发生倾覆的重要原因之一。', '过去式: overturned 过去分词: overturned 现在分词: overturning 第三人称单数: overturns');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('disparage', '[dɪ\'spærɪdʒ]', 'vt.蔑视；贬损', '1. The Arya Samaj did much to encourage Hindu nationalism, but it did not disparage the knowledge of the West, and it established many schools and colleges. 雅利安社大力地鼓励了印度的民族主义，但它并没有蔑视西方的知识，也建立了很多学校和大学。', '副词: disparagingly 名词: disparagement 过去式: disparaged 过去分词: disparaged 现在分词: disparaging 第三人称单数: disparages');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tentative', '[\'tentətɪv]', 'adj.不确定的；暂时的；试验性质的；犹豫不决的', '1. He still held a tentative relationship with Mary. 他还和玛丽保持着若即若离的关系。 2. Could we make a tentative appointment for Friday? 我们能暂时先约在星期五吗? 3. We\'ve drawn up a tentative program for the next two weeks. 我们制定了一个之后两个星期的试探性计划。 4. Each step he took was slightly tentative. 他每走一步都有些迟疑不决。', '副词: tentatively 名词: tentativeness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('matte', '[mæt]', 'adj.表面无光泽的；粗糙的 n.[冶]锍；冰铜 =mat. =matt.', '1. This paper fully introduced the industrial tests and the basic theory of roasting Antimony matte containing Gold by rotary-kiln. 本文全面论述了含金锑锍回转窑焙烧工业性试验及其理论基础。 2. Melting behavior of silica flux in the converting process of high grade copper matte was investigated. 研究了高品位铜冰铜转炉吹炼石英熔剂熔化行为。 3. The consumption and utilization rate of oxygen for copper matte converting under steady production conditions are simulated. 对稳定生产条件下冰铜吹炼过程耗氧量及全期氧气利用率进行仿真计算。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lump', '[lʌmp]', 'n.块；团；笨重的人；瘤 v.使成块；形成团状；归并；(笨重地)移动', '1. The surgeon excised the lump from her breast. 外科医生切除了她乳房的肿块。 2. It was amazing to watch the lump of clay take life beneath the sculptor\'s hands. 看着泥团在雕塑家手下成了栩栩如生的形象真令人惊叹。 3. The heat brought his fingers back to life,but did nothing for the cold lump in the pit of his stomach. 炉火使手指缓过劲来了，但对他肚子里的那团凉气却无济于事。 4. Since the urease activity in soil is close correlated with the growth of stem lump mustard and soil metabolism, which is a key indicator of soil ecology and soil fertility. 土壤脲酶活性高低反映出茎瘤芥生长和土壤代谢状况，可作为茎瘤芥土壤生态和肥力水平的一个良好指标。 5. The oatmeal lumps if you don\'t stir it well. 如果你不好好搅拌，麦片粥会结块。', '过去式: lumped 过去分词: lumped 现在分词: lumping 第三人称单数: lumps');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('superintend', '[ˌsuːpərɪn\'tend]', 'v.管理；监督；指挥', '1. The manager is superintending the staff\'s work. 经理正在监督工人的工作。 2. He was appointed to superintend the toy department. 他获任玩具部的负责人。', '名词: superintendence 过去式: superintended 过去分词: superintended 现在分词: superintending 第三人称单数: superintends');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sophism', '[\'sɒfɪzəm]', 'n.诡辩', '1. After all, dialectic is very close to the sophism. 思辨与诡辩，只有一步之遥。 2. \"That\'s a beautiful sophism\" said the girl with a smile more beautiful still. “那是一种美丽的诡辩，”女孩子说，露出了更加美好的笑容。 3. Dialectical reasoning needs the \"supervision\" of analytical reasoning, otherwise it will lead to sophism. 辩证理性需要分析理性的“监督”，否则就会沦为诡辩。 4. Dialectical reasoning needs the \"supervision\" of analytical reasoning,otherwise it will lead to sophism. 辩证理性需要分析理性的“监督”,否则就会沦为诡辩。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incense', '[\'ɪnsens]', 'n.香；阿谀 vt.对 ... 敬香；熏香；激怒', '1. Distant dreams rise like incense. 梦在远方化成一缕香。 2. The monk burned a stick of incense in the incense burner. 和尚在香炉里焚上一柱香。 3. To pray for health, every pilgrim would incense and worship here. 想祈求健康去除病魔的信徒们都要到这里烧香拜佛。 4. Some people enjoy using incense. 一些人喜欢使用熏香。', '过去式: incensed 过去分词: incensed 现在分词: incensing 第三人称单数: incenses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('drove', '[droʊv]', 'n.畜群；一大群；移动的人群或大批的东西 v.开车；驱赶；迫使（drive的过去式）', '1. He drove into the ditch completely unaware. 他不知不觉地把车开进了沟里。 2. The child\'s continual crying drove me to distraction. 那孩子不断的哭声弄得我几乎要发狂。 3. Avarice drove him into theft. 贪婪驱使他偷窃。 4. He struggled with his assailants and eventually drove them off. 他同攻击他的人进行搏斗，最后把他们赶走了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('plaster', '[\'plæstər]', 'n.石膏；灰泥；膏药 v.涂以灰泥；敷以膏药；使 ... 平', '1. His broken leg was encased in plaster. 他折的腿打上了石膏。 2. They closed the cracks in the wall with plaster. 他们用石膏把墙上的裂缝填满了。 3. This plaster may crack when it dries. 这种灰泥变干时可能会龟裂。 4. The plaster had started to come away from the wall. 灰泥已经开始从墙上脱落。 5. Will it take long to plaster the ceiling? 把天花板涂上灰泥要花很长时间吗?', '形容词: plastery 名词: plasterer 过去式: plastered 过去分词: plastered 现在分词: plastering 第三人称单数: plasters');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('invigorate', '[ɪn\'vɪɡəreɪt]', 'vt.增添活力；鼓舞；激励', '1. Serving to invigorate; stimulating. 使兴奋的使人精力充沛的; 使兴奋的 2. I feel invigorated by all this fresh air! 空气很清新，我觉得精神焕发！', '副词: invigoratingly 名词: invigoration 过去式: invigorated 过去分词: invigorated 现在分词: invigorating 第三人称单数: invigorates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('symposium', '[sɪm\'poʊziəm]', 'n.讨论会；酒会；论文集', '1. We will hold a symposium this afternoon. 今天下午，我们要召开一次讨论会。 2. In this symposium, my part is only to sit in silence. 在这次讨论会上，我只要安静的坐着就够了。', '名词复数: symposiums');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('realm', '[relm]', 'n.领域；王国', '1. They exist only in the physical realm. 它们只存在于物质感官的领域。 2. He made outstanding contributions in the realm of foreign affairs. 他在外交领域作出了卓越贡献。 3. The material realm is one area that everyone relates to. 物质领域是与每个人有联系的一个地方。 4. He was banished from the realm. 他被驱逐出境。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reverse', '[rɪ\'vɜːrs]', 'v.逆转；倒退；互换；改变 adj.相反的；反面的；颠倒的 n.相反；背面；失败；倒档', '1. The government has failed to reverse the economic decline. 政府未能扭转经济滑坡的趋势。 2. He reversed the car into a tree. 他倒车撞到了树上。 3. Statistics showed a reverse trend to that recorded in other countries. 统计数字表明这种趋向与其他国家所示情况迥异。 4. Count down in reverse order 10, 9, 8... 倒数--10、 9、 8... 5. In hot weather, the reverse happens. 在热天,情况相反。', '副词: reversely 名词: reverser 过去式: reversed 过去分词: reversed 现在分词: reversing 第三人称单数: reverses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pare', '[per]', 'v.削减；剥或削（某物）的皮；修剪（某物）边缘', '1. Our budget has been pared to the bone. 我们的预算已削减到最低限度。 2. We were asked to pare down our budget. 我们被要求削减预算。 3. She is paring the apple. 她正在削苹果皮。 4. She is paring her nails. 她正在修剪指甲。', '名词: parer 过去式: pared 过去分词: pared 现在分词: paring 第三人称单数: pares');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bode', '[boʊd]', 'v.预示；为……的兆头', '1. The bad trading figures do not bode well. 这些交易数额欠佳，预示公司前景不妙。 2. His careful habits bode well for his future. 他那认真的习惯预示著他会有好的前途。 3. That didn\'t bode well for the Lakers chances. 这对湖人来说并不是好兆头。 4. These figures do not bode well for the company\'s future. 这些数据对于公司的前景不是个好兆头。', '过去式: boded 过去分词: boded 现在分词: boding 第三人称单数: bodes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('traduce', '[trə\'duːs]', 'vt.诽谤；中伤', '1. It is not easy to traduce his character. 要中伤他的人格并非易事。', '副词: traducingly 名词: traducement 过去式: traduced 过去分词: traduced 现在分词: traducing 第三人称单数: traduces');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('correspondent', '[ˌkɔːrə\'spɑːndənt]', 'n.通讯记者；通信者 adj.与 ... 一致的；相应的', '1. The newspaper has a foreign correspondent. 这家报纸有个外国通讯记者。 2. A good correspondent does not procrastinate. 一位勤于写信的通信者不会拖延。 3. You know what a poor correspondent I am. 你知道我是一个多么懒于写信的人。 4. The result was correspondent with my wishes. 结果与我的愿望是一致的。', '副词: correspondently');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('trench', '[trentʃ]', 'n.沟；沟渠；战壕 v.挖沟；侵占', '1. The farmers gouged out a trench across the field. 农民们挖了一条穿过田野的沟。 2. They dig trench to keep the forest fire from spread. 他们挖沟以阻止森林大火蔓延。 3. I forgot to dig a trench around the tent. 我忘了在帐篷四周挖一条沟。 4. They toiled all day digging the trench. 他们整天艰苦地挖壕沟。 5. The troops received orders to trench the outpost. 部队接到命令在前哨周围筑壕加强防卫。', '过去式: trenched 过去分词: trenched 现在分词: trenching 第三人称单数: trenches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('frisk', '[frɪsk]', 'v.蹦跳；嬉戏；搜身 n.雀跃；欢欣鼓舞', '1. There are lambs frisking in the meadow. 那儿有些在草地上跳来跳去的小羊。 2. Are they going to frisk all the passengers? 他们要搜查每个乘客的身体吗? 3. Everyone was frisked before getting on the plane. 每个人都经过搜身才登上飞机。', '名词: frisker 过去式: frisked 过去分词: frisked 现在分词: frisking 第三人称单数: frisks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('jape', '[dʒeɪp]', 'v.戏言；笑料；嘲弄', '1. Even a schoolboy\'s jape is supposed to have some ascertainable point. 即使一个小男生的戏言也可能有一些真义。 2. He became the public jape in school, because he overreached when imitating others. 他因画虎类犬在学校成了众人的笑料。', '名词: japer 过去式: japed 过去分词: japed 现在分词: japing 第三人称单数: japes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('peer', '[pɪr]', 'n.同辈；同等的人；贵族 vi.凝视；窥视', '1. Children are easily influenced by their peers. 孩子很容易受同辈影响。 2. He was valued by both his peer and his superiors. 他的同级和上级都很器重他。 3. The opinions of his peers are more important to him than his parents\' ideas. 在他看来，他同辈人的观点比他父母的观点更为重要。 4. It will not be easy to find his peer. 很不容易找到像他那样的人. 5. She peers through the mist, trying to find the right path. 她透过雾眯着眼看，想找出正确的路。', '过去式: peered 过去分词: peered 现在分词: peering 第三人称单数: peers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('diffuse', '[dɪ\'fjuːz]', 'vt.扩散；散开；传播 vi.弥漫；扩散 adj.冗长的；四散的', '1. The problem is how to diffuse power without creating anarchy. 问题在于如何将权力分散而不造成无政府状态。 2. Fashion trends diffuse themselves rapidly around the globe. 时装新潮很快就在全世界流行起来。 3. The roses diffuse the scent to the air miles around. 玫瑰花的香味儿弥漫在几英里的空气中。 4. He resolved to diffuse the special knowledge that he possessed. 他决心要传播他所具有的特别的知识。 5. Around the cluster is a huge vague diffuse nebulae. 围绕该星团的是一个巨大的模糊的弥漫星云。 6. Professor Smith cut off their diffuse speech and agreed to help them. 史密斯教授打断他们冗长的演讲,答应帮助他们。', '副词: diffusely 名词: diffuseness 过去式: diffused 过去分词: diffused 现在分词: diffusing 第三人称单数: diffuses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('perspicacious', '[ˌpɜːrspɪ\'keɪʃəs]', 'adj.颖悟的；聪明的；有洞察力的', '1. It is very perspicacious of you to find the cause of the trouble so quickly. 你真是明察秋毫，问题的原因这麽快就找出来了。', '副词: perspicaciously 名词: perspicaciousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('polyglot', '[\'pɑːliɡlɑːt]', 'adj.通晓多种语言的；多种语言混合的 n.通数国语言的人；用数国语言记载的书', '1. Thanks to his polyglot aptitude, he made rapid progress. 由于他有学习语言的天才，他学习的进度很快。 2. He was a round old man with a guttural, polyglot accent. 他是一位肥胖的老人，讲话时带有多种语言混合的多喉音的声调。', '名词: polyglotism');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incertitude', '[ɪn\'sɜːtəˌtjuːd]', 'n.疑惑；不确定；无把握', '1. Chapter 2: we introduce the development of incertitude theory. 第二章：介绍不确定性理论的发展。 2. Process Entropy is a measurement for the incertitude degree of process. “流程熵”是反应流程不确定程度的量度。 3. The evidence theory and fuzzy integral can abate the incertitude and improve the accuracy of decision. 证据理论和模糊积分融合方法可以减少决策过程中的不确定性，大大的提高了决策的精度。 4. Crisis control with crisis as the object is characterized by incertitude, urgency and preventiveness. 危机管理的对象是危机,它具有不确定性、应急性和预防性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('quaint', '[kweɪnt]', 'adj.离奇有趣的；古色古香的；古怪的', '1. Old photographs seem quaint to us today. 旧照片现在就我们来看来似乎古怪有趣。 2. The meadow and brook are quaint. 草地和小河很有趣。 3. Grandma lives in a quaint old cottage. 奶奶住在一栋古色古香的乡间别墅里。 4. Our neighbor is a quaint old lady. 我们的邻居是位古怪的老太太。', '副词: quaintly 比较级: quainter 最高级: quaintest 名词: quaintness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inroad', '[\'ɪnroʊd]', 'n.侵袭；消耗某物；进展', '1. Hospital bills had made deep inroads into her savings. 住院的花销用去她一大笔积蓄。 2. Already the children had made considerable inroads on the food. 孩子们早已吃掉不少食物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unprepossessing', '[ˌʌnˌpriːpə\'zesɪŋ]', 'adj.（外表）不吸引人的', '1. Though unprepossessing to look at, he is highly intelligent. 他虽然相貌平平，但却很有才气。', '副词: unprepossessingly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('low', '[loʊ]', 'adj.低的；少的；低落的；低声的；卑劣的；低等的 adv.低地；低声地；低下地；廉价地 n.低水平；低价；低谷 v.哞哞叫', '1. The price they quoted was very low. 他们报的价很低。 2. Shadows are longer when the sun is low in the sky. 太阳很低时，物体的影子就很长。 3. We must reorder these items because stock gets low. 我们必须再订购这些物品,因为库存越来越少了。 4. He\'d play the violin when he was in low spirits. 他情绪低落的时候就拉小提琴。 5. The sun hung low over the misted valley. 太阳低悬在薄雾笼罩的山谷之上。 6. The value of the pound has fallen to a new low against the dollar. 英镑兑换美元的比值已经跌倒新的低点。', '比较级: lower 最高级: lowest 名词: lowness 过去式: lowed 过去分词: lowed 现在分词: lowing 第三人称单数: lows');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('maverick', '[\'mævərɪk]', 'n.未打烙印的小牛；持不同意见者 adj.标新立异的', '1. Politically, she\'s a bit of a maverick. 在政治方面，她有点自行其是。 2. The Republican maverick was disliked and distrusted by too many in the party. 而在共和党内部，有太多人对这位特立独行者抱以嫌恶和不信任的态度。 3. Robby was a maverick vice cop, never doing things in legal way. 华比是个特立独行的黑警察，从不以正当手段行事。 4. The maverick Republican has been facing some harsh rhetoric from the far-right. 这个独来独往的共和党人一直面临一些来自党内极右势力的严辞批判。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('champ', '[tʃæmp]', 'v.大声地嚼；迫不及待 n.冠军(=champion)', '1. The horse is champing his hay. 马在大声咀嚼干草。 2. The boys were champing to start. 男孩儿们恨不得马上就出发。 3. He was champing with rage at the delay. 他对这一延误着急上火。 4. He was beat to a pulp by the reigning champ. 他被现任冠军打得死去活来。', '过去式: champed 过去分词: champed 现在分词: champing 第三人称单数: champs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('erase', '[ɪ\'reɪs]', 'v.抹去；擦掉；[计算机]擦除', '1. She couldn\'t erase the incident from her memory. 她难以忘记那次事件。 2. I did my best to erase the event from my memory. 我尽全力从记忆中抹去这件事。 3. There is no way to erase what I have done. I am sorry. 我所做的事已是无法抹去了。我很抱歉。 4. You can erase pencil marks with a rubber. 你可以用橡皮擦掉铅笔记号。', '形容词: erasable 名词: erasability 过去式: erased 过去分词: erased 现在分词: erasing 第三人称单数: erases');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('contemplate', '[\'kɑːntəmpleɪt]', 'vt.注视；沉思；打算', '1. He stood contemplating the painting. 他站着审视那幅图画。 2. It terrified me to contemplate the consequence of your action. 一想到你行动的后果,我就感到害怕。 3. The doctor contemplated the difficult operation he had to perform. 医生细想他要进行的棘手的手术。 4. We contemplate obtaining a technical license. 我们希望获得一项技术许可证。', '名词: contemplator 过去式: contemplated 过去分词: contemplated 现在分词: contemplating 第三人称单数: contemplates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('apron', '[\'eɪprən]', 'n.围裙；停机坪；台口；遮挡板', '1. My apron is so dirty that I have to wash it. 我的围裙太脏了，我不得不洗它。 2. She tied an apron around her waist. 她将围裙系在腰间。 3. She made up the remaining cloth into an apron. 她把余下来的布缝成一条围裙。 4. A fighter plane is revving up on the hanger apron. 飞机库前面停机坪上，一架战斗机正在起动。', '过去式: aproned 过去分词: aproned 现在分词: aproning 第三人称单数: aprons');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('captivate', '[\'kæptɪveɪt]', 'vt.迷住；迷惑', '1. He was captivated by her beauty. 他被她的美色迷住了。 2. The kindergarten children were captivated by the variety of animals in the zoo. 幼儿园的孩子们被动物园里的各种动物吸引住了。 3. The son is so captivate with the woman that he does not heed his parents\' warning. 儿子为这个女人神魂颠倒，全然不顾他父母的告诫。', '名词: captivation 过去式: captivated 过去分词: captivated 现在分词: captivating 第三人称单数: captivates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mediocre', '[ˌmiːdi\'oʊkər]', 'adj.平庸的；平凡的', '1. This leads to mediocre training, fitness, and performance. 这将导致平庸的训练，体能和成绩。 2. Calico Rackham Jack had mediocre accomplishments as a pirate. 卡利科拉克姆杰克平庸的成绩已成为海盗。 3. That foursome alone should make Arizona very competitive in the mediocre National League West. 这个四人组合将会让亚利桑纳在平凡的国家联盟西区非常具有竞争力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wistful', '[\'wɪstfl]', 'adj.渴望的；忧思的；留恋的', '1. The boy looks with wistful eyes at the toy on display. 那男孩看著展出的玩具，眼中流露出渴望的神情。 2. The poor mother has wistful reminiscences of her lost youth. 这个贫穷的母亲怅惘地回忆她已经逝去的青春。 3. His sole reference to Watergate was wistful. 他对水门事件的唯一反应就是陷入沉思。 4. She had a last wistful look at the house. 她留恋地最后朝那房子看了一眼。', '副词: wistfully 名词: wistfulness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('opponent', '[ə\'poʊnənt]', 'n.对手；反对者；敌手 adj.反对的；敌对的', '1. He was assailed by his political opponent. 他遭到政敌的攻击。 2. I tried to comfort him after he was defeated by his opponent. 他被对手击败后，我尽力安慰他。 3. He knocked down his opponent with a powerful left. 他一记有力的左手拳将对手击倒。 4. He is slashing wildly at his opponent with a sword. 他正用剑疯狂地朝对手乱砍。 5. The company, which had long been an opponent of electrification, changed its stance earlier this year in light of slipping global sales. 该公司长期以来一直反对的电气化，改变了其立场，在今年早些时候，鉴于全球销售下滑。', '名词: opponency');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('defiance', '[dɪ\'faɪəns]', 'n.蔑视；违抗；挑衅', '1. His defiance of the law cost him dearly. 蔑视法律使他付出沈重的代价。 2. Those who bid defiance to the law will get into trouble. 蔑视法律者终要倒霉。 3. They went in defiance of the order. 他们违抗命令还是去了。 4. He had been deposed because of his defiance of Roman law. 亚那因为违抗罗马的法律而被罢免。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('prevision', '[priː\'vɪʒən]', 'n.先见；预感', '1. It would be a first as there are no prevision in the UEFA rules. 这将是第一例此类事件，因为此前欧足联从未有过先例规则。 2. Some prevision warned the explorer of trouble. 某种预感警告探险者将有麻烦发生。', '形容词: previsional 过去式: previsioned 过去分词: previsioned 现在分词: previsioning 第三人称单数: previsions');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('impediment', '[ɪm\'pedɪmənt]', 'n.障碍；阻碍；口吃', '1. The main impediment to growth is a lack of capital. 影响发展的主要障碍是缺乏资本。 2. No impediment could shake my determination. 任何障碍都不能动摇我的决心。 3. War is one of the greatest impediments to human progress. 战争是人类进步的最大阻碍之一。 4. By much pains, the orator overcame a natural impediment in his speech. 这位演说家用苦练的方法克服了天生的口吃毛病。', '形容词: impedimental');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gear', '[ɡɪr]', 'n.传动装置；齿轮；排挡；工具；装备 v.调整；使适应于；以齿轮连起', '1. Careless use of the clutch may damage the gears. 离合器使用不慎可能损坏传动装置。 2. The gear just would not come unstuck. 齿轮就是松不开来。 3. The car has four forward gear and one reverse gear. 那汽车有四个前进挡和一个倒挡。 4. Lifting electromagnet is a kind of lifting gear. 起重电磁铁是起重工具的一种。 5. Education should be geared to the children\'s needs and abilities. 教育应适应儿童的需要和能力。', '过去式: geared 过去分词: geared 现在分词: gearing 第三人称单数: gears');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('molten', '[\'moʊltən]', 'adj.熔化的；炽热的；铸造的 melt的过去分词.', '1. The molten metal was run into a mould. 熔化的金属被倒进模内。 2. The rising sun danced in water like molten gold. 初升的太阳犹如熔化的金子在水中荡漾。 3. Deep inside the Earth are very hot molten rocks called lava. 地球内部深处是十分炽热的岩浆的岩石熔化物。 4. As the plates separate, hot molten mantle material flows up to fill the void. 随着板块的分开，炽热的熔融地幔物质向上流动，以填充空隙。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('malfunction', '[ˌmæl\'fʌŋkʃn]', 'n.故障；失灵 v.发生故障；不起作用', '1. The pilot was forced to bail out due to technical malfunction. 由于技术故障飞行员被迫跳伞。 2. Every compartment had some minor breakage or malfunction to report. 每间舱房总有些小毛病或机件失灵的事故上报。 3. Practice shows us that traditional tools work, especially considering that financial engineering can malfunction. 实践表明，传统的手段往往奏效，尤其是考虑到金融工程学有可能失灵。 4. The computer malfunctioned and printed out the wrong data. 这个计算机出了故障,打印出错误的资料。', '过去式: malfunctioned 过去分词: malfunctioned 现在分词: malfunctioning 第三人称单数: malfunctions');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('retract', '[rɪ\'trækt]', 'v.缩回；收回；撤销', '1. The undercarriage on light aircraft does not always retract in flight. 轻型飞机飞行时起落架不一定缩回。 2. I decided to retract what I had said before. 我决定收回前面说过的话。 3. Sir Alex has added his backing and believes Franco should retract his comments. 弗格森爵士支持自己的助理，并且强调里斯本竞技俱乐部主席应该收回自己的控诉。 4. The accused refused to retract his statement. 那被告拒不撤销其供述。', '形容词: retractable 名词: retractability 过去式: retracted 过去分词: retracted 现在分词: retracting 第三人称单数: retracts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lukewarm', '[ˌluːk\'wɔːrm]', 'adj.微温的；不热情的', '1. Can you give a cup of lukewarm water? 你可以帮我倒杯温水吗? 2. Our enjoyment seemed rather lukewarm. 我们的欣赏热情似乎不高。 3. He gave only lukewarm support to our plan. 他只是半心半意地支持我们的计划。', '副词: lukewarmly 名词: lukewarmness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('grief', '[ɡriːf]', 'n.悲痛；忧伤', '1. She uttered a wail of grief. 她悲痛地大声尖叫。 2. She was prostrate with grief. 她因悲痛而一蹶不振。 3. The poor woman was buried in grief after her son died. 这个可怜的妇人在儿子死后一直沉浸在悲痛之中。 4. No words can express my grief. 我的忧伤无法用语言表达。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('logistics', '[lə\'dʒɪstɪks]', 'n.物流；后勤学；运筹学', '1. I wish to make logistics my lifetime career. 我愿把物流作为我的终生事业。 2. Logistics is unique, and it never stops! 物流是独特的，它从不停止。 3. Logistics is a branch of military science. 后勤是军事科学的一个分支。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('earthy', '[\'ɜːrθi]', 'adj.泥土的；粗俗的；朴实的；世俗的', '1. The houses in the village are mostly earthy. 村里的房子多数是用泥土打造的。 2. The air is full of an earthy smell after the rain. 雨后的空气里弥漫着一种土腥味。 3. He often has got a earthy sense of humour. 他常常有粗俗的幽默感。 4. Michael has an earthy sense of humour; he likes rude jokes. 迈克尔有一种粗俗的幽默感，他喜欢讲粗俗的笑话。', '副词: earthily 比较级: earthier 最高级: earthiest 名词: earthiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('odoriferous', '[ˌoʊdə\'rɪfərəs]', 'adj.有香味的；芳香的；臭的；令人反感的', '1. Now new research is beginning to unlock the secrets of the odoriferous bulb. 而现在，一项新的研究即将揭开这种散发着臭味的球茎的秘密。 2. Bouquet. Odoriferous quality of a wine, particularly the odour of fine wines acquired during aging. 陈香、酒香：葡萄酒的香气质量，尤其指高档葡萄酒在陈酿过程中所获得的香气。 3. Pharmaceutical taste. Unpleasant taste sometimes acquired by wines sotred near odoriferous chemicals. 药味：当葡萄贮藏在有味的化学物质附近时，有时会带上的一种令人不快的杂味。 4. There are a great number of Odoriferous fountains in Liupanshan Mountain area,south Ningxia. 六盘山地区多处有臭水泉群出露。', '副词: odoriferously 名词: odoriferousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('prospect', '[\'prɑːspekt]', 'n.希望；前景；景色 v.勘探；寻找', '1. A rich harvest is in prospect. 丰收在望。 2. I see little prospect of an improvement in his condition. 我看他的情况没有什么改进的希望。 3. What do you think about the marketing prospect? 你觉得市场前景怎么样? 4. The prospect from the balcony was breathtaking. 从阳台上看去景色美极了。 5. They went there to prospect for gold . 他们去那儿勘探金矿。', '过去式: prospected 过去分词: prospected 现在分词: prospecting 第三人称单数: prospects');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('slur', '[slɜːr]', 'n.诽谤；耻辱；污点；污迹 n.[音]连音符 v.诋毁；中伤；草率地看过；忽略；含糊地念；印刷模糊', '1. That was an awful slur, but it wasn\'t really surprising. 这是无耻的诽谤，但是实际上也不足为奇。 2. I will not easily forgive her for putting that slur on me in public. 我会宽恕她公然诽谤我。 3. The slur is to tell the singer to sing the two notes coherently. 连音符号是为了告诉演唱者前后两个音符是要连贯唱出的。 4. In modern notation it would be marked with horizontal dashes under a slur. 现代记号法中，在连音符号下将会标记出水平破折号。 5. She had dared to cast a slur on his character. 她竟敢对他的人品加以诋毁。', '过去式: slurred 过去分词: slurred 现在分词: slurring 第三人称单数: slurs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('estranged', '[ɪ\'streɪndʒd]', 'adj.疏远的；隔离的 动词estrange的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. His mother had been born in the country, on a farm, and felt involved with the land but estranged from its people. 她母亲生在农村的一个农庄里，对这里的土地很有感情，但和这里的人是疏远的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('consequential', '[ˌkɒnsə\'kwenʃəl]', 'adj.重要的；间接的；随之发生的；自高自大的', '1. Rarely has the world faced a choice more clear or consequential. 这个世界面临如此清晰而重大的选择是很少有的。 2. The report discusses a number of consequential matters that are yet to be decided. 这份报告讨论了许多有待决定的重大问题。 3. We shall not be liable for incidental or consequential damages. 本公司对附带损坏或间接损坏不负任何责任。 4. She was injured and suffered a consequential loss of earnings. 她受了伤因而收入受损。', '副词: consequentially 名词: consequentiality');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('impartial', '[ɪm\'pɑːrʃl]', 'adj.公正的；不偏不倚的', '1. He was not an impartial witness because of his affinity with the accused. 他不是公正的见证人，因为他与被告有姻亲关系。 2. He is an impartial judge. 他是一位公正的法官。 3. People in the city held the impartial judge in high regard. 这个城市的人们都很尊敬这位公正的法官。 4. An impartial judge can settle our argument. 公正的仲裁人能解决我们的争端。', '副词: impartially 名词: impartiality');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('posit', '[\'pɑːzɪt]', 'v.假定 v.安置', '1. Most religions posit the existence of life after death. 大多数宗教都假定人死后生命仍存在。', '过去式: posited 过去分词: posited 现在分词: positing 第三人称单数: posits');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('repugnant', '[rɪ\'pʌɡnənt]', 'adj.令人厌恶的；讨厌的；抵触的', '1. I find his racist views totally repugnant. 我十分厌恶他的种族主义观点。 2. All food was repugnant to me during my illness. 我生病时吃什么都恶心。 3. It is repugnant to me even to speak to him. 我甚至连和他说话都感到讨厌。 4. Some people eat foods that are repugnant to others. 某些人讨厌的食物,有些人却爱吃。', '副词: repugnantly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scud', '[skʌd]', 'n.疾驶；飞云或雾；阵雨；阵风 v.疾行；掠过', '1. Clouds scud past still unhurried! 乱云飞渡仍从容! 2. The scud had banked over the moon, and it was now quite dark. 飘飞的雾，蒙住月亮，夜色幽暗。 3. The yacht was scudding along before the wind. 那只帆船正乘风笔直疾驶。 4. You could lie on your back watching clouds scud across the sky, and maybe later walk down to the store for a Popsicle. 你可以躺下来看天空的云卷云舒,或是去商店买一根冰棍。', '过去式: scudded 过去分词: scudded 现在分词: scudding 第三人称单数: scuds');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('grandeur', '[\'ɡrændʒər]', 'n.庄严；伟大；宏伟；壮观', '1. The place has a gracious air of faded grandeur. 这个地方有一种庄严褪去之后的神圣之感。 2. This poem praises the grandeur of the Yellow River. 这首诗歌颂了黄河的伟大气魄。 3. He has delusions of grandeur. 他自以为很了不起。 4. She wants to travel first-class: she must have delusions of grandeur. 她想坐头等舱旅行，她一定自以为很了不起。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tractable', '[\'træktəbl]', 'adj.（正式）易驾驭的', '1. Gold and silver are tractable metals. 金和银是容易加工的金属。 2. Stener had always been very tractable. 斯坦纳总是容易对付的。 3. They are mighty sagacious, tractable creature. 它们都是十分伶俐，十分容易驾驭的动物。', '副词: tractably 名词: tractability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('temptation', '[temp\'teɪʃn]', 'n.诱惑；引诱物', '1. I can\'t resist the temptation. 我不能抵挡诱惑。 2. She yielded to temptation and had another chocolate. 她禁不住诱惑，又吃了一块巧克力。 3. She fell an easy victim to his temptation. 她经不起他的诱惑，轻易地被骗了。 4. An expensive bicycle is a temptation to thieves. 高档自行车对窃贼是个诱惑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unflappable', '[ˌʌn\'flæpəbl]', 'adj.镇定自若的；临危不乱的', '1. A busy manager needs a completely unflappable secretary. 经理工作忙就需要一个头脑十分冷静的秘书。', '副词: unflappably 名词: unflappability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('elysian', '[ɪ\'liːʒən]', 'adj.快乐的；福地的；极乐的', '1. She\'s holed up in the Elysian Fields Projects. 她是伊甸园计划的一部分。 2. It is demon region, elysian still? 是魔域，还是乐土？ 3. She’s holed upin the Elysian Fields Projects. 她是伊甸园计划的一部分。Elysian.;天堂的。 4. Silicon Valley is company year great dream all the time is Elysian. 硅谷一直是企业春秋大梦的乐土。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cloister', '[\'klɔɪstər]', 'n.修道院；寺庙；回廊；隐居地 v.远离尘世；隐居；用环廊环绕', '1. The nuns live in a cloister of calm. 修女们住在一个幽静的修道院里。 2. He coiled around the moist cloister pillars. 他环抱着回廊那潮湿的柱子。', '过去式: cloistered 过去分词: cloistered 现在分词: cloistering 第三人称单数: cloisters');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('premature', '[ˌpriːmə\'tʃʊr]', 'adj.提前的；过早的；早产的 n.早产儿；早熟', '1. A fire caused the premature closing of the exhibition. 火灾迫使展览会提前结束。 2. This disease produces premature aging of the brain. 这种疾病使大脑过早衰老。 3. The role of the filler is to prevent premature release of CO2. 该填充料的作用是防止过早的释放出二氧化碳。 4. The baby was five weeks premature. 这个孩子是提早五周生下来的。 5. Prompt action saves premature baby 职员反应迅速保早产儿平安', '副词: prematurely 名词: prematureness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('overture', '[\'oʊvərtʃər]', 'n.提议；提案；主动表示；序曲 v.提议；建议', '1. And, knowing little about Geely, it didn\'t take the overture seriously, according to people familiar with the situation. 据知情人士透露，由于对吉利知之甚少，福特汽车没有认真对待这一提议。 2. He resolved, therefore, to let things take their course without making any direct overture to the count. 所以他决定让事情顺其自然发展，而不向伯爵作任何正面的提议。 3. Many spokesmen attacked consumingly this overture. 大会上许多的发言人强烈抨击了这项提案。 4. Three-fours of the people agree with the overture presently. 目前有四分之三的人赞成该提案。 5. And, knowing little about Geely, it didn\'t take the overture seriously, according to people familiar with the situation. 据知情人士透露，由于对吉利知之甚少，福特汽车没有认真对待这一提议。', '过去式: overtured 过去分词: overtured 现在分词: overturing 第三人称单数: overtures');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('underrate', '[ˌʌndə\'reɪt]', 'v.低估；看轻', '1. I don\'t underrate the decorative side of life. 我并不低估生活中起装饰作用的东西的价值。 2. I fear that I underrate the difficulty of the task. 我担心我低估了这项任务的困难。 3. Han Jia, you\'d better not underrate me. 韩佳,你可别瞧不起我。 4. Never underrate your rival\'s strength. 低估。任何时候都不要低估对手的实力。', '过去式: underrated 过去分词: underrated 现在分词: underrating 第三人称单数: underrates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('judiciousness', '[dʒʊ(ː)\'dɪʃəsnɪs]', 'n.明智', '1. He offers little in the way of red-meat rhetoric to his audiences, some of whom are surprised, and disappointed, by his persistent judiciousness. 对于以激烈言辞挑起听众情绪的修辞，他采用的很少；他的带着固执的贤明让有一些人感到惊讶，因而失望。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('canon', '[\'kænən]', 'n.教规；标准；准则；真经；真作；（公认的）作家或音乐家；大教堂教士；轮唱曲 n.Canon: 佳能（相机品牌）', '1. A person specializing in canon law is respectable. 对教规有专门研究的人很值得尊敬。 2. This canon has been enacted by the church council very recently. 这项规定最近刚刚由教堂理事会颁布。 3. His behavior is against social canon. 他的行为不符合社会规范。 4. His behavior offends the canons of good manners. 他的行为冒犯了公认的礼貌规范。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gauge', '[ɡeɪdʒ]', 'n.测量仪器；测量标准；（铁道的）轨距；（钢丝等的）直径；（枪管的）口径 v.估计；判断；测量', '1. The fuel gauges dropped swiftly. 燃料表指针迅速下降。 2. What gauge of wire should we use for this job? 我们干这活应该用多大号的铅丝? 3. This is a narrow-gauge railway. 这是一条窄轨铁路。 4. We must gauge the diameter of wire first. 我们必须先测量电线的直径。 5. It was difficult to gauge how people would respond. 大家的反应如何难以估计。', '形容词: gaugeable 过去式: gauged/gaged 过去分词: gauged/gaged 现在分词: gauging/gaging 第三人称单数: gauges/gages');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('eminence', '[\'emɪnəns]', 'n.显赫；崇高；高处', '1. He is a statesman of great eminence. 他是个声名显赫的政治家。 2. A leader\'s eminence does not imply a right to impose his will on his peers. 领导人处于显赫地位并不意味着他有权把自己的意志强加给和他处于平等地位的公民。 3. Authors of the highest eminence seem to be fully satisfied with the view that each species has been independently created. 地位最崇高的作者们似乎完全满足于一种看法，即认为每种动物都是单独创造的。 4. There were rumors that the new emperor resented her influence and her claims of eminence. 有传言说新皇帝对于利维娅无所不在的影响和崇高的声望甚为不满。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pigment', '[\'pɪɡmənt]', 'n. 色素； 颜料 v. 把 ... 加颜色； 变色', '1. This pigment is a good common food additive. 该色素是稳定性好的食品添加剂。 2. How is retinal pigment denaturation treated? 视网膜色素变性怎样治疗？ 3. The primary white pigment is titanium dioxide. 最重要的白色颜料是二氧化钛。 4. Of course, pigment is not the only part of a fresco. 当然，颜料还不是画面的全部。 5. You just expand or shrink the millions of pigment cells or chromatophores in your skin to instantly change color. 你只需要展开或收缩你皮肤里的上百万个色素细胞或色素体就可以立即变色。', '形容词: pigmentary 过去式: pigmented 过去分词: pigmented 现在分词: pigmenting 第三人称单数: pigments');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('interlope', '[ˌɪntə\'loʊp]', 'vi.(为图私利)干涉他人之事；闯入', '1. Engage in unlicensed business operation;do business without a license;interlope 无证经营', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('implant', '[\'ɪmplænt]', 'v.深植；灌输；嵌入；移植 n.移植物；植入物', '1. Teachers implant sound principles in the mind of children. 老师把健全的原则灌输在儿童心中。 2. You need to have a spontaneous education, or implant, put into your body to teach you. 你们需要有一个自然发生的教导，或者灌输，进入你们身体来教导你们。 3. Conclusion Favites implant inlay after horizontal osteotomy is one of the ideal methods for microgenia. 结论水平截骨后采用天然角蜂巢珊瑚石人工骨嵌入植骨是矫正小颏畸形的可取方法之一。 4. Surgeons implant blood essel grafts to proide an alternate route to damaged or blocked essels. 外科移植血管可为受伤或阻滞的血管提供另一个途径。', '形容词: implantable 过去式: implanted 过去分词: implanted 现在分词: implanting 第三人称单数: implants');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('freelancer', '[\'friːlænsər]', 'n.自由职业者', '1. Working with a specific niche can make a lot of sense for a freelancer. 对一个自由职业者来说，在某个特定小众领域内发挥自己的专长是比较靠谱的选择。 2. When you\'re overworked at the office, your employer may allow you to subcontract one or two projects to a freelancer. 当你在办公室工作太久的时候，你的雇主会允许你转一两个项目给自由职业者做的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cloudburst', '[\'klaʊdbɜːrst]', 'n.倾盆大雨；暴雨', '1. The bus was delayed by a cloudburst. 由于大暴雨，公共汽车来迟了。 2. Today, there was a 10-minute cloudburst. 今天，有个十分钟的大暴雨。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bricklayer', '[\'brɪkleɪər]', 'n.砖匠', '1. The foreman took on ten more men as bricklayers. 工头又雇佣了十多个人作泥瓦匠。 2. The boy was apprenticed to a bricklayer. 那男孩子被送给一个泥瓦匠当学徒。', '名词: bricklaying');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('band', '[bænd]', 'n.乐队；队；一群 n.带；箍；波段 v.绑扎 v.联合；结合', '1. The band played a lively tune. 乐队演奏了一支轻快的乐曲。 2. The brass band is banging away in the park. 铜管乐队在公园里吹吹打打。 3. They are a teenager band made up of four cool boys. 他们是一支由四名酷哥组成的少年演唱队。 4. A band of robbers held up the train. 一群强盗抢劫了火车。 5. She used a rubber band to tie her hair. 她用一根橡皮筋扎头发。 6. If you band the bird\'s leg, you can identify it later. 如果你在鸟腿上套上标记环,以後就能认出它。 7. The children banded together to buy a present for their teacher. 孩子们合起来为他们的老师买了一件礼物。', '过去式: banded 过去分词: banded 现在分词: banding 第三人称单数: bands');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mime', '[maɪm]', 'n.哑剧；丑角；模仿 vt.做哑剧表演；模仿 vi.演出哑剧角色', '1. They will perform a short mime later. 待会他们将表演一出短的哑剧。 2. I couldn\'t speak Chinese, but I showed in mime that I wanted a drink. 我不会讲汉语，但我作摹拟动作表示要一杯饮料。 3. He mimed the part of a drunken man. 他以哑剧形式表演醉汉。 4. Ask a child to come to the front and pick a card and mime the action. 叫一个学生到教室前边来，拿一张卡片并模仿卡片上要求的动作。', '名词: mimer 过去式: mimed 过去分词: mimed 现在分词: miming 第三人称单数: mimes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pragmatic', '[præɡ\'mætɪk]', 'adj.实用主义的；实际的', '1. The American people are pragmatic by nature. 美国人的性格是注重实际。 2. They\'re pragmatic about the spending cuts. 他们在削减开支方面很务实。 3. We need to adopt a more pragmatic approach. 我们需要采用一种更为实际的方法。 4. Now what we need is pragmatic action but none of your empty talk. 我们现在要实际的行动,不能光说大话,放空炮。', '形容词: pragmatical 副词: pragmatically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('headstrong', '[\'hedstrɔːŋ]', 'adj.顽固的；刚愎的；任性的', '1. Mrs. Ferrars is a very headstrong, proud woman. 费拉尔斯太太是个非常顽固、傲慢的妇人。 2. The headstrong impetuous man rushed into things without forethought. 这个顽固的莽汉，不预先考虑，仓促行事。 3. She\'s hopelessly headstrong; she always gets up against people in authority. 她刚愎自用到了不可挽救的地步，老是与主管人员发生冲突。 4. We cannot tolerate his headstrong actions. 我们不能容忍他的任性行为。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('privation', '[praɪ\'veɪʃn]', 'n.贫困；匮乏；丧失', '1. They endured years of suffering and privation. 他们饱受多年的煎熬与贫困。 2. Cold is the privation of heat. 所谓冷就是缺乏热量。 3. His death was a great privation to his colleagues. 他的死对他的同事们来说是一个巨大的损失。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ecdysis', '[\'ekdɪsɪs]', 'n.(动物)蜕皮；换羽毛', '1. Recovery will be achieved after ecdysis. 世界任何中、西医研究治疗，只能把病毒溶解在血液中循环，所以要求患者禁止吃腥、辣等有刺激性食物。 2. Venom is discharged and ecdysis will appear from the focus 30 minutes after applying the drug. 皮肤病属真菌病毒，是生命力极强的生命体。 3. The process of toads ecdysis was reported,and the significance of environmental protection and the commercialization of bufonic was discussed. 报道了中华大蟾蜍自然蜕皮（蟾蜍衣）的过程，并讨论了蟾蜍衣商品化的经济意义和环保意义。 4. In the period of nymph stage and ecdysis peak, the control effects was better but it need highly professional technique and not suitable for guiding farmer to control the midges. 在吸浆虫蛹期、羽化高峰期防治虽能获得较好的防治效果，但需要专业技术人员掌握发育进度，不适合指导群防群治；', '名词复数: ecdyses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('embankment', '[ɪm\'bæŋkmənt]', 'n.堤防；筑堤', '1. The river flowed the embankment. 河水已溢出了堤岸。 2. The van slipped (a few feet) down the embankment. 那客货车沿堤坝向下滑动了（几英尺）。 3. An embankment was raised to prevent a river from overflowing. 堤岸是为了防止河流泛滥而建造的。 4. We should reinforce the river embankment before the wet season. 雨季前夕，我们要加固河坝。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dotage', '[\'doʊtɪdʒ]', 'n.老耄；老迷糊；溺爱', '1. We have to look after grandfather now he\'s in his dotage. 祖父已经年迈昏愦，我们必须照顾他。 2. He has dotage because of old age. 他因年老而糊里糊涂。 3. Merlin fell in a dotage on the damsel. 墨林深深地爱上那少女。 4. Dotage is not the real love and favour is not protection. 溺爱不是真爱，偏袒不是保护。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pediatrics', '[ˌpiːdi\'ætrɪks]', 'n.[医]小儿科 =paediatrics(英）.', '1. But the American Academy of Pediatrics has a warning about such advice. 但是小儿科的美国人学院有一警告大约如此的忠告。 2. And now a new study in Pediatrics shows that the shoes are particularly dangerous for beginners and girls. 并且现在一项小儿科的最新研究显示滑轮鞋为初学者和女孩带来了显著的威胁。', '形容词: pediatric');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('surplus', '[\'sɜːrpləs]', 'n.过剩；顺差；盈余 adj.过剩的；多余的', '1. Mexico has a large surplus of oil. 墨西哥有大量过剩的石油。 2. Countries with surplus are called creditor nations. 有顺差的国家则称为债权国。 3. Surpluses of food can be sold for cash. 多余的食物可卖钱。 4. Every country has a lot of surplus labor. 每个国家都有大量的剩余劳动力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('canny', '[\'kæni]', 'adj.精明的；谨慎的；节俭的；狡诈的 adv.<苏格兰>仔细地', '1. The canny old lady knew that the book is too expensive. 那精明的老太太知道那本书太贵了。 2. His a canny merchant who knows where his benefit is. 他是一个精明的商人，深知自己的利益所在。 3. Though his tone was respectful, sometimes obsequious, he was also canny. 尽管语气中颇有敬意，有时候甚至逢迎，但他很谨慎。 4. Johnson was plainly a canny individual. 约翰逊显然是个狡猾的人物。', '副词: cannily 比较级: cannier 最高级: canniest 名词: canniness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lassitude', '[\'læsɪtuːd]', 'n.无力；没精打采；疲倦', '1. A deadly lassitude has taken hold of him. 他全身酸软无力。 2. Sometimes we feel lassitude on a hot summer day. 我们在炎热的夏日有时感到没精打采。 3. With all my lassitude I have strength enough to see it out. 尽管我那么困倦,我还是有足够看到结果的力气。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('angular', '[\'æŋɡjələr]', 'adj.有角的；消瘦的；有尖角的', '1. A radio receiver and directional antenna used as a system to determine the angular direction of incoming radio signals. 无线方向探测器一种无线电接收和指向天线系统，用来确定收到的无线电信号的角方向 2. Angular forms, outlines, or corners. 角形角形，角的轮廓或棱角 3. An angular face. 瘦削的脸庞 4. Angular distance is the distance between two objects measured as an angle from a given point. 角距离，是由一定点到两物体之间所量度的夹角。', '副词: angularly 名词: angularness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('covert', '[\'koʊvɜːrt]', 'adj.隐蔽的；偷偷摸摸的；隐密的 n.掩蔽物；树丛；覆羽', '1. Some people say this was a covert scheme. 有人说，这是阴谋。 2. I was only doing my job as a covert agent. 作为一个隐蔽的代理人 3. He stole a covert glance at her across the table. 他朝桌子对面偷偷地瞥了她一眼。 4. Every measure, both overt and covert, is being taken against terrorists. 每一种方法，公开的和隐密的，都用来对付敌人。 5. The brush provided a covert for game. 那块灌木丛为游戏提供了掩蔽物。', '副词: covertly 名词: covertness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reticulation', '[rɪˌtɪkjə\'leɪʃən]', 'n.网目；网状（物）', '1. A new type solid reticulation positive grid was studied. 介绍了一种新型立体网状正极板栅。 2. There is mild septal thickening and reticulation in the posterior subpleural region on the right.This is unassociated with adjacent pleural thickening. 右侧胸膜下可见轻度间隔增厚及网状改变，和胸膜增厚部位相隔较远。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('determination', '[dɪˌtɜːrmɪ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.决心；测定；规定；(正式)决定；定位', '1. He was utterly ruthless in his determination to succeed. 他下定决心争取成功。 2. Our sales people need determination and drive. 我们的推销人员需要有决心和干劲。 3. The determination of the amount of iron in ore is very important. 矿石中铁含量的测定是很主要的。 4. The determination will aversely affect the outcome of the game. 这个规定将逆转比赛结果。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ratification', '[ˌrætɪfɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.批准；认可', '1. The present treaty shall come into force immediately after its ratification. 本条约在批准后将立即生效。 2. The new arrangement will take effect after the completion of ratification procedures for both sides. 新安排在双方各自完成必要的批准程序后生效。 3. If the contract involves matters on commission, such stipulation shall have no force and effect without the ratification given by the commissioning authority. 契约内容涉及委办事项者，并应经委办机关之认可，始生效力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fillet', '[fɪ\'leɪ]', 'n.鱼片或肉片；束发带 vt.（用发带）装饰；切片', '1. A narrow border, molding, or fillet. 扁带饰窄条，装饰用嵌线或窄带 2. A bony fillet of fish. 一块多骨的鱼片 3. Will you fillet it for me please? 请给我把鱼骨头剔掉好吗？ 4. He put a fillet steak in the bun. 他把一片无骨牛排放进小圆面包里。', '过去式: filleted 过去分词: filleted 现在分词: filleting 第三人称单数: fillets');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('memorandum', '[ˌmemə\'rændəm]', 'n.【商】备忘录；【法】交易备忘录；契约书', '1. It seems quite easy to write a memorandum. 看来写备忘录也很容易。 2. Let\'s give this memorandum the once-over. 让我们大略地看一下备忘录。 3. He sent us a memorandum about the meeting. 他给我们寄来了会议备忘录。 4. He noted down the date of the meeting in the memorandum book. 他把会议日期记到备忘录里。', '名词复数: memorandums');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('literate', '[\'lɪtərət]', 'n.识字的人；受过教育的人；博学的人 adj.有读写能力的；博学的；优美的；精通文学的', '1. Though nearly twenty he was barely literate. 他都快二十了，还是睁眼瞎子。 2. The old man has to ask a literate to read the letter his son write him. 这位老人得找个能识字的人来读儿子来的信。 3. Every literate person should read this book. 凡有文化的人都该一读此书。 4. Becoming computer literate can be frustrating. 学习电脑是很折磨人的事。 5. I think everyone should be literate. 我认为人人都应该能读会写。', '副词: literately 名词: literateness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('evade', '[ɪ\'veɪd]', 'v.逃避；躲避；规避', '1. He could not evade the law. 他逃避不了法律。 2. They evade paying taxes by living abroad. 他们住在国外以逃避交税。 3. In order to evade the persecution of fascists, he had to escape abroad. 为躲避法西斯的迫害，他不得不流徙到国外。 4. Give me a direct answer, and stop evade the issue. 给我一个直截了当的回答，不要回避这一问题。', '形容词: evadable 名词: evader 过去式: evaded 过去分词: evaded 现在分词: evading 第三人称单数: evades');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tare', '[ter]', 'n.皮重；包装重量 n.野碗豆；莠草 (复数）tares: 不良成分. vt.量皮重', '1. The facts s tare us in the face. 事实明摆在我们面前。 2. Please tell me the cargo the tare and the size? 请告诉我货物的包装重量和尺寸？ 3. Net Weight: the gross weight less tare. 净重:总重扣除皮重后的重量。 4. Agile is a kindly person and tare care of us. 秋天来了，天气凉了！各位邻居要注意身体啊！', '过去式: tared 过去分词: tared 现在分词: taring 第三人称单数: tares');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('herbivorous', '[hɜː\'bɪvərəs]', 'adj.食草的', '1. Terrestrial snails are herbivorous. 陆地蜗牛是食草的。 2. The camel is a herbivorous animal. 骆驼是一种食草动物。 3. It was the main food for herbivorous dinosaurs. 它就是食草性恐龙的主要食物。', '副词: herbivorously');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('retaliation', '[rɪˌtæli\'eɪʃn]', 'n.报复；反击', '1. Retaliation only escalates a bully\'s aggression. 报复只会助长欺凌者的侵犯气焰。 2. Europe finds that trade retaliation can backfire. 欧洲发现进行贸易报复可能适得其反。 3. He never said a single word in retaliation. 他从未说过一句反击的话。 4. Retaliation, Recklessness and Shield Wall will no longer be cancelled if you switch stances while the effect is active. 反击风暴，鲁莽跟盾墙，在发动后，假如切换状态不会取消效果。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('measly', '[\'miːzli]', 'adj.（俚）微不足道的；患麻疹的', '1. What a measly birthday present! 多麽小气的生日礼物哇！ 2. He gave us measly little portions of cake. 他给了我们少得可怜的一点蛋糕。', '比较级: measlier 最高级: measliest');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rafter', '[\'ræftər]', 'n.椽；屋梁', '1. The big rafter is visible in this room. 这间屋子粗大的椽子可以看得见。 2. The carpenter working on the rafter passed his axe down to his mate below. 在椽子上干活的木匠将斧子传给下面的伙伴。 3. The red hen flew all the way to the top of the roof and sat on a rafter. 红母鸡一路飞到屋顶上并坐在一块屋梁上。', '形容词: raftered');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('decibel', '[\'desɪbel]', 'n.分贝（音量的单位）', '1. The noise pollution reached a high decibel level. 噪音污染达到了很高分贝。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('moralistic', '[ˌmɔːrə\'lɪstɪk]', 'adj.狭隘道德观的；说教的', '1. He has become more moralistic. 他的道德观越来越狭隘了。 2. I am really fed up with his moralistic attitude. 我真是受够了他那说教的态度。', '副词: moralistically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dote', '[doʊt]', 'v.溺爱', '1. Parents often dote on their youngest child. 父母通常宠爱最小的孩子。 2. I just dote on hot buttered scones! 我就是喜欢吃涂黄油的热司康饼！ 3. It seems quite natural for mothers to dote on their children. 母亲溺爱孩子似乎是很自然的事。', '名词: doter 过去式: doted 过去分词: doted 现在分词: doting 第三人称单数: dotes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('strew', '[struː]', 'vt.散播；撒满；点缀', '1. They strewed seeds over the earth. 他们把种子撒在地里。 2. Thousands of temples are strewn throughout the hills of Bali. 巴厘岛的山丘上散布着成千上万个寺庙。 3. There are papers strewn all over the floor. 地板上到处撒满了纸。 4. Shells of all shapes and sizes strew the long narrow beach. 各种各样的贝壳点缀着狭长的海滩。', '过去式: strewed 过去分词: strewn/strewed 现在分词: strewing 第三人称单数: strews');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mask', '[mæsk]', 'n.伪装；面罩；面具；[计算机]掩码 v.掩饰；戴面具；遮盖', '1. They did so under the mask of charity. 他们是打着慈善的幌子这么做的。 2. He longed to throw off the mask of respectability. 他渴望丢掉那副道貌岸然的伪装。 3. Her sociable manner is really a mask for a very shy nature. 她那好交际的作风，实际上是她腼腆天性的伪装。 4. The bank robber wears a stocking mask. 那个抢劫银行的匪徒戴着长筒袜面罩。 5. Her smile masked true feelings. 她的微笑掩饰了她的感情。', '形容词: maskable 过去式: masked 过去分词: masked 现在分词: masking 第三人称单数: masks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('torrid', '[\'tɔːrɪd]', 'adj.酷热的；热情的；色情的；困难的', '1. She almost can tolerate any kind of torrid days. 她几乎能忍受各种酷热的天气。 2. They carried on a torrid love affair. 他们曾有过炙热的爱情。 3. They faced a torrid time in tonight\'s game. 在今晚的比赛中，他们面临了一段困难的时期。', '副词: torridly 比较级: torrider 最高级: torridest 名词: torridity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('edict', '[\'iːdɪkt]', 'n.法令；布告', '1. The edict was subject to many interpretations. 这项法律附加许多解释。 2. Stubbs the plasterer was much downcast at this dreadful edict. 泥水匠斯塔布斯对这道使人敬畏的法令十分沮丧。 3. The no-brooch edict went out weeks ago. 不要胸针的布告在几星期以前就出来了。 4. They caballed against the emperor\'s edict. 他们密谋反对皇帝的谕旨。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hawker', '[\'hɔːkər]', 'n.沿街叫卖的小贩', '1. I bought that book from mobile hawker. 我从流动小贩那里买到了那本书。 2. I am not a holder of any valid hawker licence. 本人并不是任何有效小贩牌照持有人。 3. The hawker cried his wares throughout the town. 那小贩沿街叫卖商品。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('utilitarian', '[ˌjuːtɪlɪ\'teriən]', 'adj.功利的；实用的 n.功利主义者', '1. In the selection, he attempts to clarify the utilitarian standard. 在这段选文中，他试图对功利标准作一清楚表述。 2. The buildings were utilitarian rather than decorative. 这些建筑是实用性的，而不是装饰性的。 3. He is very down to earth and is a real utilitarian. 他那个人很现实, 是个十足的功利主义者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('shudder', '[\'ʃʌdər]', 'vi.战栗；发抖 n.战栗；震颤', '1. She shuddered at the sight of the dead body. 她一看到死尸就战栗起来。 2. She shuddered at the memory of school exams. 她一想到学校的考试就不寒而栗。 3. He shuddered with cold. 他冷得发抖。 4. His whole body shuddered with fury. 他的整个身体都因为恐惧而发抖。 5. The sight of the coffin sent a shudder through him. 看到那副棺材，他浑身一阵战栗。', '副词: shudderingly 过去式: shuddered 过去分词: shuddered 现在分词: shuddering 第三人称单数: shudders');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('extinct', '[ɪk\'stɪŋkt]', 'adj.灭绝的；熄灭的；消亡的', '1. This is an extinct species of fish. 这是一种已经灭绝的鱼。 2. This species will be extinct in a few decades. 几十年后这个物种将会灭绝。 3. An extinct volcano can no longer erupt. 一个灭绝的火山已不能再爆发。 4. My hope of getting some employment was extinct. 我要找到工作的希望落空了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('skewer', '[\'skjuːər]', 'n.串肉杆；针 v.用杆串好', '1. Marinated cubes of lamb threaded on a skewer. 串制的切块烧羊肉。 2. The best “partner” for cool beer in this summer is our assorted skewer! 清凉啤酒搭配美味串烧，释放夏季好心情！ 3. I used a skewer to make an extra hole in my belt. 我用扦子在腰带上又打了一个眼儿。 4. He skewered his foot on a nail. 他的脚踩在钉子上了。', '过去式: skewered 过去分词: skewered 现在分词: skewering 第三人称单数: skewers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('repatriate', '[ˌriː\'peɪtrieɪt]', 'n.被遣返回国者 v.把 ... 遣返回国；回国；寄（钱）回国', '1. How long will you live? When you repatriate? 你住多长时间呢?什么时候回国? 2. The UK owner cannot be compelled to repatriate foreign earnings. 英国业主不必缴回在国外获得的利润。 3. In this part, you need to formulate in detail repatriate the plan. 在这一部分，你需要制定详细的归国计划。 4. They would prefer tax amnesties to persuade people to repatriate their money. 因而，他们更主张税务部门能够通过采取税务赦免的手段来鼓励那些纳税人把资金从离岸金融中心带回母国。', '名词: repatriation 过去式: repatriated 过去分词: repatriated 现在分词: repatriating 第三人称单数: repatriates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reflect', '[rɪ\'flekt]', 'v.反映；反射；反省；归咎；显示', '1. Her sad looks reflected the thought passing through her mind. 她忧戚的面容反映出她内心的思想。 2. The results reflect the greatest credit upon all concerned. 这些成绩带给所有有关人员最大的荣誉。 3. The sunlight was reflected in the water. 日光由水面反射出来。 4. I often reflect on the beauty and complexity of life. 我们经常思考人生的美丽与复杂。', '过去式: reflected 过去分词: reflected 现在分词: reflecting 第三人称单数: reflects');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('plunge', '[plʌndʒ]', 'v.使投入；跳入；栽进；下降，急降，突降 n.投入；跳入', '1. She was about to plunge into something. 她就要采取什么行动了。 2. Don\'t plunge head first into another person\'s room. 别冒冒失失地撞进别人的房间。 3. The sudden jolt plunged her forward. 突然颠了一下，她向前打了个趔趄。 4. I waved my dog to plunge into the water. 我挥手示意我的狗跳入水中。 5. So why not take the plunge and have it over? 你为什么不鼓起勇气把这事赶紧解决了呢?', '过去式: plunged 过去分词: plunged 现在分词: plunging 第三人称单数: plunges');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fatuity', '[fə\'tjuːətɪ]', 'n.愚蠢；愚昧', '1. This is no doubt the first step out of confusion and fatuity. 这无疑是摆脱混乱与愚味的第一步。 2. The person of the stupid fatuity, then would be more stupid ignorant. 无知愚昧的人，则会更加无知愚昧。 3. Incapacity of square controller fatuity is mixed in corruption is corrupt. 中方负责人昏庸无能和贪污腐败。 4. God never complaints people\'s fatuity, but people always complain god\'s injustice. 上帝从不埋怨人们的愚昧,人们却埋怨上帝的不公平。', '名词复数: fatuities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('miff', '[mɪf]', 'n.小争执；微怒 vt.（使）生气', '1. His criminal plan didn\'t carry through, that drove him in a miff. 罪恶的计划没有实现，让他恼羞成怒。 2. If Mabel should get another miff, they\'d never be able to appease her. 如果梅宝儿再发怒的话，他们就没办法使她息怒了。 3. If Mabel should get another miff,they\'d never be able to appease her. 如果梅宝儿再发怒的话，他们就没办法使她息怒了。 4. Also, I won 2nd place at the 2008 Kitchen Design “DAPUR” at MIFF 2008 fair. 此外，我还获得了2008马来西亚国际家具博览会的“DAPUR”橱柜设计的二等奖。', '过去式: miffed 过去分词: miffed 现在分词: miffing 第三人称单数: miffs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('amateur', '[\'æmətər]', 'n.外行；业余爱好者 adj.业余（爱好者）的', '1. An amateur shouldn\'t play roulette for high stakes. 外行不该下大赌注赌轮盘赌。 2. You\'re a professional, but I am an amateur. 你是专业的,而我是业余的。 3. Don\'t let yourself be beaten by an amateur. 不要让自己给一个业余运动员打败了。 4. He is an amateur photographer. 他是个业余摄影爱好者。', '名词: amateurism');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('puncture', '[\'pʌŋktʃər]', 'n.刺穿；刺孔 v.刺穿；削弱', '1. Some cyclists carry repair outfits in case they have a puncture. 有些骑自行车的人带修理工具，以防车胎被刺破。 2. He demonstrated how to mend a puncture. 他示范如何修补车胎刺孔。 3. Our tires do not puncture easily. 我们的轮胎不易爆破。 4. I wish something would happen to puncture her ego. 我希望让她碰个钉子。', '形容词: puncturable 过去式: punctured 过去分词: punctured 现在分词: puncturing 第三人称单数: punctures');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mayhem', '[\'meɪhem]', 'n.有意的破坏或暴行；[法]重伤罪；故意的伤害罪', '1. The kids began to create mayhem in the garden. 孩子们开始在花园里大肆破坏。 2. There was absolute mayhem when everyone tried to get out at once. 众人蜂拥而出，造成了极大的混乱。 3. There was absolute mayhem when the cow got into the village hall. 那牛闯进村会议厅，造成一片混乱。 4. Hidden beneath the overall drop in homicide and other violent crime is a soaring rate of mayhem among teenagers. 在杀人罪和其他暴力犯罪整体减少的背后是青少年犯重伤害罪的急剧上升。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nymph', '[nɪmf]', 'n.女神；美丽的少女；蛹', '1. There are many stories about the nymphs in Roman fairy tales. 罗马神话中有许多关于女神的故事。', '形容词: nymphal');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('askew', '[ə\'skjuː]', 'adj.歪斜的 adv.斜地', '1. The picture over there is askew. 那儿的画挂歪了。 2. He arrived out of breath with his tie askew. 他到的时候气喘吁吁，领带系歪着。 3. His glasses had been knocked askew by the blow. 他的眼镜一下子被打歪了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('constellation', '[ˌkɒnstə\'leɪʃən]', 'n.星座；星群', '1. A constellation is a stellar system. 一个星座就是一个恒星星系。 2. The dragon constellation was visible in the sky. 在天空中可以看到龙星座。 3. The Great Riff of the Summer Milky Way splites the constellation. 夏日，星群被银河中的不发光的分子尘雾分开。', '形容词: constellational');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dorsal', '[\'dɔːrsl]', 'adj.(动物）背的；背部的；背侧的', '1. The shark\'s dorsal fin was cut off by the fisherman. 鲨鱼的背鳍被渔夫割了下来。', '副词: dorsally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('conservatory', '[kən\'sɜːrvətɔːri]', 'n.温室；音乐学院', '1. On Sunday, he provided a picnic brunch in Central Park\'s Conservatory Garden. 周日，他在中央公园的温室花园搞野餐活动。 2. The conservatory must be protected! 温室必须被保护！ 3. He learned to bel canto in a conservatory. 他在音乐学院学习的是美声唱法。 4. One does not learn to straddle a cello that way at a conservatory. 音乐学院是不会教人这样骑着大提琴演奏的。', '名词复数: conservatories');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('essential', '[ɪ\'senʃl]', 'adj.本质的；必要的；重要的 n.要素；必需品', '1. This is of course still the essential method. 这当然仍是本质的方法。 2. This is desirable but by no means essential to the primary objective of validating mathematical models of aircraft behaviour. 对于验证飞机性能的数学模型这一主要目的来说，这是必须的，但决不是最本质的. 3. Concentration is essential if you want to do a good job. 如果你想把事情做好,专心是必要的。 4. Mass education is essential in promoting democracy. 民众教育对提倡民主是非常重要的。 5. What are the essentials of good teaching? 成功教学的要素是什么?', '副词: essentially 名词: essentiality');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('loop', '[luːp]', 'n.环；圈；回路；环形线路 vt.以圈结；以环连结；使 ... 成环（圈） vi.形成环；环形运动', '1. This control may be closed loop or open loop. 控制可以是闭环的也可以是开环的。 2. Her wavy hair fell in loose wisps and loops upon her shoulders. 她那一头波浪般的长发一簇簇一圈圈地散垂在肩上。 3. He looped a scarf around his neck. 他把围巾在脖子上围成一圈。 4. I have to loop the wooden pegs around the garden. 我不得不用木桩来环住园地。', '过去式: looped 过去分词: looped 现在分词: looping 第三人称单数: loops');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('elliptical', '[ɪ\'lɪptɪkl]', 'adj.椭圆的；省略的；简要的', '1. If the satellite has an elliptical orbit, the result is a spiral wave, a miniature version of the pinwheel pattern of our galaxy. 如果卫星的轨道是椭圆的，就会产生螺旋波，就像是银河系纸风车形状的缩影。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('diminuendo', '[dɪˌmɪnju\'endoʊ]', 'n.(音乐)渐弱', '1. The song of the oyster, though not silenced, was diminuendo con amore. 牡蛎之歌，虽然还未沉寂，已渐唱渐弱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('demotic', '[dɪ\'mɑːtɪk]', 'adj.平民的；民众的；通俗的', '1. I am referring to Languages such as Demotic Egyptian and Ionic Greek. 我所指的语言是像通俗的埃及语和作为词根的希腊语。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('particular', '[pər\'tɪkjələr]', 'adj.特定的；专指的；特殊的；特别的；挑剔的 n.详情；细节', '1. They depend on a particular historical situation. 它们取决于特定的历史境况。 2. I have nothing particular to do this evening. 今晚我没有什么特殊的事要做。 3. Clouds must be given a particular attention. 必须对云给予特别的注意。 4. She\'s very particular about what she wears. 她对衣著很讲究。 5. The account is correct in every particular. 所述的每一细节都正确无误。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sagacious', '[sə\'ɡeɪʃəs]', 'adj.聪明的；睿智的', '1. He thought me much more sagacious than I was. 他把我看得太高明了，而我实际上并不是这样。 2. The sagacious minister offered what he considered a rather clever explanation. 道貌岸然的牧师说了一套他认为相当聪明的解释。 3. The leader made a sagacious decision. 领导做了英明的决定。 4. He is the most sagacious member of the committee. 他是委员会里最富洞察力的成员。', '副词: sagaciously 名词: sagaciousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('evince', '[ɪ\'vɪns]', 'v.表明；表示', '1. The boy evinces great intelligence. 这个男孩表现出很高的智慧。 2. The intrinsic value of tussle is to evince one\'s aversion. 斗争的本质就是表明自己的厌恶之情。 3. He evinced great sorrow for what he had done. 他对自己的所作所为深表歉疚。 4. She at last condescended to evince awareness of his proximity. 最后她才纡贵屈尊地表示出她注意到他在旁边。', '形容词: evincible 过去式: evinced 过去分词: evinced 现在分词: evincing 第三人称单数: evinces');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('imitation', '[ˌɪmɪ\'teɪʃn]', 'n.模仿；效法 adj.假造的；冒充的', '1. Young children learn how to speak by imitation. 儿童通过模仿学说话。 2. He grew beards in imitation of the actor. 他为了模仿那个演员,蓄起了胡子。 3. His style is a slavish imitation of his teacher\'s. 他一味模仿教师的风格，毫无创意。 4. Her innocence is only an imitation. 她的天真只是一种伪装。', '形容词: imitational');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('comport', '[kəm\'pɔːrt]', 'v.举止；行为；相称；适合 n.高脚盘', '1. A judge should comport himself authoritatively. 法官举止必须要庄严。 2. I do not know how I would comport myself. 我不知道我应该怎样行动。 3. Such actions do not comport with your high status. 那样的行为与你崇高的社会地位不相称。', '过去式: comported 过去分词: comported 现在分词: comporting 第三人称单数: comports');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('leery', '[\'lɪri]', 'adj.机敏的；有戒心的；留神的', '1. I tend to be a bit leery of cut-price bargains\'. 我对减价商品有点戒心。', '副词: leerily 比较级: leerier 最高级: leeriest 名词: leeriness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('entangle', '[ɪn\'tæŋɡl]', 'vt. 使 ... 纠缠； 使 ... 复杂； 卷入； 使 ... 混乱', '1. By equating it to killing babies they entangle the science in the politics of abortion. 通过将其等同于杀死婴儿，他们把科学卷入堕胎政治当中。', '名词: entanglement 过去式: entangled 过去分词: entangled 现在分词: entangling 第三人称单数: entangles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('astute', '[ə\'stuːt]', 'adj.机敏的；精明的；狡猾的', '1. But by this point, any astute businessperson has a new product waiting in the wings, ready to hit the market and revitalize his business. 但到了此时，任何机敏的业主都已经开发出新产品，准备好重新进入市场开始自己新的生意。 2. Only Parmalat\'s seemingly astute ability to rapidly grow earnings and revenues with acquisitions had placated those concerns. 不过，帕玛拉特所拥有似乎很机敏的能力，可以通过收购快速提高利润和收入，才打消市场疑虑。 3. Astute salesmen know how to invest emotionally. 精明的商人懂得如何感情投资。 4. Zhou Enlai was too astute to rail against reality. 周恩来是一个非常精明的人，他不会诅咒现实。', '副词: astutely 名词: astuteness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ascribe', '[ə\'skraɪb]', 'v.归因于；归于', '1. He ascribes his success to good luck. 他把他的成功归功于幸运。 2. You should not ascribe your failure to bad luck. 你不应该把自己的失败归因于运气不好。 3. It \'s wrong to ascribe all that have happened simply to the war . 把发生的一切归咎于战争是错误的。 4. This song is often ascribed to Bach. 这首歌曲常被说成是巴赫做的。', '过去式: ascribed 过去分词: ascribed 现在分词: ascribing 第三人称单数: ascribes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('quondam', '[\'kwɒndəm]', 'adj.过去的；以前的', '1. Im sorry that we have to keep the quondam price. 很遗憾我们不得不保持原价。 2. These quondam rulers of China have had a bad reputation abroad. 这些显赫一时的中国统治者们在国外的声誉很坏。 3. At one time I asked her :\"Who do you love more,quondam boyfriend or me?\"... 我曾经问过她:\"你爱你以前的男朋友多一点,还是爱我多一点? 4. It has many outstanding advantage than the quondam oil pattern fire yoke . 比过去的油式点火线圈具有许多突出的优点。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hoop', '[huːp]', 'n.箍；铁环；裙撑；呼呼声 v.加箍于；包围；发呼呼声', '1. A long, bag-shaped fishing net held open by hoops. 长袋网一种用箍圈固定开口处的长的袋形渔网 2. The worker bent an iron rod into a hoop. 工人把铁条弯成箍。 3. The wooden tub is fitted with the iron hoop. 木盆都用铁箍箍紧。 4. The hoop rolled along the pavement. 圆环沿人行道滚动。 5. The girl cut her coat, hoop a thing, only leave mammilla. 女娃娃把衣服剪成这,箍个这,光剩个奶头了。', '过去式: hooped 过去分词: hooped 现在分词: hooping 第三人称单数: hoops');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lingual', '[\'lɪŋɡwəl]', 'adj.舌的；舌音的；语言的 n.舌音；舌音字', '1. The result shows that objective lingual cue affects memory effect. 结果显示，客观语言提示影响人的记忆效果。 2. Its brilliant elegant lingual art, can be called \"Great works\". 它那璀灿优美的语言艺术，真可谓“天地妙文”。 3. Maximum lingual inclination was observed in the lower first molars. 最大唇（颊）侧倾斜为正门齿，最大舌侧斜则为第一大臼齿。 4. The lingual meaning is an information to be comprehended and built up by words. 从信息哲学的角度来看,语言的意义就是借助于语词而被理解和建构着的信息。', '副词: lingually');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('smug', '[smʌɡ]', 'adj.自鸣得意的；沾沾自喜的；整洁的', '1. You\'ve got nothing to be smug about. 你有什么值得自鸣得意的。 2. He needn\'t be so smug, I know something he didn\'t know. 他用不着那么沾沾自喜，我懂得某些他不懂得的东西。', '副词: smugly 比较级: smugger 最高级: smuggest 名词: smugness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gamut', '[\'ɡæmət]', 'n.【音乐】全音阶；长音阶；全音域 n.全部；整个范围', '1. Several musical compositions make clever use of different gamut, arpeggio （their varieties included） as a means of expressing music. 许多乐曲都是巧妙地运用了各种音阶、琶音和弦和分解和弦（包括它们的种种变体）作为表现音乐的手段。 2. The training and practice of gamut , semi-gamut, arpeggio etc, play an important part in piano teaching. 在钢琴教学中,音阶、半音阶、琶音、属七和减七和弦琶音、双八度以及双三度等这些技术类型的训练占着重要的地位。 3. The exhibition runs the whole gamut of artistic styles. 这次展览包括了所有艺术风格的作品。 4. Gamut mapping is a key technology for color management. 色域匹配是色彩管理的一项关键技术。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('transpose', '[træn\'spoʊz]', 'vt.调换；颠倒顺序；【数】移项 n.【属】转置阵；转置', '1. Dyslexics often transpose letters in a word. 诵读困难者经常改换话语的文字。 2. To cause to change places; transpose. 使改变地方；调换；使换位 3. NO WAY OUT/ A 2-coin transpo with a BIG difference. NO出路/ 2 ，金币转一个很大的区别。 4. Returns the matrix transpose of a given matrix. 返回一个给定矩阵的转置矩阵。', '形容词: transposable 过去式: transposed 过去分词: transposed 现在分词: transposing 第三人称单数: transposes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stellar', '[\'stelər]', 'adj.星(状的)；和电影明星有关的；主要的；一流的', '1. Collisions between the gas clouds may trigger a stellar baby boom. 气体云之间的碰撞可能会触发产星高潮。 2. Now an international team of astronomers says you can blame gusts of stellar wind. 现在一个国际天文学团队说，原因在于猛烈的星风。', 'none');
