INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dismal', '[\'dɪzməl]', 'adj.阴沉的；凄凉的；暗的', '1. We were all depressed by the dismal weather. 阴沉的天气让我们都感到压抑。 2. He tossed about until the appearance of the dismal London daylight, when he sprang up desperately, and walked off to his uncle\'s lodgings in Bury Street. 他翻来复去，等到伦敦那阴沉的白天开始上曙光，便一骨碌爬了起来，前往柏利街他叔父的寓所。 3. Africa will be the highlight of an otherwise dismal year. 非洲将是这异常凄凉的一年里的亮点。 4. There was something to celebrate about amid the dismal environment on rocky Patmos. 在多岩的拔摩岛凄凉的环境中，原来也有值得庆祝的事。', '副词: dismally 名词: dismalness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rational', '[\'ræʃnəl]', 'adj.合理的；理性的；能推理的 n.有理数', '1. Your choice was perfectly rational under the circumstances. 在那种情况下,你的选择是相当合理的。 2. Man is a rational being. 人是有理性的生物。 3. No rational person would go to work in his pyjamas. 任何神智正常的人都不会穿着睡衣去上班。 4. The rational numbers also fit into this scheme. 有理数也适用于这个图形。', '副词: rationally 名词: rationalness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('prodigy', '[\'prɑːdədʒi]', 'n.惊人的事物；奇迹；神童；天才', '1. The man is a prodigy of learning. 此人学识渊博。 2. Critics were not gammoned by this latest prodigy. 评论家不为最近发生的反常的事所欺骗。 3. The report of such a prodigy awakened my curiosity. 这些奇迹的传闻，激起了我的好奇心。 4. She was a child prodigy on the violin. 她是神童小提琴手。', '名词复数: prodigies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dimple', '[\'dɪmpl]', 'n.酒窝；涟漪 v.(使）出现酒窝；(使）起波纹', '1. Mary has two dimples when she smiles. 玛丽笑时露出两个笑靥。 2. A cute dimple just appeared in your face. 一个可爱的酒窝刚在你的脸上浮现。 3. The fracture of composites assumes toughness dimple. 复合材料的拉伸断口假设为韧窝混合断裂. 4. In the sunlight, a fresh breeze dimple the surface of Bay Roberts. 阳光下清新的微风吹得罗伯茨湾的海水泛起阵阵涟漪。', '形容词: dimply 过去式: dimpled 过去分词: dimpled 现在分词: dimpling 第三人称单数: dimples');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('accumulate', '[ə\'kjuːmjəleɪt]', 'v.积累；增加；聚集', '1. They set out to accumulate a huge mass of data. 他们开始积累大量的资料。 2. Dust and dirt soon accumulates if a house is not cleaned regularly. 房屋不经常打扫,尘土很快就越积越多。 3. True poetry accumulates meaning every time it is read. 真正好诗愈念涵义愈丰富。 4. However, as the evidence began to accumulate, experts from the zoo felt obliged to investigate. 然而，当证据日趋增多时，该动物园的专家们感到有必要进行调查。', '形容词: accumulable 过去式: accumulated 过去分词: accumulated 现在分词: accumulating 第三人称单数: accumulates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lactic', '[\'læktɪk]', 'adj.乳（汁）的；来自乳汁的', '1. Now they wear rubber fingers treated with lactic acid. 现在他们戴上了用乳酸处理过的橡皮指套。 2. A salt or an ester of lactic acid. 乳酸盐或乳酸酯 3. Anhui BBCA & Galactic Lactic Acid Co., Ltd. 安徽丰原格拉特乳酸有限公司 4. Dancheng Jindan Lactic Acid Industrial Co., Ltd. 郸城金丹乳酸实业有限公司', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cupidity', '[kjuː\'pɪdəti]', 'n.贪心；贪婪', '1. He was very regretful for his cupidity when he felt very thirsty and wanted to buy a bottle of drink or an ice cream, but he had no money. 当感觉非常口渴，想买瓶饮料或者一个冰激凌，却一分钱没有时，他为自己的贪心而感到后悔。 2. Avoid cupidity of money and glory. 避免对金钱和荣誉的贪婪。 3. There was a glimmer of cupidity in those small, cunning eyes of his. 他狡猾的小眼睛里露出了一丝贪婪的神情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('genetics', '[dʒə\'netɪks]', 'n.遗传学', '1. Genetics is beyond my scope. 遗传学不是我的专长。 2. Charaka also knew the fundamentals of genetics. 查拉卡也知道遗传学的基本原理。 3. In genetics, genes were formerly called factors. 在遗传学上，基因以前被称为遗传因子。 4. This week, we look back at a major discovery in genetics. 这周，我们来回顾一下遗传学中的主要表现。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ignorant', '[\'ɪɡnərənt]', 'adj.无知的；愚昧的；不知道的', '1. He\'s so ignorant that he cannot write his own name. 他很无知，连自己的名字都写不出。 2. She regarded her critics as ignorant and prejudiced. 她认为那些批评她的人既无知又存有偏见。 3. Ignorant children sometimes laugh at beggars and tramps. 无知的孩子们有时会嘲笑乞丐和无家可归的人。 4. His ignorant behaviour at the dinner table caused much embarrassment. 他在餐桌上举止粗鲁，在座的人颇为难堪。', '副词: ignorantly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('papyrus', '[pə\'paɪrəs]', 'n.纸莎草；纸草；草制成之纸', '1. In those days, paper was made from s strips of the papi papyrus plant. 当时的纸是由纸莎草植物的剥离物制成的。 2. In those days, paper was made from strips of the papyrus plant. 在那些日子里，纸是由纸草植物条制成的。 3. The word paper, in fact, is derived from the word papyrus. 实际上，纸这个词（paper）就是由纸莎草\"Papyrus\"引伸而来。', '名词复数: papyruses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('outgrowth', '[\'aʊtɡroʊθ]', 'n.自然的发展；后果；副产品；长出物', '1. Enthusiasm is the natural outgrowth of all your efforts toward success. 热忱是你为成功所付出所有努力的自然结果。 2. Inflation is an outgrowth of war. 通货膨胀是战争带来的后果 3. Revolution is a frequent outgrowth of tyranny. 革命是暴政促成的常有结果。 4. Technology is the outgrowth of science. 技术是科学的副产品。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('curdle', '[\'kɜːrdl]', 'v.凝结；变稠 v.(使)结成凝乳；变成凝乳状', '1. The sight made my blood curdle. 那景象使我不寒而栗。 2. The milk has curdled and become sour. 牛奶凝结变酸了。 3. If the sauce reaches too high a temperature, it will curdle. 如果酱汁的温度太高，会凝固。 4. Lemon juice curdles milk. 柠檬汁可使牛奶结成凝乳。', '过去式: curdled 过去分词: curdled 现在分词: curdling 第三人称单数: curdles');
