INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('innuendo', '[ˌɪnju\'endoʊ]', 'n.讽刺；含沙射影；讥讽 v.说讽刺话', '1. Mark told by innuendo that the opposing team would lose the game 马克暗讽地说敌队会在比赛中输掉。 2. Mark told by innuendo that the opposing team would lose the game. 马克暗讽地说敌队会在比赛中输掉。 3. There have been too many unpleasant innuendoes in this debate and not enough facts. 在这场辩论中据实而争者少，含沙射影者多，令人生厌。 4. I don\'t innuendo anyboby or anything. 我并未影射如何人或任何事。', '名词复数: innuendoes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flip', '[flɪp]', 'vt.掷；轻击；弹 vi.翻转 n.（跳水或体操动作中的）空翻；轻弹；浏览 adj.无礼的；冒失的；轻率的', '1. Let\'s flip a coin to see who goes first. 我们来掷硬币看谁先去。 2. Kids flip frisbees while their elders chat. 孩子们玩飞盘，大人聊天。 3. He flipped a crumb across the room. 他把面包屑弹到房间另一头。 4. She flipped the insect from her face. 她将昆虫从脸上弹掉。 5. He flipped to a fresh page and began to write. 他翻到另外一页,开始写了起来。 6. The gymnast had to do a double back flip. 这个体操运动员得做一个360度后空翻。 7. Don\'t be flip with me. 不要对我油腔滑舌。', '比较级: flipper 最高级: flippest 过去式: flipped 过去分词: flipped 现在分词: flipping 第三人称单数: flips');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('figment', '[\'fɪɡmənt]', 'n.虚构的东西', '1. That Sunday is a figment of the world\'s imagination . 星期天是世界想象出来的虚构物。 2. Doctor, are you suggesting the pain is a figment of my imagination? 医生，你是说这疼痛是我想像出来的喽?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('remittent', '[rɪ\'mɪtnt]', 'adj.(病)间歇性的；忽好忽坏的', '1. Begin, remittent thought understanding is skimble-scamble also. 开始，上上下下的思想熟悉也不统一。 2. Two good shots, remittent, drawing wool collects deep feeling. 两根棒针，上上下下，牵引毛线汇成深情。 3. During the first week there is a gradually increasing remittent fever. 第一周驰张热逐渐升高。 4. Trachecotomy was some effective but dyspnea can not remittent uncompletely. 4均有遗留有明显的肺实质损害如肺纤维化，肺脓肿、空洞，支气管扩张，肺顺应性下降等。', '副词: remittently 名词: remittence');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('confirm', '[kən\'fɜːrm]', 'v.证实；批准；确定', '1. His letter confirmed everything. 他的信证实了一切。 2. The treaty was confirmed by the president. 条约已被总统批准。 3. Could you confirm the dispatch date? 您可以确定发货日期吗?', '形容词: confirmable 名词: confirmability 过去式: confirmed 过去分词: confirmed 现在分词: confirming 第三人称单数: confirms');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('speleology', '[ˌspiːli\'ɒlədʒi]', 'n.洞穴学', '1. Proceedings of the 9th International Congress of Speleology. 岩溶地区水利水电建设一些环境地质问题的探讨。 2. His interest in the kindred field of speleology was promptly revived. 他感兴趣的领域的骨肉洞穴学的迅速恢复。 3. The Father of Modern Cave Exploring (Speleology) was Norbert Casteret (1897-1987), who was honoured with a stamp issued by France 18th September 2000. 父现代洞穴探险（洞穴）是诺伯Casteret （ 1897年至1987年） ，谁很荣幸与纪念邮票由法国2000年9月十八号。 4. Other sports activities are mountaineering, hiking, canyoning, speleology, mountain-biking, archery, climbing, rappel on rock and on bridge, skiing on stones, kayak and rafting on rivers of the surrounding area. 其他体育运动有在周围地区的登山、远足、峡谷穿越、探洞、山地骑行、射箭、攀岩和速降（在山岩或桥上）、滑石、划艇和漂流。', '形容词: speleological 名词: speleologist');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('desert', '[\'dezərt]', 'n.沙漠；荒地；应得(的惩罚或奖励) v.遗弃；离弃；放弃；擅离职守', '1. Two thirds of the country is dry or desert. 这个国家有三分之二的地方气候干燥,或者是沙漠。 2. Some of them died of thirst in the desert. 他们中有些人在沙漠中渴死了。 3. Water can transform a desert into a garden. 水能把一片不毛之地变成一座花园。 4. The baby\'s mother deserted him soon after giving birth. 那个母亲生下他后不久就把他遗弃了。', '名词: deserter 过去式: deserted 过去分词: deserted 现在分词: deserting 第三人称单数: deserts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lancet', '[\'lænsɪt]', 'n.[医]柳叶刀；[建]尖顶窗', '1. The study is in the Lancet medical journal. 这项研究刊登在柳叶刀医学杂志上。 2. Doctors need more training to deal with the victims of bomb blasts given the current threat of terrorism, a Lancet paper says. 一篇柳叶刀报纸称，在当前恐怖主义的威胁下，医生需要为炸弹爆炸的受害者进行更多的训练。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cater', '[\'keɪtər]', 'v.提供饮食及服务；迎合；满足', '1. Our hotel also caters for weddings and parties. 本饭店也承办婚礼、宴会。 2. These hotels cater especially to foreign tourists. 这些旅馆专门为外国游客提供服务。 3. They only publish novels which cater to the mass market. 他们只出版迎合大众市场的小说。 4. TV programs must cater for many different tastes. 电视节目必须满足观众的不同爱好。', '名词: caterer 过去式: catered 过去分词: catered 现在分词: catering 第三人称单数: caters');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('swing', '[swɪŋ]', 'n.摇摆；改变；冲力；秋千 v.摇摆；旋转；动摇', '1. The swing of the ship made many people seasick. 船的摇摆使许多人晕船。 2. The willow branches swing in the breeze. 柳枝迎风摇摆。 3. I used to swing, but then age and good taste overtook me. 我原来喜欢赶时髦，后来随着年龄的增长和审美观的改变便不再那样了。 4. Tiny changes here can be felt in the backswing and lead to big improvements in the hit swing. 这里在后摆时能够感受出来的很小的改变就可以让你在击球摆动上得到很大的进步。 5. This will swing public opinions against the government. 这将使公共舆论转而反对政府。', '形容词: swingy 过去式: swung 过去分词: swung 现在分词: swinging 第三人称单数: swings');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('treaty', '[\'triːti]', 'n.条约；协定', '1. The treaty gave (a) fresh impetus to trade. 这条约使双方的贸易又推进了一步。 2. There is a contentious clause in the treaty. 这条约中有一条有争议的条款。 3. The Government has signed a treaty with Moscow. 政府已与莫斯科签了一项条约。 4. The house was sold by private treaty. 这所房子以私人协议的方式售出。', '名词复数: treaties');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('grandstand', '[\'ɡrænstænd]', 'n.正面看台；观众 v.哗众取宠的表演；卖弄技巧', '1. He swiped the ball into the grandstand. 他把球打到看台上去了。 2. It\'s shady in the grandstand and more comfortable for you. 正面看台阴凉,你会比较舒适。 3. The grandstand and the match place are segregated by baffles. 球场的观众区与比赛区被挡板隔开了。 4. Politicians will grandstand about remaking finance. 政客们会为重整金融体系而轮番上台表演。', '名词: grandstander 过去式: grandstanded 过去分词: grandstanded 现在分词: grandstanding 第三人称单数: grandstands');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('curtail', '[kɜːr\'teɪl]', 'v.缩减；削减；截短', '1. Illness has curtailed her sporting activities. 她因病而减少了体育活动。 2. The government hopes to curtail public spending. 政府希望缩减公共事业开支。 3. The government hopes to curtail public spending in the next tax year. 政府希望在下个财税年度减少公家开支。 4. Given this, China will continue to take measures to curtail the trend of deflation. 因此,中国还要继续采取措施以遏制通缩的趋势。', '名词: curtailer 过去式: curtailed 过去分词: curtailed 现在分词: curtailing 第三人称单数: curtails');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('blasphemy', '[\'blæsfəmi]', 'n.亵渎神明；亵渎神明的言词', '1. Murder and blasphemy are mortal sins. 谋杀和亵渎神明的言词都是不可饶恕的大罪。 2. Their conversation was full of blasphemy. 他们的谈话中充满了渎犯神灵的言词。', '名词复数: blasphemies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('enchant', '[ɪn\'tʃænt]', 'v.施魔法；使迷惑；使喜悦；使陶醉', '1. The act of enchanting. 使用魔法迷惑的行为 2. Enchanting as if with a magic spell; fascinating. 令人心醉的使如同有魔咒般迷住的; 迷人的 3. She was enchanted with the flowers you sent her. 她非常喜欢你送的花。', '过去式: enchanted 过去分词: enchanted 现在分词: enchanting 第三人称单数: enchants');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('irremediable', '[ˌɪrɪ\'miːdiəbl]', 'adj.不能补救的；不能挽回的', '1. This influence is often not irremediable. 这种影响往往不是立杆见影的。 2. The whole city was affected by the irremediable calamity. 整个城市都受到了这次无法补救的巨大灾难的影响。 3. He is faced with the fact of an irremediable marital breakdown. 他面临着不可挽救的婚姻破裂的事实。', '副词: irremediably');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('productivity', '[ˌprɑːdʌk\'tɪvəti]', 'n.生产率；生产力', '1. We should aim with efforts for higher productivity. 我们应该力争达到更高的生产率。 2. This will help do away with heavy manual labour and raise productivity. 这可以帮助消除繁重的体力劳动，提高劳动生产率。 3. Improved productivity justifies an increase in wages. 提高了生产力理应增加工资。 4. The workers are trying their best to increase productivity. 工人们正竭尽全力提高生产力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('awkward', '[\'ɔːkwərd]', 'adj.尴尬的；笨拙的；（设计）别扭的', '1. It\'s a little awkward, because he\'s my friend but I\'m still his boss. 他是我朋友,而我又是他老板,这真有点尴尬。 2. He felt awkward and uncomfortable. 他感到尴尬和不舒服。 3. He seemed as awkward and rough as ever. 他跟从前一样拙笨和粗鲁。 4. Swans are surprisingly awkward on the land. 天鹅在陆地上笨的出奇。', '副词: awkwardly 名词: awkwardness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ban', '[bæn]', 'v.禁止；剥夺权利 n.禁令；禁止', '1. The government has banned the use of chemical weapons. 政府已经禁止使用化学武器。 2. She was banned from athletics for two years after failing a drug test. 她在药检中被查出服用禁用药物而被禁赛两年。 3. A ban on the importation of drugs has been issued recently. 最近已经发布了禁止进口毒品的法令。 4. There is a ban on smoking in the theatre. 这剧院内禁止吸烟。', '名词复数: bani 过去式: banned 过去分词: banned 现在分词: banning 第三人称单数: bans');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('disposable', '[dɪ\'spoʊzəbl]', 'adj.可任意处理的；一次性的 n.用完即可丢弃的东西', '1. The brochure is disposable after the meeting. 会议结束后,可以任意处理这本小册子。 2. The advertisement is aimed at people in their 20s with high disposable incomes. 这个广告的对象是那些二十多岁且可支配收入高的人士。 3. These medical cotton balls are all disposable. 这些医用棉球仅限于一次性使用。 4. It is more hygienic to use disposable paper tissues. 使用一次性餐巾纸更为卫生。', '名词: disposability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('egress', '[\'iːɡres]', 'n.外出；外出权；出路；出口 v.外出', '1. Safe access and egress can be achieved by various methods. 可以采用各种方法安全的进入或离开。 2. The secured area should meet all life safety code egress requirements. 受保护区域要满足所有的生命安全法规对出口的要求。', '过去式: egressed 过去分词: egressed 现在分词: egressing 第三人称单数: egresses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('abundant', '[ə\'bʌndənt]', 'adj.丰富的；充裕的', '1. Indonesia is abundant in petroleum deposits. 印尼的石油蕴藏量丰富。 2. The agricultural commodities are abundant this year. 今年的农产品很丰富。 3. Birds concentrate in places where food is abundant. 鸟聚集在食物丰盛的地方。 4. There is abundant firewood in the forest. 森林里有充裕的薪柴可用。', '副词: abundantly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('specimen', '[\'spesɪmən]', 'n.标本；样本', '1. This specimen is richly variegated in colour. 这件标本上有很多颜色。 2. Arthur brought out his specimen box. 亚瑟拿出了他的标本箱。 3. He is still a fine specimen of health. 他仍是健康的典范。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('convene', '[kən\'viːn]', 'vi.集合 vt.集合；召集；召唤', '1. The tribunal will convene tomorrow. 法庭将于明日开庭。 2. The committee will convene at 11.30 next Thursday. 委员会将在下星期四上午 11:30 开会。 3. The Board shall convene an emergency meeting to review and confirm such report. 董事会应召开紧急会议对该报告进行审议并核准。 4. People were convened here for an emergency meeting. 人们被召集到这里举行紧急会议。', '形容词: convenable 名词: convener 过去式: convened 过去分词: convened 现在分词: convening 第三人称单数: convenes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('filibuster', '[\'fɪlɪbʌstər]', 'n.妨碍议事；妨碍议事者；掠夺兵；海盗 v.阻挠议案通过；掠夺', '1. The democrats organized a filibuster in the senate. 民主党党员在参议院上组织了阻挠议事。 2. Supporters of the law filibustered to prevent it from being revised. 法律的支持者阻碍议案通过，以防法律被修改。', '名词: filibusterer 过去式: filibustered 过去分词: filibustered 现在分词: filibustering 第三人称单数: filibusters');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('arrogance', '[\'ærəɡəns]', 'n.傲慢；自大', '1. I disliked him for his arrogance. 我讨厌他的傲慢。 2. It is easy to misconstrue confidence as arrogance. 很容易将信心误解为傲慢。 3. The biggest failure of life is arrogance! 人生最大的失败是自大！ 4. The arrogance spells danger and may signal the beginning of a crisis. 自大便是危机的开端，此时国家将危在旦夕。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sonorous', '[\'sɑːnərəs]', 'adj.洪亮的；响亮的；作响的；堂皇的', '1. There is a sonorous bell in the tower. 塔里有一口洪亮的钟。 2. It was possible that the sweetly sonorous hymns stimulated me. 这洪亮悦耳的圣歌是能够刺激我的。 3. Sonorous singing came from the distance. 从远处传来高亢的歌声。 4. Sonorous bugle aroused everyone from sleep. 嘹亮的号声将每个人从睡梦中唤醒。', '副词: sonorously 名词: sonorousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('condign', '[kən\'daɪn]', 'adj.相当的；适宜的', '1. Condign English basic skill, especially written. 有英语基础，特别是书面英语能力。 2. The public approved the condign punishment. 公众一致称赞这个罪判得很恰当。 3. When dietary CP utilizable efficiency was the highest, dietary fiber contents were ADF 7.4%, DNF 16.4% and CF 5.5%, which is condign dietary fiber levels in emu dietary. CP利用率最大时的日粮纤维含量分别是:ADF 7.;4%25、NDF 16 4. Develop condign retail distributor to be project distributor, selectively develop and train project distributor according to project item and project distributor characteristics. 发展适宜的零售经销商同时成为项目经销商,针对项目产品与项目经销商特点,选择性开发项目经销商,并予以培训;', '副词: condignly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('indubitable', '[ɪn\'djuːbɪtəbəl]', 'adj.不容置疑的；明确无疑的', '1. It\'s indubitable to his loyalty. 他的忠诚无可置疑。 2. The facticity of manuscript is indubitable. 手稿的真实性是毋庸置疑的。 3. The growth of the whole market is not indubitable as expectancy. 整个市场的成长不如预期是很明确的。', '副词: indubitably');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('clientele', '[ˌklaɪən\'tel]', 'n.客户', '1. The shop caters to a small, wealthy clientele. 这家店迎合少数有钱顾客的需求。 2. The restaurant has a large regular clientele. 这家餐馆有很多常客。 3. My clientele has always favoured quality rather than quantity. 我的老主顾们总是注意质量而不是数量。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('perfunctorily', '[pə\'fʌŋktrəli]', 'adv.敷衍地；潦草地；表面地', '1. Almanac has been written on time, all kinds of awards have been perfunctorily reviewed, and special conferences of research on poetry convened annually. 每年都按时书写自己的年鉴，敷衍地评选出各种不同的诗歌奖项，召开若干次关于诗的专门研究会议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flaccid', '[\'flæsɪd]', 'adj.软弱的；没气力的；无活力的', '1. Even while the muscles appear flaccid, some nerve threads may be functional. 甚至当肌肉出现无力，一些神经纤维可能还是有功能的。 2. His breathing was hoarse, his face livid, his limbs flaccid, his belly prominent. 他的呼吸声沙哑，脸色苍白，双腿无力，肚子鼓胀。', '副词: flaccidly 名词: flaccidity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('disconcert', '[ˌdɪskən\'sɜːrt]', 'v.使困惑；使仓皇失措；使尴尬', '1. He was disconcerted to find the other guests formally dressed. 他看到其他客人都穿得正正经经的，觉得很尴尬。', '副词: disconcertingly 过去式: disconcerted 过去分词: disconcerted 现在分词: disconcerting 第三人称单数: disconcerts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wreak', '[riːk]', 'vt.发泄；施行（报复）；造成（破坏等），带来（灾难性的后果）', '1. Timid people always wreak their peevishness on the gentle. 怯懦的人总是把满腹牢骚向温和的人发泄。 2. I am determined to wreak vengeance on John. 我决心向约翰报仇。 3. The survivor is determined to wreak her revenge on the murderer of her family . 这位幸存者决心要报复杀害她家人的凶手 4. The earthquake wreaked havoc on the city. 地震对这个城市造成了大破坏。', '过去式: wreaked 过去分词: wreaked 现在分词: wreaking 第三人称单数: wreaks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stoke', '[stoʊk]', 'v.给(炉子)添燃料；煽动；<俚>大吃', '1. The caretaker stokes up twice a day. 管理员每天往火里加两次煤。 2. Soon, it came time for her to stoke the fire. 不久，添柴的时候到了。 3. She likes to stoke up quarrels between people. 她喜欢挑起人们之间的不和。 4. He continued to stoke up hatred in his speeches. 他在讲话中不断加深人们的仇恨。', '过去式: stoked 过去分词: stoked 现在分词: stoking 第三人称单数: stokes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('demure', '[dɪ\'mjʊr]', 'adj.严肃的；端庄的；矜持的', '1. To counterbalance the hairdo, Tymoshenko\'s outfits needed to be demure yet commanding. 为了平衡发型的风格 2. She looks like a very demure young lady. 她看上去像一个矜持的少女。', '副词: demurely 比较级: demurer 最高级: demurest 名词: demureness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('excavate', '[\'ekskəveɪt]', 'v.挖掘；挖开；发掘（古物）', '1. It took a long time to excavate the ancient city of Troy. 挖掘古老的特洛伊城，花了很长时间。 2. I let him excavate around the mine. 我准许他在金矿周围挖掘。 3. They plan to excavate a large hole. 他们计划挖个大洞。 4. The archaeologists excavated a buried city. 考古学家发掘出一个埋在地下的城市。', '过去式: excavated 过去分词: excavated 现在分词: excavating 第三人称单数: excavates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('subtle', '[\'sʌtl]', 'adj.微妙的；敏锐的；不明显的；精细的；狡猾的', '1. There were subtle hints in his letter. 他的信中有些微妙的暗示。 2. What meaning will my subtle signal make? 我的微妙信号表达了什么意思? 3. She has a very subtle mind. 她有个很敏锐的头脑。 4. Satire is a high and subtle art. 讽刺是一门崇高而又含蓄的艺术。', '副词: subtly 比较级: subtler 最高级: subtlest 名词: subtleness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('infection', '[ɪn\'fekʃn]', 'n.传染；传染病；影响', '1. Are you sure there is no danger of infection now? 你敢不敢肯定现在已经没有传染的危险了? 2. This infection is transmitted by mosquitoes. 这种传染病是由蚊子传染的。 3. He was infected with a latent infection. 他被感染了一种潜伏性的传染病。 4. This new type of infection is resistant to antibiotics. 这种新的传染病对抗菌素有抗药性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('freestanding', '[\'friː\'stændɪŋ]', 'adj.独立式的', '1. The freestanding machine takes up 25-percent less space than conventional systems. 这 种独立式的机器比传统的系统少占用25%25的空间。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nihilism', '[\'naɪɪlɪzəm]', 'n.（否认一切宗教信仰和道德观念的）虚无主义；无政府主义；（精神病学）虚无幻觉 Nihilism. 无政府主义运动(19世纪俄国的一次革命活动).', '1. The negation of the infinite leads straight to nihilism. 对无极的否认会直接导向虚无主义。 2. This finale is correlative with his viewpoint of nihilism an d humanitarianism. 这种结局与周氏的虚无主义和个人主义的人道主义世界观密不可分。 3. There are lots of reasons why nihilism triumphed. 无政府主义获胜有很多原因。', '形容词: nihilistic 副词: nihilistically 名词: nihilist');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('obscure', '[əb\'skjʊr]', 'adj.难解的；不著名的；微暗的；[语音学]轻音的 v.使 ... 模糊；隐藏；变模糊 n.模糊不清的东西', '1. The rules for the competition are somewhat obscure. 比赛的规则有点让人费解。 2. The reasons why he did it are obscure. 他做那事的理由还不清楚。 3. The report had been published in an obscure German journal. 这个报道刊登在德国一家不著名的报纸上。 4. He set the bed in an obscure corner. 他把床放在一个昏暗的角落。 5. The moon was obscured by clouds. 月亮被云遮住了。 6. Hence things whichhave perplexed you and made the case more obscure have served to enlighten meand to strengthen my conclusions. 因此，那些使你们大惑不解并且使案情更加模糊不清的事物，却会对我有所启发，并且能加强我的论断。', '副词: obscurely 比较级: obscurer 最高级: obscurest 名词: obscureness 过去式: obscured 过去分词: obscured 现在分词: obscuring 第三人称单数: obscures');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('phantom', '[\'fæntəm]', 'n.幻影；幽灵 adj.错觉的；幻影的；幽灵的', '1. The phantom that my mind pursued, was another and more real child. 我的心灵追求的幻影是另一个较为真切的孩子。 2. It is the sort of night when phantom may walk. 这种夜晚正是幽灵出没的时候 3. Have you heard the story of the phantom riders passing by in the night? 你听说过夜间飘过的幽灵骑士的故事吗？ 4. Because Phantom Hourglass takes place in the same world as The Wind Waker, you\'ll once again be traveling among a lot of relatively small islands. 因为幻影的沙漏发生在与风之仗相同的世界里，所以，你会再一次地在许多相关的小岛间旅行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tire', '[\'taɪər]', 'n.轮胎；金属圈 v.使疲倦；厌烦；劳累', '1. There is no tread on the tire - you should put on a new one. 这条轮胎已经磨平了，你应该换一条新的。 2. The tires of this car don\'t have enough air in them. 这辆汽车的轮胎气不足了。 3. I never tire of reading Shakespeare. 我对莎士比亚的作品百读不厌。 4. The ceremony was short so as not to tire them. 仪式很简短，以免使他们疲劳。', '过去式: tired 过去分词: tired 现在分词: tiring 第三人称单数: tires');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('delude', '[dɪ\'luːd]', 'v.欺骗；迷惑；蛊惑', '1. He deluded her with empty promises. 他用虚假的诺言哄骗了她。 2. She deluded herself with false hopes. 她以虚幻的希望欺骗自己。 3. You must not delude him into believing it. 你不可误导他相信那件事。 4. Candidates running for president often delude the voters with election promises. 参加总统竞选的候选人往往以竞选许诺来蛊惑选民。', '副词: deludingly 名词: deluder 过去式: deluded 过去分词: deluded 现在分词: deluding 第三人称单数: deludes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vendetta', '[ven\'detə]', 'n.仇杀；相互复仇', '1. She conducted a personal vendetta against me. 她对我有宿仇。 2. For years he pursued a vendetta against the Morris family. 多年来他一直在寻求向莫里斯家族报世仇。 3. The only verdict is vengeance, a vendetta, held as a votive not in vain. 唯一的结论就是复仇,一种仇恨,作为一种虚无的奉献。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('coax', '[koʊks]', 'v.哄；诱骗；灵巧慢慢地做', '1. The clerk is always able to coax the customers into good humor. 那个售货员总是能够把顾客哄得高高兴兴的。 2. Mother ran after me, murmuring fine words to coax me. 母亲在后面小跑着，嘴里还在不断地说着好话哄我。 3. I\'ve come back to coax a respectable sum of money out of an aged woman who happens also to be my mother. 我回来的目的，是从一个老太婆手上诱骗一笔数目可观的金钱，她碰巧是我母亲。', '副词: coaxingly 名词: coaxer 过去式: coaxed 过去分词: coaxed 现在分词: coaxing 第三人称单数: coaxes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('discharge', '[dɪs\'tʃɑːrdʒ]', 'v.排出；释放；解雇；放电；解除；清偿债务 n.卸货；释放；发射；放电；准许离开；排出物', '1. The Nile discharge itself into the Mediterranean. 尼罗河水注入地中海。 2. The water pipe doesn\'t discharge freely. 水管排水不畅。 3. The judge discharged the prisoner. 法官把囚犯释放了。 4. I am going to discharge our chauffeur. 我要解雇我们的司机。 5. How long will the discharge of the cargo take? 卸货需要多久？', '形容词: dischargeable 名词: dischargee 过去式: discharged 过去分词: discharged 现在分词: discharging 第三人称单数: discharges');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('catastrophe', '[kə\'tæstrəfi]', 'n.大灾难；大祸；彻底失败', '1. The earthquake was a terrible catastrophe. 这次地震是个可怕的灾难。 2. He is teetering on the edge of catastrophe. 他在大灾难的边缘徘徊。 3. The catastrophe would be stamped in their minds. 那场灾难将会深深地印在他们的头脑里。 4. Their other problems paled into insignificance beside this latest catastrophe. 最近发生这一灾祸后,他们其他的问题都显得无关重要了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pretentious', '[prɪ\'tenʃəs]', 'adj.自命不凡的；自负的；矫饰的；炫耀的', '1. He is a talented but pretentious writer. 他是一个有才华但自命不凡的作家。 2. That young man is extremely pretentious. 那个年轻人非常自命不凡。 3. He imposed his pretentious books on the public. 他把他写的自认为不错的书强行推销给大众。 4. People are so much more pretentious nowadays. 现在的人比以前浮华得多。', '副词: pretentiously 名词: pretentiousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('monsoon', '[ˌmɑːn\'suːn]', 'n.季风；雨季', '1. The ship beat back against a monsoon. 船逆着季风艰难地行驶。 2. The monsoon is an important topic in the scientific research of the atmosphere. 摘要季风作为气象科学的一个重要课题，许多人都作了大量研究。 3. The monsoon will run to the end of the next month. 雨季会持续到下个月底。 4. Travelling is much more difficult during the monsoon. 在雨季出行要难得多。', '形容词: monsoonal');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('feud', '[fjuːd]', 'n.长期不和；争执 n.封地 v.长期斗争；结世仇', '1. The two tribes were long at feud with each other. 这两个部族长期不和。 2. Insults only served to inflame the feud. 侮辱只是起了加剧长期不和的作用。 3. The timing of the transaction raises questions about the status of Mr.Murdoch\'s feud with John C. 交易的时机使人对默多克与自由媒体主席马龙的争执状态产生疑问。 4. The barriers between Europe and Asia set up by the religious feud of Christianity and Islam were lowered. 欧亚之间因基督教和伊斯兰教这种宗教争执而树立的障碍逐步消除。 5. The two families have been at feud with each other. 两个家族之间有世仇。', '过去式: feuded 过去分词: feuded 现在分词: feuding 第三人称单数: feuds');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sod', '[sɑːd]', 'n.(一块)草皮；草地；家伙；困难的事；鸡奸者 v.用草皮覆盖；诅咒', '1. The playground was covered with sod. 操场上覆盖着草皮。 2. He preferred the cleanness and tidiness of the wild sod. 他喜欢荒野草地的清洁和整齐。 3. You stupid sod! 你这个蠢蛋！ 4. The new boss is a mean sod! 新来的上司是个大坏蛋！ 5. Oh, sod it! I\'m not doing any more. 哼，去他妈的！我不干了。', '过去式: sodded 过去分词: sodded 现在分词: sodding 第三人称单数: sods');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('solicit', '[sə\'lɪsɪt]', 'vt.恳求；征求；勾引 vi.(妓女)拉客', '1. We solicit your close cooperation with us in this matter. 我们恳求您对于此一事件能给予协助和合作。 2. We should often solicit opinions from the masses . 我们应该经常征求群众意见。 3. They were planning to solicit funds from a number of organizations. 他们正计划向一些机构募集资金。 4. To solicit a judge means to offer him bribes. 引诱法官就是给予贿胳。 5. She was fined for soliciting. 她因拉客而被罚款。', '名词: solicitation 过去式: solicited 过去分词: solicited 现在分词: soliciting 第三人称单数: solicits');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('commencement', '[kə\'mensmənt]', 'n.开始；毕业典礼', '1. The commencement of articulate speech belongs to this period. 音节分明的语言即开始于这一期。 2. Seeds begin to burgeon at the commencement of spring. 春天来临时种子开始发芽。 3. At commencement, academic degrees are officially given. 在毕业典礼上，学位被正式颁发。 4. The commencement was held in the grand hall. 毕业典礼在豪华的大厅举行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('purse', '[pɜːrs]', 'n.钱包；小钱袋；(获奖)奖金 vt.皱起；放进钱包', '1. When did you first miss your purse? 你什么时候发现丢了钱包的? 2. The loss of her purse caused her much inconvenience. 丢失钱包给她带来了诸多不便。 3. This piece of china is beyond my purse. 这件瓷器我买不起。 4. Her purse was stolen when she was on the bus. 她的手袋在公共汽车上被偷了。 5. The sour taste made her purse her lips. 酸味使她皱起嘴唇。', '形容词: purselike 过去式: pursed 过去分词: pursed 现在分词: pursing 第三人称单数: purses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('myopia', '[maɪ\'oʊpiə]', 'n.近视；缺乏远见', '1. The new contact lenses will correct for his myopia. 这副新隐形眼镜将帮助矫正他的近视。 2. For Lorca,New York is a symbol of spiritual myopia(Edwin Honig). 对洛卡来说，纽约是精神缺乏远见的象征(埃德温·霍尼格)。', '形容词: myopic 副词: myopically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('proficient', '[prə\'fɪʃnt]', 'adj.熟练的；精通的 n.能手', '1. He is proficient in English with customer. 他能熟练运用英语与客人交谈。 2. After reading this book, you will be proficient in writing. 读完这本书，你会精于写作。 3. My friend is proficient in three languages. 我的朋友精通三种语言。 4. She was very proficient in music. 她非常精通音乐。 5. He doesn\'t look like a proficient in golf. 他看起来不像是个打高尔夫球的专家。', '副词: proficiently');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('onerous', '[\'ɑːnərəs]', 'adj.繁重的', '1. Overtime work is often onerous, though it is well paid. 报酬很好，但常常是很繁重的。 2. She desired a fixed occupation-no matter how onerous, how irksome. 她希望有个固定的职业，不管这个职业多么繁重，多么令人厌倦。 3. I\'ve always led an onerous timetable but I like it. 我的日程表总是排得紧紧的，但我喜欢这样。', '副词: onerously 名词: onerousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ebb', '[eb]', 'n.退潮；衰落 vi.落潮；衰退', '1. They started sailing on the ebb. 他们于退潮时出航了。 2. But the moments will never ebb away. 但那些瞬间永远不会退潮。 3. Private and public virtues were at the lowest ebb. 公德与私德均在衰落之中。 4. Manufacturing business is now at a low ebb. 制造业现正处于衰落中。 5. Fishing boats were standing down with the ebb. 渔船趁着落潮出航。', '过去式: ebbed 过去分词: ebbed 现在分词: ebbing 第三人称单数: ebbs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('debonair', '[ˌdebə\'ner]', 'adj.温文尔雅的；无忧无虑的；<古>和蔼亲切的；高兴的', '1. You\'re also charming, debonair and always right. 你还是非常迷人、温文尔雅的，而且总是对的。 2. The headwaiter was debonair with the guests but firm with the waiters. 领班对客人温文有礼,但是对侍者却很强硬。', '副词: debonairly 名词: debonairness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('timbre', '[\'tæmbər]', 'n.音色；音质', '1. I fell in love with the subtly plaintive timbre of the Qiang flute. 我喜欢上了羌笛那略带哀怨的音色。 2. Timbre can be regarded as the ultimate carrier of musical opuses. 音色可以说是诠释和表现作品的最终载体。 3. The willow whistle he made himself has a pleasant timbre. 他自制的柳笛，音质非常好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cyclical', '[\'sɪklɪkl]', 'adj.循环的；周期的', '1. No, gossip is cyclical and karmic, like a boomerang. 不，流言是循环的，是有因果的，就像自食其果。 2. Video gaming is a cyclical industry in which new consoles are launched every five or six years. 视频游戏是以新主机发售开始每五六年为一个循环的工业。 3. In other words, follow cyclical changes in the income of residents of savings and consumption decisions. 换而言之，是跟随经济周期的收入变化决定了居民的储蓄和消费行为。 4. But gaming is a cyclical business, and success in one round does not guarantee success in the next. 但游戏是一个周期性产品，一个周期的成功并不意味着下一个周期也会同样成功。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('frisky', '[\'frɪski]', 'adj.活泼的；快活的；有性要求的', '1. I feel quite frisky this morning. 我今天上午觉得精神挺足。 2. The morning fresh air makes me feel quite frisky. 早晨清新的空气使我感到十分愉快。', '副词: friskily 比较级: friskier 最高级: friskiest 名词: friskiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ingenious', '[ɪn\'dʒiːniəs]', 'adj.机灵的；精巧的；有独创性的', '1. The ingenious boy made a radio set for himself. 这个聪明的男孩自己做了一台收音机。 2. He invented an ingenious excuse for being late. 他为迟到编造了一个巧妙的借口。 3. It was an intricate and ingenious system. 这是一个复杂而精致的体系。 4. I never heard anything more ingenious than your suggestion. 我从来没有听见过象你这样有独创性的提法。', '副词: ingeniously 名词: ingeniousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('subliminal', '[ˌsʌb\'lɪmɪnl]', 'adj.下意识的；潜意识的', '1. These little eye movements may also help expose a person\'s subliminal thoughts. 这种小幅的眼球运动也可能揭露了我们下意识的想法。 2. The soft sell approach gets to consumers in a subliminal way. 软广告通过潜意识的作用来影响消费者。 3. The subliminal data can be from a prerecorded or live signal. 潜意识信息能来自于预先录制的，或者活体信号。', '副词: subliminally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('valedictory', '[ˌvælɪ\'dɪktəri]', 'adj.告别的 n.告别词；告别演说', '1. Children would write valedictory speeches about KP2. 孩子们将会为KP2写段告别词。 2. At graduation the students presented each other with valedictory inscriptions. 毕业时同学们互相题词勉。 3. the student with the best grades who delivers the valedictory at graduation. 在毕业典礼上致告别词的最好级别的学生。 4. The student with the best grades delivered the valedictory at graduation. 最好级别的学生在毕业典礼上致了告别词。', '名词复数: valedictories');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gambol', '[\'ɡæmbl]', 'v.跳跃；雀跃；耍闹 n.跳跃；雀跃；嬉戏', '1. There are many children gamboling around. 那儿有很多嬉戏蹦跳的儿童。 2. He determined to revisit the scene of the last evening\'s gambol. 他决计再到昨晚嬉戏的地方去一趟。', '过去式: gamboled/gambolled 过去分词: gamboled/gambolled 现在分词: gamboling/gambolling 第三人称单数: gambols');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dishearten', '[dɪs\'hɑːrtn]', 'vt.使沮丧；使泄气', '1. Don\'t let the defeat dishearten you. 不要因这一挫折而气馁。 2. The death of her mother disheartened her. 她母亲的死使她失去勇气。', '副词: dishearteningly 名词: disheartenment 过去式: disheartened 过去分词: disheartened 现在分词: disheartening 第三人称单数: disheartens');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scad', '[skæd]', 'n.[鱼]竹荚鱼；许多；大量', '1. This certainly worked, and the first scad to hit the water was inhaled by a very large fish. 这无疑起了作用，第一次打鲹水是一个非常大的鱼吸入。 2. Scads of people are in the hall. 许多人在大厅里。', '名词复数: scad');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('liken', '[\'laɪkən]', 'v.比作；比拟；使像', '1. Someone likens his voice to the croak of a bull-frog. 有人把他的声音比作牛蛙的叫声。 2. Life can be likened to a journey with an unknown destination. 生命可以被比作一次不知目的地的旅行。 3. We often liken the heart to a pump. 我们常把心脏比拟为水泵。', '过去式: likened 过去分词: likened 现在分词: likening 第三人称单数: likens');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('linoleum', '[lɪ\'noʊliəm]', 'n.油布；油毯', '1. He wrapped his son up in a linoleum. 他用油布包着儿子。 2. The acid ate through the linoleum. 酸把漆布腐蚀穿了。 3. Did you know the linoleum had a pattern? 你知不知道那个油布毯是有花纹的？ 4. The only time I was ever scared was on the first floor with the red linoleum. 我唯一一次感到害怕是在铺着红色油毡的一楼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('adlib', '[æd\'lɪb]', 'v.临时穿插；信口说出', '1. Here is a restaurant where you pay fixed price and eat adlib. 这里有一家餐馆，你付一定的钱随便吃。 2. The actress forgot some of her lines and had to adlib. 女演员忘了几句台词，于是只好即兴编凑。 3. I had forgotten to bring my notes and had to speak adlib. 我忘记带讲稿了,只好临时讲几句。 4. AdLib, Inc. is a private, non-profit, community based, consumer controlled, ... mmpp147 mesesoft. net 泰国--娜塔丽雅 Crack top theme a4u A4Y ginny amoi hisap konek ...', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('intent', '[ɪn\'tent]', 'adj.热切的；专心的；决心的 n.意图；目的；意向；含义', '1. He\'s intent on going to Australia. 他热切希望到澳大利亚去。 2. Her intent look showed how much she had missed her sister. 她的专心的目光说明她是多么想念她的姐姐。 3. He\'s intent on moneymaking. 他一心一意地赚钱。 4. She is intent on getting the job done quickly. 她决心尽快把这件事情做好。 5. No one could spy out the intent and meaning of it. 没有人能查出它的意图和意义。', '副词: intently 名词: intentness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('affiliate', '[ə\'fɪlieɪt]', 'n.分公司；附属机构 vt.使隶属于；接纳；追溯 vi.发生联系', '1. It is an affiliate of the Red Cross. 它是红十字会的一个份子。 2. Do I get the product as part of the affiliate program? 我得到的附属产品作为节目? 3. I affiliate myself with their team to get more information on the share market. 我和他们组密切联系以获得更多股票市场的信息。 4. The Committee regrets that it cannot right now affiliate your group to their Society. 那个委员会很抱歉，不能马上将你们的团体并入他们的学会。 5. If we affiliate, we will have a better chance to win. 如果我们加入的话，赢的可能性更大。', '名词: affiliation 过去式: affiliated 过去分词: affiliated 现在分词: affiliating 第三人称单数: affiliates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('apothegm', '[\'æpəˌθem]', 'n.格言', '1. It has been an apothegm these five thousand years, that toil sweetens the bread it earns. “面包是亲手赚来的才好吃”，这句格言恐怕有五千年的历史了。 2. Investment Apothegm: While choosing higher returns, do not neglect the cost of higher investment risks. 投資箴言：在追求高回報的同時，可別忽略了更高的投資風險！ 3. It brings joviality,but is never flighty:it coruscates with increasingly refreshed vitality,and the apothegm of love continues to spread. 它让人心情轻松愉悦，却毫不轻浮，且焕发日益光鲜的生命力，爱的箴言在故事里继续流传。 4. From him, I learn apothegm of the life, you should be straightforward in the world, it is also a basic principle, isn\'t it? 从爸爸那里我学到了人生的箴言：立于人世间直字应当先。这何尝不是基本的道理......', '形容词: apothegmatic 副词: apothegmatically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cultivated', '[\'kʌltɪveɪtɪd]', 'adj.栽植的；有教养的 动词cultivate的过去式和过去分词.', '1. It is a pity to let this cultivated land lie idle. 这些耕地丢荒了，真让人可惜。 2. The cultivated area is being further extended. 耕地正进一步扩大。 3. This lady has always been gentle and cultivated. 这个女人素来温文尔雅。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mobile', '[\'moʊbl]', 'adj.移动的；易变的；活动的 n.<美>汽车；可动雕塑；悬挂饰物；活动物体', '1. Additionally, consumers continue to embrace mobile personal devices. 此外,消费者接受移动个人设备的热情依然不减。 2. He had a mobile, expressive, animated face. 他有一张多变的，富于表情的，生动活泼的脸。 3. He has a broken leg and isn\'t very mobile. 他的腿摔伤了,活动不便。 4. A specially equipped car makes a handicapped person more mobile. 有特殊装置的汽车使得残障者比以前更易于活动。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unstinting', '[ʌn\'stɪntɪŋ]', 'adj.无限制的；慷慨的', '1. Not all observers, however, think that China\'s unstinting appetite for commodities is super. 然而，并不是所有的观察家们都认为中国对资源商品无止境的需求很好。 2. We all appreciate your unstinting help. 我们都感谢你不吝相助。 3. I can\'t speak too highly of the unstinting help I received. 我对我得到的慷慨帮助无论怎样称赞都不会过分。', '副词: unstintingly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('superstition', '[ˌsuːpər\'stɪʃn]', 'n.迷信；没有根据的理论', '1. It\'s a common superstition that black cats are unlucky. 认为黑猫不吉利，这是一种普遍的迷信思想。 2. He holds that ignorance leads to superstition. 他认为无知会导致迷信。 3. That superstition was prevalent among them. 那种迷信在他们之间广为流传。 4. The superstition still lingers on among them. 那种迷信仍然残留在他们的脑海中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('jeer', '[dʒɪr]', 'v.嘲弄；揶揄；奚落 n.嘲笑；讥评', '1. They all jeered at the foolish speaker. 他们都嘲笑那个愚蠢的演说者。 2. He jeered at the defeated opponent. 他揶揄着被击败的对手。 3. He was stabbed to the heart by the girl\'s jeer. 那女孩的嘲讽深深地刺伤了他的心。 4. He ran off,their jeers ringing in his ears. 他一跑了之', '副词: jeeringly 名词: jeerer 过去式: jeered 过去分词: jeered 现在分词: jeering 第三人称单数: jeers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inspection', '[ɪn\'spekʃn]', 'n.视察；检查', '1. He made an inspection of the school. 他视察了这所学校。 2. I gave the radio a thorough inspection before buying it. 我把收音机彻底检查了一遍才买了下来。 3. We aren\'t nearly ready for the inspection. 对检查一事，我们还远未准备好。', '形容词: inspectional');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('taciturn', '[\'tæsɪtɜːrn]', 'adj.沉默寡言的', '1. He didn\'t say anything because he was so taciturn. 他不说一句话,因为他是如此沉默寡言。 2. He was taciturn and unsociable,and rarely spoke to you. 他总是不声不响，冷冰冰的，难得跟你交谈。', '副词: taciturnly 名词: taciturnity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('penultimate', '[pen\'ʌltɪmət]', 'adj.倒数第二的', '1. Y is the penultimate letter of the alphabet. Y是字母表中倒数第二个字母。 2. November is the penultimate month of the year. 十一月份是一年中倒数的第二个月。', '副词: penultimately');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('personage', '[\'pɜːrsənɪdʒ]', 'n.名流；要人；人物；角色', '1. He is fast becoming a personage. 他很快成为名人。 2. Gradually he was becoming quite a personage. 他逐渐变成了一个相当重要的人物。 3. He was a great and historical personage. 他是一位伟大的历史人物。 4. He played the personage of Hamlet in the play. 他在这个剧中扮演哈姆雷特。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('Byzantine', '[\'bɪzəntiːn]', 'adj.拜占庭的；拜占庭式建筑风格的；错综复杂的；暗中的 n.拜占庭人', '1. The chief sources for the Greek mathematical works are Byzantine Greek codices. 希腊的数学著作主要取材于拜占庭的希腊文手抄本。 2. That is a bill to simplify the Byzantine tax structure. 那是一项简化错综复杂的财税结构的议案。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('peninsula', '[pə\'nɪnsələ]', 'n.半岛', '1. His house is located on the tip of the peninsula. 他的房子位于半岛的顶端。 2. Leizhou Peninsula lies opposite Hainan Island. 雷州半岛正对着海南岛。', '形容词: peninsular');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('communicate', '[kə\'mjuːnɪkeɪt]', 'v.传达；沟通；交流', '1. He has communicated his wishes to me. 他已经把他的愿望告诉了我。 2. I like to communicate with my family. 我喜欢和我的家人沟通。 3. The door communicates with my room. 这门和我的房间相通。 4. Good manners are not only about the way we talk, but also about all other things we do when we communicate with other people. 好的礼节不仅仅是指我们谈话的方式,还包括我们在与别人交流时进行各种活动的处理办法与态度。', '名词: communicator 过去式: communicated 过去分词: communicated 现在分词: communicating 第三人称单数: communicates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('split', '[splɪt]', 'v.分裂；将…分成若干部分；分摊；分离；劈开；裂开；<俚>离开 n.劈开；裂口；分裂；一份；水果冰淇淋 adj.分裂的；意见分歧的', '1. The party split into petty factions. 该党分裂成若干小派系。 2. The vote split the Labour Party. 那场选举使工党分裂了。 3. She split the class into groups of four. 她按四人一组把全班分成若干小组。 4. The arrow just split the apple in half. 箭把苹果分成两半。 5. Frost caused the split in the rock. 霜冻使岩石裂了一条缝。 6. They believe the killer has a split personality. 他们认为这个凶手人格分裂。', '名词: splitter 过去式: split 过去分词: split 现在分词: splitting 第三人称单数: splits');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('apocalyptic', '[əˌpɑːkə\'lɪptɪk]', 'adj.预示灾祸的；启示的；(使人想到) 世界末日的', '1. He \"hates being apocalyptic\" but says his grandchildren will have to choose how to minimise their exposure to the risks. 他\"不喜欢预言灾难\" 2. Parts of the ocean there look just absolutely apocalyptic. 海洋的很多区域看上去完全像是世界末日。', '副词: apocalyptically 异体字: apocalyptical');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('devour', '[dɪ\'vaʊər]', 'v.吞食；毁灭；贪婪地阅读', '1. He sat by the fire, devouring beef and onions. 他坐在火炉旁，狼吞虎咽地吃着牛肉和洋葱。 2. We watched the flames devour the entire building. 我们看着火苗吞噬整座大楼。 3. The child devours fairy tales. 这孩子专注地听着童话故事。', '副词: devouringly 名词: devourer 过去式: devoured 过去分词: devoured 现在分词: devouring 第三人称单数: devours');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('limousine', '[\'lɪməziːn]', 'n.豪华轿车', '1. She has a chauffeur-driven limousine. 她有一辆由私人司机开的豪华轿车。 2. The women cackled when they saw the movie star step out of the limousine. 当看见那位明星从豪华轿车里走出来时，那些妇女们议论纷纷，并发出咯咯地笑声。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('proverbially', '[prə\'vɜːbiəli]', 'adv.无人不知地；谚语地', '1. The woman is proverbially stupid. 这个女人是出名的愚蠢。 2. Taking the first step proverbially costs the most. 常言道，万事开头难。 3. Why, medicine is proverbially nasty. 药当然难吃啰。 4. The proverbially dour New EnglandPuritan. 一个抑郁的新英格兰清教徒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('disgust', '[dɪs\'ɡʌst]', 'n.厌恶；憎恶；反感 vt.使厌恶；使作呕', '1. She turned away in disgust. 她厌恶地转过脸去。 2. His behavior filled her with disgust. 她对他的行为充满了厌恶。 3. He returned downstairs in disgust. 他厌恶地转身下楼。 4. I can only feel disgust for these criminals. 对这些罪犯我只感到憎恶。 5. His ideas disgust me; they are terrible. 他的一些想法使我很反感，它们实在是太可怕了。', '过去式: disgusted 过去分词: disgusted 现在分词: disgusting 第三人称单数: disgusts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('injurious', '[ɪn\'dʒʊrəriəs]', 'adj.有害的；中伤的', '1. Smoking is injurious to health. 吸烟对健康有害。 2. All sediment deposition is not injurious . 并不是所有的泥沙淤积都是有害的。 3. His behavior is injurious to the interests of the vast majority of people. 他的行为有损于大多数人民的利益。', '副词: injuriously 名词: injuriousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('careen', '[kə\'riːn]', 'vi.(船)倾斜；猛冲 vt.使倾斜', '1. Their ship was put into port to careen and refit. 他们的轮船被送入港口倾侧待修。 2. The driver lost control and the car careened down the hill. 因司机失控，那辆汽车就横冲直撞地冲下山去。 3. They careened the fishing boat to repaint the hull. 他们将渔船倾斜过来重新油漆船体。', '名词: careener 过去式: careened 过去分词: careened 现在分词: careening 第三人称单数: careens');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('auditorium', '[ˌɔːdɪ\'tɔːriəm]', 'n.礼堂；观众席', '1. The auditorium seats 3,000 people. 这个礼堂可坐三千人。 2. The stage is thrust forward into the auditorium. 舞台向前突出，伸入观众席。 3. The competition hasn\'t begun, but you can already hear the hubbub from the auditorium. 比赛还没开始，观众席上已经人声鼎沸了。', '名词复数: auditoriums');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('seismic', '[\'saɪzmɪk]', 'adj.地震的', '1. Most materials have different seismic properties. 大多数物质都具有不同的地震的特性。 2. This earthquake measured 7 according to the seismic survey. 经测定，这次地震的烈度为七级。', '副词: seismically 名词: seismicity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pendulous', '[\'pendʒələs]', 'adj.下垂的；摇摆的；摇摆不定的', '1. The dewlap should not be pendulous and excessive. 喉部不应该下垂或过于夸张。 2. The muzzle should be deep without pendulous flews. 口的末端呈正方形而平。 3. Pose of a kind of pendulous is advocating the beauty of asymmetry, even if costar. 有一种摇摆的姿势倡导着不对称的美，即使是配角。', '副词: pendulously 名词: pendulousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('slew', '[sluː]', 'n.沼地；回转；许多 v.转向 动词slay的过去式.', '1. He faced a whole slew of problems. 他面临了一大堆的问题。 2. This year has seen a whole slew of novels set in Hong Kong. 今年出现了许多以香港为背景的小说。 3. The car slewed round on the icy road. 车在结冰的路上打滑了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pyromania', '[ˌpaɪroʊ\'meɪniə]', 'n.纵火狂', '1. Results Most of pyromania with mental disorder were male youth. 方法分析44例精神障碍者的纵火行为。 2. The Fourth of July domestic culinary pyromania is followed by community pyrotechnics. 七月四日，人们在家里食完人间烟火，接下去就是社区的烟花会。 3. Let us discuss, first, five of the most common manias: kleptomania, pyromania, dipsomania, megalomania, and monomania . 首先让我们讨论五种最常见的狂热症：盗窃狂症，纵火狂症，耽酒狂症，妄想自大狂症，偏执狂症。 4. Methods The individual information, psychogenic data of 44 pyromania with mental disorder were analysed. 方法分析44例精神障碍者的纵火行为。', '形容词: pyromaniac');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('guilt', '[ɡɪlt]', 'n.罪行；内疚', '1. We now have the absolute proof of his guilt. 我们现在有他犯罪的确凿证据。 2. The king was infamous for his guilt of many infamies. 那个国王因罪恶多端而臭名昭著。 3. His friend corroborated his guilt. 他的朋友证实了他的犯罪。 4. The law presumes innocence until guilt is proved. 在罪状未证实前，法律假定被告无罪。', '形容词: guilty 副词: guiltily');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('walrus', '[\'wɔːlrəs]', 'n.海象', '1. He seemed hardly to notice the big walrus. 他几乎没有注意到那只大海象。', '名词复数: walrus');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('groove', '[ɡruːv]', 'n.槽；纹；习惯 v.开槽；使 ... 快活', '1. Wheels leave grooves in dirt roads. 车轮在泥路上留下凹痕。 2. Sliding doors and windows move in groove. 滑动门和滑动窗都在凹槽中移动。 3. The needle moves along the groove on a record. 唱针沿着唱片表面的细纹移动。 4. It\'s time to get out of the groove here. 该是摆脱这种枯燥乏味的生活方式的时候了。 5. The sink shelf is grooved so that the water will run off. 洗涤池上开槽是为了让水流走。', '过去式: grooved 过去分词: grooved 现在分词: grooving 第三人称单数: grooves');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('trustworthy', '[\'trʌstwɜːrði]', 'adj.可信赖的', '1. Facts have shown us that he is trustworthy. 事实已经向我们表明他是可信赖的。 2. I hope he is a trustworthy person , also he has humor and likes outdoor activities. 我希望他是一个可信赖的人，同样是有幽默感的，喜欢户外活动。', '副词: trustworthily 比较级: trustworthier 最高级: trustworthiest 名词: trustworthiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('entice', '[ɪn\'taɪs]', 'v.诱使；引诱', '1. The promise of higher pay enticed me into the new job. 高薪诱使我从事了这个新工作。 2. Nothing will entice the children from television. 没有任何东西能把孩子们从电视机前诱开。 3. The boy was enticed into playing truant. 这个男孩被引诱逃学。', '副词: enticingly 名词: enticement 过去式: enticed 过去分词: enticed 现在分词: enticing 第三人称单数: entices');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pathogen', '[\'pæθədʒən]', 'n.病原体', '1. The opposite end latches onto the pathogen. 相对的一端锁在病原体上。 2. Clostridium difficile is a gram-positive enteric pathogen. 摘要难辨梭状芽孢杆菌是一种革兰阳性肠道病原体。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('prop', '[prɑːp]', 'n.支柱；支持者；倚靠人 n.道具 n.螺旋桨；推进器 v.支撑；维持', '1. The roof of the tunnel was supported by wooden props. 坑道顶用木柱支撑。 2. Mr. Helton was the hope and the prop of the family. 希尔顿先生成了一家的希望和支柱。 3. He was for several years the main prop and animator of Roosevelt himself. 他有几年是罗斯福本人的主要支持者和鼓舞者。 4. Her daughter was the only prop to the old lady during her illness. 她女儿是老太太病中唯一的依靠。 5. We will now add a prop model with physics properties. 我们现在添加有物理性的道具模型。 6. The wooden prop makes the machine look outdated. 木制螺旋桨的机器看起来过时了。 7. He propped his bicycle up against the fence. 他把脚踏车靠在篱笆上。', '过去式: propped 过去分词: propped 现在分词: propping 第三人称单数: props');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('slit', '[slɪt]', 'n.裂缝；狭长的切口 vt.切开；撕裂；使成狭缝', '1. A slit skirt revealed shapely legs. 开叉的裙子暴露出匀称的腿。 2. I could see them through the slit in the curtains. 我通过窗帘的裂缝可以看到他们。 3. Her skirt has a long slit. 她的裙子上有个细长的开口。 4. A slit is provided for the coin to drop through. 狭长的口子是供投硬币用的。 5. Slit the roll with a sharp knife. 用快刀把面包卷切开。', '形容词: slitty 名词: slitter 过去式: slit 过去分词: slit 现在分词: slitting 第三人称单数: slits');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('predominant', '[prɪ\'dɑːmɪnənt]', 'adj.主要的；占优势的；显著的', '1. The predominant feature of his character was pride. 他的性格中主要的特点是骄傲。 2. Identify any predominant architectural approaches. 明确主要的体系结构方法。 3. It is the land which makes the predominant contribution. 土地为我们作出了最显著的贡献。 4. It has been suggested that most individuals harbour one predominant dermoscopic type among their naevi. 大多数患者的痣都有一个显著的皮肤镜表现型。', '副词: predominantly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('disclaim', '[dɪs\'kleɪm]', 'v.放弃；否认；弃权；拒绝', '1. She disclaimed ownership of the vehicle. 她放弃了这辆车的所有权。 2. The gang disclaimed all responsibility for the explosion. 这个匪帮否认与这次爆炸事件有关系。', '过去式: disclaimed 过去分词: disclaimed 现在分词: disclaiming 第三人称单数: disclaims');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('idol', '[\'aɪdl]', 'n.偶像 n.菩萨', '1. The pop singer is the idol of young people. 这位流行歌手成为年轻人崇拜的偶像。 2. The youngsters greeted their idol with a hail. 那群年轻人向他们的偶像欢呼致敬。 3. Don\'t make an idol of money. 不要崇拜财富。 4. The set includes a golden fertility idol pen holder, an Ark of the Convenant business card holder and a Holy Grail paperclip holder. 该套桌饰包括一个催子菩萨形状的金色笔筒，一个方舟形状的合同名片夹和一个圣杯形状的回形针收集器。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('secrete', '[sɪ\'kriːt]', 'vt.隐藏；隐匿 vt.分泌', '1. He found the money secreted in a drawer. 他找到了藏在抽屉里的钱。 2. Squirrels secrete a supply of nuts for winter. 松鼠为准备过冬而藏坚果。 3. He secreted himself to avoid being caught. 他为了躲避追捕，隐匿起来了。 4. The kidneys secrete urine. 肾脏是分泌尿液的器官。', '过去式: secreted 过去分词: secreted 现在分词: secreting 第三人称单数: secretes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hyperactivity', '[ˌhaɪpəræk\'tɪvəti]', 'n.活动过度；极度活跃', '1. Since Mr Sarkozy is known for his hyperactivity, nobody doubts that he will move fast. 既然萨尔科齐先生因极度活跃而众所周知，没有人怀疑他会很快有所动作。 2. Given the effects of cocaine on people, hyperactivity may seem like a fairly obvious reaction. 我们已经知道，人若是服用了可卡因，最明显的表现可能是极度活跃。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('grant', '[ɡrænt]', 'v.授予；同意；承认；认为 n.授予物；补助金；同意；给予；财产转让 Grant. n.格兰特(男名)', '1. Visa exemption does not grant the right to work. 豁免签证并不授予工作的权利。 2. We grant the truth of what you said. 我们同意你说的是事实。 3. I grant that your explanation is reasonable. 我承认你的解释是合理的。 4. I take it for granted you have read this book. 我认为你一定读过这本书。', '形容词: grantable 名词: granter 过去式: granted 过去分词: granted 现在分词: granting 第三人称单数: grants');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('abolish', '[ə\'bɑːlɪʃ]', 'vt.废除；革除；消灭', '1. Abraham Lincoln abolished slavery in the United States. 亚伯拉罕·林肯在美国废除了奴隶制。 2. There are many bad customs and laws that ought to be abolished. 有许多不良的习俗和法规应予以废除。 3. They petitioned the government to abolish hanging. 他们向政府请愿，要求废除绞刑。 4. The legislature passed a law to abolish the surtax. 立法机关通过了一项废除附加税的法令。', '形容词: abolishable 名词: abolisher 过去式: abolished 过去分词: abolished 现在分词: abolishing 第三人称单数: abolishes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('expediency', '[ɪk\'spiːdiənsi]', 'n.权宜；方便；私利', '1. All his actions are governed by expediency. 他所有的行动都是一种权宜之计。 2. An ambitious politician was guided by expediency rather than principle. 一个有野心的政客常为私利而不是原则来指导。', '名词复数: expediencies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('verve', '[vɜːrv]', 'n.活力；热忱；神韵；特殊才能', '1. It was a performance of verve and vitality. 这是一场充满激情与活力的演出。 2. It is moreover a book of astonoshing wit and verve. 这还是一本充满惊人的机智和活力的小说。 3. He was almost fizzing with combat verve. 投入战斗的急切心情几乎叫他达到了兴奋的状态。 4. Your impudent look reflects my verve when I was young. 你轻率的样子很有我当年的神韵。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sibling', '[\'sɪblɪŋ]', 'n.兄弟姐妹', '1. He felt inferior to his older sibling. 他感到比他的兄妹们低一等。 2. I have two brothers and a sister: three siblings in all. 我有两个哥哥和一个妹妹: 共有三个兄妹。 3. A sibling or spouse may fulfill this role. 兄弟姐妹或配偶能担当这个角色。 4. Many of us hate living in the shadows of a more successful sibling. 我们很多人都讨厌活在更为成功的手足的阴影下。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fatigue', '[fə\'tiːɡ]', 'n.疲劳；疲乏；劳务杂役 v.（使）疲劳 adj.疲劳的', '1. She hoped to sleep off her fatigue. 她希望睡一觉之后会消除疲劳。 2. The aeroplane wing showed signs of metal fatigue. 机翼显出有金属疲劳的现象。 3. He was beaten out with fatigue when he got home. 他回到家里时已是疲惫不堪。 4. Who is on fatigue duty today? 今天谁担任杂役? 5. The patient fatigues easily. 病人容易疲劳。 6. They were shedding their fatigue. 身上疲劳的感觉渐渐都消失了。', '过去式: fatigued 过去分词: fatigued 现在分词: fatiguing 第三人称单数: fatigues');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('filter', '[\'fɪltər]', 'n.过滤器；滤色镜；滤光器 v.过滤；渗透', '1. We usually clear the water with a filter. 我们通常用过滤器使水净化。 2. You can also filter to focus on specific areas. 你也可以设置过滤器来只关注一些特定的区域。 3. Filter selection is made using inherent spectra. 滤色镜的选择必须利用固有光谱。 4. A yellow filter is placed in front of the camera lens to assure that no blue light will be imaged. 为了不使蓝光进入相机而成像，可在相机的透镜前加一黄滤色镜。 5. It won\'t take long to filter the coffee. 用不了多少时间就可以把咖啡过滤好。', '形容词: filterless 名词: filterer 过去式: filtered 过去分词: filtered 现在分词: filtering 第三人称单数: filters');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('grill', '[ɡrɪl]', 'n.烤架；铁格子；烧烤(食物) vt.拷问；(在烤架上)烤', '1. We have to clean the grill before we start a fire. 在生火前我们必须把烤架清理干净。 2. Put the hamburgers on the grill. 把汉堡牛排放到烤架上。 3. There is no grill in Room Service. 客房服务部不卖烧烤的食品。 4. He spent the summer bussing tables in a downtown grill. 整个夏季，他都在城里一个烧烤店帮助清理餐桌。 5. Had he asked any friends to grill him in a mock interview? 他可曾请朋友向他提问，对他进行模拟面试?', '名词: griller 过去式: grilled 过去分词: grilled 现在分词: grilling 第三人称单数: grills');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('astringent', '[ə\'strɪndʒənt]', 'adj.收敛性的；止血的；严酷的；涩味的 n.收敛剂；止血药', '1. It has an astringent effect. 这个有止血的作用。 2. The movie was originally conceived by Wilder as an astringent satire on Hollywood. 这部电影最初是由怀尔德构想，作为对好莱坞严厉的讽刺作品。 3. The fruit has a tart and astringent flavour. 这个水果有一种酸涩的味道。 4. You can use astringent to make your skin less oily. 你可以使用收敛剂让皮肤少出油。', '副词: astringently 名词: astringency');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('caprice', '[kə\'priːs]', 'n.反复无常；任性；异想天开', '1. A hailstorm in July is a caprice of nature. 七月天的一场冰雹是大自然的反复无常的变化。 2. Her refusal to go to the party is a mere caprice. 她拒绝参加宴会完全是无理由的突发之举。 3. Soryy! Please,forgive me for caprice! 对不起！请原谅我的任性！ 4. Caprice makes a woman beautiful. 女人任性就是美。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('eligible', '[\'elɪdʒəbl]', 'adj.有资格的；合适的', '1. Mary is not eligible for an award. 玛丽没有申请助学金的资格。 2. Anyone over the age of 18 is eligible to vote. 任何年满18岁的人都有资格投票。 3. I know an eligible young lady who would be an excellent cooperator for you. 我认识一个合适的年青女士,她能成为你最称心如意的合作者。', '副词: eligibly 名词: eligibility');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bile', '[baɪl]', 'n.胆汁；坏脾气；愤怒', '1. The secretion of bile is useful for our bodies. 胆汁的分泌对我们的身体很有用处。 2. Bile helps the body break down fat in food. 胆汁帮助人体分解食物中的脂肪。 3. It rouses my bile to see him. 我一看见他就会生气。 4. It\'s difficult talking to him these days; he seems full of bile since his wife left him. 最后同他说话很难，自从他妻众离他而去之后，他似乎总是怒气冲天。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hammer', '[\'hæmər]', 'n.锤；榔头 vi.锤击；反复敲打 vt.锤打；严厉批评', '1. He hit the nail into the wall with a hammer. 他用一把锤子把钉子打进墙里去。 2. He smashed a hole in the window with a hammer. 他用锤子在玻璃上打了个洞。 3. He took a hammer and recessed a hole into the wall. 他拿起一个榔头，在墙上敲出一个洞。 4. He dashed into the porch and began to hammer on the door. 他冲上门廊用力捶起门来。 5. The police hammered the door. 警察不停地敲门。', '名词: hammerer 过去式: hammered 过去分词: hammered 现在分词: hammering 第三人称单数: hammers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('retch', '[retʃ]', 'v.作呕；反胃', '1. The strange smell made me retch. 这种怪味闻的我直干哕。 2. The stomach is afflictive recently, still often retch! What drug to take? 最近胃难受，还经常干呕！吃什么药？ 3. The sunlight was too bright and the cabin too smelly - anything could make me retch. 阳光太刺眼，舱内气味太难闻——任何一样东西都让我恶心。 4. The first sip made him want to retch and he kept the liquid in his mouth for some time before finally forcing himself to swallow it. 呷了口汤,觉得恶心,在口中含了半天,勉强的咽下去。', '过去式: retched 过去分词: retched 现在分词: retching 第三人称单数: retches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scab', '[skæb]', 'n.痂；疥癣；破坏罢工者；[俚]无赖 v.结疤；破坏罢工', '1. It is as if grief is the scab that permits healing. 悲伤好象是帮助愈合的结痂。 2. When you cut yourself, blood clots and forms a scab. 当你弄伤了自己,血会凝固、结痂。 3. Still, should the scab of the sheep cause the shepherd to recoil? 可是羔羊的疥癣应当使牧羊人却步吗? 4. The scab looked out for the workers at the demonstration. 那工贼监视着示威游行的工人们。 5. The cut began to scab. 伤口开始结痂了。', '过去式: scabbed 过去分词: scabbed 现在分词: scabbing 第三人称单数: scabs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fragrance', '[\'freɪɡrəns]', 'n.香味', '1. This tiny flower gives forth a pleasant fragrance. 这种小花散发出一种令人愉快的香味。 2. The flowers send forth special fragrance. 这些花散发出特别的香味。 3. Lavender has a delicate fragrance. 薰衣草有淡淡的香味。 4. The girl held the flower to her face and the inhalation of its fragrance made her happy. 女孩将花拿到面前闻了一下,花香使她高兴。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('subsume', '[səb\'suːm]', 'v.归入；纳入；包含；包括', '1. This creature can be subsumed in the class of reptiles. 这种生物可以归入爬行动物一类。 2. The new treaty subsumes all past agreements. 新协议包含了所有过往的契约。', '形容词: subsumable 过去式: subsumed 过去分词: subsumed 现在分词: subsuming 第三人称单数: subsumes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gesture', '[\'dʒestʃər]', 'n.手势；姿势 v.作手势表达', '1. Japanese don\'t use as much gesture as Europeans. 日本人使用手势没有欧美人那样多。 2. The children were diverted with his funny gesture. 他那滑稽的手势使孩子们很开心。 3. He put his arm round her in a protective gesture. 他用一只手臂围住她做出保护的姿势。 4. He raised his hands in a gesture of despair. 他举起双手做出绝望的姿势。 5. The doctor gestured me to take off my coat. 医生做手势要我脱去外套。', '形容词: gestural 副词: gesturally 名词: gesturer 过去式: gestured 过去分词: gestured 现在分词: gesturing 第三人称单数: gestures');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cord', '[kɔːrd]', 'n.细绳；索；纽带', '1. He tied the package with a cord. 他用绳子把包裹扎紧。 2. The dancer could kick over a cord four feet from the ground. 这位舞蹈家能把脚举到离地4英尺的绳索上面。 3. His mouth was taped, his hands and feet bound with curtain cord. 他的嘴上粘着胶布，手脚给窗帘拉索捆着。 4. Cindy and her fiance think of their letter as cord of love. 辛迪和她未婚夫把他俩的来往书信看作爱情的纽带。', '名词: corder 过去式: corded 过去分词: corded 现在分词: cording 第三人称单数: cords');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wily', '[\'waɪli]', 'adj.狡猾的', '1. Foxes are supposed to be wily creatures. 据说狐狸是狡猾的动物。 2. We must eat our fruit from the wily serpent\'s jaws. 我们必须从那条狡猾的蛇的嘴巴里去抢食果实。', '副词: wilily 比较级: wilier 最高级: wiliest 名词: wiliness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('acclimate', '[\'ækləmeɪt]', 'v.使习惯于新环境', '1. May you acclimate to the new environmant soon. 我希望你能很快适应这种新环境。 2. How much time does she need to acclimate? 需要多少时间才能适应? 3. Jim have become acclimate to this weather since he move here. 吉姆搬到这里后，他已适应这里的天气。 4. Several things can be done to help the snake acclimate. 可以通过几件事帮助这些蛇去适应新环境。', '过去式: acclimated 过去分词: acclimated 现在分词: acclimating 第三人称单数: acclimates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('phoenix', '[\'fiːnɪks]', 'n.凤凰；不死鸟', '1. The phoenix is a nonexistent bird. 凤凰其实并不存在。 2. Phoenix,like dragon, is the totem of the Chinese people. 凤鸟同龙一样，是中国古代民族的图腾。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gustatory', '[\'gʌstəˌtoʊrɪ]', 'adj.味觉的', '1. Methodology.Initiating method to gustatory activity. 标准/规范英文名： Sensory analysis. 2. The open-plan kitchen brings you both gustatory and visual pleasure. 开放式厨房让您享受味觉和视觉的双重盛宴。 3. The bacterial protein in wastewater of gustatory production is the material of high-protein feed. 味精生产废水中存在的菌体蛋白是市场畅销的饲料蛋白之一。 4. Transversus linguae of lingual muscles are more developed.The gustatory glands are seen in radix linguae. 舌肌的横纹肌发达，味腺只见于舌根部。', '副词: gustatorily 异体字: gustative');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('proliferate', '[prə\'lɪfəreɪt]', 'v.繁殖；增生；使 ... 激增；使 ... 扩散', '1. Microbes proliferate rapidly. 微生物繁殖迅速。 2. Health food shops proliferate in this region. 保健食品店在这个地区增加了。 3. Fantasies proliferate where facts are few. 事实缺乏则幻想增多。 4. Dishonest vendors proliferate, forcing true entrepreneurs out of the industry. 无信用的小商贩激增,将好企业从行业中驱赶出来。', '形容词: proliferative 名词: proliferation 过去式: proliferated 过去分词: proliferated 现在分词: proliferating 第三人称单数: proliferates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('deputize', '[\'depjutaɪz]', 'v.代理；代表', '1. He will deputize for the foreign minister. 他将代理外交部长。 2. Dr Mitchell\'s ill so I\'m deputizing (for her). 米切尔博士病了，所以我做代理(她的)工作。 3. Ms Green has asked me to deputize for her at the meeting. 格林女士请我代表她出席会议。 4. There is a dearth of princes who could deputize for the sovereign. 缺少能代表君主的王子。', '名词: deputization 过去式: deputized 过去分词: deputized 现在分词: deputizing 第三人称单数: deputizes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('jesting', '[\'dʒestɪŋ]', 'adj.滑稽的；好笑的 动词jest的现在分词形式.', '1. One given to jesting. 爱开玩笑的人 2. Stop jesting and be serious for a moment! 别开玩笑了，严肃一会儿吧！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dampen', '[\'dæmpən]', 'v.(使)潮湿；使沮丧；抑制', '1. Please dampen that sponge for me. 请把那海绵弄湿了给我。 2. The camp supplies dampened during the long rainy season. 营地补给品在漫长的雨季里变潮湿了。 3. The bad news dampened our spirits. 这恶耗使得我们精神沮丧。 4. Nothing can dampen my spirit and darken my life. 没有什么能使我沮丧，使我生活暗淡。', '名词: dampener 过去式: dampened 过去分词: dampened 现在分词: dampening 第三人称单数: dampens');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('awl', '[ɔːl]', 'n.锥子；尖钻', '1. He works with a file, a chisel, and an awl. 他工作起来又用锉刀，又用凿子，又用锥子。 2. I accidentally broke the upper end of the awl. 我一不小心把这个锥桯子折断了。 3. \"But of course,\" the captain said. \"To begin with, I use an awl.\" “好吧，”上尉说道，“首先，我用的工具是钻子。”', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nonflammable', '[ˌnɒn\'flæməbəl]', 'adj.不燃烧的', '1. Although nonflammable, oxygen is a strong oxidizer. 尽管不可燃，氧是一种强氧化剂。 2. Nonflammable, thus safe and convenient for use. 本品属非易燃品，操作安全，使用方便。 3. Now, many wooden floors are nonflammable. 现在许多的木地板都具有阻燃这个功能。 4. Product is nonflammable and does not support combustion. 该产品为不可燃物不支持燃烧.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('conclave', '[\'kɑːŋkleɪv]', 'n.秘密会议；教皇选举会议；红衣主教团', '1. A conclave of cardinals was held to elect the new Pope. 枢机主教团举行了秘密会议来选举新教皇。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('prophecy', '[\'prɑːfəsi]', 'n.预言 =prophesy.', '1. He seemed to have the gift of prophecy. 他似乎有预言的天赋. 2. No prophecy can be expected to go on all fours. 凡预言皆不能指望其完全应验。', '名词复数: prophecies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wrath', '[ræθ]', 'n.愤怒；激怒', '1. The mother allayed her son\'s wrath. 母亲平息了他儿子的愤怒。 2. Envy and wrath shorten the life. 嫉妒和愤怒会缩短生命。 3. A gentle answer turns away wrath, but a harsh word stirs up anger. 和善的回答能驱散愤怒,但是粗鲁的话语却能激起怒火。 4. The wrath of the people is now aroused. 人们被激怒了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hunch', '[hʌntʃ]', 'n.预感；块；肉峰 v.弯腰驼背', '1. He always follows his hunch. 他总是凭直觉行事。 2. I have a hunch that it will snow soon. 我有快要下雪的预感。 3. My hunch is that PR is merely a counterweight to the media\'s strong, commercially driven appetite for bad news. 我的感觉是，公关只是一个平衡块，平衡媒体由商业利益驱动的对负面新闻的贪欲。 4. Stand straight, don\'t hunch your shoulders! 站直了, 别耸肩!', '过去式: hunched 过去分词: hunched 现在分词: hunching 第三人称单数: hunches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cajole', '[kə\'dʒoʊl]', 'v.(以甜言蜜语)哄骗', '1. It is difficult to cajole him into consent. 骗取他的同意很难。 2. How can we cajole his father out of punishing him? 我们怎样才能说服他的父亲不惩罚他呢? 3. They tried to cajole their daughter out of marrying him. 他们试图用甜言蜜语诱使女儿打消跟他结婚的念头。', '副词: cajolingly 名词: cajoler 过去式: cajoled 过去分词: cajoled 现在分词: cajoling 第三人称单数: cajoles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('suggestive', '[sə\'dʒestɪv]', 'adj.提示性的；影射的；暗示的；挑逗性的', '1. The treatment given here is suggestive rather than thorough. 这里所给出的论述是提示性的而不是完整的。 2. His behavior was suggestive of a cultured man. 他的举止暗示他是一个有教养的人。 3. He gave her a suggestive glance. 他用挑逗的目光看了她一眼。', '副词: suggestively 名词: suggestiveness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stealth', '[stelθ]', 'n.秘密行动；鬼祟；隐形飞机；隐蔽性', '1. She prefers to do good by stealth. 她喜欢秘密地为他人做好事。 2. Without a family to depend on, they hunt alone, slinking through the shadows, surviving on stealth and intelligence. 因此没有家庭可以依赖，他们只能独自狩猎，潜行阴暗处，靠著的是鬼祟以及智取才能生存下来。 3. The burglars had entered the house by stealth. 窃贼偷偷进入那所房子。 4. The stealth bomber made its maiden flight in 1989. 那架隐形轰炸机在1989年完成它的处女飞行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('outspoken', '[aʊt\'spoʊkən]', 'adj.直言无讳的；坦率的 动词outspeak的过去分词.', '1. He is an outspoken critic of the government. 他是一个直言批评政府的人。 2. His outspoken remarks made him an easy target for the opposition. 他那番直言不讳的言语使他成了反对派的主要抨击对象。 3. Uncle Frank is an outspoken man. 弗朗克叔叔是个坦率的人。 4. My boss is an outspoken critic of my ideas. 我的上司总是对我的想法进行坦率的评论。', '副词: outspokenly 名词: outspokenness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('screen', '[skriːn]', 'n.屏幕；银幕；隔板；屏风；掩蔽物；纱窗；纱门；筛子 v.掩蔽；包庇；放映；筛；检查', '1. The advertisement is full of the TV screen today. 今天，电视屏幕被广告占据。 2. Buzz suddenly appeared on my computer screen. 巴兹突然出现在我的电脑屏幕上。 3. Familiar scenes were imaged on the screen. 银幕上映出了熟悉的景象。 4. Someday I will be a star on the big screen. 有一天我将成为大银幕上的明星。 5. The curtains screen out the sunlight. 窗帘遮住了阳光。', '形容词: screenable 名词: screener 过去式: screened 过去分词: screened 现在分词: screening 第三人称单数: screens');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('recollection', '[ˌrekə\'lekʃn]', 'n.回忆；记忆力；记忆；回忆起的事物', '1. I have no recollection at all of my childhood. 我完全记不起我的儿童时代了。 2. They have not been here within my recollection. 我记得他们从未到过这里。 3. His recollection of the campaign is not too clear. 他对竞选的记忆不是那么清楚。 4. That evening together is one of my happiest recollections. 我们一起欢度的那个晚上是我最快乐的事情之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wastrel', '[\'weɪstrəl]', 'n.挥霍无度的人；败家子；流浪汉；浪荡子', '1. He is a notorious wastrel in our company. 他在我们公司是个有名的饭桶,什麽事都做不好。 2. His neighbour denounce him as a wastrel who had dissipated his inheritance. 他的邻居谴责他是个败家子，把遗产都挥霍光了。 3. Seryozhka in himself is a nonentity, a sluggard, a drunkard, and a wastrel, but when he has his red lead or compasses in his hand he is at once something higher, a servant of God. 谢辽日卡本人是个微不足道的人，懒汉，酒鬼，手里一有钱就花光，然而一旦他手里拿着铅丹或者两脚规，他就成了个高尚的人物，上帝的仆人了。 4. Based on sorts of reasons,the it is suggested that the wastrel with half-year outflowing should... 鉴于多种原因,应当确立流浪半年以内的流浪儿童为分类救助的重点。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('despotism', '[\'despətɪzəm]', 'n.独裁；专制；暴政；专制政府', '1. A large proportion of the best citizen hate his despotism. 一大部分最好的公民都痛恨他的专制君主统治。 2. The despotism was toppled. 暴政被推翻了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ploy', '[plɔɪ]', 'n.策略；手段', '1. The Iraqi regime has used diplomacy as a ploy to gain time and advantage. 伊拉克政权一直利用外交作为争取时间和优势的策略。 2. His ploy is to pretend to be ill. 他的手法就是装病。 3. This is a ploy to gain publicity for his new book. 这是为他的新作求名的手段。 4. It is all a ploy to distract attention from his real aim. 那纯粹是障眼法，用以分散人们对他真正意图的注意力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('caste', '[kæst]', 'n.印度的世袭阶级；(排他的)社会团体；种姓；等级制度', '1. Long had been in the process of the caste system which still exists today. 印度长久以来的世袭阶级今天仍然存在。 2. He came from the highest Hindu caste. 他出身印度最高的种姓。 3. The caste system is still strong in India. 种姓制度在印度仍然很牢固。 4. I suppose you also have a caste system in your society. 我想你们的社会里也有一种等级制度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ancillary', '[\'ænsəleri]', 'adj.辅助的；附属的 n.助手；辅助设备', '1. The transport corps is ancillary to the infantry. 运输队是步兵的辅助部队。 2. Practice in the deft use of words may well be ancillary to the study of science. 熟练使用文字的练习对于科学的研究也是有帮助的。 3. Expensive ancillary equipment was required for the operation to work. 操作这样的系统曾需要昂贵的辅助设备。', '名词复数: ancillaries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ready', '[\'redi]', 'adj.准备好的；现成的；乐意的；情愿的', '1. The troops were ready for anything. 部队已做好了一切准备。 2. The letter is ready for the post. 信已准备好，可以寄出了。 3. I have no ready answer to the question. 我没有现成的答案。 4. We are ready to render them assistance. 我们乐意援助他们。', '比较级: readier 最高级: readiest 名词: readiness 过去式: readied 过去分词: readied 现在分词: readying 第三人称单数: readies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mealy', '[\'miːli]', 'adj.(蔬菜或水果)粉质的；有斑点的；苍白的；不坦率的', '1. \"I only know two sorts of boys. Mealy boys, and beef-faced boys.\" (Charles Dickens) “我只知道两种男孩，脸色苍白的和胖得满脸横肉的。”(查尔斯·狄更斯) 2. Don\'t be so mealy mouthed, say what you mean! 别这么绕弯子了', '比较级: mealier 最高级: mealiest 名词: mealiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vituperate', '[vaɪ\'tjuːpəˌreɪt]', 'v.痛斥；辱骂', '1. The prince vituperated against the developers for ruining London\'s skyline. 王子斥责土地开发商破坏了伦敦市建筑物映在空中的轮廓线之美。', '名词: vituperator 过去式: vituperated 过去分词: vituperated 现在分词: vituperating 第三人称单数: vituperates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('protean', '[\'proʊtiən]', 'adj.千变万化的；变化不定的', '1. Yet in protean China, one constant is that opposing the Communist state brings down a mailed fist. 然而，在千变万化的中国，常有的现象是反对共产主义国家会导致铁腕手段。 2. In today\'s art world, a place without living culture heroes, you can\'t even imagine such a protean monster arising. 在今天不存在文化英雄的艺术世界里，你甚至无法想像这样一位千变万化的怪物产生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('kangaroo', '[ˌkæŋɡə\'ruː]', 'n.袋鼠', '1. The kangaroo is a native of Australia. 袋鼠是产于澳大利亚的动物。 2. A kangaroo carries its young in a pouch. 大袋鼠以肚袋装小袋鼠。 3. The kangaroo uses its back legs to jump. 袋鼠是用牠的后脚在跳。', '名词复数: kangaroo');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('morsel', '[\'mɔːrsl]', 'n.少量；一口；一片 v.分成小块', '1. He wouldn\'t do such silly things if he had a morsel of sense. 他要是有一点常识的话，就不会干这种傻事。 2. Between the cup and the lip a morsel may slip. 吃到嘴里的才算是你的。 3. He had a morsel of food caught between one tooth and another. 他的齿缝里嵌进了一小片食物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('finale', '[fɪ\'næli]', 'n.终曲；结局', '1. The music worked up to a rousing finale. 该乐曲达到激动人心的高潮而结束。 2. Which season finale are you most excited to watch? 你最希望看到的季结局是哪部片子? 3. The bowler\'s release is the “grand finale” of the approach. 球员的出手是整套步法的\'大结局\'。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lumber', '[\'lʌmbər]', 'n.木材；木料 v.伐木 vi.缓慢地移动 vt.拖累', '1. I followed the road down past the piles of lumber. 我穿过成堆木材，沿着路走下去。 2. Iron mined in order to topple trees for lumber. 开采铁矿则是为了砍伐树木以获取木材。 3. They slapped together a cabin out of old lumber. 他们利用旧木料草草地盖起了一间小屋。 4. Among the sawmill customers are the chair factory and other users of cut lumber. 在锯木场的客户中是那些椅子工厂及其他木料用户。 5. He was a lumberjack, living in lumber camps of the American Northwest. 他是个伐木工，住在美国西北的伐木营地里。 6. He refused to lumber himself with a family. 他不愿有家室拖累。', '副词: lumberingly 名词: lumberer 过去式: lumbered 过去分词: lumbered 现在分词: lumbering 第三人称单数: lumbers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('deportment', '[dɪ\'pɔːrtmənt]', 'n.风度；举止', '1. He maintained a hard, careless deportment. 他保持一种严酷的，漠不关心的态度。 2. The old housekeeper, with a gracious severity of deportment , waves her hand towards the great staircase. 老管家带着一种庄重严肃的态度，朝那座大楼梯挥了一下手。 3. He is austere and grave in deportment. 他举止庄重严肃。 4. Young ladies used to have lessons in deportment. 少女以前要上仪态课。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flora', '[\'flɔːrə]', 'n.植物；群落 （大写）Flora：[罗神]花神弗洛拉； 弗洛拉（女名）.', '1. My professor studies flora of the Palaeozoic Era. 我的教授研究古生代的植物群。 2. Flora of clay desert is similar to that of detritus desert. 粘土荒漠上的植物和碎石荒漠上的植物相似。 3. The results indicated that allelopathic weed Solidago canadensis L. had a significant influence on the microbial flora. 结果表明，具化感作用潜力的加拿大一枝黄花明显影响了土壤中根部微生物群落多样性。 4. The humans upon Earth were primitive in nature, living from roots and plants in simple dwellings constructed from the local flora and fauna. 地球上的人类在本性上是纯朴的，以根茎和庄稼为生，在当地的植物和动物群落中构建简单的住所。 5. He had asked Flora for the Croydens\' file. 他请弗洛拉取来了克罗伊敦夫妇的文件夹。', '名词复数: floras');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stethoscope', '[\'steθəskoʊp]', 'n.听诊器 v.用听诊器诊断', '1. The stethoscope is a medical instrument. 听诊器是一种医疗器械。 2. The physician was aided by the stethoscope. 这医生有听诊器的帮助。', '形容词: stethoscopic 副词: stethoscopically 名词: stethoscopy');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hallow', '[\'hæloʊ]', 'v.使 ... 神圣；视为神圣', '1. But in a large sense we cannot dedicate; we cannot consecrate; we cannot hallow this ground. 不过，从广义上说，我们没有资格奉献这片土地，也未能给它以荣光，使之神圣。 2. This area was hallowed by sacred memories. 这个地区由于宗教上的纪念意义而被视为圣地。', '过去式: hallowed 过去分词: hallowed 现在分词: hallowing 第三人称单数: hallows');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dawdle', '[\'dɔːdl]', 'v.磨蹭；浪费时间；闲逛', '1. Look sharp! Do not dawdle about like that. 快点！别这么磨磨蹭蹭了。 2. Look smart! Don\'t always dawdle about like that! 快一点！别总是那么拖拖拉拉！ 3. He dawdles the hours away watching television. 他把时间都荒废在看电视上了。 4. Don\'t dawdle over your clothing. You\'re so beautiful already. 不要再在衣着上花费时间了，你已经够漂亮的了。', '副词: dawdlingly 名词: dawdler 过去式: dawdled 过去分词: dawdled 现在分词: dawdling 第三人称单数: dawdles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('espousal', '[ɪ\'spaʊzl]', 'n.订婚；结婚；信奉；拥护', '1. Does anybody see my espousal ring? 有人看到我的订婚戒指吗？ 2. Is there anybody see my espousal ring? 有人看到我的订婚戒指吗？ 3. Many stories have been handed down among the Chinese people about a judge known for his fearless espousal of justice. 中国民间流传着许多有关包公的传说，称他为“包青天”、“青天大老爷”，称赞他执法严明，铁面无私，为老百姓做主。 4. The espousal of a notion of public good, drawing people beyond the personal and consumerist. 信奉工艺的理念，引导人们超越个人的、消费者的境界。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('steeple', '[\'stiːpl]', 'n.尖塔', '1. Most Norman churches feature a tall steeple. 高高的尖塔是多数诺曼教堂的特色所在。 2. Orthodox Christian churches often have elaborate steeples. 传统的基督教堂都有精致的尖塔。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wag', '[wæɡ]', 'v.(狗)摇摆(尾巴)；(狗尾巴)摇摆；摇(头或手表示不赞成)；逃学；饶舌；<古>离别 n.摇摆；诙谐幽默的人；逃学', '1. Dogs wag their tails when they are pleased. 狗一高兴就摇尾巴。 2. The dog\'s tail wagged. 那只狗的尾巴摇摆着。 3. They often persuaded me to wag school. 他们常劝我逃学。 4. The news set tongues wagging. 那则消息使人们议论纷纷。 5. The dog greeted its master with a wag of its tail. 狗摇着尾巴迎接主人。', '名词: wagger 过去式: wagged 过去分词: wagged 现在分词: wagging 第三人称单数: wags');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('collage', '[kə\'lɑːʒ]', 'n.拼贴；拼贴画；杂烩', '1. Many zines tend to rely on comics, illustration, and collage. 不少杂志往往依靠漫画，插图，拼贴。 2. A collage of coloured paper covers a table top . 一副彩纸拼贴画盖在桌面上。 3. That is only a collage of conflicting memories. 那只是破碎记忆的汇集。', '名词: collagist 过去式: collaged 过去分词: collaged 现在分词: collaging 第三人称单数: collages');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sated', '[seɪt]', 'vt.使心满意足；过份地给与', '1. Nothing could sate the careerist\'s greed for power. 什么也满足不了这个野心家的权力欲。 2. She sated with sleep. 她睡腻了。', '过去式: sated 过去分词: sated 现在分词: sating 第三人称单数: sates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('extrude', '[ɪk\'struːd]', 'v.挤出；压出；逐出；拉伸（主要用于CAD制图）', '1. Extrude the first part of the claw. 挤出爪子的第一部分。', '过去式: extruded 过去分词: extruded 现在分词: extruding 第三人称单数: extrudes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bankrupt', '[\'bæŋkrʌpt]', 'adj.破产的；道德败坏的；枯竭的 n.破产者；无知的人 vt.使破产', '1. If your liabilities exceed your assets, you may go bankrupt. 如果你所负的债超过你的资产，你就会破产。 2. I was bankrupt and unable to pay his debts. 我破产了，不能偿还他的债务。 3. He has been feeling low since he went bankrupt. 破产后他一直很消沉。 4. He believes that modern society is morally bankrupt. 他认为现代社会已丧失道德观念。 5. He realizes the bankrupt\'s assets. 他变卖破产者的财产。 6. Foolish expenditures will bankrupt him. 胡乱的花费将使他破产。', '形容词: bankruptive 名词: bankruptcy 过去式: bankrupted 过去分词: bankrupted 现在分词: bankrupting 第三人称单数: bankrupts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('immolate', '[\'ɪməleɪt]', 'vt.为供神而宰杀；供奉牲礼', '1. He would immolate himself for their noble cause. 他愿意为他们的崇高事业牺牲自己。 2. I never thought you will payed such immolate. 我决没想过要你做出这样的牺牲。 3. Immolate youth to go over .This isn\'t my want. 所以，要成功，所必须付出的方式，要谨慎...待续.. 4. Immolate domesticity for aspire after career galvanization. 为追求事业发展而牺牲家庭生活。', '名词: immolation 过去式: immolated 过去分词: immolated 现在分词: immolating 第三人称单数: immolates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('garner', '[\'ɡɑːrnər]', 'v.贮藏；收集；得到 n.谷仓 Garner. n.加纳(姓氏)', '1. Squirrels garner nuts for the winter. 松鼠为过冬储存松果。 2. The facts are garnered from various sources. 这些资料是从各种渠道搜集到的。 3. Mr.Smith gradually garnered a national reputation as a financial expert. 史密斯先生逐渐赢得全国金融专家的声誉。 4. Mr. al-Jaafari has been unable to garner support outside his own party. 贾法里一直以来不能得到其他的党派支持。', '过去式: garnered 过去分词: garnered 现在分词: garnering 第三人称单数: garners');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pyre', '[\'paɪər]', 'n.火葬柴堆', '1. The widow leapt into the funeral pyre. 这个寡妇跳进火葬柴堆。 2. The glow of a funeral pyre slowly dies by the silent river. 火葬灰中的红光在沉静的河边慢慢地熄灭下去。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('grumble', '[\'ɡrʌmbl]', 'v.发牢骚；抱怨；轰鸣 n.怨言；牢骚；轰隆声', '1. A lot of students grumble about heavy reading assignments. 许多学生发牢骚说阅读量太大。 2. It\'s not like him to grumble at her. 抱怨她可不像他的做法。 3. We\'ve got nothing to grumble about. 我们没什么可抱怨的。 4. They will grumble about having to do the work. 他们将为不得不干那项工作而抱怨。 5. I don\'t want to hear another grumble from you. 我不愿再听到你的怨言了。', '形容词: grumbly 副词: grumblingly 名词: grumbler 过去式: grumbled 过去分词: grumbled 现在分词: grumbling 第三人称单数: grumbles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('colonnade', '[ˌkɑːlə\'neɪd]', 'n.柱廊；列柱', '1. The terrace was embraced by the two arms of the colonnade. 平台由两排柱廊环抱。 2. This colonnade will take you out of the palace and the game. 这条柱廊将带你离开宫殿和游戏。 3. In the colonnade outside the theatre, a young servant came up to the two women. 在剧场的圆柱走廊里有一个小厮向她们迎上前来。 4. She turned her back to Newt, looked into the infinite colonnade of the woods. 她转过身去背对着纽特，望着那无穷无尽的行道树。', '形容词: colonnaded');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('instrumental', '[ˌɪnstrə\'mentl]', 'adj.仪器的；乐器的；有帮助的；可做为手段的 n.器乐曲；[语]工具格', '1. These tests require an extremely sophisticated instrumental effort. 这些试验需要极其尖端仪器才能办到。 2. I like instrumental music better than vocal music. 我喜欢器乐胜于声乐。 3. His instrumental works are popular amongst the students. 他的器乐曲在学生中很受欢迎。 4. Your advice has been instrumental in settling the question. 你的劝告对决这个问题是有帮助的。 5. His instrumental works are popular amongst the students. 他的器乐曲在学生中很受欢迎。', '副词: instrumentally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lyric', '[\'lɪrɪk]', 'adj.抒情的 n.抒情诗；歌词', '1. The anthology reveals a prejudice in favour of lyric poets. 这部选集显示出对抒情诗人有所偏爱。 2. His earlier work announced a lyric talent of the first order. 他的早期作品显露了一流的抒情才华。 3. He is a fine writer of lyrics. 他是个优秀的抒情诗作家。 4. I\'m deeply moved by this lyric of Shelley\'s. 我被雪莱的这首抒情诗深深打动了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('swear', '[swer]', 'v.咒骂；发誓；宣誓 n.誓言；咒骂；发誓', '1. Shut up! How dare you swear at me like that! 住嘴，你竟敢那样咒骂我! 2. You have no right to swear at me like that! 你无权那样咒骂我！ 3. I swear by Almighty God that I will tell the truth. 我对万能的上帝发誓我要说真话。 4. They swore an oath to carry out their duties faithfully. 他们发誓要忠实履行自己的职责。 5. Don\'t forget your swear for me. 不要忘记你对我发过的誓言。', '名词: swearer 过去式: swore 过去分词: sworn 现在分词: swearing 第三人称单数: swears');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sully', '[\'sʌli]', 'v.玷污；弄脏 n.<古>污点；污斑', '1. I wouldn\'t sully my hands by acceptinga bribe. 我决不接受贿赂，一尘不染。 2. You shouldn\'t sully his character for no reason. 你不应该平白无故地污蔑他人格低下。 3. Any further recalls will sully their reputations, perhaps irreparably. 再有任何召回事件都会玷污它们的声誉，而且可能无法挽回。 4. No speck of dirt had ever sullied his hands. 他的双手从来都是一尘不染。', '名词复数: sullies 过去式: sullied 过去分词: sullied 现在分词: sullying 第三人称单数: sullies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('antipathy', '[æn\'tɪpəθi]', 'n.憎恶；反感；不相容', '1. Honest men have a natural antipathy to politicians. 诚实的人对政客们有一种自然的嫌恶。 2. He showed a strong antipathy to this place. 他对这个地方表示了强烈的反感。 3. The strong personal antipathy between the two scholars is very obvious. 那两位学者之间的格格不入是很明显的。', '名词复数: antipathies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fodder', '[\'fɑːdər]', 'n.饲料；专门的工具；素材 v.(用饲料)喂', '1. Timothy can be used as fodder for cattle. 猫尾草可以作为喂牛的牧草。 2. The cattle battened on the plentiful fodder. 牲畜靠丰美的饲料养得膘肥体壮。 3. Food and fodder should go ahead of troops and horses. 兵马未动，粮草先行。 4. We are not just voting fodder for professional politicians. 我们不仅仅是专门为职业政客们投票的工具。', '过去式: foddered 过去分词: foddered 现在分词: foddering 第三人称单数: fodders');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rowdy', '[\'raʊdi]', 'adj.吵闹的；粗暴的', '1. A rowdy group of boys ran through the streets. 一群吵闹的男孩跑过街道。 2. The teacher made the rowdy class quiet down. 老师使这吵闹的班级安静了下来。 3. He was beaten to death by a rowdy person. 他被一个暴徒打得死去活来。', '副词: rowdily 比较级: rowdier 最高级: rowdiest 名词: rowdiness 名词复数: rowdies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('monotonous', '[mə\'nɑːtənəs]', 'adj.单调的', '1. The preacher\'s monotonous voice put me to sleep. 传教士单调的声音催我入眠。 2. His monotonous whistling grated on her nerves. 他单调的口哨声令她的神经受不了。', '副词: monotonously 名词: monotonousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lynch', '[lɪntʃ]', 'v.处以私刑', '1. Before night they wanted to lynch him, but he was gone. 还没到晚上他们就想私自干掉他，可是他已经跑了。', '名词: lyncher 过去式: lynched 过去分词: lynched 现在分词: lynching 第三人称单数: lynches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('piazza', '[pi\'ɑːzə]', 'n.广场；市场(尤指意大利城镇中的)；走廊', '1. Siena\'s main piazza was one of the sights of Italy. 锡耶纳的主要广场是意大利的名胜之一。 2. They walked out of the cafeteria, and across the piazza. 他们走出自助餐厅,穿过广场。 3. A boy is flying a kite in the piazza. 一个小男孩在阳台上放风筝。', '名词复数: piazzas');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('raze', '[reɪz]', 'v.夷为平地；摧毁；消除；抹去', '1. The city was razed by an earthquake. 地震把这个城市夷为平地。 2. The troops attacked his village and razed it to the ground. 军队攻击了他的村子，把村子夷为平地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('testy', '[\'testi]', 'adj.易怒的；暴躁的', '1. The flash of anger took many voters by surprise because Fukuda had kept his testy temperament under wraps as leader. 福田在发布会上的这句气话让选民们大吃一惊，因为这位前首相先生向来是喜怒不形于色。 2. A doctor was called in to see a rather testy aristocrat. 一个性格相当暴躁的贵族召来了一位医生为他检查。', '副词: testily 比较级: testier 最高级: testiest 名词: testiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tangible', '[\'tændʒəbl]', 'adj.可触摸的；实际的；有形的；确凿的', '1. It is the only tangible object the astronomer can handle. 这是天文学家能够掌握的唯一可接触的对象。 2. The tension between them was almost tangible. 他们之间的紧张关系几乎让人都感觉得出来。 3. The plan brought few tangible benefits to the poor. 这个计划没有给穷人带来多少实际好处。 4. Fossils give us tangible evidence that dinosaurs really existed. 化石给了我们恐龙确实存在的确切证据。', '副词: tangibly 名词: tangibility');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('momentum', '[moʊ\'mentəm]', 'n.势头；动力；（物理）动量', '1. They began to lose momentum in the second half of the game. 在比赛的下半场，他们的势头就逐渐减弱。 2. We should continue to maintain good growth momentum. 我们应继续保持良好的增长势头。 3. I am picking up momentum every single day. 我现在每天都会获得动力。 4. The peace movement gained momentum. 和平运动获得了动力。', '名词复数: momenta');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('frigid', '[\'frɪdʒɪd]', 'adj.寒冷的；冷淡的；(指女性)性冷淡的', '1. Huhhot is a frigid city in winter. 冬天的呼和浩特是一个寒冷的城市。 2. Frigid winds blew from the north. 寒风从北方吹来。 3. His frigid glance made me afraid. 他那冷淡的目光让我害怕。 4. She returned his smile with a frigid glance. 对他的微笑她报以冷冷的一瞥。', '副词: frigidly 名词: frigidity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('coma', '[\'koʊmə]', 'n.昏迷', '1. The patient rallied from the coma. 病人从昏迷中苏醒过来。 2. Daddy lingered in a coma for several days. 爸爸昏迷了数日。', '形容词: comal 名词复数: comas');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('harpsichord', '[\'hɑːrpsɪkɔːrd]', 'n.大键琴', '1. Can we dance to the harpsichord? 我们能跟着大键琴一起跳舞吗？', '名词: harpsichordist');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('drub', '[drʌb]', 'v.棒打；彻底击败', '1. I shall be surprised if they do not take another drubbing in Africa. 他们若不在非洲再吃一次败仗，那倒是怪事了。', '名词: drubber 过去式: drubbed 过去分词: drubbed 现在分词: drubbing 第三人称单数: drubs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nephritis', '[ne\'fraɪtɪs]', 'n.肾炎', '1. A person with nephritis must avoid all exertion. 肾炎病人必须避免做任何要用劲的事。 2. Hide sexual nephritis to remedial method there is? 隐匿性肾炎有什么好的治疗方法？', '名词复数: nephritides');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pennant', '[\'penənt]', 'n.长三角旗；信号旗；奖旗', '1. A pennant lolled from the mast. 信号旗松散地从桅杆上垂下来 2. The revitalize team comes from the cellar to win the pennant . 该队重整旗鼓，从最后一名一跃而赢得冠军奖旗。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('futility', '[fjuː\'tɪləti]', 'n.无用；无益；无价值', '1. A sense of futility stole over her. 一种没用的感觉向她袭来。 2. She finally perceived the futility of her protest. 她最终感到她的抵抗是无用的。 3. We see the futility of finger-pointing. 我们认为指责毫无益处。 4. As soon as he had felt these regrets,he realized their futility. 一有这种后悔的感觉,他马上认识到后悔是无益的。', '名词复数: futilities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fungi', '[\'fʌndʒaɪ]', 'n.菌类；蘑菇；霉菌', '1. The seed-borne fungi and seed germination test were examined by using blotter method. 经吸水纸法培养莴苣种子无菌类附著。 2. Patulin is a secondary metabolite produced mainly in rotten parts of fruit by a wide range of fungi. 棒曲霉素是由水果腐烂部位的真菌类产生的次生代谢产物。 3. The lawn was covered with fungi. 草地上到处都是蘑菇。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mirage', '[mə\'rɑːʒ]', 'n.海市蜃楼；幻想', '1. A mirage is an optical illusion. 海市蜃楼是一种视错觉。 2. Although the morning was young, the hazy mirage was up. 天色虽早，朦胧的海市蜃楼却已经出现。 3. Perhaps we are all just chasing a mirage. 也许我们都只是在追逐一个幻想。 4. I stared at the canteen as if it were a mirage. 我看着那水壶就好象看着一个幻想。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('purported', '[pər\'pɔːrtɪd]', 'adj.传说的；据说的 动词purport的过去式和过去分词.', '1. The purport of the statement is that the firm is bankrupt. 该项声明大意是说该商行已经破产。 2. The purported author of the story. 这个故事传说中的作者', '副词: purportedly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('erect', '[ɪ\'rekt]', 'vt.使竖立；建立；建造 adj.直立的；竖立的；笔直的', '1. They erected their tent at the foot of the mountain. 他们在山脚下支起了帐篷。 2. The town will erect a monument to its war heroes . 这个市镇将为该城的战斗英雄们立个纪念碑。 3. Six policemen started to erect a roadblock. 六个警察着手建立一道路障。 4. They plan to erect an apartment house on that property. 他们计划在那片地产上建造一座公寓楼。 5. She held her head erect and her back straight. 她昂着头，把背挺得笔直。', '形容词: erectable 副词: erectly 名词: erectness 过去式: erected 过去分词: erected 现在分词: erecting 第三人称单数: erects');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('orthodontics', '[ˌɔːrθə\'dɑːntɪks]', 'n.畸齿矫正学', '1. Not for use during orthodontics treatment. 在正牙治疗期间禁用。 2. Orthodontics plays a major role in dental esthetics. 正畸治疗是改善牙列美观的重要手段。 3. The orthodontics effect of upper-incision was better. 上切牙拥挤矫治效果较下切牙好。 4. It provides science analysis in diagnosis and research of orthodontics. 该系统为口腔正畸医学的诊断和研究提供科学的分析依据。', '形容词: orthodontic 副词: orthodontically 名词: orthodontist');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lattice', '[\'lætɪs]', 'n.格子；格状物；[物]点阵 v.制做格子；使成格状', '1. Click the left mouse button corresponding lattice placed pawn. 鼠标左键点击相应的格子放置棋子。 2. In this paper, the computer simulation method for fluid flows and Lattice Automata method are studied in detail. 摘要针对流体系统的特点，研究了模拟流体流动的格子自动机方法。 3. A lattice vacancy is a simple example of an imperfection. 点阵空位就是不完美性的一个简单例子。', '形容词: latticed 过去式: latticed 过去分词: latticed 现在分词: latticing 第三人称单数: lattices');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('revolt', '[rɪ\'voʊlt]', 'n.叛乱；反抗；反感 v.叛乱；起反感', '1. The revolt was suppressed in a matter of hours. 叛乱在几小时之内就镇压下去了。 2. All North Africa would flame into revolt. 整个北非将激起反抗。 3. Her mere experience and the free out-of-door life of country caused her nature to revolt at such confinement. 她那简单的经验和自由自在的乡村户外生活，使她对这个窒息的地方起了反感。 4. The peasants revolted against their oppressors. 农民们起义反抗他们的压迫者。', '名词: revolter 过去式: revolted 过去分词: revolted 现在分词: revolting 第三人称单数: revolts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('encroach', '[ɪn\'kroʊtʃ]', 'v.侵占；侵犯；侵害', '1. His new house encroached on my land. 他的新房子侵占了我的土地。 2. I\'m sorry to encroach upon your time, but I really need your help. 抱歉，要来占用你的时间，可是我确实需要你的帮助。 3. The new law doesn\'t encroach upon the rights of the citizen. 新的法律没有侵犯公民的权益。 4. The army must never encroach upon the people\'s interests. 军队绝不能损害人民的利益。', '名词: encroacher 过去式: encroached 过去分词: encroached 现在分词: encroaching 第三人称单数: encroaches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('embezzlement', '[ɪm\'bezlmənt]', 'n.盗用；挪用；侵占', '1. The official has fallen into disrepute for his embezzlement of the public funds. 那名官员因盗用公款而声名狼藉。 2. In recent months, the owners of a number of companies have been arrested and charged with fraud and embezzlement. 最近几个月，有不少公司负责人被逮捕，并以诈欺与盗用公款的罪名被起诉。 3. Their embezzlement bankrupted the firm. 他们贪污挪用公款使商行破产了。 4. He turns thumbs down on things like embezzlement and tax evasion. 他反对象挪用公款和逃税的事情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('serfdom', '[\'sɜːrfdəm]', 'n.农奴身份；农奴制', '1. The serfs were liberated after abolishing serfdom. 废除农奴制度后，农奴们获得了解放。 2. This movement overthrew the serf system and freed a million serfs and slaves . 这一运动推翻了农奴制，并且解放了百万农奴和奴隶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('defeatist', '[dɪ\'fiːtɪst]', 'adj.失败主义者的 n.失败主义者', '1. He failed again and again simply because he had maintained his defeatist attitude. 因为他一直坚持失败主义的态度，所以失败了一次又一次。 2. He is a pessimist and a defeatist. 他是悲观主义者，也是失败主义者。 3. The defeatist always see their stagnant circumstances as limiting. 失败主义者把困境当成牢笼，毫无办法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('committed', '[kə\'mɪtɪd]', 'adj.忠诚的；坚定的；献身于某种事业的；委托的', '1. He was a strongly committed comrade of the Party. 他是一个对党非常忠诚的同志。 2. With a new moon in Gemini, you\'d find all the range you need to stay committed. 随着新月在双子座，你会发现所有你想要坚定的范围。 3. They are committed socialists. 他们是坚定的社会主义者。 4. This development area is committed to creating a perfect investment environment. 这个开发区致力于创造一个完美的投资环境。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nettle', '[\'netl]', 'n.荨麻 v.以荨麻刺；激怒', '1. Nettle is a kind of common wild plant. 荨麻是一种普通的野生植物。 2. When the nettle is young, the leaf makes an excellent vegetable. 嫩荨麻的叶子是一种非常好吃的蔬菜。 3. It was clear that my remarks nettled her. 显然，我的言语激怒了她。 4. I was rather nettled by his rude questions. 他粗鲁的问题使我很恼火。', '过去式: nettled 过去分词: nettled 现在分词: nettling 第三人称单数: nettles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('entity', '[\'entəti]', 'n.实体；存在；本质', '1. A corporation is treated by the law as an entity. 法人在法律上被视为一个实体。 2. It describes the change in an entity\'s state. 它描述了一个实体的状态变化。', '名词复数: entities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('slither', '[\'slɪðər]', 'v.（使）滑行；（使）滑动', '1. They slither wildly as they slip away across the universe. 它们不受拘束的滑动着,就像他们正漫步于星辰间。 2. They slither while they pass, they slip away across the universe 这些鸟虽然他们通过,他们溜横跨宇宙', '形容词: slithery 过去式: slithered 过去分词: slithered 现在分词: slithering 第三人称单数: slithers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tyrant', '[\'taɪrənt]', 'n.暴君；专制的君主；专横的人', '1. The emperor was a tyrant. 那皇帝是个暴君。 2. This ruler is a pitiless tyrant. 这个统治者是一个冷酷的暴君。 3. Mr Smith was a high-handed tyrant in his office. 史密斯先生在他办公室里是个专横跋扈的独裁者。 4. Her grandfather is a tyrant who insists on absolute silence at the dinner table. 她祖父是个专横的人，坚持吃饭时绝对禁止讲话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dispose', '[dɪ\'spoʊz]', 'v.清除；处理掉；解决；杀死；打败', '1. I want to dispose of these old books. 我想处理掉这些旧书。 2. Most complaints can be disposed of pretty quickly. 大多数投诉可以很快地解决。 3. The president ruthlessly disposed of his rivals. 这位总统无情地除掉了政敌。 4. She disposed of the champion in straight sets. 她一盘未输战胜了冠军。', '名词: disposer 过去式: disposed 过去分词: disposed 现在分词: disposing 第三人称单数: disposes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('innate', '[ɪ\'neɪt]', 'adj.天生的；固有的', '1. Ability is not innate, but comes through practice. 本事不是天生的，是锻炼出来的。 2. You obviously have an innate talent for music. 你显然有天生的音乐才能。 3. Children have an innate ability to learn language. 孩子具有天生的学习语言的能力。 4. The love is the innate strength. 爱是与生俱来的力量!', '副词: innately 名词: innateness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fern', '[fɜːrn]', 'n.羊齿植物；蕨', '1. The fern quickly grew from the earth. 羊齿很快地从地里长出来。 2. The hillsides are covered with ferns. 山坡上长满了蕨类植物。 3. We can identify several classes of fern. 我们可以识别几种蕨类植物。', '形容词: ferny');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('relevance', '[\'reləvəns]', 'n.中肯；关联；相关性', '1. I don\'t see the relevance of your question. 我不懂你这个问题有什么意义。 2. His answer bore little relevance. 他的回答无关痛痒。 3. And they do that at the expense of relevance. 它们这样做是以关联为代价的。 4. I really can\'t see what relevance is has, I\'m afraid. 恐怕我确实看不出那有什么关系。', '异体字: relevancy');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('insolvency', '[ɪn\'sɒlvənsi]', 'n.无力偿还；破产', '1. The scope of the Insolvency Fund Scheme and the claims and settlement procedures will largely be the same as those under the existing ECAS. 无力偿还债务基金计划的范围，以及申索和结算程序大体上会与现时的雇员补偿援助计划相同。 2. But, like a borrower whose insolvency would bring down a bank, he may calculate that much of his former backers\' anger is bluster, covering a fear of their own impotence. 但是，就像一位借款人一样，无力偿还会让银行倒闭，穆萨拉夫可能盘算着，他以前的支持者的强烈的愤概只不过是恐吓，以掩盖他们自身的无能。 3. The company is in a state of insolvency. 公司处于破产状态。 4. The idea of my insolvency cooled down her flames immediately. 一想到我破产了，她的热情顿时冷却。', '名词复数: insolvencies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('asperity', '[æ\'sperəti]', 'n.刻薄；严厉；(气候等的)严酷；粗糙', '1. He spoke to the boy with asperity. 他严厉地对那男孩讲话。 2. The asperity of the winter had everybody yearning for spring. 严冬之苦让每个人都渴望春天。 3. If such additives are used then the chemical activity may not be restricted to the asperity contacts. 如果使用了上述添加剂,化学反应可能就不限于表面粗糙的接触。', '名词复数: asperities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('piercing', '[\'pɪrsɪŋ]', 'adj.尖锐的；刺耳的；刺骨的；穿透的 动词pierce的现在分词形式.', '1. A piercing mournful wail cut through the air, as if intent on tormenting the weak of heart. 一阵尖锐的、凄惨的叫声在空中盘旋了一阵，好像故意在绞痛这些人的脆弱的心。 2. All of a sudden a piercing scream broke the silence. 突然，刺耳的尖叫声打破了寂静。 3. The piercing wind fanged his ears. 刺骨的寒风吹得他耳朵疼痛。 4. The fighters walked on against the piercing wind. 战士们冒着刺骨的寒风前进。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('paralyze', '[\'pærəˌlaɪz]', 'vt. 使 ... 瘫痪； 使目瞪口呆 =paralyse（英）', '1. Otherwise, my dread of criticism can paralyze me. 不然的话，我对批评的恐惧将让我行为瘫痪。 2. Even the smallest slip could permanently paralyze the patient. 即使最小的失误都会导致小朱利安终身瘫痪。', '副词: paralyzingly 名词: paralyzation 过去式: paralyzed 过去分词: paralyzed 现在分词: paralyzing 第三人称单数: paralyzes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('quantum', '[\'kwɑːntəm]', 'n.定量；额；量；量子', '1. When each process finishes its quantum , it will be swapped with other process . 当每个过程都完成了他们的分配量，它将会被与其他过程交换。 2. Liability was admitted by the defendant, but the case went to trial because they could not agree the quantum of damages. 被告承认有责任，但案子还是拿到法庭审判，因为双方当事人不能就损害赔偿金金额达成协议。 3. The annual export quantum reaches ten million sets. 年出口量达到一千多万台。 4. The spin phenomenon exists only in quantum theory. 只有在量子理论中才出现这样的自转效应。', '名词复数: quanta');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('spontaneous', '[spɑːn\'teɪniəs]', 'adj.自发的，自然的，本能的；自然产生的', '1. He is spontaneous to offer help. 他主动提供帮助。 2. It is a spontaneous cheer from the crowd. 那是群众自发的喝彩。 3. The spontaneous applause cut the singer short. 自发的掌声打断了歌唱家的演唱。 4. The eruption of volcanoes is spontaneous. 火山爆发是自然产生的。', '副词: spontaneously 名词: spontaneousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lava', '[\'lɑːvə]', 'n.熔岩；火山岩', '1. The molten lava ran down the mountain. 熔岩从山上流下来。 2. That volcano cast forth lots of lava and ashes. 那火山喷了出大量熔岩和灰烬。 3. Lava could account for the mare infill on the Moon. 火山岩能解释月球表面大片的阴暗区的形成。 4. Back in the smelting, pull the lever to open the lava pit. 回到熔炼房间，拉下控制杆打开火山岩坑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('chastise', '[tʃæ\'staɪz]', 'v.严惩；责难；鞭笞', '1. Should I applaud my husband or chastise him? 我是该称赞还是责罚我的丈夫呢？ 2. The leader chastised that man who made a mistake. 领导严厉惩罚了那个犯错误的人。 3. Our government chastised the behaviors of NATO. 我国政府强烈谴责了北约的行为。 4. My father used to chastise my brothers with whips. 父亲过去常以鞭打惩罚我的兄弟。', '形容词: chastisable 名词: chastisement 过去式: chastised 过去分词: chastised 现在分词: chastising 第三人称单数: chastises');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ingratiating', '[ɪn\'ɡreɪʃieɪtɪŋ]', 'adj.讨好的；奉承的', '1. There was such an ingratiating tone about Hurstwood\'s voice, the insinuation was so perceptible that even Carrie got the humour of it. 赫斯渥说话时带着讨好的口气，他的意思那么明显，连嘉莉也听出了话中的诙谐意思。', '副词: ingratiatingly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('controvert', '[\'kɑːntrəvɜːrt]', 'v.议论；辩驳；驳击', '1. The statement of the last witness controvert the evidence of the first two. 最后一个证人的陈述反驳了前两人的证词。 2. I shall have to controvert one or two ideas that are almost universally accepted. 我要反驳一两个几乎是公认的观点。 3. These two schools controvert against each other in domestic and foreign countries. 无论在国内还是在国外，都存在着这两种马克思哲学诠释理论的激烈争论。 4. In my opinion, the more abusive they are, the better; Anyway no amount of abuse can controvert the three points I\'ve dealt with. 我看越骂越好，我讲的这三条总是骂不倒的。', '形容词: controvertible 过去式: controverted 过去分词: controverted 现在分词: controverting 第三人称单数: controverts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('feigned', '[feɪnd]', 'adj.假装的；不真诚的 动词feign的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. Feign authorship of a novel. 冒充小说的著作人 2. Her efforts to feign cheerfulness weren\'t convincing. 她的强颜欢笑并不使人信服。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gratuity', '[ɡrə\'tuːəti]', 'n.小费；赠物；赏钱', '1. Gratuity is customary in this money-mad metropolis. 在这个金钱至上的大都市里，给小费是司空见惯的。', '名词复数: gratuities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('depressed', '[dɪ\'prest]', 'adj.沮丧的；降低的；不景气的；萧条的；[动]扁平的；[植]匍匐的 动词depress的过去式及过去分词.', '1. The thought of having to take the exam again depressed me. 想到还需重新考试，我就感到沮丧。 2. She got depressed and began to let things slide. 她情绪低落，一切都听之任之。 3. We were all depressed by the dismal weather. 阴沉的天气让我们都感到压抑。 4. He gets cheerful and depressed by turns. 他的情绪高一阵低一阵。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('miniature', '[\'mɪnətʃər]', 'adj.小型的；小规模的 n.缩图；小画像；小模型', '1. The little girl has a miniature camera. 小女孩有个小型照相机。 2. The child was playing with his miniature railway. 这孩子正在玩他的小型玩具铁路。 3. The room resembled a miniature battlefield. 这个房间很像一个缩小了的战场。 4. She is just like her mother in miniature. 她简直是她母亲的缩影。', '名词: miniaturist');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('malediction', '[ˌmælə\'dɪkʃən]', 'n.诅咒；咒骂；诽谤', '1. Would you turn their distress into a malediction? 你要借他们的苦难来咒骂他们吗？ 2. I heard the people\'s malediction against him. 我听到人们对他的咒骂。', '形容词: maledictory');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('malevolent', '[mə\'levələnt]', 'adj.有恶意的；恶毒的', '1. Unfortunately there are some malevolent people out there and it is best not to take undue risks. 不幸的是在外面的世界里有一些恶毒的人，最好不要过分去冒险招惹他们。 2. As Father Ralph came in holding Meggie\'s hand, her malevolent gaze beat the child\'s down. 当拉尔夫神父拉着麦琪的手走进来时，她那恶毒的眼光马上压倒了孩子。', '副词: malevolently');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('extemporaneous', '[ekˌstempə\'reɪnɪəs]', 'adj.即兴的；不用讲稿的；临时的；权宜的', '1. He made an extemporaneous speech. 他作了即席演说。 2. An accomplished extemporaneous speaker. 一位高明的即席演讲者 3. An extemporaneous policy decision. 一个权宜的政策决定 4. She made an extemporaneous speech on the ceremony. 她在典礼上做了一次即兴演讲。', '副词: extemporaneously 名词: extemporaneity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('recline', '[rɪ\'klaɪn]', 'v.躺；靠在；斜倚；倚靠；依赖', '1. I recline upon the still unwithered grass and whisper to myself, \"Perfect day\" 那绿草尚未枯黄，我躺在草地之上，喃喃地自言自语道：“大好的秋光!” 2. She reclined lazily on the cushions. 她懒洋洋地靠在靠垫上。 3. She reclined her head against my shoulder. 她把头倚在我的肩上。 4. We shouldn\'t recline too much upon book learning. 我们不应过多地依赖书本知识。', '名词: reclination 过去式: reclined 过去分词: reclined 现在分词: reclining 第三人称单数: reclines');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('univocal', '[juː\'nɪvəkəl]', 'adj.单一的意思；意义明确的', '1. A series of univocal and concise equations was developed. 建立起物理意义更明晰的方程组。 2. The president declared that it was important to send a univocal message of support to the beleaguered country. 总统宣称对处于困境中的国家，明确表示支持是很重要的。', '副词: univocally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('acquit', '[ə\'kwɪt]', 'v.宣布无罪；开释；原谅；表现', '1. He was acquitted of the crime. 他被宣告无罪。 2. They tried to bribe the judge to acquit them. 他们试图贿赂法官判他们无罪。 3. Will the court acquit him of the crime? 法庭会宣判他无罪释放吗? 4. I acquit Edward of all essential misconduct. 我原谅爱德华的所有根本过错。', '名词: acquitter 过去式: acquitted 过去分词: acquitted 现在分词: acquitting 第三人称单数: acquits');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('recombine', '[ˌriːkəm\'baɪn]', 'v.再结合；重组', '1. That provides ample opportunity for strains to mingle and recombine. 那就给毒株混杂与重组提供充足的机会。 2. We recombine them to preserve as many structural interactions as possible, while at the same time making lots of mutations. 我们重组他们以保护近可能多的结构间交互作用，同时制造大量突变。', '过去式: recombined 过去分词: recombined 现在分词: recombining 第三人称单数: recombines');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mistral', '[\'mɪstrəl]', 'n.密史脱拉风(冬季法国南部的一种乾冷而强劲的北风或西北风)', '1. Windsurfer?men?/?women?-?Mistral?one?design? 男子/女子帆板米氏级? 2. In 1904 Mistral won the Nobel Prize for Literature. 1904年，米斯特拉尔获得诺贝尔文学奖。 3. Van Gogh longed to meet Mistral, whose work he read and admired. 梵高曾经渴望和米斯特拉尔会面，因他读过后者的作品，十分仰慕。 4. The \"Mistral\" turns in an adjacent road 150m in front of the \"Tunisie\". “米斯米切尔”转到了“突尼西亚”前方150米处的一个毗邻的道路上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sumptuous', '[\'sʌmptʃuəs]', 'adj.华丽的；奢侈的', '1. The poor girl was astonished by the sumptuous furnishings of the mansion. 这个贫穷的女孩被大厦里的豪华的陈设惊呆了。 2. Life is a sumptuous funeral and burial. 生命是一场华丽的礼葬。 3. The king gave a sumptuous banquet. 国王举行一次奢侈的宴会。 4. The millionaire gave a sumptuous banquet. 百万富翁举行了一次奢侈的宴会。', '副词: sumptuously 名词: sumptuousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mint', '[mɪnt]', 'n.薄荷；造币厂；<口>巨额 vt.铸造(硬币)；伪造 adj.完美无缺的', '1. Sage, mint and dill are all herbs. 鼠尾草、 薄荷、 莳萝均为药草。 2. He put the sugar, mint and a little soda into a tall tumbler. 他在一只高脚杯子中加了糖、薄荷和一点苏打水。 3. The Royal Mint will strike a commemorative gold coin. 英国皇家造币厂将铸造一种纪念金币。 4. Father left him a mint of money. 父亲留给他一大笔钱。 5. The Romans learned to mint from the Greeks. 罗马人从希腊人那里学会了铸造钱币。', '形容词: minty 名词: minter 过去式: minted 过去分词: minted 现在分词: minting 第三人称单数: mints');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bruise', '[bruːz]', 'n.瘀青；擦伤；挫伤 vi.碰伤；擦伤 vt.使挫伤', '1. His face is a mass of bruise after the fight. 他打完架后脸上青一块紫一块的。 2. She is lucky to get off with just a few bruise. 她幸免于难,只是有几处擦伤。 3. She had a dilly of a bruise on her arm. 她手臂上有一块显眼的伤痕。 4. It can range from a minor Bruise or sprain to a skull fracture with Brain damage or a spinal-cord injury with paralysis. 其范围从小型挫伤或扭伤到大脑受损的头颅裂开或麻痹性脊椎伤害。 5. Soft fruit bruises easily. 细嫩的水果容易碰损。 6. She fell and bruised her knee. 她摔倒在地，膝盖上起了紫血块。', '过去式: bruised 过去分词: bruised 现在分词: bruising 第三人称单数: bruises');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reputation', '[ˌrepju\'teɪʃn]', 'n.好名声；声誉，名声，名气', '1. This store has an excellent reputation for fair dealing. 这家商店因公平交易而获好名声。 2. He has not too good a reputation in the matter of honesty. 就诚实而言, 他的名声不太好。 3. He trades on his father\'s reputation. 他用他父亲的名誉牟利。 4. He spotted his reputation by lying repeatedly. 他因反复说谎而败坏了自己的名声。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('slice', '[slaɪs]', 'n.薄片；部分；曲球 v.切成薄片；割；切开', '1. Please give me a slice of bread. 请给我一片面包。 2. This is just a slice of life. 这只是人生的一个片段罢了。 3. He also gets a slice of the profit. 他也得到一份利润。 4. A slice is a curving shot from left to right with severe sidespin. 右曲球是一种带有相当于顺时钟旋转导致剧烈向右弯曲的击球。 5. Slice the mushrooms thinly and fry in butter. 把蘑菇切成薄片,用黄油抄。', '形容词: sliceable 名词: slicer 过去式: sliced 过去分词: sliced 现在分词: slicing 第三人称单数: slices');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('shabby', '[\'ʃæbi]', 'adj.破旧的；寒酸的；低劣的，无耻的；卑劣的', '1. He owns nothing beyond the shabby house. 除了那个破旧的房子,他一无所有。 2. His shabby appearance creates a bad impression. 他那寒酸的样子给人留下不好的印象。 3. She is none the less beautiful for her shabby clothing. 即使她衣衫褴褛，却仍然美丽。 4. His reasoning is weak, even shabby. 他的论证软弱无力，甚至可以说很拙劣。', '副词: shabbily 比较级: shabbier 最高级: shabbiest 名词: shabbiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('accelerate', '[ək\'seləreɪt]', 'v.加速；提前；跳级', '1. Our present task is to accelerate economic growth. 加速经济发展是我们当前的任务。 2. The leader is losing ground as the rest of the runners accelerate. 领先者在其余赛跑者加速时就逐渐失去了优势。 3. We will accelerate the reform of the financial system under these circumstances. 在这一背景情况下,我们将加快金融体制改革。 4. The decline of her health seemed to suddenly accelerate. 她的健康状况好像突然提前衰退了。', '形容词: accelerative 过去式: accelerated 过去分词: accelerated 现在分词: accelerating 第三人称单数: accelerates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('repeal', '[rɪ\'piːl]', 'v.废止；撤消 n.废止；撤消', '1. The bill seek to repeal the existing legislation. 该议案企图废除现存的有关立法。 2. He has planed to repeal a number of the current radical policies. 他已经计划撤销许多当前激进的政策。 3. We\'ll have to repeal if we don\'t get that order soon. 假如不可很快拿到货,我们只有取消啦。 4. Many voted for the repeal of that property law. 许多人投票赞成废止那项财产法。', '形容词: repealable 名词: repealer 过去式: repealed 过去分词: repealed 现在分词: repealing 第三人称单数: repeals');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scion', '[\'saɪən]', 'n.后裔；接穗；幼枝', '1. He\'s the scion of a very wealthy newspaper-publishing family. 他是一个非常富有的报纸出版业家族的后裔。 2. The bottom of the scion is cut in the shape of the letter V. 接穗的底端被切成字母V字形。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hasty', '[\'heɪsti]', 'adj.匆匆的；轻率的；急忙的', '1. Some people are prone to jump to hasty conclusions. 有些人往往作出轻率的结论。', '副词: hastily 比较级: hastier 最高级: hastiest 名词: hastiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('baroque', '[bə\'roʊk]', 'adj.巴洛克式的；过份雕琢的；奇形怪状的 n.巴洛克式；巴洛克风格', '1. A development of Baroque,f it will be found a congruous decoration for baroque churches. 巴落克式样，它的发展被发现适合装饰成为巴洛克式的教会。 2. The Rococo style of art emerged in France in the early 18th century as a continuation of the Baroque style. 早期的十八世纪时，洛可可式的艺术风格在法国被视为巴洛克式艺术风格的延续。 3. A development of Baroque,f it will be found a congruous decoration for baroque churches. 巴落克式样，它的发展被发现适合装饰成为巴洛克式的教会。 4. The Rococo style of art emerged in France in the early 18th century as a continuation of the Baroque style. 早期的十八世纪时，洛可可式的艺术风格在法国被视为巴洛克式艺术风格的延续。', '副词: baroquely');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scaffold', '[\'skæfoʊld]', 'n.鹰架；绞刑台；脚手架', '1. He was about to be led to the scaffold when at the eleventh hour a messenger arrived bringing a royal pardon. 就在他要被带上断头台的最后时刻，一名使者带来了女王的赦免令。 2. The worker fell down from the scaffold. 那个工人从脚手架掉了下来。', '过去式: scaffolded 过去分词: scaffolded 现在分词: scaffolding 第三人称单数: scaffolds');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('havoc', '[\'hævək]', 'n.大破坏；混乱 vt.破坏', '1. The earthquake wreaked havoc on the city. 地震对这个城市造成了大破坏。 2. This concentration of airborne firepower played havoc with the enemy forces. 这次机载火力的集中攻击给敌军造成很大破坏。 3. A major power failure wreaked havoc in New York last night. 昨晚纽约大停电引起了一片混乱。 4. The fear inside of China is that excess RMB volatility could wreak havoc on a still fragile financial system. 中国国内的担心是，过度的人民币震荡可能给仍然脆弱的金融体制造成大混乱。 5. His hard work wreaks havoc in his personal life. 他拼命工作破坏了他的私人生活。', '过去式: havocked 过去分词: havocked 现在分词: havocking 第三人称单数: havocs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mendacity', '[men\'dæsəti]', 'n.虚假；撒谎', '1. During his lifetime, Vespucci prospered from his mendacity. 终其一生，瓦斯普契因撒谎成性而飞黄腾达。 2. So dogs may be able to sniff out bombs.But they can\'t pick up the smell of mendacity. 因此，狗狗们可以嗅出爆炸物，但是他们不能嗅出撒谎的人。', '名词复数: mendacities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('impressionable', '[ɪm\'preʃənəbl]', 'adj.易受影响的', '1. The child is at an impressionable age. 这孩子正处于易受影响的年龄。 2. Children are more impressionable than adults. 儿童较成年人更易受影响。', '名词: impressionability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stigma', '[\'stɪɡmə]', 'n.耻辱；污名 n.柱头', '1. There should be no stigma attached to being poor. 贫穷不应该与耻辱扯上任何关系。 2. Sadly, borrowing from the fund carries a stigma. 然而，悲哀的是向基金借钱成为了一种耻辱。 3. Her behavior will leave a stigma on her family. 她的行为将给她的家庭留下污名。 4. Divorce has lost much of its stigma, or shame. 离婚也就不再带有那么多的污名或耻辱。 5. The pollen is shed directly on the stigma. 花粉直接散落在柱头上。', '形容词: stigmal 名词复数: stigmata');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('convoke', '[kən\'voʊk]', 'vt.召集(会议)', '1. The king convoke parliament to cope with the impending danger. 国王召开国会以应付迫近眉睫的危险。 2. Convoke doesn\'t change a spell\'s mana cost or converted mana cost. 召集不会改变咒语的法术力费用或总法术力费用。 3. Convoke a meeting for review program with other quality engineer. 定期组织召开部门内项目回顾。 4. Turn a mode to convoke through blog, it\'s not fangle, however, maybe better than a forum. 换个方式，用部落格来传达，虽然不是新鲜事，或许，总比佳礼的来的好。', '名词: convoker 过去式: convoked 过去分词: convoked 现在分词: convoking 第三人称单数: convokes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('labile', '[\'leɪbəl]', 'adj.易变的；不稳定的', '1. Such physical entanglements are usually labile. 这种物理缠结往往是不稳定的。 2. These are more commonly described as the \"labile\" metal concentrations. 这些通常称之为“不稳定”金属浓度。', '名词: lability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('advert', '[\'ædvɜːrt]', 'n.广告 vi.注意；谈到（后接to）', '1. She answered an advert for a job as a cook. 她应聘了厨师的招聘广告。 2. She came across and advert for the book Bible Basics. 她偶然留意到圣经基础这本书。', '过去式: adverted 过去分词: adverted 现在分词: adverting 第三人称单数: adverts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('formation', '[fɔːr\'meɪʃn]', 'n.形成；队形；编队；构造；[地]地层', '1. Let us now examine the process of its formation. 我们现在就来研究这个形成过程。 2. School life has a great influence on the formation of a child\'s character. 学校生活对小孩个性的形成有很大影响。 3. The airplanes few over in formation. 飞机编成队形在空中飞过。 4. The troops lined up in parade formation. 部队排成阅兵队形。', '形容词: formational');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('toil', '[tɔɪl]', 'n.辛苦；苦工；罗网；圈套 v.费力地做；苦干；跋涉', '1. We were quite exhausted with the toil. 我们因那件辛苦的工作而感到十分疲惫。 2. Every grain of it comes from hard toil. 粒粒皆辛苦。 3. Thus his youth had been spent in rude and ill-paid toil. 他的青年时期便是那样在干着报酬微薄的辛苦工作中消磨过去的。 4. He was destined to plod the path of toil. 他注定要在艰辛的道路上跋涉。 5. I shall have to toil and moil all my days. 我必须一年到头拼命地干。', '名词: toiler 过去式: toiled 过去分词: toiled 现在分词: toiling 第三人称单数: toils');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fetid', '[\'fetɪd]', 'adj.有恶臭的；臭的', '1. A fetid odor sickened the hospital workers. 恶臭的气味令医院工作人员作呕。 2. The air of the room was fetid with stale tobacco smoke. 房间里的空气有陈烟的臭味。', '副词: fetidly 异体字: foetid 名词: fetidness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('perjury', '[\'pɜːrdʒəri]', 'n.伪证罪；伪誓；背信弃义', '1. He was accused of perjury with the intention of incriminating his employer. 他被控告犯有意图加罪于其雇主的伪证罪。', '形容词: perjurious 副词: perjuriously 名词复数: perjuries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mirth', '[mɜːrθ]', 'n.欢乐；欢笑', '1. The end of mirth is the beginning of sorrow. 欢乐是结束就是悲哀的开始。 2. Christmas is a time of mirth, especially for children. 圣诞节是个快乐的日子，尤其是对孩子们。 3. The announcement was greeted with much hilarity and mirth. 这一项宣布引起了热烈的欢呼声。 4. When I told them what had happened to me, they all chortled with mirth. 我把我的事告诉他们以后,他们咯咯地笑起来了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('accolade', '[\'ækəleɪd]', 'n.表扬；嘉奖；武士爵位的授与', '1. His new book received accolade from the papers. 他的新书受到报纸的热烈赞扬。 2. He enjoys that double-edged accolade of being a \"friend of China\". 福田很享受作为\"中国人的朋友\"而获得的双方的赞誉。 3. In Hollywood, an \"Oscar\" is the highest accolade. 奥斯卡金像奖是好莱坞最高荣誉奖。', '过去式: accoladed 过去分词: accoladed 现在分词: accolading 第三人称单数: accolades');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nectar', '[\'nektər]', 'n.花蜜；甜美的饮料；众神饮用的酒', '1. Nectar and pollen are very nutritious. 花蜜和花粉是很有营养的。 2. Bees gather nectar and make it into honey. 蜂采花蜜制成蜂蜜。 3. Even nectar is poison if taken to excess. 美酒过量也会变成毒药。 4. The wine is good, like drinking nectar. 这种酒真好喝, 好像琼浆玉液一般。', '形容词: nectarous');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('resident', '[\'rezɪdənt]', 'n.居民；住客；住院医生 adj.居住的', '1. The residents of the town are proud of its new library. 该镇的居民都为镇上新建的图书馆感到自豪。 2. I have been resident in this hotel for two weeks. 我已经在这家旅馆里住了两个星期了。 3. I would get the neurosurgery resident down here. 我想请神经外科住院医师下楼到这儿来。 4. This dove was resident with us all the year round. 这只鸽子一年到头居住在这里和我们为伴。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mutton', '[\'mʌtn]', 'n.羊肉', '1. Fish doesn\'t go well with mutton. 鱼和羊肉在一起不好吃。 2. People like to have mutton in the winter. 冬天人们喜欢吃羊肉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('quench', '[kwentʃ]', 'v.熄灭；结束；冷淬；解渴', '1. Water will quench a fire. 水可以灭火。 2. Nothing could quench her longing to return home again. 她重返家园的念头怎么也打消不掉。 3. Hot steel is quenched to harden it. 烧热的钢淬火使它坚硬。 4. Her sarcastic remarks quenched his passion. 她讽刺的话冷却了他的热情。', '形容词: quenchable 名词: quencher 过去式: quenched 过去分词: quenched 现在分词: quenching 第三人称单数: quenches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('buoyant', '[\'buːjənt]', 'adj.有浮力的；心情愉快的；趋于上涨的', '1. A boat must be made of buoyant material. 船一定要用有浮力的材料来做。', '副词: buoyantly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('canary', '[kə\'neri]', 'n. 金丝雀； 加那利舞； 加那利白葡萄酒； <俚>告密者', '1. The canary has escaped from its cage. 金丝雀从笼中逃掉了。', '名词复数: canaries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('obviate', '[\'ɑːbvieɪt]', 'v.排除；消除；避免', '1. By far,it can\'t obviate seismic possibility. 到目前为止，还不能排除地震的可能性。 2. The new road obviates the need to drive through the town. 有了新路,车辆不必再穿行市区了。', '名词: obviation 过去式: obviated 过去分词: obviated 现在分词: obviating 第三人称单数: obviates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('allude', '[ə\'luːd]', 'v.暗示；暗指', '1. I didn\'t allude to anything or anybody. 我并未影射任何人或任何事。 2. He did not even allude to his brother\'s engagement to Mary. 他兄弟与玛丽订婚的事他只字未提。 3. What were you alluding to just now? 你刚才指的是什么？', '过去式: alluded 过去分词: alluded 现在分词: alluding 第三人称单数: alludes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('virile', '[\'vɪrəl]', 'adj.有男子气概的；有生殖能力的；精力充沛的', '1. She is both virile and feminine. 她既有男子的气概，又有女性的娇柔。 2. Babbitt was expansive and virile . 巴比特健谈,男子气概十足。 3. See the handsome but effeminate young man; he has no virile character. 瞧这个奶油小生,哪有一点儿男子汉的气概啊！ 4. His style of singing is very virile . 他演唱的风格浑厚有力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('commotion', '[kə\'moʊʃn]', 'n.骚动；混乱；喧闹', '1. His appearance caused a commotion. 他的出场引起一场骚动。 2. The discovery caused a tremendous commotion in the scientific world. 那项发现在科学界引起极大的震动。 3. His reverie had thrown him into severe commotion. 他的白日梦把他带入了严重的混乱。 4. You are making a great commotion about nothing. 你简直是在无理取闹。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('potable', '[\'poʊtəbl]', 'adj.适于饮用的', '1. They voraciously drank all the potable water at one time. 他们贪婪地一下就喝光所有饮用水。 2. They set up purifying systems in places where the water was not potable. 他们在许多水质不适合饮用的地方建立了净化系统。', '名词: potability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('envision', '[ɪn\'vɪʒn]', 'vt.想象；设想', '1. But the competition of man against man is not the simple process envisioned in biology. 但是人反对人的竞争不是象生物学中所想象的那种简单过程。 2. I can\'t envision him doing such a terrible thing. 我不敢想象他能做出这种可怕的事。 3. I cannot envision him as president. 我无法想像他是总统。 4. They didn\'t envision any problems with the new building. 他们没想到这栋新楼会有什么问题。', '过去式: envisioned 过去分词: envisioned 现在分词: envisioning 第三人称单数: envisions');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('aristocracy', '[ˌærɪ\'stɑːkrəsi]', 'n.贵族；贵族阶级', '1. He objected to the toadying to aristocracy. 他反对对于贵族阶级的奉承。 2. He objected to the toadying to aristocracy. 他反对对于贵族阶级的奉承。 3. Coastal Georgia was too firmly held by an entrenched aristocracy for him ever to hope to win the place he intended to have. 滨海的佐治亚州是那样牢牢地掌握在一顽强的贵族阶级手中，在这里，他就休想有一天会赢得他所刻意追求的地位。', '名词复数: aristocracies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nil', '[nɪl]', 'n.无；零', '1. Our immediate capacity for an offensive was nil. 我们尚无立刻进攻的时机。 2. Our football team won by four goals to nil. 我们的足球队以四比零取胜。 3. My knowledge of the subject is practically nil. 我在这方面的知识几乎等于零。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dullard', '[\'dʌlɑːrd]', 'n.笨蛋', '1. For years, teachers had figured him for a dullard. 多年来老师们都以为他是个笨蛋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('depraved', '[dɪ\'preɪvd]', 'adj.堕落的；颓废的；卑鄙的 动词deprave的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. Moralists also denounced depraved behaviour in the baths. 道德学家同样谴责这种堕落的行为。 2. Santiago congresswoman Maria Antonieta Saa says the non-alcoholic cafes appeal to the \"depraved simplicity\" of men\'s minds. 圣地亚哥女国会议员玛利亚认为这些不卖酒的咖啡馆吸引了男性思想中堕落的成分。', '副词: depravedly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('counterpart', '[\'kaʊntərpɑːrt]', 'n.职务相当的人；对应物；相似之物；副本', '1. The secretary of state is the counterpart of the foreign minister. 国务卿相当于外交部长。 2. The sale director phoned her counterpart in the other firm. 这位销售主任给另一家公司的销售主任打电话。 3. Night is the counterpart of day. 黑夜与白天相辅相成。 4. I racked my memory in vain for its counterpart in literature: perhaps you could think of one. 我绞尽脑汁也想不出它在文学中的对等物，也许你可以想出一个。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('peachy', '[\'piːtʃi]', 'adj.桃似的；桃色的；<口>出色的', '1. I really like your peachy face, shiny eyes and cherry mouth. 我真的喜欢你蜜桃般的脸，羞答答的眼睛和樱桃般的嘴。 2. Her peachy complexion was gone;it was now masked by a color that should never be found on human skin - bright orange.She shrugged. 她粉扑扑的肤色完全消失了，取而代之的是一种完全不属于人类肤色的亮橘色，这样看上去，她好像戴上了一个奇怪的面具。 3. They bought a peachy new sports car. 他们买了一辆很好的新跑车。', '比较级: peachier 最高级: peachiest 名词: peachiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('steadfast', '[\'stedfæst]', 'adj.坚定的；毫不动摇的', '1. Our nation is patient and steadfast. 我们的国家是有耐心的，立场是坚定的。 2. He adopted a steadfast attitude towards this issue. 他对这件事采取坚定的态度。 3. He is of a resolute and steadfast disposition. 他的性格非常刚毅。', '副词: steadfastly 名词: steadfastness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('contention', '[kən\'tenʃn]', 'n.争论；争辩；争夺；论点', '1. This is an issue of great contention at the moment. 眼下这个问题是争论的热点。 2. The subject deserves contention. 这个问题值得争论。 3. The judge balanced the contention of both parties . 法官权衡了双方的争辩。 4. Three players are in contention to win the title. 三个运动员在争夺这个项目的冠军。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('refulgent', '[rɪ\'fʌldʒənt]', 'adj.辉煌的；灿烂的', '1. I can image the refulgent look at that time. 想象着它当年辉煌的样子。 2. Our company will keep the client as the god,keep mutual benefit as the base,and set up a refulgent future together. 公司将以顾客至上诚信为本为宗旨，在共同发展互惠互利的基础上，与新老顾客共创辉煌的未来。', '副词: refulgently 名词: refulgence');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dross', '[drɔːs]', 'n.浮渣；糟粕；无价值之物', '1. They tried to purge metal of dross. 他们试图清除金属熔化时浮升表面的渣滓。 2. For foreign cultures, we should discard their dross and select their essence. 对于外来文化，我们要取其精华，去其糟粕。 3. The best players have gone off to the big clubs, leaving them the dross. 最好的队员都投奔大俱乐部去了，留给他们这些不怎么样的球员。 4. What\'s gold and silver? Mere dross. 金银财宝，身外之物。', '形容词: drossy');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bibulous', '[\'bɪbjʊləs]', 'adj.高度吸收的；酗酒的', '1. Than: Basically be to inspect bibulous rate, bibulous rate is lower better. 比： 主要是考察吸水率，吸水率越低的越好。 2. I throw open my windows and from the yard outside came the hot uncommon sounds of bibulous laughter and unsteady steps. 我打开窗户，外面院子传来不平常的，醉汉的笑声和不稳的脚步声。 3. Use the need of water to assure fire protection, should build an upriver driveway and bibulous establishment. 为保证消防用水的需要，应修建通向水源的车道和吸水设施。 4. But it can control the bibulous of handsheet in the demanding range through accession suitable waterproof. 但通过添加适量的防水剂可以使纸板的吸水值在要求的范围内。', '副词: bibulously 名词: bibulousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('oratory', '[\'ɔːrətɔːri]', 'n.讲演术；演说；祈祷室；小礼拜堂 Oratory. n.（天主教）奥拉托利会', '1. He dazzled the crowd with his oratory. 他的演说术使听众赞叹不已。 2. He pulverized the opposition with the force of his oratory. 他能言善辩把对方驳得体无完肤。 3. In front of the bed is a prie-Dieu, borrowed from the oratory. 床的前面是一张从经堂里搬来的祈祷椅。 4. The wedding will be at the Brompton Oratory next month. 婚礼下月将在布拉姆顿教堂举行。', '名词复数: oratories');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('impenitent', '[ɪm\'penɪtənt]', 'adj.不知悔改的；顽固的', '1. His impenitent attitude is really annoying. 他死不改悔的态度真令人生气。 2. The Son of God Himself was sent to plead with the impenitent city. 上帝的儿子亲自奉差遣来到这个顽梗的城邑，发出恳切的劝告。 3. But because of your hard and impenitent heart you are storing up wrath for yourself on the day of wrath when God\'s righteous judgment will be revealed. 你竟任著你刚硬不悔改的心，为自己积蓄忿怒，以致神震怒，显出他公义审判的日子来到。 4. Paul explains in Romans 1:24, 26, 28, that God reveals His wrath by turning impenitent men over to the inevitable results of their rebellion. 保罗在罗马书一章二十四、二十六和二十八节解释说，上帝任凭邪恶的人承受他们犯罪的结果，这就是上帝的愤怒了。', '副词: impenitently 名词: impenitence');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mesa', '[\'meɪsə]', 'n.平顶山 Mesa. n.梅瑟（美国亚利桑那州中南部一城市名）', '1. Built atop a near-impenetrable mesa deep in the south of Mulgore, this collection of tents and thatched huts serves as the tauren\'s central home. 建立在南莫高雷中心一个几乎无法攻破的平顶山上，这里到处是帐篷和茅草棚，是牛头人的主要家园。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('philanthropic', '[ˌfɪlən\'θrɒpɪk]', 'adj.博爱的；慈善的', '1. Such a long-term perspective is not a philanthropic dream. 这种长期的观点不是一种博爱论。 2. The old gentleman was renowned far and wide for his philanthropic generosity. 老先生因乐善好施而闻名遐尔。 3. The list also takes into account philanthropic donations . 该排行榜的评估也将慈善捐助资金计算在内。 4. He was appointed as the image ambassador of the philanthropic activity. 他被委任为此次慈善活动的形象大使。', '副词: philanthropically 异体字: philanthropical');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('derogatory', '[dɪ\'rɑːɡətɔːri]', 'adj.毁谤的；贬损的；侮辱的；贬义的', '1. Such conduct will be derogatory to his reputation. 那样的行为将会毁损他的名誉。 2. I can\'t bear his derogatory remarks about my brother\'s character. 我无法忍受关于贬低我兄弟人品的评论。 3. The word `pig\' is a derogatory term for policeman. pig是个侮辱警察的词。 4. This word is often used in a derogatory sense. 这个词常用于贬义。', '副词: derogatorily 名词: derogatoriness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('jurisdiction', '[ˌdʒʊrɪs\'dɪkʃn]', 'n.管辖权；司法权；审判权；控制权', '1. This affair is within his jurisdiction. 这件事情在他的管辖权限之内。 2. The village you speak of does not fall under my jurisdiction. 你所说的这个村庄不在我的管辖范围内。 3. That case is under the jurisdiction of this court. 那宗案件属本法庭受理范围。 4. The court has no jurisdiction over foreign diplomats living in this country. 法院对居住在本国的外交官无裁判权。', '形容词: jurisdictional 副词: jurisdictionally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bliss', '[blɪs]', 'n.幸福；极乐；天赐的福', '1. They were in a state of bliss during the honeymoon. 他们在蜜月期间幸福无比。 2. The first six months of marriage were sheer bliss. 刚结婚的半年,他们沉浸在极乐之中。 3. Tom was swimming in bliss. 汤姆处于极乐之中。 4. Innocence is bliss. 无知便是福。', '形容词: blissful 副词: blissfully 名词: blissfulness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hawk', '[hɔːk]', 'n.鹰；鹰派人物、主战分子；贪婪的人；清嗓 v.沿街叫卖；散布；鹰扑；放鹰行猎；清嗓', '1. The hawk is hovering overhead. 鹰在头顶上盘旋。 2. The hawk pounced on its prey and carried it off. 那只鹰向那小动物猛扑过去把它叼走了。 3. He is neither a dove nor a hawk, but betwixt and between. 他既不是鸽派，也不是鹰派，而是中间派。 4. In a free market, retailers hawk their wares. 自由市场里商贩们不停地叫卖着。', '形容词: hawkish 副词: hawkishly 名词: hawkishness 过去式: hawked 过去分词: hawked 现在分词: hawking 第三人称单数: hawks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mortality', '[mɔːr\'tæləti]', 'n.死亡率；死亡数目；必死性', '1. Infant mortality is still very high in some developing countries. 某些发展中国家的婴儿死亡率仍然很高。 2. If this disease spreads, the doctors fear that there\'ll be a high mortality. 如果这种病传播开来，医生们担心死亡率将会很高。 3. The mortality from lung cancer is increasing. 肺癌死亡人数在增多。 4. These deaths are reminders of our own mortality. 这些死亡提醒我们总有一天会死去的命运。', '名词复数: mortalities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('enshrine', '[ɪn\'ʃraɪn]', 'v.奉为神圣；珍藏', '1. The constitution enshrines the basic rights of all citizens. 宪法中神圣地记载著全体公民的基本权利。 2. National parks enshrine important American values and aspirations. 国家公园体现着美国重要的价值观与理想。', '异体字: inshrine 名词: enshrinement 过去式: enshrined 过去分词: enshrined 现在分词: enshrining 第三人称单数: enshrines');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('relaxation', '[ˌriːlæk\'seɪʃn]', 'n.消遣；松弛；放松', '1. Fishing is his favorite relaxation. 他最喜爱的消遣是钓鱼。 2. His day is evenly divided between work and relaxation. 他一天的时间一半花在工作上，一半用在娱乐上。 3. You need more rest and relaxation. 你需要多休息，松弛一下。 4. Would you like to have some relaxation after swimming? 游完泳后你愿意放松一下吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('traceable', '[\'treɪsəbl]', 'adj.可追踪的；起源于', '1. Most telephone calls are traceable. 大多数电话都可查出是从哪里打来的。 2. It\'s a tradition that is traceable back to the 15th century. 这是一个传统，起源于十五世纪。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('polish', '[\'pɑːlɪʃ]', 'n.光泽；上光剂；优雅；精良 v.擦亮；磨光；推敲；完善 Polish. adj.波兰的；波兰人的；波兰语的 n.波兰语', '1. A hot plate will spoil the polish on this table. 热盘子会毁坏桌面的光泽。 2. This car polish is an effective shield against rust. 这种汽车上光蜡很有防锈作用。 3. With this polish you can give a good high gloss to the wood. 使用这种上光蜡可使木器表面极为光亮平滑。 4. Now we have a presentable great speaker whose polish reminds me of Will Smith. 现在我们能言善辩的总统，他的优雅一直让我想起了威尔史密斯。 5. I polished my buttons with a handkerchief. 我用手帕把钮扣擦亮。 6. When I awoke, a Polish man came to my room, held my hand and looked at me with friendly eyes. 当我醒来时,一名波兰人走过来,他握着我的手,亲切地望着我。 7. My spoken Polish is better than my written Polish. 我的波兰语说得比写得好。', '名词: polisher 过去式: polished 过去分词: polished 现在分词: polishing 第三人称单数: polishes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('whirlpool', '[\'wɜːrlpuːl]', 'n.漩涡 Whirlpool. n.惠尔普（美国电子电气公司)', '1. The canoe was sucked (down) into the whirlpool. 那独木舟卷进漩涡里了。 2. The child dropped into the whirlpool from the ship. 小孩从船上掉进了漩涡。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unwieldy', '[ʌn\'wiːldi]', 'adj.笨重的；笨拙的；庞大的', '1. He is carrying an unwieldy parcel. 他拿着一个笨重的包裹。 2. This machine is too unwieldy to move. 这台机器太笨重了, 很难搬动。 3. It is too unwieldy for practical calculations. 它用于实际计算太麻烦了。 4. The company is an unwieldy organization. 这个公司的办事机构庞大。', '副词: unwieldily 比较级: unwieldier 最高级: unwieldiest 名词: unwieldiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('narrative', '[\'nærətɪv]', 'n.故事；叙述 adj.叙述的；叙述体的', '1. She took up the narrative where John had left off. 她接着讲约翰未讲完的故事。 2. His adventure made an interesting narrative. 他的冒险是个有趣的故事。 3. Tatham was lost in wonder at the narrative. 泰瑟姆听了这个故事，惊奇得出了神。 4. Narrative makes up most of the book. 这本书的大部分篇幅都是叙述性的。 5. The lines form a prelude to his long narrative poem. 这几行诗是他那长篇叙事诗的序诗。', '副词: narratively');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sheathe', '[ʃiːð]', 'vt.包；插入鞘；覆 =sheath.', '1. The human body needs iron to capture oxygen, copper and chromium to absorb energy, cobalt to sheathe our nerves and zinc to help our genes. 人体需要铁来捕捉氧，需要铜与铬来吸收能量，需要钴来包覆我们的神经，又仰赖锌协助基因。 2. The human body needs iron to capture oxygen, copper and chromium to absorb energy, cobalt to sheathe our nerves and zinc to help our genes. 人体需要铁来捕捉氧，需要铜与铬来吸收能量，需要钴来包覆我们的神经，又仰赖锌协助基因。', '名词: sheather 过去式: sheathed 过去分词: sheathed 现在分词: sheathing 第三人称单数: sheathes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('egocentric', '[ˌiːɡoʊ\'sentrɪk]', 'adj.自我中心的；利己的', '1. He is egocentric and never considers others. 他是个以自我为中心不为别人着想的人。 2. A husband should give up his egocentric desires in order to serve his wife &family. 作为一个丈夫要放弃利己的欲望，来照顾他的妻子和家庭。', '副词: egocentrically 名词: egocentricity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('trudge', '[trʌdʒ]', 'v.缓慢或吃力地走 n.长途跋涉', '1. The old man trudged home through the deep snow. 老人踩着积雪，步履艰难地往家走。 2. He trudge three hour in the snow to get back home. 他在雪中跋涉三个钟点才回到家。 3. It was a long trudge up the hill. 那段上山的路很难走。', '名词: trudger 过去式: trudged 过去分词: trudged 现在分词: trudging 第三人称单数: trudges');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('operative', '[\'ɑːpərətɪv]', 'adj.有效的；至关重要的；运作的 n.技工；侦探', '1. This law becomes operative on 12 May. 此法令自5月12日起生效。 2. The boss is hopping mad about it and `mad\' is the operative word. 老板对此事暴跳如雷,“暴跳如雷”这个成语在句中最重要。 3. The oil rig is now fully operative. 石油钻塔现全面开工。 4. The station will be operative again in January. 该车站将于一月份恢复使用。 5. He is the most skilled operative in the factory. 他是工厂里最娴熟的技工。', '副词: operatively');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('acrimonious', '[ˌækrɪ\'moʊniəs]', 'adj.尖刻的；激烈的；刻薄的；辛辣的', '1. His tendency to utter acrimonious remarks alienated his audience. 他发表尖刻言论的倾向使得他的听众疏远了他。 2. His parents went through an acrimonious divorce. 他的父母在激烈争吵中离了婚。', '副词: acrimoniously 名词: acrimoniousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sodden', '[\'sɑːdn]', 'adj.浑身湿透的 v.(使)湿透', '1. His clothes were sodden with rain. 他的衣服被雨水淋得湿透了。 2. My shoes are sodden from walking in the rain. 我在雨里这么一跑，鞋都湿了。', '副词: soddenly 名词: soddenness 过去式: soddened 过去分词: soddened 现在分词: soddening 第三人称单数: soddens');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('execration', '[ˌeksɪ\'kreɪʃən]', 'n.诅咒；被诅咒的人或物', '1. Deserving of execration;hateful. 该咒骂的；可憎的 2. Deserving of execration; hateful. 该咒骂的；可憎的 3. Results: The result indicated that early intervention for CKD had reduced the execration of clinical value. 研究结果：研究结国指出及早发现慢性肾脏病并接受治疗，与减缓临床生化值恶化有关联； 4. The sense of wrongs, the injusties, the oppression, extortion, and pillage of twenty years suddenly culminated and found voice in a raucous howl of execration. 二十年来所深受的损害、压迫、勒索、掠夺和不公平的对待，一下子达到了最高峰，在一阵粗声粗气的谩骂叫嚣里发泄出来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('impend', '[ɪm\'pend]', 'vi.迫近；逼迫；即将发生', '1. Crucial events impend in Europe. 欧洲即将发生具有决定意义的事变。', '过去式: impended 过去分词: impended 现在分词: impending 第三人称单数: impends');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('observatory', '[əb\'zɜːrvətɔːri]', 'n.天文台；气象台；了望台', '1. The stadium lights polluted the sky around the observatory. 体育馆的灯光使得天文台周围的天空不那么宜于观测了。 2. According to the observatory, there will be a total solar eclipse tomorrow. 天文台预测，明天将会出现全日食。 3. The Observatory issued only an amber rainstorm signal and a thunderstorm warning. 天文台只是发出黄色暴雨警告及雷暴警告。', '名词复数: observatories');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('phonetic', '[fə\'netɪk]', 'adj.语音的；语音学的', '1. The major parts of the investigation concentrated on the phonetic system of the standerd Mongolian. 本论文用声学语音学的理论和方法对现代蒙古语标准音语音系统进行了系统的分析。', '形容词: phonetical 副词: phonetically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('autocrat', '[\'ɔːtəkræt]', 'n.独裁者', '1. The autocrat strove in vain to deal with the situation. 那个独裁者努力应付这个情况,却徒劳无功。 2. He was an accomplished politician and a crafty autocrat. 他是个杰出的政治家,也是个狡黠的独裁者。', '形容词: autocratic 副词: autocratically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vapid', '[\'væpɪd]', 'adj.索然无味的', '1. He did the same thing year by year and found life vapid. 他每年做着同样的事，觉得生活索然无味。 2. The next issue is that reviewing is generally dull and vapid. 接下来的问题就是，复习是一个枯燥无味的工作。', '副词: vapidly 名词: vapidity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('interweave', '[ˌɪntər\'wiːv]', 'v.使交织；使混杂', '1. Your destiny is interwoven with mine. 你的命运已和我的命运结合在一起了。', '过去式: interwove 过去分词: interwoven 现在分词: interweaving 第三人称单数: interweaves');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('willow', '[\'wɪloʊ]', 'n.柳树；柳木制品', '1. You\'d better hack off the branch of that willow. 你最好把那棵柳树的枝丫砍掉。 2. A willow is a brush painting spring scenery. 一株柳树，是一支描绘春天的彩笔。', '过去式: willowed 过去分词: willowed 现在分词: willowing 第三人称单数: willows');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('irony', '[\'aɪrəni]', 'n.反讽；讽剌之事', '1. The good point is that the irony fully reflected. 好的地方是反讽完全出来了。 2. Irony was widely used in the works of Kafka and LuXun. 卡夫卡和鲁迅的小说中都广泛应用了反讽的艺术手法。 3. The great irony is that despite all his explanation nobody believed him. 最具讽刺意味的是：尽管他竭力解释，可没一个人相信他。 4. After Peanuts left,I could not help thinking about this irony. 落花生去后，我总是不住的这样想这件讽刺的事。', '名词复数: ironies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dome', '[doʊm]', 'n.圆屋顶；苍穹；<俚>脑袋；圆形的火山口 vt.加圆屋顶于...上；使成圆屋顶 vi.成圆顶状', '1. Italian architect celebrated for his work during the Florentine Renaissance. His greatest achievement is the octagonal ribbed dome of the Florence cathedral. 布鲁内莱斯基，菲利波1377－1446意大利建筑师，其作品在佛罗伦萨文艺复兴时期享有盛名。其杰作是佛罗伦萨大教堂的八边形肋骨穹隆 2. A transparent dome on the top of an aircraft, through which celestial observations are made for navigation. 天文观测舱，领航舱飞机顶部的一个透明圆顶形结构，航行时可通过它作天文观测 3. Upward pressure from underlying magma domes the surface. 地下岩浆的向上推力使地面成圆顶形。 4. The dome of St. Paul Cathedral is well known in the world. 圣保罗教堂的圆顶闻名于世。', '过去式: domed 过去分词: domed 现在分词: doming 第三人称单数: domes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hilt', '[hɪlt]', 'n.柄；刀把；剑柄', '1. The hilt of the sword is missing. 这把剑的柄不见了。 2. He had studded the sword hilt with jewels. 他在剑柄上镶嵌了宝石。 3. Is the hilt a bit flexible? 刀把是不是有点松动？ 4. He hurts her with the hilt. 他用剑柄碰伤她了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unmoved', '[ˌʌn\'muːvd]', 'adj.无动于衷的；坚定的；没有动过的；不动摇的', '1. He remained unmoved even when I began to cry. 当我开始哭泣时,他还是无动于衷。 2. It\'s impossible to remain unmoved by her reports of the famine. 任何人对她报道的饥荒情况都不可能无动于衷。 3. He is unmoved in his decision. 他对他的决定很坚定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('punch', '[pʌntʃ]', 'vt.按(键)；以拳重击；开洞；剪票 n.殴打 n.打洞器；钻孔机 n.感染力 n.（酒、水、糖等制成的)鸡尾酒', '1. If you punch in the wrong code, the alarm sounds. 如果你按错了代码,警示器就会响起来。 2. He punched the policeman on the nose and was arrested. 他猛击那个警察的鼻子，结果被逮捕了。 3. The conductor punched his bus ticket. 售票员用剪票夹在他的汽车票上打孔。 4. The punch stunned me for a moment. 那一拳把我打得昏了一阵。 5. Many British movies lack emotional punch. 很多英国电影缺乏感染力。 6. Sometimes even a bowl of fruit punch could make people drunk. 有时候即使一碗水果鸡尾酒,人们也可能会喝醉。', '形容词: punchless 过去式: punched 过去分词: punched 现在分词: punching 第三人称单数: punches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dabble', '[\'dæbl]', 'v.喷洒；玩水；泼溅；涉猎；浅尝', '1. She dabbled her hands in the fountain. 她把手伸到喷泉中玩水。 2. Children like to dabble in water. 孩子们喜欢玩水。 3. He just dabbles in politics. 他仅仅是涉足政治而已。 4. I have to be careful, for I dabble with poisons a good deal. 我不得不小心一点,因为我常和毒物接触。', '过去式: dabbled 过去分词: dabbled 现在分词: dabbling 第三人称单数: dabbles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gallant', '[\'ɡælənt]', 'adj.英勇的；(男子对女子)殷勤的；华丽的；雄伟的 n.时髦男士；对女子殷勤的男士；求爱者 v.献殷勤', '1. These gallant soldiers will protect our country. 这些勇敢的士兵会保卫我们的国家的。 2. He was very gallant at the ball. 他在舞会上对妇女大献殷勤。 3. Her poverty had been a venial fault for two gallant gentlemen. 她的贫穷对那两位殷勤的绅士而言，只是一个微不足道的缺点。 4. The garden was made gallant with tulips. 花园里种著郁金香显得气派不凡。 5. When he puts on his best clothes he certainly looks like a gallant. 他穿上最好的衣服时，当然像个时髦人物了。', '副词: gallantly 过去式: gallanted 过去分词: gallanted 现在分词: gallanting 第三人称单数: gallants');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flourish', '[\'flɜːrɪʃ]', 'v.茂盛；繁荣；挥舞；活跃 n.挥舞；花样；炫耀；华丽词藻', '1. There were two or three palm trees flourishing in the promenade garden. 街心花园里有两三棵枝繁叶茂的棕榈树。 2. Plants will not flourish without water. 没有水植物就不会长得茂盛。 3. These plants flourish in a damp climate. 这些植物在潮湿的气候下长势茂盛。 4. Our business seemed to flourish. 我们在生意看上去很兴隆。 5. She rode by with a flourish of her whip. 她骑马挥鞭而过。', '名词: flourisher 过去式: flourished 过去分词: flourished 现在分词: flourishing 第三人称单数: flourishes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('orchard', '[\'ɔːrtʃərd]', 'n.果园', '1. The children were skylarking in the orchard. 孩子们在果园里嬉戏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('barcode', '[bɑː\'kəʊd]', '条码', '1. The system includes barcode printing and scanning technology. 该系统包括条码打印和扫描技术。 2. The first product to have a barcode on it was a pack of Wrigley\'s gum. 第一个印上条码的产品是一包青箭口香糖。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('viscid', '[\'vɪsɪd]', 'adj.粘质的', '1. Herbs, erect, viscid pubescent throughout. 全部的草本，直立，黏的短柔毛。 2. Buds ellipsoid, glabrous, viscid. 芽椭圆形，无毛，黏。 3. Having the texture or properties of gum; sticky and viscid. 粘性的有树胶的质地或特性的；胶粘的 4. Buds russet, conical or ovoid-conical, slightly viscid. 芽赤褐色，圆锥形圆锥状的或卵球形，稍黏。', '副词: viscidly 名词: viscidity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gnarled', '[nɑːrld]', 'adj.树木多瘤节的；粗糙的 动词gnarl的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. This royal garden is full of ancient gnarled trees. 这座皇家花园有很多长有瘤节的古树。 2. The ancient tree\'s gnarled branches look quite beautiful in the sunset. 古树盘结的树枝在夕阳下显得格外美丽。 3. His gnarled fingers fumbled as he tried to spring the latch. 他用粗糙的手指摸索着，试图关上门闩。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('misinform', '[ˌmɪsɪn\'fɔːrm]', 'vt. 告诉 ... 错误的消息', '1. I regret to say you have been misinformed (about that). 很遗憾，(关於那事)你听到的情况不确。', '名词: misinformant 过去式: misinformed 过去分词: misinformed 现在分词: misinforming 第三人称单数: misinforms');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('melon', '[\'melən]', 'n.甜瓜', '1. We garnished the melon with strawberries. 我们给甜瓜配上草莓。 2. Saya mempunyai sebuah Kiwi dan sebuah Melon. 我有一个猕猴桃和一个甜瓜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('asteroid', '[\'æstərɔɪd]', 'n.小行星；海盘车 adj.星状的', '1. This asteroid takes 238 years to orbit the sun. 这颗小行星需要花238年绕太阳运行一周。 2. Asteroid lies between Mars and Jupiter. 小行星位于火星与木星之间。 3. But he wanted to locate the impact site of the asteroid. 但是他想确定小行星的撞击地点. 4. Large meteorites actually come from the asteroid belt. 大型陨星实际上是来自小行星带。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('saturate', '[\'sætʃəreɪt]', 'v.使浸透；使充满；使饱和 adj.浸透的；饱和的；深颜色的', '1. We lay on the beach, saturated in sunshine. 我们躺在沙滩上，沐浴在阳光里。 2. We were caught in the rain and came home saturated. 我们挨了雨淋, 回家时已浑身湿透。 3. The air was saturated with the perfume of the flowers. 空气中飘荡着花香。 4. The films manufactured by Hollywood are saturated in the cinemas all over the world. 在全世界电影市场上充斥着好莱坞的影片。', '形容词: saturable 名词: saturator 过去式: saturated 过去分词: saturated 现在分词: saturating 第三人称单数: saturates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vengeance', '[\'vendʒəns]', 'n.报复；报仇', '1. But the vengeance of Juno was not yet satiated. 但是朱诺报复之心不死。 2. He is seeking vengeance upon his boss. 他正在找机会报复他的老板。 3. She denounced vengeance against him. 她扬言要向他报仇。 4. These villagers invoked vengeance on their enemies. 这些村民们祈求天神向敌人报仇。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('adroit', '[ə\'drɔɪt]', 'adj.熟练的；灵巧的；机敏的；善于…的', '1. He is adroit in handling machinery. 他对于使用机器颇为熟练。 2. He soon became adroit at steering the boat. 他很快就熟练掌握了驾船技术。 3. Let\'s meet one of the adroit artisans. 我们就要去认识一位巧手中的巧手。 4. She gave the newsman an adroit reply. 她机敏地回答了记者的问题。', '副词: adroitly 名词: adroitness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('conquest', '[\'kɑːŋkwest]', 'n.征服；占领地；战利品；俘虏', '1. They succeeded in the conquest of the city. 他们成功地征服了这座城市。 2. The Normans ruled England by right of conquest. 诺曼人征服了英格兰成了统治者。 3. The conquest of this rare disease has always been her aim. 征服这种罕见的疾病一直是她奋斗的目标。 4. The Romans extended their conquests to Britain. 罗马人把征服范围扩大到了不列颠。', '名词复数: conquests');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inconsequential', '[ɪnˌkɑːnsɪ\'kwenʃl]', 'adj.不合逻辑的；不合理的；不重要的', '1. Most of what she said was pretty inconsequential. 她说的大部分都是很不合逻辑的。 2. Scientists say that those discrepancies are actually inconsequential. 科学家说那些差异其实都无关紧要。', '副词: inconsequentially 名词: inconsequentiality');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ineffable', '[ɪn\'efəbl]', 'adj.无法形容的；说不出的；避讳的', '1. The beauty of a sunset is ineffable. 日落的美是难以形容的。 2. Mercds turned her eyes with an ineffable look towards heaven. 美塞苔丝带着一种难以形容的神情抬头望天。 3. The terror had at long intervals given place to a feeling of an almost ineffable sweetness. 这种胆战心惊的感觉就偶尔让位给一种简直说不出的甜蜜的感觉了。 4. The name of the Deity is ineffable. 神的名字是忌讳说的。', '副词: ineffably 名词: ineffability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('polyandry', '[ˌpɑːli\'ændri]', 'n.一妻多夫制；一雌多雄配合', '1. Typically, polyandry was practiced in parts of China and Tibetans in Nepal. 具有代表性地，一妻多夫制在中国的某些地区和尼泊尔的藏族人中被实行。', '形容词: polyandric');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gangly', '[\'ɡæŋɡli]', 'adj.身材瘦长(难看)的', '1. That gangly sack of shit, third from the front. He\'ll be the first. “那个丑八怪，前面数第三个，他会是第一的。” 2. I had never seen a chap as tall and gangly as he was. 我从没见过像他那样又瘦又高的人。 3. At Monaco he had shown faith in a gangly, young striker called George Weah. 在摩纳哥他信任身材瘦小的年轻射手威赫。 4. He remained a gangly, reticent figure hovering at the edge of our family life. 瘦高而沉默的他，一直徘徊在我们家庭生活的边缘。', '比较级: ganglier 最高级: gangliest');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('deleterious', '[ˌdelə\'tɪriəs]', 'adj.有害的', '1. This food be deleterious to health . 这食物有害健康。 2. Such weather is deleterious on plants. 这种天气对植物有害。 3. Some drugs have a deleterious effect on the body. 有些药品对身体有害', '副词: deleteriously 名词: deleteriousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('colander', '[\'kɑːləndər]', 'n.滤器；漏勺', '1. Use a colander to strain the vegetables. 把蔬菜放在漏筐里控控水。 2. When you\'ve boiled the cabbage, strain off the water through a colander. 当你把卷心菜煮开后，用漏勺把水滤掉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('interim', '[\'ɪntərɪm]', 'adj.暂时的；临时的；中间的 n.中间时期；过渡时期；暂定', '1. He worked on an interim basis. 他只是个临时工。 2. Who will lead the interim government? 谁将领导临时政府? 3. They submitted an interim report. 他们递交了一份临时报告。 4. It may turn out to be an interim technology. 这可能只是个过渡技术。 5. What are you doing in the interim? 这期间你在干什么?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dispatch', '[dɪ\'spætʃ]', 'v.派遣；发送；迅速完成；处死 n.急件；派遣；发送；新闻报道', '1. A messenger was dispatched to take the news to the soldiers at the front. 一名通讯员被派去给前线士兵送消息。 2. We have to ask you to dispatch the consignment immediately. 我们得要求你立即发送该批货物。 3. We soon dispatched the chocolate cake. 我们很快就吃完了那个巧克力蛋糕。 4. The criminal will be dispatched today. 那名罪犯将于今日被处决。 5. I threw the dispatch to him and asked him to take prompt actions. 我把那份急件扔给他,让他立刻采取措施。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('exhale', '[eks\'heɪl]', 'v.呼气；散发', '1. Take a deep breath, then exhale slowly. 深吸一口气，然后慢慢呼气。 2. She exhaled slowly to show her annoyance. 她长叹以示厌烦。 3. He lit his cigar and exhaled smoke. 他点燃雪茄，然后吐出烟雾。 4. He exhaled the pungent odor of garlic. 他散发出刺鼻的大蒜味。', '过去式: exhaled 过去分词: exhaled 现在分词: exhaling 第三人称单数: exhales');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dereliction', '[ˌderə\'lɪkʃn]', 'n.废弃；放弃；玩忽职守；海水退后露出的新陆地', '1. I can\'t stand your dereliction of duty. 我不能容许妳玩忽职守. 2. This policeman was punished for his dereliction of duty. 这名警察因玩忽职守罪被判了刑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pulchritude', '[\'pʌlkrɪtjuːd]', 'n.美丽', '1. My home town has became more and more pulchritude. 我们的家乡变得越来越美丽了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cryogenic', '[ˌkraɪə\'dʒenɪk]', 'adj.低温的；冷冻的', '1. Requiring or suitable to cryogenic storage. 低温存储的需要或适合低温存储的 2. All cryogenic liquids are extremely cold. 所有低温液体的温度都极低。 3. Use tongs to immerse and remove objects from cryogenic liquids. 用夹具浸入低温液体中来移动物体。 4. Flexible wedges with Stellite seating faces for cryogenic service. 适用于低温环境的钨铬钴合金阀座面的柔性楔板。', '副词: cryogenically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('oscillate', '[\'ɑːsɪleɪt]', 'v.振动；摆动；彷徨；犹豫', '1. The price of grain slightly oscillated last year. 去年的谷物价格略有波动。 2. A pendulum oscillates. 摆锤能摆动。 3. Manic depressives oscillate between depression and elation. 躁狂抑郁症患者抑郁与躁狂交替发作。 4. He oscillates between political extremes. 他的政治观点在两个极端之间摇摆不定。', '形容词: oscillatory 名词: oscillator 过去式: oscillated 过去分词: oscillated 现在分词: oscillating 第三人称单数: oscillates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('skiff', '[skɪf]', 'n.轻舟；小船', '1. The skiff was dancing at the stern. 小艇直在海浪中摇摆。 2. We have cut them down to a skiff now. 我们搞得他们只剩一条小艇了。 3. Pedrico is looking after the skiff and gear. 彼得利科在守着船和船上的东西。 4. Raw spray whiplashes the skiff, freezing as it strikes. 湿冷的浪花抽打着小船，随打随冻成冰。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cosset', '[\'kɑːsɪt]', 'v.宠爱；溺爱 n.宠儿；宠物(尤指羔羊)', '1. As a child,she has been spoiled and cosseted. 作为一个小孩子，她一直被宠爱着。 2. Our kind of travel is definitely not suitable for people who expect to be cosseted. 我们这类型的旅游肯定不适合那些希望被宠溺着的人。 3. His grandpa and grandma cosset him, they will give whatever he wants. 他爷爷奶奶惯着他，他要什么就给什么。 4. Man-made stone mesa also is integral kitchen \"cosset\". 人造石台面也是整体厨房的“宠儿”。', '过去式: cosseted 过去分词: cosseted 现在分词: cosseting 第三人称单数: cossets');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('throng', '[θrɔːŋ]', 'n.人群；一大群；大量 v.群集；挤满', '1. A patient throng was waiting in silence. 一大群人耐心地静候着。 2. She had to press through the throng to reach the stage. 她不得不穿过拥挤的人群走上舞台。 3. He was met by a throng of journalists and photographers. 他受到一大群记者和摄影师的迎接。 4. The rapid influx of well-meaning aid agencies that now throng the dusty remnants of Port-au-Prince has contributed to the confusion. 迅速涌入的救援机构出于善心帮助，但大量群集在太子港的废墟之中却是乱上添乱。 5. The rapid influx of well-meaning aid agencies that now throng the dusty remnants of Port-au-Prince has contributed to the confusion. 迅速涌入的救援机构出于善心帮助，但大量群集在太子港的废墟之中却是乱上添乱。', '过去式: thronged 过去分词: thronged 现在分词: thronging 第三人称单数: throngs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('almond', '[\'ɑːmənd]', 'n.杏仁；扁桃；巴旦木，巴旦杏', '1. He brought me a bag of almond paste. 他给我带来一袋杏仁软糖。 2. There was a taste of almond in the cake. 那蛋糕有一点杏仁味道。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('aspire', '[ə\'spaɪər]', 'v.热望；立志', '1. Do you aspire to know the heights, and depths, and lengths, and breadths? 你是否热望要知道上帝的长阔高深？ 2. And thousands of young players aspire to be like him. 千千万万的年轻球手立志要想成为象他那样的英雄。 3. Woman should not only aspire to be educated but also persue independence. 女性不仅应该立志接受教育，还应该追求独立。', '副词: aspiringly 名词: aspirer 过去式: aspired 过去分词: aspired 现在分词: aspiring 第三人称单数: aspires');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('amateurish', '[\'æmətərɪʃ]', 'adj.业余的；不熟练的', '1. I used to be a amateurish astronomer using the telescope to observe stars. 我以前是业余的天文家，用望远镜观察星星。 2. Detectives described the burglary as crude and amateurish. 侦探称这次夜盗是拙劣的生手干的。', '副词: amateurishly 名词: amateurishness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('calumniate', '[kə\'lʌmnɪˌeɪt]', 'vt.中伤；诽谤', '1. Why do you have to calumniate the rights of the case! 翻译1为什么你们要诽谤事情的真相! 2. Do not calumniate good people, otherwise you will be punished. 不要污衊好人,否则你会遭到报应的。 3. Calumniating me is to calumniate your friend! 诽谤我也就是诽谤你的朋友! 4. You do more, under the pretext of unmasking yourself, you calumniate yourself. 尤其是，借口说您要暴露自己，您其实是在诽谤自己，这真可怕。”', '名词: calumniation 过去式: calumniated 过去分词: calumniated 现在分词: calumniating 第三人称单数: calumniates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flirt', '[flɜːrt]', 'n.调情的人；卖弄风骚的人 vi.调情；玩弄；掠过；轻率对待 vt.忽然弹出；摇动', '1. They say he\'s a terrible flirt. 据说他是调情色鬼。 2. Is Kelly a flirt, who goes from boy to boy? 凯莉是个卖弄风骚、朝三暮四的人吗? 3. She\'ll be fixed as the silliest flirt who ever made her family ridiculous. 她就会变成让他家族蒙羞的风骚蠢女人。 4. He enjoys flirting (with the girls in the office). 他爱(与办公室的女职员)调情。 5. The children flirted water to each other\'s face. 这些小孩相互朝对方的脸上弹水。', '过去式: flirted 过去分词: flirted 现在分词: flirting 第三人称单数: flirts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('crib', '[krɪb]', 'n.婴儿小床；食槽 v.抄袭；拘禁', '1. Walk softly as you approach the baby\'s crib. 当你走近婴儿小床时，步子轻一点。 2. Please pour the leftovers into the crib. 请把剩饭倒进食槽。 3. He didn\'t want anybody to crib the answers from him. 他不希望任何人抄袭他的答案。', '名词: cribber 过去式: cribbed 过去分词: cribbed 现在分词: cribbing 第三人称单数: cribs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('provisory', '[prə\'vaɪzərɪ]', 'adj.有附文的；有附带条件的；暂时的', '1. a provisory clause 附有条件的条文. 2. provisory clause n. 限制性条款词句 3. provisory programme 临时议程, 暂定节目 4. provisory program 临时议程, 暂定节目', '副词: provisorily');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('utopian', '[juː\'toʊpiən]', 'adj.乌托邦式的；梦想的 n.空想家', '1. Much of early American family life took place within communal or Utopian societies. 早期美国家庭生活主要产生于村社或乌托邦式社会。 2. As with most art movements that begin with manifestos, the Bauhaus school had a Utopian element. 正如大部分的艺术运动都始于某些宣言一样，包豪斯学派也有着乌托邦式的色彩。 3. If we are wrong, Jesus of Nazareth was merely a Utopian dreamer who never came down to earth. 如果我们是错的，耶稣基督只不过是一个从未涉足地球的乌托邦空想家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lucrative', '[\'luːkrətɪv]', 'adj.合算的；获利的', '1. There is a lucrative black market in car fittings. 有一个能赚钱的汽车配件黑市。 2. Her husband is reaching after a more lucrative situation. 她丈夫正在谋求一个待遇较佳的职位。 3. They surrendered the lucrative bonds for no reason. 他们莫名其妙地放弃了那些正在升值的公债。 4. It was not a lucrative profession. 那是一个没有多少油水的职业。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('execute', '[\'eksɪkjuːt]', 'vt.执行；实行；处决；完成', '1. Congress makes the laws; the President executes them. 国会制定法律，总统执行法律。 2. We then execute the code that we want to test. 接下来,我们执行我们要测试的代码。 3. Now that we have made the decision, we may execute the scheme as previously agreed. 既然我们已经做了决定,我们就可以实行既定方案了。 4. They executed the king. 他们把国王处决了。', '形容词: executable 名词: executer 过去式: executed 过去分词: executed 现在分词: executing 第三人称单数: executes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('crass', '[kræs]', 'adj.粗鲁的；愚钝的；非常的', '1. He\'s so crass, and there\'s no way I would date him. 他很没风度，我不可能跟他约会的。 2. He made crass comments about her worn-out clothes. 他不留情面地评价了她被磨损的衣服。 3. He\'s so crass to talk to. 别跟他费口舌了，他太笨了。', '副词: crassly 比较级: crasser 最高级: crassest 名词: crassitude');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('emblazon', '[ɪm\'bleɪzn]', 'vt.饰以纹章；使有光彩；颂扬', '1. Look, our athletes are marching into the arena! They all look full of vigour in sweat-shirts emblazoned with the name of our school. 看，我校的运动员进场来了！他们穿着印有我校校名字样的运动衫，看上去个个精力充沛。', '名词: emblazoner 过去式: emblazoned 过去分词: emblazoned 现在分词: emblazoning 第三人称单数: emblazons');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('disbar', '[dɪs\'bɑːr]', 'v.取消律师资格', '1. The bar association condemned the lawyer\'s actions but did not disbar him. 律师协会谴责了这个律师的行为，但没有取消他的律师资格。 2. The prosecutor in the case was recently disbar red and given a day in jail. 该案的公诉人近期被取消了律师资格并被判入狱一天。 3. Should the Referee consider any contestant\'s hair too long and/ or unclean, he may disbar the contestant from the bout. 如果主审认为选手头发太长或不干净，可以取消该选手出赛。 4. The Referee Commission may disbar any official or competitor who does not comply with this regulation. 任何大会职员及选手未按规定穿著者,裁判委员会可取消其资格。', '名词: disbarment 过去式: disbarred 过去分词: disbarred 现在分词: disbarring 第三人称单数: disbars');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('muddle', '[\'mʌdl]', 'n.混乱；糊涂 vt.使混乱；使糊涂；弄糟 vi.胡乱应付；混乱', '1. There was a muddle over our hotel accommodation. 我们旅馆的食宿安排十分混乱。 2. Your room\'s in a real muddle. 你的房间真是乱七八糟。 3. The old lady gets in(to) a muddle trying to work the video. 那老太太想开录像机，但是越搞越糊涂。 4. The cleaner had muddled my papers, and I couldn\'t find the one I wanted. 清洁工把我的文件弄乱了，我找不到我要的那份了。 5. We muddle along from day to day. 我们一天天地混日子。', '名词: muddler 过去式: muddled 过去分词: muddled 现在分词: muddling 第三人称单数: muddles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('auspice', '[\'ɔːspɪs]', 'n.预兆；吉兆；赞助；主办', '1. With peace and auspice every of your years. 每一月都是平安吉祥。 2. He took that as an auspice of happiness. 他把那看作是幸福的徵兆。 3. It is the symbol of dignitary, reverence , and auspice. 这是权贵;尊严和吉祥的象征. 4. Jane\'s aunt disliked him very much and had some bad auspice . 简的阿姨非常讨厌他并有一些坏预兆。', '名词复数: auspices');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('deprivation', '[ˌdeprɪ\'veɪʃn]', 'n.剥夺；免职；匮乏；丧失', '1. The deprivation of his citizenship shocked him. 被剥夺公民权这一做法令他很吃惊。 2. Deprivation of office is hanging over his head. 他面临着免职的威胁。 3. Low birth rate is related to economic deprivation. 低出生率和经济贫困有关。 4. The report has spotlighted real deprivation in the inner cities. 这篇报道披露了旧城区的贫困真相。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('substantial', '[səb\'stænʃl]', 'adj.大量的；坚固的；实质的；可观的 n.本质；重要部份', '1. New economic development policies led to substantial and rapid growth. 新的经济发展政策带来了快速和大量的增长。 2. Those workers have built many substantial buildings in the recent years. 近几年那些工人建造了许多坚固的建筑。 3. The reforms have made substantial headway. 改革取得了实质的进展。 4. The article is devoid of substantial matter. 这篇文章缺乏实质性的内容。', '副词: substantially 名词: substantiality');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('defray', '[dɪ\'freɪ]', 'v.支付', '1. My father has to defray my education. 我父亲得支付我的教育费用。 2. The grant helped defray the expenses of the trip. 补助金帮助支付旅行费用。 3. After defraying all the expenses, they were able to lay aside fifteen yuan each month. 在支付所有的开支以后，他们每月能积蓄十五元。', '形容词: defrayable 名词: defrayal 过去式: defrayed 过去分词: defrayed 现在分词: defraying 第三人称单数: defrays');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bloated', '[\'bloʊtɪd]', 'adj.浮肿的；发胀的；傲慢的；熏制的 动词bloat的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. Her face is bloated and squarish. 她的脸浮肿成方形了。 2. His face became a purplish, bloated ruin resembling a fungus-growth. 他的面孔因此变成了一片浮肿而略带紫色的废墟，看起来就像一个涨大的蘑菇。 3. Due to indigestion, the baby is a little bloated. 由于消化不良，宝宝有点胀肚。 4. And then, the red-eyed devil will rule the frothing nothingness that remains, bloated and content. 然后这个玩红了眼的魔王就傲慢且心满意足地统治着这片什么也不剩的虚无的世界。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('circuitous', '[sər\'kjuːɪtəs]', 'adj.迂回的；绕行的', '1. The more circuitous route would be the quickest. 采取比较迂回的路线，可能是捷径。 2. Many alien plants have become introduced by highly circuitous routes. 许多外来植物是通过极其迂回曲折的道路引进的。 3. They took a circuitous route to avoid reporters. 他们绕道避开了记者。 4. We had to take a circuitous route because of an accident on the turnpike. 由于收费公路上发生了事故,我们不得不绕路走。', '副词: circuitously 名词: circuity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unconscious', '[ʌn\'kɑːnʃəs]', 'adj.失去知觉的；无意的', '1. He lay unconscious in a pool of blood. 他失去知觉，躺在血泊之中。 2. This wounded soldier was unconscious from his loss of blood. 这名伤员由于失血过多而昏迷不醒。 3. He is unconscious of having made a serious error. 他未察觉到已犯了严重的错误。 4. I was unconscious of her presence. 我不知道她在场。', '副词: unconsciously 名词: unconsciousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('throne', '[θroʊn]', 'n.王位；君主', '1. Henry IV usurped the throne of England. 亨利四世篡夺了英国的王位。 2. He set up a claim to the throne. 他自称王位是属于他的。 3. He was only eight when he ascended the throne. 他登上王位时才八岁。 4. He swore allegiance to the throne. 他宣誓效忠国王。', '过去式: throned 过去分词: throned 现在分词: throning 第三人称单数: thrones');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pamphlet', '[\'pæmflət]', 'n.小册子', '1. He gave me a pamphlet for my call numbers. 他给了我一个小册子记录电话号码。 2. The pamphlet was written to his party. 这本小册子是特地为他的政党所写的。', '形容词: pamphletary');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('promote', '[prə\'moʊt]', 'vt.促进；提升；升迁；发起；促销，推销', '1. They discussed how to promote cooperation between the two countries. 他们讨论如何促进两国间的合作。 2. He has been promoted to general manager. 他已被提升为总经理。 3. He failed to get promoted for lack of resolution. 他因缺乏果断力而未能得到升迁。 4. He promoted a campaign to remind the public of protecting the wildlife. 他发起了一项旨在提醒人们保护野生动物的活动。', '形容词: promotable 名词: promotability 过去式: promoted 过去分词: promoted 现在分词: promoting 第三人称单数: promotes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sculpt', '[skʌlpt]', 'v.雕刻 n.雕刻；雕塑；雕刻品；雕塑品', '1. I\'ve ever had time to sculpt a bust of my father and to burnish it. 我甚至花时候雕了一尊我父亲的半身像，并把它擦得锃亮。 2. If I\'m trapped here. I could always sculpt a statue out of this beam! 如果我被困在这了，我可以常常用这个木梁刻雕像！ 3. The sculpt is so diaphanous. 这雕刻品造型挺别致，有点意思。', '过去式: sculpted 过去分词: sculpted 现在分词: sculpting 第三人称单数: sculpts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('jocular', '[\'dʒɑːkjələr]', 'adj.打趣的；滑稽的；诙谐的', '1. Halsey gave Victor Henry a jocular prod with two fingers. 海尔赛打趣地用两个手指戳了维克多·亨利一下。 2. William\'s jocular personality makes him a very popular person. 威廉风趣的个性使他成为广受欢迎的人。 3. He is a jocular man, especially around women. 他是个诙谐的人，特别当著女人的面时。', '副词: jocularly 名词: jocularity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('acquired', '[ə\'kwaɪəd]', 'adj.已取得的；已获得的；已成习惯的 动词acquire的过去式和过去分词.', '1. Our conclusions are based on all acquired knowledge, rather than on guesses or imagination. 我们的结论基于全部可获得的知识，而不是基于猜测和想象。 2. Smoking and alcoholic drinks are an acquired taste and are not in born. 抽烟喝酒的嗜好并不与生俱来,而是后天养成的。 3. She sought out and acquired all his early paintings. 她找到并获得了他早期画的所有的画儿。 4. She had acquired much wisdom during her long life. 她经年累月造就了很高的智慧。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('aria', '[\'ɑːriə]', 'n.咏叹调；唱腔', '1. The opera was marred by an awkward aria. 整部歌剧毁在咏叹调部分的不够熟练。 2. This song takes off from a famous aria. 这首歌仿效一首著名的咏叹调。 3. The audience applauded after the soprano sang the aria so beautifully. 女高音将咏叹调唱得十分完美,观众爆发出热烈的掌声。 4. This aria is soft and melodious. 这段唱腔流畅而圆浑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('trophy', '[\'troʊfi]', 'n.奖品；战利品 adj.显示身份的；有威望的', '1. She won a silver trophy for shooting. 她在射击比赛中获得银奖。 2. The trophy was bestowed upon the winner. 奖品授给了优胜者。 3. They wanted to take his scalp as a trophy. 他们想拿他的头皮当作战利品。 4. The hunter put the lion\'s head on the wall as a trophy. 猎人把狮子的头挂在墙上当纪念品。 5. Nick always wanted to lead a trophy life. 尼克一直想过耀眼的生活。', '名词复数: trophies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('repel', '[rɪ\'pel]', 'vt.排斥；抵制；击退；使反感 vi.排斥；反感', '1. The positive poles of two magnets repel each other. 两块磁铁的正极互相排斥。 2. They stood prepared to repel any attack. 他们准备好打退一切进攻。 3. The crew repelled the attack. 船员击退了进攻。 4. A country must have the will to repel any invader. 一个国家得有决心击退任何入侵者。 5. The positive poles of two magnets repel each other. 两块磁铁的正极互相排斥。', '名词: repeller 过去式: repelled 过去分词: repelled 现在分词: repelling 第三人称单数: repels');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('phial', '[\'faɪəl]', 'n.小药瓶；小玻璃瓶', '1. He left the room,and returned in five minutes with a phial. 他离开房间，不到五分钟，拿着一只小药瓶回来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lateral', '[\'lætərəl]', 'adj.侧面的；横向的；旁边的 n.侧面；[语]侧音 vi.完成横向穿越', '1. The slight keel and lateral rail design provide directional stability and excellent tracking. 船身轻微倾起及侧面的扶手设计均有助转向及航行时高稳定性。 2. For the lateral movement of solids we again need to specify a mechanism. 对固体颗粒的横向运动，我们还需提出一种机制。 3. set fire to sth 4. Lateral renal malrotation is relatively uncommon. 摘要侧面肾脏异常旋转是相当少见。', '副词: laterally 过去式: lateraled/lateralled 过去分词: lateraled/lateralled 现在分词: lateraling/lateralling 第三人称单数: laterals/laterals');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('generate', '[\'dʒenəreɪt]', 'vt.产生；发生；引起', '1. 75% of France\'s electricity is generated by nuclear reactors. 法国75%25的电能产生于核反应堆。 2. We can\'t generate enough power for the entire city. 我们不能为整个城市产生足够的能量。 3. We need someone to generate new ideas. 我们需要有人出新主意。 4. This hatred was generated by racial prejudice. 这种仇恨是由种族偏见引起的。', '过去式: generated 过去分词: generated 现在分词: generating 第三人称单数: generates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ambush', '[\'æmbʊʃ]', 'n.埋伏；伏兵 v.埋伏；伏击', '1. He suspected an ambush. 他感到有埋伏。 2. They laid an ambush for the enemy patrol. 他们埋伏起来准备伏击巡逻的敌人。 3. The ambush was a dozen well-armed men. 以少数武装兵做伏兵。 4. If we go in after them, they can ambush us easily. 只要我们跟进去，他们就能轻易地打我们一个埋伏。', '名词: ambusher 过去式: ambushed 过去分词: ambushed 现在分词: ambushing 第三人称单数: ambushes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ritzy', '[\'rɪtsi]', 'adj.豪华的；高雅的；时髦的', '1. This is a really ritzy hotel,isn\'t it? 这真是间豪华的旅馆，不是吗？ 2. That\'s really a ritzy dress. 那真是条时髦的裙子。', '比较级: ritzier 最高级: ritziest');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ivory', '[\'aɪvəri]', 'n.象牙；乳白色', '1. The men trafficked with the natives for ivory. 这些人与土着居民做买卖以换取象牙。 2. The professor lived in an ivory tower. 这个教授生活在象牙塔中。 3. His nails resemble the ivory keys of the spinet. 他的指甲象白色的琴键一样。', '名词复数: ivories');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('grit', '[ɡrɪt]', 'n.砂砾；粗砂石；勇气；决心 vt.覆以砂砾；咬紧牙关 vi.发出刺耳声', '1. Grit is spread on roads to make them less slippery in icy weather. 在结冰的天气，在路上撒上砂砾心免路面太滑。 2. Because all the gears are enclosed within the hub, road grit can\'t get inside to abrade the metal parts. 因为所有的齿轮都套在轮毂内，路面上的砂石不会跑进齿轮之间磨损金属部件。 3. The soldiers showed that they had plenty of grit. 士兵们表现得很有勇气。 4. Mountaineering in a blizzard needs a lot of grit. 在暴风雪中登山需要极大的勇气和毅力。 5. You have to grit your teeth and work hard. 你一定要咬紧牙关，努力工作。', '过去式: gritted 过去分词: gritted 现在分词: gritting 第三人称单数: grits');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('convoluted', '[\'kɑːnvəluːtɪd]', 'adj.旋绕的；费解的 动词convolute的过去式和过去分词.', '1. For us, justice is only an aspiration because we don\'t have the money to get through the convoluted legal system that seems to have been built to help lawyers make money. 对我们来说，公正仅仅是一种渴望，因为我们没有钱去完成令人费解的法律过程，这个法律体系看起来似乎是为了帮助律师赚钱而建立起来的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('statute', '[\'stætʃuːt]', 'n.法令；法规；条例', '1. Working hours are limited by statute. 工作时间有法令限制。 2. The sole purpose of this statute is to promote mining. 这项法令的唯一目的就是要促进矿业开采。 3. We must obey the statutes in this country. 我们必须遵守这个国家的法规。 4. Penalties are laid down in the statute. 法规中有关于惩罚措施的规定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('notch', '[nɑːtʃ]', 'n.刻痕；等级；切口 vt.赢得；刻凹痕；计分', '1. I cut a notch in a stick. 我在一根棍子上刻了一个V字形。 2. He acted up to the notch in that matter. 那件事他干得很出色。 3. This one is a notch better than the other. 这一个要比那一个高一等。 4. The monitor is really a notch above us. 班长确实比我们略胜一筹。 5. He is keen to notch up yet another success. 他渴望能再次成功。', '过去式: notched 过去分词: notched 现在分词: notching 第三人称单数: notches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gab', '[ɡæb]', 'n.饶舌；爱说话；多嘴 v.空谈；瞎扯；唠叨', '1. Stop your gab! 别闲聊了！ 2. Colin should make a good salesman; he\'s got the gift of the gab and persistence. 科林应该能成为一名出色的推销员,他伶牙俐齿而且很有毅力。 3. I have no toleration for his gab. 我不能忍受他的唠叨。 4. I hate it when people gab in movie theaters. 我讨厌在电影院看电影总是说个没完的人。', '名词: gabber 过去式: gabbed 过去分词: gabbed 现在分词: gabbing 第三人称单数: gabs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('avarice', '[\'ævərɪs]', 'n.贪财；贪婪', '1. The old man shows great avarice for money. 这个老头视钱如命。 2. Avarice drove him into theft. 贪婪驱使他偷窃。 3. Avarice is the root of all evils. 贪婪是万恶之源。 4. He fell victim to his own avarice. 他由于贪婪而自食其果。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('recess', '[rɪ\'ses]', 'n.休息；幽深处；凹缝；壁龛；放假 v.放入壁龛；作凹处；休息', '1. They have no recreation or recess in their work. 他们并没有休息或停工时间。 2. He approached imperceptibly the gloomy recess. 他不知不觉地走到了幽暗的山岔。 3. I push the problem down into the dim recess of my mind. 我把这个问题藏到内心深处，不去多想它。 4. The attic sloped down from the centre, and the trunk was lying in a far recess. 阁楼从中央倾斜而下，这个木箱正好放在远端的壁龛里。 5. The conference will recess till tomorrow morning. 会议暂时休会，明天上午继续开会。', '过去式: recessed 过去分词: recessed 现在分词: recessing 第三人称单数: recesses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('numismatist', '[nuː\'mɪzmətɪst]', 'n.钱币奖章收藏家；钱币学家', '1. Numismatist:You completed the collection of coins. 货币学家：你完成了货币的搜集。 2. 83、Numismatist:You completed the collection of coins. 货币学家：你完成了货币的搜集。 3. numismatist n. 钱币收藏家；', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('patronage', '[\'pætrənɪdʒ]', 'n.赞助；光顾；任免权', '1. I am sorry to say that my patronage ends with this. 很抱歉，我的赞助只能到此为止。 2. The theatre is under the patronage of the art council. 那剧院得到了艺术委员会的赞助。 3. We respectfully solicit your continuous patronage. 恭请继续光顾。 4. Customer patronage, however, can be facilitated if there are similar stores in the same locale. 然而，如果在一个地方有一些类似的商店，顾客会更容易光顾。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('psychology', '[saɪ\'kɑːlədʒi]', 'n.心理；心理学', '1. I can\'t understand that man\'s psychology. 我无法理解那个人的心理。 2. She had no personal life and no private psychology. 她没有个人的生活和隐秘的心理活动。 3. Many people failed in the psychology test. 很多人在心理测试环节被淘汰。 4. This is fluky psychology, also be pure belong to accidental. 这是侥幸心理，亦是纯属偶然。', '名词复数: psychologies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('terrace', '[\'terəs]', 'n.平台；阳台；梯田 vt.使成梯田；给 ... 建阳台', '1. We sat on the terrace in the evening. 晚上我们坐在平台上。 2. The terrace afforded a fine view. 从屋顶平台上可以看到美好的景色。 3. Do you wish to sit at a table on the terrace? 你想坐在阳台上的桌旁吗? 4. The terrace channels are convenient for irrigation. 梯田的沟渠便于灌溉。 5. You may have to terrace your land or build raised beds. 你可能需要把地弄成梯田状，或是垫高。', '过去式: terraced 过去分词: terraced 现在分词: terracing 第三人称单数: terraces');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('indigence', '[\'ɪndədʒəns]', 'n.贫穷', '1. Dickens contrasts the opulence of France\'s nobility with indigence of her peasants. 锹更斯比较法兰西贵族的富裕与其农民的贫穷。 2. By hard work, many Americans have raised themselves from indigence to wealth. 许多美国人通过辛勤的工作，从贫穷变得富有。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('convergent', '[kən\'vɜːrdʒənt]', 'adj.趋集于一点的；会聚性的；收敛的', '1. On this basis, a convergent interactive programming algorithm is developed in this paper for solving these nonlinear multiobjective group decision making problems. 由此，建立了一个求解非线性多目标群体决策问题的收敛的交互规划算法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('accrete', '[ə\'kriːt]', 'v.共生；附着；增加', '1. However, if a black hole passes through a cloud of interstellar matter, or is close to another \"normal\" star, the black hole can accrete matter into itself. 然而，当一个黑洞穿过一片星云，或者靠近另一个正常恒星时，黑洞将会使它自身的物质增加。', '过去式: accreted 过去分词: accreted 现在分词: accreting 第三人称单数: accretes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('trim', '[trɪm]', 'v.修剪；削减；装饰；调整帆以适应风向 adj.整洁的；匀称的 n.修剪；整齐；装饰', '1. I\'ll have my hair trimmed tomorrow. 明天我要修剪头发。 2. We have to trim our cost if we want to increase our profit. 我们如果想增加利润，就必须削减开支。 3. They trim their Christmas trees with strings of colored lights. 他们用一串串的彩灯装饰圣诞树。 4. The crew is in trim for the boat-race. 船员们都准备就绪，等待比赛的开始。 5. The new house has a trim appearance. 那幢房子有整洁的外观。 6. I\'d just like a trim and don\'t make it too short. 只需要修剪一下，不要修得太短。', '副词: trimly 比较级: trimmer 最高级: trimmest 名词: trimness 过去式: trimmed 过去分词: trimmed 现在分词: trimming 第三人称单数: trims');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('consul', '[\'kɑːnsl]', 'n.领事；（古罗马）执行官员；（1799年至1804年间法国的）三名主要执政官之一', '1. He is applying to the Consul for a visa. 他正向领事申请签证。 2. The Consul frowned, nodded, and turned away. 领事蹙紧眉头，点点头，转身离去。', '形容词: consular 名词: consulship');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ambidextrous', '[ˌæmbi\'dekstrəs]', 'adj.双手都灵巧的；熟练的', '1. A switch-hitter in baseball should be naturally ambidextrous. 左右开弓的棒球运动员自然是两手都善用的。 2. I\'m neither left-handed nor right-handed; I\'m ambidextrous. 我不是只用左手或右手,我是双手并用。 3. Able to use both hands with equal facility; ambidextrous. 两只手都能发挥相同作用的；双手灵巧的 4. I\'m neither left-handed nor right-handed ； I\'m ambidextrous. 我女儿是双手灵活的人，因为她左右手都能画。', '副词: ambidextrously');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('arrest', '[ə\'rest]', 'vt.逮捕；拘留 n.逮捕；拘留', '1. The police arrested the thief. 警察逮捕了小偷。 2. You shouldn\'t arrest him without warrant. 你不能毫无根据地逮捕他。 3. The constable stop the car and arrest the driver. 警官使车停住并将司机扣留。 4. The riot led to the arrest of three young men. 暴乱导致3 个年轻人被捕。', '名词: arrester 过去式: arrested 过去分词: arrested 现在分词: arresting 第三人称单数: arrests');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('compensate', '[\'kɑːmpenseɪt]', 'v.补偿；赔偿；付报酬', '1. Nothing can compensate for the loss of one\'s health. 什么都不能补偿健康受损。 2. She was compensated by the insurance company for her injuries. 她受伤后获得保险公司的赔偿。 3. You will have to compensate us for the loss. 你必须赔偿我们的损失。', '形容词: compensative 名词: compensator 过去式: compensated 过去分词: compensated 现在分词: compensating 第三人称单数: compensates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bodyguard', '[\'bɑːdiɡɑːrd]', 'n.警卫员；保卫人员；保镖', '1. The Premier\'s bodyguard was waiting there. 首相的护卫人员在那儿等着。 2. The big guystanding at his side may be his bodyguard. 站在他身旁的那个大个子可能是他的保镖。 3. His bodyguard leapt into action. 他的保镖立即采取行动。 4. The big guy standing at his side may be his bodyguard. 站在他身旁的那个大个子可能是他的保镖。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ensnare', '[ɪn\'sner]', 'v.诱捕；诱入圈套；陷害', '1. To ensnare or prevail over with trickery. 诈骗用诡计使相信或说服 2. Entangling Roots and Ensnare work on Heroes again. 树根缠绕和诱捕再次对英雄有效。 3. To catch in or as if in a net; ensnare. 诱入陷阱用网捕捉或似用网状物捕捉;诱捕。 4. To catch in or as if in a trap;ensnare. 设陷阱用陷阱或类似用陷阱的方式捕获;设陷阱捕捉', '异体字: insnare 名词: ensnarement 过去式: ensnared 过去分词: ensnared 现在分词: ensnaring 第三人称单数: ensnares');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('varnish', '[\'vɑːrnɪʃ]', 'n.油漆；掩饰；光泽面；指甲油 v.粉饰；涂油漆于；使光亮', '1. The varnish was made to imitate wood grain. 油漆刷出来像木纹。 2. She covers her selfishness with a varnish of good manners. 她用一种表面上很有礼貌的态度来掩饰她的自私。 3. The hot plate may spoil the varnish on the table. 这只热盘子会损坏桌面的光泽。 4. I chipped my nail varnish when I was cooking. 我烧菜的时候，指甲油脱落了。 5. He tried to varnish over the truth with a lie. 他试图用谎言来掩盖真相。', '名词: varnisher 过去式: varnished 过去分词: varnished 现在分词: varnishing 第三人称单数: varnishes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fault', '[fɔːlt]', 'n.缺点；故障；过错；[地]断层 v.找 ... 错误', '1. I like him despite his faults. 虽然他有很多缺点，我仍然喜欢他。 2. He has many faults, but vanity is not one of them. 他有很多缺点，但并没有虚荣心。 3. There is a fault in the electrical system. 电路系统出了故障。 4. It was not our fault that we were late. 这次迟到不是我们的错。 5. No one could fault his performance. 他的演出无懈可击.', '过去式: faulted 过去分词: faulted 现在分词: faulting 第三人称单数: faults');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('enflame', '[ɪn\'fleɪm]', 'v.（使）激怒；（使）燃烧；（使）发炎 =inflame.', '1. The administration worries that the talks could further enflame the national debate. 可译为“政府担心,这种会谈可能进一步触发全国性大辩论”。 2. Brief, solid, affirmative as a hammer blow, this is the virile word, which must enflame lips and save the honor of our people, in these unfortunate days of anachronistic imperialism. 强有力的回答“不”像锤击声那样短暂、有力、干脆，这就是在帝国主义横行霸道的不幸日子里该从我们口中愤怒地喷发而出，用以挽救我们民族尊严的词。 3. 1.Brief, solid, affirmative as a hammer blow, this is the virile word, which must enflame lips and save the honor of our people, in these unfortunate days of anachronistic imperialism. 强有力的回答“不”像锤击声那样短暂、有力、干脆，这就是在帝国主义横行霸道的不幸日子里该从我们口中愤怒地喷发而出，用以挽救我们民族尊严的词。 4. 6.Brief, solid, affirmative as a hammer blow, this is the virile word, which must enflame lips and save the honor of our people, in these unfortunate days of anachronistic imperialism. 强有力的回答“不”像锤击声那样短暂、有力、干脆，这就是在帝国主义横行霸道的不幸日子里该从我们口中愤怒地喷发而出，用以挽救我们民族尊严的词。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('palpitate', '[\'pælpɪteɪt]', 'vi.悸动；心跳；发抖', '1. Spread the palpitate frequency love till ending. 循着心跳的频率爱到永不分离。 2. To still be palpitate after all of days. 过去多日了仍然为此心跳. 3. How is giddy palpitate handled after drunk wine? 醉酒后头晕心慌怎么处理呢？ 4. Is congenital palpitate the conceal phenomenon of heart disease? 先天性心慌是心脏病的潜伏现象吗？', '副词: palpitatingly 过去式: palpitated 过去分词: palpitated 现在分词: palpitating 第三人称单数: palpitates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('adumbrate', '[\'ædəmbreɪt]', 'v.画轮廓；预示', '1. Lung cancer has what symptom, have adumbrate? 肺癌有哪些症状，有预兆吗？ 2. What does cancer have to adumbrate? 癌症有什么预兆？ 3. Via what there is does first time forthcoming month adumbrate? 第一次来月经有什么预兆吗？ 4. The recent development adumbrate a world-wide revolution in computer technology. 最新事态的发展预示着一场全球性的计算机技术革命。', '形容词: adumbrative 副词: adumbratively 名词: adumbration 过去式: adumbrated 过去分词: adumbrated 现在分词: adumbrating 第三人称单数: adumbrates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('clement', '[\'klemənt]', 'adj.仁慈的；温和的', '1. A clement judge reduced his sentence. 一位仁慈的法官为他减了刑。', '副词: clemently');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nucleate', '[\'njuːklɪˌeɪt]', 'v.(使)成核；(使)集结 adj.有核的', '1. The observations are that birefringent needles tend to nucleate heterogeneously. 用光学显微镜可以跟踪到随着时间的推移，这种结构的成核和自组装的过程。', '名词: nucleation 过去式: nucleated 过去分词: nucleated 现在分词: nucleating 第三人称单数: nucleates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('strand', '[strænd]', 'n.缕；(线等的)股；海滨，河岸，海滩 v.使陷于困境；弄断；使落后；（使）搁浅', '1. She twirled a strand of hair round her finger. 她把一绺头发卷绕在手指上。 2. One strand of silk doesn\'t make a thread; one tree doesn\'t make a forest. 单丝不成线,独木不成林。', '过去式: stranded 过去分词: stranded 现在分词: stranding 第三人称单数: strands');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('titanic', '[taɪ\'tænɪk]', 'adj.巨大的；[化]钛的 n.[T-]泰坦尼克号（船名）', '1. Four days after the Titanic set out, a very big iceberg floated towards her. 泰坦尼克号出发四天以后，一座巨大的冰山向它漂来。 2. The Titanic and all her crew were in Davy Jones\'s locker. 泰坦尼克号及其全体船员均都葬身鱼腹。 3. He owns a detailed miniature of the Titanic. 他有一艘泰坦尼克号的精致小模型。', '副词: titanically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('untapped', '[ˌʌn\'tæpt]', 'adj.塞子未开的；未使用的', '1. An untapped cask of wine is stored quite well. 一桶未去塞的酒储存的很好。 2. Wind is an untapped energy resource. 风力是未使用的能源。 3. Kids have a natural sense of industry that goes largely untapped. 孩子们身上有一种在很大程度上未被开发的勤奋天赋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('demarcate', '[\'diːmɑːrkeɪt]', 'v.划分；划界', '1. The playing area is demarcated by a white line. 运动场地以白线为界。', '名词: demarcator 过去式: demarcated 过去分词: demarcated 现在分词: demarcating 第三人称单数: demarcates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dissect', '[dɪ\'sekt]', 'v.解剖；切细；仔细研究；详细分析', '1. In biology class we had to dissect a frog. 上生物课时我们得解剖青蛙。 2. In spite of this some brave scientists did dissect bodies. 尽管如此，一些勇敢的科学家仍坚持解剖人体。', '形容词: dissectible 名词: dissector 过去式: dissected 过去分词: dissected 现在分词: dissecting 第三人称单数: dissects');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('plead', '[pliːd]', 'v.辩护；恳求；提出借口；认罪', '1. You should get a lawyer to plead for your case. 你该请一位律师为你的案子辩护。 2. I heard him plead in court only once. 我只有一次听到他在法庭上作辩护。 3. With that kind of man you will plead in vain. 你恳求那种人将是白费力气。 4. He would see her and plead his cause again in person. 他要去见她，当面再度恳求。', '形容词: pleadable 副词: pleadingly 名词: pleader 过去式: pleaded/pled 过去分词: pleaded/pled 现在分词: pleading 第三人称单数: pleads');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('harry', '[\'hæri]', 'vt.不断骚扰；打扰；侵扰；侵掠 n.哈里（人名）', '1. We have to harry him for money. 我们不得不常常缠着他要钱。 2. The tax authorities have been harrying her for repayment. 税务当局不断逼她缴税。 3. He was harried by constant bothering of his fans. 他的崇拜者的不断打扰令他十分苦恼。 4. The army harried the enemy\'s border. 军队不断地袭扰敌方的边境。', '过去式: harried 过去分词: harried 现在分词: harrying 第三人称单数: harries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('revealing', '[rɪ\'viːlɪŋ]', 'adj.有启迪作用的；透露内情的；袒露身体的 动词reveal的现在分词.', '1. And when this book is found,the ice shall melt from this place, revealing starships created by this pyramid,left behind as reminders of their work and interaction on your planet. 而当发现这本书的时候，经由这金字塔创造有启迪作用的恒星飞船，作为他们工作的暗示者留在后面以及同你们的行星相互作用。 2. Some say that this does not matter, because the process of doing the analysis is more important and revealing than the results of the analysis themselves. 有人说这无关紧要，因为分析的过程比分析结果本身更为重要，也更有启迪作用。', '副词: revealingly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('perspire', '[pər\'spaɪər]', 'v.出汗；流汗；分泌', '1. On the scorching summer day, he who is apt to sweat will perspire heavily. 炎炎夏日，爱出汗的他挥汗成雨。 2. If a person is inclined to perspire, does this affect the impact of fragrance? 如果一个人容易出汗，会影响香水的效果吗？', '过去式: perspired 过去分词: perspired 现在分词: perspiring 第三人称单数: perspires');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('oust', '[aʊst]', 'v.逐出；夺取；取代', '1. The umpire ousted the arguing player from the game. 裁判员将那位不服判决的运动员罚下场。 2. Fox was ousted from office but he had nothing to say for himself. 福克斯被赶下台，但是他没有什么可特别为自己辨护的。 3. The rebels finally managed to oust the government from power. 反叛者最后总算夺取了政权。 4. I \'m sorry to say nothing could oust a computer. 很遗憾，什么也不可能取代计算机。', '过去式: ousted 过去分词: ousted 现在分词: ousting 第三人称单数: ousts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('insouciant', '[ɪn\'suːsiənt]', 'adj.漫不经心的；漠不关心的', '1. Americans are remarkably insouciant about this development. 美国人对这个数字漫无关心。 2. But not all central bankers are so insouciant. 然而，不是所有的央行人士都对此高枕无忧。 3. His insouciant handling of the oil spill in the Gulf is under fire from all sides. 他处理波斯湾漏油事件的漫不经心遭至各路讨伐。', '副词: insouciantly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sweltering', '[\'sweltərɪŋ]', 'adj.酷热的', '1. On sweltering summer days, sleeping is just fine. 夏日炎炎正好眠。', '副词: swelteringly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('waddle', '[\'wɑːdl]', 'v.蹒跚而行；摇摇摆摆地走 n.摇摆的步子；蹒跚', '1. A short plump woman came waddling along the pavement. 有个矮胖女子一摇一摆地沿人行道走来。 2. It was very funny the way in which the penguins used to waddle . 企鹅走路的那样子真是滑稽。 3. He headed towards her at a breakneck waddle. 他一摇一摆迅速朝她身边跑去。', '名词: waddler 过去式: waddled 过去分词: waddled 现在分词: waddling 第三人称单数: waddles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('optimist', '[\'ɑːptɪmɪst]', 'n.乐观主义者', '1. Then, an unbending optimist bought the company. 后来一位坚决的乐观主义者收购了这家公司。 2. So it\'s safe to say I\'m an aggressive optimist. 所以可以说我是个有进取心的乐观主义者。', '形容词: optimistic 副词: optimistically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hermit', '[\'hɜːrmɪt]', 'n.隐士；遁世者', '1. A hermit used to live in the cave. 一位隐士曾经住在那个山洞里。 2. The old hermit was very cagey about her past life. 老隐士对自己过去的生活守口如瓶。', '形容词: hermitic 副词: hermitically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tackiness', '[\'tækinəs]', 'n.粘性；胶粘性', '1. It can improve the tackiness of finishing coats. 涂层耐刮性和耐曲绕性优秀。 2. Reduced tackiness and stickiness during and after application. 在使用中或使用后能减少粘性。 3. It has good tackiness, elasticity, flexibility and penetration. 该产品具有良好遮盖性，但不会过分填充，压花性能好，不会切浆。 4. Influence of tackiness agent mixture ratio and the dosage of frothier, padding and adhesive proportion on foaming body performance were studied. 试验研究了发泡剂、填充物、胶粘剂的用量，以及胶粘剂的配比对发泡体性能的影响。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hydrate', '[\'haɪdreɪt]', 'n.水化物 v.（使）水合', '1. Chloral hydrate is a rapidly effective hypnotic. 水合氯醛为一种作用迅速的催眠药。 2. Shea &Rose Hip gently hydrate &add gloss. 玫瑰果籽及雪亚脂令你的头发水泽光滑。 3. Natural Gas Hydrate: the savior of energy crises? 可燃冰:能源危机的拯救者? 4. Methane Hydrate - an alternative fuel source? 甲烷水合物-替代燃料来源?', '名词: hydration 过去式: hydrated 过去分词: hydrated 现在分词: hydrating 第三人称单数: hydrates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pall', '[pɔːl]', 'n.遮盖物；幕；棺罩 v.变得平淡乏味；感到腻烦；覆盖；盖上棺罩', '1. A pall of mystery seem to hang over it all. 整个事件似乎笼罩上一层神秘的气氛。 2. A pall of smoke hung over the town. 市镇上空笼罩着一层烟幕。 3. An unvaried pall of cloud muffled the whole expanse of sky from zenith to horizon. 一望无际的云幕蒙住了从天顶到地乎线的整个夜空。 4. It stands on two trestles, under the pall. 它被安放在两个木架上,上面盖了一块盖棺布。 5. The pleasures of sunbathing began to pall on us after a week on the beach. 我们在沙滩上呆了一周之后，对日光浴已经兴致大减。', '过去式: palled 过去分词: palled 现在分词: palling 第三人称单数: palls');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fester', '[\'festər]', 'v.溃烂；化脓；恶化 n.脓疮；溃烂', '1. A dirty wound will probably fester. 一个弄脏了的伤口,可能会化脓。 2. It\'s lucky that the wound did not fester. 幸好伤口没有化脓。 3. The crisis will fester. 危机将会进一步恶化。 4. A broken bone can heal, but the wound a word opens can fester forever. 骨头断了可以治愈好，但是言语造成的伤害将会一直恶化下去。', '过去式: festered 过去分词: festered 现在分词: festering 第三人称单数: festers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('debris', '[də\'briː]', 'n.碎片；残骸', '1. Falling debris rained on us from above. 碎片从上面像雨点儿一样落在我们身上。 2. They hunted through the debris on the floor to find the ring. 他们找遍了地板上的碎片去找戒指。 3. The sea throws up all sorts of debris on the beach. 大海把各种残骸碎片都冲上海滩。 4. Emergency teams are still clearing the debris from the plane crash. 各抢救小组仍在清理失事飞机的残骸。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('emend', '[i\'mend]', 'vt.修订；校订', '1. Many men are needed to emend this book. 修订这本书需要许多人手。', '名词: emender 过去式: emended 过去分词: emended 现在分词: emending 第三人称单数: emends');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('perigee', '[\'perɪdʒiː]', 'n.近地点；最近点', '1. The Moon reaches its absolute perigee once a year. 月球每年有一次达到它的绝对近地点。 2. When perigee and perihelion coincide tidal range is at its greatest. 当月球与地球到达它们的近地点和近日点的时间恰好重合时，就会引起最大的潮汐。', '形容词: perigeal');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('casualty', '[\'kæʒuəlti]', 'n.事故；伤亡者；伤亡人数；<英>急诊室', '1. The cottage was a casualty of the forest fire. 那小屋被森林大火烧毁。 2. She read through the casualty list anxiously. 她忧虑地把伤亡人员名单从头到尾看了一遍。 3. The casualty of the traffic accident was a doleful record. 这一交通事故地伤亡人数是一个令人伤心的记录.', '名词复数: casualties');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('extract', '[\'ekstrækt]', 'vt.摘录；提取；拔出；榨出；选取 [计算机] 提取. n.摘录；精华；榨出物', '1. She extracted passages for the students to translate. 她选了些短文让学生翻译. 2. She extracted a small notebook from her handbag. 她从手提包里取出了一个小笔记本。 3. He tried to extract his pole from the mud. 他试图用力将杆子从泥中拔出来。 4. It takes a major operation to extract money from a minor poet. 要从小诗人那儿榨出钱来，得施行一次大手术。 5. I would like to quote two extracts from the book. 我很想引用这本书的两段文字。', '形容词: extractable 名词: extractor 过去式: extracted 过去分词: extracted 现在分词: extracting 第三人称单数: extracts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incipient', '[ɪn\'sɪpiənt]', 'adj.起初的；初期的', '1. There are signs of incipient labour market weakness. 有迹象表明，就业市场初显疲软之态。 2. Regulators are already acting to head off incipient problems. 监管部门已经开始行动，将问题消灭在萌芽阶段。 3. She felt for him an incipient tenderness, but scarcely any passion. 她对他的好感只是一种刚刚萌芽的柔情，还根本谈不上什么爱情。 4. What we see then is an incipient global inflation. 我们看到的是初期阶段的全球通胀。', '副词: incipiently 名词: incipiency');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('instill', '[ɪn\'stɪl]', 'vt.逐渐灌输；滴注', '1. The idea was gradually instilled in the mind of the young prince. 那种思想已逐渐灌输到了年幼的王子的头脑中。 2. Fear of the father is instilled into some children from their infancy. 有的小孩从小就慢慢养成害怕父亲的心理。 3. We must instill a sense of duty in our children. 我们必须在我们的孩子当中灌输一种责任感。 4. The nursery teacher instilled the need for kindness into my children. 幼儿园教师不断地向孩子们灌输仁慈的必要。', '名词: instillation');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fabric', '[\'fæbrɪk]', 'n.结构；织物；构造', '1. The whole fabric of the society was changed by the war. 战争改变了整个社会结构。 2. The cost of repairing the fabric of the church was very high. 修理教堂结构的花费非常大。 3. This fabric has a tear in it. 这织物上有个破洞。 4. The fabric was displayed on a wired stand. 那种织物陈列在金属制的架子上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vague', '[veɪɡ]', 'adj.不明确的；模糊的；茫然的；犹豫不决的', '1. At the back of his mind was the vague idea that he had met her before. 他隐隐约约地觉得以前曾经见过她。 2. She is so vague that I can never understand what she is trying to say. 她说话含含糊糊，我怎么也听不明白她想说些什么。 3. His vague ideas crystallized into a definite plan. 他那些模糊的想法变成了一个明确的计划。 4. I\'m quite vague about what happened. 我对发生的事很不了解。', '副词: vaguely 比较级: vaguer 最高级: vaguest 名词: vagueness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ejaculate', '[i\'dʒækjuleɪt]', 'v.射精；射出；突然说出', '1. In later years, the urge to ejaculate becomes less pressing. 在后来的岁月里，射精的强烈欲望减弱了。', '名词: ejaculator 过去式: ejaculated 过去分词: ejaculated 现在分词: ejaculating 第三人称单数: ejaculates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unregulated', '[ˌʌn\'reɡjuleɪtɪd]', 'adj.不规范的；紊乱的；不受管理的', '1. She has violent and unregulated nature. 她生性狂放，不受拘束。 2. This fully shows that unregulated market economy is doomed to not work. 这充分说明，不受管理的市场经济是注定行不通的。 3. For centuries, it was an unregulated, unsystematic business. 数百年来，这都是一个混乱、无系统的行业。 4. If we followed him, all risk management would become unregulated. 如果我们按照他的思路，所有的风险管理都将变得不受监管。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('antithesis', '[æn\'tɪθəsɪs]', 'n.对照；正相反；对比法', '1. Slavery is the antithesis of freedom. 奴役与自由是对立的。 2. The antithesis of death is life. 与死相对的是生。 3. The style of his speech was in complete antithesis to mine. 他和我的讲话方式完全相反。', '名词复数: antitheses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('disdain', '[dɪs\'deɪn]', 'n.轻蔑 v.蔑视', '1. Laval brushed this aside with disdain. 赖伐尔以轻蔑的态度拒绝了。 2. The receptionist looked at me with disdain when I walked into Suffolk College asking to enrol. 当我走进萨克福大学，要求报读时，接待员用轻蔑的眼神看着我。 3. He disdained that man for snobbishness and was unwilling to talk to him. 他鄙视那个势利小人，不愿和他说话。', '过去式: disdained 过去分词: disdained 现在分词: disdaining 第三人称单数: disdains');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('canard', '[kə\'nɑːrd]', 'n.谣言；误传；鸭式飞机', '1. That canard was proved to be true later. 那谣言后来被证明是真的。 2. I hoped everybody could not be disturbed by canard and slapstick. 我希望大家不要被谣言和闹剧打扰。 3. Who said that I got married. That is a canard. 谁说我结婚了，那是个谣传。 4. We remove these rear controls and install them as canard controls. 我们把尾部控制改为鸭式控制。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mendicant', '[\'mendɪkənt]', 'n.乞丐；托钵僧 adj.行乞的；托钵修道会的', '1. He seemed not a ordinary mendicant. 他好象不是寻常的乞丐。 2. Nevertheless,he used to travel as a wandering mendicant. 虽然如此，但他还是会常常像托钵僧一样旅行。', '名词: mendicancy');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('outstrip', '[ˌaʊt\'strɪp]', 'v.超过；跑过', '1. It is a case of the student outstripping the teacher. 这是一个学生超过老师的例子。 2. Demand is outstripping current production. 现在需求逐渐超过了生产能力。 3. We soon outstripped the slower runners. 我们很快就超过那些跑得慢的人。', '过去式: outstripped 过去分词: outstripped 现在分词: outstripping 第三人称单数: outstrips');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('patrician', '[pə\'trɪʃn]', 'adj.贵族的；显贵的 n.贵族', '1. Its patrician dignity was a picturesque sham. 它的贵族的尊严只是一套华丽的伪装。 2. She comes from an old patrician family. 她出身名门望族。 3. The old patrician was buried in the family vault . 这位老贵族埋在家族的墓地里。', '副词: patricianly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bouquet', '[bu\'keɪ]', 'n.花束；称赞；酒香', '1. He bought a bouquet at the florist. 他在花店买了一束花。 2. She laid the bouquet on the newly turfed grave. 她把那束花放置在新铺上草皮的坟墓上。 3. Ribbon hung from the bride\'s bouquet was tied in a bow. 从新娘的花束上垂下来的丝带打成了一个结。 4. In his speech there were bouquets for everyone who had helped him. 在他的演讲里，他赞美了每一位帮助他的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('descendant', '[dɪ\'sendənt]', 'n.后裔；子孙；后代', '1. He is a descendant of Queen Victoria. 他是维多利亚女王的后裔。 2. I am a descendant of George Washington. 我是乔治华盛顿的后代子孙。 3. A static method does not change when inherited by a descendant class. 当被子孙类继承时，静态方法并不改变。 4. The coastal areas were occupied by the descendants of Greek colonists. 沿海地带居住着希腊殖民者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rigor', '[\'rɪgə]', 'n.严格；严厉；严酷；艰苦；严密；精确；[医]寒战；僵直；强直', '1. The crime will be treated with the full rigor of the law. 这一罪行会严格依法审理。 2. The expedition suffered all the rigors of a Canadian winter. 这支探险队饱受了加拿大严冬的折磨。 3. It shows the rigor of a scientific proof. 这体现了科学实证的严密。 4. Rigor mortis had already set in. 尸体已经僵硬。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('affectation', '[ˌæfek\'teɪʃn]', 'n.假装；虚饰；做作', '1. He made an affectation of indifference. 他装出无动于衷的样子。 2. This article is written in a simple style, free from any kind of affectation. 这篇文章语言质朴，毫无矫饰。 3. I dislike the affectation of her action. 我不喜欢她做作的行为。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cipher', '[\'saɪfər]', 'n.密码；阿拉伯数字；零；暗号 v.计算；做算术；将 ... 写成密码', '1. The army uses a special cipher so that military messages are kept secret. 军队使用一种特殊密码,军事电讯因此得以保密。 2. The cipher took me three weeks before I hit it. 我费了3个多星期才把这密码解释出来。 3. Age is only a number, a cipher for the records. A man can\'t retire his experience. He must use it. Experience achieves more with less energy and time. 年龄只是个阿拉伯数字。一个人不能让他的经验退休。他必须用它。依靠经验，可以用较少的精力和时间获得更多。 4. I couldn\'t cipher out why she was there. 我搞不清她为什么会在那儿。', '过去式: ciphered 过去分词: ciphered 现在分词: ciphering 第三人称单数: ciphers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('yearn', '[jɜːrn]', 'v.渴望；想念；盼望；同情', '1. He yearned to return to his native land. 他渴望回到故乡。 2. He yearned for a sight of the old, familiar faces. 他渴望一见那些熟悉的老面孔。 3. The child yearns much toward his friends. 那小孩很想念他的朋友。 4. They yearned for his return. 他们盼望着他回来。', '副词: yearningly 名词: yearner 过去式: yearned 过去分词: yearned 现在分词: yearning 第三人称单数: yearns');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('deviant', '[\'diːviənt]', 'adj.不正常的；离经叛道的 n.异常的人', '1. Not typical, usual, or regular; not normal; deviant. 反常的，异常的非一般的、不平常的或非惯例的; 不正常的; 反常的', '名词: deviance');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('response', '[rɪ\'spɑːns]', 'n.反应；回答；响应；答复', '1. The tax cuts produced a favourable response from the public. 税额削减受到了公众的欢迎. 2. I\'m sorry; the correct response is B. 不好意思,正确回答应该是B。 3. There was an enthusiastic response to my suggestions. 我的提议得到了热情的响应。 4. 他提出指控后迅即得到答复。 他提出指控後迅即得到答覆.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('armory', '[\'ɑːmərɪ]', 'n.军械库；兵工厂', '1. We must hurry back to the Armory and get the decorating done. 我们得赶快回到军械库去，把全部的布置工作完成。 2. The armories were important in the World War II. 兵工厂在二战中是很重要的。', '名词复数: armories');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('injunction', '[ɪn\'dʒʌŋkʃn]', 'n.指令；命令；禁令', '1. When the system works, all of the parts of the system are connected and transmit injunction and data by the ways thereinafter. 系统工作时,系统各部分通过以下方式连接并且传送指令和数据。 2. He ignored the headmaster\'s injunction to be silent. 他不理睬校长要他保持安静的命令。 3. His application for an injunction was refused. 他要求法院发禁令的申请被拒绝。 4. The military government dissolved the injunction. 军政府废除了禁令。', '形容词: injunctive');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('somnolent', '[\'sɑːmnələnt]', 'adj.〈正式或文〉昏昏欲睡的；催眠的；使人瞌睡的', '1. The noise of the stream had a pleasantly somnolent effect. 小河潺潺的流水声有宜人的催眠效果。', '副词: somnolently');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ordnance', '[\'ɔːrdnəns]', 'n.大炮；军械；军需品；军械署', '1. She worked in an ordnance factory during the war. 战争期间她在一家兵工厂工作。 2. Hundreds of ordnance factories are recruiting people now. 几百家兵工企业正在面向社会招聘人才。 3. The pirate ships in the West Indies were armed with heavy ordnance. 西印度群岛的海盗船武装有大量军火。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rescript', '[\'riːskrɪpt]', 'n.法令；重写的东西', '1. This rule is set forth in the rescript of the Emperor Antoninus. 这项规定是在安东尼皇帝颁布的法令中提出的。 2. Meanwhile, he organized officials to compile the Record of Clan and issued rescript to rectify clan marriage. 同时，他组织官员修撰《氏族志》，并颁布《诫励氏族婚姻诏》等。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('slue', '[sluː]', 'v.(使)旋转 n.旋转', '1. The cat sighed to say: \"The mice on the world is slue. 猫叹了口气说：“世上老鼠是极多的。 2. Slough: Also slue A stagnant swamp, marsh, bog, or pond, especially as part of a bayou, an inlet, or a backwater. 也作slue停滞的水域,泥泞的沼泽:浑浊的沼泽、湿地、泥塘或池塘,尤指作为海湾、水湾或死水的一部分。 3. The breed slue of tea tree, distributing very wide, breed with China most, occupy 60 % above. 茶树的品种极多，分布甚广，品种以中国最多，占60%25以上。 4. Umbrella room type cyme, axil is born or the top is born, scattered, slue is spent. 伞房式聚伞花序,腋生或顶生,疏散,有极多花。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sophistry', '[\'sɑːfɪstri]', 'n.诡辩', '1. He won the argument by sophistry. 他靠诡辩赢了那场争论。 2. Universities incline wits to sophistry and affection. 大学使才智偏于诡辩和矫情。', '名词复数: sophistries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('leaven', '[\'levn]', 'n.发酵剂；酵母；要素；影响力 v.使 ... 发酵；影响', '1. We often use leaven when baking breads. 烤面包时，我们经常使用发酵剂。 2. The leaven of reform was working. 改革的影响力在起作用。', '过去式: leavened 过去分词: leavened 现在分词: leavening 第三人称单数: leavens');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('counterfeit', '[\'kaʊntərfɪt]', 'n.膺品；伪造品 adj.假冒的；假装的 v.仿造；伪装；假装', '1. This ten-dollar bill is a counterfeit. 这张十元钞票是伪钞。 2. We suspect the paper to be a counterfeit. 我们疑心这个证件是伪造的。 3. This note is counterfeit, but that one\'s good. 这张钞票是假的，那张是真的。 4. And eyes will be very difficult to counterfeit. 而且眼睛将是非常难以仿造的。', '名词: counterfeiter 过去式: counterfeited 过去分词: counterfeited 现在分词: counterfeiting 第三人称单数: counterfeits');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incite', '[ɪn\'saɪt]', 'v.煽动；刺激；激励', '1. Stop anyone trying to incite the people. 有人煽动，实行挡驾。 2. On Sabertron, the Destrons incite an uprising among the prisoners. 塞伯特恩之迪斯坦逆党煽动囚犯暴动。', '名词: incitement 过去式: incited 过去分词: incited 现在分词: inciting 第三人称单数: incites');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dingy', '[\'dɪndʒi]', 'adj.肮脏的；昏暗的', '1. He lives in a dingy room. 他住在一个肮脏的屋子里。 2. His office is really dark and dingy . 他的办公室实在是又暗又脏。 3. It was a rather dingy night, although a fair number of stars were out. 这是个昏暗的夜晚，虽然天空中有相当数量的星星。', '副词: dingily 比较级: dingier 最高级: dingiest 名词: dinginess');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('somatic', '[soʊ\'mætɪk]', 'adj.身体的；肉体的；体壁的', '1. The computerists make no real distinction between behavioral learning and somatic learning. 计算机专家没有真正区别行为的学习和肉体的学习。', '副词: somatically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('acrobat', '[\'ækrəbæt]', 'n.杂技演员；见风使舵的人', '1. The acrobat\'s feat took the audience\'s breath away. 杂技演员的惊险动作使观众为之咋舌。', '形容词: acrobatic 副词: acrobatically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('alcove', '[\'ælkoʊv]', 'n.凹室；壁龛', '1. The bed fits neatly into the alcove. 床正好放进壁凹。 2. We partitioned off the alcove to make another bedroom. 我们把凹室分隔开作另一间卧室。 3. His desk was in an alcove to one side of the chimney. 他的书桌在一间凹室内，一边是烟囱。 4. Dooku couldn\'t quite see the other droid around the edge of the alcove. 杜库从壁龛的角上看不太清楚另一个机器人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('purchase', '[\'pɜːrtʃəs]', 'vt.购买 n.购买；购买的物品', '1. She purchased a number of shares in the company. 她在公司里买了一些股票。 2. Tickets must be purchased two weeks in advance. 票必须提前两周买。 3. The receipt is your proof of purchase. 这张发票是你购物的凭据. 4. The house is the most expensive purchase I have ever made. 房子是我买过的最贵的东西。', '名词: purchaser 过去式: purchased 过去分词: purchased 现在分词: purchasing 第三人称单数: purchases');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('spineless', '[\'spaɪnləs]', 'adj.无脊椎的；没有骨气的；懦弱的', '1. A jellyfish is a spineless animal. 水母是无脊椎动物。 2. My supervisor is a spineless person. He never stands behind his decisions. 我的主管是一个没骨气的人。他不敢为他做的决定负责。 3. At a time of crisis, why are Britain\'s politicians so spineless? 危急时刻，为何英国政治家如此懦弱？', '副词: spinelessly 名词: spinelessness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('import', '[\'ɪmpɔːrt]', 'n.进口；意义；进口商品 v.进口；输入', '1. The government has imposed strict controls over the import of luxury goods. 政府对奢侈品的进口采取了严格的管制。 2. You should grasp the import of your mother\'s remarks. 你应该领会到你妈妈说话的含义。 3. The miscellaneous expenses of import are so much! 进口货物的杂费太多了！ 4. It is profitable to import food. 进口食品可赚钱。', '形容词: importable 名词: importability 过去式: imported 过去分词: imported 现在分词: importing 第三人称单数: imports');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('clench', '[klentʃ]', 'v.紧握；紧咬；牢牢地抓住；确定 n.牢牢抓住；钉紧', '1. You walk in circles, kick the ground, clench your fists and throw your arms in the air. 你绕圈走着，脚踢地面，紧握拳头，在空中挥舞着手臂。', '过去式: clenched 过去分词: clenched 现在分词: clenching 第三人称单数: clenches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('discreet', '[dɪ\'skriːt]', 'adj.谨慎的；不引人注意的；朴素的，简易的', '1. It was not discreet of you to say that. 你那样说有欠考虑。 2. Be more discreet or you\'ll get yourself talked about. 要更谨慎些－－否则你就会成为人们的话柄。 3. I\'ll certainly be most discreet in my conversation. 我在谈话中当然会十分小心的。 4. It was a discreet apartment in a quiet street. 那是间位於一条僻静的街上不引人注意的公寓房间。', '副词: discreetly 名词: discreetness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('splashy', '[\'splæʃi]', 'adj.大而显眼的；引人注目的', '1. \"Who on earth would want such a splashy dress? “究竟谁会买件这么惹人注目的衣服？” 2. A cheap showy rhinestone bracelet,a splashy half-page ad. 廉价艳丽的水晶手镯，惹人注目的半页广告。 3. The celebrity couple had a splashy wedding in London. 那一对名人在伦敦举行了惹人注目的隆重婚礼。 4. We dreamed of doing something big of splashy,something significant. 我们都梦想郭作一番大事业，作有意义的事情。', '副词: splashily 比较级: splashier 最高级: splashiest 名词: splashiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('deign', '[deɪn]', 'v.（有时作贬义或作反语）屈尊；施惠于人；赐予', '1. He did not deign to an answer. 他不屑置答。 2. Now that she is rich and famous, she does not deign to visit her former friends. 既然她现在又有钱又出名，便再也不愿屈尊去看望从前的朋友了。 3. At times he might even deign to speak to them. 有些时候，他也以恩赐的神情同他们谈谈话。 4. I fear my Julia will not deign my lines. 我担心我的朱莉亚不会欣然接受我的书信。', '过去式: deigned 过去分词: deigned 现在分词: deigning 第三人称单数: deigns');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('demote', '[ˌdiː\'moʊt]', 'vt.降级；降职', '1. He was demoted from sergeant to corporal. 他由中士降到下士。 2. I should demote you from senior minister to elder. 我要把你从高级牧师降级为长老。 3. Why did the mayor demote the official? 为什么市长要把这名官员降职？', '名词: demotion 过去式: demoted 过去分词: demoted 现在分词: demoting 第三人称单数: demotes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('uniform', '[\'juːnɪfɔːrm]', 'n.制服 adj.一致的；统一的', '1. He looks very manly in his uniform. 他穿着制服十分精神。 2. The students are wearing school uniforms. 学生们穿着校服。 3. The rows of houses were uniform in appearance. 这一排排的房屋外表都是一样的。 4. Their internal temperatures are essentially uniform with the environment. 它们的体温与周围环境基本上是一致的。', '副词: uniformly 名词: uniformity 过去式: uniformed 过去分词: uniformed 现在分词: uniforming 第三人称单数: uniforms');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('damper', '[\'dæmpər]', 'n.风阀；减音器；阻尼器；抑制', '1. Damper actuators and air quality control document should be sent today. 今天应当发送风阀执行器及空气质量控制文件。 2. Now the damper became a must, a life saver! 现在制音器变成必需设备,救助器! 3. We have got control problem, yaw damper inoperative. 我们操作系统故障，偏航阻尼器不工作了。 4. Rain put a damper on our picnic plans. 大雨阻止了我们的野餐计划', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('oppress', '[ə\'pres]', 'v.使烦恼；压迫', '1. Cares oppressed his spirits. 忧虑使他心情抑郁。 2. The king oppressed his people with terrible taxes and punishments. 国王以苛捐杂税和严刑来压迫人民。 3. Free governments do not oppress their people or attack other free nations. 自由政府不会压迫其人民或者攻击其他自由国家。', '名词: oppressor 过去式: oppressed 过去分词: oppressed 现在分词: oppressing 第三人称单数: oppresses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('splice', '[splaɪs]', 'n.接合；衔接 v.接合；衔接 vt.拼接', '1. Film editors used to splice reels of film together to make a whole movie. 以前的电影剪辑人员是将几卷影片接合成一部电影。 2. The reference spectra was the signal obtained by coupling the two fibers with a splice bushing. 参考光谱是通过将两个纤维与一个接合套筒耦合后获得的信号。 3. Film editors used to splice reels of film together to make a whole movie. 以前的电影剪辑人员是将几卷影片接合成一部电影。 4. The reference spectra was the signal obtained by coupling the two fibers with a splice bushing. 参考光谱是通过将两个纤维与一个接合套筒耦合后获得的信号。 5. The splice piece shall be cut to length and secured to the bundle on one of the main runs to allow easy field installation across the splice line. 按相应长度切断拼接件并将管束固定在一根主要导压管上，这样可以方便地通过拼接管线进行现场安装。', '名词: splicer 过去式: spliced 过去分词: spliced 现在分词: splicing 第三人称单数: splices');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ambulatory', '[\'æmbjələtɔːri]', 'adj.可走动的；[医]非卧床的；流动的；[法律]可变更的；可撤销的 n.回廊；步道', '1. The biggest failures in ambulatory and home health care are those that lead to hospitalization. 在非卧床与居家健康照护中最大的失败是导致患者住院。 2. Outpatient rehabilitation includes day hospital, outpatient ambulatory care and home-based rehabilitation. 门诊康复包括日托医院、门诊流动护理和家庭康复。', '副词: ambulatorily 名词复数: ambulatories');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flaunt', '[flɔːnt]', 'v.挥动；夸耀；（厚颜无耻地）炫耀；飘扬；张扬', '1. He flaunts his queer style as a savage might flaunt a top-hat retrieved from somebody\'s dustbin. 他对自己那种怪异的文体加以夸耀这恰似一个野人从别人的垃圾箱里捡出一顶礼帽时那种洋洋得意的样子。 2. The baseballer flaunt his cup to his friends. 那名棒球选手向他的朋友炫耀他的奖杯。 3. NO need to flaunt,Qiao has attracted a lot of attention. 无需炫耀，但桥新家具已深深吸引住无数视线。', '副词: flauntingly 名词: flaunter 过去式: flaunted 过去分词: flaunted 现在分词: flaunting 第三人称单数: flaunts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('trunk', '[trʌŋk]', 'n.树干；(汽车后部)行李箱；大箱子；象鼻；躯干 (复)trunks: 男用运动裤.', '1. The branch has separated from the trunk of the tree. 这个树枝已从树干上脱落了。 2. I eulogize the tall and straight trunk of the white poplar. 我赞美白杨树那挺拔的树干。 3. The trunk is chock-full. There is no more room. 车尾行李箱里塞满了东西。一点空隙都没有了。 4. He crammed all his clothes into the trunk. 他把他所有的衣服硬塞进皮箱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stunt', '[stʌnt]', 'n.特技；阻碍成长 vt.阻碍成长；表演特技', '1. Have you watched a stunt flying? 你看过特技飞行表演吗? 2. The stunt pilot looped his plane. 特技飞行员驾机在天上转圆圈。 3. Her latest stunt is riding a motor cycle through a ring of flames. 她的最新特技表演是骑摩托车钻火圈。 4. Lack of the right food may stunt growth. 缺乏适当的食物会阻碍发育。', '名词: stuntedness 过去式: stunted 过去分词: stunted 现在分词: stunting 第三人称单数: stunts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gallop', '[\'ɡæləp]', 'n.疾驰；飞奔 v.飞驰；急速进行', '1. The horse went off at a gallop across the field. 那匹马疾驰起来跑过田野。 2. All the horses broke into a gallop. 所有的马突然飞奔起来。 3. The donkey began to trot faster , then to gallop. 驴开始跑得快起来了，然后飞奔。 4. Two people gallop whip and spur, do not come in the city a little while. 两人快马加鞭飞驰，不一会儿就来到城里。', '名词: galloper 过去式: galloped 过去分词: galloped 现在分词: galloping 第三人称单数: gallops');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flimsy', '[\'flɪmzi]', 'adj.轻而薄得；易坏的；不足信的 n.复写纸；薄纸副本', '1. She wore a flimsy dress. 她穿一件薄连衣裙。 2. It is a flimsy cardboard box. 那是一个不结实的纸箱。 3. The evidence against him was flimsy. 指控他的证据不足信。 4. A close inspection of this argument would reveal how flimsy it is. 仔细想想这个问题就会发现它其实毫无根据。', '副词: flimsily 比较级: flimsier 最高级: flimsiest 名词: flimsiness 名词复数: flimsies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bilk', '[bɪlk]', 'v.赖账；蒙骗；避开；使挫败 n.诈骗；骗子', '1. It is a new tendency of the present economic domain crime of utilizing the cell- phone message to bilk. 利用手机短信实施诈骗犯罪是当前经济领域犯罪的新动向。', '名词: bilker 过去式: bilked 过去分词: bilked 现在分词: bilking 第三人称单数: bilks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('compel', '[kəm\'pel]', 'v.强迫；迫使；使不得已', '1. Nothing can compel me to do such a thing. 没有什么可以强迫我做这件事。 2. I was compelled to do so by absolute necessity. 我因绝对的需要,被迫这样做的。 3. The heavy rain compelled us to stay indoors. 大雨迫使我们呆在户内。 4. Duty compelled the soldiers to volunteer for the mission. 责任驱使军人必须志愿加入此任务', '形容词: compellable 副词: compellably 名词: compeller 过去式: compelled 过去分词: compelled 现在分词: compelling 第三人称单数: compels');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vital', '[\'vaɪtl]', 'adj.至关重要的；有活力的；生死攸关的', '1. The government saw the introduction of new technology as vital. 政府认为引进新技术至关重要。 2. She\'s a very vital sort of person. 她是个精力旺盛的人。 3. Confronted with such a vital problem of life and death, he looked as cool as a cucumber. 面对着这样重大的生死问题,他的神态却异常冷静。', '副词: vitally 名词: vitalness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dispute', '[dɪ\'spjuːt]', 'v.争论；辩驳；争议；质疑 n.争论；争端；争吵', '1. The couple disputed where to spend the holiday. 夫妻俩为上哪儿度假而发生争论。 2. It is ridiculous to dispute about such a thing. 为这样的事情而争论简直荒谬可笑。 3. \"I\'m not disputing what you say, matt.\" said Tremaine, shaking his head. “我并不是要跟你辩驳，麦特”，屈里曼说，摇摇头。 4. Now there was just one point on the boundary left to dispute. 边界上有一点引起争议。 5. A long dispute means that both parties are wrong.( Voltaire) 持久的争论意味着双方都是错的。(伏尔泰)', '名词: disputer 过去式: disputed 过去分词: disputed 现在分词: disputing 第三人称单数: disputes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fallacious', '[fə\'leɪʃəs]', 'adj.使人误解的；谬误的；不合理的', '1. The argument is fallacious, for it is based on a set of factual flaws. 这段论述是谬误的，因为它的基础与事实不符。 2. This inference is fallacious without reasonable evidence to support it. 这个推断是谬误的没有合理的证据支持它。', '副词: fallaciously');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('digression', '[daɪ\'ɡreʃn]', 'n.离题；脱轨', '1. Here a short digression becomes necessary. 这里有必要加一点题外的话。 2. After this digression we return now to our original problem. 在这一段插话以后，现在回到原来的问题。 3. Now let\'s return from this digression to our subject. 现在咱们言归正传。 4. The wreck was caused by the digression of the two ships. 这次遇难事件是由两只轮船的脱离航道引起的。', '形容词: digressional');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('braggart', '[\'bræɡərt]', 'n.吹牛者；自夸者 adj.吹牛的；自吹者', '1. Modest by nature, she was no braggart, preferring to let her accomplishments speak for themselves. 她天性谦虚,从不自吹,喜欢以自己的成就来表明一切。 2. However, Captain Prien was no braggart 不过，普里恩舰长却不是一个夸大其词的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fabulous', '[\'fæbjələs]', 'adj.极好的；巨大的；传说中的', '1. I must go to taste your fabulous cooking. 我一定去尝一尝您精湛的烹调。 2. The minutes of evening twilight are fabulous . 短暂的黄昏景色真令人惊叹。 3. You look fabulous, you\'ll knock them dead tonight. 你看上去漂亮极了,今晚肯定把他们迷倒。 4. The museum has a fabulous collection of jewels. 该博物馆有著惊人的珠宝收藏。', '副词: fabulously 名词: fabulousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reconnaissance', '[rɪ\'kɑːnɪsns]', 'n.侦察；勘察', '1. A patrol was sent on reconnaissance. 一支巡逻队被派去执行侦察任务。 2. The squadron flew a reconnaissance mission. 该空军中队执行一侦察任务。 3. A reconnaissance plane was circling over the enemy\'s position. 一架侦察机正在敌人阵地上空盘旋。 4. The uranium reconnaissance was undertaken in the U.K. 在英国境内曾开展过铀矿勘察工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bearing', '[\'berɪŋ]', 'n.轴承；举止；忍受；支撑物；影响', '1. These non-contact seals do not limit bearing speed. 这些非无接触式密封件不限制轴承转速。 2. Shanghai HRB bearing Supplies Company Ltd. 上海哈轴轴承配套有限公司。 3. Her dignified bearing throughout the trial made everyone believe she was innocent. 在整个审讯的过程中，她那端庄的举止使得每个人都相信她是无辜的。 4. The pain was almost past bearing. 疼痛几乎无法忍受。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('console', '[kən\'soʊl]', 'vt.安慰；慰藉 n.仪表盘；操控台；(游戏)平台；落地式支座', '1. I tried to console her, but in vain. 我试着去安慰她，但是无效。 2. He consoled himself with the thought that it might have been worse. 他聊以自慰的是幸亏事情没有更糟。 3. He was beyond my skill to quiet or console! 我可没有那个本事使他安静下来，或者能给他慰藉！ 4. There are many lights and electrical instruments on the computer console. 电脑控制板上有许多小灯和电子设备。', '形容词: consolable 副词: consolingly 名词: consoler 过去式: consoled 过去分词: consoled 现在分词: consoling 第三人称单数: consoles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('multiplicity', '[ˌmʌltɪ\'plɪsəti]', 'n.多数；重复；多样', '1. India also has a multiplicity of languages. 同时印度也是一个多语言的国家。 2. They found a multiplicity of errors in the article. 他们在文章中发现了许多错误。 3. A true study of history is sure to be of multiplicity. 真正的历史研究必须是多元化的。 4. Multiplicity is the base on which to construct a new world order. 多极化是建立世界新秩序的力量基础。', '名词复数: multiplicities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('spleen', '[spliːn]', 'n.脾；脾气；怒气', '1. The spleen is the source of phlegm production. 脾为生痰之源。 2. The stomach lies between the liver and the spleen. 胃位于肝和脾之间。 3. I waited for him to get the rest of the spleen out of his system. 我等着他把心头的余努全部发泄出来。 4. When I get frustrated and angry, I have to vent my spleen on someone. 我受尽挫折，怒火冲天时，禁不住想找谁发一顿脾气。', '形容词: spleeny');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('resume', '[rɪ\'zuːm]', 'v.重新开始；再继续 n.简历；履历；摘要', '1. We resumed our work after a rest. 休息之后我们重新开始工作。 2. I tried to persuade her to resume her job as secretary. 我试图劝她重新干她的秘书工作。 3. Two days later, they resumed their journey. 两天以後,他们继续旅行。 4. We\'ll stop now and resume at two o\'clock. 我们现在停下来, 到两点再干。 5. I enclosed my resume in my letter. 我在信里附上了我的简历。', '形容词: resumable 名词: resumer 过去式: resumed 过去分词: resumed 现在分词: resuming 第三人称单数: resumes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('chipper', '[\'tʃɪpər]', 'n.木材削片机；薯条机；薯条店 adj.爽朗的；活泼的；精力充沛的 v.鸟唧唧叫；喋喋不休地说', '1. The workers were feeding branches into the wood chipper. 工人们正把树枝放进这个木头切片机。 2. I am a girl always with smile, chipper but sensitive sometimes. 我是一个特别爱笑的女生，爽朗的性格中夹着一丝敏感。 3. He was actually pleasant to be around and was by far the most chipper boy I knew. 事实上，有他在，是很令人愉快的，而且他是我认识的男生中性情最为开朗的一位。 4. The Lakers, on the other hand, were chipper after fending off the Celtics. 而湖人，在另一方面来说，在防死了凯尔特人之后好像显得更加精力充沛。', '过去式: chippered 过去分词: chippered 现在分词: chippering 第三人称单数: chippers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wreathe', '[riːð]', 'v.环绕；盘绕；作成花圈', '1. The local people used to wreathe the guest\'s head in leaves. 当地人过去常把树叶缠在宾客的头上。 2. Mist wreathed the hilltops. 山顶上薄雾环绕。', '过去式: wreathed 过去分词: wreathed 现在分词: wreathing 第三人称单数: wreathes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('obese', '[oʊ\'biːs]', 'adj.极肥胖的', '1. Obese people find it difficult to stop overeating. 胖人觉得一吃就过量，难以控制。 2. Obese patients are advised to change their diet. 建议肥胖病人改变饮食。', '副词: obesely 名词: obeseness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('levee', '[\'levi]', 'n.集体接见；招待会；堤岸；码头 v.筑堤', '1. The Major General attended the President\'s levee in full uniform. 那位少将身着全套军服出席总统的招待会。 2. Crews are rushing to build a four-foot-tall levee around the eastern Missouri community. 工作人员急着在密苏里东部地区建造一座四英寸高的堤坝。', '过去式: leveed 过去分词: leveed 现在分词: leveeing 第三人称单数: levees');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('divine', '[dɪ\'vaɪn]', 'adj.神圣的；神的 vt.推断 vi.预言；理解 n.牧师；神学家', '1. In the Dragon Pond are divine fish. 可都是龙潭里的神鱼啊。 2. Her elegance and beauty was simply divine. 她高雅的气质和美丽的外表简直是上天的恩赐。 3. That play we saw last night was simply divine! 我们昨天晚上看的那出戏真是好极了！ 4. To err is human,to forgive is divine. 犯错误是人之常情，宽恕才难能可贵。 5. At last I divined the truth. 我终于看穿了事情的真相。 6. I don\'t believe that astrologers are able to divine. 我不相信占星家能作预言。 7. He was selected to be a divine for the church. 他被选为教堂的牧师。', '副词: divinely 比较级: diviner 最高级: divinest 名词: divineness 过去式: divined 过去分词: divined 现在分词: divining 第三人称单数: divines');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('obelisk', '[\'ɑːbəlɪsk]', 'n.方尖石碑；（印刷术）剑号', '1. The shadow of the obelisk spanned the terrance. 方尖塔的影子落在平台上。 2. Far away on the last spur , there was a glittering obelisk. 远处，在最后一个山峦上闪烁着一个方尖塔。 3. The obelisk is built in memory of those who died for their country. 这座方尖塔是为了纪念那些为祖国献身的人而建造的。', '形容词: obeliscal');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('leeward', '[\'liːwərd]', 'adj.背风的；下风的 n.背风处', '1. Frontal slope is increased in the upward side，but decreased in the leeward side. 当冷锋位于迎风坡时,其坡度减小,位于背风坡时,其坡度增大。 2. Leeward arterial roads in city can serve as pollute air transpire corridors. 污染空气的排放通道宜利用城市中顺风向的较为通直的干道。 3. Industrial districts are generally situated to the leeward of the cities. 工业区一般都设在城市的下风。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('secure', '[sə\'kjʊr]', 'adj.安全的；牢靠的；稳妥的 vt.使安全；获得；固定', '1. If you are not sure it is secure, do not debug it. 如果您不能确定它是安全的,请不要调试它。 2. His place in history is now secure. 他在历史上的地位现在已经稳固了。 3. A climber needs secure footholds. 攀登的人脚踩的地方要很牢固。 4. We must create a secure and reliable international environment of lasting peace and stability. 我们要创造安全可靠、长期稳定的国际和平环境。 5. Some measures are needed to secure the farmland against shift sand. 需要采取措施使农田免遭流沙的侵袭。', '形容词: securable 副词: securely 比较级: securer 最高级: securest 名词: securement 过去式: secured 过去分词: secured 现在分词: securing 第三人称单数: secures');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mosaic', '[moʊ\'zeɪɪk]', 'n.马赛克；镶嵌图案 v.镶嵌；用马赛克装饰 adj.【大写】摩西的', '1. I stared for hours at the elaborate pattern in the mosaic. 我对着马赛克上精密的图案注视了好几个小时。 2. Archaeologists have worked for years to piece together the huge mosaic. 考古学家经年累月拼组这幅巨大的马赛克。 3. It\'s a rich mosaic of meadows, rivers and woods. 这是一幅由草地，河流，树木组成的五光十色的镶嵌画。 4. The sky this morning was a mosaic of blue and white. 今天早上的天空是幅蓝白相间的画面。 5. Mosaic a design on a rosewood box. 将一个图案嵌入红木盒子上。', '名词: mosaicist 过去式: mosaicked 过去分词: mosaicked 现在分词: mosaicking 第三人称单数: mosaics');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('emissary', '[\'emɪseri]', 'n.密使；特使', '1. He had never sought the role of a minor presidential emissary. 他从来也没有去追求过出任无足轻重的总统密使的角色。 2. Mr. Miller was sent as an emissary for the peace talks. 米勒先生被作为特使派遣去参加和平谈判。', '名词复数: emissaries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('painkiller', '[\'peɪnkɪlər]', 'n.止痛药', '1. Take this painkiller, it usually acts fast. 把止痛药吃了，这个药见效很快。 2. Tylenol, my painkiller of choice, has this as the main active ingredient. 是我常用的止痛药，泰诺的主要成分。', '形容词: painkilling');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('forestall', '[fɔːr\'stɔːl]', 'v.领先；占先一步；先发制人，阻止，妨碍', '1. She forestalled my plan to meet her. 她抢在我前面，使我要去接她的计划落了空。 2. I have my objection all prepared,but Stephens forestall me. 我已做好准备要提出反对意见，不料斯蒂芬斯却抢先了一步。 3. We must act now to forestall disaster. 我们现在必须采取行动以防灾难。 4. We installed an alarm system to forestall break-in. 我们安装了一套警报系统来预防小偷的闯入。', '名词: forestaller 过去式: forestalled 过去分词: forestalled 现在分词: forestalling 第三人称单数: forestalls');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('upgrade', '[ˌʌp\'ɡreɪd]', 'vt.升级；提高；改善 adv.向上地 n.升级；上坡', '1. Please click here to upgrade your Player. 请单击此处,升级您的播放器。 2. Companies need to upgrade servers. 公司需要对服务器升级。 3. We need to upgrade the pay and status of teachers. 我们需要提高教师的工资和地位。 4. We must try to upgrade our cattle to the required standard of meat. 我们必须努力提高牛的品级，使之达到所要求的食用肉标准。 5. After a short break, the climbers continued upgrade. 稍事休息後,攀登者们继续往山上走。 6. The power plant received a new upgrade. 那个电厂进行了一次升级改造。', '过去式: upgraded 过去分词: upgraded 现在分词: upgrading 第三人称单数: upgrades');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('characterize', '[\'kærəktəraɪz]', 'vt.表示 ... 的典型；赋予 ... 特色', '1. The novelist characterizes his heroine as capricious and passionate. 这位小说家把女主人公刻画成变化无常而又多情的人。 2. He may be characterized as a man of hobbies. 他可以被称作是一个有癖好的人。 3. Your work is characterized by lack of attention to details. 你的工作特点是缺乏对细节的注意。 4. Bold outlines and warm colors characterize his dominate style in painting. 他大胆的绘画和所有的暖色调表现了他独有的绘画特色。', '名词: characterizer 过去式: characterized 过去分词: characterized 现在分词: characterizing 第三人称单数: characterizes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bleak', '[bliːk]', 'adj.萧瑟的；阴郁的；严寒的；无希望的', '1. The bleak breeze blights the brightly blooming blossom. 萧瑟的微风吹枯了盛开着的花。 2. The bleak ground pullulated with jackrabbits. 荒凉的土地上到处是长耳大野兔。 3. The world was not always so bleak. 这个世界不是生来就如此凄冷的。 4. It\'s a bleak look-out for the coal industry as the number of pit closures increases. 煤井关闭的数目日多，煤炭工业前景暗淡。', '副词: bleakly 比较级: bleaker 最高级: bleakest 名词: bleakness 名词复数: bleak');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nuptial', '[\'nʌpʃl]', 'n.婚礼 adj.婚姻的；婚礼的；交配季节的', '1. Their nuptials were performed by the local priest. 他们的婚礼由当地牧师主持。 2. Naturally I watch the nuptial of the prince and the princess of wales. 自然我观看了威尔士王子和王妃的婚礼。 3. He would not leave much mystery for the nuptial night. 他将不会给新婚之夜留下多少神秘。 4. Before the couple enters their nuptial room, their parents will choose one of the elders who have healthy children. 在新婚夫妇进入洞房之前，他们的父母亲会挑出一位有健康儿女的长辈。', '副词: nuptially');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bacterium', '[bæk\'tɪriəm]', 'n.细菌', '1. Most of disease is caused from bacterium. 大多数疾病都是由细菌引起的。 2. A bacterium was identified as the cause for his duodenal ulcer. 一种细菌被断定为造成他十二指肠溃疡的根源。', '名词复数: bacteria');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stitch', '[stɪtʃ]', 'n.一针；疼痛；碎布条 v.缝合', '1. Every stitch was in its right place. 每一针的位置都很贴切。 2. When she sews she makes long stitches. 她做针线活时针脚很大。 3. He felt a sort of stitch in his heart. 他感到有点心痛。 4. The doctor can stitch up the wound skillfully. 这位医生缝合伤口技术甚高。', '名词: stitcher 过去式: stitched 过去分词: stitched 现在分词: stitching 第三人称单数: stitches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('herdsman', '[\'hɜːrdzmən]', 'n.牧民', '1. The herdsman looks after a herd of animals. 牧人放牧着一群牲畜。 2. The animals were herded into the fold by the herdsmen. 那群牲畜被牧人赶进圈里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ignominy', '[\'ɪɡnəmɪni]', 'n.(尤指公开的)羞耻；屈辱', '1. They suffered the ignominy of defeat. 他们蒙受了失败的耻辱。', '名词复数: ignominies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('jaded', '[\'dʒeɪdɪd]', 'adj.疲倦不堪的；厌倦或缺乏热情的', '1. He looks jaded. 他看来疲惫不堪。 2. They mustn\'t worry; they must sleep; and rest stole into their jaded bones. 他们不用担心,他们必须睡觉,于是他们疲惫不堪的筋骨不知不觉地松弛了。 3. He has a jaded appetite. 他的食欲不振。 4. Here is a dish that will revive jaded palates. 这道菜简直可以恢复迟钝的味觉。', '副词: jadedly 名词: jadedness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('faultfinder', '[fɔːlt\'faɪndə]', 'n.吹毛求疵的人', '1. The faultfinder will find faults even in paradise. 吹毛求疵的人就是到了天堂也会挑出错误。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('considerable', '[kən\'sɪdərəbl]', 'adj.重要的；相当大的；可观的', '1. The mayor is a considerable official. 市长是一位重要的官员。 2. He is a considerable person in that college. 他是那所学院相当重要的人物。 3. The economy was a considerable issue in the campaign. 在竞选运动中经济是一个重要问题。 4. His remarks provoked considerable comment. 他的话引起了相当大的议论。', '副词: considerably');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('peek', '[piːk]', 'v.偷看；窥视 n.偷看；窥见', '1. Larry takes a peek out of the window. 赖瑞往窗外偷看了一下。 2. Anyone who dared to peek was condemned to death. 任何敢偷看的人被定死罪。 3. Future is a tarnishing mirror, anyone who tries to peek just can see a vague outline with a old and worrying face. 未来是面晦暗的镜子，任何试图向里面窥视的人只能看到一张苍老而焦虑的脸的模糊轮廓。 4. Anyone who dared to peek was condemned to death. 任何敢偷看的人被定死罪。', '过去式: peeked 过去分词: peeked 现在分词: peeking 第三人称单数: peeks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('germinate', '[\'dʒɜːrmɪneɪt]', 'v.发芽；开始生长', '1. The cabbage germinated within a week. 白菜一星期内就发芽了。 2. Warmth is needed for the seeds to germinate. 种子发芽需要适当的温度。 3. An idea for a novel began to germinate in her mind. 一部小说的构思已经在她的头脑中萌发。 4. I saw everything about me surge forth and germinate. 我看见我周围的万物汹涌向前，欣欣向荣。', '形容词: germinative 名词: germination 过去式: germinated 过去分词: germinated 现在分词: germinating 第三人称单数: germinates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('molest', '[mə\'lest]', 'v.骚扰；干扰；调戏', '1. The dog that molested the sheep was killed. 那只骚扰绵羊的狗被杀死了。 2. We did not dare to molest the big dog. 我们不敢惊扰那只大狗。 3. He was found guilty of molesting a young girl. 他被判猥亵少女罪。', '名词: molestation 过去式: molested 过去分词: molested 现在分词: molesting 第三人称单数: molests');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('conspire', '[kən\'spaɪər]', 'v.阴谋；协力；共谋，串通一气', '1. They conspire against the government. 他们阴谋推翻政府。 2. But if any force tries to conspire and work against the people\'s will, we might be compelled to take that way despite our unwillingness. 但是如果有人试图搞阴谋反对人民的意愿，那么我们将被迫做我们不愿做的事。', '副词: conspiringly 名词: conspirer 过去式: conspired 过去分词: conspired 现在分词: conspiring 第三人称单数: conspires');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('plateau', '[plæ\'toʊ]', 'n.高原；平稳；稳定状态 vi.到达平稳阶段', '1. The plateau extends for many miles. 高原连绵许多英里。 2. The ranch is in the middle of a large plateau. 该牧场位于一个辽阔高原的中部。 3. After a period of rapid inflation, price have now reach a plateau. 经急剧通货膨胀之后物价现已趋于平稳。 4. Mortgage rates declined, then reached a plateau. 抵押价格下跌，然后达到稳定水平 5. The athletic footwear market has not yet plateaued. 运动鞋市场并没趋于平稳。', '名词复数: plateaus 过去式: plateaued 过去分词: plateaued 现在分词: plateauing 第三人称单数: plateaus');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('seep', '[siːp]', 'v.渗出；渗漏 n.渗漏；小泉；水坑', '1. Blood was beginning to seep through the bandages. 血开始从绷带上渗出来。 2. Oil is seeping out through a crack in the tank. 油箱的裂缝漏出油来了。 3. The teacher stopped speaking to allow time for the meaning of his words to seep through. 那位老师停止讲话，以便留出时间(让学生们)理解他所讲的意思。', '过去式: seeped 过去分词: seeped 现在分词: seeping 第三人称单数: seeps');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tenuous', '[\'tenjuəs]', 'adj.脆弱的；稀薄的；贫乏的；纤细的；空洞的', '1. Our existence is far more tenuous than we might think. 但我们的生命远比想像的要脆弱。 2. Cassini had passed through a tenuous cloud. 卡西尼号还曾经穿越过稀薄的云层。 3. The air ten miles above the earth is very tenuous. 地面往上十英里处的气体是非常稀薄的。 4. He gave a tenuous account of his past life. 他对他过去的生活说得很含糊。', '副词: tenuously 名词: tenuousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('terse', '[tɜːrs]', 'adj.简洁的；简明的', '1. I admire his terse style of writing. 我很欣赏他那简洁的写作风格。 2. Her reply about the matter was terse. 她对此事的答复简明扼要。', '副词: tersely 比较级: terser 最高级: tersest 名词: terseness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('diva', '[\'diːvə]', 'n.歌剧女主角；著名女歌手', '1. In the opera world and beyond, she was the diva of divas. 无论是在歌剧领域内还是之外，她都是名伶中的天后。 2. He has acted as a wounded diva, instead of being a man. 他看上去就想个受伤的女演员一样，而不是一个男人。 3. He explains why Beverly Sills became America\'s beloved diva. 他解释了为什么贝克佛蕾·西尔斯能成为美国最受爱戴的演员。', '名词复数: divas');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('infirm', '[ɪn\'fɜːrm]', 'adj.体弱的；虚弱的；意志薄弱的；不坚定的；不牢靠的 n.体弱的人', '1. She\'s old and infirm and has to keep to the house. 她因年老体弱而足不出户。 2. Hunter is infirm of purpose. 亨特为人优柔寡断。 3. It\'s an infirm title to property. 这是不牢靠的产权。 4. We should support for the aged and infirm. 我们应该援助年老的人和体弱的人。', '副词: infirmly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('smudge', '[smʌdʒ]', 'n.污点；渍痕；浓烟 v.（使）变脏；（使）模糊', '1. You\'ve got a smudge on your cheek. 你脸上有一块污迹。 2. Wash your hands or you\'ll make smudges on the writing paper. 把手洗乾净，别把写字的纸弄脏了。 3. You have a smudge of chocolate on your shirt. 你的衬衫上有一块巧克力的污渍。 4. Wet ink smudges easily. 墨水没乾很容易弄出污迹。', '形容词: smudgy 副词: smudgily 名词: smudginess 过去式: smudged 过去分词: smudged 现在分词: smudging 第三人称单数: smudges');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('remunerative', '[rɪ\'mjuːnərətɪv]', 'adj.有报酬的；有利益的', '1. He is prepared to make a living by accepting any remunerative chore. 为了生计,他准备接受任何有酬报的杂活。 2. Is it necessary to decide between remunerative work and meaningful work? 是不是一定要在高回报的工作与有意义的生活中间做一个选择呢？ 3. It\'s a vast and remunerative market even with high prices. 这是一个巨大的高额利润回报的市场，甚至价格高的离谱。', '副词: remuneratively 名词: remunerativeness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('intersect', '[ˌɪntər\'sekt]', 'v.贯穿；(和 ... )相交；交叉', '1. The plain is intersected by a network of canals. 一个运河网络贯穿这片平原。 2. These two fences intersect at the creek. 这两片篱笆在一条羊肠小道相交。 3. The two roads intersect at the suburb of the city. 两条路在城郊交叉。 4. Streets usually intersect at right angles. 马路通常以直角交叉。', '过去式: intersected 过去分词: intersected 现在分词: intersecting 第三人称单数: intersects');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('retard', '[\'riːtɑːrd]', 'vt.妨碍；迟延；拖住 vi.受到延迟 n.阻止；迟延；减速', '1. Cold weather retards the growth of the crops. 寒冷的天气妨碍了庄稼生长。 2. Lack of science and education retards social progress. 缺乏科学和教育会妨碍社会进步。 3. They also used it for sunburns and to retard the aging process. 他们还用它来防治日光灼伤，以及延缓衰老过程。 4. The heavy rain retarded our arrival by seventy minutes. 大雨使我们推迟了七十分钟才到达。 5. The rearward regiments are in painful retard. 后续部队受到令人难以忍受的阻碍。', '名词: retarder 过去式: retarded 过去分词: retarded 现在分词: retarding 第三人称单数: retards');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('buffoon', '[bə\'fuːn]', 'n.丑角；缺乏教养之人', '1. The man painted his hair into blue,looking like a buffoon. 那人的头发染成了艳绿色，看上去像个小丑。 2. The crowd laugh an guffaw as soon as they see the ridiculous manner of the buffoon. 大家一见小丑那种滑稽样子,立刻哄堂大笑。 3. He is far more than the blustering buffoon who was on the stage on Monday. 本周一他在记者会上的表现犹如一个口无遮拦的跳梁小丑，但是赖特绝不止这么简单。', '名词: buffoonery');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mogul', '[\'moʊɡl]', 'n.显要人物；权势之人；小雪坡', '1. If he\'s young, he\'s a software mogul. 如果他很年轻，就是一个软件界巨子。 2. The football captain was the mogul of the school. 那足球队长是该校的大人物。 3. I don\'t deny that your sister comes the mogul over us, now and then. 我并不否认，你姐姐老是象个暴君似的骑在我们头上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('anorexia', '[ˌænə\'reksiə]', 'n.厌食症', '1. NPU tablets are well suited for anorexia patients. 网络处理器片非常适合性厌食症患者。 2. I think this is deliberately-induced anorexia. 我以为这是人为地制造厌食症。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('slay', '[sleɪ]', 'vt.杀害；残杀；<俚>使大笑', '1. Two visitors were brutally slain yesterday. 昨天有两名游客惨遭杀害。 2. The slaves slew their masters with swords. 奴隶们用刀杀死了主人。', '名词: slayer 过去式: slew 过去分词: slain 现在分词: slaying 第三人称单数: slays');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('possessed', '[pə\'zest]', 'adj.着魔的；冷静的；拥有的 动词possess的过去式及过去分词.', '1. She was ranting and raving like she was possessed. 她像着了魔似的大喊大叫。 2. He is able to remain possessed even in times of great trial. 他能够在极其艰难的时候都能保持冷静。 3. He was possessed of great self-confidence. 他极有自信。 4. She is possessed of a wonderfully calm temperament. 她性情非常文静。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('derangement', '[dɪ\'reɪndʒmənt]', 'n.精神错乱', '1. In order to have the stuff of a tyrant, a certain mental derangement is necessary. 为了成就一个暴君，一定程度的精神错乱是必须的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('blazon', '[\'bleɪzn]', 'v.以纹章装饰；宣布 n.纹章；盾徽', '1. The teacher blazoned she would punish the bad student. 老师宣布她将惩罚那个坏学生。 2. I blazon my house. 我以家徽装饰我的家。', '名词: blazoner 过去式: blazoned 过去分词: blazoned 现在分词: blazoning 第三人称单数: blazons');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rhetoric', '[\'retərɪk]', 'n.修辞；修辞学；华丽虚饰的语言', '1. The sentence contains impassioned rhetoric. 这个句子含有富有表现力的修辞。 2. How the influence of rhetoric upon context is felt? 试论修辞对语境的体现作用? 3. Do you know something about rhetoric? 你懂点修辞学吗? 4. This falls under the head rhetoric. 这个属于修辞学项目。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('woo', '[wuː]', 'v.寻求支持；求爱；求婚', '1. Politicians try to woo the voters before an election. 在选举前政治家们都力争选民的支持。 2. His efforts to woo her to his side proved fruitless. 他试图说服她站到自己一边的努力徒劳无功。 3. He wooed and won her. 他向她求爱成功而结婚。 4. I will never try to woo someone with fine car or gift. 我绝不会用香车和礼物来求婚。', '名词: wooer 过去式: wooed 过去分词: wooed 现在分词: wooing 第三人称单数: woos');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lucre', '[\'luːkər]', 'n.钱财(尤指不义之财)；利润', '1. You can\'t bribe me;I don\'t want you filthy lucre. 你别向我行贿，我不要你的臭钱。 2. I\'m going to write a book for the lucre of gain. 我打算写本书赚点钱。 3. You can\'t bribe me; I don\'t want you filthy lucre. 你别向我行贿，我不要你的臭钱。 4. He was blinded by the lust of lucre . 利欲使他不辨是非。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('maim', '[meɪm]', 'v.使伤残', '1. He was maimed in a First World War battle. 他在第一次世界大战的一埸战斗中受伤致残。 2. She survived the accident but she was maimed for life and will never walk again. 她在意外事故中大难不死，但却终身残废，再也不能行走了。', '名词: maimer 过去式: maimed 过去分词: maimed 现在分词: maiming 第三人称单数: maims');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hatchet', '[\'hætʃɪt]', 'n.短柄小斧；战斧', '1. Hit and run raiders armed with a hatchet but wearing no armour for stealth. 萨卡特卡斯突袭者使用战斧轻装上阵，是游击战术的大师。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gulp', '[ɡʌlp]', 'v.吞咽；喘气；抑制 n.吞食；[计]字节组', '1. He gulped his food. 他狼吞虎咽地吃东西。 2. She gulped nervously, as if the question bothered her. 她紧张地咽了一下，似乎那问题把她难住了。 3. She crawled onto the river bank and lay there gulping in air. 她爬上河岸,躺在那里喘着大气。 4. You must gulp back your vindictiveness 你必须抑制住你的复仇心理。 5. He downed the vodka in one gulp. 他将伏特加酒一饮而尽。', '副词: gulpingly 名词: gulper 过去式: gulped 过去分词: gulped 现在分词: gulping 第三人称单数: gulps');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('acme', '[\'ækmi]', 'n.顶点；极点', '1. It reached its acme of perfection. 它到达完美的最高点。 2. Schubert reach the acme of his skill while quite young. 舒伯特的技巧在他十分年轻时即已达顶峰。 3. His landscapes were deemed the acme of beauty. 他的风景画被视为美之极致。 4. His calligraphy has reached the acme of perfection. 他的书法已达到出神入化的境界。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('assimilate', '[ə\'sɪməleɪt]', 'v.使同化；吸收', '1. The USA has assimilated people from many different countries. 美国已经同化了许多来自不同国家的人。 2. Europeans and Jews do not readily assimilate. 欧洲人和犹太人不易同化。 3. Immigrants often want to assimilate quickly. 移民经常想迅速同化。 4. Some foods are assimilated more easily than others. 有些食物比另一些食物容易吸收。', '名词: assimilator 过去式: assimilated 过去分词: assimilated 现在分词: assimilating 第三人称单数: assimilates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('squelch', '[skweltʃ]', 'v.发出嘎吱声；压扁；镇压 n.嘎吱声；压扁；静噪电路', '1. She squelched along the muddy path. 她沿着泥泞小径格吱格吱地走。 2. The two boxers glowered each other to squelch the other. 两位拳击手凶狠地互相瞪着眼,想以此镇住对方。 3. He pulled his foot out of the mud with a squelch. 他扑哧一声从烂泥里拔出脚来。', '名词: squelcher 过去式: squelched 过去分词: squelched 现在分词: squelching 第三人称单数: squelches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dishevel', '[dɪ\'ʃevəl]', 'vt.使蓬乱；弄乱', '1. To disarrange or rumple; dishevel. 弄乱或弄皱；弄凌乱 2. To disarrange or rumple;dishevel. 弄乱或弄皱;弄凌乱 3. To disarrange or rumple ;dishevel. 弄皱衣服、弄乱头发. 4. To disarrange or rumple; dishevel . 打乱或弄乱；使蓬乱。', '名词: dishevelment 过去式: disheveled/dishevelled 过去分词: disheveled/dishevelled 现在分词: disheveling/dishevelling 第三人称单数: dishevels/dishevels');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('snuggle', '[\'snʌɡl]', 'v.依偎；挨近', '1. They snuggled up together in bed. 他们依偎着躺在床上。 2. He snuggled his head onto her shoulder. 他把头倚在她肩上。', '过去式: snuggled 过去分词: snuggled 现在分词: snuggling 第三人称单数: snuggles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('frigidity', '[frɪ\'dʒɪdəti]', 'n.寒冷；冷淡；性冷淡', '1. In order to protect the refugees from being killed and refrain them from starvation and frigidity, the missionaries did a lot of jobs, to which they devoted great love. 大屠杀期间，传教士们为了保护难民的生命安全，为了数十万难民免于饥饿与寒冷，从各方面给予了高度的关心，做了大量的工作，倾注了极大的爱心。 2. Doctor Simpson believes that Suzie\'s frigidity is due to some hang-up about men. 辛普森大夫认为苏西的性冷淡是由于她对男人有着异常的精神反应。 3. The reason that causes female frigidity is very much, the metropolis such as excessive overworked and disease affects the person\'s sexual desire. 造成女性性冷淡的原因很多，过度劳累和疾病等都会影响到人的性欲。 4. Doctor Simpson believes that Suzie\'s frigidity is due to some hang-up about men. 辛普森大夫认为苏西的性冷淡是由于她对男人有着异常的精神反应。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('clarify', '[\'klærəfaɪ]', 'vt.澄清；阐明；净化', '1. These brief remarks may serve to clarify the fact. 这些简要的评论可以澄清事实。 2. The teacher\'s explanation clarified the puzzling problem. 老师的说明澄清了困扰的问题。 3. Would you please clarify your question? 请你把你的问题说清楚好吗？ 4. She asked him to clarify what he meant. 她要他说清楚他是什么意思。', '名词: clarification 过去式: clarified 过去分词: clarified 现在分词: clarifying 第三人称单数: clarifies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fury', '[\'fjʊri]', 'n.愤怒；狂暴；狂怒的人；泼妇 Fury. n.[罗神]复仇女神', '1. He slammed the door with a vehement fury. 他愤怒地用力把门关上。 2. He was white with fury. 他气得脸色发白。 3. In a fury, she could not speak. 她气得连话也说不出来。 4. The fury of the storm abated. 暴风雨的威力已经减弱。', '名词复数: furies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('impair', '[ɪm\'per]', 'vt.损害；削弱 [计算机] 损伤.', '1. Loud noise would impair your hearing. 大的噪音会损害你的听觉。 2. Smoking can impair the sexual response. 抽烟可以削弱性反应。 3. His illness has impaired his efficiency. 生病降低了他的效率。 4. Don\'t boil the sauce as this and impair the flavor. 酱汁还要煮沸，否则会影响味道。', '名词: impairment 过去式: impaired 过去分词: impaired 现在分词: impairing 第三人称单数: impairs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('commonsense', '[\'kɒmən\'sens]', 'adj.有常识的；明白事理的 n.常识', '1. The commonsense commonwealth government no longer uses the uncommon commonplace. 有常识的联邦政府不再使用不寻常的陈腐之言。 2. The reader is given the commonsense tools that patients need in order to have ownership of their disease. 读者被给为了有他们的疾病的所有权，病患需要的有常识的工具。 3. He is sadly lacking in commonsense. 他极为缺乏常识。 4. Anybody who has commonsense will not believe such a rumour. 有点常识的人都不会相信这样的谣言。', '形容词: commonsensible 副词: commonsensibly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('natal', '[\'neɪtl]', 'adj.出生的；诞生的 Natal. n.纳塔尔（巴西东北部的海港城市；南非共和国东南部以前的省份）', '1. Trelawney\'s astrology is natal or genethiliacal astrology. 特劳里妮的占星术是依据出生日期所进行的占星。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hyphen', '[\'haɪfn]', 'n.连字号 v.以连字号连接', '1. The dash is longer than the hyphen. 破折号比连字号长。 2. Use a hyphen inside a character set to specify a range. 使用连字号内的字符集，以指定一个范围。', '过去式: hyphened 过去分词: hyphened 现在分词: hyphening 第三人称单数: hyphens');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('utilize', '[\'juːtəlaɪz]', 'vt.<美>利用或使用 =utilise（英）', '1. What criteria do you utilize in selecting employees? 在筛选雇员时你使用什么标准？ 2. In order to utilize land more fully, they adopted close planting. 为了更充分利用土地，他们采取了密植的办法。', '形容词: utilizable 名词: utilization 过去式: utilized 过去分词: utilized 现在分词: utilizing 第三人称单数: utilizes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nutrient', '[\'nuːtriənt]', 'adj.营养的；滋养的 n.营养物；营养品', '1. Clay contains available nutrient elements. 粘土会有有用的营养元素。 2. The nutrient in the soil acts as a stimulus to growth/to make the plants grow. 土壤中的养分能促进植物生长。 3. Sulfur is an essential nutrient for plants. 硫是植物的一种重要的营养元素。 4. Books are the nutrient of the whole world. 书藉是全世界的营养品。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('theocracy', '[θi\'ɑːkrəsi]', 'n.神权政体；神权政治；神权国家', '1. The theocracy controls the security. 在伊朗，掌控安全部门的是神职人员。 2. Such was the case with the Tibetan theocracy. 西藏的神权就是这样一种情形。 3. Theocracy and the fetters of religion. 政教合一，宗教桎梏沉重。 4. The theocracy’s religious teachings buttressed its class order. 农奴结婚、生子和死亡都得纳税。', '名词复数: theocracies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('jumble', '[\'dʒʌmbl]', 'vi.掺杂；混杂 vt.使混乱；搞乱 n.混杂；混乱 n.环形小甜饼', '1. This might be compared with the jumble of wavelengths of sound that go to make up ordinary noise. 这种现象可以与合在一起构成普通噪音的声波波长的混杂情况相比。 2. Reminiscent of experimental film or abstract expressionist paintings, the software creates an animated jumble of bright and energetic abstract light compositions. 实验电影或抽象表现主义绘画让人回想起该软件创建了一个明亮的光线和有力的抽象作品动画混杂。 3. This might be compared with the jumble of wavelengths of sound that go to make up ordinary noise. 这种现象可以与合在一起构成普通噪音的声波波长的混杂情况相比。 4. Reminiscent of experimental film or abstract expressionist paintings, the software creates an animated jumble of bright and energetic abstract light compositions. 实验电影或抽象表现主义绘画让人回想起该软件创建了一个明亮的光线和有力的抽象作品动画混杂。', '过去式: jumbled 过去分词: jumbled 现在分词: jumbling 第三人称单数: jumbles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inured', '[ɪn\'juəd]', 'adj.习惯的 动词inure的过去式及过去分词形式.', '1. He had become inured to ridicule. 他已受惯了他人的讥笑。 2. Once old Joe had inured himself to the solitary life of a widower, he began to improve in health and spirit. 一旦老乔适应了鳏夫的孤独生活，他的身体和精神状况便开始好转了。 3. Living in the far North had inured him to cold. 居于极北部使他习惯于寒冷。 4. After living here for years I\'ve become inured to the cold climate. 我在此地居住多年，已习惯寒冷的气候。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rend', '[rend]', 'v.撕破；分裂；劈开；强夺', '1. Wolves will rend a lamb to pieces . 狼群会把一只羔羊撕成碎片。 2. The stillness was rent by thunderous applause. 雷鸣般的掌声打破了寂静。 3. The party was rent in two. 这个政党分裂成两派。 4. The integrated country will rend into several independent regions sooner or later. 那个完整的国家早晚会分裂成几个独立的地区。', '过去式: rent/rended 过去分词: rent/rended 现在分词: rending 第三人称单数: rends');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inappreciable', '[ˌɪnə\'priːʃɪəbəl]', 'adj.微不足道的(小得难以觉察的)', '1. He said what he did was inappreciable. 他说他所做的事情微不足道。 2. He said what he has did is inappreciable. 他说他所做的事情微不足道。 3. The work he does are inappreciable he said. 他说他所做的事情微不足道。 4. My father seemed inappreciable to me for years. 从小到大，父亲在我眼里，好像是微不足道。', '副词: inappreciably');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('convict', '[kən\'vɪkt]', 'vt.宣判 ... 有罪；使 ... 知罪 n.囚犯；罪犯 adj.被定罪的', '1. You can\'t convict a man of a crime on circumstantial evidence alone. 不能只靠旁证就判定一个人有罪。 2. The criminal was convicted of murder. 歹徒被判谋杀罪。 3. He was convicted of his errors. 他认识到自己所犯的过失。 4. The convict fled away with a hostage. 囚犯带着一个人质跑了。 5. Let a convict person go free without any punishment. 让被定罪的人自由，不进行任何惩罚。', '过去式: convicted 过去分词: convicted 现在分词: convicting 第三人称单数: convicts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('oratorio', '[ˌɔːrə\'tɔːrioʊ]', 'n.(通常以《圣经》内容为主题的)清唱剧；神剧', '1. Its peaks are the symphony and the oratorio. 其顶峰为交响乐和清唱剧。 2. Haydn wrote his oratorio The Creation and another equally splendid work for voices, The Seasons. 海顿写了清唱剧《创世纪》和另一首也同样很出色的声乐作品《四季》。', '名词复数: oratorios');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('foreordain', '[ˌfoʊrɔː\'deɪn]', 'vt.预先注定', '1. It was foreordained that the company would suffer a spectacular collapse. 这个公司注定要彻底垮台。', '名词: foreordainment 过去式: foreordained 过去分词: foreordained 现在分词: foreordaining 第三人称单数: foreordains');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vigorous', '[\'vɪɡərəs]', 'adj.精力充沛的；有力的；元气旺盛的', '1. Old as he is, he is none the less vigorous and active. 虽然他年纪很大了，他仍然精力充沛。 2. He never ceased to chase after his dream in his vigorous youth. 在精力充沛的年轻时代他从未停止过追求自己的梦想。 3. She gave the floor a vigorous sponge all over. 她用海绵把地板 使劲儿擦了一遍。 4. He uttered several vigorous expletives when he dropped the iron on his foot. 他的熨斗掉下砸在脚上，他随口骂了几声。', '副词: vigorously 名词: vigorousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('drastic', '[\'dræstɪk]', 'adj.激烈的；重大的；极端的', '1. His view brings a drastic argument. 他的观点引起激烈的争论。 2. Drastic measures were taken to combat inflation. 已采取激烈措施对付通货膨胀。 3. Talk to me before you do anything drastic. 你采取任何重大行动之前要跟我谈谈。 4. Our budget needs drastic revision. 我们的预算需作重大修改。', '副词: drastically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pitch', '[pɪtʃ]', 'n.球场；程度；音调；推销；投掷；街头商贩摊位；沥青；树脂；松脂 v.投；颠簸；搭帐篷；定调；推销；用沥青覆盖', '1. The pitch is too small to play football on. 球场太小了, 无法踢足球。 2. Speculation has reached such a pitch that a decision will have to be made immediately. 这种胡乱猜测甚嚣尘上，已经到了必须立即解决的程度了。 3. The pitch depends on the frequency. 音调的高低是由频率决定的。 4. He has a very clever sales pitch. 他推销商品的口才很好。 5. She pitched the ball as far as she could. 她尽力把球投得远一些。', '过去式: pitched 过去分词: pitched 现在分词: pitching 第三人称单数: pitches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('outlet', '[\'aʊtlet]', 'n.出路；出口；通风口；批发商店，经销店', '1. He needs an outlet for all that pent up anger. 他那积愤需要有机会倾吐. 2. Playing rock music is a good outlet for his energy. 弹奏摇滚乐是他发泄精力的好方法。 3. So long as you dare the inner ear, you can find the outlet truly. 只要你敢于迷路,你才能真正找到出路。 4. Do not sit or lean unnecessarily close to the airbag outlet. 如无必要,不要靠近气袋出口。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rebus', '[\'riːbəs]', 'n.字谜；画谜', '1. This is called rebus writing, and is a tremendously common pattern in all early writing systems. 这称作谜画写字，是早期书写系统中非常普遍的一种方式。 2. Most people know a sort of puzzle called rebus. 大多数人都知道有一种称为画谜的猜谜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('arroyo', '[ə\'rɔɪoʊ]', 'n.干涸的河道；峡谷；小河', '1. Arroyo and Pargo would work off the bench as well. 阿罗约和帕戈同样是很好的补充。 2. Arroyo easily had more popular support than Estrada. 阿罗约轻易地就获得了比埃斯特拉达要多的民众支持。 3. It is the biggest raly against Arroyo in recent years. 这是菲律宾近些年来爆发的最大规模的一次游行。 4. The central bank said it had apologized to Arroyo for the mistake. 另外，银行还为此事向总统阿罗约进行了道歉。', '名词复数: arroyos');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hinge', '[hɪndʒ]', 'n.铰链；关键 vt.用铰链装 vi.依情况而定', '1. The two bones are articulated like a hinge. 这两块骨头由关节铰链般连接起来。 2. Rust is eating away the iron hinge. 铁锈正腐蚀着铁铰链。 3. This was the hinge of fate of the whole campaign. 这是决定整场战役命运的关键点。 4. Your arm should hinge from the shoulder. 你的手臂应该像从肩膀铰链住一般。 5. His acceptance will hinge upon the term. 他接受与否将依条件而定。', '过去式: hinged 过去分词: hinged 现在分词: hinging 第三人称单数: hinges');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('slot', '[slɑːt]', 'n.狭缝；槽；投币口；时间段；职位；（鹿的）足迹 v.插入；留细长的孔；放置', '1. She placed her card in a slot on the outside the bank. 她在银行外面把她的卡片塞进一条窄缝。 2. A cleaner slot is already reserved. 清洗器插槽已被保留。 3. He inserted a coin into the slot. 他把硬币插入投币口。 4. The best way to accomplish what on the list is to give each task a specific time slot. 完成单子上的各项任务的最好方法是给每项工作留出一个专门的时间。 5. We can slot in the new entry in alphabetical order. 我们可以按照字母顺序将新词条安插进去。', '过去式: slotted 过去分词: slotted 现在分词: slotting 第三人称单数: slots');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('miraculous', '[mɪ\'rækjələs]', 'adj.奇迹的；不可思议的', '1. Pu-erh tea becomes alive during a miraculous process that facilitates the development of active yeast cultures. 普洱茶在一个促进活跃的酵母栽培的发展的奇迹的程序期间变化而成。 2. And then the most miraculous thing happened. 然后最不可思议的事发生了。 3. If so, it possessed muscles of a quite miraculous quality. 果真如此的话，它所长的肌肉当具有不可思议的素质。', '副词: miraculously 名词: miraculousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nominate', '[\'nɑːmɪneɪt]', 'vt.提名；指派；登记赛马参加比赛', '1. I nominate Bill for the club president. 我提名比尔为俱乐部主席候选人。 2. Only students may nominate someone for the award. 只有学生才可以提名一些教师去拿这个奖项。 3. The board nominated him as the new director. 董事会指定他为新董事。', '名词: nominator 过去式: nominated 过去分词: nominated 现在分词: nominating 第三人称单数: nominates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('draconian', '[drə\'koʊniən]', 'adj.严厉的；残酷的 Draconian. adj.（古雅典立法者）德拉古的', '1. The city needs a draconian way of dealing with robbers. 这个城市需要一个严苛的办法来对付强盗。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('taxing', '[\'tæksɪŋ]', 'adj.费力的；棘手的 动词tax的现在分词形式.', '1. Raising a creative child can be taxing. 培养一个有创造性的孩子可能会费心费力。 2. Although the day had presented no taxing challenge, he had conducted himself with dignity and ability. 这一天，虽然没有遇到什么棘手的挑战，他的行为举止都表现了他的尊严和才干。', '副词: taxingly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('abstention', '[əb\'stenʃn]', 'n.节制；戒绝；(投票)弃权', '1. Without abstention, he must be a super winner in mundane competition. 如果不善加节制，那么，最后在世俗事务的竞争中，他将会变成一位超强的赢家。 2. Abstention from drinking and smoking is the only way to improve your poor health. 戒掉烟酒是改变你不良健康状况的唯一途径。 3. There were high levels of abstention in the election. 那次选举中有许多人弃权。 4. The motion is carried by 200 votes to 150, with 60 abstentions. 以200票对150票通过此项动议，但有60票弃权。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('decrepit', '[dɪ\'krepɪt]', 'adj.破旧的；衰老的', '1. We fell the old antiquated and decrepit schoolhouse into disuse. 我们淘汰了已经破烂不堪的旧校舍。 2. The decrepit old man led a poor life. 这个老翁贫困潦倒。 3. A decrepit old man sat on a park bench. 一个衰弱的老人坐在公园的长凳上。', '副词: decrepitly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('forgo', '[fɔːr\'ɡoʊ]', 'vt.放弃；弃绝；对...断念', '1. The workers agreed to forgo a pay increase for the sake of greater job security. 工人们为了工作更保险，同意放弃增加工资的要求。 2. We\'ll have to forgo our rest hour to gather in the wheat before the storm begins. 为了在风暴来到之前收完小麦,我们就只好放弃休息的时间了。 3. Time to prepare was a luxuary he would have to forgo. 因为时间不够，他不得不放弃做准备工作。 4. She decided to forgo dessert for a few days. 她决定几天不吃甜点心。', '名词: forgoer');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('interpose', '[ˌɪntər\'poʊz]', 'v.插入；插嘴；介入；调停', '1. He interposed his considerable bulk (ie body) between me and the window, so that I could not see out. 他个头很大，夹在我和窗户之间，我看不见外边的东西了。 2. `But how do you know that?\' he interposed. ｀那麽你是怎麽知道那件事的呢?＇他插嘴问道。 3. He interposed himself between them to stop them fighting. 他挤进两人中间，阻止他们打架。', '名词: interposal 过去式: interposed 过去分词: interposed 现在分词: interposing 第三人称单数: interposes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sustain', '[sə\'steɪn]', 'vt.支持；承受；维持；认可；经受', '1. His hope for future sustained him. 对未来的希望支持了他。 2. The ice will not sustain your weight. 这冰承受不了你的体重。 3. Some species may not be able to sustain the pressure from such prevalent raids. 一些物种无法承受这种猖撅的偷猎行为带来的压力。 4. They had sufficient food to sustain life. 他们有足够维持生命的食物。', '形容词: sustainable 名词: sustainability 过去式: sustained 过去分词: sustained 现在分词: sustaining 第三人称单数: sustains');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('banquet', '[\'bæŋkwɪt]', 'n.宴会 vi.参加宴会 vt.宴请；设宴', '1. The manager was called on to speak at the banquet. 经理应邀在宴会上讲了话。 2. He met the foreign friends and gave a banquet in their honour. 他会见了外国朋友，并设宴招待了他们。 3. The president gave the Prince and his attendants a farewell banquet. 总统为王子和他的随员举行了告别宴会。 4. We gave him a farewell banquet yesterday. 我们昨天为他举行了告别宴会。 5. It\'s interesting for me to banquet. 对我来说参加宴会很有意思。 6. They banqueted her like a queen when she became director of that company. 她成为公司的董事后，他们把她当成女王般设宴款待她。', '名词: banqueter 过去式: banqueted 过去分词: banqueted 现在分词: banqueting 第三人称单数: banquets');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ominous', '[\'ɑːmɪnəs]', 'adj.不祥的；预兆的', '1. That evening has an ominous silence. 那晚有着不祥的寂静。 2. She often has an ominous presentiment. 她时时有一种不祥的预感。 3. There were ominous dark clouds gathering overhead. 不祥的阴霾在头顶上汇聚。 4. He had a fall, which was ominous of his downfall. 他曾跌倒，这是他垮台的征兆。', '副词: ominously 名词: ominousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('acquaintance', '[ə\'kweɪntəns]', 'n.熟人；相识；了解', '1. He is not a friend of mine, only an acquaintance. 他不是朋友我的,只是个熟人。 2. I made his acquaintance at a party. 我是在一次聚会上认识他的。 3. Their acquaintance was of long standing. 他们相识多年。 4. He has only a limited acquaintance with the matter. 他对这件事的了解很有限。', '名词: acquaintanceship');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('neutralize', '[\'nuːtrəlaɪz]', 'v.使中立；使无效；中和', '1. Switzerland was neutralized in 1815. 瑞士于一八一五年实现中立。 2. High taxes will neutralize increased wages. 高税收将抵销增加了的工资。 3. Nothing could neutralize its good effects. 没有什么能抵消它所产生的好影响。 4. Lime was used to neutralize the acidity of the soil. 曾用石灰来中和土壤中的酸性。', '名词: neutralizer 过去式: neutralized 过去分词: neutralized 现在分词: neutralizing 第三人称单数: neutralizes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('synergic', '[sɪ\'nɜːdʒɪk]', 'adj.协作的；合作的', '1. Synergic itself may make the enemy. 协作本身可能成为敌人。 2. Learn about a powerful synergic methods helping build high performance teams. 深入学习一个先进的融合方法系统来提高跨文化团队建设的能力。 3. By game theory theory knowable, be not synergic rich to weichi is inefficient. 经济全球化促使世界经济高度相关 ,因而一国的经济决策难以孤立于世界其他国家的经济政策之外。由博弈论理论可知 ,非协作博弈是低效率的。在经济全球化的背景下 ,经济政策的国际协调尤显重要。 4. We put forward total model and general frame of synergic production procedure controlling based on workflow combining whit WfMS technology. 结合工作流技术，提出了基于工作流的协同生产过程控制总体模型和协同生产过程总线框架模型。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('segment', '[\'seɡmənt]', 'n.部分；弓形；瓣；段；节 vt.分割', '1. The company dominates this segment of the market. 这家公司控制了这一部分市场。 2. She cleaned a small segment of the painting. 她把画儿上的一小部分擦干净了。 3. The waiter brought us a dish of orange segments. 服务员给我们端来一盘掰开的橘子瓣。 4. Essentially, each segment is its own address space. 从本质上来说,每个段就是自己的地址空间。 5. Do you know how to segment an orange? 你知道怎么切橙子吗?', '形容词: segmentary 过去式: segmented 过去分词: segmented 现在分词: segmenting 第三人称单数: segments');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('enmity', '[\'enməti]', 'n.敌意；憎恨；不和', '1. He felt great enmity towards his brother. 他对他弟弟满怀敌意。 2. He returned my generous act with enmity. 他对我恩将仇报。 3. There shall be no enmity on my part. 我这方面可没有什么怨恨。 4. They are at enmity with each other. 他们彼此不和。', '名词复数: enmities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('aureole', '[\'ɔːrioʊl]', 'n.光环；光轮 =aureola.', '1. An aureole of romance plays about him. 他身上闪耀着浪漫的光辉。 2. They laid down the crown, and retained no aureole. 他们放下了冠冕，却没有保留光轮。', '异体字: aureola');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('equivocate', '[ɪ\'kwɪvəkeɪt]', 'vi.说模棱两可的话；支吾其词', '1. Don\'t equivocate with me I want a straight answer to a straight question! 别跟我绕弯子--我问的问题直截了当，回答也要直截了当！', '名词: equivocator 过去式: equivocated 过去分词: equivocated 现在分词: equivocating 第三人称单数: equivocates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vibrancy', '[\'vaɪbrənsi]', 'n.生气勃勃；鲜艳；振动', '1. In case of abnormal noise or excessive vibrancy during the running, it is necessary to stop the machine immediately to check and remove the faults. 运转过程中，如发现异常噪声或过大振动应立即停机检查，排除故障。 2. The site bears testimony to one of the earliest and longest-lasting encounters between China and the West based on the vibrancy of international trade. 站点熊证词到一个最早和长持久的遭遇在中国和根据国际贸易振动的西方之间。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('doyen', '[\'dɔɪən]', 'n.老资格；首席', '1. She founded the club and is now our doyenne. 她创建了这个俱乐部，现在是我们的元老。 2. Simon Baron-Cohen, a doyen of the field who works at Cambridge University, draws similar conclusions. 剑桥大学教授,业内资深人士西蒙拜伦-科恩,也得出类似结论。 3. China doyen professional golfer Mr. Zhang will host a junior clinic and giving signature in the tournament. 我国首席高尔夫球员张先生将亲临现场为青少年选手做球技指导及签名。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('concave', '[\'kɒnkeɪv]', 'adj.凹的 n.凹面；凹线；凹形', '1. The palm of one\'s hand is slightly concave. 人的手掌是微凹的。 2. A cylinder is a hollow tube with a closed concave base that permits it to stand upright. 钢瓶是中空的管道，封闭的底部是凹入的，这样可以直立起来。 3. His figure looks very funny in the concave mirror. 他的样子在凹镜里显得非常可笑。 4. These are aberration-corrected holographic concave gratings. 下表所列为像差校正全息凹面光栅。', '副词: concavely 名词: concaveness 过去式: concaved 过去分词: concaved 现在分词: concaving 第三人称单数: concaves');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scourge', '[skɜːrdʒ]', 'n.灾难；祸患；鞭子 vt 鞭笞；折磨；使痛苦；严惩.', '1. After the scourge of war came the scourge of disease. 战乱之后瘟疫又接踵而来。 2. Inflation was the greatest scourge of society. 通货膨胀是社会上的最大祸害。 3. The cruel captain used a scourge on his disobedient sailor. 那残忍的船长鞭打不服从命令的水手。 4. To scourge a man is to beat him with a whip . 鞭笞人就是用鞭子抽打他的人。', '名词: scourger 过去式: scourged 过去分词: scourged 现在分词: scourging 第三人称单数: scourges');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('heartrending', '[\'hɑːtˌrendɪŋ]', 'adj.令人心碎的；伤心的', '1. Time dulls the most exquisite emotions and softens the most heartrending grief. 时间会缓和最激烈的情感，减轻最伤心的悲痛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cloture', '[\'kloʊtʃə]', 'n.讨论终结 vt.结束辩论', '1. To apply cloture to(a parliamentary debate). 结束辩论而付诸表决采用终结辩论以表决的方法结束（国会辩论） 2. About two percent of all home loans are ring for cloture. 大约有2%25房屋贷款现陷入困境。 3. Research the cultural surrounding-in which Taoism\"s Tao philosophy conception been created: maternal cloture. 对于道家“道”概念自古便有许多见解、学说。 4. If Reid files a cloture motion, the Senate would vote on it on Nov. 13 because the Senate is not in session on Veterans’ Day. 如果雷德提出以表决方式结束审议，参议院会在11月13日进行表决，因为参议院在退伍军人节将休会。', '过去式: clotured 过去分词: clotured 现在分词: cloturing 第三人称单数: clotures');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('medal', '[\'medl]', 'n.奖章；勋章；纪念章 vi.获得奖章', '1. He got a medal for bravery. 他因勇敢而获得一枚奖章。 2. She was awarded a medal for bravery. 她因勇敢而获得奖章。 3. He got a medal for his gallantry. 他因勇敢而赢得一枚勋章。 4. The soldier earned a medal for bravery. 这名战士因作战勇敢而获得了勋章。 5. Winning the medal was a feather in his cap. 获得奖章是他的荣誉。', '形容词: medallic 过去式: medaled/medalled 过去分词: medaled/medalled 现在分词: medaling/medalling 第三人称单数: medals/medals');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('indulge', '[ɪn\'dʌldʒ]', 'vt.迁就；纵情于；放任 vi.放纵自己于 ...', '1. If you will indulge me for one moment, I think I can explain the matter to you. 你要是容我把话说完,我想我可以把此事给你解释清楚。 2. It pleased me to indulge her wishes. 放手满足她的欲望，使我感到高兴。 3. He no longer indulged himself in smoking. 他不再过度吸烟了。 4. He indulged his children too much. 他太纵容他的孩子们了。 5. I shall forget about dieting today. I\'m just going to indulge. 今天我要把节食计划置之脑后,想吃什么就吃什么。', '名词: indulger 过去式: indulged 过去分词: indulged 现在分词: indulging 第三人称单数: indulges');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rollicking', '[\'rɑːlɪkɪŋ]', 'adj.喧闹而欢乐的 动词rollick的现在分词和动名词形式.', '1. The orchestra dashed off into a rollicking movement. 乐队一个劲地轻快地奏起来。 2. At a rollicking youth rally, boys and girls celebrated boisterously. 在一个热闹的年轻人聚会上，男孩女孩们开心的庆祝着。 3. Among historians of science, that\'s what is known as a rollicking and auspicious start. 在科学历史学家中，这就是所谓的快乐而幸运的开始。', '副词: rollickingly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('conceal', '[kən\'siːl]', 'vt.隐藏；隐瞒；掩盖', '1. He concealed himself behind the tree. 他藏在树后。 2. It is against law to conceal evidence. 隐藏证据是违法的。 3. It is wrong for a man to conceal things from his wife. 一个男人对妻子隐瞒事情是不对的。 4. She tried to conceal what she had done to them. 她试图隐瞒对他们所做的事。', '形容词: concealable 名词: concealer 过去式: concealed 过去分词: concealed 现在分词: concealing 第三人称单数: conceals');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('admonish', '[əd\'mɑːnɪʃ]', 'vt.警告；训诫；告诫；提醒；敦促', '1. He was admonished for his carelessness. 他因粗心受到警告。 2. His wife admonished him not to drive too fast. 他的妻子警告他开车不要超速。 3. He has very sternly admonished student. 他十分严厉地训诫了学生。 4. He was admonished against doing wrong. 人们告诫他不要做坏事。', '副词: admonishingly 名词: admonisher 过去式: admonished 过去分词: admonished 现在分词: admonishing 第三人称单数: admonishes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('machination', '[ˌmæʃɪ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.阴谋；图谋', '1. The spy, a past master of machination and maneuver, was caught at last. 这个老奸巨滑的间谍终于被逮住了。 2. The British bourgeoisie, past masters of machination and manoeuvre, are a class which knows best when to compromise. 英国资产阶级历来老奸巨猾，是最善于在适当的时候作出妥协的一个阶级。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bestow', '[bɪ\'stoʊ]', 'v.授予；给予；<古>使用；<古>放置', '1. The trophy was bestowed upon the winner. 奖品授给了优胜者。 2. He wished to bestow great honors upon the hero. 他希望将那些伟大的荣誉授予这位英雄。 3. The surgeon bestowed eyesight on my blind son. 外科医生给了我的盲人儿子视力。 4. Bestow less time on daydreaming. 少花时间胡思乱想吧。', '形容词: bestowable 名词: bestowal 过去式: bestowed 过去分词: bestowed 现在分词: bestowing 第三人称单数: bestows');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('translucent', '[træns\'luːsnt]', 'adj.半透明的', '1. A translucent design was impressed on the paper. 一个半透明的设计被印在纸上。 2. She is wearing her translucent pajamas. 她穿着半透明的睡衣。', '副词: translucently 名词: translucence');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('anguish', '[\'æŋɡwɪʃ]', 'n.苦闷；痛苦 v.（使）极苦闷；（使）极痛苦', '1. Physical disability causes mental anguish. 生理伤残会引起心理苦闷。 2. I expected something with a terrible anguish that tortured my heart. 在极度揪心的苦闷中我似乎在期待着某种东西。 3. The quarrel caused her great anguish. 争吵给她造成了极大的痛苦。 4. Her mental anguish was beyond words. 她内心的痛苦难以用言语形容。 5. Physical disability causes mental anguish. 生理伤残会引起心理苦闷。', '过去式: anguished 过去分词: anguished 现在分词: anguishing 第三人称单数: anguishes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mortuary', '[\'mɔːrtʃueri]', 'n.停尸间；太平间 adj.与死有关的；丧葬的', '1. In the mortuary there are many stiffened corpses. 停尸房中摆满了僵冷的尸体。 2. A mortuary is where those who knew the deceased can come to pay their last respects. 太平间是死者的朋友可以见死者最后一面的地方。 3. Franz and the count descended these, and found themselves in a mortuary chamber. 弗兰兹和伯爵拾级而下，发觉他们已站在了一个坟场的交叉路口。 4. Her mortuary temple at Deir el-Bahari has many architectural merits. 她的葬礼神殿位于德伊埃尔巴哈里，颇具建筑学价值。', '名词复数: mortuaries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('carnivorous', '[kɑː\'nɪvərəs]', 'adj.食肉的；肉食性的', '1. Among the carnivorous animals are the leopard, lion, and tiger. 食肉动物中有豹子、狮子和老虎。 2. The latter are carnivorous, like hawks, tigers and men of action. 后者是食肉动物,如鹰,虎和善于行动的人。 3. The Venus Flytrap is a carnivorous plant. 补蝇草是肉食性植物。 4. The teeth of the ruminant are specialised, unlike those of a carnivorous animal. 反刍家畜的牙齿很特殊，完全不同于肉食动物。', '副词: carnivorously 名词: carnivorousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('encapsulate', '[ɪn\'kæpsjuleɪt]', 'v.装入胶囊；封进内部；压缩；概括', '1. We often try to take what varies in a system and encapsulate it. 我们经常试着找出系统中的变化并封装它。 2. In fact, you can define a function to encapsulate them. 事实上，您可以自己定义一个函数来封装它们。 3. The chairman\'s short statement encapsulates the views of the committee. 主席的简短陈词概括了委员会的观点。 4. This story encapsulates scenes from his childhood. 这个故事讲的是他童年的事。', '异体字: incapsulate 名词: encapsulation 过去式: encapsulated 过去分词: encapsulated 现在分词: encapsulating 第三人称单数: encapsulates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('attune', '[ə\'tjuːn]', 'v.使协调；使调和；调音', '1. His ear is still attune to the sound of the London suburb. 他的耳朵对伦敦郊区的语音仍然一听就能辨别。 2. We/Our ears are becoming attuned to the noise of the new factory nearby. 我们[我们的耳朵]逐渐适应了附近新工厂的噪声。', '过去式: attuned 过去分词: attuned 现在分词: attuning 第三人称单数: attunes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('facilitate', '[fə\'sɪlɪteɪt]', 'vt.促进；帮助；使 ... 容易', '1. Friendly contacts between different peoples facilitate the cultural and economic interchange. 各国人民的友好接触促进文化和经济交流。 2. We facilitate them to resist the enemy. 我们帮助他们与敌人对抗。 3. The new underground railway will facilitate the journey to all parts of the city. 新的地下铁路将为去城市各处提供方便。', '形容词: facilitative 名词: facilitator 过去式: facilitated 过去分词: facilitated 现在分词: facilitating 第三人称单数: facilitates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incrustation', '[ˌɪnkrʌ\'steɪʃn]', 'n.污垢；硬壳 = encrustation.', '1. Salt from the sea have encrust on the dry sand. 海水中的盐分在乾燥的沙子上结成硬皮。 2. A coating or an incrustation of filth or refuse. 污垢污物或垃圾的覆盖层或凝结物 3. The walls were decorated by incrustation with marble. 墙上镶嵌着大理石的装饰面。 4. A coating or an incrustation of filthor refuse. 污垢污物或垃圾的覆盖层或凝结物。', '异体字: encrustation');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('proffer', '[\'prɑːfər]', 'v.提供；提出 n.提供；提议；提供物', '1. He refused the proffered wine. 他拒绝了对方端过来给他的酒。 2. She proffered him her resignation. 她向他递交了辞呈。 3. His proffer of advice was not accepted finally. 他所提供的建议最后没被采纳。 4. I gave her a proffer of help. 我给了她一个援助性的建议。', '名词: profferer 过去式: proffered 过去分词: proffered 现在分词: proffering 第三人称单数: proffers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('molecule', '[\'mɑːlɪkjuːl]', 'n.分子；微粒', '1. A molecule is made up of atoms. 分子由原子组成。 2. Two atoms of hydrogen combine with one atom of oxygen to form a molecule of water. 两个氢原子和一个氧原子结合而成一个水分子。 3. We can see many molecules flying in the air when a sunbeam penetrated the dark room. 当一束光线穿进暗淡的房间时，我们可以看到空气中有许多小颗粒在飞舞。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('capsule', '[\'kæpsjuːl]', 'n.胶囊；太空舱；荚膜；概要 v.概括；装入胶囊 adj.精简的；微型的', '1. The capsule is filled with small soluble cases. 胶囊里充满了可溶的小颗粒。 2. This capsule is to be taken every four hours. 这种胶囊每隔四小时服一次。 3. This capsule is used for animals. 这个太空舱是用来装载动物的。 4. The capsule is a part of the spaceship in which the pilots live and work. 太空舱是宇宙飞船的一部分，宇航员是在太空舱里活动工作的。 5. Would you please capsule the news? 你能概括下这则新闻吗？ 6. This is a capsule description of the event. 这就是关于那个事件的简要介绍。', '过去式: capsuled 过去分词: capsuled 现在分词: capsuling 第三人称单数: capsules');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dodder', '[\'dɒdə]', 'v.步履不稳；蹒跚 n.[植]菟丝子', '1. The poor old man is beginning to dodder. 那位可怜的老头开始变得衰弱颤抖了。 2. After the accident, the driver could only dodder along. 事故后，司机只能蹒跚而行。 3. A few days after her operation, she could only dodder along. 她术后几天内只能蹒跚而行。 4. Dodder can reduce agricultural productivity and can render a seed crop unmarketable. 菟丝子会使农业减产，还会使种子作物滞销。', '名词: dodderer 过去式: doddered 过去分词: doddered 现在分词: doddering 第三人称单数: dodders');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bootless', '[\'buːtlɪs]', 'adj.无用的；无益的', '1. I \"trouble deaf heaven with my bootless cries\". 我“哭天天不应”。 2. He robs himself that spends a bootless gridf. 无益的悲伤只是掠夺自身. 3. A bootless 4-year-old enjoys his ride on a swing pushed by his grandfather at a park in Chatham, Canada. 在加拿大查坦的一座公园里，一名光脚的四岁男童让阿公推著秋千乐在其中。 4. The cry brought him skulking back to his master and a blunt bootless kick sent him unscathed across a spit of sand, crouched in flight. 这么一嚷，狗就怯懦地回到主人跟前，它被没穿靴子的脚猛踢了一下，虽没伤着，却倦缩着逃到沙滩另一头。', '副词: bootlessly 名词: bootlessness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('harmony', '[\'hɑːrməni]', 'n.和谐；协调；调和；和声', '1. An enterprise should be full of fairness and harmony. 一个企业内部应该充满公平与和谐。 2. Their life is a natural harmony. 他们的生活是一种自然的和谐。 3. There was not much harmony in international affairs during those years. 那些年国际事态不很协调。 4. Almost unconsciously she dressed in harmony with this note of simplicity. 她简直不自觉的打扮得跟这朴素的调子很调和。', '名词复数: harmonies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fortitude', '[\'fɔːrtətuːd]', 'n.刚毅；坚毅；不屈不挠', '1. There was no lack of gallantry and fortitude. 并不缺乏勇气和刚毅。 2. I know that my body lacks the fortitude and courage of a strapping young man, and that I cannot find my niche in life. 我知道我身上缺少一个男子汉所应该有的刚毅和果敢，顶不起一片天空。 3. Patience and fortitude conquer all things. 耐心与坚毅征服一切。 4. People who lack internal fortitude often become victims of those who have self-discipline. 那些缺乏内在坚毅的人往往会成为那些自律性很强的人的牺牲品。', '形容词: fortitudinous');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dignitary', '[\'dɪɡnɪteri]', 'n.高贵的人；高官 adj.地位尊贵的', '1. The dignitary also said that a solution must be worked out to put an end to the recent political unrest in the country. 该高官也说，必须提出一种解决方法，以将该国最近的政治动荡加以平息。', '名词复数: dignitaries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lien', '[\'liːən]', 'n.留置权；扣押权', '1. The court granted me a lien on my debtor\'s property. 法庭授予我对我债务人财产的留置权。 2. For the loan, he could have a lien placed on your home. 因为此笔贷款,他对你的住房享有留置权。 3. The garage has a lien on her car until she pays the repair bill. 汽车修理部在她小汽车上拥有留置权，该权利将延续到付清修理费。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('alibi', '[\'æləbaɪ]', 'n.不在场证明或辩解；托辞 v.辩解；找托辞开脱', '1. They\'ve got nothing on me I\'ve got an alibi. 他们没抓我的罪证,我有不在现场的证据。 2. The false alibi threw the police off the scent. 那个不在犯罪现场的伪证使警方失去了线索。 3. The alibi was fabricated by him. 这种托辞是他臆造出来的。 4. I was disappointed that Cathy cooked up an alibi. 我感到很失望的是凯瑟编造了一个托辞。', '名词复数: alibis 过去式: alibied 过去分词: alibied 现在分词: alibiing 第三人称单数: alibis');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('smattering', '[\'smætərɪŋ]', 'n.一知半解；一点点 动词smatter的现在分词形式.', '1. He has a smattering of knowledge about physics. 他对物理一知半解。 2. He only has a smattering of French. 他只懂一点法语。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ledger', '[\'ledʒər]', 'n.总帐；分类帐', '1. I\'ll have to check the entries in the ledger. 我得核对一下总帐的项目。 2. Rule out that entry in the ledger, the transaction was cancelled. 那项交易已取消了，请从分类帐上划去那笔帐目。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('plague', '[pleɪɡ]', 'n.瘟疫；麻烦；灾祸 vt.折磨；烦扰；造成麻烦', '1. Plague came in the wake of earthquake. 地震之后紧跟着就是瘟疫。 2. A great plague was then raging in the city. 那时一场大瘟疫正在该城肆虐。 3. He\'s been avoiding me like the plague since our quarrel. 我们吵架以後，他一直如避蛇蝎似的躲著我。 4. A plague of locusts affected the harvest a lot this year. 蝗灾大大影响了今年的丰收。 5. A demon or spirit once was thought to plague sleeping people. 梦魔被认为折磨睡觉的人的魔鬼或灵魂', '名词: plaguer 过去式: plagued 过去分词: plagued 现在分词: plaguing 第三人称单数: plagues');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sojourn', '[\'soʊdʒɜːrn]', 'n.旅居；逗留 v.旅居；逗留', '1. During his sojourn in Africa he learned much about native customs. 他在寄居非洲期间，学得了许多当地的风俗。 2. I was already feeling better for my sojourn here. 我在此逗留期间，觉得体力日渐恢复。 3. He should sojourn in villages and hamlets. 他应该在乡村小住数日。 4. He sojourned with a friend in Wales for two weeks. 他在威尔士一个朋友那儿住了两个星期。', '名词: sojourner 过去式: sojourned 过去分词: sojourned 现在分词: sojourning 第三人称单数: sojourns');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('carnage', '[\'kɑːrnɪdʒ]', 'n.大屠杀；残杀', '1. The battlefield was a scene of utter carnage. 战场完全是一片大屠杀的惨象。 2. Refugees crossed the border to escape the carnage in their homeland. 难民越过边界逃避国内的大屠杀。 3. Imagine the carnage if they ever escaped their cages. 想象一下它们一旦逃出铁笼后会出现的残杀景象！ 4. The ancient Rome battlefield was a scene of great carnage. 古罗马战场曾尸横遍地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fishery', '[\'fɪʃəri]', 'n.渔场；渔业', '1. Every family in this area makes a living on their fisheries. 这块地的每个家庭都以渔场为生。 2. The ship is engaged in pelagic fishery. 这艘船从事远洋渔业。 3. The golden age of whale fishery is over. 捕鲸业的黄金时代已过去。', '名词复数: fisheries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ballad', '[\'bæləd]', 'n.歌谣；诗歌；谣曲', '1. This poem has the distinctive flavour of a ballad. 这首诗有民歌风味。 2. The old man sang us a ballad. 老人给我们唱了一首歌谣。 3. The singer led off with a popular ballad. 歌唱家首先唱了一首流行的民歌。 4. The musician made the legend into a beautiful ballad. 这位音乐家把传说编成了一首美丽的民谣。', '形容词: balladic');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('yeast', '[jiːst]', 'n.酵母；发酵剂 vi.发酵；起泡沫', '1. Yeast can be used in making beer and bread. 酵母可用于酿啤酒和发面包。 2. The excess yeast is saved for future use. 剩余的酵母粉被保留下来以备以后使用。 3. The quality of rapid-fermenting yeast would directly influence yellow rice wine fermentation and wine quality. 机械化速酿酒母生产为机械化黄酒大罐发酵的优良发酵剂。 4. I want to re-pitch yeast in a red fermentation. 我要再草地红色酵母发酵。', '过去式: yeasted 过去分词: yeasted 现在分词: yeasting 第三人称单数: yeasts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sepulchral', '[sə\'pʌlkrəl]', 'adj.坟墓的；丧葬的；阴深的', '1. He spoke in sepulchral tones. 他用低沉的语调说话。 2. He looks quite sepulchral. 他看上去阴沉沉的。 3. There was a rather sepulchral atmosphere in the room. 房间里有一种颇为阴沈的气氛。', '副词: sepulchrally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('naive', '[naɪ\'iːv]', 'adj.天真的；幼稚的', '1. He derides her naive attitude. 他嘲弄她天真的态度。 2. Children always ask naive questions. 小孩子总问天真的问题。 3. This theory was intended to deceive naive people. 这一理论旨在欺骗天真群众。 4. The politician made a naive decision. 这个政治家做了一个幼稚的决定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pundit', '[\'pʌndɪt]', 'n.权威人士；专家；博学的印度人', '1. If you believe the fashion pundits,we\'ll all be wearing pink this year. 如果你相信这个时尚界的权威人士，我们今年全部都要穿成粉红色。 2. The pundits disagree on the best way of dealing with the problem. 如何妥善处理这一问题，专家众说纷纭。', '名词: punditry');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('desolate', '[\'desələt]', 'adj.荒凉的；荒芜的；孤单寂寞的', '1. We saw few houses in the desolate valley. 在这荒凉的山谷里,我们很少见到房子。 2. The railway station became desolate in the war. 战争期间，这个火车站变得荒凉了。 3. Heavy rain will wash away the soil from desolate hills. 大雨将把泥土从荒凉的山丘上冲走。 4. This place is desolate of all vegetation. 这个地方不长草木。', '副词: desolately 名词: desolateness 过去式: desolated 过去分词: desolated 现在分词: desolating 第三人称单数: desolates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('comedienne', '[kəˌmiːdi\'en]', 'n.喜剧女演员', '1. They applauded their favorite comedienne as she came on the stage. 当他们最喜欢的女喜剧演员登台时,他们鼓掌欢迎。 2. As proof of her versatility, the comedienne has appeared in films of extremely diverse character. 这位女喜剧演员出演了风格迥异的影片，这证明了她的多才多艺。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('forestry', '[\'fɔːrɪstri]', 'n.林学；林业', '1. Dendrology is one foundational course in the Specialty of Forestry. 树木学是林学专业的专业基础课。 2. Forestry and water conservancy made new progress. 林业、水利建设取得了新进展。 3. Mountainous areas, covered by forests, are the very place for forestry development. 森林覆盖的山区正是适合发展林业的地方。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('specialize', '[\'speʃəlaɪz]', 'v.专攻', '1. This shop specializes in chocolates. 这个商店专门出售巧克力。 2. He specializes in oriental history. 他专门研究东方史。 3. I specialize in the sale of cotton piece goods. May I act as your agent? 我专营棉布买卖，我可作为你们的代理吗？ 4. \"A science fiction cannot not be regarded as a mere entertainment, but in fact it tells the reader much more.\" \"科幻小说不能简单地看成是供消遣的，而实际上它给读者展示更深刻的内容。\"', '过去式: specialized 过去分词: specialized 现在分词: specializing 第三人称单数: specializes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('orotund', '[\'ɔːrətʌnd]', 'adj.(声音)宏亮的；(文风)夸大的', '1. \"Boy\'s son is orotund very soft. 男孩子声音很柔。 2. You talk an orotund bility a little bit bigger good?I can not hear clearly. 您说话声音能大一点好吗？我听不清楚。 3. But person\'s ear can make twos distinguishing time needed orotund the most short is 0.1. 而人耳能够把两个声音分辨出来所需要的时间最短为0.;1秒。 4. That is orotund but don\'t give up, he tells you, telling a friend\'s story for you. 那个声音却不放弃，他告诉你，要给你讲一个朋友的故事。', '名词: orotundity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('crumb', '[krʌm]', 'n.【C】碎屑；少许；<俚>无价值的人', '1. She swept up the crumbs. 她打扫了碎屑。 2. Ruth nearly choked on the last crumb of her pastry. 鲁斯几乎被糕点的最后一块碎屑所噎住。 3. He gave me a few crumbs of information about the writer. 他为我提供了有关这位作家的一些情况。 4. The boss finally gave a few crumbs of praise for their hard work. 老板总算给予他们的努力少许表扬。', '过去式: crumbed 过去分词: crumbed 现在分词: crumbing 第三人称单数: crumbs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fusillade', '[ˌfjuːsə\'leɪd]', 'n.（枪炮）齐射；连发；连珠炮似的批评', '1. Our fusillade from the left flank caught them by surprise. 我们从左侧的枪炮齐射使他们吃惊。 2. He faced a fusillade of questions from the waiting journalists. 正在等候的记者们向他发出连珠炮似的提问。', '过去式: fusilladed 过去分词: fusilladed 现在分词: fusillading 第三人称单数: fusillades');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('enrapture', '[ɪn\'ræptʃər]', 'vt.使狂喜；使出神', '1. We were enraptured by the view of the mountains. 我们看到山峦景色，心花怒放。', '名词: enrapturement 过去式: enraptured 过去分词: enraptured 现在分词: enrapturing 第三人称单数: enraptures');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('animosity', '[ˌænɪ\'mɑːsəti]', 'n.憎恶；仇恨', '1. As the years have passed, the animosity between the two has only grown. 几年过去了，这种憎恶之感却在不断增加。 2. Celtic Football Club boss Gordon Strachan insists there is no animosity between him and Sir Alex Ferguson. 凯尔特人队的主教练斯特拉坎坚称他和弗格森之间没有相互憎恶。 3. There is great animosity between the two classes. 这两个阶级之间有很深的仇恨。 4. He has a strong animosity against his enemy. 他对敌人有强烈的仇恨。', '名词复数: animosities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('prologue', '[\'proʊlɔːɡ]', 'n.开场白；序言；序幕', '1. The prologue of the book is a famous writter. 这本书的序言是由一个著名作家写的。 2. At the beginning, I wrote the prologue in Chinese. 最初，我用中文写了本版的序言。 3. The murder was the prologue to World War I. 这场谋杀是第一次世界大战的序幕。 4. Certainly, this was only the splendid prologue. 当然，这只是精彩的序幕。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inexorable', '[ɪn\'eksərəbl]', 'adj.无情的；不可阻挡的；坚决不变的 n.坚定不移的人', '1. He made an inexorable demand. 他提出一个无情的要求。 2. All flashed indignant or appealing glances at the inexorable Davis. 大家都把愤怒、哀求的目光投向冷酷无情的戴维。 3. Our reform made an inexorable march of progress. 我们的改革取得了势不可挡的进展。 4. Cynthia was inexorable; she would have none of him. 辛西娅很坚决；她绝不接受他。', '副词: inexorably 名词: inexorability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('prong', '[prɔːŋ]', 'n.叉状物；尖齿；分支；(进攻、论点等的)方面 v.刺；贯穿；翻掘', '1. One of the prongs of the garden fork went through his foot. 园艺叉子的一个尖齿把他的脚扎了。 2. Never cut off the third prong and try to fit it into a two-hole outlet. 千万不要把三线插头改成两线插头来使用。 3. the two prongs of a river 河流的两条分支 4. The second prong of a crisis-resolution strategy must aim to boost banks\' capital. 危机解决策略的另一个方面在于必须以推动银行资本为目标。', '过去式: pronged 过去分词: pronged 现在分词: pronging 第三人称单数: prongs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bait', '[beɪt]', 'n.饵；引诱 v.以饵引诱；逗弄；中途休息', '1. The fish snapped at the bait. 那鱼一下子咬住了鱼饵。 2. Earth worms are often used as bait. 蚯蚓常用作鱼饵。 3. The steaming cake was a bait for the hungry boy. 那热气腾腾的蛋糕对这个饥饿的男孩是个诱惑。 4. As soon as I mentioned money he rose to the bait, and became really interested. 我一提钱他便怦然心动，上了我的钩。 5. They bait the mousetrap with stale cheese. 他们用变质的乳酪作捕鼠夹的诱饵。', '名词: baiter 过去式: baited 过去分词: baited 现在分词: baiting 第三人称单数: baits');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vex', '[veks]', 'vt.使恼怒；使恼火；烦扰；使困惑', '1. She was vexed at her failure. 她因失败而苦恼。 2. His silly chatter would vex you. 他那无聊的闲扯会使你烦恼。 3. His continuous chatter vexes me. 他唠叨不休，真烦死我了。 4. There was another grave problem to vex him. 还有一个使他困惑的严重问题。', '副词: vexedly 名词: vexer 过去式: vexed 过去分词: vexed 现在分词: vexing 第三人称单数: vexes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fraction', '[\'frækʃn]', 'n.小部分；少许；分数；片段', '1. Mother\'s careful with her money, and spends only a fraction of her earnings. 母亲用钱很审慎,只花自己收入很小的一部分。 2. The door opened a fraction. 门稍微开了条缝。 3. I can only pay a fraction of my bill. 我只付我的帐单的一小部分。 4. Open the window a fraction, please. 请把窗户打开一点。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('affidavit', '[ˌæfə\'deɪvɪt]', 'n.宣誓书', '1. Fairford ran over the affidavit. 费尔福特把宣誓书匆匆看了一遍。 2. But an affidavit filed by Eastern Health as a response to the lawsuit shows the error rate is actually much higher. 但在东部卫生组织回应这场官司的宣誓书中，误差率实际上远远高于预期。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tournament', '[\'tʊrnəmənt]', 'n.锦标赛；比赛；比武', '1. Winning the tournament gratified the golf champion. 那位高尔夫球世界冠军为赢得锦标赛而感到高兴。 2. His victory in the tournament earned him $50000. 他在这次锦标赛中获胜，挣得了5万元。 3. I won the tennis tournament. 我赢了那场网球比赛。 4. She went out in the first round of the tournament/went out of the tournament in the first round. 她在比赛的第一轮比赛中遭淘汰。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('execrate', '[\'eksɪˌkreɪt]', 'vt.憎恶；咒骂；厌恶', '1. Shall execrate you with the ungodly. 咒骂你的不敬。 2. Those that bless you I will bless, those that curse you, I will execrate. 我将祝福那些祝福你的人，我也将诅咒那些诅咒你的人。 3. Those that bless you I will bless,those that curse you, I will execrate. 天主对亚伯兰说：“离开你的家乡，你的亲人和你父亲的家，到一个我指引你去的地方。 4. There is, in the synagogue, in the mosque, in the pagoda, in the wigwam, a hideous side which we execrate, and a sublime side, which we adore. 圣殿、清真寺、菩萨庙、神舍，所有那些地方都有它丑恶的一面，是我们所唾弃的，同时也有它卓绝的一面，是我们所崇敬的。', '形容词: execrative 名词: execrator 过去式: execrated 过去分词: execrated 现在分词: execrating 第三人称单数: execrates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('heliotrope', '[\'hiːliətroʊp]', 'n.天芥菜属植物；淡紫色', '1. In the beginning, there are only heliotrope flowers on the treetops. 开始时，干枯的树梢上开满了淡紫色的花； 2. So Laurie played and Jo listened, with her nose luxuriously buried in heliotrope and tea roses. 这样劳瑞便弹了起来。裘把自己的鼻子惬意地埋在无芥菜和庚申蔷薇花簇中倾听着。 3. There are many heliotrope flowers on the top of the trees outside of the window of my apartment. 窗外大树的顶端开满了淡紫色的花。 4. Notes of heliotrope flowers and vanilla - combine to create the warm floral base notes. 天芥草及云呢拿-混合为散发温暖花香的基调。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('epithet', '[\'epɪθet]', 'n.性质描述词；称号；浑名', '1. What\'s wrong here is the epithet \"stinking\". 错就错在那个“臭”字上。 2. The film is long and dramatic but does not quite earn the epithet \"epic\". 这部影片篇幅长，戏剧性强，不过还不能誉为“史诗”。 3. In \'Alfred the Great\', \'the Great\' is an epithet. “阿尔弗雷德大帝”中的“大帝”是个称号。 4. He cursed me, using a lot of rude epithets like \"bloody\". 他用了一大串诸如“该死的”之类的粗俗词语来诅咒我。', '形容词: epithetic');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('detritus', '[dɪ\'traɪtəs]', 'n.碎石；碎屑', '1. Flora of clay desert is similar to that of detritus desert. 粘土荒漠上的植物和碎石荒漠上的植物相似。 2. Detritus usually consists of gravel, sand and clay. 岩屑通常是由砂砾、沙和粘土组成的。 3. A channel is no sooner cut than it chokes in its own detritus. 一个河道刚被切割了不久，很快又被它自己的碎屑物质所充塞。', '形容词: detrital 名词复数: detritus');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('naivety', '[naɪ\'iːvəti]', 'n.质朴；朴素；天真', '1. Ann\'s naivety is at least a fault on the right side. 安的天真行为至少是一种值得称道的缺点。 2. The President smiled, with fatigued tolerance for a minor person\'s naivety. 总统笑了笑，疲惫地表现出对一个下级人员的天真想法的宽容。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('interlace', '[ˌɪntər\'leɪs]', 'v.（使）交织；（使）组合；（使）交错', '1. Her mother interlaces her hair with ribbons. 母亲用缎带把她的头发扎起来。 2. The top branches of the two trees interlace with one another. 这两棵树的树顶树枝相互交织在一起。 3. The interlacing branches on the picture look poetic. 图上交错的树枝看起来很有诗意。 4. Riparian zone was an important interlace or eco-tone between aquatic ecosystems and upland ecosystems. 湖滨带是水生和陆地生态系统间的过渡带或生态交错区。', '名词: interlacement 过去式: interlaced 过去分词: interlaced 现在分词: interlacing 第三人称单数: interlaces');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('billow', '[\'bɪloʊ]', 'n.巨浪；如巨浪翻腾的东西 v.（像巨浪般）汹涌；波动；使翻腾', '1. The billow of the atlantic dash high on the rock during a storm. 暴风雨时，大西洋的巨浪冲撞岩石掀得很高很高。 2. Billows of flame swept through the forest. 熊熊烈火席卷森林。 3. The wind blew hard and the sea was billowing. 疾风劲吹，海浪汹涌。 4. A door shuts with a bang and curtains billow into the room. 房门砰地一声关上了，窗帘被风翻卷着吹向屋内。', '形容词: billowy 名词: billowiness 过去式: billowed 过去分词: billowed 现在分词: billowing 第三人称单数: billows');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hormone', '[\'hɔːrmoʊn]', 'n.荷尔蒙；激素', '1. Ethylene is a growth hormone in plants. 乙烯是植物中一种生长荷尔蒙。 2. The hormone treatment might lead to the man growing breasts. 给男性注射许多的女性荷尔蒙可能导致他们长出乳房。 3. Estrogen hormone therapy advice is not yet uniform. 激素激素治疗意见尚不统一。 4. Emotional states can affect our hormone levels. 情绪会影响激素水平。', '形容词: hormonal 副词: hormonally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('distinctive', '[dɪ\'stɪŋktɪv]', 'adj.独特的，有特色的，与众不同的', '1. Soldiers wear a distinctive uniform. 士兵们穿着特制的制服。 2. The beer impressed me with its distinctive taste. 那种啤酒以它独特的口味给我留下了深刻的印象。 3. He has a distinctive goatee, so I can recognize him easily. 他留着独特的山羊胡子，所以我很容易就认出他来了。', '副词: distinctively 名词: distinctiveness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('conspicuous', '[kən\'spɪkjuəs]', 'adj.显著的；显眼的；显而易见的', '1. Lincoln is a conspicuous example of a poor boy who succeeded. 林肯是一个穷苦孩子而功成名就的出色例子。 2. He was conspicuous for his bravery. 他因骁勇而出名。 3. A traffic sign should be conspicuous. 交通标志应该明显。 4. Notices shall be put in conspicuous places. 要保证把布告贴在显眼的地方。', '副词: conspicuously 名词: conspicuousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('conscientious', '[ˌkɒnʃɪ\'enʃəs]', 'adj.认真的；谨慎的；负责的', '1. The janitor is very conscientious. 那个管理员很认真。 2. He\'s changed into a conscientious worker. 他已成为一个工作认真的人了。 3. Be more conscientious about your work. 要更谨慎做你的工作。 4. This essay is a most conscientious piece of work. 这篇论文是精雕细刻的工作.', '副词: conscientiously 名词: conscientiousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('torrential', '[tə\'renʃl]', 'adj.倾泻的；急流的；（感情、言辞等）猛烈的', '1. Torrential rain began to pour as soon as I stepped into the room. 我刚进门, 暴雨就倾泻而下。 2. We got caught in a torrential downpour. 我们遇上一场瓢泼大雨。 3. The torrential flood annihilated the village. 山洪冲毁了这个村落。', '副词: torrentially');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dissolve', '[dɪ\'zɑːlv]', 'vt.使溶解；解散；消除；解决(问题)；使沮丧 vi.溶解；液化；消散；变得模糊 n.叠化画面', '1. Dissolve one tablet in warm water. 将一片药片溶解在热水中。 2. The parliament was dissolved. 议会解散了。 3. As president, he can dissolve parliament on a whim. 作为总统，他可以随意解散议会。 4. Plasmin is the main protease to break down and dissolve thrombus. 胞浆素是消除和分解血栓的主要蛋白酶。 5. Ice dissolved in the warm weather. 冰在温暖的天气中溶化了。', '形容词: dissolvable 名词: dissolver 过去式: dissolved 过去分词: dissolved 现在分词: dissolving 第三人称单数: dissolves');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incantation', '[ˌɪnkæn\'teɪʃn]', 'n.咒语；魔法', '1. This is an incantation that can spell anybody. 这是一句能迷惑住人的咒语。 2. Under these circumstances it acquires the charm of an incantation. 在这种情况下，该字象咒语一般具有一种魔力。', '形容词: incantational');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('warranted', '[\'wɒrəntɪd]', 'adj.担保的；保证的 动词warrant的过去分词和过去式.', '1. They bid stock prices up far beyond what the trend in real business profits warranted. 他们把股票价格哄抬到远远超过企业的实际利润趋势所能保证的股票价值。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('transfer', '[træns\'fɜːr]', 'v.转移；调任；转乘 n.迁移；移动；换车；汇兑', '1. The exhibition was transferred to another city two days later. 两天后,这个展会转移到另外一个城市。 2. She has been transferred to another department. 她已被调往另一个部门。 3. I took the subway and then transferred to the bus. 我搭乘地铁然后再改乘公共汽车。 4. Our company will have a transfer to London. 我们公司将迁往伦敦。', '形容词: transferable 名词: transferability 过去式: transferred 过去分词: transferred 现在分词: transferring 第三人称单数: transfers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gnomic', '[\'noʊmɪk]', 'adj.格言的', '1. It\'s by no means gnomic, for he\'s such a brown-noser. 赵本山：精辟啥啊，他是屁精。 2. Moreover, the pithy sayings in gnomic style such as what you introduced here seem more suitable for children. 而且，较之我所介绍的冗长故事而言，您所展示的这类箴言式的短句可能更适合孩子的胃口。 3. IN FRANCE railway crossings are adorned with a small lesson for a life of gnomic brevity. 法国许多铁路的交叉路口都配有一些警示标牌，上面书写着短小精辟的人生格言。 4. At this low ebb, his hero Cantona begins to magically appear to offer him gnomic advice, like an aphoristic life coach. 在人生低谷，他的英雄偶像简东拿奇妙地出现在眼前，激励他，像一名常给励志格言的生命教官。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dose', '[doʊs]', 'n.剂量；一剂；一服 vt.给 ... 服药', '1. Take one dose of this cough syrup three times a day. 每天服三次这种止咳糖浆，每次服一剂量。 2. The doctor prescribed an oral dose of medicine. 医生开了一剂口服药。 3. A dose of this medicine will put you right. 这药你只要服一剂，你的病就会好的。 4. Failing the exam was a hard dose to swallow. 考试不及格是一服难咽的苦药。 5. She dosed up the children with cough syrup. 她把止咳糖浆给孩子们吃了。', '名词: doser 过去式: dosed 过去分词: dosed 现在分词: dosing 第三人称单数: doses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rejoinder', '[rɪ\'dʒɔɪndər]', 'n.回答；反驳；第二次答辩', '1. She always has a witty rejoinder to any question. 她总是对待任何问题都能机智的回答。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sentinel', '[\'sentɪnl]', 'n.哨兵；传送器；[计]标记符号 v.放哨；设岗哨', '1. The sentinel was stationed on a hill. 哨兵被派在山上站岗。 2. The press is a sentinel of our liberty. 新闻界是捍卫我们自由的卫兵。 3. At either end of the bridge a sentinel stood with rifle at ready. 桥的两头各有一名哨兵，荷枪实弹守卫着。', '过去式: sentineled/sentinelled 过去分词: sentineled/sentinelled 现在分词: sentineling/sentinelling 第三人称单数: sentinels/sentinels');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inoculate', '[ɪ\'nɑːkjuleɪt]', 'v.给 ... 注射疫苗；灌输', '1. A corps of doctors arrived to inoculate the recruits. 一队医生来给新兵打防疫针。', '形容词: inoculative 名词: inoculator 过去式: inoculated 过去分词: inoculated 现在分词: inoculating 第三人称单数: inoculates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('paranoia', '[ˌpærə\'nɔɪə]', 'n.偏执狂；妄想狂', '1. Paranoia runs rampant in this person\'s psyche. 这种人心理充满了偏执狂。 2. Maintain healthy paranoia about competitors. 对竞争者要保持一种健康的偏执狂心态。 3. I took a list of the traits of paranoia from a psychiatrist recently. 最近，我从一位精神病医生那里拿来一张妄想狂症状的单子。 4. But Rachel continued to lapse into bouts of paranoia and aggression. 但雷切尔继续陷于一阵阵的妄想狂及侵略行为中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sleight', '[slaɪt]', 'n.熟练；巧妙；诡计；狡诈', '1. The trick is done simply by sleight of hand. 变这个戏法全凭手法敏捷。 2. He makes a coin disappear by sleight of hand. 他一转手便把硬币变得没了。 3. He\'s used sleight of hand on the accounts. 他在账目上做了手脚。 4. The company accounts show a little financial sleight of hand. 公司帐目显示在财务上耍了一点手腕.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('propagate', '[\'prɑːpəɡeɪt]', 'v.繁殖；增殖；传播；传送', '1. Most plants propagate by seed. 大多数植物靠种子繁殖。 2. Insects propagate themselves by means of eggs. 昆虫以产卵繁殖后代。 3. This kind of cell propagates faster in warm environment. 在温暖的环境中,这种细胞增殖更快。 4. We should propagate scientific ideas . 我们应该传播科学思想。', '形容词: propagable 名词: propagator 过去式: propagated 过去分词: propagated 现在分词: propagating 第三人称单数: propagates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('criteria', '[kraɪ\'tɪəriə]', 'n.标准；尺度；准则 名词criterion的复数形式.', '1. It was necessary to satisfy stringent criteria to justify its use. 使用苛刻的标准来评价其实用性是完全必要的。 2. The criteria will be different from those that pertain elsewhere. 这里的标准将不同于其他地方适用的标准。 3. They commonly focus attention upon easily recognizable criteria of action. 它们通常把注意力集中在作用的易于识别的尺度上。 4. Is the defined method and the criteria made known to all staff concerned? 公司有否向有关职员公布该编配方法和准则?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('oath', '[oʊθ]', 'n.誓言；誓约；咒骂语', '1. Repeat the oath after me. 请跟着我宣誓。 2. The judge received their oath of allegiance. 法官听取了他们的忠诚誓言。 3. Tom stood by his oath to his father. 汤姆遵守他给父亲立下的誓言。 4. She carries an oath rod that will destory the minds of those it strikes. 她携带着一根誓约之杖，能够摧毁所有被杖击中者的意识。', '名词复数: oaths');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('episode', '[\'epɪsoʊd]', 'n.一段情节；片段；轶事；插曲', '1. The first episode goes out next Friday evening at 8.00 pm. 下星期五晚上8时播出第一集。 2. Relating to or resembling an episode. 插曲似的关于或类似插曲的 3. One of the funniest episodes in the book occurs in chapter 6. 书中最有趣的情节是在第6章。 4. The episode of this film sounds good. 这部电影的插曲很好听。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('banister', '[\'bænɪstər]', 'n.栏杆的支柱；楼梯的扶栏 =bannister.', '1. He arched over the banister to grab her hand. 他拱起身子越过栏杆去抓她的手。 2. He had to lie over the banister because he was getting dizzy. 他感到晕眩，只得靠在栏杆上。 3. Pay much attention to the banister since it is just painted. 这边的扶手才刚被粉刷过,很容易掉色。 4. The boys amused themselves by sliding down the banister. 男孩们从楼梯扶手滑下以取乐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vesture', '[\'vestʃə]', 'n.衣服；覆盖物 vt.用衣服盖住；穿衣', '1. Our city offer overseas in vesture fair service for production aside from infrastructure. 我市除了向外国投资者提供基础设施外，还提供良好的生产服务设施。', '过去式: vestured 过去分词: vestured 现在分词: vesturing 第三人称单数: vestures');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dilemma', '[dɪ\'lemə]', 'n.困境；进退两难', '1. In the process of modern urban development, we often find ourselves in a dilemma. 在都市的发展中,我们往往会陷入困境。 2. The bad weather put us in a dilemma——shall we move on or go back? 糟糕的天气使我们进退两难——是继续前进呢,还是打道回府？', '形容词: dilemmatic');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('arbitrate', '[\'ɑːrbɪtreɪt]', 'v.仲裁', '1. Mr.Smith has been asked to arbitrate between the employers and their workers. 已经请了史密斯先生来仲裁雇主与工人之间的纷争。 2. They agreed to arbitrate their dispute. 他们同意经仲裁解决争端。', '过去式: arbitrated 过去分词: arbitrated 现在分词: arbitrating 第三人称单数: arbitrates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hue', '[hjuː]', 'n.色调；色彩；样子；意味；信仰；喊叫', '1. The cool hue in the picture is distinct from the other ones. 这幅画的冷色调与其他画截然不同。 2. Her normally rosy face took on a deeper hue. 她平常玫瑰色的脸上呈现出更深的色彩。 3. The diamond shone with every hue under the sun. 这颗钻石在阳光下显得色彩斑斓。 4. This puts a different hue on the matter. 这么一来,事情的性质就不一样了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('periphrastic', '[ˌperɪ\'fræstɪk]', 'adj.迂回曲折的；[语]迂说法的', '1. Being a man true to my word, today we ll look at two such constructions, the ablative absolute and the passive periphrastic ; as well as the dative of agent. 身为言而有信之人，今天我要介绍独立从格和迂说被动这两种结构，以及施事予格（间接受格）的用法。 2. Most of the time, a periphrastic construction with a dative of agent will be very cumbersome to translate in to English. 大多数情况下，有施事予格的迂说结构要翻译成英文时会变得很累赘； 3. Finally, let s look at the Dative of agent today.Instead of the ablative of agent, with periphrastic constructions, the dative of agent is used. 最后我们来看施事予格（间接受格），在迂说结构中我们不用施事从格而使用予格。 4. Some common English expression used to translate a periphrastic construction are: Has to be, had to be, should, ought, must. 迂说只是一个简单概念所用的花俏名称，表示以迂迴方式说明某事的概念。', '副词: periphrastically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('convivial', '[kən\'vɪviəl]', 'adj.好交际的；愉快而随和的；联欢的', '1. Fahmy was transparent and subtle, convivial and abrasive. 法赫米这个人既开朗又含蓄,善于交际而又粗暴。 2. They tend to be sociable and convivial and \"like a laugh\". 他们具有乐天的个性，喜欢放声大笑。 3. Everyone likes to have dinner with her because she is such a convivial person. 每个人都喜欢和她共进晚餐，因为她是个相当友善的人。 4. The three spend a convivial evening together. 3人一起度过了一个欢乐的夜晚。', '副词: convivially 名词: conviviality');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('plaintive', '[\'pleɪntɪv]', 'adj.哀伤的；可怜的', '1. I heard a plaintive cry. 我听到一声悲伤的哭泣。 2. The song has plaintive melody. 这首歌曲的曲调悲伤。', '副词: plaintively 名词: plaintiveness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ostracize', '[\'ɑːstrəsaɪz]', 'vt.放逐；排斥', '1. He was ostracized by his colleagues for refusing to support the strike. 他因不支持罢工而受同事排斥。', '过去式: ostracized 过去分词: ostracized 现在分词: ostracizing 第三人称单数: ostracizes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('investiture', '[ɪn\'vestɪtʃər]', 'n.任职仪式；授权仪式', '1. President Bush attended the investiture or formal swearing-in ceremony for Chief Justice John Roberts early this morning. 早上，布什总统参加了罗伯特斯的就职宣誓仪式。 2. The elegant Sarkozy family posed Kennedy-style for the cameras on investiture day. 在授权日,高贵的萨科齐家庭以肯尼迪风格的姿势出现在镜头前。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('factual', '[\'fæktʃuəl]', 'adj.事实的；真实的', '1. The jury was convinced of the factual testimony. 陪审团相信了这充满事实的证词。 2. They couched criticisms in factual language. 他们用事实的语言表达了批评。 3. This seems to be slanted against us from getting factual data. 这不利于我们获得真实的数据。 4. He has difficulty distinguishing between imaginary and factual information. 他难以区分假想的和真实的信息。', '副词: factually 名词: factuality');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('retrench', '[rɪ\'trentʃ]', 'v.减少开支；削减花费', '1. Inflation has forced us to retrench. 因通货膨胀我们不得不紧缩开支。', '名词: retrencher 过去式: retrenched 过去分词: retrenched 现在分词: retrenching 第三人称单数: retrenches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hemisphere', '[\'hemɪsfɪr]', 'n.半球', '1. the party out ofoffice 2. If you cut a round fruit into two, each half is a hemisphere. 如果你把一个圆的水果切成两半，每一半就是一个半球。 3. The Northern Hemisphere is the part of the world north of the equator, and the Southern Hemisphere is south of the equator. 北半球是地球赤道以北的部分，南半球是赤道以南的部分。', '形容词: hemispheric 副词: hemispherically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('championship', '[\'tʃæmpiənʃɪp]', 'n.锦标赛；冠军；拥护', '1. How did the team prepare for the team championship? 你们的队伍是怎么准备这次锦标赛的？ 2. Her best moment was her first championship race. 她最棒的那一次比赛是她第一次参加锦标赛。 3. She made her mark by winning a championship. 她获得冠军，一举成名。 4. He gloried in his winning the championship. 他因获得冠军而洋洋得意。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bauble', '[\'bɔːbl]', 'n.小玩意；美观的便宜货；华而不实的小件装饰品；丑角手杖', '1. The shop sells baubles as well. 这家商店也销售廉价珠宝。 2. A bauble is a showy ornament of little value. 廉价珠宝是华而不实的装饰品。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('panegyric', '[ˌpænə\'dʒɪrɪk]', 'n.赞辞；夸大的颂词', '1. He made a speech of panegyric. 他作了一个颂扬性的演讲。 2. That is why that stock option enjoys panegyric when it appeared. 正因为如此，股票期权从一产生就备受推崇。 3. Listen to the panegyric which neighbor makes of neighbor. 听听邻居是怎样恭维邻居的吧。', '形容词: panegyrical 副词: panegyrically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hedonist', '[\'hiːdənɪst]', 'n.快乐主义者；享乐主义者', '1. According to her it\'s bad to have high ideals, but good to be a hedonist! 依她说，怀抱着高尚的理想是坏的，做享乐主义者是好的！ 2. Though he professed to be a socialist and declared \"class war\" on the capitalist system, he heartily enjoyed all that money could buy and squandered several fortunes like a true hedonist. 他自称是社会主义者并宣布向资本主义制度进行“阶级战争”，却迷恋于金钱带来的一切，为了享乐而挥霍了大笔财富。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rendezvous', '[\'rɑːndɪvuː]', 'n.约会；约会地点；汇合点 vi.汇合；集合', '1. He didn\'t recognize the address of the rendezvous. 他没有辨认出约会的地点。 2. She made the rendezvous with only minutes to spare. 她还差几分钟时才来赴约。 3. He didn\'t tell me the rendezvous. 他没有告诉我约会时间与地点。 4. The cafe is a popular rendezvous for young lovers. 这个咖啡馆是年轻恋人的约会圣地。 5. They will rendezvous in the park. 他们将在公园会合。', '名词复数: rendezvous 过去式: rendezvoused 过去分词: rendezvoused 现在分词: rendezvousing 第三人称单数: rendezvous');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('plank', '[plæŋk]', 'n.厚板；支撑物；政纲条目 vt.铺板；用力放下；<口>立即付钱', '1. The deck of the sailing ship was made of thick planks. 这艘帆船的甲板是用厚木板制作的。 2. He has planed the plank smooth. 他已把木板刨平。 3. The plank was resting on a trestle on the landing. 支架在降落的时候会支撑在一个架柱上。 4. The party\'s main plank is reducing taxes. 该党政纲的基点是减税。 5. He planked the well over. 他用木板把井盖上。', '过去式: planked 过去分词: planked 现在分词: planking 第三人称单数: planks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('outmoded', '[ˌaʊt\'moʊdɪd]', 'adj.过时的 动词outmode的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. He still hugs his outmoded beliefs. 他还死守着他那些过了时的信条。 2. His political philosophy tends to be written off as an outmoded fantasy. 他的政治观点往往被认为是不合时宜的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('peeve', '[piːv]', 'v.气恼；怨恨', '1. The iniquities of the unions are her pet peeve at the moment. 此时协会中的歪风邪气是令她最气恼的事。', '过去式: peeved 过去分词: peeved 现在分词: peeving 第三人称单数: peeves');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('aspirant', '[ə\'spaɪərənt]', 'n.怀抱大志者；野心家 adj.有抱负的；有野心的', '1. The aspirant should meditate on Him. 求道者应该对他进行冥想。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('animated', '[\'ænɪmeɪtɪd]', 'adj.生气勃勃的；栩栩如生的；动画片的', '1. Amongst the objects in the scene, they soon discovered an animated one. 她们很快在这些景物中发现了一个生气勃勃的目标。 2. Your colorful teeth and tongue may be calling attention to the vivid and colorful stories you tell and the animated way you express yourself. 你的鲜艳的牙齿和舌头可能是提醒大家注意你说的栩栩如生的故事以及你生动的表达自我的方式。 3. At Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute, architectural students move around in an animated image of the Parthenon, examining that noble structure\'s roof and columns. 在伦塞勒工业学院，建筑专业的学生们围着一个栩栩如生的巴台农神庙图像转圈子，仔细研究那宏伟建筑的屋顶和圆柱。 4. The art or process of preparing animated cartoons. 摄制动画片的制作艺术或过程。', '副词: animatedly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('roundabout', '[\'raʊndəbaʊt]', 'adj.绕道的；迂回的 n.环形交叉路口 n.(英)旋转木马 n.紧身短上衣', '1. We drove home by a roundabout route. 我们绕远道驾车回家。 2. The taxi didn\'t go by the direct route, but in a roundabout way. 出租车没有走直路，而是绕道行驶。 3. She suggested it in a very roundabout way. 她很婉转地提出了这个建议。 4. I entered the village by the little roundabout lane. 我由一条迂回曲折的小径进了村。 5. Turn left at the next roundabout. 在下一个环形交叉路口向左转。 6. The kids were pushing the roundabout at a giddy speed. 孩子们推动着旋转平台快得令人眩晕。 7. There was a slight noise behind her and she turned just in time to seize a small boy by the slack of his roundabout and arrest his flight. 这时在她身后传来一声轻微的响声，她转身一把抓住了一个小男孩的短外套的衣角，他想跑都跑不掉了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('proposal', '[prə\'poʊzl]', 'n.求婚；建议；提议', '1. She had had many proposals but preferred to remain single. 许多人向她求过婚, 但她愿过独身生活。 2. The manager made a proposal for uniting the two companies. 经理提出了将两家公司联合起来的建议。 3. Various proposals were put forward by the employees for increasing sales. 员工们摆出了各种提高销售额的提议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('turret', '[\'tɜːrət]', 'n.小塔；角楼；（攻城用）塔车；镜头转台', '1. This ancient turret has attracted many visitors. 这座古老的塔楼吸引了很多游客。 2. A fortress often has turrets. 堡垒往往带有塔楼。 3. Drop a grenade when a turret opens, but beware of bullets being fired at you. 当角楼打开的时候，扔出手榴弹，一定要注意躲避射向你的子弹。 4. The soldier scaled the wall of the fortress by turret. 士兵通过塔车攀登上了要塞的城墙。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ravishing', '[\'rævɪʃɪŋ]', 'adj.令人陶醉的 动词ravish的现在分词形式.', '1. The race is so ravishing, and the Olympics is so charming, 比赛如此引人入胜，奥运如此富有魅力， 2. Besides the ravishing moving pictures, the dialogs in the films hold the same balance. 除了电影引人入胜的画面外，影片中人物之间的对白也占有举足轻重的地位。', '副词: ravishingly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ulterior', '[ʌl\'tɪriər]', 'adj.隐秘的；别有用心的；将来的；进一步的；遥远的', '1. This lever must serve some ulterior purpose. 这撬棒准是用于不可告人的目的的。 2. There was no ulterior motive in his proposal. 他的建议里没有不可告人的动机。 3. I want to know what is our ulterior action. 我想要知道下一步的行动是什么。', '副词: ulteriorly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reverie', '[\'revəri]', 'n.幻想；白日梦 =revery.', '1. He was lost in reverie. 他深深陷入幻想。 2. She fell into a reverie about her childhood. 她沉浸在对童年往事的遐想中。 3. He is indulging in reveries about the future. 他正沉浸于对未来的幻想之中。 4. He drifted off into reverie again. 他迷迷糊糊的又陶醉在自己的白日梦中了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dutiful', '[\'duːtɪfl]', 'adj.顺从的；尽职的；责任感强的', '1. I hope you\'ll be a dutiful daughter-in-law. 我希望你做个孝顺的儿媳妇。 2. Bertha would eventually become the dutiful and submissive spouse. 伯莎最终会成为那种本分驯良的妻子。 3. The eldest was an extraordinary sailor -- brave, dutiful, tough and adventurous. 大儿子是一个非凡的水手：坚强、勇敢、尽职，而且富于冒险精神。 4. They are hard working and dutiful. 他们很努力工作，富有责任感。', '副词: dutifully 名词: dutifulness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('offbeat', '[ˌɔːf\'biːt]', 'adj.不平常的；离奇的；反传统的 n.弱拍', '1. His style is offbeat but highly creative. 他的风格很不寻常但非常有创造力。 2. I like his offbeat sense of humor. 我喜欢他与众不同的幽默感。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('doodle', '[\'duːdl]', 'v.乱写；乱画；信手涂鸦 n.乱写；乱画 Doodle n.谷歌涂鸦（搜索引擎谷歌Google于节日和其他纪念日在主页上展示的定制版谷歌图标）', '1. Brad was doodling on a sheet of paper. 布拉德在一张纸上乱写。 2. Stop doodling on my notebook! 别在我的笔记本上乱画！', '过去式: doodled 过去分词: doodled 现在分词: doodling 第三人称单数: doodles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('condor', '[\'kɑːndɔːr]', 'n.大兀鹰；秃鹰金币', '1. The condor soars above the mountain heights. 禿鹰翱翔于高山之上。 2. A very large bird - they call it a condor - was circling in the sky. 一只很大的鸟，他们管它叫神鹰，正在天空盘旋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('differentiate', '[ˌdɪfə\'renʃieɪt]', 'vt.区分；使差异；求导数 vi.区别；产生差别；区别对待', '1. Can you differentiate one variety from the other? 你能将这两个品种区别开来吗? 2. He cannot differentiate the two flowers. 他无法辨认这两种花。 3. The only way to differentiate yourself from the competition is through service. 只有服务才能真正使你在竞争中凸显。 4. I cannot differentiate between these two things. 我无法区别这两个东西。', '名词: differentiation 过去式: differentiated 过去分词: differentiated 现在分词: differentiating 第三人称单数: differentiates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('audit', '[\'ɔːdɪt]', 'n.审计；查帐 vt.旁听；审计', '1. As usual, the yearly audit will take place in December. 跟往常一样，年度审计将在十二月份进行。 2. They work non-stop to finish the audit on time. 他们不停地工作以按期完成审计工作。 3. He had read the audit chief\'s report about the embezzlement and cash loss. 他已读过查帐部主任关于这件贪污加现款盗窃案的报告。 4. But everyone was there, helping to examine the bank\'s records for the special audit Mr. Bell was taking. 但是每个人都在那儿，帮助检查银行的记录，因为贝尔先生正在进行特别查帐。 5. Which course do you want to audit? 你想旁听哪门课?', '过去式: audited 过去分词: audited 现在分词: auditing 第三人称单数: audits');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('loath', '[loʊθ]', 'adj.不愿意的；勉强的 =loathe；loth.', '1. I loath to go with him. 我不愿和他一起去。 2. She seemed somewhat loath to depart. 她似乎不愿意离开。 3. He is loath to get out of bed on cold morning. 在寒冷的早晨他讨厌起床。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('conflate', '[kən\'fleɪt]', 'v.合并；异文合并', '1. The results of the two experiments were conflated. 这两项实验的结果合并在一起了。 2. Can these two definitions be conflated, or must they be kept separate? 这两个定义可以合成一个呢，还是必须分开?', '名词: conflation 过去式: conflated 过去分词: conflated 现在分词: conflating 第三人称单数: conflates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('thrall', '[θrɔːl]', 'n.奴隶；束缚 v.<古>奴役；束缚', '1. He treats his wife like a thrall. 他把妻子当作奴隶看待。 2. Do you take me as your thrall? 你以为我是你的奴隶吗？ 3. Not his ascendency alone, however, held me in thrall at present. 目前束缚着我们，并不只是他的支配地位。', '名词: thralldom 过去式: thralled 过去分词: thralled 现在分词: thralling 第三人称单数: thralls');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('predator', '[\'predətər]', 'n.食肉动物；掠夺者；（动物的）捕食性天敌', '1. Young birds are very vulnerable to predators. 幼小的鸟易受食肉动物伤害。 2. The polar bear is the biggest land predator of them all. 顾名思义，北极熊的出产地为北极，是世界上体积最巨型的陆上食肉动物。 3. To Romanians, Russia is a predator. 而对罗马尼亚人而言，俄国人则是掠夺者。 4. Lion is a predator in the nature. 狮子是大自然中的掠夺者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('senile', '[\'siːnaɪl]', 'adj.年老的；衰老的；年老所致的', '1. It has a special effect in preventing the skin from being chapped and senile. 它是具有防止皮肤皲裂和衰老的特效。', '副词: senilely');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mare', '[mer]', 'n.母马；母驴；(月球等)表面阴暗处', '1. The mare is sold for 300 dollars. 母马卖了300美元。 2. A mule is a cross between a mare and a donkey. 骡子是母马和公驴的杂交后代。 3. He kept 20 mares for breeding. 他养了二十头母驴用来繁殖。 4. The mare is carrying a foal now. 这匹牝马已怀驹了。', '名词复数: maria');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('elaborate', '[ɪ\'læbəreɪt]', 'adj.详尽的；复杂的；精心的；精美的 v.详细地说明；用心制作；推敲；变得复杂', '1. He launched into an elaborate explanation of his theory. 他开始详尽地阐发他的理论。 2. Her elaborate hairstyle, to her disappointment, just amused us. 令她失望的是,她复杂的发型只让我们感到好笑。 3. It was not the old man to indulge in elaborate preliminaries. 这位老人向来不做那种煞费苦心的开场白。 4. She had prepared herself for a very elaborate show. 她准备了一场非常精美的表演。 5. She went on to elaborate her argument. 她进而详尽阐述了她的论点。', '副词: elaborately 名词: elaborateness 过去式: elaborated 过去分词: elaborated 现在分词: elaborating 第三人称单数: elaborates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fervor', '[ˌfɜːvə]', 'n.热诚；热心 =fervour(英).', '1. He groaned as the need caught him up in its fervor. 热诚的需求俘虏了他，他呻吟着。 2. Now that I look back, those were days with a religious fervor. 回想起来，那些日子还带点宗教似的热诚。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sprout', '[spraʊt]', 'v.长芽；萌芽；迅速成长 n.芽；年幼者', '1. The seeds will sprout in a few days. 这些种子几天后就会发芽。 2. These potatoes have begun to sprout. 这些马铃薯开始发芽了。 3. The seeds sprout into small, hairlike seedings. 种子发育成小小的、毛茸茸的幼苗。 4. He sprouted up six inches a year. 他一年长高了六英寸。 5. In spring, here, drizzle moistens land , also feed rice sprout. 春天，这里细雨蒙蒙，滋润着土地，也哺育着稻苗。', '过去式: sprouted 过去分词: sprouted 现在分词: sprouting 第三人称单数: sprouts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sequela', '[sɪ\'kwiːlə]', 'n.后遗症；继发性的后果', '1. Does laser treat myopia to there is sequela? 激光治疗近视有后遗症吗？ 2. Drink 2 times can gastrorrhagia have sequela? 喝酒二次胃出血会有后遗症吗？', '名词复数: sequelae');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('omnipotent', '[ɑːm\'nɪpətənt]', 'adj.全能的；无所不能的 Omnipotent：上帝.', '1. If I were omnipotent for a day, I want world peace, no more hunger. 如果有一天我变得全能的话，我想要世界和平，没有饥饿。 2. An omniscient and omnipotent God must be above such humanlike constraints. 全知与全能的上帝理当超越人类能力的限制。 3. They are equally omnipotent in their regard as two of themost treasured Lakers in Los Angeles history. 作为洛杉矶历史上最伟大的湖人球员，他们都是无所不能的。 4. One by one, as they march, our comrades vanish from our sight, seized by the silent orders of omnipotent Death. 在行进中我们的同伴一个个消失，被无所不能的死亡悄悄下令攫走了。', '副词: omnipotently 名词: omnipotence');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('forerunner', '[\'fɔːrʌnər]', 'n.先驱；祖先；预兆；[体育]赛前试滑滑道的人', '1. He was the forerunner of the resistance. 他是这个反抗运动的先驱者。 2. She is a forerunner of the modern women\'s movement. 她是现代妇女运动的先驱。 3. Mr. Sun Yat sen is the forerunner of the Chinese revolution. 孙中山先生是中国革命的先驱。 4. Penicillin was the forerunner of modern antibiotics. 青霉素是现代抗生素的先导。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('relieved', '[rɪ\'liːvd]', 'adj.放心的；放松的 动词relieve的过去式和过去分词.', '1. She looked immensely relieved when she heard the news. 她一听到这个消息似乎立刻放心了。 2. They exchanged relieved glances. 他们如释重负地彼此看了看。 3. She had a relieved look on her face. 她脸上现出宽慰的表情。 4. The thief relieved him of his wallet. 那小偷把他的钱包偷走了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('capitalize', '[\'kæpɪtəlaɪz]', 'vt.以大写字母写；使 ... 资本化；估价 vi.利用', '1. Don\'t forget to capitalize the first letter in the sentence. 不要忘记把句子中首词的第一个字母大写。 2. Please capitalize the report. 请用大写字母写这份报告。 3. He has decided to capitalize all his property . 他决定把全部财产变为资本。 4. Everyone should capitalize on his opportunity. 每个人都应当利用机会。', '形容词: capitalizable 过去式: capitalized 过去分词: capitalized 现在分词: capitalizing 第三人称单数: capitalizes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('paucity', '[\'pɔːsəti]', 'n.少数；少量', '1. The paucity of fruit was caused by the drought. 水果缺乏是由于干旱造成的。 2. The results are often unsatisfactory because of the paucity of cells. 因细胞稀少，结果常令人不满意。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('adobe', '[ə\'doʊbi]', 'n.泥砖；土坯；泥砖建筑物；制砖粘土 Adobe. n.美国奥多比电脑软件公司', '1. The villagers built their houses with adobe. 村民们用晒乾的泥砖造房子。 2. This way the adobe can be shaped into bricks of the desired size. 用这种方法，泥砖土就能被塑成所需尺寸的砖。 3. But people who work with adobe must experiment. 但是从事土坯工作的人必须做试验。 4. Adobe is soil that contains at least forty percent clay. 土坯是包含至少百分之四十粘土的土壤。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tinker', '[\'tɪŋkər]', 'n.修补匠；焊锅 vi.做焊锅匠；笨拙地修补 vt.修补；调整；改进', '1. Sure enough, he saw the tinker walking toward him. 果然，他看到小炉匠向他走过来。 2. He likes tinkering with computers. 他喜爱乱改进计算机。 3. He\'s been tinkering with that engine for hours, but it still won\'t go. 他花了几个小时摆弄那个引擎,想修好它,但它还是不转。 4. Other scientists tinker with Darwin by borrowing a page from the creationists\'book. 其他科学家借上帝创造宇宙论者们书中的片言只语来修补达尔文的理论。', '过去式: tinkered 过去分词: tinkered 现在分词: tinkering 第三人称单数: tinkers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('elite', '[eɪ\'liːt]', 'n.精英 adj.精英的；优秀的', '1. The elite are the competitive focus of 21 century. 精英人才是21世纪国际间竞争的焦点。 2. It is a luxury brand established for the elite and the affluent. 这是一个为精英群体和富人所创设的奢侈品牌。 3. It is indubitable that he is an elite in information technology. 毫无疑问，他是信息技术界的精英。 4. Public opinion is influenced by the small elite who control the media. 舆论为少数控制着新闻媒介的上层人士所左右。 5. This is an elite group reserved for members only. 这是仅为会员保留的精英小组。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('slaver', '[\'slævər]', 'n.口水；胡言乱语；贩奴人(船) v.垂涎；淌口水；恭维奉承', '1. Today\'s slaver will drain into tomorrow\'s tear. 现在流的是哈喇子，将成为明天的眼泪。 2. The dealer was slavering over some precious stones. 那商人对一些宝石垂涎欲滴。 3. He slavered during the nap. 午睡时，他流口水了。', '过去式: slavered 过去分词: slavered 现在分词: slavering 第三人称单数: slavers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('roughen', '[\'rʌfn]', 'v.弄粗弄崎岖不平', '1. Roughen the surface before applying the paint. 先把表面弄毛糙再涂颜料。', '过去式: roughened 过去分词: roughened 现在分词: roughening 第三人称单数: roughens');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cache', '[kæʃ]', 'n.隐藏所；藏身处；【计】高速缓冲存储器；缓存 v.把……藏起来；【计】把……储存于超高速缓冲存储器', '1. One of the patrols discovered an arms cache. 巡逻队中有一人发现了一批武器的藏匿之处。 2. The bar silver is in the north cache, you can find it by the trend of the east hummock, ten fathoms south of the black crag with the face on it. 银条在北面秘窖,可顺着东边圆丘的斜坡,在黑岩石以南十寻处找到。 3. Philippines police have arrested more than 60 people and found a major arms and ammunition cache, in raids after a poll-related massacre in the south. 菲律宾警方在南部政治大屠杀之后进行突击搜捕，逮捕60多人、发现了一个大型武器弹药隐藏处。 4. The data needed is found in the cache. 在高速缓冲存储器中找到所需数据。 5. He cached his toys under his bed. 他把他的玩具藏在床下。', '过去式: cached 过去分词: cached 现在分词: caching 第三人称单数: caches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gustation', '[gʌs\'teɪʃən]', 'n.品尝；味觉', '1. Through Jia Bao-Yu\'s olfaction and gustation, his spiritual love and facultative desire was emphasized. 通过贾宝玉的嗅觉与味觉，进入他的深层意识与美感触觉，突显他的精神恋爱与官能欲望。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('limn', '[lɪm]', 'v.描写；描绘', '1. \"I always have the impulsiveness to limn the whole world. 我总有一种冲动，想要描述整个世界。\" 2. To limn their portraits, stately, beautiful, and emulate at will, 绘出他们描绘的图景，宏伟，美丽，随意地模仿 3. Electrochemical Performance of Surface Modified LiMn 表面处理对LiMn电化学性能的影响 4. Keywords LiMn 2O 4;oxygen atmosphere;kinetics;synthesis; 锰酸锂;氧气气氛;合成动力学;', '名词: limner 过去式: limned 过去分词: limned 现在分词: limning 第三人称单数: limns');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('circuit', '[\'sɜːrkɪt]', 'n.巡回；线路；环形；电路；回路 v.巡回；绕 ... 环形', '1. For many years he was top banana on the circuit. 几年来,他是巡回剧团里的主角。 2. The commanding officer made a circuit of the camp. 指挥官在营地巡视一周。 3. Complete minor repairs to circuit wiring. 完成线路小修。 4. The circuit is a conventional ring counter. 此线路是一个普通的环形计数器。 5. I hit the lunch-and-lecture circuit again. 我又去参加那些巡回午餐演讲了。', '过去式: circuited 过去分词: circuited 现在分词: circuiting 第三人称单数: circuits');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('finagle', '[fɪ\'neɪɡl]', 'v.欺骗；哄骗；欺瞒', '1. Shady stockbrokers who finagle their clients out of fortunes. 把客户的钱都骗光的可疑的证券经纪人 2. He is a master of finagle and accommoda-tion; he is purposeful and principled. 他诡诈，善于适应环境，并果断，有原则性。 3. He is a master of finagle and accommodation; he is purposeful and principled. 他诡诈,善于适应环境,并果断,有原则性。 4. I guess because of that my coach could finagle tickets to go see games, especially the doubleheaders. 我猜想由于我的教练能够弄到球票去看比赛，特别是很靠前排的座位。', '名词: finagler 过去式: finagled 过去分词: finagled 现在分词: finagling 第三人称单数: finagles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sting', '[stɪŋ]', 'vt.刺痛；使苦恼；欺诈 vi.叮；刺痛 n.刺；刺痛；讽刺', '1. Her ingratitude stung him. 她的忘恩负义使他痛心。 2. The smoke began to sting his eyes. 烟开始刺痛他的眼睛。 3. Those harsh words stung me bitterly. 那些严厉的言辞使我感到非常痛苦 4. They used to sting their clients. 他们过去常诈骗客户。 5. It is the nature of the scorpion to sting . 蝎子生下来就会蛰人。 6. A bee pricks the skin with its sting. 蜜蜂用螫针刺皮肤。', '副词: stingingly 过去式: stung 过去分词: stung 现在分词: stinging 第三人称单数: stings');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('arson', '[\'ɑːrsn]', 'n.纵火；纵火罪', '1. This fire was no doubt caused by arson. 这场火灾无疑是由纵火引起的。 2. Arson has been ruled out ecause artificial fire. 失火原因已排除人为纵火。 3. He was brought to trial on charges of arson. 他以纵火罪被送法院审理。 4. The jury convicted the accused man of theft and arson. 陪审团判决被告犯有偷窃和纵火罪。', '名词: arsonist');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hybrid', '[\'haɪbrɪd]', 'n.混合物；杂种；混血儿 adj.杂种的；混合的', '1. The music was a hybrid of western pop and traditional folk song. 这种音乐融合了西方流行音乐和传统民歌。 2. A mule is a hybrid of a donkey and a horse. 骡子是公驴和母马交配而生的杂种。 3. She is a hybrid of the African and the Chinese. 她是中非混血儿。 4. He is interested in hybrid animals. 他对杂交产生的动物感兴趣。', '名词: hybridism');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('thespian', '[\'θespiən]', 'adj.悲剧的；戏剧的；(古希腊诗人)狄斯比斯的 n.演员；悲剧演员', '1. The actress demonstrated thespian talents at her first audition. 这位女演员第一次试镜就展现出戏剧天分。 2. The thespian players think that the theater is thoroughly thrilling. 戏剧演员认为剧场是最令人兴奋的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('landslide', '[\'lændslaɪd]', 'n.山崩；滑坡；占绝对优势的选举', '1. The heavy rain was responsible for the landslide. 山崩应归于下大雨。 2. A landslide has blocked off traffic moving south towards the motorway. 山崩阻碍了高速公路上向南方行驶的车辆。 3. The landslide earthed up the pool where the animals usually drank. 滑坡填塞了动物通常来饮水的这个水坑。 4. Opinion polls forecast a Conservative landslide. 民意测验预示保守党有获得压倒性多数票的可能。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('repartee', '[ˌrepɑːr\'tiː]', 'n.机灵的回答；妙语如珠的对话', '1. Violence is the repartee of the illiterate. 暴力是文盲常采用的巧妙应答。 2. This diplomat possessed an excellent gift for repartee. 这位外交官具有卓越的应对才能。 3. I enjoy listening to their witty repartee. 我很喜欢听他们妙语连珠的对答。 4. The repartee flies back and forth across the dinner table. 宴会上妙语连珠对答如流。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('expel', '[ɪk\'spel]', 'vt.驱逐；开除；排出', '1. Russia has lately decided to expel a US diplomat from its land, . 俄国最近驱逐了一名美国外交官。 2. He was expelled from the school. 他被学校开除了。 3. The headmaster decided to make an example of the pupil and expel him from the school. 校长决定开除该生以儆效尤。 4. The lungs expel carbon dioxide when we exhale. 当我们呼气时,肺所排出来的是二氧化碳。', '形容词: expellable 名词: expeller 过去式: expelled 过去分词: expelled 现在分词: expelling 第三人称单数: expels');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scratch', '[skrætʃ]', 'v.抓；搔（痒）；划破；划掉 n.抓痕；乱写；抓的声音；起跑线 adj.无让步的', '1. The dog is scratching at the door. 狗正在抓门。 2. He pretended to scratch his ear. 他假装搔耳朵。 3. I had to scratch my head to remember his name. 我只想苦苦地回忆他的名字。 4. Be careful not to scratch the furniture. 小心别刮坏家具。 5. There\'s a scratch on the side of my car. 我的汽车侧面有一道划痕。', '名词: scratcher 过去式: scratched 过去分词: scratched 现在分词: scratching 第三人称单数: scratches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ridicule', '[\'rɪdɪkjuːl]', 'n.嘲笑；愚弄；笑柄 v.嘲笑；愚弄', '1. To choose such a line of work is to invite ridicule. 选择从事这个行业会惹人嘲笑。 2. Her conduct subjected her to public ridicule. 她的行为使她受众人嘲笑。 3. He is the object of ridicule among his classmates. 他常常是班里同学愚弄的对象。 4. His conduct subjected him to public ridicule. 他的行为使他成为公众的笑柄。 5. He had become inured to ridicule. 他已受惯了他人的讥笑。', '名词: ridiculer 过去式: ridiculed 过去分词: ridiculed 现在分词: ridiculing 第三人称单数: ridicules');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tripod', '[\'traɪpɑːd]', 'n.(摄影机的)三脚架；三脚用具；三足鼎', '1. Please seat the camera on the tripod. 请把相机放在三脚架上。 2. It\'ll stay stable with a tripod. 有三角架就稳了。 3. This bronze tripod used to be a symbol of emperorship. 这个铜鼎曾经是代表国家政权的神器。', '形容词: tripodal');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pell-mell', '[ˌpel\'mel]', 'adv.乱七八糟地；混乱地 adj.杂乱的；混乱的 n.乱七八糟；混乱；杂乱', '1. The books were scattered pell-mell over the floor. 书本凌乱地散置在地上。 2. The children rushed pell-mell down the stairs. 孩子们乱哄哄地冲下楼去。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('irksome', '[\'ɜːrksəm]', 'adj.厌恶的；讨厌的；令人厌烦的', '1. She always speaks irksome complaints. 她总是发出令人厌烦的牢骚。 2. It is irksome to do the same work every day for ten years. 十年来每天都做同样的工作令人厌烦。', '副词: irksomely 名词: irk-someness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lionize', '[\'laɪənaɪz]', 'vt.崇拜；看重 =lionise(英).', '1. Marilyn wanted to be loved, not lionized. 玛里琳要的是爱而不是崇拜。', '名词: lionization 过去式: lionized 过去分词: lionized 现在分词: lionizing 第三人称单数: lionizes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('avuncular', '[ə\'vʌŋkjələr]', 'adj.叔伯的；（尤指举止态度）像叔伯的；与叔、伯、舅有关的', '1. He was now playing the role of disinterested host and avuncular mentor. 他现在正扮演着慷慨的主人和伯父似的指导人的角色。 2. He adopts an avuncular tone of voice when giving advice to junior colleagues. 他用长辈的口气劝告年轻的同事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('limber', '[\'lɪmbər]', 'adj.柔软的；灵活的 v.使变柔软；做准备活动 n.前车；污水道', '1. Gymnasts do everyday exercises to keep themselves limber. 体操运动员每天都做运动保持身体柔软。 2. Before running, he liked to limber up. 在跑步前，他喜欢先热身以使身体柔软灵活。 3. I always do a few easy exercises to limber up before a match. 我在比赛前总要做些简单的准备活动。 4. The commander ordered the troops to limber up and move out. 指挥官下令把炮装上牵引车开出去。 5. However in this case it means there is no room for a team, limber or caisson. 但是这样就没有足够空间加上炮组，前车以及弹药箱了。', '副词: limberly 名词: limberness 过去式: limbered 过去分词: limbered 现在分词: limbering 第三人称单数: limbers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('servile', '[\'sɜːrvl]', 'adj.屈从的；奴隶的；不自由的', '1. He was made to do servile tasks. 他被迫做奴隶的工作。', '副词: servilely 名词: servileness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nonplus', '[ˌnɒn\'plʌs]', 'vt.使困惑；使为难 n.迷惑；困惑；僵局', '1. The professor is never at a nonplus,and never perplexed by a problem. 那位教授从来不会感到困惑，也不会被任何问题所难倒。', '过去式: nonplused/nonplussed 过去分词: nonplused/nonplussed 现在分词: nonplusing/nonplussing 第三人称单数: nonpluses/nonplusses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sequester', '[sɪ\'kwestər]', 'vt. 使 ... 隔绝； 隐退 vt. 扣押', '1. The retired film star sequestered herself from the world. 这位退休的影星过着隐居的生活。', '过去式: sequestered 过去分词: sequestered 现在分词: sequestering 第三人称单数: sequesters');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('feckless', '[\'fekləs]', 'adj.软弱的；无用的；不负责任的', '1. Her husband was a charming, but lazy and feckless man. 她的丈夫讨人喜欢，但却是个懒惰没有出息的人。 2. And Washington is annoyed at Europe\'s feckless attempts at economic reforms. 美国方面对欧盟不痛不痒的经济改革也懊恼不已。', '副词: fecklessly 名词: fecklessness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('microbe', '[\'maɪkroʊb]', 'n.微生物；细菌', '1. The probe is sensitive enough to detect the presence of a single microbe. 这个探针的灵敏度很高，足以测出任何微生物的存在。 2. Being small may also have helped the microbe absorb nutrients more efficiently. 体积微小同样可以帮助微生物更加有效地吸收养分。 3. A quiet meteorologist first noticed the microbe menace. 一位沉默寡言的气象学家首先注意到了细菌威胁。', '形容词: microbial');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('diabolical', '[ˌdaɪə\'bɑːlɪkl]', 'adj.恶魔的；糟糕的；残忍的', '1. This manoeuvre of his is a diabolical conspiracy. 他这一手是个居心叵测的大阴谋。 2. The traffic was diabolical in Beijing. 北京的交通很糟糕。', '副词: diabolically 异体字: diabolic 名词: diabolicalness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('poltroon', '[pɑːl\'truːn]', 'n.胆怯者；懦夫 adj.胆怯的', '1. No one likes to be regarded as a poltroon. 没有人喜欢被认为是懦夫。', '名词: poltroonery');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('preliminary', '[prɪ\'lɪmɪneri]', 'adj.初步的；预备的；开始的 n.初步行动；准备；初步措施', '1. They have made a preliminary investigation. 他们已经做了初步的调查。 2. Our team got beaten in the preliminary rounds of the competition. 我们队在这次比赛的预赛中遭淘汰。 3. Movies at the preliminary stage were silent. 电影在初期是无声的。 4. There are a lot of preliminaries to be gone through before you can visit a foreign country. 在出访外国之前要做好许多准备工作。', '副词: preliminarily 名词复数: preliminaries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('induce', '[ɪn\'duːs]', 'vt.引起；促使；劝服；引诱', '1. The medicine will induce sleep. 这种药会引起睡意。 2. They hoped their work would induce social changes. 他们希望自己的工作可以引起社会上的某些变化。 3. I can\'t think what induced her to marry him. 我想不出到底是什么原因促使她嫁给他。 4. Alcohol can induce a loosening of the tongue. 酒精可使人信口开河。', '形容词: inducible 过去式: induced 过去分词: induced 现在分词: inducing 第三人称单数: induces');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('autonomy', '[ɔː\'tɑːnəmi]', 'n.自治；自治权；自主', '1. The separatist is demanding full autonomy for their state. 分裂主义者在要求他们的州完全自治。 2. They are agitating to assert autonomy. 他们正在鼓吹实行自治。 3. The central government granted autonomy to a national minority. 中央政府对少数民族授予自治权。 4. County boroughs lose their autonomy. 自治郡失去了它们的自治权。', '名词: autonomist 名词复数: autonomies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('release', '[rɪ\'liːs]', 'n.释放；让渡；发行 vt.释放；让与；准予发表；发射', '1. The prisoner was questioned before his release. 囚犯被释放之前受到了审问。 2. The puffball is ready to release its spores. 尘菌已经要释放孢子了。 3. The electrons in the upper band eventually release energy, thereby emitting photons. 上层能带中的电子最后会发射光子释放能量。', '过去式: released 过去分词: released 现在分词: releasing 第三人称单数: releases');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('terrain', '[tə\'reɪn]', 'n.地带；地形', '1. The car blitzed through rough terrain. 这辆汽车长驱穿越了崎岖地带。 2. Valley glaciers are confined to valleys in mountainous terrain. 山谷冰川只限于多山地带的山谷。 3. It\'s a difficult terrain for tanks. 这是坦克作战的困难地形。 4. They stopped and began to reconnoitre the terrain. 他们停下来，开始勘测地形。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('transcend', '[træn\'send]', 'v.超越；胜过', '1. Humans should always transcend their limits. 人类应该不断超越自己的极限。 2. We can\'t transcend the limitations of the ego. 我们无法超越自我的局限性。 3. They transcend national borders and generations. 它们超越国界及世代。 4. The song of the future must transcend creed. 赞美未来的颂歌一定要胜过这类教条。', '过去式: transcended 过去分词: transcended 现在分词: transcending 第三人称单数: transcends');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('conference', '[\'kɒnfərəns]', 'n.会议；讨论会；协商会；会谈', '1. He is in conference. 他正在开会。 2. An international conference will be held in Beijing next month. 一个国际性的会议下月将在北京举行。 3. There will be a banquet following the conference. 会议过后将有一个宴会。 4. We are all fully confident that the conference will be a great success. 我们都有充分的信心,这次会议将会非常成功。', '形容词: conferential');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nice', '[naɪs]', 'adj.好的；美妙的；友好的；令人愉快的；精细的', '1. It\'s a nice day today. 今天天气很好。 2. How nice of you to do that! 你那样做真是太好了！ 3. I brought her a very nice present from Soochow. 我从苏州给她带来一件美妙的礼物。 4. People there are very nice to tourists and foreigners. 那儿的人们对待旅行者和外国人都非常友好。', '副词: nicely 比较级: nicer 最高级: nicest 名词: niceness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tariff', '[\'tærɪf]', 'n.关税；价目表 vt.交关税', '1. Tariff barriers crimped the flow of imports. 关税障碍妨碍了进囗货的流入。 2. The government decided to impose a protective tariff on foreign cars. 政府决定对进口汽车征收保护税。 3. A copy of tariff is placed in each room of the hotel. 旅馆的每一个房间都有一份价目表。', '过去式: tariffed 过去分词: tariffed 现在分词: tariffing 第三人称单数: tariffs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('topsy-turvy', '[ˌtɑːpsi\'tɜːrvi]', 'adv.颠倒地；乱七八糟地 adj.颠倒的 n.颠倒(=topsy-turviness)', '1. This sudden development turned all our plans topsy-turvy. 这一情况出现得很突然，把我们的计划全都打乱了。 2. Burglars had turned the house topsy-turvy. 窃贼把房子翻得乱七八糟。 3. He holds the book topsy-turvy. 他把书拿倒了。', '副词: topsy-turvily 比较级: topsy-turvier 最高级: topsy-turviest 名词: topsy-turviness 名词复数: topsy-turvies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fraternity', '[frə\'tɜːrnəti]', 'n.兄弟般的感情；手足之情；友爱；同人；兄弟会', '1. There is a strong spirit of fraternity among these isolated people. 这些与世隔绝的人之间有强烈的兄弟般的情谊。 2. There is deep fraternity between the brothers. 他们兄弟之间有着浓厚的手足之情。 3. America is well-known for its equality, liberty and fraternity. 美国因它的平等、自由、友爱而闻名于世。 4. He\'s a member of the medical fraternity. 他是医务界的一员。', '名词复数: fraternities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tangle', '[\'tæŋɡl]', 'n.缠结；混乱；纠纷 vt.使缠结；使混乱；使陷入 vi.纠缠；乱作一团；<口>吵架；争论', '1. The wool got in a fearful tangle. 毛线乱成了一团。 2. His financial affairs are in such a tangle. 他的钱财是糊涂帐。 3. We employed a lawyer to straighten our legal tangle. 我们雇了一位律师把法律纠纷理出头绪。 4. The little girl tangled the yarn her mother was knitting. 小女孩把她妈妈在编结的毛线弄得纠结在一起了。 5. He was really a tough guy to tangle with. 他真是一个难缠的人。', '形容词: tangly 过去式: tangled 过去分词: tangled 现在分词: tangling 第三人称单数: tangles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('coy', '[kɔɪ]', 'adj.腼腆的；怕羞的；羞怯的 v.<古>态度娇羞', '1. Please don\'t be so coy. 请不要那么腼腆。 2. She is coy about her love affairs. 她对于她的恋爱情事很腼腆。 3. Women are coy and play hard to get . 女人生性害羞，且爱故作矜持。 4. Don\'t be so coy, and I know you\'d like to do the job. 不要这样忸怩作态,我知道你真的喜欢这份工作。', '副词: coyly 比较级: coyer 最高级: coyest 名词: coyness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('manifestation', '[ˌmænɪfe\'steɪʃn]', 'n.表现；示威运动；显灵', '1. She noticed this slight hint of manifestation of the colour bar. 她注意到了这个微小的种族歧视的表现。 2. This riot is only one manifestation of people\'s discontent. 这骚乱仅仅是人们不满的一种表露而已。 3. That manifestation showed our power. 那次示威运动显示了我们的力量。 4. She claimed to have seen manifestation of dead people in the haunt house. 她说她在那闹鬼的房子里看见了死人显灵。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vicissitude', '[vɪ\'sɪsɪtuːd]', 'n.变化；变迁；兴败；盛衰 n.[古诗]代谢；交替；沉浮', '1. It reflects the vicissitude of society. 它反映了社会的变迁兴衰。 2. What vicissitude and symbolic meaning do such beautiful and unique trappings bear? 这种俏丽别致的服饰，承载着怎样大历史变迁和寓意象征？ 3. Idiosyncrasy and vicissitude had combined to stamp Sergeant Troy as an exceptional being. 个人的特性和身世的沉浮都表明特罗依中士是一个非同寻常的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unidimensional', '[ˌjuːnɪdaɪ\'menʃənəl]', 'adj.线性的；一维的；一度空间的', '1. From Unidimensional Control to Differentiated Coordination. 从线性控制到使有差异的协调。 2. Proposes pictureencryption algorithm based on the double unidimensional chaos system. 摘要 提出了一个基于双一维混沌系统的图像加密算法。 3. Gold does dance to its own tune, and it\'s not a unidimensional story of just the strength or weakness of the dollar. 黄金以自己的旋律波动，而且不再是美元强弱的一维故事了。 4. This article adopts unidimensional optimization method to optimize the design, and optimum parameter can be attained. 本文采用一维寻优的方法,对条筒尺寸进行优化设计,确定其最佳工艺参数。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('centripetal', '[sen\'trɪpɪtl]', 'adj.向心的', '1. It is called the centripetal acceleration. 这叫做向心加速度。 2. The structure of A Rose for Emily is centripetal. 福克纳的《献给艾米莉的玫瑰》的艺术结构是向心式的 ; 3. The centripetal effects of a homogeneous population. 同类人种倾向集中的作用 4. The comparison shows the centripetal tendency of the complements. 比较之后，可以看出补语演变过程中的向心趋势。', '副词: centripetally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wrinkle', '[\'rɪŋkl]', 'n.皱纹；方法 vt.使起皱纹；皱着 vi.起皱', '1. She\'s beginning to get wrinkles round her eyes. 她的眼角开始有皱纹了。 2. My findings add a new wrinkle to each scenario. 我的发现为两种说法都提供了一点想法。 3. Too much sunbathing will wrinkle your skin. 皮肤晒得过分就能起皱纹。 4. He wrinkled up his forehead in perplexity. 他困惑地皱起了眉头。 5. The apples are beginning to wrinkle. 这些苹果开始起皱纹了。', '形容词: wrinkly 过去式: wrinkled 过去分词: wrinkled 现在分词: wrinkling 第三人称单数: wrinkles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('v.', '[viː]', 'abbr.动词(=verb) abbr.伏特(=volt)', '1. His legs sprawl out in V while he was watching TV. 他看电视时双腿呈V字形伸开。 2. You are the best girl I\'v meet here. 你是我在网上遇到的最好的女孩。 3. Let u and v be nonconsecutive vertices on c. 设u和v是c上不相邻的两个顶点。 4. The plot/graph of I versus V is a straight line. I随V的变化曲线是一条直线', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('discernible', '[dɪ\'sɜːrnəbəl]', 'adj.可辨别的', '1. His face was barely discernible in the gloom. 在黑暗中很难看得清他的脸。 2. Recurring themes are readily discernible in the annals of history . 在历史纪录上完全可以找到重复的主题。', '副词: discernibly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('choreography', '[ˌkɔːri\'ɑːɡrəfi]', 'n.编舞艺术；舞蹈编排', '1. His style of choreography is flamboyant. 他的舞蹈设计风格是复杂夸张的。 2. The choreography respects the subject-matter. 舞蹈设计应顾及舞蹈的主题。 3. Today, choreography is an essential component of many performing arts. 当今,舞蹈编排已成为诸多表演艺术的重要组成部分。', '形容词: choreographic 副词: choreographically 名词复数: choreographies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('compliment', '[\'kɑːmplɪmənt]', 'n.称赞；恭维；(复数)致意 vt.恭维；称赞', '1. I was embarrassed by their compliment. 对他们的称赞我感到很不安。 2. I feel greatly flattered at your compliment. 我对你的称赞感到受宠若惊。 3. They paid him a high compliment. 他们非常恭维他。 4. My compliments to your wife. 向您的夫人致意。 5. He complimented her on her new dress without even looking at it. 他连看都没看一眼，就称颂她的新衣服。', '过去式: complimented 过去分词: complimented 现在分词: complimenting 第三人称单数: compliments');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hector', '[\'hektər]', 'n.赫克托(①男子名 ②荷马史诗《伊利亚特》中的一勇士名) hector. v.威吓；恐吓 n.恃强凌弱的人', '1. You betrayed me, Hector...And for that, the punishment is death. 你背叛了我，赫克托，为此，惩罚便是死亡。 2. When Hector recovered he led such a charge, with Paris on one side of him, Aeneas on the other, that the Greeks fled in good earnest. 待赫克托伤愈后，他带头出击，身旁有帕里斯与埃涅阿斯左右相辅，来势之猛，使希腊人望风披靡。', '过去式: hectored 过去分词: hectored 现在分词: hectoring 第三人称单数: hectors');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('raucous', '[\'rɔːkəs]', 'adj.沙哑的；粗声的；刺耳的', '1. I heard sounds of raucous laughter upstairs. 我听见楼上传来沙哑的笑声。 2. His raucous laughters irritated me. 他那粗哑的笑声令人头痛。 3. He speaks in a deep and raucous voice. 他讲话浊声浊气的。', '副词: raucously 名词: raucousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('feature', '[\'fiːtʃər]', 'n.特征；特色；容貌；特写；故事片 vt.以 ... 为特色 vi.起重要作用', '1. Their candor is a very pleasing feature. 他们的坦白是很愉快的特征。 2. Wet weather is a feature of life in this area. 天气潮湿是这个地区生活的一个特色。 3. Her mouth is her best feature. 她的嘴是她容貌上最好看的部分。 4. The local newspaper ran a feature on child labor. 地方报纸登载一篇有关童工的特写。 5. This restaurant seems to feature vegetarian dishes. 这家餐厅似乎以素菜为其特色。 6. Jazz and Blues feature prominently in the magazine. 爵士和蓝调在杂志中占重要篇幅。', '过去式: featured 过去分词: featured 现在分词: featuring 第三人称单数: features');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('brake', '[breɪk]', 'n.制动器；闸；刹车 v.刹车', '1. There\'s too much travel on the brake, it needs tightening. 制动器太松了，需要调紧。 2. After the work, remember to shut off the brake and remain neatness. 使用后必须拉闸,要保持卫生。 3. The brake doesn\'t grip properly. 刹车不灵了。 4. A lot of the cost of maintenance go into renew brake. 很多的维修费用都花在了更换煞车方面。 5. The car in front of me stopped suddenly and I had to brake. 我前面那辆小汽车突然停住，我只好刹车。', '过去式: braked 过去分词: braked 现在分词: braking 第三人称单数: brakes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('orifice', '[\'ɔːrɪfɪs]', 'n.孔', '1. Every person has two nasal orifices. 一个人有两个鼻孔。 2. A mouse ran out from the dark orifice of the cave. 一只老鼠从黑暗的洞口跑出。', '形容词: orificial');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('quadruped', '[\'kwɑːdruped]', 'n.四足动物 adj.四足的', '1. An analogous part of the leg of a dog or other quadruped. 似骹骨狗或其它四足动物腿上的类似部位 2. A quadruped mammal. 四足哺乳动物 3. A joint, as of a bird or quadruped, corresponding to the human elbow. 关节，肘部鸟或四肢动物的关节，相当于人的肘 4. The part of the body of a human being or quadruped on either side of the backbone and between the ribs and hips. 腰部人类或四足动物的身体部分，位于脊柱两侧，肋骨与臀部之间', '形容词: quadrupedal');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('devise', '[dɪ\'vaɪz]', 'vt.设计；发明；遗赠', '1. This time we\'ll devise a better solution. 这次我们将设计一种新的解决方案。 2. The government devised a scheme for redeveloping the city center. 政府制定了市中心重建计划。 3. He devised a new type of transistor. 他发明了一种新的晶体管。', '形容词: devisable 名词: deviser 过去式: devised 过去分词: devised 现在分词: devising 第三人称单数: devises');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('herbaceous', '[ɜːr\'beɪʃəs]', 'adj.草本植物的；叶状的', '1. We have a herbaceous borderround our garden. 我们花园的四周有一圈草本植物的花坛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('defile', '[dɪ\'faɪl]', 'vt.弄脏；污损；败坏；玷污 vi.以纵队前进 n.(山间)小道；狭谷', '1. Who are these men who defile the grassy borders of our roads and lanes. 是谁污损了我们大路和小路两旁的草坪。 2. Insults alone cannot defile a person\'s honour. 仅靠辱骂不可能败坏一个人的名誉。 3. Do not defile yourselves by any of these things. 在这一切的事上，你们都不可玷污自己。 4. Then the people of Israel will no longer stray from me, nor will they defile themselves anymore with all their sins. 好使以色列家不再走迷离开我，不再因各样的罪过玷污自己，只要作我的子民，我作他们的神。', '副词: defilingly 名词: defilement 过去式: defiled 过去分词: defiled 现在分词: defiling 第三人称单数: defiles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('asymmetric', '[ˌeɪsɪ\'metrɪk]', 'adj.不对称的', '1. Nevertheless, it remains asymmetric in early-onset strabismus. 但是在早发性斜视的病人，则一直维持看不对称的运动觉。 2. The different speed for each direction gives it the asymmetric label. 在每个方向有不同速度使它得到了不对称的招牌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('meditation', '[ˌmedɪ\'teɪʃn]', 'n.沉思；冥想', '1. He is deep in meditation. 他陷入沉思中。 2. Meditation is a form of guided thought. 沉思是一种引导思维的形式。 3. She found peace through yoga and meditation. 她通过瑜伽和冥想找到了宁静。', '形容词: meditational');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('shawl', '[ʃɔːl]', 'n.披肩；围巾 vt.用披肩；用围巾', '1. She threw a shawl over her shoulders. 她匆匆地把披肩披在肩上。 2. The baby was enveloped in a shawl. 婴儿裹在围巾里。 3. She pulled a shawl over her shoulders and went out. 她在肩上披上一条围巾就出去了。 4. She gathered the shawl about her shoulders to keep out the wind. 为了抵御风寒，她用披肩裹住了她的双肩。', '过去式: shawled 过去分词: shawled 现在分词: shawling 第三人称单数: shawls');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fatidic', '[fə\'tɪdɪk]', 'adj.(=prophetic)预言的；预言性的', '1. fatidic: adj. 预言的。', '异体字: fatidical');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mandatory', '[\'mændətɔːri]', 'adj.法定的；义务的；强制性的；受委托的 n.受托管理者', '1. It\'s mandatory to pay taxes. 缴税是义务性的。 2. Mandatory retirement ages need to go. 强制退休年龄必须废除。 3. Cremation is mandatory in most areas of Guangdong. 火化在广东大部分地区是强制性的。', '名词复数: mandatories');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('shopworn', '[\'ʃɑːpwɔːrn]', 'adj.在商店中陈列旧了的；陈旧的；磨损的', '1. He was fat and looked shopworn around the nose and mouth. 他人长得胖，鼻头和嘴巴部分显出一副不合时宜的可怜相。 2. And I think we\'re entering a phase where this marriage between advertising and editorial is getting a bit shopworn. 我觉得目前广告和编辑之间的结合已经老掉牙了。 3. However, despite his life-and-death battle with Diaz, Marquez should not be viewed as shopworn by any stretch of the imagination.Clean living and a Spartan work ethic has preserved him to an extent. 不过，即便经历了与迪亚兹生死大战，也丝毫不能将马奎兹当做老旧之人，因为严谨的生活以及斯巴达克式的作风已在一定程度上保养了他。 4. shopworn anecdotes.See Synonyms at trite 陈旧的轶事参见', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('plenitude', '[\'plenɪtuːd]', 'n.丰富；足够的状况', '1. I can feel the plenitude and joy during my work every day. 在工作的日子里，我感觉每天都很充实、快乐。 2. Life breeds both plenitude and void, exuberance and depression. 生命同时滋养着充盈和空无、生机和萎靡。', '形容词: plenitudinous');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('venerate', '[\'venəreɪt]', 'v.尊敬；尊崇；崇拜', '1. They came to venerate him as a symbolic figure. 他们把他当作偶像来崇拜。 2. They venerate the old man\'s memory. 他们怀着崇敬之情纪念那位老人。 3. And love, young man, love and venerate the ideal. 青年人啊，热爱理想，崇敬理想吧。 4. Merchant should aways venerate his heart. 商人应该尊崇自己的内心.', '名词: venerator 过去式: venerated 过去分词: venerated 现在分词: venerating 第三人称单数: venerates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('blade', '[bleɪd]', 'n.刀刃；刀锋；桨叶；叶片', '1. The blade needs sharpening. 这刀刃需要磨一磨。 2. The blade slashed his leg open. 刀刃把他的腿划破了。 3. The blade is chipped in a few places. 刀锋有几个地方缺口。 4. The propellar blade is powered by a diesel engine. 螺旋桨叶由柴油发动机驱动。', '形容词: bladed');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('analyze', '[\'ænəlaɪz]', 'vt.分析；解析；研究', '1. Can you analyze the structure of the sentence for me? 你能给我分析一下这个句子的结构吗？ 2. Let\'s analyze the problem and see what went wrong. 让我们分析一下这道题，看什么地方出错了。 3. You should analyze the essence of the problem. 你应该剖析问题的实质。 4. They will take the problem apart and analyze it. 他们会深入剖析这个问题。', '形容词: analyzable 名词: analyzation 过去式: analyzed 过去分词: analyzed 现在分词: analyzing 第三人称单数: analyzes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dissolute', '[\'dɪsəluːt]', 'adj.放荡的；放纵的；肆意挥霍的', '1. Intemperate in the pursuit of pleasure; dissolute. 放荡的，浪荡的无节制地追寻欢乐; 浪荡的 2. One who acts without moral restraint; a dissolute person. 放荡不羁的人行动没有道德约束的人; 放荡的人 3. Given over to dissipation; dissolute. 放荡的沉迷于挥霍无度的; 放荡的', '副词: dissolutely 名词: dissoluteness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('depressant', '[dɪ\'presnt]', 'adj.有镇静作用的 n.镇静剂', '1. Despite being classified as a depressant, alcohol initially acts as a stimulant on the central nervous system. 虽说被划定为镇静剂，酒精最初却是被当作中枢神经系统的兴奋剂。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dagger', '[\'dæɡər]', 'n.短剑；匕首；[印]剑号', '1. He parried the sword with his dagger. 他用短剑挡开了马刀。 2. Put the dagger back in its sheath. 把短剑插回鞘内。 3. The hoodlum stabbed at me with a dagger. 小流氓用匕首向我刺来。 4. The kind whisper went to my heart like a dagger. 这仁慈的低语象一把匕首直刺进我的心。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sentient', '[\'sentiənt]', 'adj.有知觉的；有感情的', '1. This means that your capabilities as a sentient being have been greatly curtailed. 这意味着你的知觉存在能力被大大缩减。 2. We are taking our power back to determine our fate as a conscious and sentient species upon earth. 我们正收回我们的力量来确定我们作为地球上一个有意识和有感情的物种的命运。', '副词: sentiently');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('synoptic', '[sɪ\'nɒptɪk]', 'adj.摘要的；纵观全局的 Synoptic. adj.与《新约》前三本福音书有关的', '1. There are many vortex patterns on synoptic maps. 摘要天气图上有许多种涡旋型式。', '副词: synoptically 异体字: synoptical');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pound', '[paʊnd]', 'n.磅；英镑 n.（汽车）扣押所；宠物收留所 vt.捣碎；敲打；连续猛击 vi.咚咚地走；怦怦地响', '1. I lost several pounds last month. 我上个月瘦了好几磅。 2. The shop is selling choice apple, so I buy 3 pound. 那商店在卖上选苹果,所以我买了三磅。 3. There is a 1 pound admission charge. 入场费为1英镑。 4. I paid him b pound , and he gave me 20 pence change. 我付了一英镑 5. Have you redeemed your car from the pound? 你有没有取回被扣的汽车? 6. The farmers pound rice in a mortar. 农民们在臼中舂米。 7. Do not pound up the stairs! 上楼梯不要跺脚！', '名词: pounder 名词复数: pound 过去式: pounded 过去分词: pounded 现在分词: pounding 第三人称单数: pounds');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bucket', '[\'bʌkɪt]', 'n.【C】水桶；（机器上的）桶装物；大量 vi.颠簸行进；下倾盆大雨 vt.装在桶里', '1. Go and fill this bucket with water for me. 去替我装满一桶水来。 2. He came down the hill carrying a bucket of water. 他提著一桶水下山来了。 3. I knocked over the bucket and the water poured (out) all over the floor. 我打翻了水桶，水流了一地。 4. They buy tickets by the bucket and sell them at a profit. 他们买了很多票,并且再卖掉以获取利润。 5. The old car bucketed along at about thirty. 那辆旧车以30公里左右的时速行驶。 6. The girl was bucketing water from the well. 那姑娘在用桶从井里打水。', '过去式: bucketed 过去分词: bucketed 现在分词: bucketing 第三人称单数: buckets');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('felony', '[\'feləni]', 'n.重罪', '1. Such action constitutes a felony. 这样的行为实际上等于犯了重罪。 2. But he\'s now facing new felony charges. 但是他面临其他重罪指控。', '名词复数: felonies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ablution', '[əb\'luːʃən]', 'n.洗身；洗礼；斋戒沐浴', '1. In the picture the ablution is completed, and the person who has performed it is ready to start to start his prayer. 在图中洗礼是完整的，只有执行了洗礼的人才可以祈祷。 2. As the herald of the new civilization, Desdemona allures the conceited hero to take off armour and attend the ablution of the new civilization. 苔斯狄蒙娜装扮成新文明的使者，诱使自以为是的英雄卸下恺甲，参加了新文明的洗礼。', '形容词: ablutionary');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('absenteeism', '[ˌæbsən\'tiːɪzəm]', 'n.（无故）旷课；（无故）旷工', '1. He\'s concerned about your absenteeism. 他很关注你旷课的问题。 2. Employee absenteeism has gotten out of hand. 雇员的旷工现象已经失去控制。 3. There were strict sanctions against absenteeism. 旷工会受到严厉的处分。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('condole', '[kən\'doʊl]', 'v.慰问', '1. We visited Frank to condole with him on the death of his father. 我们看望了弗兰克，对他父亲的去世向他表示慰问。', '形容词: condolatory 名词: condoler 过去式: condoled 过去分词: condoled 现在分词: condoling 第三人称单数: condoles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('grate', '[ɡreɪt]', 'n.栅；壁炉 vt.装格栅于 v.磨擦；磨碎；（使）烦恼', '1. The fire in the grate, too, had burned low. 炉栅里的火也已经很微弱了。 2. The old man leaned forward and knocked his pipe out against the grate. 老人俯下身子，在壁炉格栅上敲出烟斗里的烟灰。 3. There is a grate on the grimy floor. 龌龊的地面上有栅栏。 4. There were red coals in the grate. 壁炉里有烧红的煤块。 5. The teacher\'s chalk grated on the blackboard. 老师的粉笔在黑板上发出刺耳的摩擦声。', '过去式: grated 过去分词: grated 现在分词: grating 第三人称单数: grates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('corpus', '[\'kɔːrpəs]', 'n.资料；文集', '1. The bilingual corpus in this paper is LDC parallel texts in Hong Kong newspaper. 本文中所用的双语语料是LDC的关于香港的双语新闻报道。 2. So the veracity of chunking descends on real different field corpus. 因而，在跨领域的真实语料情况下，语块识别的精确率有很大的下降。 3. I\'ve got the corpus of Shakespeare\'s works. 我有莎士比亚全集。 4. This corpus has altogether 15 volumes. 这部文集共有十五卷。', '名词复数: corpora');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('venal', '[\'viːnl]', 'adj.<正式>受贿的；贪赃枉法的', '1. The venal policeman accepted the bribe. 贪污的警察收受贿赂。 2. Venal judges are a disgrace to a country. 贪污腐败的法官是国家的耻辱。 3. I never intimidate ordinary folks. I only intimidate those venal officials. 我从来不吓唬老百姓，只吓唬那些贪官污吏。 4. Most were useless rather than venal. 他们中的多数只是无能，但还没有贪赃枉法。', '副词: venally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('porridge', '[\'pɔːrɪdʒ]', 'n.粥；麦片粥', '1. She spooned out bowls of porridge. 她用匙舀出了几碗粥。 2. The dog quickly lapped up all the porridge. 狗不一会儿就把所有的粥都舐光了。 3. I had a bowl of porridge for breakfast. 我早餐吃了一碗麦片粥。 4. We can ask Sarah to make porridge for you,if you like. 要是你喜欢喝粥，我们可以叫萨拉给你做麦片粥。', '形容词: porridgy');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bedeck', '[bɪ\'dek]', 'vt.装饰；修饰', '1. The duchess bedeck herself with jewel. 公爵夫人用珠宝装扮自己。', '过去式: bedecked 过去分词: bedecked 现在分词: bedecking 第三人称单数: bedecks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('knead', '[niːd]', 'v.揉(面粉等)；按摩；捏制', '1. The little boy kneaded the dough into a ball. 那个小男孩把面团揉成了球状。 2. Pizza dough must be knead for five minutes. 做比萨饼的面团要揉5分钟。 3. After she kneaded his muscles, he felt very comfortable. 她给他按摩了肌肉以后，他感到很舒服。 4. Having been long sitting there, I have to knead the lame muscles of my legs. 因为在那儿坐了很久，我不得不按摩我那僵硬的腿部肌肉。', '名词: kneader 过去式: kneaded 过去分词: kneaded 现在分词: kneading 第三人称单数: kneads');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('secede', '[sɪ\'siːd]', 'v.正式脱离或退出', '1. The Republic of Panama seceded from Colombia in 1903. 巴拿马共和国于1903年脱离哥伦比亚。', '过去式: seceded 过去分词: seceded 现在分词: seceding 第三人称单数: secedes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lumberjack', '[\'lʌmbərdʒæk]', 'n.伐木工；吊木材机器 =lumberman.', '1. The lumberjack used an axe to cut down the tree. 这个伐木工人用斧头砍倒了这棵树。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('epaulet', '[\'epəˌlet]', 'n.肩章；肩饰', '1. Lens:Li3 Bing Bing the Jing, epaulet, handcuffs all together, with really about. 镜头：李冰冰警服、肩章、手铐都齐了，和真的差不多。 2. Our products range from hang-tag/brand label,Woven label,Care label,Trade marks, Leather trade marks,Epaulet,zipper-puller,button, and other accessories. 深圳宇乐服装辅料有限公司真诚欢迎生产销售服装辅料的新老客户与本公司建立合作伙伴关系。 3. Nevertheless, this piece of photograph is not openly resembling, illuminate downward from altitude however, can see his general crown and aureate epaulet only. 不过，这张照片不是正面像，而是从高处往下照的，只能看到他的将军帽顶和金色肩章。 4. Including the computer bead piece embroidery, the rope embroiders, the badge embroidery, the epaulet epaulet badge, the automobile symbol badge embroidery, the computer embroiders! 电脑珠片绣，贴布绣，绳索绣，立体绣，徽章，汽车车标章子绣花刺绣等各种电脑绣花！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('jounce', '[dʒaʊns]', 'v.震动；摇撼；颠簸 n.摇动；震动', '1. His tooth gave another red-hot jounce. 他的牙齿又火辣辣地疼了一下。 2. Install the jounce bumper on the upper spring mount. 在上部弹簧固定处安装避震器。 3. The Vehicle Jounce phenomenon at bridge head is discussed and solution is presented. 在继承原有的粉喷桩设计理论的基础上，根据新的设计思路提出新的设计方案。 4. In China, North to Harbin, South to Qingjiang one line, West to Wuzhong one line, East to Bohai Gulf island and northeast Border Line.People of wide area felt egregious jounce. 在华夏大地，北至哈尔滨，南至清江一线，西至吴忠一线，东至渤海湾岛屿和东北国境线，这一广大地区的人们都感到异乎寻常的摇撼。', '过去式: jounced 过去分词: jounced 现在分词: jouncing 第三人称单数: jounces');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('crusade', '[kruː\'seɪd]', 'n.改革运动 vi.参与斗争或运动 Crusade. n.十字军东征', '1. It\'s a crusade against corruption. 这是一场反腐败的运动。 2. He was deeply involved with the anti-drugs crusade. 他深深地涉入了反毒品运动。 3. The college students are active to crusade against the nuclear weapons. 大学生们积极投入开展反对核武器的运 动。 4. We must crusade for world peace. 我们必须为世界和平而奋斗。 5. In the first real crusade Jerusalem was captured. 第一次真正的十字军东征时攻下了耶路撒冷。', '名词: crusader 过去式: crusaded 过去分词: crusaded 现在分词: crusading 第三人称单数: crusades');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('intercessor', '[ˌɪntə\'sesə]', 'n.仲裁者；调解人', '1. Catholics pray to Mary as an intercessor. 天主教徒向玛利亚祈祷，并把她看作仲裁者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('defraud', '[dɪ\'frɔːd]', 'v.诈骗', '1. He defrauded the author of his property. 他把这个作家的财产骗走了。 2. She was charged with intent to defraud. 她被指控犯有蓄意诈骗钱财罪。', '名词: defraudation 过去式: defrauded 过去分词: defrauded 现在分词: defrauding 第三人称单数: defrauds');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('browbeat', '[\'braʊbiːt]', 'v.威吓；恫吓', '1. For many Britons accustomed to watching Thatcher browbeat enemies and dress down aides, it seemed like only a matter of time before her support for Major would cool. 对很多看惯撒切尔向她的政敌怒目而视或斥责僚属的英国人来说，她对梅杰的支持迟早都会冷却。 2. I won\'t be browbeaten into accepting your proposals. 我不会在威迫之下接受你的提议。 3. The judge browbeat the witness. 那法官威吓证人。', '名词: browbeater 过去式: browbeat 过去分词: browbeaten 现在分词: browbeating 第三人称单数: browbeats');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('corporal', '[\'kɔːrpərəl]', 'adj.肉体的；身体的；个人的 n.(陆军或空军)下士；[宗](供放面包和圣餐杯用的)圣餐布', '1. He could not resist the corporal temptation. 他无法抵抗肉体的诱惑。 2. A teacher should not give students corporal punishment. 老师不应该体罚学生。 3. corporal possession 私有财产 4. He was advanced to the rank of corporal. 他被提升为下士。', '副词: corporally 名词: corporality');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unfailing', '[ʌn\'feɪlɪŋ]', 'adj.永恒的；无穷的；可靠的', '1. Their discipline and good behaviour was unfailing. 他们的纪律和良好行为始终如一。 2. She fought the disease with unfailing good humour. 她始终抱乐观态度同疾病斗争。 3. Nature is always an unfailing fountain of inspiration. 大自然永远是灵感的泉源。 4. Everyone admired her patience and unfailing good humour. 人人都佩服她的耐心和永不衰减的好脾气。', '副词: unfailingly 名词: unfailingness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sparring', '[spɑːrɪŋ]', 'n.拳击；争论 动词spar的现在分词形式.', '1. Have you been sparring with Helen again? 你又一直在与海伦争吵吗？ 2. The boxers sparred for a while taking each other\'s measure. 拳击手彼此冲杀了一会儿，试探对方情况。 3. The two boys wee sparring and John tapped George\'s claret. 约翰和乔治在打架，结果约翰把乔治的鼻子打出血了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('convulsion', '[kən\'vʌlʃn]', 'n.抽搐；震动；动乱', '1. The story is so funny it has us in convulsion. 这故事滑稽极了，使我们笑得不亦乐乎。 2. The child reacted to the drug by going into convulsions. 这孩子全身痉挛，对药物有反应。 3. The child\'s nervous illness often threw her into convulsion. 这孩子的神经性疾病常使她产生痉挛。 4. The President\'s assassination led to political convulsion. 总统遇刺引起了政治骚乱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('repute', '[rɪ\'pjuːt]', 'n.名声；名气；声望 v.认为；以为', '1. He is held in high repute. 他名声很好。 2. Round 1900 his repute was still untarnished. 在1900年前后他的名声仍很响亮。 3. She is a singer with some repute. 她是个小有名气的歌手. 4. The wine is in high repute worldwide. 这酒在世界上享有盛名。', '过去式: reputed 过去分词: reputed 现在分词: reputing 第三人称单数: reputes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pony', '[\'poʊni]', 'n.小马；小型的东西 v.付清', '1. Rhett bought his daughter a pony to ride on. 瑞德给他的女儿买了一匹小马来骑。 2. The boy got a pony as a birthday gift. 这个男孩得到的生日礼物是一匹小马。 3. She drank a pony of brandy. 她喝了一小杯白兰地。 4. I wish you\'d pony up the money you owe. 我希望你将欠的钱付清。', '名词复数: ponies 过去式: ponied 过去分词: ponied 现在分词: ponying 第三人称单数: ponies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('budget', '[\'bʌdʒɪt]', 'n.预算 vt.编预算；为 ... 做预算 vi.节省开支 adj.廉价的；不贵的', '1. Congress has approved the new educational budget. 国会通过了新的教育预算。 2. Our budget needs drastic revision. 我们的预算需作重大修改。 3. The government has budgeted 10000000 pounds for education spending. 政府将10000000英镑编入教育预算。 4. The government plans to budget a new hospital. 政府计划在预算中拨款建一家新医院。 5. If we budget carefully, we\'ll be able to afford a new house. 如果我们精打细算就能买一座新房子了。 6. You can buy high-quality goods at budget prices there. 你可以在那买到物美价廉的商品。', '形容词: budgetary 名词: budgeter 过去式: budgeted 过去分词: budgeted 现在分词: budgeting 第三人称单数: budgets');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cavort', '[kə\'vɔːrt]', 'v.骑马腾跃；嬉闹', '1. Stop cavorting around and sit still, just for five minutes! 别欢蹦乱跳的，坐好了，就五分钟！', '过去式: cavorted 过去分词: cavorted 现在分词: cavorting 第三人称单数: cavorts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('explicit', '[ɪk\'splɪsɪt]', 'adj.明确的；清晰的；清楚的；露骨的', '1. They gave explicit reasons for leaving. 他们明确地说出了离开的原因。 2. A man can try his best to perfect and improve himself only if he has strong desires and explicit goal. 只有怀着强烈的欲望,有着明确的目标,一个人才能竭尽全力去完善自我,提升自我。 3. He has an explicit understanding of this. 他对这个了解得很清晰。 4. He gave me explicit directions on how to get there. 他清清楚楚地告诉我怎样到达那里。', '副词: explicitly 名词: explicitness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('conflagration', '[ˌkɒnflə\'greɪʃən]', 'n.大火灾；大火；爆发', '1. Both awaited the last judgment and resurrection of the dead after the final conflagration of the universe. 两者都等待宇宙大火灾之后的最后审判和从死亡中复活。 2. The heavy rain extinguished the conflagration. 大雨扑灭了这场大火。 3. The fire brigade soon got the conflagration under control. 消防队很快就把火控制住了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('limpid', '[\'lɪmpɪd]', 'adj.清澈的；清晰的', '1. The Li River is limpid with crystal water. 漓江明洁如镜，清澈见底。 2. A limpid stream ran through the little town. 一条清澈的小溪穿过这个小镇。', '副词: limpidly 名词: limpidity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('expulsion', '[ɪk\'spʌlʃn]', 'n.驱逐；开除；排气', '1. The King ordained the persecution and expulsion of the Jews. 国王颁布了犹太人的迫害和驱逐。 2. The threat of expulsion is hanging over all Portuguese clubs because of a dispute in the SuperLiga. 这项驱逐令是针对所有葡萄牙的俱乐部，因为他们在葡超联赛中的争端。 3. The club faces expulsion from the football league. 这家具乐部面临被足协开除。 4. We soon heard of the expulsion of the military adviser. 我们很快就听说了军事顾问被开除的消息。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('yeoman', '[\'joʊmən]', 'n.自耕农；小地主；侍从；[美]海军文书 adj.自耕农的；忠实的 Yeoman. n.约曼(人名)', '1. The yeoman could never own and work on their land after the movement. 那场运动后，自耕农再也不能拥有并在他们自己的土地上耕耘了。 2. It was not the aristocrat but the yeoman who determined the nation\'s policies. 决定国家政策的不是贵族,而是自耕农。 3. This man was a yeoman all his life. 这个人当了一辈子的侍从。 4. Her uncle spent two years on a warship as a yeoman. 她舅舅在军舰上当了两年文书军士。 5. Our company believes that workers\' yeoman service is the key to success.Reach win-win with joint efforts. 公司认为员工的卓越贡献是治亿科技成功的关键，通过双方的共同努力达到\"双赢\"。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('biennial', '[baɪ\'eniəl]', 'adj.两年一次的；两年生的 n.两年生植物；两年一次的事', '1. Every union has its own annual or biennial meeting. 每个工会都有自己的年会或每二年一次的大会。 2. The workers were strongly against the biennial election. 工人们强烈反对两年一次的选举。 3. They met at biennial conventions. 他们是在两年举行一次的大会上遇见的。 4. All annual and biennial plants are monocarpic. 所有一年生及二年生植物都是结果一次后死去。 5. This is a biennial, and one of the most useful pasture plants we have. 这是两年生植物,也是我们最有用的牧草之一。', '副词: biennially');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('undercut', '[ˌʌndər\'kʌt]', 'v.削弱；廉价出售或工作；从下边切 n.（牛的）嫩腰肉；下部切割；切口；切球', '1. However, for most of the target audience, this will undercut the message badly. 然而，对于大多数观众来说，这会削弱影片所要传达的讯息的张力。 2. Some members of the board were trying to undercut the chairman\'s authority. 委员会的某些成员试图削弱主席的权力。', '过去式: undercut 过去分词: undercut 现在分词: undercutting 第三人称单数: undercuts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cognizant', '[\'kɑːɡnɪzənt]', 'adj.已认识；既知道；晓得', '1. Are you cognizant of all the complexities of the language? 你知道这种语言的各种各样的复杂特征吗? 2. He was not cognizant of the danger . 他没认识到危险性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('arresting', '[ə\'restɪŋ]', 'adj.醒目的；引人注意的；有趣的 动词arrest的现在分词形式.', '1. This is one of the most arresting galaxy smash-up images to date. 这是目前的最引人注目的星系碰撞图像之一。 2. Her aspect was fair and arresting. 她的外表，漂亮标致，惹人注目。 3. When the houses were finished, they were effective and arresting. 房屋建造完成后显得精巧而壮观。', '副词: arrestingly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('prevaricate', '[prɪ\'værɪkeɪt]', 'v.支吾其辞；搪塞', '1. Tell us exactly what happened and don\'t prevaricate. 有什麽就原原本本地告诉我们吧，别躲躲闪闪的。 2. He accused the minister of prevaricating. 他指责部长用搪塞蒙混过关。', '名词: prevarication 过去式: prevaricated 过去分词: prevaricated 现在分词: prevaricating 第三人称单数: prevaricates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reside', '[rɪ\'zaɪd]', 'vi.居住；属于；存在', '1. This family has resided in this city for 60 years. 这个家族住在本城已有60年了。 2. They reside in a cottage at the foot of the mountain. 他们住在山脚下的一所小屋里。 3. The real power resides in the people. 真正的权力属于人民。 4. Memory has been shown to reside in some metals. 已经证实，记忆存在于某些金属中。', '名词: resider 过去式: resided 过去分词: resided 现在分词: residing 第三人称单数: resides');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('blockade', '[blɑː\'keɪd]', 'n.【C】封锁；阻碍物 vt.封锁；挡住', '1. Enemy ships tried to run the blockade. 敌军船只企图突破封锁线。 2. They are threatening to impose a blockade on the country. 他们威胁说要对该国实行封锁。 3. A blockade of all the harbor of that country will require thousands of warships. 封锁那个国家的所有港口需要成千上万艘战舰。 4. The house had a lot of blockades surrounded to prevent the fire stretching. 为了防止这个房子火势蔓延，屋子周围布满了障碍物。 5. The enemy\'s ships blockaded the harbor. 敌人的军舰封锁了港口。', '名词: blockader 过去式: blockaded 过去分词: blockaded 现在分词: blockading 第三人称单数: blockades');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vicarious', '[vaɪ\'keriəs]', 'adj.代理的；担任代理的；替身的；代替性的；有同感的', '1. She is not content with her vicarious authority. 她不甘心只拥有一个代理的职权。 2. The products involved in this authorization certificates include all series products contaning our company\'s trademark and all vicarious products. 本授权证书，涉及商品，含本公司商标的所有系列产品及所代理的全部产品。', '副词: vicariously 名词: vicariousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hypothetical', '[ˌhaɪpə\'θetɪkl]', 'adj.假设的；假定的', '1. This is a purely hypothetical situation. 这纯粹是一种假设的情景。 2. Let me put a hypothetical question to you. 让我问你一个假设的问题。 3. It must be emphasized that these estimates are hypothetical. 必须强调说明，这些估算都是假定的。', '副词: hypothetically 异体字: hypothetic');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gyrate', '[\'dʒaɪreɪt]', 'adj.旋涡状的；旋转的 v.旋转', '1. Gyrate The dancers gyrated wildly to the strong beat of the music. 跳舞者随着音乐的强烈节奏而猛烈地旋转着。 2. The dancers gyrated wildly to the strong beat of the music. 跳舞者随着音乐的强烈节奏而猛烈地旋转着。', '名词: gyrator 过去式: gyrated 过去分词: gyrated 现在分词: gyrating 第三人称单数: gyrates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('entrancing', '[ɪn\'trɑːnsɪŋ]', 'adj.使人神魂颠倒的；使人入神的 动词entrance的现在分词.', '1. This strange entrancing delight had come. 新奇的令人神魂颠倒的快乐已经到来了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('choir', '[\'kwaɪər]', 'n.唱诗班；合唱队；唱诗班的席位', '1. The choir sang the 23rd Psalm. 唱诗班唱《旧约·诗篇》之第23篇。 2. The choir sang the amens beautifully. 唱诗班唱的阿门非常优美。 3. The choir sang sweetly, and none more so than the Welsh boy. 唱诗班唱得很悦耳，尤其是没人比得上那个威尔士男孩儿。 4. The choir was singing distinctly out of tune in places. 合唱团有些地方明显唱走调了。', '过去式: choired 过去分词: choired 现在分词: choiring 第三人称单数: choirs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dubious', '[\'duːbiəs]', 'adj.怀疑的；可疑的；不确定的', '1. I feel dubious about his honesty. 我对他的诚实表示怀疑。 2. I am dubious about accepting the offer of the job. 我犹豫不定是否接受提供给我的那份工作。 3. I remain dubious about her motives. 我对她的动机仍存疑念。 4. The testimony given by him is dubious. 他所作的证据是可疑的。', '副词: dubiously 名词: dubiousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sovereign', '[\'sɑːvrən]', 'n.元首；君主；最高统治者；金镑 adj.具有主权的；至高无上的；极好的', '1. The sovereign completely recovered from his illness. 元首完全自病中复原了。 2. No earthly sovereign can do what he pleases. 没有一个世间君王可以为所欲为。 3. A sovereign fell, bright and new, on the soft pile of the tablecloth. 一枚金镑，锃亮而崭新，落在厚实柔软的桌布上。 4. Morocco is a sovereign independent monarchy. 摩洛哥是个有主权而独立的君主国。', '副词: sovereignly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('expurgate', '[\'ekspərɡeɪt]', 'vt.净化；删去', '1. To expurgate(a book,for example)prudishly. 删节谦逊地删节(如一本书) 2. To expurgate(a book, for example) prudishly. 删节谦逊地删节（如一本书） 3. He is capabled of bring out an expurgate edit0ion of wordsworth. 他几乎做的出出版华兹华斯作品的删改本（洁本）。 4. He is capable of bring out an expurgate edit0ion of wordsworth. 他几乎做的出出版华兹华斯作品的删改本（洁本）。', '名词: expurgation 过去式: expurgated 过去分词: expurgated 现在分词: expurgating 第三人称单数: expurgates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('instructive', '[ɪn\'strʌktɪv]', 'adj.教育性的；有启发的；有益的', '1. Misfortunes are helpful and instructive. 不幸是有益的。 2. Both formations provide instructive early examples of integration. 两者的成立提供了一体化的有益的先例。', '副词: instructively 名词: instructiveness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('log', '[lɔːɡ]', 'n.原木；圆木；(航海、飞行)日志；(船)计程仪 v.伐木；记入(日志)', '1. They are sawing a log into planks. 他们把原木锯成一块块厚板。 2. My brother is chopping logs for the fire. 我哥哥正在为生火劈柴。 3. A log got in his way as he drove. 一根圆木挡住了他开车的去路。 4. The log twiddled round and round in the river. 那根圆木在河水中转来转去。 5. We\'ll log another section of the area today. 今天我们要砍伐另一部分林区的树木。', '过去式: logged 过去分词: logged 现在分词: logging 第三人称单数: logs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ductile', '[\'dʌktaɪl]', 'adj.易延展的；柔软的；易教导的', '1. This metal is light and workable and ductile. 这种金属既轻，又易加工，延展性也好。 2. Artists use copper because it\'s one of the most ductile metals. 艺术家们使用铜作材料，是因为铜是延展性最好的金属之一。 3. Clay is ductile when it\'s mixed with water. 粘土和水混合，就变得柔软可塑。 4. Cadmium is a lustrous, silver-white, ductile, very malleable metal. 镉是一种有光泽的，银白色的，非常柔软的，延展性很好的金属。', '名词: ductility');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('paltry', '[\'pɔːltri]', 'adj.微不足道的；琐碎的；无价值的；可鄙的', '1. His influence on this matter is paltry. 他对这件事的影响是微不足道的。 2. This is a paltry sum to pay for such a masterpiece. 对这样一部杰作只付这么一点钱, 未免太少了。 3. It\'s paltry to do that job. 做这件工作是毫无价值的。 4. How can you deliberately get up such paltry falsehoods? 你怎么能故意编造出这么卑鄙的谎话?', '副词: paltrily 比较级: paltrier 最高级: paltriest 名词: paltriness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('disinterested', '[dɪs\'ɪntrəstɪd]', 'adj.不感兴趣的；无私欲的；公平的；公正的 动词disinterest的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. But, the mere idea of having that much money is enough to make even the most disinterested students pay attention in a social studies class. 可是，哪怕仅仅是想到有这么一大笔钱，已经足够使那些对此最不感兴趣的学生也关注起这门社会学课程。 2. He is a disinterested person. 他是一个没有私心的人。 3. The God makes everyone disinterested. 上帝对每个人都是公平的！ 4. The judge gave a disinterested verdict. 法官作出了公正的判决', '副词: disinterestedly 名词: disinterestedness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tart', '[tɑːrt]', 'adj. 酸的； 尖酸的； 刻薄的 n. 果馅饼； <俚>妓女', '1. She replied, speaking for the first time, in her usual tart and offhand way. 于是她开口回答了，用她平常那种尖酸刻薄的声调随口说道。 2. She popped the tart into the oven. 她把果馅饼很快地放进烤箱里。', '副词: tartly 比较级: tarter 最高级: tartest 名词: tartness 过去式: tarted 过去分词: tarted 现在分词: tarting 第三人称单数: tarts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('laceration', '[ˌlæsə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.撕裂；锯齿状的伤口', '1. He has a laceration on his right arm. 他的右臂有处撕裂伤。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('assertive', '[ə\'sɜːrtɪv]', 'adj.断定的；自信的', '1. In love, you are assertive and possessive. 在爱情方面，你非常强势，占有欲很强。 2. Assertive teachers with a constant eye on these students can keep them in line. 凶一点的老师，只要使个眼神就能使他们归队。 3. Her assertive manner has made her a success. 她显出十分有信心的态度，使她获得成功。 4. You should try and be more assertive. 你应该努力坚定信心。', '副词: assertively 名词: assertiveness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('observant', '[əb\'zɜːrvənt]', 'adj.观察力敏锐的；（对法律、习俗、传统等）谨慎遵守的', '1. Journalists are trained to be observant. 新闻记者都要训练成有敏锐观察力的人。 2. She was intelligent and highly observant. 她聪明并且很有观察力。 3. An observant shop assistant had remembered exactly what the man was worn. 有个机警的店员准确地记着那个男子的穿著。 4. You should be observant of the traffic rules. 你应该遵守交通规则。', '副词: observantly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('revelry', '[\'revlri]', 'n.狂欢；欢宴', '1. The sound of revelry filled the house yesterday. 昨天这个屋子里充满了欢闹声。 2. The revelry was snubbed by my father. 我父亲终止了那次狂欢宴会。', '形容词: revelrous 名词复数: revelries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('commodity', '[kə\'mɑːdəti]', 'n.商品；日用品；有价值之物', '1. Coal is becoming a rare commodity. 煤正在成为一种稀缺商品。 2. In spite of the depression, the price of commodity is still high 尽管有些萧条,但商品的价格仍然很高。 3. The country is heavily dependent on its exports of agricultural commodities. 这个国家很大程度上依靠农产品的出口。 4. Time is our most valuable commodity. 时间是最有价值之物。', '名词复数: commodities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fecundity', '[fɪ\'kʌndəti]', 'n.多产；富饶；繁殖力', '1. In the worst places, fecundity tends to track instability. 在最惨的地方,越是动荡,人们越是多产。 2. The boy\'s fecundity of imagination amazed his teacher. 男孩想像力的丰富使老师感到讶异。 3. The probability of survival is the reciprocal of fecundity. 生存的概率是生殖力的倒数。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('squirt', '[skwɜːrt]', 'v.喷出；溅迸；注射 n.水枪；注射器；喷出', '1. If all else fails, the species can also squirt ink, like octopuses. 如果变色之后仍被敌人发现，它们则会像章鱼一样喷出墨液，并在墨液掩护下逃生。 2. In it spends to be generally American to squirt in the hole. 在从这个洞里喷出如花一般美的颜色。 3. When the operating medium contains some granules, you can squirt lotion or lubricant to clean the seal face, making sure a reliable seal. 当输送的介质不洁或含有少量颗粒时，为保护密封面，确保达到可靠的密封，还可给这一装置注射相应的清洗剂或润滑剂对密封面进行清洗。 4. The little boy wants to buy a squirt gun. 这个小男孩想买个水枪。', '名词: squirter 过去式: squirted 过去分词: squirted 现在分词: squirting 第三人称单数: squirts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('culpable', '[\'kʌlpəbl]', 'adj.该责备的；有罪的', '1. THe man who killed children is culpable. 杀害小孩的人应该受谴责。 2. I can not be held culpable for their mistakes. 不能把他们的错误归咎于我。 3. The judge found the man culpable. 法官认为那个人有罪。', '副词: culpably 名词: culpability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('frolic', '[\'frɑːlɪk]', 'v.嬉戏 n.嬉戏；欢乐的活动 adj.嬉戏的', '1. The children froliced in the garden after school. 孩子们放学后在花园里嬉戏。 2. He smiled to see the children\'s frolics. 他看到孩子们嬉戏而微笑。 3. They had a frolic in the country. 他们在乡村度过了一段欢乐的时光。 4. The gloom he was feeling gave way to frolic. 他心头的愁闷都被欢乐代替了。 5. I hope frolic songs are always round you and bring you endless happiness.Merry! 愿欢乐的歌声,时刻萦绕着你,使你的人生充满幸福喜悦,永浴与无尽的欢乐年华。祝圣诞快乐!', '名词: frolicker 过去式: frolicked 过去分词: frolicked 现在分词: frolicking 第三人称单数: frolics');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('devious', '[\'diːviəs]', 'adj.迂回的；弯曲的；不正直的；狡猾的', '1. The coach followed a rather devious course to its destination. 长途汽车要绕很多弯路才到达目的地。 2. Let\'s take the devious route home to avoid the crowds in the main roads. 为了避免大街上的拥挤，我们还是绕道回家去吧。 3. Go along the lotus pond, it is a devious road. 沿着荷塘，是一条曲折的小煤屑路。 4. His devious nature was shown in half lies and small dishonesties. 他不正直的天性表现在小谎话及细小的不诚实行为中。', '副词: deviously 名词: deviousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pitcher', '[\'pɪtʃər]', 'n.水罐；[棒球]投手；[植]瓶状叶', '1. The pitcher contains enough water for all of us. 那水罐可容纳足够我们全体饮用的水。 2. If you would be busy and fill your pitcher,come,O come to my lake. 如果你忙着要把水罐灌满，来吧，到我的湖边来吧。 3. The pitcher retired three batters. 这个棒球投手使三个击球手出局。 4. But even in victory, another pitcher was lost. 虽然赢了球，却失去了另一位投手。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('engender', '[ɪn\'dʒendər]', 'v.产生；引起', '1. Finally, managers can use intuition to bypass in-depth analysis and move rapidly to engender a plausible solution. 最后，管理者可通过直觉绕开深奥的分析而快速产生一个可能的解决办法。 2. An unguided ramble into its recesses in bad weather is apt to engender dissatisfaction with its narrow, tortuous, and miry ways. 天气不好的时候，没有向导带路而独自漫游到谷内幽深之处的人，容易对蜿蜒其间的狭窄的泥泞小道产生不满情绪。', '名词: engenderer 过去式: engendered 过去分词: engendered 现在分词: engendering 第三人称单数: engenders');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('putrefy', '[\'pjuːtrɪfaɪ]', 'v.使腐烂', '1. They will not putrefy but rather ferment. 它们虽没有变腐但的确发酵了。 2. They will not putrefy but rather ferment. 它们虽没有变腐但的确发酵了。 3. And those cheeses that we like so well are made from milk that has stood long enough to putrefy. 那些深受我们喜爱的奶酪是牛奶长时间存放，腐败后制成的。 4. Likewise glorious gifts and foundations are like sacrifices without salt and but the painted sepulchres of alms which soon will putrefy and corrupt inwardly. 同样，荣耀的馈赠与捐献就像是没有放盐的祭品，只不过是经过油漆的墓穴，里边的东西很快就会腐朽糜烂。', '过去式: puttrefied 过去分词: puttrefied 现在分词: puttrefying 第三人称单数: puttrefies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tapestry', '[\'tæpəstri]', 'n.挂毯 v.饰以织锦画', '1. This tapestry is a work of art. 这张挂毯是件艺术品。 2. The wall of my living room was hung with a tapestry. 我的起居室的墙上挂着一块壁毯。 3. Such strange events are all part of life\'s rich tapestry. 这些怪事都是丰富多彩的人生的一部分。', '名词复数: tapestries 过去式: tapestried 过去分词: tapestried 现在分词: tapestrying 第三人称单数: tapestries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reign', '[reɪn]', 'n.君主统治；在位期 v.统治；支配', '1. He has a tyrannical reign on his empire. 他是个残暴的皇帝。 2. People will remember the tyrannies of his reign. 人们不会忘记他统治时期的暴行。 3. The reign of Queen Victoria lasted more than sixty years. 维多利亚女王的统治持续了六十多年。 4. The American Revolution took place during the reign of George III. 美国独立战争发生在英王乔治三世统治时期。 5. He reigned over the country for forty years. 他统治了这个国家四十年。', '过去式: reigned 过去分词: reigned 现在分词: reigning 第三人称单数: reigns');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lurid', '[\'lʊrɪd]', 'adj.可怕的；骇人听闻的；苍白的；耀眼的', '1. Last night I met a wild and lurid bandit. 昨晚我遇到了一个野蛮而可怕的强盗。 2. The paper gave all the lurid details of the murder. 这份报纸对这起凶杀案骇人听闻的细节描述得淋漓尽致。 3. Moonlight gave the statue a lurid luminescence. 月光使这座雕塑发出苍白的光亮。 4. The lurid sunset puts a red light on their faces. 耀眼的夕阳映红了他们的脸。', '副词: luridly 名词: luridness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fastidious', '[fæ\'stɪdiəs]', 'adj.过分讲究的；挑剔的；苛求的；一丝不苟的 =particular.', '1. She is too fastidious about her food and clothing. 她太讲究吃穿。 2. She is so fastidious about her food that I never invite her for dinner. 她对食物过于挑剔，因此我从不请她吃饭。 3. The fact was that I became more and more fastidious as I grew older. 事实上，随着年龄的增长，我变得越来越吹毛求疵了。 4. Everything was planned in fastidious detail. 样样都一丝不苟地计划好了。', '副词: fastidiously 名词: fastidiousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('molding', '[\'moʊldɪŋ]', 'n.塑造物；装饰用嵌线 动词mold的现在分词形式.', '1. The sharp edge or ridge formed by two surfaces meeting at an angle, as in a molding. 尖脊两个平面以某种角度相接所形成的尖突的边或脊形，如铸模中的 2. A decorative upright trimming or molding along the edge of a table top, tray, or shelf. 边缘装饰在桌子顶部、托盘或书架边缘处的直立的装饰品或造型 3. A narrow, convex molding. 圆凸线一种窄的凸圆造型 4. A narrow border, molding, or fillet. 扁带饰窄条，装饰用嵌线或窄带', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ponderous', '[\'pɑːndərəs]', 'adj.笨重的；笨拙的；乏味的', '1. The elephant lowered its ponderous body into the water. 大象把它那笨重的身躯浸入水里。 2. After a whole day\'s work, he walked upstairs with a ponderous, lumbering gait. 在结束一天的工作后，他迈着沉重而笨拙的步子上楼了。 3. I don\'t like his ponderous style of writing. 我不喜欢他冗长乏味的文风。', '副词: ponderously 名词: ponderousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('forage', '[\'fɔːrɪdʒ]', 'n.粮草；饲料；搜寻粮草 v.喂；掠夺', '1. She teaches them to fish, forage, hunt, and defend themselves. 她教他们捕鱼，搜寻粮草，追捕，和防卫它们自己。 2. Flickers are woodpeckers that can hammer trees but prefer to forage on the ground. 闪烁啄木鸟能敲打树木但更喜欢到地面搜寻粮草。 3. There is much forage for the cattle. 那儿有很多喂牛的饲料。 4. Most species provide good forage. 大多数种提供好饲料。 5. There is much forage for the cattle. 那儿有很多喂牛的饲料。', '名词: forager 过去式: foraged 过去分词: foraged 现在分词: foraging 第三人称单数: forages');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('underestimated', '[ˌʌndər\'estɪmeɪt]', 'n.低估 v.低估', '1. The figure of $10 million was a serious underestimate. 一千万美元这个数据是一个严重的低估。 2. It seems to have been due to his consistent underestimate of her political weight. 看来是由于希思一贯低估她的政治能量。 3. Never underestimate the power of a woman. 决不要低估妇女的力量。 4. Don\'t underestimate the difficulties of the work. 不要低估了这项工作的艰巨性。', '名词: underestimation 过去式: underestimated 过去分词: underestimated 现在分词: underestimating 第三人称单数: underestimates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('roil', '[rɔɪl]', 'vt.搅浑；激怒 vi.动荡', '1. Cash is king as debt markets roil. 在债市动荡的时候，现金就是一切。 2. Some of her habits are off - putting but don\'t let them roil you. 她的一些习惯让人恶心，但最好别烦你 3. Some of her habits are off - putting but do not let them roil you. 她的一些习惯让人恶心，但最好别烦你 4. An adverse ruling from the court could roil the muni market. 法庭颁布的不利条款也有可能扰乱市政公债市场。', '过去式: roiled 过去分词: roiled 现在分词: roiling 第三人称单数: roils');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('indignity', '[ɪn\'dɪɡnəti]', 'n.侮辱；轻蔑；有伤尊严', '1. She was subjected to indignity and humiliation. 她受到侮辱和羞辱。 2. The bandits subject us to all sort of indignity. 强盗们对我们加以各种侮辱。 3. They inflicted all kinds of indignities on their captives. 他们对俘虏百般侮辱。 4. This is the indignity for female. 这是对女性的侮辱.', '名词复数: indignities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('locust', '[\'loʊkəst]', 'n.蝗虫；洋槐；刺槐', '1. The locust swarm has destroyed all the crops and vegetables. 蝗虫群毁坏了所有的庄稼和蔬菜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('deflated', '[dɪf\'leɪtɪd]', 'adj.灰心丧气的；泄气的 动词deflate的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. The act of deflating or the condition of being deflated. 放气，瘪掉抽气的动作或缩小的状态 2. Deflated. Used of a tire. 漏气的泄了气的。用于指轮胎 3. I felt quite deflated by your nasty remark. 你那些难听的话使我觉得无地自容。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stifle', '[\'staɪfl]', 'vt.使窒息；扼杀；扑灭；抑制 vi.窒息 n.(马的)后膝关节', '1. The gas stifled them. 他们被煤气熏得透不过气来。 2. The smoke filled the room and almost stifled the firemen. 屋里浓烟弥漫呛得消防队员喘不过气来。 3. We should stifle it in the cradle before it becomes worse. 我们应该在事态变坏前就把它扼杀在萌芽期。 4. She tried hard to stifle her laughter. 她强忍住笑。 5. I am stifling in this close room. 在这个窄狭的房间里面我感到憋闷。', '名词: stifler 过去式: stifled 过去分词: stifled 现在分词: stifling 第三人称单数: stifles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sartorial', '[sɑːr\'tɔːriəl]', 'adj.男式服装的；裁缝的；缝纫的', '1. John has been known for his sartorial elegance. 约翰因为衣着讲究而出名。', '副词: sartorially');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('plankton', '[\'plæŋktən]', 'n.浮游生物', '1. Plankton is at the bottom of the marine food chain. 浮游生物处于海洋食物链的最底层。', '形容词: planktonic');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('genesis', '[\'dʒenəsɪs]', 'n.起源；发生 Genesis：《创世纪》（旧约圣经第一卷）.', '1. Minor change to Genesis support. 对起源的支持略微的改变。 2. We cannot yet satisfactorily explain the genesis of the universe. 我们仍不能令人满意地解释宇宙的起源。 3. These effects are of considerable importance in the genesis of a number of important arrhythmias. 这些效应在某些重要的心律失常的发生上有相当重要的意义。 4. My future work is to use this system to carry out genetic screenings to identify novel genes regulating the neuronal genesis and morphogenesis. 本实验室将利用果蝇进行遗传筛选，寻找影响神经细胞发生及形态形成的分子机制。', '名词复数: geneses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incisor', '[ɪn\'saɪzər]', 'n.门牙', '1. The prosthesis of incisor immediate implant is practical and effective. 刻烤瓷冠修复单个前牙种植体是一种切实可行的方法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rehearsal', '[rɪ\'hɜːrsl]', 'n.排练；彩排', '1. The symphony is in rehearsal now. 这支交响乐正在排练中。 2. This is not a concert, but more of a rehears. 与其说那是一场音乐会，倒不如说是一次排练。 3. Is there a rehearsal for the concert? 音乐会有彩排吗? 4. I had panic attacks during rehearsal. 彩排的时候我有过多次的恐慌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sophisticated', '[sə\'fɪstɪkeɪtɪd]', 'adj.老练的；精密的；复杂的；久经世故的', '1. She is such a sophisticated woman that she saw through his trick at the first sight. 她是个十分老练的女人,她一眼就看穿了他的把戏。 2. As far as defense is concerned, we need to buy more sophisticated weapons. 就防御的观点来说，我们需要购买更多精密的武器。 3. The publisher\'s techniques for the promotion of his books have become increasingly sophisticated since the 1950s. 自20世纪50年代以来,出版商推销书籍的方式愈加复杂。 4. I\'d rather deal with a simple man than a sophisticated man. 我宁愿与纯朴的人打交道,不愿与世故的人交往。', '副词: sophisticatedly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bugaboo', '[\'bʌɡəbuː]', 'n.鬼怪；令人困扰的事', '1. But creating something useful is the bugaboo. 但是，创造出有用的东西听来有点唬人。 2. The bugaboo this time is black holes. 这次扮演毁灭世界的妖魔鬼怪的是黑洞。 3. Fables of nurses; bugaboo for children; Jehovah for men. 奶妈发明了妖怪来吓唬小孩，也发明了耶和华来吓唬大人。 4. When you’re worried about something, that can be a real bugaboo. 如果你的心里有忧虑的事情，那么这的确会困扰的你睡眠。', '名词复数: bugaboos');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('engross', '[ɪn\'ɡroʊs]', 'v.使全神贯注；独占；正式誊写；用大字体书写', '1. She was engrossed in painting. 她全神贯注于绘画。 2. Engrossed in his book he forgot the time. 他全神贯注地看书忘记了时间。 3. She used to tell me that she thought I ought to expect some gratification from him for my company, for indeed he did, as it were, engross me. 她常对我说应该从他那里得到一些好处，做为我陪伴他的报酬，因为他的确好象独占了我。 4. He can\'t engross all the money. 他独占所有的钱是不可能的。', '名词: engrosser 过去式: engrossed 过去分词: engrossed 现在分词: engrossing 第三人称单数: engrosses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flush', '[flʌʃ]', 'v.冲洗；发红；将某人赶出 n.脸红；冲洗；（纸牌）同花牌；【计算机】冲洗', '1. Father asked me to flush off the garage floor. 父亲叫我冲洗车库的地板。 2. The toilet won\'t flush properly. 马桶不好冲。 3. Don\'t forget to flush the toilet after use. 用完厕所,不要忘了冲。 4. Mary flushed crimson with embarrassment. 玛丽羞得脸红了。 5. A flush of excitement crept into his face. 兴奋的红晕爬上他的脸。', '比较级: flusher 最高级: flushest 名词: flusher 过去式: flushed 过去分词: flushed 现在分词: flushing 第三人称单数: flushes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('brisk', '[brɪsk]', 'adj.敏锐的；活泼的；活跃的；轻快的；凛冽的 v.（使）轻快', '1. His movements were brisk and boyish. 他的动作仍很敏捷，孩子气。 2. He was a vigorous, brisk person. 他是一个强壮的，活泼有力的人。 3. Diana \'s brisk, commanding voice rang out from a passage way. 黛安娜活泼而威严的声音从一条过道中传了出来。 4. Trading was brisk on the Stock Exchangetoday. 今日证券交易所交投活跃。 5. He brisked up his pace at the beautiful sight. 看到那美丽的景色，他加快了脚步。', '副词: briskly 比较级: brisker 最高级: briskest 名词: briskness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('desirable', '[dɪ\'zaɪərəbl]', 'adj.令人满意的；性感的；有吸引力的；值得的；令人向往的 n.有吸引力的人或物', '1. It is desirable that we (should) provide for the poor at Christmas. 在圣诞节施舍穷人是可喜的事。 2. It is desirable that atomic energy should be used for peaceful purpose. 原子能应该为了和平的目的而使用，这是合乎情理的。 3. You will also make some desirable acquaintances. 你也可以结识几个合意的朋友。 4. He found her intensely desirable. 他觉得她极其性感。 5. The girl is a desirable. 这个女孩是个有吸引力的人。', '副词: desirably 名词: desirability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('canvas', '[\'kænvəs]', 'n.油画；帆布；（帆布）画布', '1. The artist showed me his canvases. 画家给我看了他的油画。 2. He bought the canvas for ten thousand dollars. 他以一万美元买下这幅油画。 3. The hole was covered (over) with canvas. 这个洞被帆布遮盖住了。 4. The plumber stowed all his gear in a canvas bag. 管子工把他所有的工具都装进一只帆布袋里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('despise', '[dɪ\'spaɪz]', 'vt.轻视', '1. He claims to despise riches. 他宣称蔑视钱财。 2. You must not despise a man because he is poor. 你不可因一个人贫穷而轻视他。 3. I despise his refusing to accept responsibility. 他拒不承担责任，我鄙视他。 4. It is incorrect to despise woman. 轻视妇女是错误的。', '名词: despisal 过去式: despised 过去分词: despised 现在分词: despising 第三人称单数: despises');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('protrude', '[proʊ\'truːd]', 'v.突出；伸出', '1. Helen\' s teeth protrude too far. 海伦的牙齿太突出了。 2. It made his great nose protrude more arrogantly. 这就使得他的大鼻子更加傲慢地翘起来。 3. He is hurt by a shelf protruding from the wall. 他被一个从墙上伸出的架子伤着了。 4. He managed to hang on to a piece of rock protruding from the cliff. 他设法抓住了悬崖上向外伸出的岩石。', '形容词: protrudent 过去式: protruded 过去分词: protruded 现在分词: protruding 第三人称单数: protrudes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fort', '[fɔːrt]', 'n.堡垒；要塞', '1. The men in the fort sallied at dawn. 堡垒里的人在黎明时出击。 2. They built an adobe fort, which is now a museum. 他们建造的泥砖堡垒，现已成为博物馆。 3. The enemy soon occupied the fort. 敌人很快占领这座要塞。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('legacy', '[\'leɡəsi]', 'n.遗赠物；先人或过去遗留下来的东西 adj.[计算机]旧系统的', '1. He left me a small legacy in a nuncupative will, as a token of his kindness to me. 他囗头遗言上遗留给我一点小小遗产作为他对我关爱的表征。 2. These are the cultural legacies of the Renaissance. 这些是文艺复兴时期的文化遗产。', '名词复数: legacies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cereal', '[\'sɪriəl]', 'n.麦片粥；谷类食物 adj.谷类的；谷物的', '1. He sprinkled sugar over his cereal. 他在麦片粥里撒上了糖。 2. I have a bowl of cereal every morning. 我每天早晨吃一碗麦片粥。 3. The breakfast cereal is enriched with vitamins. 维生素增加了早餐谷类食物的营养价值。 4. The disease attacks cereal crop. 这种疾病侵害了谷类作物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sheer', '[ʃɪr]', 'adj.极轻薄的；陡峭的；全然的 adv.垂直地 v.避开；转向', '1. Chiffon is a fabric of sheer silk or rayon. 薄绸是一种极薄的丝绸或人造丝织物。 2. It\'s very difficult to climb a sheer cliff. 攀登陡峭的悬崖是很困难的。 3. She played a trick on him out of sheer devilment. 她捉弄他完全是为了寻开心。 4. He\'s so impatient that waiting in queues is sheer purgatory for him. 他毫无耐性，对他来说排队等候完全是活受罪。 5. The ground dropped away sheer at our feet. 我们脚下的地面垂直地陷落下去。 6. When he saw me coming he sheered off in the opposite direction. 他一看到我过来，掉头就走了。', '副词: sheerly 比较级: sheerer 最高级: sheerest 名词: sheerness 过去式: sheered 过去分词: sheered 现在分词: sheering 第三人称单数: sheers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mast', '[mæst]', 'n.船桅；旗杆；天线杆 abbr.磁性环形激波管(风洞研究用)(=Magnetic Annular Shock Tube)', '1. The mast went by the board in the storm. 那船桅在暴风雨中落于船外。 2. We heared the flaps of the sail against the mast. 我们听见帆拍击着船桅的声音。 3. Flags were flying on every mast. 旗帜在每根旗杆上飘扬。 4. The flag was riding up the mast. 旗帜飘荡着升上旗杆。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('deviate', '[\'diːvieɪt]', 'v.偏离；脱离 n.叛离者；偏差；不正常的人或物 adj.离经叛道的', '1. Don\'t always deviate to minor issues. 不要老是偏离到次要问题上去。 2. You will not deviate from your present course. 你不能偏离目前航线 3. His remarks usually deviate from truth. 他的话通常都与事实不符。 4. Do not deviate from the beaten track. 不要逸出常轨。', '形容词: deviatory 名词: deviator 过去式: deviated 过去分词: deviated 现在分词: deviating 第三人称单数: deviates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vascular', '[\'væskjələr]', 'adj.血管的；脉管的；充满活力的', '1. The basic disorder might be vascular dysfunction leading to local vasospasm and to systemic hypotension. 其基本的改变可能是血管的功能障碍导致局部的血管痉挛和低血压。 2. Furthermore, ECs obtained from these vascular malformations can be used as an experimental model to study SAH-induced vasoconstriction. 此外，这些来源于畸形血管的内皮细胞可作为研究蛛网膜下腔出血引发血管收缩的实验模型。', '名词: vascularity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lullaby', '[\'lʌləbaɪ]', 'n.摇篮曲；催眠曲；任何轻柔的音乐 v.唱摇篮曲使安眠；使安静', '1. The mother was crooning a lullaby to her baby. 母亲正对婴儿哼着摇篮曲。 2. We sang our little son a sweet lullaby. 我们给小宝宝唱了支甜美的摇篮曲。 3. The duchess sang a sort of lullaby to the baby. 公爵夫人对孩子唱了一首催眠曲一样的歌子。 4. Their prayers roll across the water and fall upon my ears like a lullaby rocking me to sleep. 他们的祷告横跨水滚动并且下跌在我的像晃动我的催眠曲的耳朵睡觉。', '名词复数: lullabies 过去式: lullabied 过去分词: lullabied 现在分词: lullabying 第三人称单数: lullabies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('attenuate', '[ə\'tenjueɪt]', 'v.变细；稀释；变弱 adj.细的；薄的；减少的', '1. In a forest, wet wood and needles attenuate the signals. 在森林中，潮湿的树木与针叶会使讯号变弱。 2. We are asking a network or system to attenuate certain frequencies. 我们正在要求一个网络或系统去压制某些频率。', '名词: attenuation 过去式: attenuated 过去分词: attenuated 现在分词: attenuating 第三人称单数: attenuates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('amenable', '[ə\'miːnəbl]', 'adj.顺从的；通情达理的；经得起检验的；对...负有义务的', '1. They had three very amenable children. 他们有三个很听话的孩子。 2. We are amenable to the law . 我们应该服从法律。 3. He is proud that his wife is amenable to reason. 他的妻子是个通情达理的人,为此他引以为豪。 4. This case is not amenable to the normal rules. 这件事经不起常规的检验。', '副词: amenably 名词: amenability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gloss', '[ɡlɑːs]', 'n.光彩；光泽；虚饰 n.注释；注解 v.掩盖；（使）有光泽 v.作注释', '1. The surface gloss had begun to crack. 表面的光彩已经开始衰退了。 2. Repair your face, shine your gloss! 修复你的容颜，绽放你的光彩！ 3. With this polish you can give a good high gloss to the wood. 使用这种上光蜡可使木器表面极为光亮平滑。 4. The gel gives your hair a gloss. 发胶使你的头发有了光泽。 5. The minister has put a different gloss on recent developments. 部长就局势的最新发展作了另一番解释。 6. It is bad policy to gloss over the difficulties. 掩盖困难是不明智的。 7. It is a difficult word that needs to be glossed. 它是一个需加注释的难词。', '名词: glosser 过去式: glossed 过去分词: glossed 现在分词: glossing 第三人称单数: glosses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reinstate', '[ˌriːɪn\'steɪt]', 'vt.使复位；恢复', '1. There he proposed to reinstate the ancient Olympic Games. 会议上，他提出恢复古代奥林匹克运动会。 2. A scheduled task will then reinstate their membership after that time. 计划任务，然后恢复其会员国后，那个时候。', '名词: reinstatement 过去式: reinstated 过去分词: reinstated 现在分词: reinstating 第三人称单数: reinstates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('abortive', '[ə\'bɔːrtɪv]', 'adj.失败的；流产的；发育不全的', '1. We had to abandon our abortive attempts. 我们的尝试没有成功，不得不放弃。 2. Somehow the whole abortive affair got into the FBI files. 这件早已夭折的案子不知怎么就进了联邦调查局的档案。 3. All efforts to trace and locate her next of kin proved abortive. 一切追查并找到其亲属的努力证明流产了。 4. Even an abortive attempt is better than a failed strategy. 即使是不成熟的尝试，也胜于胎死腹中的策略。', '副词: abortively 名词: abortiveness');
