INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('azure', '[\'æʒər]', 'n.天蓝色；碧空 adj.蔚蓝的', '1. His eyes are azure. 他的眼睛是天蓝色的。 2. He looked up at the azure and was lost in thought. 他抬头看着蓝天，沉思起来。 3. I write this post under gorgeously azure skies. 我在灿烂的蓝天下撰写这篇文章。 4. The sun shone out of a clear azure sky. 清朗蔚蓝的天空中阳光明媚。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fracture', '[\'fræktʃər]', 'n.破碎；骨折 vt.破碎；破裂 vi.断裂', '1. A fellow team member says it was a clean fracture without complications. 一位队友表示这只是纯粹的锁骨破碎，没有任何并发症。 2. He had several injuries, including three fractures. 他多处受伤，其中三处骨折。 3. If you sneeze too hard, you can fracture a rib. 打喷嚏太用力的话肋骨可能会骨折。 4. Many people predicted that the party would fracture and split. 很多人预言该党将分崩离析。 5. Her leg fractured in two places. 她的腿有两处骨折。', '过去式: fractured 过去分词: fractured 现在分词: fracturing 第三人称单数: fractures');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('produce', '[prə\'duːs]', 'v.生产；引起；提出；制片；分娩 n.产品；农产品', '1. This tree produces rubber. 这些树生产橡胶。 2. It is certain that we shall produce this kind of engine. 毫无疑问,我们将生产这种发动机。 3. The plain weave is comparatively inexpensive to produce. 相对来说,平纹组织的生产成本较低。 4. His announcement produced gasps of amazement. 他宣布的消息引起了一片惊叹声。 5. This shop sells native produce. 这家商店出售土特产品。', '形容词: producible 过去式: produced 过去分词: produced 现在分词: producing 第三人称单数: produces');
