INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('conserve', '[kən\'sɜːrv]', 'n.蜜饯；果酱 v.保存；保持；节省；用糖保存', '1. This is a recipe for strawberry conserve. 这是制作草莓酱的食谱。 2. I was surprised to find that the strong man liked to eat conserves. 我很惊讶地发现这个强壮的男人喜欢吃蜜饯。 3. This is a recipe for strawberry conserve. 这是制作草莓酱的食谱。 4. We must learn to conserve what remains. 我们必须学会保存那些剩余的资源。', '形容词: conservable 名词: conserver 过去式: conserved 过去分词: conserved 现在分词: conserving 第三人称单数: conserves');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ligneous', '[\'lɪgnɪəs]', 'adj.木质的；木头的', '1. Does B exceed can you take a ligneous thing? 超能照出木质的东西吗？ 2. Description: Evergreen, ligneous, large lianas; stems twisted. 形态特徵：常绿、木质藤本；茎扭旋。 3. Stems twining, 2-4 cm, much branched, striate, glabrous, ligneous at base. 缠绕的茎，2-4厘米，多分枝，具条纹，无毛，木质在基部。 4. Reoccupy white porcelain, or simple ligneous knob does shake handshandle. 再用白瓷、或简单的木制旋钮做拉手。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tractability', '[ˌtræktə\'bɪləti]', 'n.驯良；温顺；易处理', '1. The issue of organizational size is important to fulfill both educational objectives and provide tractability in the project. 组织大小的议题重要实现两者的教育目的而且提供计画的驯良。 2. His intelligence, tractability, and eager disposition make him an agreeable companion and willing worker. 他的智慧，温顺易训，和热衷于被支配工作，使它可以成为一个很适合的工作伙伴和乐于配合的工作者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('testator', '[tes\'teɪtə]', 'n.立遗嘱者', '1. A will needs the signature of the testator and two witnesses. 一份遗嘱需要立遗嘱人和两个证人签字. 2. A testator may revoke or alter a will he previously made. 遗嘱人可以撤销、变更自己所立的遗嘱。 3. A will is revoked by the subsequent marriage of the testator. 遗嘱人的再次结婚将导致(结婚前所立)遗嘱的无效。 4. The testator must have the mental capacity and be free of mental disorder. 立遗嘱人必须有思维能力', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('obstacle', '[\'ɑːbstəkl]', 'n.障碍；绊脚石', '1. Lack of education is an obstacle of success. 缺乏教育是成功的障碍。 2. This is the chief obstacle to world peace. 这是世界和平的主要障碍。 3. He took every obstacle in his stride. 他轻易地度过一切难关。 4. Overstaffing has become the obstacle for reforms. 人浮于事已成为改革的绊脚石。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('divest', '[daɪ\'vest]', 'v.剥除；脱去；剥夺；摆脱', '1. It is an interesting question how far men will retain their relative rank if they were divest of their clothes. 假使剥去了人们的衣服的话，到底彼此的阶级能够维持到什么程度，倒是一则有趣的问题。 2. He cannot divest himself of this idea. 他不能抛弃他的这个想法。', '名词: divestment 过去式: divested 过去分词: divested 现在分词: divesting 第三人称单数: divests');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tear', '[ter]', 'vt.撕掉；扯下；扰乱 vi.流泪；撕破 n.眼泪；（撕破的）洞或裂缝；撕扯', '1. Take the book from Alice, she will tear it. 把书从艾丽斯那拿开，她会撕了它的。 2. Nails that project may tear your clothes. 突出的钉子会刮坏你的衣服。 3. Her heart was torn by anxiety. 她焦虑得心都快碎了。 4. Don began to tear up when he talked about his son. 唐谈论起他的儿子就开始哭。 5. My wife burst into tears when she heard the bad news. 我太太听到这个坏消息就哭了起来。', '名词: tearer 过去式: tore 过去分词: torn 现在分词: tearing 第三人称单数: tears');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reparable', '[\'repərəbəl]', 'adj.能补救的；可挽回的', '1. We can hope the damage is reparable. 但这点损伤，我们还是可以有望弥补的。 2. Reparable damage to the car;reparable wrongs. 对汽车造成可修理的损害; 3. The woman work seven o\'clock.The man repar the car a quater past five.The girl study portuguese nine thirty-five. 提供六个人的活动时间： 一个女人、一个男人、一个女孩、一个男孩、你和我。 4. Her mistakes looked easily reparable in the light of her restored self-confidence. 她恢复了自信心以后,所犯的错误似乎也并非不可补救了。', '副词: reparably 名词: reparability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('custodian', '[kʌ\'stoʊdiən]', 'n.管理人；保管人；监护人', '1. The custodian of the fund will cash the replenishment check at the bank and place the cash in the petty cash box. 备用金保管人到银行将这张补充支票兑成现金并存放到零用现金箱中。 2. During the period of continued existence of a trust plan, the trust company shall choose a commercial bank with sound and stable operation performance to act as the custodian. 信托计划存续期间，信托公司应当选择经营稳健的商业银行担任保管人。 3. A custodian or trustee is appointed to oversee the debtor\'s property to protect it from loss. 指定一位监护人或管理人来监管债务人的财产免受损失。', '名词: custodianship');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('genre', '[\'ʒɑːnrə]', 'n.类型；流派', '1. My favorite music genre is blues. 我最喜欢的音乐种类是蓝调。 2. What genre does the movie fall into---comedy or tragedy? 这部电影是什么风格?喜剧还是悲剧? 3. Later musicians created works based on this genre. 后来乐工也模仿创作曲子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reconnoiter', '[ˌrekə\'nɔɪtə]', 'v.侦察；勘查；勘测', '1. It seems wise to reconnoiter before entering the town. 在进入那城以前，先侦察一下是明智的。 2. Malicious users can use this information to reconnoiter the naming schema in your organization and attack key infrastructure services. 恶意用户可以使用这个信息来侦察您的组织机构的名计划，并攻击关键基本设施服务。', '名词: reconnoiterer 过去式: reconnoitered 过去分词: reconnoitered 现在分词: reconnoitering 第三人称单数: reconnoiters');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ethnology', '[eθ\'nɑːlədʒi]', 'n.人种学；社会人类学', '1. Dr. Henderson is a famous expert on Asian ethnology. 汉德森博士是著名的亚洲民族学专家。 2. Ethnology has been variously defined in different national traditions. 由于不同的民族传统，民族学有着各种不同的定义。 3. It is a conclusion of deep importance in ethnology. 这个结论在人类学上是极端重要的。', '形容词: ethnologic 副词: ethnologically 名词: ethnologist');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incise', '[ɪn\'saɪz]', 'vt.切入；切割；雕刻', '1. We need make a incise estimate in addavance. 我们需要事先作出准确的估计。 2. To mark, incise, or cover with a line or lines. 画线用线标记、雕刻或画线于 3. Incise the superficial and deep fasciae. 切开浅、深筋膜。 4. Flexible and sharp, it can incise, expose, exenterate and heal. 它灵活多变又清晰明确，能雕刻、能揭露、能清洁、能治愈。', '过去式: incised 过去分词: incised 现在分词: incising 第三人称单数: incises');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('homily', '[\'hɑːməli]', 'n.训诫；说教', '1. She delivered a homily on the virtues of family life. 她进行了一场家庭生活美德方面的说教。', '名词: homilist 名词复数: homilies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('buxom', '[\'bʌksəm]', 'adj.(妇女)丰满的；有健康美的；屈服的；<古>愉快的', '1. The lady on the right is a little more buxom. 右边的那位女士长得略微丰满标致一些。 2. A generation ago buxom actresses were popular. 一代人以前丰满的女演员很受欢迎。 3. The chief operator was a buxom lady of forty or so with a heavy Southern accent. 总接线员是个四十岁左右，南方口音很重的长得丰满的女人。', '副词: buxomly 名词: buxomness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('virulent', '[\'vɪrələnt]', 'adj.有毒的；有恶意的；充满敌意的', '1. This virus was both lethal and virulent. 这种病毒不但致死率高，而且毒性极强。 2. Most virulent opposition came from the Irish Americans. 最恶意的反对来自爱尔兰裔美国人。 3. I stood up for her despite the virulent criticism. 尽管她遭到恶毒的批评，我还是维护她。', '副词: virulently 名词: virulence');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('calipers', '[\'kæləpɜːz]', 'n.弯脚器；测径器；卡尺 名词caliper的复数形式.', '1. A master list of calibrated equipment was found, but it did not cover colorimeter, sclerometer, vernier caliper and micrometer calipers. 被技工校准过的设备的名单已经找到,但其中并不包含色度计、硬度计、游标卡钳和千分尺测径器。 2. Simply standard measurement tools like micrometers or calipers may not require this indepth strategy and planning. 简单的标准测量工具如千分尺、卡尺可能不需要这样浓度的战略和计划。 3. This kind of sensors has been used in the electronic digital calipers with liquid resistant function and it works normally under water and coolant. 这种传感器已经成功地应用于新型防水电子数显卡尺中，可以在具有切削液条件的环境下正常工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('infer', '[ɪn\'fɜːr]', 'vt.推断；猜测；暗示 vi.作出推论', '1. We can infer the meaning of the word in the context. 我们可以从上下文中推断这个词的含义。 2. They infer a conclusion from the facts. 他们从事实中推断出结论。 3. I infer that my proposal has been accepted. 我推测我的建议已被接受。 4. Ragged clothing infers poverty. 衣衫褴褛意味着贫困。 5. We can infer from his expression that he is frustrated. 我们可以从他的表情中推断出他很沮丧。', '形容词: inferable 副词: inferably 名词: inferrer 过去式: inferred 过去分词: inferred 现在分词: inferring 第三人称单数: infers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flatcar', '[\'flætkɑːr]', 'n.平台型铁路货车', '1. He curls up in a flatcar and watches the sky. 他在一节平板车上蜷作一团、望着夜空。 2. It can undertake the overhaul of many types of train, such as self-tipping train torpedo train, N17 flatcar sand &stone carriage. 设施完备，技术力量强，主要承接机车解体大修用铁路自翻车、铁水车、N17平车、砂石车的大修及上车制造业务。 3. With double trailing arms and 12 shafts, the 20m long flatcar was perfect for carrying giant equipment. 该平板双纵12轴，平板长20米，非常适合装载。 4. Computer vehicle 6, DY vehicle 120, high vehicle 10, flatcar 45, Huang Jiaoji 2, crepe rubber machine 2. 电脑车6台，DY车120台，高车10台，平车45台，电脑切纸机1台，啤机2台，黄胶机2台，白胶机2台。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tract', '[trækt]', 'n.大片土地；器官系统；[解]道；束 n.小册子', '1. He owns a large tract of forest. 他拥有一大片森林。 2. He took many photos of the wide tracts of desert in North Africa. 他拍了许多关于北非的广大沙漠的照片。 3. Osteoporosis is a late complication of digestive tract disease. 骨质疏松症是消化道疾病的晚期并发症之一。 4. He had an infection in the upper respiratory tract. 他上呼吸道感染。 5. He wrote all the campaign tracts. 这些竞选传单全是他写的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('adage', '[\'ædɪdʒ]', 'n.格言；谚语；古话', '1. The adage really enlightened me since my youth. 这句格言从我青年时代起就给了我真正的启示。 2. Nearly 150 years later, variations of this adage are still quoted. 差不多在150年之后，这个变化了的谚语一直被引用。 3. But the old adage that men grow into office has not proved true in my experience. 但是，根据我的经验，人们所谓的工作岗位造就人材这句古话并不正确。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('puberty', '[\'pjuːbərti]', 'n.【U】青春期；春情发动期', '1. A boy\'s voice cracks at puberty. 男孩在青春期嗓音改变. 2. Everyone has attitudinal issues during his puberty. 每个人在青春期时都会有态度上的问题。 3. The beautiful girl just arrived at puberty. 这个美丽的姑娘情窦初开。', '形容词: pubertal');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hostility', '[hɑː\'stɪləti]', 'n.敌意；敌对状态；公开战争', '1. I feel no hostility towards anyone. 我对任何人均无敌意。 2. There is open hostility between the two leaders. 两位领导人表现出公开的敌意。 3. We should turn hostility into friendship. 我们应该化干戈为玉帛。 4. Gay men and lesbians say there is less overt hostility than in the west and certainly less physical harassment. 男女同性恋者表示，在中国绝少存在西方那种公开的敌意，也的确少有肉体上的骚扰。', '名词复数: hostilities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('indolent', '[\'ɪndələnt]', 'adj.懒惰的；慢性的', '1. I don\'t want to make friends with indolent persons. 我不喜欢和懒惰的人交朋友。 2. Those who revel in the Internet tend to lead an indolent life. 沉迷于网络的人往往过着懒散的生活。 3. Leprosy is an indolent infectious disease. 麻风病是一种顽固的传染性疾病。 4. Indolent lymphoma can have a very long duration often without the need for treatment but is not often cured. 慢性淋巴瘤通常发展期漫长并且不需要治疗，但是通常也难以治愈。', '副词: indolently');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('patronize', '[\'peɪtrənaɪz]', 'vt.以高人一等的态度对待；经常光顾；资助', '1. He resented the way she patronized him. 她待他那种屈尊纡贵的样子，他十分愤恨。 2. Some television programmes tend to patronize children. 有些电视节目往往以大人的观点对待儿童。 3. I\'ll never patronize that store again. 我再也不去光顾那家商店了。 4. The restaurant is patronized by politicians and journalists. 这家饭馆常有政治家和记者光顾。', '副词: patronizingly 名词: patronization 过去式: patronized 过去分词: patronized 现在分词: patronizing 第三人称单数: patronizes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gangrene', '[\'ɡæŋɡriːn]', 'n.坏疽；脱疽；腐败堕落的根源 v.生坏疽；腐败；使生坏疽', '1. When gangrene set in,his foot had to be amputated. 他的脚生了坏疽', '形容词: gangrenous 过去式: gangrened 过去分词: gangrened 现在分词: gangrening 第三人称单数: gangrenes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('laminate', '[\'læmɪnət]', 'vi.切成薄板 vt.把...制成薄板 n.薄板制品', '1. On all cars, a windshield of laminated glass is compulsory. 夹心的挡风玻璃是强制使用在所有车辆上的。', '名词: laminator 过去式: laminated 过去分词: laminated 现在分词: laminating 第三人称单数: laminates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('four-poster', '[\'fɔːrp\'əʊstər]', 'n.有四柱的床', '1. The style is four columns, three gates, three brims, five water dypasses in this wooden-like stone archway. 该坊形制为四柱三门三重檐五滴水仿木青石雕花牌坊。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('jaundiced', '[\'dʒɔːndɪst]', 'adj.患黄疸病的；有偏见的；嫉妒的', '1. She saw him now with jaundiced eyes, and told herself that at last she had discovered his true colours. 如今她以偏见的眼光打量他,并对自己说她终于发现了他的真实面目。 2. She spoke with a jaundiced tone. 原文:她说话带着一点醋意。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('blockage', '[\'blɑːkɪdʒ]', 'n.封锁；障碍；[医]阻塞', '1. If the blockage worked, they could retreat with dignity. 如果封锁发生作用，他们可以体面地撤退。 2. The interview clears lines of communication of emotional blockage. 访谈可以消除情感交流渠道上的障碍。 3. People can also calles cause a blockage when they try to clean up out their ears . 当人们试着清洁他们的耳朵也可能会引起障碍。 4. A blockage in the arteries could be very dangerous. 动脉阻塞是很危险的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('icing', '[\'aɪsɪŋ]', 'n.(糕饼表层的)糖衣 动词ice的现在分词形式.', '1. I wanted to frost the cake with icing. 我想给蛋糕上撒一层糖霜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bard', '[bɑːrd]', 'n.吟游诗人；诗人', '1. I\'ll use my bard song to help you concentrate! 我会用我的吟游诗人歌曲帮你集中精神! 2. A sorrowful bard tells a tale of his imprisoned comrades. 一个悲伤的吟游诗人讲述了一个关于他被囚禁的战友的故事。', '形容词: bardic 过去式: barded 过去分词: barded 现在分词: barding 第三人称单数: bards');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('limb', '[lɪm]', 'n.肢体；枝干；树枝 vt.肢解', '1. Men and women have four limbs; two arms and two legs. 人都有四肢，两只胳膊两条腿。 2. He stood up and stretched his limbs. 他站起来,伸了伸胳膊和腿。 3. A grey squirrel is scampering from limb to limb. 一只灰色的松鼠在树枝间跳来跳去。 4. The workers saw off a limb from the tree. 工人从树上锯下了一根大树枝。', '过去式: limbed 过去分词: limbed 现在分词: limbing 第三人称单数: limbs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('maze', '[meɪz]', 'n.迷宫；曲径；迷惑 vt.使迷惑', '1. We were lost in the maze for several hours. 我们在迷宫里兜了好几个小时出不来。 2. I twisted through a maze of narrow corridors. 我弯弯曲曲地穿行迷宫式的狭窄走廊。 3. The psychologist raced the rats through a long maze. 经过长时间的迷惑心理学家揭穿胡言蜚语。', '过去式: mazed 过去分词: mazed 现在分词: mazing 第三人称单数: mazes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wrangle', '[\'ræŋɡl]', 'v.争论；吵架 n.争吵', '1. The children wrangle about who should sit in front. 孩子们为了谁该坐在前面而争吵。 2. He will give in to his opponent\'s claim rather than wrangle over a disputed point. 他会向对手的要求让步，而不会因争议点而大声争论。 3. The children were wrangling over the new toy. 孩子们为新玩具争吵。 4. Tell the boys of playing there not to wrangle. 告诉在那儿玩的男孩子们不要吵闹。 5. They are hand in hand, without wrangle. 他们手拉手，不吵也不闹。', '过去式: wrangled 过去分词: wrangled 现在分词: wrangling 第三人称单数: wrangles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bail', '[beɪl]', 'n.保释；杓；把手；保证金；担保人 vt.保释；往外舀水；使摆脱困境 vi.舀空', '1. Bail was refused on the presupposition of his guilt. 已料到他罪名成立而不准保释。 2. He repudiated the court\'s decision to offer bail. 他不接受法庭的保释裁决。 3. The magistrate refused his bail. 地方法官不准他保释。 4. She was granted bail with a surety of $500. 她交了500元保证金，获得保释。 5. Bail out a person committed to prison. 把一个在押的人保释出来。 6. The boat will sink unless we bail out. 我们要不把积水清除掉，船就要沉了。', '名词: bailer 过去式: bailed 过去分词: bailed 现在分词: bailing 第三人称单数: bails');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('detergent', '[dɪ\'tɜːrdʒənt]', 'n.清洁剂 adj.用于清洗的', '1. No detergent can shift these stains. 任何清洁剂都不能除掉这些污迹。 2. I\'ve tried this new detergent with excellent results. 我试用了这种新型洗涤剂，效果很好。 3. We only use detergent liquids in our restaurant. 我们只在饭店用清洁剂。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('intermittent', '[ˌɪntər\'mɪtənt]', 'adj.间歇的；断断续续的', '1. They saw the intermittent flashes from a lighthouse. 他们看见了灯塔发出一闪一灭的光。 2. He has intermittent bursts of interest. 他的兴趣是一阵阵的。 3. She suffered from intermittent headache. 她患间歇性头痛。 4. There was intermittent debate about. 有过断断续续的辩论。', '副词: intermittently 名词: intermittence');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('clam', '[klæm]', 'n.蛤；沉默寡言的人 vi.保持沉默；挖蚌', '1. Yup! I also like clam soup and sea cucumbers. 对呀！我还喜欢蛤仔汤和海参。 2. Everybody shut up like a clam as soon as you mention it. 你一提及此事，大家便都闭口不言 3. He is a clam about his business dealing. 他对自己的生意买卖守口如瓶。 4. It started off well, but he seemed to clam up towards the end. 刚开始很，但是最后他似乎有些沉默。', '名词: clammer 过去式: clammed 过去分词: clammed 现在分词: clamming 第三人称单数: clams');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('plangent', '[\'plændʒənt]', 'adj.轰鸣的；悲哀的', '1. Today\'s world, a lot of places left already sprinkler and farm cattle, leaving even plangent machine times. 今天的世界,许多地方早已离别了水车和耕牛,甚至正在离别轰鸣的机器时代。', '副词: plangently 名词: plangency');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scurrilous', '[\'skɜːrələs]', 'adj.说话粗鄙恶劣的；无礼的；下流的；恶言诽谤的', '1. She is often quite scurrilous in her reference to me. 她一提起我，常常骂骂咧咧的。 2. Her scurrilous performances have already condemned her. 她的信口漫骂的演出已给她定了罪。 3. The hoodlums defiled the church with their scurrilous writing. 这群无赖写了许多庸俗下流的东西,玷污了这座教堂。 4. I shall not reply to such a scurrilous attack upon me. 对我的毁谤性攻击，我将不予以回驳。', '副词: scurrilously 名词: scurrilousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('kidnap', '[\'kɪdnæp]', 'v.绑架', '1. Police have uncovered a plot to kidnap the President\'s son. 警方已侦破一起绑架总统之子的阴谋。 2. If you improve security at embassies, they kidnap businessmen. 如果你加强了大使馆的安全防范，他们就绑架商人。', '名词: kidnapper 过去式: kidnapped/kidnaped 过去分词: kidnapped/kidnaped 现在分词: kidnapping/kidnaping 第三人称单数: kidnaps/kidnaps');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dejected', '[dɪ\'dʒektɪd]', 'adj.沮丧的；灰心的 动词deject的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. Repeated failure had left them feeling very dejected. 他们三番五次失败后情绪非常低落。 2. He was dejected to learn that he had failed the examination. 得知考试不及格,他便垂头丧气。', '副词: dejectedly 名词: dejectedness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('typographical', '[ˌtaɪpə\'ɡræfɪkl]', 'adj.排字上的；印刷上的 =typographic.', '1. My primary frustration with this book is the many typographical errors. 我最感失望的是，本书有许多的印刷/排版错误。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('coagulate', '[koʊ\'æɡjuleɪt]', 'v. 凝结； 凝固 adj. <古> 凝结的； 凝固的', '1. An enzyme that occurs in gastric juice causes milk to coagulate. 胃液中的一种酶能使乳类凝结。 2. In extreme polarity, dreams coagulate into thought-form that is resonant. 在极端极性中，梦想凝结成共振的思想形态。 3. Blood began to coagulate around the edges of the wound. 血液开始在伤口的边缘凝固。 4. The production of cheese requires the use of enzymes to coagulate or curdle the milk and the addition of other ingredients for various functions. 生产乳酪要求使用酶凝结或凝固牛奶，还要添加其他用于不同功效的原料。', '形容词: coagulable 名词: coagulability 过去式: coagulated 过去分词: coagulated 现在分词: coagulating 第三人称单数: coagulates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unilateral', '[ˌjuːnɪ\'lætrəl]', 'adj.单方面的；单边的；单系的', '1. They cancelled the contract unilateral. 他们单方面地取消了该合同。 2. They were forced to take unilateral action. 他们被迫采取单方面行动。 3. As the sole military superpower, the United States may often be able to undertake unilateral initiatives for the sake of national security. 作为一个唯一的军事超级大国，美国常常可以出于国家安全考虑去推行各种单边的倡议。 4. The unilateral total adrenalectomy was suggested. 手术方法是一侧肾上腺全切除。', '副词: unilaterally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('negotiate', '[nɪ\'ɡoʊʃieɪt]', 'vi.谈判；协商；交涉 vt.谈判达成；成功越过；议价出售', '1. We\'ve decided to negotiate with the employers about our wage claim. 我们决定就工资问题与雇主谈判。 2. We are happy to negotiate with you in that way. 我们很高兴用这种方式来和贵方协商交易。 3. Trade union leaders went back to negotiate with the government. 工会领导回去和政府进行交涉。 4. Since our contract is near its term we must negotiate a new one. 由于我们的合同快到期了，我们必须谈判新的合约。', '形容词: negotiatory 名词: negotiator 过去式: negotiated 过去分词: negotiated 现在分词: negotiating 第三人称单数: negotiates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('annotate', '[\'ænəteɪt]', 'v.注解', '1. As an option, you can annotate recorded movies with text. 如一项选择，你能够以文本给被记载的电影作注解。 2. I might want to go back and annotate this document with metadata specific to its production. 我可能希望返回去并使用针对其研究成果的元数据注解该文档。', '形容词: annotative 名词: annotator 过去式: annotated 过去分词: annotated 现在分词: annotating 第三人称单数: annotates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lofty', '[\'lɔːfti]', 'adj.高的；崇高的；高尚的；傲慢的', '1. There are lofty fells behind this village. 这个村庄后面是高高的荒山。 2. Longer shadow falls from lofty mountain. 山高投影长。 3. They saw the lofty peak in all its majesty. 他们看到了高耸的山峰，气势雄伟壮丽。 4. He has lent his name to the lofty cause. 他以自己的名义支持这一崇高的事业。', '副词: loftily 比较级: loftier 最高级: loftiest 名词: loftiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lesion', '[\'liːʒn]', 'n.损害；损伤；障碍', '1. This lesion can be lessened by surgical correction. 这种损害可通过外科矫治减弱。 2. I got a neuroanatomic lesion affecting my reticular activating system. 我有神经管能上的损伤，影响了我的网状活化系统。 3. Conclusions Hepatic sinusoidal and Disse\'s space lesion may play an important role in the liver microcirculation disturbance of CHB. 结论肝窦及窦周隙病变在肝微循环障碍中担当关键角色。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('multiply', '[\'mʌltɪplaɪ]', 'vt.乘；增加 vi.做乘法；繁衍 adv.多样地；多重地', '1. If you multiply four by five, the answer is twenty. 四乘以五,答案是二十。 2. Let us multiply the height by the width to determine the area. 用宽乘以高来确定面积。 3. This will multiply our chances of success. 这将增加我们成功的机会。 4. He managed to multiply his profits. 他成功地增加了利润。 5. He learned to multiply at the age of five. 他五岁学会做乘法。', '过去式: multiplied 过去分词: multiplied 现在分词: multiplying 第三人称单数: multiplies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('perennial', '[pə\'reniəl]', 'adj.永久的；反复出现的；多年生的 n.多年生植物', '1. Politics provides a perennial subject for argument. 政治是一种长期争论不休的话题。 2. Our perennial problem is not having enough money. 长期困扰我们的问题就是缺钱。 3. The dandelion is a perennial plant. 该蒲公英是一种多年生的植物。 4. A galaxy is an evergreen perennial. 加莱克斯草是一种多年生常绿植物。', '副词: perennially');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lithe', '[laɪð]', 'adj.柔软的；易弯的；轻盈的', '1. Little babies have lithe bodies. 小孩有柔软的身体。 2. A lithe willow is waggling back and forth by the wind. 易弯曲的柳树因为风的吹拂而不停摇摆。 3. Her movements in free gymnastics are lithe and graceful. 她的自由体操动作轻盈优美。', '副词: lithely 比较级: lither 最高级: lithest 名词: litheness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('complicity', '[kəm\'plɪsəti]', 'n.串通；共谋', '1. She did not suspect him of complicity with the authorities. 她没怀疑他会与当局串通。 2. He denied complicity in the murder. 他否认自己曾参与谋杀。 3. He was suspected of complicity in her murder. 他涉嫌合谋将她杀害。', '名词复数: complicities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('contest', '[\'kɑːntest]', 'n.竞赛；比赛 vt.驳斥；争取 vi.奋斗', '1. She won a gold medal for her fine performance in the contest. 她在竞赛中成绩优异获金牌。 2. This football match is an unequal contest. 这场足球赛是一场实力悬殊的比赛。 3. Janet said she is thinking about attending a KTV contest. 珍妮说她正考虑参加一个KTV歌唱比赛。 4. I intend to contest the judge\'s decision in another court. 我准备下次开庭时反驳法官的判决。', '形容词: contestable 名词: contestation 过去式: contested 过去分词: contested 现在分词: contesting 第三人称单数: contests');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('confiscate', '[\'kɒnfɪsˌkeɪt]', 'v.没收；充公', '1. We\'ll have to confiscate this object. 我们要没收这些物品。 2. The present policy of our Party is still to reduce rents, not to confiscate land. 目前我党方针，仍然是减租而不是没收土地。', '形容词: confiscatory 名词: confiscation 过去式: confiscated 过去分词: confiscated 现在分词: confiscating 第三人称单数: confiscates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('alternate', '[\'ɔːltərnət]', 'v.交替；轮流 adj.间隔的；轮流的；交替的 n.代替者；供替代的选择', '1. Sunny weather alternated with rain. 天气晴雨相间。 2. One should alternate work and relaxation. 工作和休息应交替进行。 3. We alternate in cleaning the room. 我们轮流打扫房间。 4. Meetings are held on alternate Thursdays. 每隔一个星期的星期四举行一次会议。 5. My alternate knows my role really well, she\'s almost better than me. 我的接替者对我的工作非常了解，她甚至比我都好。', '副词: alternately 名词: alternateness 过去式: alternated 过去分词: alternated 现在分词: alternating 第三人称单数: alternates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('duration', '[du\'reɪʃn]', 'n.持续时间；期间', '1. The duration of the movie is 110 minutes. 这部电影的持续时间是110分钟。 2. He finished the work of three years\' duration. 他用三年的时间完成了这项工作。 3. The duration of marriage is related most obviously to the expectation of life. 很明显，婚姻生活的持续时间与人的预期寿命有关。 4. Well, I\'m stuck here for the duration. 哎，这段时间我只得呆在这儿了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('attainment', '[ə\'teɪnmənt]', 'n.达到；获得 （常复数）attainments:成就； 才能； 学识.', '1. He was far from the attainment of this object. 他远未达到自己的目标。 2. Thatwill help lead you to the attainment of your goals. 那会有助于你达到目标。 3. The attainment of wealth did not make her happy. 获得财富并没有使她幸福。 4. You may well have to forego wealth and power if you want to assure the attainment of happiness and freedom. 如果你想要确保快乐与自由的获得，你可就得放开财富与权力。 5. Prof. Thomson is one scholar of the highest attainment. 汤姆生教授是一位学识渊博的学者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('benevolent', '[bə\'nevələnt]', 'adj.仁慈的；乐善好施的', '1. The original designers of the human body were benevolent beings. 人类身体的最初设计者是仁慈的生命体。 2. His benevolent nature prevented him from refusing any beggar who accosted him. 他生性仁慈的，对任何一个向他乞讨的乞丐都慷慨解囊。 3. But can some EU members continue to treat Russia as a benevolent ally? 但是，是否一些欧盟成员国仍可以把俄罗斯当作是一个乐善好施的盟友？ 4. A benevolent employer has a sincere interest in the welfare of his employees. 一个乐善好施的老板对于做好自己员工的福利待遇是真心实意的。', '副词: benevolently');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('calumny', '[\'kæləmni]', 'n.诽谤；中伤', '1. Calumny is answered best with silence. 沉默可以止谤。 2. No flame rise without smoke, no fame without calumny. 无烟不起火，无毁不成名。 3. Calumny, even from the mouth of a fool, will sometimes cut into unguarded feelings. 即使出自一个傻瓜之口的诽谤，有时候也会突然刺伤一个没有防备的人的感情。 4. Your calumny against the great is impious. 你对伟人的中伤有失虔敬。', '名词复数: calumnies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('enhance', '[ɪn\'hæns]', 'vt.提高；增加；加强', '1. He made many efforts to enhance his reputation. 他做了许多努力来提高他的声誉。 2. Martial education is an important means to exercise volition and enhance national defense notion. 提出军事教育是锻炼意志,提高国防观念的重要手段。 3. This year, we will review the functions and other aspects of District Councils and enhance our support for them. 今年将展开对区议会功能等方面的检讨,增加对区议会的支持。 4. The programme aims to enhance the employment of young people with disabilities or early signs of mental illness. 计划的目的,是加强残疾或出现精神病早期徵状的青少年的就业能力。', '形容词: enhancive 名词: enhancement 过去式: enhanced 过去分词: enhanced 现在分词: enhancing 第三人称单数: enhances');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('trance', '[træns]', 'n.【C】昏睡状态；恍惚；出神；发呆', '1. She put her son into a trance. 她使她的儿子进入昏睡状态。 2. He didn\'t answer when I spoke - he seemed to be in a trance. 我说话他没有答理---他像是陷入昏睡状态。 3. He appeared as a man in a trance. 他显得神思恍惚。 4. The heavy feeling comes over me as I enter trance. 当我进入恍惚状态，我感到全身发沉。', '形容词: trancelike 过去式: tranced 过去分词: tranced 现在分词: trancing 第三人称单数: trances');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cession', '[\'seʃn]', 'n.割让；转让', '1. Third-party states have no title to object cession. 第三国无权反对割让。 2. The cession of the territory could not be avoided because they lost the war. 因为他们输了这场战争，割让领土是无法避免的。 3. The secondary market with direct cession cannot be efficient. 直接转让二级市场，效率是不高的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sabotage', '[\'sæbətɑːʒ]', 'n.怠工；破坏 vt.破坏', '1. Their sabotage put back production badly. 他们的怠工严重影响了生产。 2. The fire at the factory was caused by sabotage. 那家工厂的火灾是有人蓄意破坏引起的。 3. They are carrying out subversion,sabotage,intervention and aggression everywhere in the world. 他们在全世界到处进行颠覆，破坏，干涉和侵略。 4. They tried to sabotage my birthday party. 他们企图破坏我的生日晚会。', '过去式: sabotaged 过去分词: sabotaged 现在分词: sabotaging 第三人称单数: sabotages');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('impetus', '[\'ɪmpɪtəs]', 'n.推动力；刺激', '1. His articles provided the main impetus for change. 他的那些文章是促进变革的主要推动力。 2. The present conflict may provide fresh impetus for peace talk. 目前的冲突可能会给和谈提供新的推动力。 3. Her speech gave an impetus to my ideas. 她的讲话激发了我的思绪。 4. His articles provided the main impetus for change. 他的那些文章是促进变革的主要推动力。', '名词复数: impetuses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('negation', '[nɪ\'ɡeɪʃn]', 'n.对立面；否定；否认；反对；不存在', '1. This political system was the negation of democracy. 这种政治制度是对民主的否定。 2. She shook her head in negation. 她摇头表示拒绝。', '形容词: negational');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('archetype', '[\'ɑːkitaɪp]', 'n.原型', '1. That old engine is the archetype of modern locomotives. 那台老式发动机是近代机车的原型。', '形容词: archetypal 副词: archetypically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('exclude', '[ɪk\'skluːd]', 'vt.排除；阻止；拒绝接受', '1. At this stage we cannot entirely exclude the possibility of staff cuts. 在目前这个阶段,我们还不能完全排除裁员的可能性。 2. I mean the last thing we would think about is to exclude the children from this plan. 我的意思是,我们绝不会考虑把孩子们排除在这个计划之外的。 3. Thick curtains help to exclude street noises. 厚窗帘有助于隔绝街上的噪音。 4. The court excluded the improperly obtained evidence. 法院不接受非正常渠道获得的证据', '形容词: excludable 名词: excludability 过去式: excluded 过去分词: excluded 现在分词: excluding 第三人称单数: excludes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nude', '[nuːd]', 'adj.（尤指艺术人像）裸的；与生俱有的；无装饰的 n.裸体画、裸体人像（尤指绘画、摄影等）', '1. Are there any nude scenes in the movie? 电影里有裸体镜头吗? 2. Early Greek art represented Aphrodite as an oriental,nude goddess type. 早期的希腊艺术中，阿佛洛狄特被表现为裸体的东方美神。 3. I\'ve got two or three things in hand just now. There\'s a rather splendid nude, actually. 目前我手头上有那么两三幅。其实，还有一幅顶呱呱的裸体画呢。', '副词: nudely 比较级: nuder 最高级: nudest 名词: nudity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('personnel', '[ˌpɜːrsə\'nel]', 'n.职员；人事部门', '1. The personnel are not happy to change these rules. 全体工作人员对改变这些规定很不高兴。 2. The company\'s main problem is the shortage of skilled personnel. 这家公司的主要问题是缺少有技术的人员。 3. Army personnel are often forbidden to fraternize with the civilian population. 军职人员常被禁止与平民百姓友好往来。 4. Personnel is organizing the training of the new menbers of staff. 人事部门正在组织新雇员的培训。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pregnant', '[\'preɡnənt]', 'adj.怀孕的；充满的；意味深长的', '1. How long has she been pregnant? 她怀孕多久了？ 2. She got pregnant and was turned out of the house by her parents. 她怀孕了，父母把她赶出了家门。 3. Women who do not ovulate regularly have difficulty in becoming pregnant. 妇女排卵期不正常就不易受孕。 4. He is a man pregnant with ideas. 他是一个思想丰富的人。', '副词: pregnantly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('extraneous', '[ɪk\'streɪniəs]', 'adj.外来的；无关的', '1. Reductant from an extraneous source is introduced. 外来的还原剂被引进来。 2. Because of the extraneous and uncontrolled factors, those may affect the dependent variable. 由于许多外来的无法控制的因素，这些因素可能影响应变因素。 3. The only extraneous item I may carry is a gift. 我带的唯一与旅行无关的物件是礼物。 4. Extraneous null statements are not always harmless. 无关的空语句并非总是无害的。', '副词: extraneously 名词: extraneousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('certitude', '[\'sɜːrtɪtuːd]', 'n.确实；确信', '1. He felt a wild desire to run after them, a certitude that he could run them down. 他有股发狂的冲动去追赶它们，他确信自己能追上。 2. \'You will like Rome,\' he said, with absolute certitude. “你会喜欢罗马的。”他深信不疑地说道。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('erudite', '[\'erudaɪt]', 'adj.博学的', '1. The lecture was not very erudite. 这次演讲的内容不很精深广博。 2. He likes to talk with erudite people. 他喜欢和学识宏达的人交往。 3. The unlearned always pretend to be erudite. 不学无术的人总是伪装知识渊博。', '副词: eruditely 名词: eruditeness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('muscle', '[\'mʌsl]', 'n.肌肉 v.硬挤；变硬实', '1. He strained his muscle in the match. 他在那次比赛中拉伤了肌肉。 2. The contraction of muscle is a reaction of the body. 肌肉的收缩是人体的一种反应。 3. He tried to muscle into the club. 他企图强行加入那个俱乐部。 4. Our competitors have been trying to muscle in for some years . 几年来，我们的竞争对手一直试图夺取利益。', '形容词: muscly 过去式: muscled 过去分词: muscled 现在分词: muscling 第三人称单数: muscles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sash', '[sæʃ]', 'n.饰带；肩带；腰带；窗框 v.系上腰带；装以窗框', '1. She girded her waist with a sash. 她以饰带束腰。 2. The officer wears sashes on his shoulders. 这名军官的肩上佩戴着肩带。 3. With this simple sash, you fend off attacks against your body. 有了这条简易的腰带，你便可以挡开对你身体的攻击。 4. Our windows have double-pane sashes. 我们的窗户有双层的玻璃窗框。', '过去式: sashed 过去分词: sashed 现在分词: sashing 第三人称单数: sashes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('malpractice', '[ˌmæl\'præktɪs]', 'n.失职；行为不当', '1. She sued her doctor for malpractice. 她控告她的医生失职。 2. Various malpractices by police officers were brought to light by the enquiry. 警察的各种不法行为经调查已揭露出来。', '名词: malpractitioner');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('litigation', '[ˌlɪtɪ\'ɡeɪʃn]', 'n.诉讼；起诉', '1. Some business disputes require litigation. 有些商业争端需提出诉讼。 2. Litigation often entails enormous expense. 诉讼通常是要花很多钱的。 3. We are pleased that the litigation has been resolved. 我们很高兴这个诉讼得到了解决。 4. These two methods share certain advantages over litigation. 这两种方法比诉讼有一定的优势。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bumble', '[\'bʌmbl]', 'v.说话含糊；语无伦次地说', '1. What are you bumbling about? 你颠三倒四地说些什麽呀?', '过去式: bumbled 过去分词: bumbled 现在分词: bumbling 第三人称单数: bumbles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('recoil', '[rɪ\'kɔɪl]', 'v.退却；畏缩；弹回；报应 n.畏缩；弹回；后坐力', '1. She recoiled at the sight of the snake. 她一见到蛇就往后缩。 2. You have to learn not to recoil from touching the insects. 你必须学会碰到昆虫而不退缩。 3. A gun recoils after being fired. 枪在射击后向后坐。 4. Plots sometimes recoil on the plotters. 阴谋有时会报应在阴谋者身上。 5. The pain of it made him recoil from the exuberance of holiday shoppers. 这痛苦使他在节日里兴高采烈的顾客面前显得有些畏缩。', '名词: recoiler 过去式: recoiled 过去分词: recoiled 现在分词: recoiling 第三人称单数: recoils');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('compete', '[kəm\'piːt]', 'v.竞争；比赛；对抗', '1. Companies must be able to compete in the marketplace. 公司一定要在市场中有竞争力。 2. Several companies are competing for the contract. 几家公司正为争取一项合同而互相竞争。 3. We can compete with the best teams. 我们能与最好的队竞争。 4. He\'s hoping to compete in the London marathon. 他期盼着参加伦敦马拉松比赛。', '过去式: competed 过去分词: competed 现在分词: competing 第三人称单数: competes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('projection', '[prə\'dʒekʃn]', 'n.投影；投射；规划；发射；凸出物；预测；放映', '1. The simplest form of projection is a perspective projection. 最简单的投影形式是透视投影。 2. Any real time objective aspect of the projection will then be lost. 投射的任何实时客观的方面就会消失。 3. Start your projection the same as outlined in Part 3. 按照本文第三部分的步骤开始投射。 4. The company\'s projection of their income was unrealistic. 公司对营利的规划不切实际。', '形容词: projectional');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('radical', '[\'rædɪkl]', 'adj.激进的；彻底的；基本的 n.激进分子', '1. I know you are radical in your thinking, but don\'t go too far. 我知道你思想激进,但不要走的太远。 2. He took up a radical position on this issue. 他对这个问题抱着激进的态度。 3. They called for a radical reform of our tax system. 他们要求对税收制度进行根本改革。 4. Lambert did not reach the more radical conclusion. 兰伯特还没有达到更本质的结论。 5. Ted is a fire-eating radical. 泰德是个咄咄逼人的激进份子。', '副词: radically 名词: radicalness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rile', '[raɪl]', 'v.激怒', '1. It riles me that he won\'t agree. 他就是不同意，真气人。 2. Instead of getting all riled up about this, we should try to figure out what to do. 与其因此发火,我们还不如想想该怎么办。 3. This won\'t be easy, because certain individuals seem determined to rile you up. 这不是件轻松的事，因为有人似乎存心让你生气。', '过去式: riled 过去分词: riled 现在分词: riling 第三人称单数: riles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hoodwink', '[\'hʊdwɪŋk]', 'v.欺骗；蒙骗；<古>隐瞒', '1. I was hoodwinked into buying fake jewels. 我受骗买了假珠宝。', '名词: hoodwinker 过去式: hoodwinked 过去分词: hoodwinked 现在分词: hoodwinking 第三人称单数: hoodwinks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('foreword', '[\'fɔːrwɜːrd]', 'n.前言；序', '1. The foreword of the book runs for six pages. 这本书的前言长达6页。 2. This paper consists of foreword and four chapters. 论文包括前言和四章正文。 3. That book has a preface, not a foreword. 那本书有序文,没有前言。 4. This book has a foreword by the President. 这本书有一篇总统作的序言。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('relent', '[rɪ\'lent]', 'v.变宽厚；变温和；动怜悯之心；缓和；（坏天气）变好', '1. At first she threatened to dismiss us all, but later she relented. 起初她威胁要解雇我们所有的人，但是后来她态度软化了。 2. The other students persuaded him to relent. 其他的学生劝说他要变得温和些。 3. The police will not relent in their fight against crime. 警方在跟犯罪分子的斗争中决不手软。 4. The pressure on us to finish this task will not relent. 我们为完成此项任务受到的压力不会减轻。', '过去式: relented 过去分词: relented 现在分词: relenting 第三人称单数: relents');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fraud', '[frɔːd]', 'n.欺骗；诈欺；骗子', '1. She was put on trial for fraud. 她因涉及诈骗罪而受审。 2. Investigation of fraud was their commission. 调查诈欺舞弊是他们的任务。 3. He told people that he was a serious and well-known musician, but he was actually a fraud. 他告诉人们说他是一个严肃的著名音乐家,实际上却是个骗子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('begrudge', '[bɪ\'ɡrʌdʒ]', 'v.嫉妒；羡慕；吝啬', '1. Nobody begrudges you your success. 没有人忌妒你的成功。 2. We should not begrudge our neighbour\'s richness. 我们不应该嫉妒邻人的富有。 3. I begrudge him his good fortune. 我羡慕他的运气好. 4. We don\'t begrudge your going to Italy. 我们并不羡慕你到意大利去。', '副词: begrudgingly 名词: begrudger 过去式: begrudged 过去分词: begrudged 现在分词: begrudging 第三人称单数: begrudges');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('curvaceous', '[kɜːr\'veɪʃəs]', 'adj.曲线美的；丰满而匀称的', '1. Girls who are attentive to their personal appearance want to be curvaceous. 爱美的女孩都希望自己拥有曲线美。 2. Hollywood seems full of curvaceous blondes. 好莱坞到处是身材正点的金发美女。', '副词: curvaceously 名词: curvaceousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('captious', '[\'kæpʃəs]', 'adj.吹毛求疵的；强词夺理的', '1. THERE IS NO CAPTIOUS CLIENT BUT FAULTY PRODUCT. 只有不完美的产品，没有挑剔的客户。 2. Beyond the mark captious chromatism, pursuit grain is consistent. 过分挑剔色差，追求纹理一致。 3. How to satisfy a net to buy customer people captious appetite? 如何满足网购消费者们挑剔的胃口？ 4. There is no captious client but faulty product and service. 没有挑剔的客户，只有不完善的产品和服务。', '副词: captiously 名词: captiousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rhapsody', '[\'ræpsədi]', 'n.狂言；狂文；[音]狂想曲', '1. The rhapsody reminds people of a vast plain. 这段狂想曲能令人联想到那辽阔的草原。', '名词复数: rhapsodies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unbend', '[ˌʌn\'bend]', 'v.伸直；解开；放松', '1. This kind of wire is easy to unbend. 这种金属线很容易弄直。 2. Right now, head, neck and back should up unbend. 此时，头、颈和背部应该向上伸直。 3. Most professors unbend outside the lecture theatre. 教授在课下大都很随便。 4. She was very formal at first, but then she unbent a little and told a joke. 她起先显得很正经，但后来变得随和些，还讲了个笑话。', '形容词: unbendable 过去式: unbent 过去分词: unbent 现在分词: unbending 第三人称单数: unbends');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ambrosial', '[æm\'broʊʒɪəl]', 'adj.美味佳肴的；芳香的；神的；适用于神的', '1. Ambro is important, his heading is formidable. 安布罗西尼对球队是重要的，他的头球非常棒。 2. Alberto, la monitoro, estas en la klasĉambro. 阿尔贝特班长在教室里。 3. Alberto, la monitoro estas en la klasĉambro. 阿尔贝特，班长在教室里。 4. Anyway, Ambro\'s goal was very important, we are closing in on fourth place. 总之，安布罗西尼的进球非常重要，我们正在靠近第四名。', '副词: ambrosially 异体字: ambrosian');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pomposity', '[pɒm\'pɒsəti]', 'n.自大；傲慢；炫耀', '1. The prince\'s manner was informal, without a trace of pomposity. 王子的态度平易谦和，没有一点傲气。 2. His remarks are full of pomposity. 他的话里充满炫耀。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('snappish', '[\'snæpɪʃ]', 'adj.脾气暴躁的；爱咬人的', '1. \"A whole nation of belligerent, snappish people?\" asked Nikolai. “一个全国好战的国家？急躁的人民？”尼可莱问。 2. Aggressive peoples who think they have a grievance, who think they\'re undervalued.Belligerent, snappish. 那些认为自己有冤屈的人民更有侵略性，他们认为自己被低估了，所以好战而且急躁。” 3. She wouldn\'t hear of it, denied that she was putting Louis in any greater danger than he already faced, turned decidedly snappish, and went off to bed. 这话她不肯听，她不承认她正在使路易斯陷入比他已经面临到的更大的危险，后来她变得十分急躁，于是走去睡了。 4. They might not send a thank-you after being treated to lunch, or they might send a snappish email that is more of a demand than a request. 在被邀请去吃午饭时他们不表达感谢，或者发送不是请求而是命令语气的粗暴的邮件。', '副词: snappishly 名词: snappishness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('altruism', '[\'æltruɪzəm]', 'n.利他主义；利他', '1. Anonymity is the truest expression of altruism. 不记名是利他主义最真的表现。 2. Altruism, according to the text books, has two forms. 根据书本上的解释，利他主义有两种表现形式。 3. His altruism won the neighbors\' respect. 他那利他的行为赢得了邻居的尊敬。 4. Ambitionthat is masked as altruism. 利他主义掩盖下的野心。', '形容词: altruistic 副词: altruistically 名词: altruist');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unearthly', '[ʌn\'ɜːrθli]', 'adj.怪异的；超自然的', '1. All of a sudden we heard an unearthly cry. 我们突然听到一声怪叫。 2. Who is calling me at this unearthly hour? 谁会在这种极不合适的时刻打电话给我呢? 3. The Grand Canyon is an unearthly sight. 大峡谷是一道超凡脱俗的风景。 4. The temples, too, in their ruin have a moonlight magic, an unearthly excellence. 这些庙宇在它们的废墟中也有一种月光般的魅力，超然出世之美。', '比较级: unearthlier 最高级: unearthliest 名词: unearthliness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lexicographer', '[ˌleksɪ\'kɑːɡrəfər]', 'n.辞典编纂者', '1. Spanish scholar famed as a Hebrew grammarian and lexicographer. 西班牙学者，为知名的希伯来语语法学家和词典编纂家。 2. To clarify some grammatical doubts, the young Ge wrote to H. Fowler, the lexicographer who produced the \"Concise English Dictionary\". 为了探索英语他冒昧去信英国《简明英语词典》的主编H-Fowler。 3. With all due respect to an enlightened but inferior lexicographer I beg to submit that it is the first. 带着对这位卑贱却开明的词典编纂家应有的敬意，我斗胆认为它是恶棍的第一伎俩。” 4. The linguistic theories are quite important for the lexicographer but practical utility is more basic for him. 基于这些词汇分层结果的原则，词典编纂者根据传统进行了分类。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('windfall', '[\'wɪndfɔːl]', 'n.风吹落的果实；意外的收获；侥幸所得', '1. After the storm she gather a basketful of windfall in the apple orchard. 风暴过後，她从苹果园地上拣了满满一篮子苹果。 2. I had a windfall from the football pools. 我从足球比赛赌博中发了一笔横财。 3. He applied the windfall to payment of his mortgage. 他把那笔意外的收入用於偿付抵押。 4. This windfall will eventually dwindle. 此类侥幸所得终将减少。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('disband', '[dɪs\'bænd]', 'v.解散；遣散', '1. The school was disbanded at noon. 学校在中午被解散了。 2. The army was disbanded when the war came to an end. 战争结束时，军队即被解散。 3. The government tried to disband the illegal organization. 政府企图解散那个非法组织。', '名词: disbandment 过去式: disbanded 过去分词: disbanded 现在分词: disbanding 第三人称单数: disbands');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('discursive', '[dɪs\'kɜːrsɪv]', 'adj.散漫的；不得要领的；[哲]推论的', '1. They complained that my writing was becoming too discursive. 他们抱怨我的文章变得太散漫的。 2. His own toast was discursive and overlong, though rather touching. 他自己的祝酒词虽然也颇为动人，但是比较松散而冗长。', '副词: discursively 名词: discursiveness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('modest', '[\'mɑːdɪst]', 'adj.谦虚的；适度的；端庄的；有节制的', '1. We should be modest and prudent. 我们应该谦虚谨慎。 2. She is very modest about her success. 她对自己的成就很谦虚。 3. I bought the house at a modest price. 我以适中的价格买下了这所房子。 4. Young girls must be modest in speech, dress and behavior. 年轻姑娘必须言词谨慎，衣着得体，行为端庄。', '副词: modestly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('presume', '[prɪ\'zuːm]', 'vt.假定；推测；姑且认定；认为是理所当然 vi.越权行事；利用', '1. The law presumes innocence until guilt is proved. 在罪状未证实前，法律假定被告无罪。 2. We presume that the factory has been fully engaged. 我们推测工厂的生产已经满负荷了。 3. That\'s the new assistant, I presume. 我想那就是新来的助理 4. I presume that this is your final answer. 我认为这就是你最后的答复。 5. May I presume to advise you? 我可以冒昧向你进一言吗？', '副词: presumedly 名词: presumer 过去式: presumed 过去分词: presumed 现在分词: presuming 第三人称单数: presumes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('uptight', '[ˌʌp\'taɪt]', 'adj.紧张的；恼怒的；因循守旧的', '1. She was uptight about the interview. 她对面谈感到紧张。 2. Please reassure the owners and managers not to get so uptight about something that makes the day a little pleasant. 请提醒老板们，经理们，不要对那些能使一天的气氛轻松起来的小事过分紧张。 3. My ex-boss was a very uptight person. 我的前任老板是一个很爱烦躁的人。', '名词: uptightness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hasten', '[\'heɪsn]', 'v.催促；赶快；加速', '1. Please hasten them to send the sample. 请催促他们寄来样品。 2. Do not hasten to bid me adieu. 不要告别得那样匆忙。 3. She hastened home after hearing the news. 听到这个消息后，她匆匆忙忙地回家。 4. Let me hasten to say that I could never do such a thing! 让我赶快说我永远不能做这样的事情！', '过去式: hastened 过去分词: hastened 现在分词: hastening 第三人称单数: hastens');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tony', '[\'toʊni]', 'n.托尼(男子名；Antony的昵称) adj.时尚的；高贵的；漂亮的 =toney.', '1. Tony hobnobbed with an attractive widow when he lived in Metz. 托尼在梅斯居住期间曾与一名漂亮的寡妇交往甚密。 2. She was the assistant director on Sir Jonathan Miller\'s Broadway production of \"King Lear,\" starring Christopher Plummer, which received two Tony Award nominations.Ms. 除此之外，艾丽娜还是一位聪明漂亮的百老汇演员。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ingest', '[ɪn\'dʒest]', 'v.咽下；摄取', '1. You will ingest only the lightest of substances. 你只将摄取最轻的物质。 2. The product itself is safe to ingest. 而产品本身是可以安全摄取的。', '形容词: ingestive 名词: ingestion 过去式: ingested 过去分词: ingested 现在分词: ingesting 第三人称单数: ingests');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('den', '[den]', 'n.兽穴；集聚地 v.穴居', '1. They lured the bear out of its den. 他们把熊从穴中诱出。 2. The lion lay asleep in its den. 狮子躺在洞里睡觉。 3. There is no den in the wide world to hide a rogue. 恶棍没有藏身之地。 4. He has made his house a den of thieves. 他把自己的家变成了一个贼窝。 5. The bears den up together during the winter. 冬天熊一起在洞穴里冬眠。', '过去式: denned 过去分词: denned 现在分词: denning 第三人称单数: dens');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('prevail', '[prɪ\'veɪl]', 'vi.盛行；获胜；劝说', '1. This old custom does not prevail now. 这种旧风俗现在已经不流行了。 2. Misty weather prevails in this part of the country. 该国的这一地区天气多雾。 3. Virtue will prevail against evil. 美德定将战胜邪恶。 4. I tried to prevail on him to stay. 我曾试图说服他留下。', '名词: prevailer 过去式: prevailed 过去分词: prevailed 现在分词: prevailing 第三人称单数: prevails');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('garbled', '[\'ɡɑːrbld]', 'adj.混乱的；曲解的 动词garble的过去式和过去分词.', '1. The nervous man gave a garbled account of the accident. 这个紧张不安的人对事故的陈述混淆不清。 2. What does the garbled code stand for? Please help me out. 请帮忙指出下面乱码处的英文是什么，谢谢。 3. Foreign newspapers gave a garbled account of the President\'s speech. 外国报纸对于总统之演说作歪曲的报道。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('neophyte', '[\'niːəfaɪt]', 'n.新手；新信徒', '1. Gaffer was no neophyte and had no fancies. 老头儿不是新手，他不会胡思乱想。 2. And even though many of them are neophyte gamblers, they often bet thousands of dollars on a single hand. 尽管他们中很多是新手，但往往一注就下数千美元。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('objective', '[əb\'dʒektɪv]', 'adj.客观的；真实的；宾语的 n.目标；目的；[物]物镜；[语]宾语', '1. From any objective perspective,it is simply too long. 从客观的角度来讲，这实在是太长了。 2. She gives an objective report of what has happened. 她就发生的事情进行客观的报告。 3. He has told a story which sound not objective. 他讲了听起来不真实的一个故事。 4. Her principal objective was international fame as a scientist. 她的主要目标是当个有国际声誉的科学家。', '副词: objectively 名词: objectiveness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('constrained', '[kən\'streɪnd]', 'adj.拘泥的；勉强的；不舒服的；受约束的；被迫的 动词constrain的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. He said it with a constrained smile. 他说这话时面带拘谨的笑容。 2. She felt constrained to carry out the new plan. 他对于执行这项新计划感到很勉强。 3. His answers were brief, constrained and evasive. 他的回答简单、勉强而且含糊其词。 4. I felt constrained to do what he told me. 做他叫我做的事,我心里很不舒服。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('memento', '[mə\'mentoʊ]', 'n.纪念品', '1. He kept a lock of her hair as a memento. 他保留着她的一束头发作纪念。 2. My friend gave me his picture as a memento before going away. 我的朋友在离别前给我一张照片留作纪念品。', '名词复数: mementos');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('imprecation', '[ˌɪmprɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.咒语；诅咒', '1. Yet such an imprecation can never be justified. 然而这一咒诅是不对的。 2. He was happy to combine in the same imprecation the two things which he most detested, Prussia and England. 他以能那样把他最恨的两件东西，普鲁士和英格兰，连缀在一句骂人的话里而感到得意。 3. The concrete adversaria and miscellanies of its folk-custom embody imprecation of people for health and auspicious. 重阳民俗的具体记事杂录,体现了人们对健康、祥和的祈盼。 4. This custom consigns people broken-down sign new wishes and 辞 old face new imprecation. 这一习俗寄托着人们破旧立新的愿望和辞旧迎新的祈求。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('felon', '[\'felən]', 'n.重罪犯', '1. He was convicted to be a felon. 他被判为重罪犯。 2. That felon tried to escape from the prison. 那名重罪犯试图从监狱中逃跑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('acoustic', '[ə\'kuːstɪk]', 'adj.听觉的；声音的；原声的；音响的', '1. You must have an acoustic problem. 你的听觉一定有问题。 2. Acoustic beauty is also very important to the modern gardens. 园林听觉美对现代景观的效果也起到了很好的作用。 3. These have very good acoustic insulation which will help cut out external sounds. 这些具有非常好的隔音效果，能够帮助隔离外界的声音。 4. Once, I backpacked around Europe and I brought an acoustic guitar with me. 有一次，我轻装环游欧洲，随身带着一把原声吉他。', '副词: acoustically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('retroactive', '[ˌretroʊ\'æktɪv]', 'adj.有追溯力的；可追溯的', '1. This will be retroactive agreement. 这些是追溯以往的合约。 2. The new law was made retroactive to 1 January. 新法令生效日期可追溯到1 月1 日. 3. They get a pay rise retroactive to last January. 他们补发了去年一月起的加薪。 4. And what does he mean by retroactive? 问：追溯是什么意思呢？', '副词: retroactively 名词: retroactivity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('acknowledge', '[ək\'nɑːlɪdʒ]', 'vt.承认；告知收到；公认；表示感谢；注意到', '1. We acknowledged the need for reform. 我们承认改革的需要。 2. Please acknowledge this cheque as soon as you receive it. 收到该支票后,请立即告知。 3. We hope you can acknowledge your mistake in public. 希望你当众认错。 4. We are sending you some money in acknowledgement of your valuable help. 我们送些酬劳，对您的大力协助聊表谢意。', '形容词: acknowledgeable 过去式: acknowledged 过去分词: acknowledged 现在分词: acknowledging 第三人称单数: acknowledges');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pesky', '[\'peski]', 'adj.讨厌的；烦人的', '1. Those pesky salesmen always call at dinner time. 那些讨厌的推销员总是在吃晚饭的时候打电话。 2. It also prevents any more pesky calls from Geneva. 此外它还避免了来自日内瓦的恼人之声。', '副词: peskily 比较级: peskier 最高级: peskiest 名词: peskiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('apotheosis', '[əˌpɑːθi\'oʊsɪs]', 'n.尊为神；神化；典范；顶峰', '1. He\'s the apotheosis of athletes. 乔丹是所有运动员的完美典范。 2. Their leader was the apotheosis of courage. 他们的领导人是勇敢的典范。 3. The American language became the apotheosis of slang. 美国语言是俚语发展的顶峰。 4. The legend of king arthur represent the apotheosis of chivalry. 亚瑟王的传说代表骑士精神的顶峰。', '名词复数: apotheoses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('girder', '[\'ɡɜːrdər]', 'n.[建]大梁', '1. The girder was clinched into the wall. 大梁被钉牢在墙中。 2. I saw with my own eyes a girder fall and crush him to death. 我眼瞅着一根大梁掉下来把他砸死了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mote', '[moʊt]', 'n.微尘；尘埃', '1. The mote of light on her laptop stretched into a bare-chested Indian warrior. 她笔记本上的光粒拉伸出一个赤裸胸膛的印第安武士。 2. A biblical phrase came to mind: \"seeing the mote in one\'s neighbor\'s eye, but not the beam in one\'s own\". 这让我想到《圣经》里的一句话：能看见别人眼里的尘埃，看不见自己眼里的木头。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('penury', '[\'penjəri]', 'n.贫穷；拮据', '1. Laid-off workers fall into penury. 下岗职工陷入贫困。 2. He was cradled in the lap of penury . 他自幼生活在贫困的环境里。 3. Hardship and penury wore him out before his time. 受穷受苦使他未老先衰。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('supplicate', '[\'sʌplɪˌkeɪt]', 'v.恳求；乞求', '1. She supplicated for pardon. 她恳求原谅。 2. He supplicates me to help. 他向我求助。', '形容词: supplicatory 名词: supplication 过去式: supplicated 过去分词: supplicated 现在分词: supplicating 第三人称单数: supplicates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('glutinous', '[\'ɡluːtənəs]', 'adj.粘性的；胶状的', '1. The grain shop is now in need of glutinous rice. 那粮店现在正需要糯米。', '副词: glutinously 名词: glutinousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('meticulous', '[mə\'tɪkjələs]', 'adj.一丝不苟的；缜密的', '1. He is noted for his meticulous scholarship. 他以治学严谨著称。 2. She is meticulous in her presentation of facts. 她介绍事实十分详细。 3. Their rooms had been prepared with meticulous care. 他们的房间是经过精心布置的。 4. The arrangements were meticulous. 布置得很缜密。', '副词: meticulously 名词: meticulosity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('drill', '[drɪl]', 'n.钻孔机；钻子；反复操练；播种机 v.练习；钻孔；(军事)训练', '1. The dentist\'s drill made a lot of noise. 牙钻发出很大的噪音。 2. Jack used a drill to bore a hole in the wall above the fireplace. 杰克用钻子在壁炉上方的墙上钻孔。 3. Today\'s art lesson came to an abrupt end when the gongs sounded for a fire drill. 今天的美术课因火灾演习的铃声大作而突然结束。 4. You\'d better set a goal before you start the drill. 练习开始前，你最好设定一个目标。 5. Listen to the first paragraph, then let them drill in teams. 听第一段,然后分组练习。', '名词: driller 过去式: drilled 过去分词: drilled 现在分词: drilling 第三人称单数: drills');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('abolition', '[ˌæbə\'lɪʃn]', 'n.废除；废止', '1. He long urged the abolition of capital punishment. 他长期要求废除死刑。 2. It has been two years since the abolition of the custom. 这种习俗已经废止两年了。 3. The abolition of foreign stereotypes was demanded in that report, yet some comrades are still promoting them. 这里叫洋八股废止，有些同志却实际上还在提倡。', '形容词: abolitionary');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reaper', '[\'riːpər]', 'reaper：n.；收割者；收割机', '1. My father taught me how to operate a reaper. 我父亲教我怎样使用收割机。 2. A rabbit got caught in the blades of the reaper. 一只兔子被卷到收割机的刀刃中去了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('formula', '[\'fɔːrmjələ]', 'n.配方；公式；规则；代乳品 adj.方程式的；（赛车的）级的', '1. They are working on the perfection of their new paint formula. 他们正在努力研制尽善尽美的新颜料配方。 2. What is the formula for water? 水的分子式是什么？ 3. Within the braces, you can include any formula. 在大括号内,可以包含任何公式。 4. It\'s the formula for converting gallons into liters. 这是加仑与升的换算公式。 5. His outwardly relaxed manner hides a sharp mind and a keen will to win, something he did a lot of on the nursery slopes of Formula BMW. 他轻松自若的举止下隐藏着敏锐的心思和渴望胜利的决心，这在他参加宝马方程式的培养期里就已经有所体现。', '形容词: formulaic 副词: formulaically 名词复数: formulas');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unenlightened', '[ˌʌnɪn\'laɪtənd]', 'adj.未受启蒙的；无知的', '1. The other computer companies were corporate and mindless, selling their products to the unenlightened masses. 对比之下，其他电脑公司则是雷同而愚钝的，只能向无知的大众推销其产品。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('simpleton', '[\'sɪmpltən]', 'n.笨蛋；傻子', '1. He tells of a Cuban fisherman who is a simpleton. 他讲的是个愚蠢的古巴渔民。 2. He did not in the least wish the future Mrs. Newland Archor to be a simpleton. 他希望未来的纽兰·阿切尔夫人至少不是头脑简单的人。 3. She represented her little brother as a simpleton. 她把她的弟弟描绘成一个傻瓜。 4. The simpleton wants to be with you together forever! 傻瓜想要永远和你在一起！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('falter', '[\'fɔːltər]', 'vi.动摇；迟疑；支吾地说；蹒跚地走 vt.蹒跚地走', '1. The business faltered and then failed. 商行生意衰退，最后倒闭了。 2. He is beginning to falter in his beliefs. 他的信仰开始有所迟疑。 3. I faltered for a while and was still unable to make a decision. 我踌躇了一阵，还是无法做决定。 4. He is beginning to falter in his beliefs. 他的信仰开始有所迟疑。 5. The sick man faltered a few steps and then fell. 这个病人摇摇晃晃地走了几步，然后就跌倒了。', '副词: falteringly 名词: falterer 过去式: faltered 过去分词: faltered 现在分词: faltering 第三人称单数: falters');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('circumstantial', '[ˌsɜːrkəm\'stænʃl]', 'adj.依情况而定的；详细的', '1. You can\'t convict him merely on circumstantial evidence. 你不能仅凭间接证据判他有罪。 2. We should point out that the evidence is purely circumstantial . 我们应该指出，证据完全是依情况而定的。 3. My wife used to dream occasionally and insist on telling me her dreams next day with circumstantial detail. 过去，我太太有时也作梦，第二天总是非得详详细细，一点不拉地讲给我听不可。 4. We must admit that the overwhelming volume of indisputable circumstantial evidence far outweighed the presumption of innocence. 我们必须承认,大量无可辩驳的详尽的证据远远压倒了关于清白的假设。', '副词: circumstantially');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cede', '[siːd]', 'v.割让(领土；权利) v.放弃', '1. That is what the regime fears most, because then it either has to shoot its own people or cede power. 这是当前伊朗政权最害怕的，因为到那时只能被迫选择开枪射击自己的人们，或放弃权力。 2. This second step will be awkward, because votes cannot be taken from members that do not want to cede them. 第二步会比较麻烦，因为投票权并不能从那些不愿放弃他们的成员那里拿过来。', '过去式: ceded 过去分词: ceded 现在分词: ceding 第三人称单数: cedes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('opalescence', '[oʊpə\'lesəns]', 'n.乳白光；蛋白光；蛋白石混浊', '1. Soon there were also flagstones beneath his shambling feet, uneven, fractured stone that nonetheless caught the light of the lantern-sphere with strange opalescence. 很快，在他的步履蹒跚的脚下，就出现了石板路，这些石头坑坑洼洼，处处断裂，在他手里水晶球的照射下，现出奇怪的乳白色光亮。 2. Analog Computation of Jun Ware Opalescence Based on Mie Scattering 基于米氏散射的钧瓷乳光模拟计算 3. Keywords Opal enamel porcelain;Opalescence;Fluorescence;Translucency;Masking effect;Optical properties; 乳光瓷;乳光;荧光;透明度;遮色效果;光学特性; 4. critical opalescence 临界乳光', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stampede', '[stæm\'piːd]', 'n.(人群的)蜂拥；惊逃 v.惊跑；蜂拥；冲动行事', '1. A stampede broke out when the doors opened. 门一开，人们蜂拥而出。 2. There was a stampede of panic-stricken crowd from the burning hotel. 从失火的旅馆中跑出来乱窜的惊惶失措的人群。 3. The horses stamped and tore down the street. 那些马惊跑起来，没着大街冲去。 4. The cattle stampeded towards the farm. 受惊的牛群向牧场涌去。', '名词: stampeder 过去式: stampeded 过去分词: stampeded 现在分词: stampeding 第三人称单数: stampedes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('proclaim', '[prə\'kleɪm]', 'vt.正式宣布；声明；表明；赞扬', '1. The president proclaimed that a new currency would be issued. 总统宣布将发行新货币。 2. She did not proclaim her intention. 她没有把自己的意图明说出来。 3. He was impelled to proclaim his doctrine. 他不得不宣扬他的教义。 4. His accent proclaimed that he was an American. 他的口音表明他是一个美国人。', '形容词: proclamatory 名词: proclaimer 过去式: proclaimed 过去分词: proclaimed 现在分词: proclaiming 第三人称单数: proclaims');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('diameter', '[daɪ\'æmɪtər]', 'n.直径', '1. The diameter of the tree-trunk is about 2 meters. 这树干的直径大约是2米。 2. We must gauge the diameter of wire first. 我们必须先测量电线的直径。 3. The axis of a circle is its diameter. 圆的轴线是其直径。', '形容词: diametral');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('demolition', '[ˌdemə\'lɪʃn]', 'n.破坏；毁坏 (复数)demolitions：炸药.', '1. There was a perfect rage for demolition. 这简直是一场疯狂的破坏。 2. Demolition runs in the family. 我们家族就是擅长搞破坏。', '名词: demolitionist');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('belie', '[bɪ\'laɪ]', 'v.掩饰；与 ... 不符；使 ... 失望', '1. His cheerful manner belied his real feelings. 他那快活的样子掩饰了他真实的感情。 2. Practical experience belies this theory. 实际经验证明这个理论是错误的。 3. Yet his actions belie that agnosticism. 然而他却言行不一。', '名词: belier 过去式: belied 过去分词: belied 现在分词: belying 第三人称单数: belies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('posse', '[\'pɑːsi]', 'n.一队；地方治安团队', '1. The posse rode down the escaping bank robber. 一队警察驾车追上了正在逃跑的银行抢动犯。 2. I come in here with my posse and my deputies but he doesn\'t like that. 我上任的时候把我的团队和副手都带过来了，而他不喜欢我这样。 3. They got a posse together, and went off to guard the river bank, and as soon as it is light the sheriff and a gang are going to beat up the woods. 他们调集了一队人马，部署在河岸上，担任守卫工作。 等天亮后，警长还亲自带一帮人到森林去搜查。 4. The posse are pursuing the thief. 武装队正追捕那贼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('override', '[ˌoʊvər\'raɪd]', 'v.推翻；无视；凌驾；超驰控制(使自动控制暂时失效而改用手动控制)；[计算机]覆盖 n.给代理人的佣金；超驰控制装置；推翻', '1. The appeal court overrode the decision of the lower court. 上诉法院撤销了下级法院的裁决。 2. We overrode their objections. 我们对他们的反对不予理睬。 3. Budgetary concerns overrode all other considerations. 预算之事比其它一切要考虑的事都重要 4. A special code is needed to override the time lock. 这定时锁要用特定密码才能打开。 5. The President has vowed to veto the measure and an override is rated as a slim prospect. 总统发誓要否决这一措施,而推翻否决被认为不太可能。', '过去式: overrode 过去分词: overridden 现在分词: overriding 第三人称单数: overrides');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tacit', '[\'tæsɪt]', 'adj.心照不宣的；缄默的；默示的', '1. They have a tacit understanding. 他俩心照不宣。 2. Our tacit treaty with her was that we could play on her lawn. 我们和她心照不宣的协定是，我们可以在她的草坪上玩。 3. The deal had the tacit approval of the President. 这笔交易得到总统的默许。 4. They were leagued together by a tacit treaty. 他们根据默契关系联合起来了。', '副词: tacitly 名词: tacitness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('jerk', '[dʒɜːrk]', 'v.急动；猛拉 n.猛拉；急动；笨蛋；<俚> 蠢人 adj.颠簸不稳的', '1. The bus jerked to a stop. 公共汽车猛然刹车停住了。 2. He jerked the string and the puppet jumped. 他猛地一拉绳子，木偶就跳了起来。 3. He give his tooth a sharp jerk and it come out 他猛一使劲把牙拔了下来 4. The knife was stuck but she pulled it out with a jerk. 那把刀子被卡住了，她猛地一拔，把它拔了出来。', '副词: jerkingly 名词: jerker 过去式: jerked 过去分词: jerked 现在分词: jerking 第三人称单数: jerks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('timorous', '[\'tɪmərəs]', 'adj.胆怯的；羞怯的', '1. He was the most timorous person in that event. 在那次事件中他是个胆小鬼。 2. She is as timorous as a rabbit. 她胆小得像只兔子。 3. \"I love you\",she murmurs in a timorous way. “我爱你”，她用非常胆怯低沉的声音说着。', '副词: timorously 名词: timorousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incommensurate', '[ˌɪnkə\'menʃərət]', 'adj.不成比例的；不相称的；不足的；不能相对应的', '1. His abilities are incommensurate to the task. 他的能力和他担负的任务不相称。', '副词: incommensurately 名词: incommensurateness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('collision', '[kə\'lɪʒn]', 'n.碰撞；冲突', '1. The car was completely wrecked by the force of the collision. 这辆汽车受到很大的撞击力而完全损坏。 2. The liner is reported to have been in collision with an oil tanker. 据报道，这艘客轮与一艘油轮相撞。 3. The Government and the unions are on a collision course. 政府和工会必将发生冲突。 4. This collision had a very unusual cause. 这次冲突有着非同寻常的原因。', '形容词: collisional');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('galaxy', '[\'ɡæləksi]', 'n.银河；星系；一群杰出的人', '1. The sun is only a very small star in the Galaxy. 太阳只是银河系中一颗很小的恒星。 2. The earth is one of the planets in the Galaxy. 地球是银河系中的星球之一。 3. Each galaxy contains myriads of stars. 每一星系都有无数的恒星。 4. The solar system is a small part of our galaxy. 太阳系是我们星系的一个小部分。', '名词复数: galaxies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('abscission', '[æb\'sɪʒən]', 'n.切断；除去；[语]顿断法', '1. An abscission zone occurs at the base of the organ. 脱落区发生在器官基部的某一特化的区域。 2. It is antagonistic to abscisic acid in abscission. 在脱落过程中生长素与脱落酸有拮抗作用。 3. Abscission of the tightly rolled, needlelike tips of the injured leaves quite often occurred. 受毒害叶片经常出现针状的叶尖从蜷缩部分脱落下来。 4. When abscission occurred,total sugar and soluble protein were decreased,but reducing sugar was increased. 当脱落发生时,培养体的总糖及可溶性蛋白的含量降低,但还原糖含量升高。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('chide', '[tʃaɪd]', 'vi.斥责；指责 vt.(温和地）责备', '1. We chide the citizen because he makes love a commodity. 我们责备庸俗的市民，那是因为他把爱变成了商品。', '副词: chidingly 名词: chider 过去式: chided/chid 过去分词: chided/chid/chidden 现在分词: chiding 第三人称单数: chides');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ascendancy', '[ə\'sendənsi]', 'n.统治权；支配力量', '1. He has (gained) the ascendancy over all his main rivals. 他(获)有压倒一切主要对手的优势。 2. He is completely under his wife\'s ascendancy. 他完全受制于其妻。 3. They established their ascendancy 他们确立了他们的支配地位。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cello', '[\'tʃeloʊ]', 'n.【C】大提琴', '1. She plays a melodious cello. 她拉着一手悦耳的大提琴。 2. She plays the cello in an orchestra. 她在管弦乐队中演奏大提琴。 3. The cello makes low and deep sounds. 大提琴发出低沉的声音。', '名词: cellist 名词复数: cellos');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('shear', '[ʃɪr]', 'n.修剪；剪下的东西；大剪刀 v.剪掉；剪；剥夺', '1. With a few quick snips of the shear, he pruned the bush. 他用大剪刀几下子就把灌木给修剪好了。 2. All her curls have been shorn off. 她的一头卷发被剪得精光。 3. I start shearing the sheep at the beginning of July. 我一般在7月初开始剪羊毛。', '名词: shearer 过去式: sheared 过去分词: sheared/shorn 现在分词: shearing 第三人称单数: shears');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('propulsion', '[prə\'pʌlʃn]', 'n.推进；推进力', '1. This aircraft works by jet propulsion. 这架飞机是喷气推进的。 2. The fish uses its tail fins for propulsion through the water. 鱼靠尾鳍在水中前进。 3. No propulsion occurs at this time. 此时无推进力产生。 4. This is the basic principle behind electromagnetic propulsion. 这是电磁推进力的基本原理。', '形容词: propulsive');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unregenerate', '[ˌʌnrɪ\'dʒenərət]', 'adj.不能再生的；顽固不化的；死不悔改的', '1. Some natural resources are unregenerate, or can be turned into unregenerate. 一些自然资源是不可再生的，或者可能变成不可再生的。', '形容词: unregenerable 副词: unregenerately 名词: unregeneracy');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('shibboleth', '[\'ʃɪbəleθ]', 'n.陈腔滥调；口令或暗语；术语', '1. The elderly politicians still cling to the outmoded shibboleths of party doctrine. 这些年迈的政治家仍然抱着党性教条的陈词滥调不放。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stodgy', '[\'stɑːdʒi]', 'adj.笨重的；沉闷的；式样难看的；难消化的', '1. They are stodgy, slow-moving players who are asleep at the helm. 这些都是体型笨重、行动迟缓的对手，他们还在睡梦中呢。 2. It\'s not stodgy to talk about money. 谈论金钱并不庸俗。 3. She poked fun at Alec because he was shy and stodgy. 她开亚历克的玩笑，因为他羞怯，同时还有些枯燥沉闷。 4. These were not the old stodgy ads listing goods for sale. 这不是那种列明打折商品的旧式、乏味的广告。', '副词: stodgily 比较级: stodgier 最高级: stodgiest 名词: stodginess');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('leash', '[liːʃ]', 'n.(系狗的)皮带；控制；约束 n.（打猎用语）三只；三个一组 v.用皮带控制；束缚', '1. Beau was pulling ahead of me with his leash. 博套着皮带拽着我走在前面。 2. He slipped the hound from the leash. 他解开皮带放掉猎狗。 3. The memes take hold of the leash. 迷因控制了基因。 4. Our parent company keeps us on a fairly short leash. 我们的母公司对我们的控制相当紧。 5. This is the phylosopher\'s mind off the leash. 这是哲学家思想摆脱了束缚结果。', '过去式: leashed 过去分词: leashed 现在分词: leashing 第三人称单数: leashes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('beleaguer', '[bɪ\'liːgə]', 'vt.围攻；使烦恼', '1. Even today, in some parts of China, it is common practice for a man to seek justice by summoning his family and their allies to beleaguer the home of the person who wronged him. 人们受了欺负，便召来家里人和亲戚围攻仇家，这在今天中国的一些地方还是司空见惯的。', '名词: beleaguerment 过去式: beleaguered 过去分词: beleaguered 现在分词: beleaguering 第三人称单数: beleaguers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('illegal', '[ɪ\'liːɡl]', 'adj.非法的；不合法的 n.非法移民', '1. The jewellery firm is just a front for their illegal trade in diamonds. 该珠宝公司不过是进行非法的钻石交易的幌子。 2. All protests are brutally repressed by the government as illegal. 所有的抗议活动都遭到当局的野蛮镇压，并被宣布为非法。 3. Their speculative buying of grain is illegal. 他们投机购买谷物是不合法的。 4. Abortion is illegal in this country. 人工流产在这个国家是不合法的。 5. The illegals couldn\'t be admitted by the authority. 非法移民是不被政府认可的。', '副词: illegally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('relenting', '[rɪ\'lent]', 'v.变宽厚；变温和；动怜悯之心；缓和；（坏天气）变好', '1. At first she threatened to dismiss us all, but later she relented. 起初她威胁要解雇我们所有的人，但是后来她态度软化了。 2. The other students persuaded him to relent. 其他的学生劝说他要变得温和些。 3. The police will not relent in their fight against crime. 警方在跟犯罪分子的斗争中决不手软。 4. The pressure on us to finish this task will not relent. 我们为完成此项任务受到的压力不会减轻。', '过去式: relented 过去分词: relented 现在分词: relenting 第三人称单数: relents');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mediate', '[\'miːdieɪt]', 'v.调停；斡旋 adj.居间的；间接的', '1. He attempted to mediate their differences. 他试图调停他们的分歧。 2. He cooled the situation down by offering to mediate between the disputing parties. 他提出愿为争执的双方调停，情况因此缓和下来。 3. A well-known local lawyer has been appointed to mediate between the employers and the union leaders, since they can\'t reach an agreement in direct talks. 既然雇主们同工会领袖无法在直接谈判中达成协议，就指定了一位当地的名律师进行调解。 4. He tried to mediate between his colleagues and management. 他设法在同事和管理阶层之间斡旋。 5. There were some mediate contacts between the two countries before their diplomatic relation was established. 在两国外交关系建立之前, 已经有些间接的接触。', '副词: mediately 过去式: mediated 过去分词: mediated 现在分词: mediating 第三人称单数: mediates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('amnesty', '[\'æmnəsti]', 'n.大赦；特赦', '1. The rebels returned home under a general amnesty. 造反的人经大赦释放回家。 2. He subscribes regularly to Amnesty International. 他定期向大赦国际捐款。 3. There is no amnesty today and there will not be any in the future. 第二点，他们一定要依照法律的程序来香港，千万不要听信会有特赦，今日没有，将来也不会有。 4. Do not use Amnesty cards or mention Amnesty International. 不要用国际特赦组织的卡片，也不要提到国际特赦组织。', '名词复数: amnesties 过去式: amnestied 过去分词: amnestied 现在分词: amnestying 第三人称单数: amnesties');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('paradigm', '[\'pærədaɪm]', 'n.范例；示范；典范；[语]词形变化表', '1. There\'s no paradigm to follow in this new industry. 在这个崭新的行业里没有范例可做参考。 2. No prevailing paradigm in science lasts forever. 科学中没有任何流行范式能够存在永远。 3. We now see paradigms and paradigm overthrows everywhere, inside of science and out. 我们现在可以随处看到典范和推翻典范的事例，无论在科学还是其他方面。 4. The Aristotelian paradigm prefers the frog perspective, whereas the Platonic paradigm prefers the bird perspective. 亚里士多德的典范偏向蛙的眼光，而柏拉图的典范偏向鸟的眼光。', '形容词: paradigmatic');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('holster', '[\'hoʊlstər]', 'n.手枪皮套', '1. After the shirt is modeled, I create the gun holster. 衬衫做好后，我开始创建手枪皮套。 2. The officer undid the flap of his holster and drew his gun. 军官打开枪套盖拔出了手枪。', '形容词: holstered 过去式: holstered 过去分词: holstered 现在分词: holstering 第三人称单数: holsters');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('warble', '[\'wɔːrbl]', 'v.用颤音唱；鸟鸣 n.颤音；动物背上的肿块', '1. A blackbird was warbling from the branch. 一只画眉鸟在枝头歌唱。 2. I heard the faint warble of Laura\'s voice. 我听到劳拉那柔和的颤音。 3. The strain was solemn and affecting, sustained as it was by the pathetic warble of a voice. 曲子既庄严又感人，是由悲怆的颤音唱出来的。', '过去式: warbled 过去分词: warbled 现在分词: warbling 第三人称单数: warbles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('puissant', '[\'pjuːɪsənt]', 'adj.强有力的；强盛的；有权力的', '1. The young man has a puissant body. 这个年轻人有一副强壮的身体。 2. This is a puissant signal, meaning the crisis is over. 这是一个强有力的信号，表示危机已经过去。 3. The kingdom used to be puissant. 这个王国曾经很强盛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hazardous', '[\'hæzərdəs]', 'adj.危险的；冒险的；碰运气的', '1. Everybody said that it was a hazardous investment. 大家都说那是一次危险的投资。 2. Dry-cleaners deal with many hazardous chemicals. 干洗工要跟很多危险的化学品打交道。 3. Nothing rewarded the hazardous experiment. 这个冒险的举动没有引起任何反应。 4. In this area arable farming is a hazardous practice. 在这个地区，可耕种的作物完全是碰运气的。', '副词: hazardously 名词: hazardousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hew', '[hjuː]', 'v.砍；劈；砍倒；砍成；固守；开辟 abbr.(美)卫生、教育及福利部(=Department of Health；Education；and Welfare)', '1. Then she two only stretch out, and let him hew away. 然后她就把两只手伸出来,让他砍掉。 2. He knew better than to attempt to hew rocks with razor. 他知道刀片不能劈石头。 3. He was told not to hew down that ancient tree. 他被告之不要砍倒那棵古树。 4. He hewed a canoe out of a tree trunk. 他把一根树干凿成独木舟。', '名词: hewer 过去式: hewed 过去分词: hewn/hewed 现在分词: hewing 第三人称单数: hews');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('massacre', '[\'mæsəkər]', 'n.大屠杀；<口>惨败 v.大屠杀；<口>彻底击败', '1. The massacre was a crime against humanity. 这场大屠杀是一桩反人类的罪行。 2. The press has reported the massacre of thousands of people for their religious beliefs. 新闻界报道了那场因宗教信仰原因而对千万人的大屠杀。 3. The game was a complete massacre; we lost 10-0. 那次比赛真是一次惨败，我们0比10输了。 4. Vichy government was the accessory of Nazi to massacre the Jews who lived in France. 维希政府是德国纳粹残害住在法国的犹太人的帮凶之一。', '名词: massacrer 过去式: massacred 过去分词: massacred 现在分词: massacring 第三人称单数: massacres');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stringent', '[\'strɪndʒənt]', 'adj.严格的；银根紧的；紧迫的', '1. Licences are only granted under the most stringent conditions. 只有符合极其严格的条件才颁发许可证。 2. People began verify their scientific hypotheses by stringent tests. 人们开始用精确的试验证实自己的科学假说。 3. Some of our most outstanding buildings have been created on a stringent budget. 我们的一些杰出作品往往是在很紧凑的预算下设计建成的。 4. Based on above analysis the stringent problems needed to resolve are put forward. 在此基础上指出今后迫切需要解决的问题。', '副词: stringently 名词: stringency');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('contort', '[kən\'tɔːrt]', 'v.(使)扭曲；走样；曲解', '1. I didn\'t care how much I had to contort my body and my principles. 我毫不顾及自己的身体和原则被怎样扭曲。 2. Her face contorted/was contorted with pain. 她的脸因疼痛而走了样。 3. It\'s very common that children contort a word out of its ordinary meaning. 小孩子曲解词义是很正常的事。', '形容词: contortive 名词: contortion 过去式: contorted 过去分词: contorted 现在分词: contorting 第三人称单数: contorts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unguent', '[\'ʌŋɡwənt]', 'n.软膏；药膏', '1. This unguent relieves rheumatism, chills and pains, and is fit for use By rheumatism sufferers. 本药膏除湿散寒，祛风定痛，适合风湿病人使用。', '形容词: unguentary');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('shriek', '[ʃriːk]', 'v.尖叫；叫喊 n.尖叫', '1. The shriek sent shivers down my spine. 那尖叫声使我的背脊起了一阵寒颤。 2. Her shriek was dulled by the loud crash of thunder. 她的尖叫声在震耳的雷声中变得低沉了。 3. Suddenly a new sound, a shrill, feminine shriek, was heard from the porch, and the cook ran into the vestibule. 突然，另一声刺耳的女人的叫喊，从门廊传了过来，接着，厨娘跑进了客厅。 4. Suddenly he began to shriek loudly. 突然他开始大声尖叫起来。', '名词: shrieker 过去式: shrieked 过去分词: shrieked 现在分词: shrieking 第三人称单数: shrieks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unthreatening', '[ʌnθ\'retnɪŋ]', 'adj.善意的；不威胁的', '1. First, it consists of an unthreatening minority position. 第一，它持有不具威胁性的少数股权。 2. Fortunately, most often fetishism and sadomasochism appear in socially harmless, unthreatening forms. 幸运的是，恋物癖和施虐受虐癖多数时候不会以危害和威胁社会的方式出现。 3. Sexual activity also remains unthreatening as long as it serves the purposes of reproduction and of male pleasure. 只要性活动服务于生殖的目的和男人愉悦的目的，那么，它也仍旧不会对社会构成威胁。 4. Could play spoiler -- he was a semifinalist last year and his draw is most unthreatening -- but that\'s about it. 前世界前5号选手，目前失去了魔法，去年的法网四强，今年与切拉、达维登科同在一个1/8区。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cold-blooded', '[koʊld \'blʌdɪd]', 'adj.(动物)冷血的；无情的', '1. What Sue had said in warmth was really the cold truth. 淑在感情热烈的时候所说的话，确实是冷酷无情的真理。 2. He fears the lancet of my art as I fear that of his.The cold steelpen. 他惧怕我的艺术尖刀，正如我害怕他的冷酷无情的钢笔。', '副词: cold-bloodedly 名词: cold-bloodedness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('interlude', '[\'ɪntərluːd]', 'n.中间；中间时间；插曲；介在中间的事件', '1. There will now be a 15-minute interlude. 现在有15分钟的中间休息。 2. Apart from a brief interlude of peace, the war lasted nine years. 除了一段短暂的和平，那场战争持续了九年。 3. Her time in Paris was a happy interlude in a difficult career. 她在巴黎期间是她艰辛的事业中一段愉快的插曲。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('brink', '[brɪŋk]', 'n.边缘；边沿；界限', '1. Natalie is living on the brink of panic. 娜塔丽正生活在痛苦的边缘。 2. She knows well that she and Louis are on a brink. 她深深知道，她和路易斯是到了危险的边沿。 3. Prosecutors said he left Enron because he knew the company was on the brink of bankruptcy. 检察官说他离开的原因是因为他知道公司已经处于破产的边沿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('headlong', '[\'hedlɔːŋ]', 'adj.头向前的；匆促而用力的；轻率的 adv.头向前地；猛然的用力的；轻率地', '1. He made a headlong plunge into the river. 他一头栽进河里。 2. The calm water ends there and the river begins a headlong plunge. 平静的河水突然中断，开始奔腾直泻而下。 3. They made a headlong dash for the door. 他们迅猛地向门口冲去。 4. She was so simple and young and headlong. 她是那么单纯、年轻和直率。 5. The child leaned towards his mother and fell headlong in front of her. 孩子俯身凑向妈妈，头朝前面倒在妈妈的面前。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scope', '[skoʊp]', 'n.机会；范围；眼界；观看的仪器 vt.仔细研究', '1. He gets a work that gives scope for his abilities. 他得到了一份有机会发挥他才能的工作。 2. He has no scope for his particular talents. 他没有施展自己特殊才能的机会。 3. It is within my scope. 那是在我的范围之内。 4. This subject is outside the scope of our inquiry. 这个问题不在我们探讨的范围之内。 5. He scopes the big picture of Israeli-Arab relations. 他认真地查看关于以色列和阿拉伯关系的大图片。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hoof', '[huːf]', 'n. 蹄； <俚>人的脚 v. 以蹄踢； 行走', '1. She tried very hard and finally she was able to write her name with her hoof. 她很努力地设法写，终能用她的蹄写出她的名字。 2. He suffered a life-threatening break during the Preakness, then developed a hoof disease. 巴布若在匹里克尼斯马赛期间发生致命的骨折，随后蹄部患病。', '名词复数: hoofs/hooves 过去式: hoofed 过去分词: hoofed 现在分词: hoofing 第三人称单数: hoofs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('underbid', '[ˌʌndər\'bɪd]', 'v.出较低的价钱；投标低于他人；以低价提供', '1. With this pool of slave labor, you can underbid any contractor in the city. 有这些可怜的劳工,你可比这城里的所有承包商出更低的价。 2. The manufacturers appear to have underbid the contracts by a wider margin than usual. 厂家对合同投的标似乎较一般低得太多。 3. Just because we underbid our rivals and got a major order, they have accused us of sharp practice. 只是因为我们投票时出价低于对手得到了一个大数量的订货单，他们便指责我们有欺诈行为。', '名词: underbid 过去式: underbid 过去分词: underbid 现在分词: underbidding 第三人称单数: underbids');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('connubial', '[kə\'njuːbiːəl]', 'adj. <正>结婚的； 夫妇的； 配偶的', '1. Hogan told me he had tasted the joys of connubial bliss. 霍根告诉我他已经尝到了比翼双飞的快乐。 2. Connubial:Relating to marriage or the married state; conjugal. 婚姻的:与婚姻或婚姻状况有关的;夫妻间的. 3. Hogan told me he had tasted the joys of connubial bliss . 霍根告诉我他已经尝到了比翼双飞的快乐。 4. Her absence had brought about danger to Edward\'s connubial happiness. 她的不在已经给爱德华幸福的婚姻带来危险。', '副词: connubially 名词: connubialism');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('extrinsic', '[eks\'trɪnsɪk]', 'adj.非固有的；非本质的；外在的', '1. The traditional culture was embodied by means of PeiTian people\'s extrinsic action and intrinsic psychology. 这些传统文化通过培田人外在的行为方式和内在的心理展现出来。', '副词: extrinsically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('counterpoise', '[\'kaʊntəˌpɔɪz]', 'v.平均；使平衡 n.平衡；砝码', '1. In very gradual, complex ways, Britain may prove to be, not the Trojan horse of American influence which France has always feared, but, on the contrary, a counterpoise to the American tide. 虽然过程缓慢，方式也很复杂，可英国也许能够证明他们并非是法国总是害怕的那种美国势力的潜在危险。恰恰相反，他们是与美国潮流抗衡的力量。 2. An influence or force tending to produce equilibrium; counterpoise. 平衡力趋向于产生平衡的影响或力量; 平衡、均衡 3. A weight that acts to balance another; a counterpoise or counterweight. 衡重体能与另一个平衡的重量; 衡重体或平衡锤', '过去式: counterpoised 过去分词: counterpoised 现在分词: counterpoising 第三人称单数: counterpoises');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('indeterminate', '[ˌɪn\'tɜːrmɪnət]', 'adj.不确定的；含混的', '1. I give indeterminate money to poor men. 我不定量给穷人一些钱。 2. Our holiday plans are still at an indeterminate stage. 我们的假日计划还没有确定。 3. This is a sort of indeterminate color. 这是一种说不清的颜色。', '副词: indeterminately 名词: indeterminateness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gripping', '[\'ɡrɪpɪŋ]', 'adj.扣人心弦的；引人入胜的 动词grip的现在分词形式.', '1. The story is so gripping;it makes you thirst for the next episode. 这故事是那么扣人心弦，使人急于要知道下文如何。 2. His thrillers are always a gripping read. 他的惊险小说向来引人入胜。 3. Perhaps more gripping events close at hand. 也许,还有更多的吸引人的大事在掌握之中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('uncouth', '[ʌn\'kuːθ]', 'adj.粗俗的；笨拙的；无教养的', '1. His nephew is an uncouth young man. 他的侄子是一个粗野的年轻人。 2. He behaves in a most uncouth way. 他的举止真是笨拙。 3. She may embarrass you with her uncouth behavior. 她的粗野行为可能会让你尴尬。', '副词: uncouthly 名词: uncouthness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('distill', '[dɪs\'tɪl]', 'v.蒸馏；滴下；吸取；提炼', '1. When carvone begins to distill, the condensation can be seen inside the thermometer adapter, thus the progress of carvone distillation can be readily monitored. 当香芹酮开始蒸馏时，在温度计转接器内可看到有冷凝，因此能够容易地监察香芹酮的蒸馏过程。 2. You had to somehow distill those feelings. 你必须试图一滴一滴提炼出这些感情。 3. We were asked to distill the crucial points of the book. 要求我们从本书中提炼出关键点。', '形容词: distillable');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('premiere', '[prɪ\'mɪr]', 'v.初次公演；初次演出 n.初次公演；初演主角', '1. The opera will premiere at the Arcadia Theater. 这出歌剧将要在阿卡迪亚剧院首映。 2. The Philharmonic will premiere works by two young Americans. 两个年青的美国人的作品将由该交响乐团首次公演。 3. Anna will premiere a movie after graduation. 安娜将迎来毕业后第一次电影演出。 4. we rehearsed frenziedly the last few days before the premiere. 公演前的那几天我们热火朝天地进行训练。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cultivate', '[\'kʌltɪveɪt]', 'vt.栽培；耕作；培养；陶冶；结交(朋友)', '1. He was granted many privileges to cultivate crops. 他被给予许多特权来培育农作物。 2. They moved to the country to cultivate the soil . 他们搬到乡下去种地。 3. The people cultivate mainly rice and beans. 这里的人们主要种植稻子和豆类。 4. Father tries to cultivate my love for art. 父亲企图培养我对艺术的爱好。', '形容词: cultivatable 过去式: cultivated 过去分词: cultivated 现在分词: cultivating 第三人称单数: cultivates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wage', '[weɪdʒ]', 'n.工资；报酬 v.开展；从事；进行(战争、运动)', '1. A postman\'s wages are 180 per week. 邮递员的工资为每周180英镑。 2. In our family both my husband and I are wage earners. 在我们家里，丈夫和我都挣工资。 3. In order to circumvent the straitjacket of national wage rates, employers in many cities offer non-pecuniary rewards to their workers. 为了避免全国工资率的约束，许多城市的雇主不以金钱的形式付给工人报酬。 4. I am saying that in most cases, if you were to look at a pure dollar-per-hour \"wage,\" you would find that many bloggers work rather inexpensively. 而是说大部分情况下，如果你在看一份一小时只有一美元报酬的工作，那么你会发现很多博客在廉价工作。 5. The government is waging a campaign against sex discrimination in industry. 政府正在展开反对工业界性别歧视的运动。', '过去式: waged 过去分词: waged 现在分词: waging 第三人称单数: wages');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('emanate', '[\'eməneɪt]', 'v.散发；发出', '1. I wish I am a cup of tea, leave the misery in my heart and emanate the fragrance! 我愿意做茶，把枯涩留在心里，散发出来的都是清香。 2. Soul Power is a power that can only emanate from within. 只有灵魂力量是从内在发出的。', '形容词: emanative 过去式: emanated 过去分词: emanated 现在分词: emanating 第三人称单数: emanates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ballerina', '[ˌbælə\'riːnə]', 'n.芭蕾舞女演员', '1. She was beyond all doubt the finest ballerina of her day. 她无疑是她那个时代最优秀的芭蕾舞演员。 2. Against all the odds she achieved her dream of becoming a ballerina. 她克服重重困难，实现了当芭蕾舞演员的梦想。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('attic', '[\'ætɪk]', 'n.阁楼', '1. She works in a dismal little room in the attic. 她在阁楼上的一间阴暗的小房间里工作。 2. I can\'t stand the closeness of the attic anymore. 我再也无法忍受阁楼的窒闷了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gestate', '[\'dʒesteɪt]', 'v.孕育；构思', '1. It was in ancient times that the thought of pedagogical pragmatics began to gestate and form. 摘要古代是教学语用学思想的孕育和形成时期。', '过去式: gestated 过去分词: gestated 现在分词: gestating 第三人称单数: gestates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lease', '[liːs]', 'n.租约；租契；租期 vt.出租；租得', '1. Our present lease on the flat expires next month. 我们这套公寓的租约下月到期。 2. An astute tenant always reads the small print in a lease. 精明的租户对租契上的每个细小之处都要讲究。 3. Does your current lease provide for showings prior to the tenant vacating the property? 您当前的租契是否规定了在房客搬出房间之前可以提前展售？ 4. The lease of my house has only a year to run . 我的房子的租约期限只有1年了。 5. This company leases out property. 这个公司出租房地产。', '形容词: leasable 名词: leaser 过去式: leased 过去分词: leased 现在分词: leasing 第三人称单数: leases');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('interlocking', '[ɪntə(ː)\'lɒkɪŋ]', 'adj.联锁的；交织在一起的 动词interlock的现在分词形式.', '1. Engagement is the state or act of interlocking. 啮合是互锁的状态或动作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vivacious', '[vɪ\'veɪʃəs]', 'adj.活泼的', '1. She is an artless, vivacious girl. 她是一个天真活泼的女孩。 2. The picture has a vivacious artistic conception. 这幅画气韵生动。', '副词: vivaciously 名词: vivaciousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('versemonger', '[\'vɜːsˌmʌŋgə]', 'n.拙劣诗人', '1. “I can re-note (came to know) Tony is (as) a versemonger (very smart) and capable man. 一直以来我知道托尼是一个非常聪明有能力的人。 2. versemonger: 拙劣诗人，打油诗人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('list', '[lɪst]', 'n.目录；名单；明细表；条纹；倾斜；<古>意向 v.列出；(使)倾斜；<古>使高兴；愿意；<古>听', '1. We should get the samples on the list to check. 我们应该索取目录上的样品来检验一下。 2. She complained about the omission of her name from the list. 她抱怨名单上遗漏了她的名字。 3. He wrote down his name on the list. 他将他的名字写在清单上。 4. Can you give me a price list with specification? 你能否给我一份有规格说明的价目单吗？ 5. We were asked to list our ten favourite songs. 我们应要求列出自己最喜爱的十首歌曲。', '名词: lister 过去式: listed 过去分词: listed 现在分词: listing 第三人称单数: lists');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('isolate', '[\'aɪsəleɪt]', 'vt.使孤立；隔离 adj.孤立的；单独的', '1. We must isolate the handful of enemies to the maximum. 我们要最大限度地孤立一小撮敌人。 2. We should never isolate ourselves from the masses. 我们永远不能脱离群众。 3. The patient should isolate from his child. 这个病人必须立刻和他的孩子隔离。 4. Scientists have isolated the virus causing the epidemic. 科学家们已分离出引起这种流行病的病毒。 5. It would mean inability to close in and isolate him. 这样，就不能把敌人驱逐到狭小的孤立的阵地上去。', '名词: isolator 过去式: isolated 过去分词: isolated 现在分词: isolating 第三人称单数: isolates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('chipmunk', '[\'tʃɪpmʌŋk]', 'n.[动] 花栗鼠', '1. This little chipmunk is hungry. 这只小花栗鼠肚子饿了。 2. A chipmunk is eating popcorn dropped on the roadside. 一只金花鼠在吃掉在路边的爆米花。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dictum', '[\'dɪktəm]', 'n.格言；名言；[律]法官的附带意见', '1. defeat the champion 2. \"All\'s well that ends well\" is the dictum of unanimous common sense. “结果好就一切都好，”这是我们的常识一致公认的名言。 3. Ever sinceWebster\'s dictum has been regarded as a principle of international law 自此，韦伯斯特的正式声明就被遵为国际法原则。', '名词复数: dicta');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scrawl', '[skrɔːl]', 'v.乱涂；潦草地写 n.瞎画；潦草的笔迹', '1. The little child was cautioned not to scrawl on the white wall. 这个小孩被警告不能在雪白的墙上涂鸦。 2. She scrawled a few words on the postcard. 她在明信片上草草地写了几个字。 3. Your beautiful handwriting puts my untidy scrawl to shame. 你漂亮的字体把我的潦草字迹比得见不得人。', '形容词: scrawly 名词: scrawler 过去式: scrawled 过去分词: scrawled 现在分词: scrawling 第三人称单数: scrawls');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('teetotal', '[ˌtiː\'toʊtl]', 'adj.绝对禁酒的；滴酒不沾的；完全的', '1. The wild man of the movies refused to join the teetotal club. 那电影狂人拒绝加入戒酒俱乐部。 2. Most of the time, the French President is teetotal and sticks to fizzy water and orange juice. 法国总统萨科齐绝大多数时候是个禁酒主义者，只喝饮料或橘汁。 3. He won\'t drink because he\'s teetotal. 他不肯喝酒,因为他是滴酒不沾的。 4. Similarly, the IQ of women drinkers showed an improvement of 2.5 points over their teetotal sisters. 同样', '副词: teetotally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('necropolis', '[nə\'krɑːpəlɪs]', 'n.大墓地', '1. The Necropolis floats above the city of Stratholme. 纳克萨玛斯墓地是漂浮在斯坦索姆城市上空的。 2. The Saqqara necropolis is close to Memphis. 塞加拉墓地离孟菲斯很近。 3. Ghost Dragons are the most powerful creature of the Necropolis. 幽灵龙是墓地里最强大的生物。 4. The necropolis was located on a hill outside the city of Rome. 墓地位于罗马城外的一座小山上。', '名词复数: necropolises');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('aplomb', '[ə\'plɑːm]', 'n.自信；沉着；镇静', '1. He delivered the speech with his usual aplomb. 他以惯常的沉着语气作了演讲。 2. She perform the duties of a princess with great aplomb. 她泰然自若地履行王妃的职责。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('thwart', '[θwɔːrt]', 'v.反对；阻碍 n.座板 adv.横过 adj.横向的', '1. She intends to thwart his plans, and be revenged on him. 她要破坏他的计划，以图报复。 2. Sometimes it isn\'t you I hate but your power to thwart me. 有时让我讨厌的并不是你，而是你阻挠我的能力。 3. I don\'t think that will thwart our purposes. 我认为那不会使我们的目的受到挫折。 4. Our course must thwart those designs. 我们的方针是必须挫败他们这种企图。 5. He made the fish fast to bow and stern and to the middle thwart. 他把绑鱼的绳子系在船头、船梢的中间的座板上。', '副词: thwartly 名词: thwarter 过去式: thwarted 过去分词: thwarted 现在分词: thwarting 第三人称单数: thwarts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('filament', '[\'fɪləmənt]', 'n.细丝；细线；灯丝；[植]花丝', '1. The kitchener is cutting a carrot to filament. 厨师正在把胡萝卜磨成细丝。 2. The light of an electric lamp comes from an incandescent filament. 电灯光亮来自白热的灯丝。 3. Originally Edison used platinum alloys for the filament, in the belief that carbon was impracticable. 爱迪生不相信碳可作灯丝用，所以一开始就用铂合金作灯丝。 4. The thread in the corolla is the short filament of a degenerated stamen. 花冠筒内丝状物为退化雄蕊的短花丝。', '形容词: filamentous');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('abandon', '[ə\'bændən]', 'v.放弃；抛弃；放纵 n.放纵', '1. Those who abandon themselves to despair can not succeed. 那些自暴自弃的人无法成功。 2. Despite some difficulties, they\'re not going to abandon the plan. 尽管他们遇到了一些困难,但并不打算放弃这个计划。 3. The cruel man abandoned his wife and child. 那个狠心的男人抛弃了他的妻儿。 4. They abandon themselves to drinking. 他们沉湎于饮酒。 5. He signed cheques with careless abandon. 他无所顾忌地乱开支票。', '名词: abandonment 过去式: abandoned 过去分词: abandoned 现在分词: abandoning 第三人称单数: abandons');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('settled', '[\'setld]', 'adj.固定的；稳定的；定居的 settle的过去式和过去分词.', '1. A desert has no settled population. 沙漠没有固定的居民。 2. Especially the internal training, as a wildly used intervention, has been settled institutionally in some large business organizations. 特别是培训，作为一种较为广泛采用的干预手段，在很多大型企业成为了一种固定的制度而存在下来。 3. There were long periods when settled government can hardly have existed. 在校长的时间内一直未存在过稳定的政府。 4. The gravitational binding means that the galaxies and other material within a mature cluster have settled into an overall dynamic equilibrium. 重力束缚的意思是在一个成熟的星系团中，星系与其他物质已经达到稳定的整体动态平衡。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('simpleton', '[\'sɪmpltən]', 'n.笨蛋；傻子', '1. He tells of a Cuban fisherman who is a simpleton. 他讲的是个愚蠢的古巴渔民。 2. He did not in the least wish the future Mrs. Newland Archor to be a simpleton. 他希望未来的纽兰·阿切尔夫人至少不是头脑简单的人。 3. She represented her little brother as a simpleton. 她把她的弟弟描绘成一个傻瓜。 4. The simpleton wants to be with you together forever! 傻瓜想要永远和你在一起！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('slumber', '[\'slʌmbər]', 'n.睡眠；微睡；休止状态 v.睡觉；打盹；静止；休眠', '1. Don\'t wake him from his slumber because he needs the rest. 不要把他从睡眠中唤醒，因为他需要休息。 2. Three girls are still slumbering peacefully. 3个女孩仍在平静地睡着。', '副词: slumberingly 名词: slumberer 过去式: slumbered 过去分词: slumbered 现在分词: slumbering 第三人称单数: slumbers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fray', '[freɪ]', 'v.恼火；紧张 v.磨损 n.吵闹；吵架；争斗 n.磨损处', '1. Tempers began to fray in the hot weather. 大热天脾气烦燥。 2. As the debate went on, tempers began to fray. 随着辩论的继续，火气就上来了。 3. Her nerves were frayed by the noises in the street. 街上的噪音使她神经紧张。 4. After spending a day with screaming children, her nerves were frayed. 与吵吵嚷嚷的孩子们呆了一天后,她的神经快要崩溃了。 5. The electric wire is fraying and could be dangerous to handle. 电线快磨破了，使用起来可能有危险。 6. The two gangsters seem to be eager for the fray. 那两个歹徒似乎唯恐不乱。', '过去式: frayed 过去分词: frayed 现在分词: fraying 第三人称单数: frays');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pestilent', '[\'pestələnt]', 'adj.致死的；有害的；传染的；讨厌的', '1. I destroy all noisome and rank weeds, I keep down all pestilent vapours. 我摧毁了一切丛生的毒草，控制一切有害的烟雾。 2. To the man of letters it is a missile that he can fling in the reader\'s face to disprove the pestilent heresy. 对于文人，它是一颗导弹，他可以把它投到读者脸上，以驳斥那种有害的邪说。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('canto', '[\'kæntoʊ]', 'n.(长诗的)篇章', '1. It\'s the fourth canto of Byron\'s \"Childe Harold\". 这是拜伦长诗《恰尔德·哈罗尔德游记》的第四章。 2. The Fifth Canto of the Srimad Bhagavatam tells of innumerable universes. 《圣典博伽瓦谭》第五篇讲述了有无数宇宙存在。', '名词复数: cantos');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('presentiment', '[prɪ\'zentɪmənt]', 'n.预感', '1. She often has an ominous presentiment. 她时时有一种不祥的预感。 2. Her presentiment was proved by the next happening things. 接下来发生的事，证实了她的预感。', '形容词: presentimental');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('prelude', '[\'preljuːd]', 'n. 序幕； 前奏； 预兆 vi. 成为 ... 的前奏（开头）', '1. It opened the prelude to Chinese civilization. 这掀开了中华文明的序幕。 2. The rural reform has opened the prelude of China\'s reform and opening-up. 农村改革揭开了中国改革开放的序幕。 3. That is the prelude to a ruined evening. 那一晚的约会就在这前奏声中毁了。 4. An intercultural dialogue should prelude such cooperative undertakings. 文化间的对话应该成为这些合作的前奏。 5. The discussions were a prelude to the treaty. 这些讨论是签订该条约的前奏。', '形容词: preludial 名词: preluder 过去式: preluded 过去分词: preluded 现在分词: preluding 第三人称单数: preludes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('blast', '[blæst]', 'n.爆炸；巨响；一阵(强风)；严厉的批评；<美俚>愉快的经历 v.爆破；摧毁；发出巨响；用力撞击；批评', '1. 27 school children were injured in the blast. 27名学龄儿童在爆炸中受了伤。 2. A blast of the trumpet gave her a start. 突然发出的喇叭声吓了她一跳。 3. A blast of wind blew my hat off. 一阵风吹走了我的帽子。 4. The press responded to his remarks with a blast of criticism. 新闻界以严厉的批评回应了他的言论。 5. A massive car bomb blasted the police headquarters. 一个巨大的汽车炸弹在警局总部爆炸。', '名词: blaster 过去式: blasted 过去分词: blasted 现在分词: blasting 第三人称单数: blasts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('decimate', '[\'desɪmeɪt]', 'v.毁掉大部分；大量杀死；使骤减', '1. Student numbers have been decimated by cuts in grants. 助学金削减後，学生人数大大减少。 2. Disease has decimated the population. 疾病使大部分人死亡。', '名词: decimation 过去式: decimated 过去分词: decimated 现在分词: decimating 第三人称单数: decimates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('spatial', '[\'speɪʃl]', 'adj.空间的', '1. Fluctuations are spatial and temporal in character. 这种波动的特点是空间性和瞬时性的。 2. Men do not excel in all spatial tasks, though. 然而男性也并没有在所以空间问题上都比女性出色。 3. They said that time is the feeling of spatial displacement. 他们说时间是空间位移的感觉。', '副词: spatially 名词: spatiality');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fold', '[foʊld]', 'vt.包；折叠；交叉；拥抱 vi.翻倍；屈服；倒闭 n.折层；折痕', '1. Dark clouds folded the hills. 乌云笼罩着群山。 2. I folded the handkerchief and put it in my pocket. 我折好手绢，放进口袋里。 3. The paper should be folded in half. 这张纸应该对折。 4. The border guard folded his arms across his chest and glared the front. 边防战士双手交叉于胸前紧紧瞪着前方。 5. if a business folds, it closes because it is not able to make enough money. 如果有公司倒闭关门,那是因为它没办法赚取足够的钱。', '形容词: foldable 过去式: folded 过去分词: folded 现在分词: folding 第三人称单数: folds');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('smear', '[smɪr]', 'v.涂抹；弄脏；诽谤 n.污点；涂料；诽谤', '1. We smeared cream on our faces. 我们在脸上搽雪花膏。 2. You should smear your hands with grease. 你该把双手涂上油脂。 3. He smeared some balm on his hand to soothe the pain. 他在手上涂了些药膏来止痛。 4. Don\'t smear the lens; I\'ve just polished it. 别把镜头弄脏了，我刚刚擦过。 5. There was a smear of blood on the wall. 墙上有一片血迹。', '过去式: smeared 过去分词: smeared 现在分词: smearing 第三人称单数: smears');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hypocrite', '[\'hɪpəkrɪt]', 'n.伪君子；伪善者', '1. According to thinking he is a hypocrite. 据认为他是一个伪君子。 2. A hypocrite is an actor, one who puts on a false face. 一个伪善者就像一个演员，戴着假的面具而已。 3. The moral hypocrite, by contrast, has convinced himself that he is acting virtuously even when he does something he would condemn in others. 道德伪善者却不同，他们总是严于律人，宽于律己，认为自己的行为最合乎道德标准。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('objection', '[əb\'dʒekʃn]', 'n.反对；异议', '1. I have no objection to their plan. 我不反对他们的计划。 2. None of them raised any objection. 他们谁也没提出反对意见。 3. He has a strong objection to getting up early. 他强烈反对早起。 4. I see no objection whatsoever. 我没有任何异议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('commence', '[kə\'mens]', 'v.开始；着手；<英>获得学位', '1. I commence from this point. 我从此点开始。 2. The second term commences in March. 第二学期自三月开始。 3. We will commence with this work. 我们要着手进行这项工作。 4. I commence a round of visit. 我开始着手一系列访问。', '名词: commencer 过去式: commenced 过去分词: commenced 现在分词: commencing 第三人称单数: commences');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nauseate', '[\'nɔːzieɪt]', 'v.作呕；产生恶感；厌恶', '1. I began to nauseate the place I was in. 我开始厌恶我所住的地方。', '副词: nauseatingly 名词: nauseation 过去式: nauseated 过去分词: nauseated 现在分词: nauseating 第三人称单数: nauseates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('warrant', '[\'wɔːrənt]', 'n.委任状；凭证；根据；正当理由 vt.担保；保证；辩解；授权', '1. The police obtained a search warrant for his house. 警察拿到了搜查他家的搜查证。 2. Have you got a warrant of fitness for your car? 你有没有一张汽车合格证书? 3. You shouldn\'t arrest him without warrant. 你不能毫无根据地逮捕他。 4. He had no warrant for his suspicion. 他没有理由那么怀疑。 5. I will warrant him an honest and reliable man . 我担保他是个诚实可靠的人。', '形容词: warrantable 副词: warrantably 名词: warrantability 过去式: warranted 过去分词: warranted 现在分词: warranting 第三人称单数: warrants');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('exculpate', '[\'ekskʌlpeɪt]', 'v.为某人开脱；证明无罪', '1. He exculpate himself from a charge of theft. 他辩白自己无盗窃嫌疑。 2. He exculpate himself from stealing the money. 他自行辩白没有偷钱。 3. How would you exculpate for them? 你如何为他们辩解？ 4. Why always have you reason to exculpate for your failure of exams, and never try to through exam one time. 怎么你总是有理由为自己考试不及格开脱，从来没有努力考好过一次。', '形容词: exculpable 名词: exculpation 过去式: exculpated 过去分词: exculpated 现在分词: exculpating 第三人称单数: exculpates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('serial', '[\'sɪriəl]', 'n.连载小说；序列；连续剧 adj.连续的；一系列的', '1. After breakfast, he went on with his serial. 早饭之后,他继续写他的连载故事。 2. Downloaded serial numbers may not be transferred. 下载的序列号不能传输。 3. Please write down your serial number. 请记录下您的序列号。 4. Most of her novels have been made into television serials at some time. 同时她的多数小说拍成了电视连续剧。 5. Currency notes have serial number. 钞票上有连续的号码。', '副词: serially');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unbidden', '[ʌn\'bɪdn]', 'adj.未经请求的；未经邀请的；自动的', '1. He walked into the room unbidden. 他径自走进了屋子。 2. He spoke out unbidden at the meeting. 他在会议上主动发言。 3. They arrived unbidden at the midnight. 他们半夜里不期而至。 4. The words flowed unbidden from my pen. 这些字句从我的笔端滚滚流出。', '异体字: unbid');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fluke', '[fluːk]', 'n.侥幸；偶然的机会；锚爪；比目鱼；吸虫；鲸的尾片', '1. His failure in history examination was a mere fluke. 他历史考试没能及格纯属偶然。 2. She is not usually good at tennis, and that winning stroke was a fluke. 她平时网球打得并不好，那取胜的一击不过是侥幸而已。 3. She was lucky enough to get the job by a fluke. 她实在是够幸运的，能在偶然中得到那份工作。 4. It was only by a fluke that these artifacts were unearthed. 这批文物的出土完全出于偶然。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dimension', '[ˌdɪ\'menʃən]', 'n. 尺寸； 次元； 容积； 维度； 范围； 方面 vt. 标尺寸； 形成 ... 尺寸', '1. Height is an external dimension. 高是外部尺寸。 2. When a dimension\'s origin is in doubt use the datums specified. 当不能确定尺寸原点时，使用规定的基准。 3. The fifth dimension creates everything that is on earth. 第五次元创造了地球上所有的东西。 4. The crystal extractors from that dimension cross through all dimensions. 从那个次元的水晶提取器穿越所有的次元。 5. We were told to dimension off the plots. 吩咐我们在图表上标出尺寸。', '形容词: dimensional 副词: dimensionally 名词: dimensionality 过去式: dimensioned 过去分词: dimensioned 现在分词: dimensioning 第三人称单数: dimensions');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('toll', '[toʊl]', 'n.伤亡人数；钟声；通行费；代价 v.敲钟', '1. The death toll mounted (to 100). 死亡人数上升(至100). 2. The government tried to keep the death toll at a lower level. 政府力图将死亡人数控制在较低标准。 3. We heard the toll of the church bells. 我们听到了教堂大钟传来的钟声。 4. When you hear the bells toll, you\'ll know I\'m not far. 当你听到钟声，就说明我已经在附近了。 5. The church bell tolled the hour. 教堂的鸣钟报时。', '过去式: tolled 过去分词: tolled 现在分词: tolling 第三人称单数: tolls');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('distinguished', '[dɪ\'stɪŋɡwɪʃt]', 'adj.卓越的；尊敬的 动词distinguish的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. The scientist is distinguished in many spheres of knowledge. 这位科学家在许多知识领域中都是杰出的。 2. The Queen conferred knighthood on several distinguished men. 女王将爵士头衔授予几位杰出人士。 3. She is a distinguished novelist and philosopher. 她是一个杰出的小说家和哲学家. 4. Distinguished guests and friends from the media: Good morning! 尊敬的各位来宾,新闻界的朋友们:上午好!', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fascia', '[\'feɪʃə]', 'n.招牌；仪表板；[解]筋膜 =ficia.', '1. Fast rhythm has made fascia way of Chen Tianqiao. 快节奏已经成为陈天桥的招牌招数。 2. No logo or special designs are to be attached to the fascia. 招牌上不允许有商标或者特殊的设计。 3. Disengage fascia from hooks on bottom of front fenders. 将仪表板从前挡泥板底部的挂钩上取下。 4. The superficial fascia is a soft connective tissue located just below the skin. 表面筋膜是一种位于皮肤下方的软结缔组织。', '形容词: fascial 名词复数: fasciae');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('farce', '[fɑːrs]', 'n.闹剧；胡闹；滑稽戏 v.添加笑料；填充', '1. Their negotiations were a farce since their leaders had already made the decision. 他们的谈判简直就是一场荒唐的笑剧，因为他们的领导们早就作出决定了。 2. It seemed to be a farce and it made us doubled up with laugher. 它看起来很像闹剧，我们都笑弯了腰。 3. The trials were a mere farce since no judges were present at all. 这些审判简直是胡闹，因为根本没有法官出席。 4. The play suddenly changes from farce to tragedy. 这部戏突然从闹剧变成悲剧。', '过去式: farced 过去分词: farced 现在分词: farcing 第三人称单数: farces');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('linguistics', '[lɪŋ\'ɡwɪstɪks]', 'n.语言学', '1. He is engaged in studies in linguistics. 他从事于语言学的研究。 2. Literary studies have been cross-fertilized by new ideas in linguistics. 文学研究从语言学方面的新见解中受益良多。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dialect', '[\'daɪəlekt]', 'n.方言；地方话', '1. Every now and then he would lapse into the local dialect. 他讲话中时而不自觉地冒出地方方言。 2. She speaks a dialect, not the Queen\'s English. 她说一口方言，不是标准英语。 3. The dialect is spoken principally in the rural areas. 这种方言主要在农村地区使用。 4. The use of dialect lent great charm to the work . 方言的运用给这部作品增添了巨大的魅力。', '形容词: dialectal 副词: dialectally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('swirl', '[swɜːrl]', 'n.漩涡；涡状形 v.（使）成漩涡；盘旋；眩晕', '1. It beckons me forward with its colorful swirl. 她召唤我走进她美丽的漩涡。 2. The car raced roughly along in a swirl of pink dust. 汽车在一股粉红色尘土的漩涡中颠簸着快速前进。 3. Dancers spun in a swirl of skirts. 跳舞的人旋转着,裙子也不停地打转。 4. The hurricane begins to swirl in a clockwise motion. 飓风开始顺时针打旋。', '形容词: swirly 过去式: swirled 过去分词: swirled 现在分词: swirling 第三人称单数: swirls');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flustered', '[\'flʌstər]', 'n.慌乱；狼狈；混乱 v.使酩醉；慌张；混乱', '1. People fluster ground leaves ship, the woman went up above all with children Immanuel gives birth to a boat. 人们慌乱地离开轮船，妇女和儿童首先上了救世主生船。', '过去式: flustered 过去分词: flustered 现在分词: flustering 第三人称单数: flusters');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('goof', '[ɡuːf]', 'n.愚蠢的人；愚蠢的错误 v.闲混；犯错误；做蠢事；把 ... 弄得一团糟', '1. I told him not to goof around. 我叫他不要游手好闲。 2. You will never be good students so long as you goof around. 如果你们成天游手好闲，就永远也成不了好学生。', '过去式: goofed 过去分词: goofed 现在分词: goofing 第三人称单数: goofs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('quadrangle', '[\'kwɑːdræŋɡl]', 'n.四边形；方形庭院', '1. We walked all over the campus from the quadrangle to the athletic grounds. 我们从方庭到操场，走遍了整个校园。 2. The covers have been installed around a quadrangle at the heart of the school. 顶盖安装在学校中心的一个四方院周围。', '形容词: quadrangular 副词: quadrangularly 名词: quadrangularness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cob', '[kɑːb]', 'n.玉米棒子；雄天鹅；短腿马；圆锥；柴泥灰墁', '1. The farmer was pleased to see his piles of corns on the cob. 农夫很高兴地看着成堆的玉米。 2. This pet rabbit makes a meal of corn on the cob. 这只宠物兔子正在享受一根玉米棒子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gargantuan', '[ɡɑːr\'ɡæntʃuən]', 'adj.巨大的；庞大的', '1. Convertibility of the currency is a gargantuan barrier. 货币的可兑换性就是一个巨大的障碍。 2. When it\'s finished, the gargantuan titanium-and-glass structure will appear to be floating on a man-made lake. 在建成后，这个巨大的钛和玻璃组成的结构将看起来像漂浮在一个人工湖上。 3. That may be a gargantuan figure for Ferrari, but we\'re hearing most of that production run is already spoken for. 这可能是一个庞大的数字，法拉利，但我们听到的大部分生产运行已经谈到的。 4. The preference is evident in the gargantuan New World Department Store in Shanghai\'s commercial heart. 显然，人们首选的是位于上海商业中心庞大的新世界百货商场。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('perish', '[\'perɪʃ]', 'vi.毁灭；消失；腐烂 vt.毁灭；使死亡', '1. We must plan our civilization or we must perish. 我们必须规划我们的文明，否则我们必定毁灭。 2. Almost a hundred people perished in the hotel fire last night. 近百人在昨夜旅馆的大火中丧生。 3. The ancient Aztec culture has all perished now. 古代阿兹台克文化现在已经全部消亡了。 4. Even the best quality rubber will perish with age. 就是最佳质量的橡胶也会因老化而腐烂。 5. Oil on your car tyres will perish them. 在你车胎上的油将会使车胎损坏。', '过去式: perished 过去分词: perished 现在分词: perishing 第三人称单数: perishes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('snip', '[snɪp]', 'n.剪；剪口；剪下的小片；不知天高地厚的人；便宜货 v.剪；剪裁；剪短', '1. With a few quick snip of the shear he prune the bush. 他用大剪刀几下子就把灌木给修剪好了。 2. These typewriters are a snip at 50. 这些打字机是50英镑一台的便宜货。 3. You pick up the scissors and snip the cord. 你拿起剪刀,剪断了那根绳索。 4. He snipped off the corner of the milk carton. 他剪掉牛奶袋的边角。', '过去式: snipped 过去分词: snipped 现在分词: snipping 第三人称单数: snips');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('monopoly', '[mə\'nɑːpəli]', 'n.垄断；独占；专利；控制', '1. Liberty and monopoly cannot live together. 自由与垄断不能并存。 2. The company will become a state-owned monopoly. 这家企业将变成一家国有的垄断企业。 3. Imperialism is the monopoly stage of capitalism. 帝国主义是资本主义的垄断阶段。 4. The government has a monopoly of oil production in that country. 在那个国家，政府独占石油开采权。', '形容词: monopolistic 副词: monopolistically 名词: monopolism 名词复数: monopolies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('affordable', '[ə\'fɔːdəbl]', 'adj.支付得起的；不太昂贵的', '1. Prepaid billing and affordable handsets on their own are not enough to ensure a rapid adoption of mobile phones, however. 然而，预付费系统以及支付得起的手机本身并并不足以确保移动电话的快速普及。 2. What is needed is a monopolistic company, perhaps government run, that can be trusted to provide safe food to the public at an affordable price. 我们需要的是一个垄断企业，可能是政府运作的可以信赖的企业，为公众提供安全可靠的食品，并且价格是公众可以支付得起的。 3. You can see by the architecture and furnishings that the original plan for this hotel was to be a trendy, yet affordable boutique hotel. 通过建筑和家具你可以看到原计划是要将它建成流行却不太昂贵的多功能旅馆。', '副词: affordably 名词: affordability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('snobbish', '[\'snɑːbɪʃ]', 'adj.势利的；自命不凡的', '1. Everyone was annoyed by his snobbish attitude. 所有的每个人都对他势利的态度反感。 2. Jane feels she can never compete with these snobbish, elegant people. 简·爱感到她永远无法同这些高雅却势利的人们竞争。 3. It is strange that he should fall in love with such a snobbish girl. 说来真怪，他居然与那位高傲的女孩子坠入情网。', '副词: snobbishly 名词: snobbishness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('perspicuity', '[ˌpɜːspɪ\'kjuːətɪ]', 'n.明晰；明了；简明', '1. For me in present\'s study life middle finger perspicuity direction. 为我在今后的学习生活,指明了方向。 2. But before Japanese bosses celebrate, they may want to consider that this golden opportunity is hardly the result of business perspicuity. 但是在庆祝他们的战利品之前，那些日本经理人或许应该明白：获得这次难得的机会决不是因为他们通晓商业经营之道。 3. It is possible to meet the needs of harmonious city through the perspicuity, marketlization and institutionalization of urban planning interest. 通过城市规划利益明晰化、市场化、制度化来适应和谐城市的要求。 4. Some people have a foolish trick of applying for aid before they have done anything whatever to aid themselves, and in fact try to talk themselves into perspicuity. 隐匿无状的神经疾病、幻想肆疟的抑郁、一发而不可收拾的种种欲念之所以骇人，正是由于人们错认它们为罕有。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inherit', '[ɪn\'herɪt]', 'v.继承；遗传', '1. The eldest son will inherit the title. 长子将继承爵位。 2. She inherited a house from her father. 她从她父亲那儿继承了一所房子。 3. The two children both inherit left-handedness from their parents. 这两个孩子都从父母身上遗传了左撇子。', '名词: inheritor 过去式: inherited 过去分词: inherited 现在分词: inheriting 第三人称单数: inherits');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('uproar', '[\'ʌprɔːr]', 'n.骚动；喧嚣', '1. The exorbitant fees caused an uproar across the land. 高昂的收费在整个地区引起了一场骚动。 2. We remained under cover for about two months until the uproar subsided. 骚动平息之前，我们躲了将近两个月。 3. His motion threw the meeting into an uproar. 他的建议在会上引起了一片吵嚷。 4. The subsequent uproar ended the class. 接下来的喧嚣结束了那堂课。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('viability', '[ˌvaɪə\'bɪləti]', 'n.生存能力；发育能力；可行性', '1. The debate over the viability of the Net\'s premier retailer is really about the future of e-commerce itself. 关于网络头号零售商生存能力的讨论事关电子商务自身的未来。 2. In it, each describes specific steps they plan to take to get on the road to economic viability. 其中，每家都描述他们计划在到达经济生存能力的道路上采取的具体步骤。 3. We review the advances in the assessment of the embryo viability based on the embryo physiology. 本文就胚胎生理特征的研究用于胚胎发育能力评估方面的进展做一综述。 4. And finally I\'ll discuss the viability of the project. 最后我要谈谈这一项目的可行性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('obstinate', '[\'ɑːbstɪnət]', 'adj.固执的；倔强的；不易屈服的；（病）难治的', '1. The obstinate child refused to answer. 这固执的孩子拒绝回答。 2. Because their hearts had turned hard, stubborn and obstinate. 重点是在于他们的心已经是硬的，是固执的，是顽固的。 3. He examined my obstinate expression, and switched to another line of attack. 他打量着一脸倔强的我，又转移战地。 4. Only a man full of the milk of human kindness could have continued to befriend the proud and obstinate young man. 只有天性善良的人才会和这个性情高傲脾气倔强的年轻人继续交往。', '副词: obstinately 名词: obstinateness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('equable', '[\'ekwəbl]', 'adj.性情温和的；变动小的', '1. It\'s lucky that his parents are so equable. 值得庆幸的是他双亲性情非常温和。 2. I like working with John because he\'s so calm and equable. 我喜欢和约翰一起工作，因为他性情沉着稳重。 3. He was too equable to fret over the demands that were laid on him. 他心平气和，不因众说纷纭而坐立不安。 4. This Mediterranean peninsula had a salubrious climate and an equable temperature. 这个地中海半岛拥有怡人的气候，气温变化较小。', '副词: equably 名词: equability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('resurrect', '[ˌrezə\'rekt]', 'v.使复活；复兴；挖出', '1. It is said that this medicine can resurrect the dead. 据说这种药能起死回生。 2. They will resurrect you at the graveyard with your gear intact. 他们会在墓地使你复活,带有完整的物品。 3. Barack Obama\'s team wants to resurrect deficit-control rules. 奥巴马团队想要赤字控制法规的回归。 4. This class shows how an object can resurrect itself. 这个类演示了如何复原自己。', '名词: resurrector 过去式: resurrected 过去分词: resurrected 现在分词: resurrecting 第三人称单数: resurrects');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('potential', '[pə\'tenʃl]', 'adj.潜在的；可能的 n.潜力；潜能 n.电位；电势', '1. These potential effects must be studied carefully. 这些潜在的影响必须仔细地加以研究。 2. Aha! Now that \'s something that has potential . 啊！ 现在这好像是很有可能的。 3. She has acting potential, but she needs training. 她有表演潜力，但需要训练。 4. He hasn\'t realized his full potential yet. 他还没有意识到他的全部潜能。 5. We can only measure the difference between the potentials of two half cells when they are linked to form an electrochemical cell. 当两个半电池连接形成一个化学电池时,我们仅能测定两个半电池之间电位的差值。', '副词: potentially');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tidy', '[\'taɪdi]', 'adj.整齐的；整洁的；<口>相当大的 vt.整理；使整洁 vi.整理；收拾', '1. She keeps her house very tidy. 她保持她的住所整整齐齐。 2. They sat in her neat and tidy kitchen. 他们坐在她那干净整齐的厨房里。 3. He has a tidy mind. 他的思维有条理。 4. Her clothes were clean and tidy. 她的衣服干净整洁。 5. His room is in a clutter so I have to tidy it up. 他的房间乱七八糟的，我不得不整理一下。 6. You\'d better tidy up before the guests arrive. 客人们到达前,你最好先把东西整理一下。', '副词: tidily 比较级: tidier 最高级: tidiest 名词: tidiness 名词复数: tidies 过去式: tidied 过去分词: tidied 现在分词: tidying 第三人称单数: tidies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mill', '[mɪl]', 'n.磨坊；工厂；磨粉机 v.碾碎；磨；（使）乱转', '1. He sends his crop to a large mill instead of grinding it himself. 他把收获的庄稼送到大磨坊去，而不是自己碾磨。 2. The logs are drifted downstream to the mill. 那些原木沿河顺水漂到工厂。 3. Com is ground into flour in a mill. 谷物在磨粉机里磨成粉。 4. He used a miller to mill the grain into flour. 他用碾磨机把谷物磨成面粉。', '过去式: milled 过去分词: milled 现在分词: milling 第三人称单数: mills');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dealing', '[\'diːlɪŋ]', 'n.经营方法；行为态度 (复数）dealings:商务往来； 交往. 动词deal的现在分词.', '1. They have a harder time dealing with fellow women. 她们更难与其他女性交往。 2. He has no tact in dealing with people. 他为人太傻，不知怎样与人交往。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('abreast', '[ə\'brest]', 'adv.并肩地；跟上', '1. The four of them walked abreast. 四人并肩而行。 2. They walked two or three abreast. 他们两三个人一排地走着。 3. Hayes\' horse fell abreast of his father\'s. 海斯和他父亲骑马并肩而行。 4. Many people stood abreast to listen to him. 许多人并肩站着听他说话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('instigate', '[\'ɪnstɪɡeɪt]', 'vt.教唆；怂恿；煽动；鼓动', '1. They instigated him to the evil deed. 他们教唆他做坏事。 2. He wouldn\'t throw the rock if that boy did not instigate him. 要不是那些男孩子怂恿他,他不会扔那块石头。 3. He instigated the ending of a free working lunch in the company. 他煽动取消公司的免费工作午餐。 4. He accused union leaders of instigating the disturbances. 他指责工会领导鼓动骚乱。', '形容词: instigative 名词: instigation 过去式: instigated 过去分词: instigated 现在分词: instigating 第三人称单数: instigates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cobbler', '[\'kɑːblər]', 'n.补鞋匠；脆皮水果馅饼；（酒、糖、柠檬汁混合的）冷饮；<古>笨拙的工匠', '1. This cobbler is rather clumsy. 这个补鞋匠真是笨手笨脚。 2. The cobbler is a spy in disguise. 补鞋匠是个伪装的间谍。 3. Cobbler should stick to his last. 补鞋匠只应守鞋楦头，人人各守本业，对别人的事少掺和。 4. I liked the cobbler you made the other day. 我喜欢你那天做的酒味冷饮。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('relinquish', '[rɪ\'lɪŋkwɪʃ]', 'vt.放弃；放手', '1. I had relinquished all hopes that she was alive. 我已经放弃了她还活着的一切希望。 2. Finally he relinquished his plan for want of business. 因生意需要他只好放弃计划。 3. He relinquished his share to his partner. 他把他的股权让给了他的合伙人。 4. She relinquished possession of the house to her sister. 她把房子的所有权让给了她妹妹。', '名词: relinquisher 过去式: relinquished 过去分词: relinquished 现在分词: relinquishing 第三人称单数: relinquishes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('irradiate', '[ɪ\'reɪdieɪt]', 'v.照耀；辐射；(使)灿烂；(使)明亮', '1. Your halo will irradiate me forever. 你的圣光将永远照耀着我。 2. We irradiate the desert with slow neutrons. 我们用低速中子照射整个沙漠。 3. The hall is not dim; the four large lamps irradiate it. 大厅并不昏暗,四盏巨大的灯照亮了它。', '形容词: irradiative 名词: irradiator 过去式: irradiated 过去分词: irradiated 现在分词: irradiating 第三人称单数: irradiates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('subtract', '[səb\'trækt]', 'vt.减去 vi.减少', '1. If you subtract 2 from 8, you get 6. 8减去2是6。 2. Please subtract a quarter of the money for your own use. 请扣除四分之一的钱由你自己支配使用。 3. The little girl has begin to learn to add and subtract. 这小女孩已在学做加减法了。', '名词: subtracter 过去式: subtracted 过去分词: subtracted 现在分词: subtracting 第三人称单数: subtracts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('intercede', '[ˌɪntər\'siːd]', 'v.仲裁；说情；调解', '1. He was quickly snubbed when he tried to intercede. 当他试着说情时很快被制止了。 2. The governor promised to interced with the Home Office on behalf of the girl. 主管人员答应替那个女孩向内政部说情。 3. Farm and labor movements began to ask the government to intercede on their behalf. 农民和劳工运动开始要求政府代表他们出面调解。', '名词: interceder 过去式: interceded 过去分词: interceded 现在分词: interceding 第三人称单数: intercedes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incinerate', '[ɪn\'sɪnəreɪt]', 'v.焚化(废物)；烧成灰；火化', '1. The flames of my rage will incinerate you! 我的怒火将把你熔为灰烬! 2. Incinerate can now be turned on or off. 烧弃现在能够被选择关闭或开启。 3. YesAttack1 - \"I\'ll incinerate them. \" -我来把他们烧成灰烬。 4. Glyph of Incinerate: Increases damage of Incinerate by 5%. 烧尽雕文：提升烧尽的伤害5%25。', '名词: incineration 过去式: incinerated 过去分词: incinerated 现在分词: incinerating 第三人称单数: incinerates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dour', '[\'daʊər]', 'adj.严厉的；不爱讲话的；沉沉的', '1. I\'m sick of dour faces staring at me from the T. V. tower. 我厌倦了电视台里瞪着我的那些严厉的面孔。 2. He was a silent, precise man with a dour nature and a hard Aberdonian accent. 他是一个沉默寡言、一丝不苟的人，性格倔强，带有很重的阿伯丁港的口音。 3. She always pretends to be dour, in fact, she\'s not. 她总表现的不爱讲话，事实却相反。 4. When it comes to more mainstream services, staff are dour and unhelpful. 当它涉及更多主流的服务时职员就会变得阴郁和无助。', '副词: dourly 比较级: dourer 最高级: dourest 名词: dourness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incorporeal', '[ˌɪnkɔːr\'pɔːriəl]', 'adj.无实体的；精神的；无形的', '1. They seemed to have the power to touch the incorporeal and see the invisible. 他们似乎有一种力量能触摸到无形的和看到不可见的东西。', '副词: incorporeally 名词: incorporeality');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tutelage', '[\'tuːtəlɪdʒ]', 'n.监护；指导；托管', '1. I gained valuable training under his tutelage. 在他的监护下,我得到有价值的训练。 2. Under the tutelage of a master craftsman,he made a great progress. 在工艺大师的指导下，他取得了重大进步。 3. A new regime was installed under French tutelage. 在法国的托管下，一个新政权成立了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('putative', '[\'pjuːtətɪv]', 'adj.假定的；被公认的', '1. There have been many attempts to track down the putative Loch Ness monster. 人们为追踪假定存在的尼斯湖水怪做了许多努力。 2. The putative leader of the terrorist organization was arrested by police in Birmingham yesterday. 此恐怖组织的公认领导人昨天在伯明罕被警方逮捕。', '副词: putatively');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rancor', '[\'ræŋkə]', 'n.敌意；恨意', '1. I know now that I could talk to the man who shot me and feel no rancor. 如果现在我见到当年击中我的狙击手，我会不带任何敌意地对待他。', '形容词: rancorous 副词: rancorously 名词: rancorousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('enthrall', '[ɪn\'θrɔːl]', 'v.迷住；迷惑；奴役', '1. Such trends do not enthrall neutrals, many of whom would prefer to see free-scoring Barcelona win tomorrow. 这些趋势并没有迷惑住中立者，他们中的很多人更愿意火力十足的巴萨明天赢球。 2. They should have been noticed, but a wizard who could enthrall an army of abyssal beasts could delude a few pilots and guards, especially the night after Fleetswake. 他们应该已经被注意到，但一个能奴役深渊野兽大军的法师，自然也能迷惑几个领航员和守卫了，特别是在舰队尾波节的夜里。 3. They should have been noticed, but a wizard who could enthrall an army of abyssal beasts could delude a few pilots and guards, especially the night after Fleetswake. 他们应该已经被注意到，但一个能奴役深渊野兽大军的法师，自然也能迷惑几个领航员和守卫了，特别是在舰队尾波节的夜里。', '副词: enthrallingly 异体字: inthrall 名词: enthrallment 过去式: enthralled 过去分词: enthralled 现在分词: enthralling 第三人称单数: enthralls');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('panel', '[\'pænl]', 'n.嵌板；仪表盘；面板；座谈小组；陪审团 v.嵌镶', '1. The builders set the panel in carefully. 建筑工人把嵌板小心地镶上去。 2. The worker will check functions of instrument panel. 工人将检查仪表盘功能。 3. Solar panels are used to power satellites. 太阳能面板用来给卫星提供动力。 4. The date for the panel discussion is fixed now. 座谈会的日期现已确定。 5. He panelled the wall with wood. 他在墙上镶上木板。', '过去式: paneled/panelled 过去分词: paneled/panelled 现在分词: paneling/panelling 第三人称单数: panels/panels');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('recumbent', '[rɪ\'kʌmbənt]', 'adj.侧卧的；休息的', '1. It glided noiselessly towards the recumbent woman. 它无声无息地向那斜倚着的女人走去。 2. The picnickers were recumbent on thick moss under a big tree. 野餐的人们在大树下厚厚的苔藓上舒适地躺着。', '副词: recumbently 名词: recumbence');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('governance', '[\'ɡʌvərnəns]', 'n.统治；支配；管理', '1. The most extreme failure of governance is violent conflict. 统治的最大失败就是暴力冲突。 2. This is an important basis for our governance. 这是政府管治能力的重要依据。', '动词: govern 形容词: governing');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flagellate', '[\'flædʒəleɪt]', 'vt.鞭打 adj.像鞭子的；鞭笞的 n.(有鞭毛的)原生动物', '1. Relating to or caused by a flagellate organism. 鞭毛虫的或由鞭毛虫引起的 2. Rootstock horizontal, flagellate or moniliform. 根茎水平，具鞭状匍匐枝的或念珠状。 3. A flagellate protozoan, such as a trypanosome, that is parasitic in the blood. 血鞭毛虫一种鞭毛原生动物，如锥体虫，寄生于血液之中 4. A flagellate protozoan,such as a trypanosome,that is parasitic in the blood. 血鞭毛虫一种鞭毛原生动物，如锥体虫，寄生于血液之中', '过去式: flagellated 过去分词: flagellated 现在分词: flagellating 第三人称单数: flagellates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('squat', '[skwɑːt]', 'v.蹲下；蹲坐；擅自占地 adj.蹲着的；矮胖胖的；低矮的 n.蹲；擅自占用的土地', '1. The old man squatted down by the fire. 老人蹲在炉火旁。 2. The savages squat around the fire. 野人们围火蹲着。 3. A squat figure sat in front of the fire. 一个蹲坐的人形坐在火炉的前面。 4. It was five times his squat height, and it would take thirty Unggoy to circumscribe its curved surface. 有他蹲坐五倍高，它的圆形弯曲的表面需要三十个温皋彝才能环抱。 5. A squat figure sat in front of the fire. 一个蹲坐的人形坐在火炉的前面。 6. The two techniques are the split and the squat. 这两种技术是箭步式和下蹲式。', '比较级: squatter 最高级: squattest 名词: squatter 过去式: squatted 过去分词: squatted 现在分词: squatting 第三人称单数: squats');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('faucet', '[\'fɔːsɪt]', 'n.水龙头', '1. The water from the faucet was cloudy. 水龙头里流出的水很混浊。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rinse', '[rɪns]', 'v.清洗；冲洗 n.清洗；染发；柔顺剂', '1. Rinse the clay from the face with a wet washcloth. 用一块湿毛巾将泥清洗干净。 2. Rinse your hair thoroughly after shampooing it. 用洗发剂洗头后,要把头发冲洗干净。 3. Use hot water to rinse the congealed fat off the dinner plates. 用热水把菜盘上凝结的油渍冲洗掉。 4. Give the plate a final rinse in cold water. 将餐具放在冷水里最后冲洗一次。', '形容词: rinsable 名词: rinser 过去式: rinsed 过去分词: rinsed 现在分词: rinsing 第三人称单数: rinses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('expressly', '[ɪk\'spresli]', 'adv.清楚地；特意地；专门地', '1. I expressly told him I wouldn\'t go. 我清楚地告诉他,我不愿去。 2. I told you expressly to lock the door. 我明白地对你说过要锁上门。 3. You were expressly told not to touch my papers. 已经明确地告诉过你不要动我的文件。 4. The rule was introduced expressly for this purpose. 这项规则是为此特意提出的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stolid', '[\'stɑːlɪd]', 'adj.不易激动的；冷漠的；神经麻木的', '1. He conceals his feelings behind a rather stolid manner. 他装作无动於衷的样子以掩盖自己的感情。 2. He glanced furtively at the stolid faces of the two detectives. 他偷偷瞥见两名侦探冷漠的脸。', '副词: stolidly 比较级: stolider 最高级: stolidest 名词: stolidity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('subsistence', '[səb\'sɪstəns]', 'n.生存；生计；存在', '1. Subsistence is not possible in such conditions. 在这种情况下是无法生存的。 2. Without the right to work, there will be no guarantee for the right to subsistence. 没有劳动权，生存权利也就没有保障。 3. They had no visible means of subsistence. 他们生计无着。 4. Even if it is also written to help people write letters to be a subsistence living. 哪怕是代笔替人写书信也能够成为一个维持生计的活。', '形容词: subsistent');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('immortal', '[ɪ\'mɔːrtl]', 'adj.不朽的；永世的 n.不朽的人物；神', '1. The spirits of the brave departed will be immortal. 英灵永在。 2. He left behind an immortal example to all posterity. 他给后世留下了不朽的典范。 3. Some people believe that the spirit is immortal. 有人相信灵魂不灭。 4. The little girl is very interested in the old legend of immortal creatures. 小女孩对有关永生的精灵的古老传奇非常感兴趣。 5. Shakespeare is one of the immortals. 莎士比亚是不朽的人物之一。', '副词: immortally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('amethyst', '[\'æməθɪst]', 'n.紫水晶；紫色', '1. Amethyst was considered to be the “papal stone”. 紫水晶也被视为了“罗马教之玉”。 2. The exquisite flowers come alive in shades of amethyst. 那些漂亮的花儿在紫水晶的映衬下显得格外夺目。 3. His eyes deepened into amethyst. 他眼睛里的血丝变成了紫色。', '形容词: amethystine');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tempest', '[\'tempɪst]', 'n.暴风雨；骚动', '1. The tempest drove the ship on the rocks. 暴风雨使船触了礁。 2. The tempest seems to be calming down. 暴风雨似乎正在平息下来。 3. The tempest had been as brief as terrific. 这一场暴风雨持续的时间虽然不长，但是却十分凶猛。 4. The political tempest finally subsided. 这场政治风暴终于平息了。', '过去式: tempested 过去分词: tempested 现在分词: tempesting 第三人称单数: tempests');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('befuddle', '[bɪ\'fʌdəl]', 'vt.使昏迷；使迷惑；使烂醉', '1. The new arrival was befuddled by the rapid-fire conversation. 新到达者被连珠炮似的谈话弄糊涂了。 2. Don\'t befuddle me with all those masses of detail. 不要拿一大堆琐事把我搞迷糊。 3. He also fabricates sensational lies to befuddle world opinion. 他也编造耸人听闻的谎言欺骗世界舆论。 4. John is very amusing when he is completely befuddled. 当约翰喝得完全糊涂了的时候，他非常有趣儿。', '过去式: befuddled 过去分词: befuddled 现在分词: befuddling 第三人称单数: befuddles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('merit', '[\'merɪt]', 'n.优点；功绩；价值 v.值得；应得', '1. This method at least had the merit of simplicity. 这种办法至少有简单明了的优点。 2. Charms strikes the sight, but merit wins the soul. 美貌吸引目光,优点赢得心灵。 3. That will subtract nothing from his merit. 那将无损于他的功绩。 4. Promotion should be based on merit alone. 晋升应完全根据功绩。 5. His new achievements merit our attention. 他取得的新成就值得关注。', '形容词: meritless 过去式: merited 过去分词: merited 现在分词: meriting 第三人称单数: merits');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('oleaginous', '[ˌoʊli\'ædʒɪnəs]', 'adj.含油的；油腻的', '1. The doctor advised him not to eat oleaginous food. 医生建议他不要吃油腻的食品。', '副词: oleaginously 名词: oleaginousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('figurine', '[ˌfɪɡjə\'riːn]', 'n.小塑像；小雕像', '1. She bought an exquisite china figurine. 她买了一尊小巧而精致的瓷塑像。 2. One month later, Dr Stauble found what could be the matching female figurine. 一个月后,斯陶布莱教授又发现了与其匹配的女性雕像。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('adjacent', '[ə\'dʒeɪsnt]', 'adj.邻近的；毗连的；接近的', '1. The house adjacent to ours has been sold. 与我们家邻接的房子已经售出。 2. His house is adjacent to mine. 他的寓所与我的相毗连。 3. The planes landed on adjacent runways. 这些飞机在毗连的跑道上降落。 4. The island of Cuba is adjacent to Florida. 古巴岛接近佛罗里达。', '副词: adjacently');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('desiccate', '[\'desɪˌkeɪt]', 'v.（使）干；干贮', '1. Tympanic center leaves the alveolus of one desiccate. 鼓膜中心则留下一变干的小孔。 2. At quintuple seven, when the yang min channel declines, the face starts to desiccate and hair to come off. 五七阳明脉衰,面始焦,发始堕。 3. Why is the skin very black? Wash wash again do not go, but see namely very dirty ah? How to make neck desiccate clean? 为什么皮肤很黑？洗又洗不去，但是就是看到很脏啊？怎样让脖子变干净？ 4. Reduce marcel: Clean thick and curly hair to be able to make everyday hair desiccate. 减少烫发：天天清洗厚而卷曲的头发会使头发变干。', '形容词: desiccative 名词: desiccation 过去式: desiccated 过去分词: desiccated 现在分词: desiccating 第三人称单数: desiccates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dwelling', '[\'dwelɪŋ]', 'n.住处；住宅', '1. He changed his dwelling recently. 他最近搬了家。 2. The smoke betrays where the dwelling lies. 炊烟起处有人家。 3. Our stable abuts against his dwelling. 我们的马厩和他的住所毗连。 4. We weathered out the winter in a lonely dwelling. 我们在一所偏僻的房子里熬过了冬天。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('boisterous', '[\'bɔɪstərəs]', 'adj.喧闹的；狂暴的', '1. But a boisterous freedom was in the air. 但空气中弥漫着放纵喧闹的气氛。 2. We can hear their boisterous laughter in the next room. 我们可以听到他们在隔壁房间的喧闹的笑声。 3. The infinite sky is motionless overhead and the restless water is boisterous. 头上是静止的无垠的天空,不息的海水狂暴。', '副词: boisterously 名词: boisterousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sag', '[sæɡ]', 'v.下垂；下跌；消沉 n.下垂；下跌；凹陷；[航海]随风漂流', '1. And higher currents will heat the lines, which could then sag dangerously close to trees and structures. 加大电流则会提高电线温度，让电线下垂，接近树木和建筑物，增加危险。 2. As a result, the skin may sag. 结果，皮肤就松弛下垂了。 3. Many prices had reached plateaus, some were beginning to sag. 许多物价已升至平稳，有些则开始下跌。 4. And higher currents will heat the lines, which could then sag dangerously close to trees and structures. 加大电流则会提高电线温度，让电线下垂，接近树木和建筑物，增加危险。', '过去式: sagged 过去分词: sagged 现在分词: sagging 第三人称单数: sags');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cogitate', '[\'kɑːdʒɪteɪt]', 'v.思考；考虑', '1. I need a few days to cogitate the problem. 我需要几天的时间来思考这问题。 2. They will cogitate over policy, and they will issue grave decisions on sustainable development. 他们会仔细考虑一些政策，对持续发展的问题作出重大决定。', '名词: cogitator 过去式: cogitated 过去分词: cogitated 现在分词: cogitating 第三人称单数: cogitates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('grace', '[ɡreɪs]', 'n.优美；优雅；恩惠 vt.使优美；使荣耀', '1. She performed on the balance beam with much grace. 她在平衡木上表演得非常优美。 2. She was a beautiful girl with the grace and poise of a natural model. 她是一个美丽的姑娘，有着模特儿的那种优雅姿态。 3. By the grace of God their lives were spared. 蒙上帝恩宠 4. Fine paintings graced the walls of the room. 这些精美的绘画使四壁生辉。', '过去式: graced 过去分词: graced 现在分词: gracing 第三人称单数: graces');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stereotype', '[\'steriətaɪp]', 'n.模式化观念；典型；老一套；铅版 v.对…形成模式化的看法；使用铅版', '1. He doesn\'t conform to the usual stereotype of the city businessman with a dark suit and rolled umbrella. 他不像典型的城市商人那样，穿一身深色的套服、 带一把收好的雨伞。 2. He fits the stereotype of a scholar. 他是典型的学者。 3. The idea is an old-fashioned stereotype. 这观点是老一套了。 4. It\'s wrong to stereotype people. 把人看作都是一样的是错误的。', '形容词: stereotypic 副词: stereotypically 名词: stereotyper 过去式: stereotyped 过去分词: stereotyped 现在分词: stereotyping 第三人称单数: stereotypes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('elm', '[elm]', 'n.榆树；榆木', '1. We planted some elms in the yard. 我们在院子里种了一些榆树。 2. The farmhouse is dignified by the great elm around it. 这家农舍由于周围的大榆树而增光不少。 3. They have lopped away the biggest of the branches of that elm overhanging the road. 他们把那棵榆树低垂在公路上的最大的枝子砍掉了。 4. Water pipes used to be made out of elm. 水管过去是用榆木做的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ignominious', '[ˌɪɡnə\'mɪniəs]', 'adj.可耻的；不名誉的', '1. The waste is one kind of ignominious behavior. 浪费是一种可耻的行为。 2. The conspiracy frittered away to an ignominious conclusion. 那个阴谋以可耻的失败而告终。 3. He made one mistake and his career came to an ignominious end. 他犯了一个错误，他的事业就很不体面地结束了。 4. There is a long, ignominious tradition in this nation of violence toward newcomers. 这个国家有个不光彩的传统，那就是对于初来乍到者的不友好。', '副词: ignominiously 名词: ignominiousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('brand', '[brænd]', 'n.烙印；商标；牌子；标记 vt.加污名于；铭记；打烙印', '1. As an author who was in a period when the new and the old interlaced, Cervantes had a brand of two ages inevitably. 作为新旧两个时代交替期的作家,塞万提斯身上不可避免地带有两个时代的烙印。 2. You may personalize the design to match your company\'s existing brand identity and design specifications. 您也可以进行个性化设计,使其符合公司的现有商标与设计规范。 3. The advertising manager may set as a goal for advertising an increase of 15 percent in consumer brand awareness in the next six months. 广告经理确定的目标为:在今后的6个月里，通过广告，提高消费者商标知晓率的15%25。 4. She\'s gone over to a milder brand of cigarettes. 她已改吸另一牌子味道较淡的香烟。 5. Those who have triumphantly withstood such strains may brand his name. 那些成功地经受了严峻考验的人们或许会污辱他的名声。', '名词: brander 过去式: branded 过去分词: branded 现在分词: branding 第三人称单数: brands');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('formative', '[\'fɔːrmətɪv]', 'adj.形成的；造形的；影响发展的 n.[语]构词成分', '1. Savagery was the formative period of the human race. 蒙昧阶段是人类的形成阶段。 2. This article talks about development of Chinese furniture from formative element, structural characteristic, decoration style and material. 本文从造型要素、结构特征、装饰风格、材料等方面探讨了中式家具的开发途径。 3. Her first year at college was a formative experience. 她大学的第一年是对其人生经历很有影响的一年。 4. Her formative years were spent in Los Angeles. 她的成长阶段是在洛杉矶度过的。', '副词: formatively');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('adamant', '[\'ædəmənt]', 'adj.坚定不移的；固执的 n.坚硬无比之物；硬石', '1. She was quite adamant that she would not come. 她坚决不来。 2. On this point I am adamant. 在这一点上我是坚定不移的。 3. She was adamant in refusing to comply with his wishes. 她固执地拒绝按他的意愿办。 4. She became as rigid as adamant. 她变得如顽石般的固执。', 'none');
