INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('circumvent', '[ˌsɜːrkəm\'vent]', 'vt.绕行；设法避开；围住', '1. We went north in order to circumvent the mountains. 我们向北行驶为了从高山绕行。 2. She planned a way to circumvent all the bureaucratic red tape. 她计划避开官僚体制下的繁文缛礼。 3. The company has opened an office abroad in order to circumvent our tax laws. 公司在国外设立一个办事处，以躲避我国的税法。 4. There is a little island circumvented by a river. 这是河流环绕的小岛。', '形容词: circumventive 名词: circumventer 过去式: circumvented 过去分词: circumvented 现在分词: circumventing 第三人称单数: circumvents');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sprint', '[sprɪnt]', 'vi.全力奔跑；冲刺 n.短距离赛跑；冲刺', '1. She sprinted off into the distance. 她飞快地跑了。 2. You\'ll have to sprint if you want to catch the train. 你要想赶上火车，就得快跑几步。 3. He had to sprint to catch the bus. 他得猛跑一阵才能赶上公共汽车。 4. He sprinted past the other runners just before reaching the tape. 他在到达终点之前全速冲刺，超越了其他赛跑者。 5. Can you explain to me the tactics in a sprint? 你能给我解释一下短距离赛的战术吗?', '名词: sprinter 过去式: sprinted 过去分词: sprinted 现在分词: sprinting 第三人称单数: sprints');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stalemate', '[\'steɪlmeɪt]', 'n.僵局；和棋；僵持状态；陷于困境 v.使陷入僵局；使陷入困境', '1. Negotiations have reached a stalemate. 谈判陷入了僵局。 2. His tricks will bring us into a stalemate. 他的花招会使我们陷入僵局。 3. The match ended in a stalemate. 比赛最终以和棋结束。 4. The war situation has been stalemated. 战争局势陷入了僵持阶段。', '过去式: stalemated 过去分词: stalemated 现在分词: stalemating 第三人称单数: stalemates');
