INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('instantaneous', '[ˌɪnstən\'teɪniəs]', 'adj.瞬间的；即刻的', '1. Relief was instantaneous. 痛苦的消除是瞬间的事 2. Death is instantaneous in a fatal accident. 在致命的事故中，死亡是即刻发生的。 3. The reaction of the audience was instantaneous. 观众即刻有了反应。 4. He had an instantaneous response. 他立刻作了反应。', '副词: instantaneously 名词: instantaneity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('apparition', '[ˌæpə\'rɪʃn]', 'n.鬼；幽灵；幻影', '1. You look as though you\'ve seen an apparition. 你好象撞见了鬼似的。 2. He saw the apparition of his dead wife. 他看见了亡妻的幽灵。 3. Whenever I go I am faced with an apparition which completely upsets me. 无论我走到哪里,总有一个幻影搅的我六神不安。', '形容词: apparitional');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mason', '[\'meɪsn]', 'n.石匠；泥瓦匠 Mason. n.梅森(人名)；共济会会员', '1. He asked the mason to make him a tombstone. 他要求这个石匠给他做一块墓碑。 2. He carved marble faster than any mason. 他雕刻大理石的速度比任何石匠都快。 3. The mason flushed the joint with mortar. 泥工用灰浆把接缝处嵌平。', '过去式: masoned 过去分词: masoned 现在分词: masoning 第三人称单数: masons');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('excoriate', '[ˌeks\'kɔːrieɪt]', 'vt.撕去皮；严厉批评', '1. To criticize severely and devastatingly; excoriate. 严厉地和带毁灭性地批评;狠批。 2. To assail with stinging criticism;excoriate. 痛责以尖刻的批评攻击；严厉地批评 3. To assail with stinging criticism; excoriate. 痛责:以尖刻的批评攻击;严厉地批评。 4. To criticize severely and devastatingly;excoriate. 严厉地和带毁灭性地批评；', '名词: excoriation 过去式: excoriated 过去分词: excoriated 现在分词: excoriating 第三人称单数: excoriates');
