INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('peripheral', '[pə\'rɪfərəl]', 'adj.外围的；不重要的 n.外围设备', '1. We dealt with the peripheral aspects of a cost reduction program. 我们谈到了降低成本计划的一些外围问题。 2. The talks made progress on peripheral issues, but failed to resolve the main dispute between the two sides. 谈判在次要的问题上取得了进展,但是没能解决双方的主要争端。 3. Unfortunately, the speeds of peripheral devices have not kept pace. 不幸的是外围设备的速度跟不上主机。 4. It minimizes distortion and peripheral vignetting at the wide end. 资讯科技将扭曲和在广泛的结束使晕映的外围设备减到最少。', '副词: peripherally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('renascent', '[rɪ\'neɪsnt]', 'adj. <正式文>复兴的； 再生的', '1. Of area creed renascent, especially from black.. 区域主义的复活，尤其从乌... 2. Jesus makes them renascent then, turn them into wanted look. 耶稣于是让他们复活，变成他们想要的样子。 3. Some renascent mortal got arthritis and myocarditis，and whether they will be senescence or juvenescence is a question. 新兴的人类得了关节炎和心肌炎。他们是否会衰老还是返老还童，这是个问题。 4. The people of china have made great effort to realise the nation renascent for hundred years. 一百年以来，中国人民为了实现民族复兴的目标做出了不懈的努力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hurl', '[hɜːrl]', 'v.用力投掷；愤慨地说出；丢下', '1. The hunter hurled his spear at the tiger. 猎人用力把他的长矛向虎投去。 2. I\'ll hurl him out of the club if he dare tell the secret! 如果他胆敢泄密，我就要把他赶出俱乐部。 3. To hurl abuse is in no way to fight. 谩骂决不是战斗。 4. Businessmen will hurl their money about to get noticed. 商人愿意挥霍钱财来引起注意。', '名词: hurler 过去式: hurled 过去分词: hurled 现在分词: hurling 第三人称单数: hurls');
