INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('empower', '[ɪm\'paʊər]', 'vt.授权；使能够', '1. The lawyer was empowered to pay all her bills. 律师已被授权偿付她的一切帐单。 2. The new laws empower the police to stop anybody in the street. 新法令授予警察可以在街上截停任何人的权利。 3. The new laws empower the police to search private house. 新的法律使警察得以搜查私人住宅。 4. Modern science and technology empower human beings to control natural forces more effectively. 现代科学技术使人类能更有效地制服自然。', '名词: empowerment 过去式: empowered 过去分词: empowered 现在分词: empowering 第三人称单数: empowers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hulk', '[hʌlk]', 'n. 废船； 笨重的人或物 vi. 赫然显现； <英口>笨拙地挪动', '1. I saw a rotting hulk on the beach. 我在海滩上看见了一艘腐烂的废船。', '过去式: hulked 过去分词: hulked 现在分词: hulking 第三人称单数: hulks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('obsequious', '[əb\'siːkwiəs]', 'adj.谄媚的；奉承的；顺从的', '1. He is obsequious to men in power. 他对有权势者谄媚。 2. The secretary is exceedingly obsequious to the manager. 这个秘书对经理极尽阿谀奉承之能事。 3. He is a worker who is obsequious to the boss. 他是个对老板卑躬屈膝的人。', '副词: obsequiously 名词: obsequiousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('patent', '[\'pætnt]', 'n.专利；特许 vt.给予专利权 adj.专利的；显著的', '1. The patent runs out in three years time. 这项专利期限为3年。 2. He got a patent for this invention. 他获得了这项发明的专利权。 3. The government patented the device to its inventor. 政府给予发明者专利权。 4. This is a packet of a patent cement mix. 这是一包专利水泥混合料。', '形容词: patentable 名词: patentability 过去式: patented 过去分词: patented 现在分词: patenting 第三人称单数: patents');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tact', '[tækt]', 'n.机智；手法', '1. We reposed great trust in his tact and discretion. 我们极为信任他的机智和谨慎。 2. A minister of foreign affairs has to have tact. 外交部长必须机智老练。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dossier', '[\'dɔːsieɪ]', 'n.档案材料；卷宗；病历', '1. The dossier in this museum which concern civil war are very rare. 这个博物馆里有关内战的档案弥足珍贵。 2. Iraq claims the contents in the weapon dossier prepared by Britain totally baseless. 伊拉克驳斥英国武器档案内容毫无根据。 3. What should the registration dossier look like? 注册文件应该看起来怎样？ 4. No application dossier can be returned, and the application fee is non-refundable. 申请表件及所缴费用均不退还。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('truant', '[\'truːənt]', 'n.懒惰鬼；旷课者 adj.偷懒的；旷课的；游荡的 v.偷懒；旷课', '1. A lazy student,in order to play truant,may play fox,pretending to be ill to have a stomachache,for example. 偷懒的学生为了逃学，可能会藏奸耍滑，比如说他会装病，说自己胃疼。 2. A lazy student,in order to play truant,may play fox,pretending to be ill to have a stomachache,for example. 偷懒的学生为了逃学，可能会藏奸耍滑，比如说他会装病，说自己胃疼。', '过去式: truanted 过去分词: truanted 现在分词: truanting 第三人称单数: truants');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reportage', '[rɪ\'pɔːrtɪdʒ]', 'n.新闻报道；报告文学', '1. The journalists wrote a sensational reportage of the scandal. 记者们对丑闻做了耸人听闻的报道。 2. His reportage fully complied with the facts. 他写的报告文学充分尊重了客观事实。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gavel', '[\'ɡævl]', 'n.(拍卖或法官所用的)槌；(中世纪英国的)贡税 v.用木槌敲', '1. The judge took up the gavel with solemnity. 法官严肃地拿起了小木槌。 2. The chairman rapped on the table twice with his gavel. 主席用他的小木在桌上重敲了两下。 3. Governor Green gaveled for attention. 格林州长敲击议事槌使大家注意。', '过去式: gaveled/gavelled 过去分词: gaveled/gavelled 现在分词: gaveling/gavelling 第三人称单数: gavels');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ersatz', '[\'ersɑːts]', 'adj.代用的；假的 n.代用品', '1. In the 16 months since the first graft, the ersatz skin has not yet been rejected by any of the patients. 第一次植皮后的16个月中，人造皮肤在每个病人身上都还没有排斥现象。 2. Instead of first-hand experiences and real interation, they have ersatz experiences on screens. 他们没有亲身体验的经历和互动，只有来自各种屏幕的虚假经历。 3. There is a flourishing trade in ersatz ginseng. 人参代用品的买卖很兴', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('decorate', '[\'dekəreɪt]', 'v.装饰；布置；装修；授予某人奖章或其他奖状', '1. We decorated the house for Christmas. 我们装饰房屋过圣诞节。 2. My mother likes to decorate rooms. 我妈妈非常喜欢装饰房间。 3. I\'ll bring some balloons to decorate. 我要带些气球去装饰装饰。 4. May I help you decorate the room? 我可以帮你装饰布置房间吗？', '过去式: decorated 过去分词: decorated 现在分词: decorating 第三人称单数: decorates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('imperturbable', '[ˌɪmpər\'tɜːrbəbl]', 'adj.沉着的；泰然自若的；镇静的', '1. Hitherto imperturbable, he now showed signs of alarm. 到现在为止都很沉着，但现在他表现出了惊慌的迹象。 2. The Doctor\'s indignation was wholly lost on his imperturbable rival. 医生的愤慨对于他的泰然自若的敌手也是毫无作用。 3. She was one of those imperturbable people who never get angry or upset. 她是那种从不生气也不烦恼的人。 4. He remained imperturbable in spite of the hysteria and panic all around him. 尽管他周围的人歇斯底里地惊慌失措, 但他仍保持冷静。', '副词: imperturbably 名词: imperturbability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('eclogue', '[\'eklɒg]', 'n.田园诗；牧歌', '1. Whenever you come, you will find Hunan a Chinese painting of landscape and an eclogue of the East. 无论什么季节，湖南都是一幅中国山水画，一首东方田园诗。 2. The first part, mainly discuss Chinese ncient pastoral eclogue the origins and the spirit substance of the literature. 第一部分，主要论述中国古代田园牧歌文学的起源及精神实质对于迟子建的影响。 3. His oil painting works always flare with rational brilliance of realism as well as pure and fresh art color and lyric quality of eclogue. 他的油画作品，始终闪耀着现实主义的理性光辉，却又不乏清新秀婉的艺术情调和田园牧歌式的抒情品质。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('din', '[dɪn]', 'n.喧嚣 v.絮聒不休地说；喧闹 DIN. abbr.德国工业标准（=German Industrial Standards）', '1. They were unable to sleep because of the din coming from the bar. 酒吧里传来的喧闹声吵得他们无法入睡。 2. Anything was preferable to that dreadful din in the house. 这屋子里乱七八糟的声音叫人难受得无以复加。 3. I need not din into your ears the importance of independent thinking. 我用不着完没了地同你谈独立思考的重要性。 4. I dinned it into him that he had to manage things differently. 我三番五次告诉他得改一改处理事情的方法了。', '过去式: dinned 过去分词: dinned 现在分词: dinning 第三人称单数: dins');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ceramics', '[sə\'ræmɪks]', 'n.（用作单）制陶术 n.(用作复）陶器', '1. This hall exhibits jadeware and ceramics. 这个馆陈列的是玉器和陶器。 2. These values are as much the subject of the gallery as are the sculptures, bronzes and ceramics produced by the different societies which have inhabited this huge area. 这些价值观可以从这片广袤地区上的雕塑，铜器，以及陶器所体现出来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('shrub', '[ʃrʌb]', 'n.灌木 n.果汁甜酒', '1. A rose is a perennial shrub or vine. 玫瑰是一种常青灌木或藤本植物。 2. There are many different kinds of shrub. 灌木有许多不同的种类。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('forgery', '[\'fɔːrdʒəri]', 'n.伪造；伪造罪；伪造物', '1. The signature is proved to be a forgery. 签字被证明是非法模仿的或伪造的。 2. He spent three years in prison for forgery. 他为了伪造而坐了三年牢。 3. I shall charge Gary with forgery and theft. 我要指控加里犯伪造罪和偷窃罪。 4. The secretary was falsely convicted of forgery. 秘书被判伪造罪很冤枉。', '名词复数: forgeries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('technocrat', '[\'teknəkræt]', 'n.技术人员；技术专家政治论者', '1. Mr Draghi\'s standing as a trusted technocrat helped restore the bank\'s reputation. 德拉基先生以众人信任的金融实力派人物身份帮助重新恢复了银行的声誉。 2. Mr Abbas has sworn in a new government led by a technocrat. 阿巴斯已经在专家政治论者领导下的新政府宣誓。', '形容词: technocratic');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('feminist', '[\'femənɪst]', 'n.女权主义者 adj.主张男女平等的；女权主义的', '1. She is a card-carrying feminist. 她是典型的女权主义者。 2. A lot of people\'s eyes glaze over if you say you are a feminist. 如果你说你是女权主义者，好多人都会愣住。 3. She is a card-carrying feminist. 她是典型的女权主义者。 4. A lot of people\'s eyes glaze over if you say you are a feminist. 如果你说你是女权主义者，好多人都会愣住。', '形容词: feministic');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inflate', '[ɪn\'fleɪt]', 'vt.使膨胀；使得意；使通货膨胀 vi.膨胀', '1. We all started to inflate our balloons and eventually one burst. 我们都开始给气球充气，结果有一个爆掉了。 2. He is inflated with pride. 他趾高气扬。 3. A few bidders inflated the prices on purpose. 几个投标人故意抬高价钱。 4. Clothing has inflated in price. 服装涨价了。', '名词: inflator 过去式: inflated 过去分词: inflated 现在分词: inflating 第三人称单数: inflates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('jargon', '[\'dʒɑːrɡən]', 'n.行话 vi.说行话', '1. Expert often confuse laymen with their jargon. 专家们常常用行话把外行弄得稀里糊涂。 2. The jargon in his talk was opaque to me. 他谈话中使用的行话对我是一团迷雾。 3. Scientists are notoriously fond of jargon. 科学家爱用行话到了声名狼藉的地步。', '形容词: jargonistic 名词: jargonist 过去式: jargoned 过去分词: jargoned 现在分词: jargoning 第三人称单数: jargons');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('devotional', '[dɪ\'voʊʃənl]', 'adj.信仰的；虔诚的；祷告的 n.简短的祈祷', '1. Devotional music had been arranged by Adhar and Ram. 阿达哈和罗姆已经安排了虔诚的音乐。 2. Nothing can take the place of a daily devotional life with Christ. 没有什么能代替每日献身于基督的生活。', '副词: devotionally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('concentrate', '[\'kɑːnsntreɪt]', 'v.专心；集中；浓缩 n.浓缩物', '1. I can\'t concentrate on my work when I\'m tired. 我累了就无法集中精力工作。 2. The confusing matters make him unable to concentrate on his study. 那么多烦心事使他无法专心学习。 3. The crowds concentrated round the palace. 人群汇集在宫殿的四周。 4. Birds concentrate in places where food is abundant. 鸟聚集在食物丰盛的地方。 5. It is an orange concentrate which you dilute with water. 这是一种兑水饮用的浓缩橙汁.', '形容词: concentrative 副词: concentratively 名词: concentrator 过去式: concentrated 过去分词: concentrated 现在分词: concentrating 第三人称单数: concentrates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('efficacious', '[ˌefɪ\'keɪʃəs]', 'adj.有效的；灵验的', '1. Vaccination for smallpox is efficacious. 种牛痘防天花是有效的。 2. This medicine is efficacious against heart disease. 这个药封心脏病有效。 3. The medicine is efficacious in stopping a cough. 这种药在止咳方面很灵验。', '副词: efficaciously 名词: efficaciousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gravitational', '[ˌɡrævɪ\'teɪʃənl]', 'adj.重力的；引力作用的', '1. It is a spontaneous gravitational instability. 原因在于其自发的重力不稳定性。 2. They are likely sources of gravitational waves. 它们很有可能就是引力波源。 3. Properties of space must depend on the gravitational potential. 空间性质一定与引力势有关。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nerve', '[nɜːrv]', 'n.神经；勇气；敏感处；叶脉；厚脸皮 v.鼓起勇气 （复）nerves: 神经紧张.', '1. A sensitive nerve in a tooth can cause great pain. 牙神经易受损伤，可产生巨痛。 2. You\'ll need plenty of nerve to sit beside him when he is driving. 他开车的时候，你得有足够的胆量才敢坐在他旁边。 3. I hit a nerve when I mentioned her dead mother. 当我提到她死去的母亲时, 我触到了她的伤心处。 4. Did he have the nerve to say that? 他竟有脸说这话吗？ 5. I nerved myself to face my accusers. 我下决心迎击指责我的人。', '过去式: nerved 过去分词: nerved 现在分词: nerving 第三人称单数: nerves');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cornucopia', '[ˌkɔːrnju\'koʊpiə]', 'n.丰饶角；富饶之源；宝藏', '1. Harvard has produced a cornucopia of leaders for the United States in many fields. 哈佛大学已经为美国各领域培养出众多的领袖。 2. The book is a cornucopia of information. 书是知识的宝库。', '形容词: cornucopian');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('naysay', '[\'neɪˌseɪ]', 'n.拒绝 v.拒绝', '1. They will naysay any policy that includes the use of nuclear weapons. 他们将反对任何涉及到使用核武器的政策', '过去式: naysaid 过去分词: naysaid 现在分词: naysaying 第三人称单数: naysays');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('makeshift', '[\'meɪkʃɪft]', 'adj.临时的 n.临时替代物', '1. We put together a makeshift tent. 我们一起搭起了一个临时帐篷。 2. They made a makeshift table from boxes. 他们把箱子做成一张临时用的桌子。 3. The makeshift tent answered their purpose. 将就代用的帐篷解决了他们的问题。 4. The dining couch was a makeshift, poor and patched but the best they had. 吃饭的椅子是临时搭建的，又破又烂，但却是他们最好的椅子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('tender', '[\'tendər]', 'adj.温柔的；脆弱的；敏感的；亲切的；嫩的；痛的 v.提出；投标 n.投标；照管人；补给船；煤水车', '1. She is always tender and soft-spoken. 她总是那么温柔,轻声细语。 2. He gave her a tender kiss. 他给了她一个温柔的吻。 3. Love is a river that drowns the tender reed. 爱情是条会淹没柔弱芦苇的河流。 4. Don\'t mention his divorce---it\'s a very tender subject. 别提他离婚的事---那是个敏感话题。 5. I\'ll tender my resignation. 我要提出辞职。 6. His tender for building a mansion has been accepted. 他承办大厦筑的投标被接受了。', '副词: tenderly 比较级: tenderer 最高级: tenderest 名词: tenderness 过去式: tendered 过去分词: tendered 现在分词: tendering 第三人称单数: tenders');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('credit', '[\'kredɪt]', 'n.信用；荣誉；学分；赞扬；贷款；赊欠；贷方；存款 (复)credits: 演职员名单. v.归功于；相信；记入贷方', '1. Credit counseling helped us get out from under. 信用咨询使我们免除了忧虑 2. Where can I see my credit score? 我在哪能看到我的信用分数? 3. They are working hard for the credit of China. 他们在为中国的荣誉而努力工作。 4. You must pass the examination to get credit for the course. 你必须通过考试才能获得那门课程的学分。 5. At the time, we used to credit everything to one person. 那时大家把什么都归功于一个人。', '过去式: credited 过去分词: credited 现在分词: crediting 第三人称单数: credits');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fussy', '[\'fʌsi]', 'adj.过分装饰的；谨慎的；挑剔的；唠叨的，抱怨的', '1. I don\'t want anything too fussy. 我不要过分装饰的。 2. The little girl dislikes her fussy parents. 小女孩讨厌她那过分操心的父母。 3. She developed a peremptory and fussy disposition. 她养成了一种蛮横和过分注意细节的性格。 4. He is very fussy about his food. 他对于食物非常挑剔。', '副词: fussily 比较级: fussier 最高级: fussiest 名词: fussiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('talon', '[\'tælən]', 'n.爪；手；爪状物；发剩的牌', '1. I have a talon with a keen edge. 我有了一对尖锐的利爪。 2. We do not open the door. Our mother do not have black talon. You are a wolf. 我们不开门，妈妈没有黑爪子，你是狼。 3. It was specifically developed for the Air Force\'s MC-130H Combat Talon II airplane. 该雷达专门开发用于空军MC-130H战斗禽爪II型飞机。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('overbearing', '[ˌəʊvə\'beərɪŋ]', 'adj.傲慢的；骄傲自大的；蛮横的', '1. No one liked his overbearing manners. 没有人喜欢他那傲慢的样子。 2. His overbearing insolence angered everyone. 他的傲慢无礼激起了大家的愤怒。 3. The aging actress was very high-strung and overbearing. 这位上了年纪的女演员非常紧张,而且骄傲自大。 4. He\'s so overbearing that no one wants to work for him. 他那么蛮横,没人愿为他工作。', '副词: overbearingly 名词: overbearingness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('diabetes', '[ˌdaɪə\'biːtiːz]', 'n.糖尿病', '1. The poor old man was afflicted with diabetes. 那可怜的老人受到糖尿病的折磨。 2. The doctor diagnosed her illness as diabetes. 医生诊断她的病是糖尿病。 3. What determines when type 1 diabetes develops? 什么导致了1型糖尿病? 4. What is so different about diabetes in children? 为什么儿童糖尿病差异如此巨大?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('billowy', '[\'bɪloʊɪ]', 'adj.波涛汹涌的；巨浪般的；巨浪的', '1. One billowy river appeared in front of the Cowhand.The Cowhand and Weaver Maid were separated on the two banks forever and could only feel their tears. 眼看追上了，王母拔下金簪一划，牛郎脚下立刻出现一条波涛汹涌的天河。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('overrule', '[ˌoʊvər\'ruːl]', 'v.驳回；否决；统治；对...施加影响', '1. I, however, retain the right to overrule any choices that you make. 但是，我仍有权推翻你所做的任何决定。 2. We were overruled by the majority. 我们的意见被多数人否决了。 3. The judge overruled the previous decision. 法官否决了以前的判决。 4. Custom and agreement overrule law. 习惯与合意可以使法律无效。', '过去式: overruled 过去分词: overruled 现在分词: overruling 第三人称单数: overrules');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unconscionable', '[ʌn\'kɑːnʃənəbl]', 'adj.不合理的；没有条理的；过度的', '1. It would be unconscionable for her to keep the money. 她若私吞那笔钱，那可就太没良心了。 2. What we are doing by glomorizing smoking is unconscionable. 而我们这种把吸烟美化的行为是昧着良心的。 3. The demands are unconscionable and impossible to meet. 这些要求是不合理的也不可能的到满足。 4. You take an unconscionable time getting dressed! 你穿衣服用的时间未免太长了！', '副词: unconscionably 名词: unconscionableness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('affluence', '[\'æfluəns]', 'n.富裕', '1. America is a country of great affluence. 美国是富裕的国家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('maxim', '[\'mæksɪm]', 'n.格言；箴言；普遍真理 Maxim: 马克西姆(姓氏).', '1. This was a maxim well understood by Turloch. 这是特洛克心领神会的格言。 2. This maxim has been done to death. 这个格言重复得太多了，简直令人发腻。 3. Please lay the maxim to your heart. 请把此格箴言记在心里。 4. Oh, should the maxim be modified a little? 哦，莎翁的这句箴言是不是应当修改？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hauteur', '[hɔː\'tɜːr]', 'n.傲慢', '1. A deeper shade of hauteur overspread his features, but he said not a word. 一阵傲慢的阴影罩上了他的脸，可是他一句话也没有说。 2. The intense vitality that had been so remarkable in the garage was converted into impressive hauteur. 先前她在车行里的那种旺盛的活力，转眼间变成了一种明显的骄傲情绪。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('peremptory', '[pə\'remptəri]', 'adj.专横的；不容反抗的；强制的', '1. His peremptory tone irritated everybody. 他那专横的口气激怒了大家。 2. He made a peremptory order. 他下达了一个必须服从的命令。', '副词: peremptorily 名词: peremptoriness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nestle', '[\'nesl]', 'v.依偎；（舒适地）安顿', '1. She nestled her head on his shoulder. 她将头依偎在他的肩上。 2. The village nestled at the foot of the hill. 那村庄位于山脚下。 3. The child nestled up to its mother and fell asleep. 孩子倚著母亲舒服地睡了。 4. The dog nestled up against the warm radiator. 狗倚著暖烘烘的散热器。', '名词: nestler 过去式: nestled 过去分词: nestled 现在分词: nestling 第三人称单数: nestles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pensive', '[\'pensɪv]', 'adj.沉思的；愁眉苦脸的', '1. He subsided into a pensive state. 他陷入了沉思。 2. The painting can inspire a pensive mood. 这幅画能引人沉思。 3. She looked pensive when she heard the news. 她听到这消息时神情严肃. 4. The woman in this painting has a pensive smile. 这幅画上的女人脸上露出忧郁的微笑。', '副词: pensively 名词: pensiveness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cavalry', '[\'kævlri]', 'n.骑兵(队)', '1. I am a soldier of the fourth cavalry. 我是第四骑兵部队的一员。 2. The cavalry is extremely majestic-looking. 这支骑兵部队非常威风凛凛。 3. They were taken in flank by a troop of cavalry. 他们的侧翼受到一队骑兵袭击。', '名词: cavalryman 名词复数: cavalries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ovation', '[oʊ\'veɪʃn]', 'n.热烈欢迎；热烈的鼓掌', '1. The hero received a great ovation from the crowd. 那位英雄受到人群的热烈欢迎。 2. He gets a standing ovation as he moves off stage. 他离开舞台时，全体观众起立热烈鼓掌。', '形容词: ovational');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ineligible', '[ɪn\'elɪdʒəbl]', 'adj.无被选任资格的；不适任的；不适当的 n.无被选任资格的人；不合录用资格的人', '1. A foreign-born citizen is ineligible for the Presidency. 外籍公民没有资格任总统。 2. Any person under the age of 18 is ineligible for benefit. 未满18岁者无资格领取补助金。', '副词: ineligibly 名词: ineligibility');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hysteria', '[hɪ\'stɪriə]', 'n.歇斯特里症；不正常的兴奋', '1. Affected by the vapors; given to spells of hysteria or low spirits. 易忧郁的，忧郁症的被忧郁影响的; 被施加了歇斯底里或情绪低落的咒语的 2. The abnormal, spasmodic swallowing of air, especially as a symptom of hysteria. 吞气症异常的痉挛性吞气，特指歇斯底里的症状', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('backslide', '[\'bækslaɪd]', 'vi.堕落；退步；背离宗教', '1. You\'ve done a good job in the exam, I hope you won\'t backslide. 你考试考得不错，我希望你不要退步。', '名词: backslider 过去式: backslid 过去分词: backslid 现在分词: backsliding 第三人称单数: backslides');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inertia', '[ɪ\'nɜːrʃə]', 'n.惯性；惰性', '1. Inertia carried the car to the pavement. 惯性使汽车驶到了人行道上。 2. Inertia is evident in our every day experiences. 惯性在我们日常生活中是很常见的。 3. Everyone has his psychological inertia, or in some way, indolence. 每个人都有一种思维惯性或者说惰性。 4. Because of the sheer inertia of the system many badly needed reform is never introduced. 纯粹是由於制度本身有惰性，很多事急需改革却从未实行。', '形容词: inertial 副词: inertially');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('adulterate', '[ə\'dʌltəreɪt]', 'v.搀 ... 使品质变劣 adj.掺假的；通奸的', '1. It is a crime to adulterate foods without informing the buyer. 不告知买主就对食物掺杂是犯罪。 2. They have to adulterate a Chinese sentence with words taken from English or Malay. 他们一句话里头总是掺杂了英语单词或马来语词汇。', '名词: adulteration 过去式: adulterated 过去分词: adulterated 现在分词: adulterating 第三人称单数: adulterates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('appetite', '[\'æpɪtaɪt]', 'n.食欲；嗜好；欲望', '1. She is suffering from lack of appetite. 她食欲不振。 2. The long walk has given me a good appetite. 走了长路使我食欲大振。 3. Mary has no appetite for hard work. 玛丽不想干艰苦的工作。 4. I have to make an effort to work up an appetite for reading. 我得努力使自己产生天天想读书的愿望。', '形容词: appetitive');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('murky', '[\'mɜːrki]', 'adj.黑暗的；朦胧的；烟雾弥漫的；含糊的；隐晦的', '1. The criminal was chained in a murky dungeon. 犯人被链子锁在黑暗的地牢里。 2. This murky sort of business would scandalise any country. 黑暗的金钱交易可以丑化任何一个国家。', '副词: murkily 名词: murkiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('drollery', '[\'droʊlərɪ]', 'n.滑稽；滑稽离奇的特性；开玩笑的行为', '1. He leaned back in his chair and laughed at the unconscious drollery of her reply. 他向椅背上一仰，觉得她的回话里含着一种无心的滑稽，不觉笑了起来。', '名词复数: drolleries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('levy', '[\'levi]', 'n.征税；召集 vt.征收；发动 vi.强收', '1. The basis of the proposals is a levy of 0.25 per cent. 建议的征税基点为百分之零点二五。 2. The nation levied all able-bodied man for the war. 国家征召所有壮丁参战。 3. The government has decided to levy a tax on import cars. 政府决定征收进口汽车税。 4. The nation levied all able-bodied man for the war. 国家征召所有壮丁参战。 5. The court may have to levy on your estate to pay your debts. 法庭可能不得不扣押你的房地产，用来偿付你的债务。', '名词: levier 名词复数: levies 过去式: levied 过去分词: levied 现在分词: levying 第三人称单数: levies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('suspicious', '[sə\'spɪʃəs]', 'adj.可疑的；多疑的', '1. I am suspicious of his intentions. 我怀疑他的用意。 2. Two suspicious characters were brought in. 逮捕了两名嫌疑犯。 3. I feel suspicious about the truth of the account. 我对于这帐目的真实性感到怀疑。 4. The locals tend to be suspicious of strangers. 当地人对陌生人往往有戒心。', '副词: suspiciously 名词: suspiciousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('luminary', '[\'luːmɪneri]', 'n.杰出人物；发光体', '1. Digital Vision Infinity 2 Luminary Part. 2 无限系列之发光体篇 For Win. 2. That luminary gazed earnestly at some papers before him. 那个大好佬在用心细看面前的报纸。 3. Keep good relationship with the targeted luminary in regions. 对客户关系进行维护。 4. Who was this novice in war with the effrontery of a luminary? 那目空一切的新生尤物是什么人？', '名词复数: luminaries');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('emaciation', '[ɪˌmeɪsi\'eɪʃn]', 'n.瘦弱；憔悴；衰弱', '1. Our hermit, on the contrary, kept a minute check of his emaciation and felt a peculiar thrill out of such an achievement. 我们的隐士，将他自己身体日渐瘦弱的过程作了一个详尽的记录，并因此而感到怪异莫名的喜悦。 2. His face was hollowed out to the point of emaciation. 他的脸瘦削到了憔悴的地步。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('eulogize', '[\'juːlədʒaɪz]', 'v.称赞；颂扬', '1. All major newspapers coincidently eulogize the government\'s positive suggestions. 各大报纸不约而同地颂扬政府积极性的建议。', '名词: eulogist 过去式: eulogized 过去分词: eulogized 现在分词: eulogizing 第三人称单数: eulogizes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wearisome', '[\'wɪrisəm]', 'adj.使疲倦的；令人厌烦的；厌烦的', '1. I am doing a wearisome work. 我在做一项无聊的工作。 2. Walking in the burning sunshine makes people wearisome. 在炙热的阳光下行走令人疲倦。 3. This is beginning to get wearisome. 这逐渐使人厌烦起来。 4. She feels wearisome by the constant noise. 她很厌烦那些没完没了的嘈杂声。', '副词: wearisomely 名词: wearisomeness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('addition', '[ə\'dɪʃn]', 'n.增加；加法；附加物', '1. In addition to a diet, she pursues various exercises on TV. 节食以外她还随电视做体操。 2. In addition to an album, I gave him a pen and a pencil. 除了一本照相簿外，我还给了他一支钢笔和一支铅笔。 3. They eat a great deal of fruit in addition. 他们还吃大量的水果。 4. Addition and division are forms of computation. 加法和除法都是计算方法。', '形容词: additional 副词: additionally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('drought', '[draʊt]', 'n.干旱', '1. The long drought famished many people. 久旱使很多人陷入饥饿。 2. Famine is often the sequel to war or drought. 饥荒往往是战争或干旱造成的。 3. We have not enough food to eat because of the drought. 因为旱灾，我们没有足够的食物可吃。 4. The soil is cracking up because of the drought. 土地因干旱而正在龟裂。', '形容词: droughty 异体字: drouth');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lavish', '[\'lævɪʃ]', 'adj.大方的；丰富的；浪费的 vt.浪费；慷慨给予', '1. A rich man can be lavish of his money. 富有的人用钱大手大脚。 2. He was lavish in his praise for her paintings. 他大力赞扬她的绘画。 3. The Empress can also represent lavish abundance of all kinds. 女皇也代表各种各样的丰富奢侈。 4. That is a vast and lavish party. 那是个规模盛大、极其铺张的宴会。 5. It is a mistake to lavish kindness ungrateful people. 对于不领情的人来说浪费感情是一种错误。', '副词: lavishly 名词: lavisher 过去式: lavished 过去分词: lavished 现在分词: lavishing 第三人称单数: lavishes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('condescending', '[ˌkɒndɪ\'sendɪŋ]', 'adj.高傲的；表现出优越感的 动词condescend的现在分词.', '1. I don\'t like Mrs Smith; she\'s condescending. 我不喜欢史密斯夫人，她总是自以为高人一等。 2. His condescending attitude really gets my back up. 他那种居高临下的恩赐态度实在使我很生气。 3. Penny\'s condescending manner really gets under my skin. 彭尼那种以恩赐态度对待别人的样子真的把激怒了。', '副词: condescendingly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incontrovertible', '[ˌɪnkɑːntrə\'vɜːrtəbl]', 'adj.不容置疑的；无可辩驳的', '1. But one point is, I would suggest, incontrovertible. 但我要说，有一点是不容置疑的。 2. This principle advanced by Lenin remains an incontrovertible truth. 列宁提出的这个原则至今仍是一个颠扑不破的真理。 3. But is the evidence really incontrovertible? 但是这些证据真的就无可争议的吗？', '副词: incontrovertibly 名词: incontrovertibility');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('purity', '[\'pjʊrəti]', 'n.纯净；纯洁；纯正；纯粹', '1. We must ensure the purity of drinking water. 我们必须确保饮用水的纯净。 2. Chinese people regard lotus as an emblem of purity. 中国人把莲花看作是纯洁的象征。 3. White symbolizes purity and cleanness. 白色代表纯洁和干净。 4. It\'s a soprano of great compass and of great purity. 这是一种音域宽广，高度纯正的女高音。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('genetic', '[dʒə\'netɪk]', 'adj.遗传的；基因的；起源的', '1. He chose genetic engineering to be his lifelong career. 他选择了遗传工程学作为终生的事业。 2. Most chromomeres contain a genetic unit. 绝大多数染色粒包含一个遗传单位。 3. The disease is caused by a genetic defect. 这种疾病的起因是基因缺陷。 4. Every living thing has its own genetic chips. 每种生物都有自己的基因芯片。', '副词: genetically 异体字: genetical');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('populous', '[\'pɑːpjələs]', 'adj.人口多的；人口稠密的', '1. China is the most populous developing country in the world. 中国是世界上人口最多的发展中国家。 2. London is the most populous area of Britain. 伦敦是英国人口最稠密的地区。', '副词: populously 名词: populousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mar', '[mɑːr]', 'vt.破坏；毁坏 n.污点；瑕疵 abbr.海上的（=maritime） Mar. abbr.三月（March）', '1. This will mar the beauty of your hair. 这会影响你头发的美观。 2. Nothing had occurred to mar this trip. 没有什么事破坏这次旅行的圆满成功。 3. Nothing happened to mar the old man\'s happiness. 那老人的幸福没有受到任何事情的破坏. 4. His handling of the crisis can make or mar his career. 他对这一危机的处理可能决定他事业的成败。', '过去式: marred 过去分词: marred 现在分词: marring 第三人称单数: mars');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('daze', '[deɪz]', 'vt. 使 ... 茫然； 使 ... 眩目 n. 恍惚； 晕眩', '1. We drove home in an absolute daze. 我们茫然一片地驱车回家。 2. I\'ve been in a complete daze since hearing the news. 自从听到那消息，我一直茫然不知所措。 3. He had been in a daze all the way to New York. 他去纽约途中一路恍惚。', '过去式: dazed 过去分词: dazed 现在分词: dazing 第三人称单数: dazes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('jigsaw', '[\'dʒɪɡsɔː]', 'n.拼图游戏；缕花锯；竖锯 vt.用竖锯锯；使互相交错搭接', '1. I got stuck with that jigsaw puzzle so I\'ve laid it aside for the time being. 我被这拼板玩具难住了，因此我暂把它放在一边。 2. We keep trying to put the jigsaw puzzle together. 我们继续尝试这种拼图游戏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('truancy', '[\'truːənsi]', 'n.逃学；旷课；玩忽职守', '1. His truancy was a constant problem. 他的逃学一直是个问题。 2. The next meeting will address the problem of truancy. 下次会议将着手解决学生的逃课问题。 3. Truancy rates at the school are very high. 这所学校的旷课率很高。 4. Truancy is common at this school. 在这个学校旷课是很普遍的。', '异体字: truantry 名词复数: truancies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('histology', '[hɪ\'stɑːlədʒi]', 'n.[生]组织学；组织机构', '1. Histology involves looking at cells under a microscope. 组织学研究包括在显微镜下观察细胞。', '形容词: histological 副词: histologically 名词: histologist 名词复数: histologies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('buoy', '[bɔɪ]', 'n.浮标；浮筒；救生圈；救生衣 v.使浮起；支持；鼓励；用浮标指示', '1. The can buoy was submerged underwater. 罐状浮标没于水下。 2. At turns, everybody bunches up as close to the buoy as they can. 在转弯的地方，大家都尽可能往浮标的地方挤。 3. A tail buoy is connected to the far end of the cable. 电缆的末端与一个尾随浮筒相连。 4. Take a life buoy with you when you go swimming. 下午去游泳的时候把救生圈带上。', '过去式: buoyed 过去分词: buoyed 现在分词: buoying 第三人称单数: buoys');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('amuse', '[ə\'mjuːz]', 'v.娱乐；消遣；使 ... 发笑', '1. I amuse myself by reading on weekends. 周末我读书消遣。 2. It is not always easy to amuse oneself on holiday. 让自己在假期里自娱并不总是容易的。 3. The boys amuse themselves by drawing caricatures of their teacher. 男孩子们以画老师的漫画取乐。 4. He could amuse us for hours with his stories of the theater. 他能接连几小时地为我们讲戏剧故事逗我们发笑。', '形容词: amusable 名词: amuser 过去式: amused 过去分词: amused 现在分词: amusing 第三人称单数: amuses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('figurative', '[\'fɪɡərətɪv]', 'adj.比喻的；象征的', '1. The word here is used in its figurative sense. 此词在这儿取的是它的比喻意义。 2. He imprisoned her,in a figurative sense. 在比喻的意义上,他把她关在牢里了。 3. This has long been taken not only literally, but also in a figurative sense, for the Orient has been considered as the source of wisdom and illumination. 很久以来人们认为这种说法不但是真实的而且还有比喻的含义，因为东方一直被认为是智慧和启蒙的发源地。 4. Baptism is a figurative ceremony. 受洗礼是象征的礼节。', '副词: figuratively 名词: figurativeness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('hoard', '[hɔːrd]', 'n.贮藏 v.贮藏；储存', '1. The squirrel kept his hoard in a tree. 这只松鼠把吃的东西藏在树里。 2. His final card remains on my bulletin hoard today. 父亲最后给我的那张卡片至今仍留在我的记事板上。 3. They dug up a hoard of Roman coins. 他们挖出了一批埋藏的古罗马硬币。 4. A large number of animals hoard plant seeds. 许多动物有贮藏植物种子的行为。', '名词: hoarder 过去式: hoarded 过去分词: hoarded 现在分词: hoarding 第三人称单数: hoards');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('deductive', '[dɪ\'dʌktɪv]', 'adj.推论的；演绎的', '1. If we employ a philosophic way of deductive thinking, then maybe it is right to say that behind every phenomenon there exists another phenomenon. 如果用哲学推论的思维法，也许这样说也是对的，即每个现象的背后都存在着另一种现象。 2. This book is devoted to the construction of a deductive theory of the electron, starting from first principles and using a simple mathematical tool, geometric analysis. 这本书献身于一个电子的演绎的理论的建设，从第一个原则开始并且使用一件简单的数学工具，几何学分析。 3. What\'s more, it is hard for educational theories to be totally built upon deductive grounds.Thus, the axiom methodology is bound to have its limitations. 教育理论难以完全建立在演绎的基础上，因而公理方法必有其局限性。', '副词: deductively');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('profane', '[prə\'feɪn]', 'adj.亵渎的；不敬神的；世俗的 v.亵渎；玷污', '1. His profane language annoyed us. 他亵渎的言语激怒了我们。 2. I was sorry, I said, to hear them so very profane. 我说，我听见他们这样的蔑教，很难过。 3. They have profane the long uphold tradition of the church. 他们亵渎了教会长期沿袭的传统。 4. His action profaned the honour of his country. 他的行为玷污了国家的荣誉。', '形容词: profanatory 副词: profanely 名词: profaneness 过去式: profaned 过去分词: profaned 现在分词: profaning 第三人称单数: profanes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('heed', '[hiːd]', 'v.注意；留心 n.注意；留心', '1. Now heed what I say. 现在注意听我要说的话。 2. She never heeded anyone\'s warning. 她从不理会任何人的警告。 3. Please heed the warning in the banner. 请留心这些警告的标牌。 4. He did not heed my gibes, and chattered on. 他没有留心我的嘲笑,继续喋喋不休地说着。 5. A good leader should always pay heed to the voice of the masses. 一位好领导应该经常注意倾听群众的呼声。', '过去式: heeded 过去分词: heeded 现在分词: heeding 第三人称单数: heeds');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('annul', '[ə\'nʌl]', 'v.废除；消减；取消；宣告无效', '1. The effect of the statute was to annul this covenant. 但州法规废除了这一契约。 2. Annul the previously transmitted clearance. 取消先前发给的许可。 3. For them, the decision to annul same-sex marriages will be personal, even painful. 对这些同性恋者来说，决定取消婚礼会是私人的，而且是痛苦的。', '过去式: annulled 过去分词: annulled 现在分词: annulling 第三人称单数: annuls');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('residual', '[rɪ\'zɪdʒuəl]', 'adj.剩余的；残余的 n.剩余部分；(复)追加酬金', '1. The debate over the residual powers of the States has been long drawn out. 有关美国剩余的权力的争论已是旷日持久的了。 2. That\'s the residual outcome of your past thoughts and actions. 那只是你过去的思想和行为所产生的残余结果。', '副词: residually');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reincarnate', '[ˌriːɪn\'kɑːrneɪt]', 'v.使化身；转生 adj.转世的', '1. Have you ever seen emperorQinshihuang reincarnate? 谁见过秦始皇转世？ 2. He Master did not reincarnate where people expected. 明师没有在人们期待的地方重生。 3. Some people believe they may reincarnate in the form of an animal. 有些人相信他们死后可能转生为动物。 4. Scores of Tibetan lamas claim to be reincarnate tulkus. 所以只能“出售”大量的白银。', '过去式: reincarnated 过去分词: reincarnated 现在分词: reincarnating 第三人称单数: reincarnates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('upright', '[\'ʌpraɪt]', 'adj.直立的；垂直的；正直的 adv.垂直地 n.垂直；竖立；竖钢琴', '1. Only humans have a natural upright posture. 只有人类才有自然直立的姿势。 2. Please put the back of your seat in an upright position. 请把座位靠背转到垂直位置。 3. He was a famous upright statesman. 他是一位著名的、正直的政治家。 4. Several columns among the ruins still stood upright. 在废墟中依然挺立着几根柱子。 5. The piano was nearly always an upright. 钢琴差不多总是直立式钢琴。', '副词: uprightly 名词: uprightness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inspired', '[ɪn\'spaɪərd]', 'adj.有创见的；有灵感的；授意的 动词inspire的过去式和过去分词.', '1. The company is aggressive and inspired. 该公司雄心勃勃，富于创新。 2. They labelled him as an inspired artist. 他们标榜他是一个有灵感的艺术家。 3. That was obviously an inspired article. 这篇文章显然是在别人授意下写出来的。 4. His ardour for the cause inspired his followers. 他对事业的热情激励着他的追随者。', '副词: inspiredly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('conducive', '[kən\'djuːsɪv]', 'adj.有助的；有益的', '1. Fresh air is conducive to health. 新鲜空气有助于健康。 2. The favourable political climate is conducive to economic investment. 良好的政治气候有利于经济投资。 3. Regularity ought to be observed, as regularity is very conducive to health. 生活应遵守规律，因为规律对健康有益。', '名词: conduciveness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('reciprocate', '[rɪ\'sɪprəkeɪt]', 'v.互换；交换；报答；往返运动', '1. Some day I will reciprocate your kindness to me. 总有一天我会报答你对我的恩德。 2. We always invite the neighbors and they never reciprocate! 我们经常宴请邻居，可他们从来不报答我们。', '形容词: reciprocative 名词: reciprocation 过去式: reciprocated 过去分词: reciprocated 现在分词: reciprocating 第三人称单数: reciprocates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('perforate', '[\'pɜːrfəreɪt]', 'v.穿孔于；刺穿 adj.有孔的', '1. Hard plastic enema tips can perforate the rectum. 硬的塑料灌肠嘴会刺破直肠。 2. This machine can perforate the sheets of stamps. 这台机器能在整版邮票上打孔。 3. Your ear drum has been perforate. 您的耳鼓膜穿孔了。 4. The perfor mance indexes thereof are tested. 检测了该醇酸树脂的各项性能。', '形容词: perforable 名词: perforator 过去式: perforated 过去分词: perforated 现在分词: perforating 第三人称单数: perforates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ream', '[riːm]', 'n.令；大量的纸；许多(文字) v.扩展；扩大；榨出（汁）', '1. Steeped in new moods and ideas, I bought a ream of paper and tried to write. 沉湎在新的心境与想法里，我买了一令纸试图写作。 2. He writes reams of verse. 他写很多的诗。', '过去式: reamed 过去分词: reamed 现在分词: reaming 第三人称单数: reams');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('stipulation', '[ˌstɪpju\'leɪʃn]', 'n.规定；契约；条款', '1. Your remarks break the stipulation of the contract. 你们的意见是违反合同规定的。 2. There\'s no stipulation as to the amount you can invest. 没有关于投资额的规定。 3. The German Government accepted this stipulation . 德国政府接受了这个条件。 4. We\'ll honor your draft when it become due only if all contract stipulation have been duly implemented by you. 只有当你方按时履行了合同条款时,我们才会如期承兑你方期票。', '形容词: stipulatory');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('comely', '[\'kʌmli]', 'adj.清秀的；美丽的；合适的', '1. With his gentle eyes and comely smile, he still leaves a sense of fortitude for his delicate nose and thin lips. 他目光柔和，笑容清秀，精致的鼻子和薄薄的嘴唇却给人一种坚毅的感觉。 2. His wife is a comely young woman. 他的妻子是一个美丽的少妇。 3. I hope my young friend will like such a comely sample of his own blood. 希望咱们那位年轻的朋友喜欢这么一位和他一脉相传的漂亮姑娘。', '比较级: comelier 最高级: comeliest 名词: comeliness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('paleolithic', '[ˌpeɪlɪə\'lɪθɪk]', 'adj.旧石器时代的', '1. The stone balls were tools of hunting in Paleolithic times. 石球是旧石器时代原始人用来狩猎的工具。 2. The soil is a mix of slate and quartz that dates back to the Paleolithic era. 是一种由页岩和石英混合而成，源于旧石器时代。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('abstruse', '[əb\'struːs]', 'adj.深奥的', '1. Philosophical semantics is too abstruse to understand. 哲学语义学深奥难懂。 2. Einstein\'s theory of relativity is very abstruse. 爱因斯坦的相对论非常难懂。', '副词: abstrusely 名词: abstruseness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rustler', '[\'rʌslər]', 'n.偷牛贼；偷马贼', '1. Initiative rustler,work is precisenes、respect. 主动积极，工作严谨、敬业； 2. The ants have cornered the rustler and are attacking it. 蚂蚁把大虫围困起来并展开进攻。 3. Just then a loud whinny came from the herd of mustangs. They began moving up the moonlit slope. “Hey! The horses!” a rustler shouted. 就在这时一声烈马的嘶叫，从远处的树林里传了出来，一个黑影在向那被月光照亮的斜坡上移动，“嘿！马！”一个偷马贼叫道。 4. Thenardier had caused the \"honest rustler\" to disappear in his fob, and was gazing at Marius with a gentleness that was almost tender. Marius broke the silence. 德纳第已把这“值钱的钞票”藏进了背心的口袋里,温和到接近柔情的程度望着马吕斯。马吕斯打破了沉默', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vying', '[\'vaɪɪŋ]', 'adj.竞争的 动词vie的现在分词.', '1. Humans vying for dominance will turn to genetics and cryogenics to compete. 为主宰世界而竞争的人将转向在遗传学和低温学领域展开竞争。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fledge', '[fledʒ]', 'vi. 长羽毛 vt. 用羽毛覆盖； 在 ... 上装羽毛； 喂养小鸟(以待其羽毛长成)', '1. Info:Motorbike leather and cordura glove Made in Aniline cowhide leather with Combo fledge nylon cordura ...... 主要材质:真皮次要材质:尼龙/锦纶适用对象:男款式:分指手套 2. More than hundred thousand Tibetan fledge across the Himalaya mountain to India. 超过10万西藏人越过喜马拉雅上逃往印度。 3. Nevertheless the resort does not have full fledge restaurant but more of a mini kitchen serving basic food. 由于我们是素食主义者，他们都跑出来看我们准备的食物。 4. I recently had the awesome experience of seeing one of my pairs fledge 8 young from a clutch twice in the same season. 作为与警戒线， bluecap父母放弃在场的年轻人，为的第一天，他们fledge与他们的抖振报警电话。', '过去式: fledged 过去分词: fledged 现在分词: fledging 第三人称单数: fledges');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('contravene', '[ˌkɒntrə\'viːn]', 'v.违反；相抵触；否定', '1. Her actions contravene the rules. 她的所作所为违反了规定。 2. This evidence contravenes our theory. 这个证据跟我们的理论不相符.', '名词: contravener 过去式: contravened 过去分词: contravened 现在分词: contravening 第三人称单数: contravenes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pine', '[paɪn]', 'n.松树；松木 vi.消瘦；渴望', '1. The pine trees defy severe cold. 松树不畏严寒。 2. It\'s a noted place for its pine tree and springs. 这是一个以松树和泉水著称的地方。 3. There is a pine forest near our house. 我们家附近有片松树林。 4. Pine is a soft wood and teak is a hard wood. 松木是软木，柚木是硬木。 5. He pined away after his daughter died. 他的女儿死后，他逐渐变得憔悴了。', '过去式: pined 过去分词: pined 现在分词: pining 第三人称单数: pines');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('absurd', '[əb\'sɜːrd]', 'adj.荒唐的；可笑的；不合理的 n.荒唐', '1. He finally recovered from an absurd infatuation. 他终于从荒唐的迷恋中醒悟过来。 2. What an absurd suggestion! 多荒谬的建议啊！ 3. We have no intention of lying down under these absurd allegations. 对这些荒谬的指控我们是不甘受辱的。 4. It was absurd of you to suggest such a thing. 你居然建议这样的事，太可笑了。 5. The proposal borders on the absurd. 该提议近乎可笑。', '副词: absurdly 名词: absurdity');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('parka', '[\'pɑːrkə]', 'n.风雪大衣；派克式外衣', '1. Look at this catalog, John. The ski parka is on sale. 约翰,你看这个目录。滑雪风衣正在促销呢。 2. He held both sides of the parka hood closed against the snow. 他把派克大衣兜帽两边都绑得紧紧的来挡住雪。 3. If you have worn shorts and a parka at the same time, you live in Ontario . 如果你同时穿着短裤和派克大衣，那你是住在安大略省。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('meek', '[miːk]', 'adj.温顺的；谦恭的', '1. It is Mrs. White that makes the decisions in that family, not her meek little husBand. 那家庭决定事情的是怀特太太，不是她那温顺的小个子丈夫。', '副词: meekly 比较级: meeker 最高级: meekest');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('timber', '[\'tɪmbər]', 'n.木材；木料', '1. He used to be a timber merchant. 他曾是一个木材商。 2. Seasoned timber does not warp. 经干燥处理的木材不会翘曲。 3. The farmer spent a day in the woods hewing timber. 这个农夫花了一天时间在森林里砍木材。 4. We are making a bed from scrap timber. 我们在用碎木料做一张床。', '过去式: timbered 过去分词: timbered 现在分词: timbering 第三人称单数: timbers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('scheme', '[skiːm]', 'n.阴谋；计划；方案 v.图谋；设计；策划；<非正式>认为', '1. Their scheme was exposed. 他们的阴谋被暴露了。 2. The police have uncovered a scheme of robbery. 警察当局破获了一起阴谋抢劫案。 3. They were bitterly opposed to the scheme. 他们强烈反对这个计划。 4. I rather doubt if such an ambitious scheme could be made a success of. 我真怀疑这样一个雄心勃勃的计划是否会成功。 5. He is scheming for power. 他在图谋争权。', '名词: schemer 过去式: schemed 过去分词: schemed 现在分词: scheming 第三人称单数: schemes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('obligatory', '[ə\'blɪɡətɔːri]', 'adj.强制性的；义务的；必须的', '1. Attendance at school is obligatory. 上学是强制性的。 2. It is an obligatory step that does not arise from revenge, rancour or other lower emotions, but from the rational necessity to make mankind gain insight. 这是一个强制性的步骤，不产生报复，怨恨或其他低的情感，但是从理性的必要性，使人类了解。 3. Attendance at primary school is obligatory. 上小学是义务的。', '副词: obligatorily');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dolorous', '[\'doʊlərəs]', 'adj.忧伤的；悲痛的', '1. I suspect he had a long and dolorous heart-to-heart with a crocodile. 我猜他和鳄鱼有着很长而忧伤的坦率交流。 2. Mr Carter\'s tone was dolorous, but there is an extraordinary lilt to Mr Obama\'s rhetoric which puts a bounce back into everyone\'s step. 卡特的语调是忧伤的，而奥巴马的言辞给人的感觉是极其轻快的，给每一个人的前进步伐都带去了动力。', '副词: dolorously 名词: dolorousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('capitulate', '[kə\'pɪtʃuleɪt]', 'v.屈从，停止反抗；有条件投降', '1. The planters’ ladies were the last to capitulate. 庄园主的夫人们是最后被征服的。 2. We will never capitulate to pressure from outside. 我们永远不会屈服于外界的压力。 3. The ememy was warned to capitulate or face annihilation. 敌人受到警告，要么投降，要么全部被歼灭。 4. The whole course of my life proves that I never capitulate. 我的全部生活历程证明我是从来不曾投降过。', '名词: capitulant 过去式: capitulated 过去分词: capitulated 现在分词: capitulating 第三人称单数: capitulates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vacillate', '[\'væsəleɪt]', 'v.游移不定；踌躇；犹豫', '1. She vacillated between hope and fear. 她时而抱有希望，时而心存恐惧。 2. But a few cadres started to vacillate. 但是,也有少数干部起了波动。 3. You are bound to vacillate at times. 有时你肯定还是会犹豫不决。 4. You can tell when they\'re stressed out, they\'ll equivocate and vacillate. 当他们压力过大时，你是可以辨别出来的，因为他们会支支吾吾、犹豫不决。', '副词: vacillatingly 名词: vacillation 过去式: vacillated 过去分词: vacillated 现在分词: vacillating 第三人称单数: vacillates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('purlieu', '[\'pɜːluː]', 'n.边缘地；常去的地方；范围；界限', '1. purlieu men [古]御猎场内的土地所有人', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pronounced', '[prə\'naʊnst]', 'adj.显著的；断然的；明确的 动词pronounce的过去式和过去分词.', '1. Age has made a pronounced change in his appearance. 岁月明显地改变了他的外貌。 2. He spoke with a pronounced English accent. 他说话带着浓重的英国口音。 3. He is a man of pronounced opinions. 他是个有坚定意见的人. 4. He has very pronounced ideas on everything. 他对每样事情都有明确的看法。 5. The two words are spelled differently, but pronounced the same. 这两个字拼写不同，但发音相同。', '副词: pronouncedly 名词: pronouncedness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('foolproof', '[\'fuːlpruːf]', 'adj.不会错的；极简单的；可靠而操作简便的；傻瓜式的', '1. No system can ever be completely foolproof. 没有一个系统可以完全不出错的。 2. They adopted a foolproof identification system. 他们采用了一种绝对可靠的识别系统。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('peep', '[piːp]', 'n.瞥见；偷看；初现 n.吱吱叫 v.窥视；慢慢露出 v.吱吱叫', '1. You\'ve only seen a peep through the curtain. 你还只是隔着帘子瞥见一眼罢了。 2. He took a peep at the back of the book to find out the answers to the questions. 他偷偷看了一下书的后面，想找出那些问题的答案。 3. You must start at the peep of dawn. 你们必须在黎明时分动身。 4. The little chicks began to peep because they were hungry. 小鸡因为饿而开始吱吱叫。 5. He squatted down to peep into the basket. 他蹲下来向篮子里窥视了一下。 6. The little chicks began to peep because they were hungry. 小鸡因为饿而开始吱吱叫。', '过去式: peeped 过去分词: peeped 现在分词: peeping 第三人称单数: peeps');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('attach', '[ə\'tætʃ]', 'v.附上；系上；贴上；使依附；使附属；使附着', '1. I attach a copy of my notes for your information. 我附上笔记一份供你参考。 2. In confirmation hereof we attach a bank statement. 为作这方面的确认我们附上银行结单。 3. Please attach these labels to your hand luggages. 请把这些标签系在您的手提行李上。 4. Please attach your business card below or fill up the information. 推荐人请在下面框中贴上您的名片,如不贴名片,则请详细填写框中各项。', '形容词: attachable 名词: attachment 过去式: attached 过去分词: attached 现在分词: attaching 第三人称单数: attaches');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rib', '[rɪb]', 'n.肋骨；肋状物 vt.装肋于；用肋状物支撑', '1. How many ribs does a man have? 一个人有几条肋骨？ 2. He broke a rib when he fell off his horse. 他从马上摔下来折断了一根肋骨。 3. God used this rib to make a woman. 上帝用这根肋骨创造了女人。 4. He has broken a rib and the doctor has strapped it up. 他断了一根肋骨，医生已包扎好了。', '过去式: ribbed 过去分词: ribbed 现在分词: ribbing 第三人称单数: ribs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flux', '[flʌks]', 'n.流量；变迁；助熔剂 vt.使熔化；使泻；涨 vi.熔化', '1. There was no flux, no people and no business. 没有流量，没有人气，没有生意。 2. Variation in the ascertained flux depends on a number of factors. 已探知的流量的变更依赖许多因素。 3. The world is in continuous flux and is impermanent. 世界变迁不已，并非是常久不变的。 4. The neutrality flux must be used before soldering . 焊接时要求用中性助焊剂。 5. Melting behavior of silica flux in the converting process of high grade copper matte was investigated. 研究了高品位铜冰铜转炉吹炼石英熔剂熔化行为。', '过去式: fluxed 过去分词: fluxed 现在分词: fluxing 第三人称单数: fluxes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('quibble', '[\'kwɪbl]', 'v.争论；推托；说模棱两可的话；说俏皮话；谬论 n.吹毛求疵；遁辞；谬论；双关话', '1. Don\'t quibble about unimportant things with me. 别为了琐碎的小事和我狡辩。 2. Stop quibbling about the use of the comma. 别再争辩逗号的用法了。 3. When heaven gives a sign,a wise man does not quibble. 当老天爷给了启示，聪明人是决不含糊的。 4. Such a quibble did not trouble Livingston and his friends. 这种诡辩并没有把利文斯顿和他的朋友难倒。 5. The only quibble about this book is the lack of colour illustrations. 这本书唯一的小瑕疵就是缺少彩色图解。', '名词: quibbler 过去式: quibbled 过去分词: quibbled 现在分词: quibbling 第三人称单数: quibbles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('coalition', '[ˌkoʊə\'lɪʃn]', 'n.结合；联合；联盟', '1. There is no coalition of members of the economy. 这种经济的各部门之间不存在联合。 2. The two parties have united to form a coalition. 这两个党已结成联盟。 3. After the election, the coalition fragmented. 选举之后，联盟瓦解了', '名词: coalitionist');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pullet', '[\'pʊlɪt]', 'n.小母鸡；[美俚]小姑娘', '1. We first need to understand pullet nutrition and reproductive development. 我们首先要了解小母鸡营养与繁殖的进展。 2. But instead the mother hen took the chick under her wing.The little pullet felt warm and safe there. 但母鸡反而把小鸡拥在翅膀里，小母鸡觉得好温暖，充满安全感。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('swill', '[swɪl]', 'v.冲洗；狂饮；流动 n.冲洗；猪饲料', '1. Please swill out the dirty basin. 请把这脏脸盆涮一下。 2. Make sure the garage is well swilled out. 请务必将车库里里外外都冲洗干净。 3. The rugby players were swilling mugs of beer at the bar. 橄榄球运动员正在酒吧间痛饮啤酒。 4. Give the pail a good swill (out). 好好冲洗水桶。', '名词: swiller 过去式: swilled 过去分词: swilled 现在分词: swilling 第三人称单数: swills');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('evildoer', '[\'iːvəl\'duːə]', 'n.为恶者；做坏事的人', '1. Hong evildoer had destroyed fists. 洪秀全曾经双拳毁妖孽。 2. Your suggestion can only aid the evildoer! 你的做法简直是为虎添翼！ 3. The Lord shall repay the evildoer according to his wickedness. 耶和华会照着恶人所作的恶来报应他。 4. Don\'t set free a tiger.; Don\'t let an evildoer go unpunished. 不能纵虎归山。', '名词: evildoing');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('undisputable', '[ˌʌndɪ\'spjuːtəbəl]', 'adj.无可置否的；无疑问的', '1. Microsoft is an undisputable software giant. 微软是软件业无可争辩超强企业。 2. Business\'s promotion behavior itself undisputable. 商家的促销行为本身无可厚非。 3. It is undisputable about this point . 这一点是没有争论余地的。 4. This is an undisputable fact, it is also an encouraging sign. 这已是一个不争的事实,也是一种可喜的现象。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inculcate', '[ɪn\'kʌlkeɪt]', 'vt.谆谆教诲；教育', '1. We failed to inculcate students with love of knowledge. 我们未能通过谆谆教诲使学生们热爱知识。 2. Classical schools inculcate wisdom and virtue. 经典学校在智慧和美德方面诲人不倦。 3. Schools inculcate children with patriotic ideas. 学校给孩子们进行爱国教育。 4. They inculcate all their children with the will to succeed. 他们向子女反复灌输立志成功的决心。', '名词: inculcation 过去式: inculcated 过去分词: inculcated 现在分词: inculcating 第三人称单数: inculcates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('indigent', '[\'ɪndɪdʒənt]', 'adj.贫穷的；贫困的；<古>欠缺的', '1. The town government is responsible for assistance to indigent people. 镇政府负责给穷人提供帮助。 2. I grown up in the condition, which with indigent matter but full of love. 我是在物质条件贫乏但却充满爱心的环境下长大。', '副词: indigently');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vaunting', '[\'vɔːntɪŋ]', 'adj.吹嘘的；骄慢的', '1. She is vaunting her successes to all of us. 她正向大家炫耀她的成就。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('predicament', '[prɪ\'dɪkəmənt]', 'n.困境', '1. They tried to weasel out of the predicament. 他们试图摆脱这种困境。 2. A loan of money would help me out of my predicament. 只需一笔贷款就能帮我摆脱困境。 3. I suddenly found myself in an awkward predicament. 我突然发现自己处于困境中。', '形容词: predicamental 副词: predicamentally');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('zephyr', '[\'zefər]', 'n.西风；和风；徐风', '1. Instead, zephyr, the most gentle of winds, carried her away. 相反，风向中最温和的西风，将她带走了。 2. I feel very comfortable in the zephyr from the sea. 从海上吹来的和风令我非常惬意。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('protagonist', '[prə\'tæɡənɪst]', 'n.主角；支持者', '1. Everybody is the protagonist in oneself story. 每个人都是自己故事里旳主角。 2. She has created a dashing young man as the protagonist of her new novel. 她在她的新小说中创造了一个精力充沛的年轻人作主角。 3. It was in this role, as the protagonist of the popular cause, that the newspaper captured the imagination of our intelligentsia. 在这种作用中，报纸作为民众事业的倡导者，又激发了我们知识界的想象力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rider', '[\'raɪdər]', 'n.骑士；附件；扶手', '1. In the far distance I saw a rider approaching. 在远处，我看见一位骑士渐渐靠近。 2. The rider forced his horse on through the storm. 骑士迫使他的马在暴风雨中前进。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('despotic', '[dɪ\'spɒtɪk]', 'adj.专横的；暴虐的', '1. Our headmaster is a despotic person. 我们的校长是个专横的人。 2. He is utterly despotic to his subordinates. 他对部属极为专横。 3. He was a despotic emperor. 他是一个暴君。 4. People rose up against the despotic rule of their potentate. 人们起来反抗君主的专制统治。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sententious', '[sen\'tenʃəs]', 'adj.说教的；简洁的；警句的', '1. The document was too sententious and pompous. 这份文件过于说教式的，华而不实。', '副词: sententiously 名词: sententiousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('parochial', '[pə\'roʊkiəl]', 'adj.地方性的；狭隘的；教区的', '1. The old parochial outlook has become a world view. 昔日的那个地方范围的观点已成了一种世界范围的观点。 2. He is rather too parochial in his outlook. 他的眼界未免过于狭隘了。 3. He could bring out the universal element in the most parochial of issues. 他能在最狭隘的问题中揭示出普遍的要素。 4. He is very interested in parochial affairs. 他对教区的事务非常感兴趣。', '副词: parochially 名词: parochialism');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mechanics', '[mə\'kænɪks]', 'n.力学；机械学；(技术的；操作的)过程；手法', '1. The Greek initiated the science of mechanics. 希腊人开创了力学这门科学。 2. Mechanics is taught by Dr. Hill. 力学由希尔博士教授。 3. As she grew older her hobbies included science and automobile mechanics. 随着年龄的增长，科学与自动车机械学也成了她的爱好。 4. He is studying mechanics and now he is learning all the parts of an engine. 他在学习机械学，目前正在学习引擎的所有部件。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('nimble', '[\'nɪmbl]', 'adj.敏捷的；伶俐的；机敏的', '1. He is a nimble climber. 他是个敏捷的登山者。 2. She knitted a pair of mittens for me with her nimble fingers. 她用灵巧的双手为我织了一副手套。 3. The nurse sewed up the wound with nimble fingers. 护士用灵巧的手指缝好了伤口。 4. Habits will make us have two nimble hands and a clumsy brain. 习惯会使我们的双手伶俐而头脑笨拙。', '副词: nimbly 比较级: nimbler 最高级: nimblest 名词: nimbleness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('consonance', '[\'kɑːnsənəns]', 'n.一致；调和；和音', '1. The literary conceptions which prevailed were in consonance with the social structure. 当时流行的文学思想是与当时的社会结构相一致的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sculptor', '[\'skʌlptər]', 'n.雕刻家', '1. The sculptor chipped away steadily at the stone. 雕刻家不断地凿那块石头。 2. The sculptor chiselled the lump of marble into a fine statue. 雕刻家把大理石块凿成优美的雕像。 3. He turned his artistic gifts to good account by becoming a sculptor. 他发挥艺术天才，成了雕刻家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('parody', '[\'pærədi]', 'n.仿作；拙劣的模仿 v.拙劣模仿；作模仿诗文', '1. Time is the wealth of change, but the clock in its parody makes it. 时间是变化的财富。时钟模仿它,却只有变化而无财富。 2. She has become a grotesque parody of her former elegant self. 她成为了以前那个举止优雅的自己的怪诞模仿品。 3. The trial was a parody of justice. 这次审判是对公正的一次拙劣的模拟。 4. His style has often been parodied. 他的风格经常被拙劣地模仿。', '形容词: parodic 名词: parodist 过去式: parodied 过去分词: parodied 现在分词: parodying 第三人称单数: parodies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('jaunty', '[\'dʒɔːnti]', 'adj.轻松活泼的；洋洋得意的；<古>时髦的；有教养的', '1. She cocked her hat at a jaunty angle. 她把帽子歪戴着,一副俏皮的样子。 2. The happy boy walked with jaunty steps. 这个快乐的孩子以轻快活泼的步子走着。 3. His full mustache curled upward in a jaunty, arrogant way. 他的全部小胡子往上翘着，显出一副扬扬得意的傲慢态度。', '副词: jauntily 比较级: jauntier 最高级: jauntiest 名词: jauntiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('relegate', '[\'relɪɡeɪt]', 'v.使降级；流放；移交；委任', '1. Mr. Taylor relegate his project to his son after he have ret. 泰勒先生退休后把他的事业移转给儿子。 2. Will Spurs be relegated to the third division? 斯珀尔斯队会降为丙级队吗?', '名词: relegation 过去式: relegated 过去分词: relegated 现在分词: relegating 第三人称单数: relegates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('idolize', '[\'aɪdəlaɪz]', 'v. 把 ... 当偶像崇拜； 极度爱慕', '1. He is an only child, and the idol of his parents. 他是个独子，是他父母的宠儿。 2. The pop singer is the idol of young people. 这位流行歌手成为年轻人崇拜的偶像。 3. The youngsters greeted their idol with a hail. 那群年轻人向他们的偶像欢呼致敬。 4. The baby boy was the idol of his family. 这小男孩是他家的宠儿。', '名词: idolization 过去式: idolized 过去分词: idolized 现在分词: idolizing 第三人称单数: idolizes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('assertiveness', '[ə\'sɜːtɪvnəs]', 'n.自信；果断', '1. Her assertiveness was starting to be seen as arrogance. 她的自信已开始被认为是自负了。 2. The assertiveness training is very helpful for improving one\'s social skill. 自信训练对提高社交技巧很有帮助。 3. You should learn to use your own assertiveness to get the things you want. 你应当学会用自己的果断得到想要的东西。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('drab', '[dræb]', 'adj.土褐色的；单调的；乏味的 n.邋遢女人；娼妓；少量', '1. There are many drab houses in the smoky mining town. 冒烟的矿内有许多土褐色的房子。 2. The female is generally drab, the male per contra brilliant. 一般来说雌性是黄褐色的，而雄性是色彩鲜明的。 3. The landscape is drab and infested with brick ovens. 景色单调，惟见砖窑遍布。 4. The life of a person who never does anything is dull and drab. 如果一个人的一生什么事情都没有做是多么迟钝和单调。 5. She pay me in drib and drab, not all at once. 她零零星星地付给我钱，而不是一次付清。', '副词: drably 比较级: drabber 最高级: drabbest 名词: drabness 过去式: drabbed 过去分词: drabbed 现在分词: drabbing 第三人称单数: drabs');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('shoulder', '[\'ʃoʊldər]', 'n.肩膀；肩部 v.承担；扛；肩负；(用肩)推挤', '1. The bullet wounded his shoulder. 子弹打伤了他的肩膀。 2. Her hand rested lightly upon his shoulder. 她的手轻轻地搭在他的肩膀上。 3. The bullet went clean through his shoulder. 子弹穿透他的肩膀。 4. We walked in the street shoulder to shoulder. 我们肩并肩走在街上。 5. The manager was ready to shoulder the blame. 经理愿意承担过失。', '过去式: shouldered 过去分词: shouldered 现在分词: shouldering 第三人称单数: shoulders');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('discomfited', '[dɪs\'kʌmfɪt]', 'vt. 使懊恼； 挫败； <古>征服 n. 挫败', '1. He was discomfited by the unexpected questions. 意料不到的问题使得他十分尴尬。', '过去式: discomfited 过去分词: discomfited 现在分词: discomfiting 第三人称单数: discomfits');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('qualms', '[kwɑːlms]', 'n.不安；良心之谴责 名词qualm的复数形式.', '1. I have no qualms about breaking it off with Andy. 和安迪分手，一点也不会令我良心不安。 2. If he had had any qualms,they would have been practical. 假如他曾有过什么不安的话，他们就会讲究实际了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ensue', '[ɪn\'suː]', 'v.跟着发生；继起；因而产生', '1. Observers waited for mayhem to ensue. 观察者等候伤害罪之一种跟着发生。', '过去式: ensued 过去分词: ensued 现在分词: ensuing 第三人称单数: ensues');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('saturated', '[\'sætʃəreɪtɪd]', 'adj.饱和的；渗透的；深颜色的', '1. Screens that must be visible under bright lights or from a distance require high contrast and more saturated colors. 在强光下或者远距离也要能够看清楚的屏幕，需要高对比度和更为饱和的色彩，上年纪的人和视力不好的人需要较大且易读的显示。 2. However, Mumetal is not especially easy to apply, and if it is saturated by an excessively strong field, it will no longer provide an advantage. 虽然高导磁合金有诸多优点，但是这种材料用起来并不是很方便，如果受到强磁场作用而达到磁饱和的话，这种材料就不再具备任何优势了。 3. High-fat dairy products are high in saturated fats, which have been linked to heart disease and cancer. 高脂肪制品在深颜色的脂肪里含量高，通常于心脏疾病和癌病联系在一起。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('arrhythmic', '[ɑː\'rɪðmɪk]', 'adj.无节奏的；心律不整的', '1. The present study demonstrates that sudden arrhythmic death is an important contributor to SIDS. 然而,目前认为在SIDS病例中心率失常易感性基因变易的真实状况的数据不充分。', '副词: arrhythmically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fatten', '[\'fætn]', 'v.养肥；使肥胖', '1. We keep animals in pens to fatten them. 我们把动物关在围栏里把它们养肥。 2. Some people deny themselves the necessaries or comforts of life in order that they may be able to help to fatten a publican. 有些人不要生活必需品和较好的享受，目的是为了可以帮助养肥酒店老板。', '名词: fattener 过去式: fattened 过去分词: fattened 现在分词: fattening 第三人称单数: fattens');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vexation', '[vek\'seɪʃn]', 'n.烦恼；令人生气的事或者引起烦恼之事', '1. What can we do to lessen her vexation? 我们做些什么才能减轻她的烦恼呢？ 2. I usually put down all vexation by mountaineering. 我常藉由登山来抛开所有烦恼。 3. Much to my vexation, I just missed a chance of visiting China. 错过一个访问中国的机会，真气人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('contract', '[\'kɑːntrækt]', 'n.合同；婚约；合约；契约 v.缩小；订合同；缩短；感染（疾病）；招致', '1. They had set a term to the contract. 他们已给合同定了期限。 2. Families sought favourable alliances, either by marriage or contract. 各个家庭通过婚姻或者婚约来建立有力的亲缘关系。 3. Several companies will bid for the contract. 数家公司要投标争取合约。 4. He managed to disengage himself from the contract. 他成功地为自己解除了契约义务。 5. The heat contracted the woollen garment. 高温让羊毛衣缩小了。', '形容词: contractible 名词: contractibility 过去式: contracted 过去分词: contracted 现在分词: contracting 第三人称单数: contracts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('unicorn', '[\'juːnɪkɔːrn]', 'n.(传说中的)独角兽', '1. The sculpture is the mythical unicorn. 这雕塑就是神话中的独角兽。 2. He is modeling a unicorn in wax . 他在用蜡制作独角兽。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('palliate', '[\'pælieɪt]', 'vt.减轻；缓和；辩解', '1. Organizations for writers palliate the writer\'s loneliness but I doubt if they improve his writing. 组织对作家减轻作家的寂寞但是我怀疑如果他们改良他的写作。', '名词: palliation 过去式: palliated 过去分词: palliated 现在分词: palliating 第三人称单数: palliates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('delusion', '[dɪ\'luːʒn]', 'n.错觉；幻觉；妄想；欺骗', '1. Tom was under the delusion that he was a VIP. 汤姆怀有错觉,认为自己是个要人。 2. Your hope of promotion is a mere delusion. 你提升的希望只不过是一种幻觉。 3. He had the delusion that he was a king. 他怀有自己是国王的妄想。 4. His arguments sound convincing but they\'re based on delusion. 他的论据听起来似乎有理，但根本上是欺骗性的。', '形容词: delusional');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('renegade', '[\'renɪɡeɪd]', 'n.叛徒；变节者；判党者', '1. His conversation with the renegade seemed to have taken all the heart out of him. 跟那个叛徒的谈话似乎使他完全失去了勇气。', '过去式: renegaded 过去分词: renegaded 现在分词: renegading 第三人称单数: renegades');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('minuet', '[ˌmɪnju\'et]', 'n.小步舞；小步舞曲', '1. He stepped a minuet gravely and gracefully. 他的小步舞跳得庄重而优美。 2. Mozart found his calling at age five composing his first minuet. 莫扎特5岁时发现了自己的天赋创作出他的第一部小步舞曲。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bolt', '[boʊlt]', 'n.门闩；螺栓；一卷布；弩箭 v.（突然）逃离；闩住；狼吞虎咽；用螺栓固定 adv.挺直地', '1. The bolt slotted smoothly into place. 插销很容易就插上了。 2. We need an eye bolt to fit this valve. 我们需要一个有眼螺栓来固定这个阀门。 3. I saw a man bolt out of our backyard. 我看到一个男人从我们家的后院窜出去。 4. The frightened boy bolted all the doors and windows. 这个吓坏了的孩子闩上了所有的门窗。 5. It annoys me if a lamppost is not bolt upright. 如果灯杆不是笔直的,我就看不过去。', '过去式: bolted 过去分词: bolted 现在分词: bolting 第三人称单数: bolts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('credo', '[\'kriːdoʊ]', 'n.信条', '1. That\"Honesty is the best policy\"is his credo for dealing. “诚实乃上策”是他做生意的信条。 2. We only have an everlasting credo: feet on the ground, before walking in a dream. 我们只有一个亘古不变的信条：脚踏实地，走在梦想之前。', '名词复数: credos');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('aeronautics', '[ˌerə\'nɔːtɪks]', 'n.航空学', '1. Aeronautics enables us to overcome great distances. 航空学使我们能征服远距离。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('imbibe', '[ɪm\'baɪb]', 'v.饮；吸收；吸入', '1. It will imbibe your body with oxygen and help relieve stress. 你将会吸入氧气，帮助自己减压。', '名词: imbiber 过去式: imbibed 过去分词: imbibed 现在分词: imbibing 第三人称单数: imbibes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('numerous', '[\'nuːmərəs]', 'adj.为数众多的；许多', '1. The Earth is only one of the numerous planets in the universe. 地球只是宇宙中众多星球中的一个。 2. Those birds have become more numerous lately. 近来那种鸟变得越来越多了。 3. Numerous interruptions have prevented me from finishing my work. 我屡遭搅扰以致工作未能完成。 4. He appeared, surrounded by his numerous progeny. 他出现时，子女前呼后拥不计其数。', '副词: numerously 名词: numerousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('promenade', '[ˌprɑːmə\'neɪd]', 'n.散步；散步场所；队列前进；方块舞 v.漫步；（舞蹈中的）队列前进', '1. A wide promenade allows many people to walk at the same time. 宽阔的人行道可容许多人同时行走。 2. The Easter promenade is well known as a fashion show. 复活节游行是众所周知的一种时装展览。 3. She promenaded the children along the sea front after lunch. 她午饭后领著孩子们沿著海滨区散步。 4. He promenaded along the beach with his wife. 他和妻子沿着海滩散步。', '名词: promenader 过去式: promenaded 过去分词: promenaded 现在分词: promenading 第三人称单数: promenades');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dictator', '[\'dɪkteɪtər]', 'n.独裁者', '1. The dictator met his doom after ten years of rule. 独裁者统治了十年终於完蛋了。 2. He paid only lip service to the dictator. 他只以空洞的应酬话对付那个独裁者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('apogee', '[\'æpədʒiː]', 'n.最高点；顶点；远地点', '1. My heart reached the throat when scenic railway got to the apogee. 过山车到达最高点的时候，我的心都提到嗓子眼儿了。 2. The markets recovered quickly and the dotcom bubble reached its apogee. 金融市场很快恢复元气，而互联网泡沫则达到其最高点。 3. Orbit has an apogee of 200 miles from the earth. 这个轨道最远点在离地球200英里的地方。 4. Apogean tides occur when the moon is at the apogee of its orbit. 远月潮在月球位于其轨道的最远点时发生。', '形容词: apogean');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inexpedient', '[ˌɪnɪk\'spiːdiənt]', 'adj.不适当的；不明智的', '1. It would be inexpedient to inform them at this stage. 在目前阶段就通知他们很不妥当。', '副词: inexpediently 名词: inexpedience');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ritual', '[\'rɪtʃuəl]', 'n.仪式；典礼；宗教仪式；固定程序 adj.仪式的；老规矩的；惯常的', '1. Don\'t be overly solemn or feel that you are taking part in some special ritual; 不要太严肃,或觉得自己正在进行某种仪式; 2. She objects to the ritual of organized religion. 她反对规范的宗教仪规。 3. A strange ritual was enacted before our eyes. 在我们眼前展现出一种奇特的仪式. 4. He performed his ablution before the ritual. 他在典礼前沐 5. So nightly baths have become a part of their ritual even to this day. 所以晚间沐浴成为他们结束一天仪式的一部分。', '副词: ritually');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('narcotic', '[nɑːr\'kɑːtɪk]', 'n.麻醉药；镇静剂；毒品 adj.麻醉的；催眠的', '1. I felt comfortable on narcotic effect. 在麻醉剂的作用下我感到舒服些。 2. Narcotics are a major threat to health. 毒品是危害健康的大敌。 3. He warned against the use of narcotic drugs. 他警告不要使用麻醉药物。', '副词: narcotically');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('penalty', '[\'penəlti]', 'n.处罚；惩罚；不利；罚球', '1. A penalty clause was written into the contract. 在合同中写入了一项罚款条款。 2. She has paid the penalty for her crimes with five years in prison. 她因犯罪受到惩罚被判刑五年。 3. One of the penalties of fame is that people point at you on the street. 当了名人的麻烦之一是在街上被人指指点点。 4. One of the penalties of fame is loss of privacy. 成名的弊端之一是失去了私人活动自由。', '名词复数: penalties');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('allegory', '[\'æləɡɔːri]', 'n.寓言；讽喻；寓意', '1. The film is an iconoclastic allegory. 电影是一个关于破坏的寓言。 2. He opens his prophecy by describing a plague of locusts, an allegory of the disasters to come upon a faithless people. 他首次预言是关于蝗虫的灾害，这是一则对无信仰的人的灾难的寓言。 3. Let me share with you a beautiful allegory. 让我与您分享一个美好的讽喻。 4. This is relayed to Montag as an allegory of society. 孟泰格将此视作社会的讽喻。', '名词: allegorist 名词复数: allegories');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('warranty', '[\'wɔːrənti]', 'n.保单；根据；保修期', '1. It is foolish to buy a car without a warranty . 购买没有保单的汽车是愚蠢的. 2. Yes, I have a one-year warranty. 是的，我有一年的保修单。 3. What warranty have you for doing this? 你这样做有什么根据? 4. This machine is still under warranty. 这台机器仍在保修期内。', '名词复数: warranties');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('zealotry', '[\'zelətri]', 'n.狂热；狂热的行为；狂言', '1. For most of the Guise family, religious zealotry was not a motive. 所以对于大多数的吉斯家族，宗教狂热并不是动机。 2. But at a time when the western world is battling to defend free speech against religious zealotry, they look particularly indefensible. 但每次当西方社会奋起身来为他们的言论自由辩护以反抗宗教狂热时，他们看起来却是那么的无言以辩。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('supernova', '[ˌsuːpər\'noʊvə]', 'n.[天]超新星', '1. This image shows the entire region around the supernova. 这张图像显示了超新星周围的整个区域。 2. The hot gas will be heated further by any supernova which go off in the galaxy. 热气体将被星系中爆发的任何超新星进一步加热。', '名词复数: supernovae');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('grisly', '[\'ɡrɪzli]', 'adj.可怕的；恐怖的', '1. Robbing graves is grisly. 盗墓是可怕的。 2. The sheriff is investigating a grisly murder. 探长在调查一起令人发指的谋杀案。 3. It is a grisly night. 恐怖的一夜。 4. The girls screamed when the grisly remains of the half-eaten corpses on the screen were shown. 当屏幕上显示出尸体被吃掉一半的恐怖残骸时，女孩子们尖叫起来。', '比较级: grislier 最高级: grisliest 名词: grisliness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('precarious', '[prɪ\'kerəriəs]', 'adj.不稳定的；不安全的', '1. She makes a rather precarious living as a novelist. 作为小说家，她过着不太稳定的生活。 2. Our financial situation is still precarious. 我们的财政状况仍不稳定。 3. What a precarious situation we were in when the avalanche started! 雪崩发生的时候我们的处境多么危险啊！ 4. He was unable to get down from his precarious position on the rocks. 他无法从岩石危险的位置上下来。', '副词: precariously 名词: precariousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ravage', '[\'rævɪdʒ]', 'v.毁坏；破坏；掠夺 n.破坏；蹂躏', '1. The forests were ravaged by fire. 森林毁于火灾。 2. Is it for you to ravage seas and land? 你认为海洋和陆地将被破坏吗？ 3. Bands of soldiers ravaged the village. 成群的士兵洗劫了村庄。 4. The rape of the countryside had a profound ravage on them. 对乡村的掠夺给他们造成严重创伤。', '名词: ravager 过去式: ravaged 过去分词: ravaged 现在分词: ravaging 第三人称单数: ravages');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('intervene', '[ˌɪntər\'viːn]', 'vi.干涉；干预；介入；调停；插入；阻挠', '1. Don\'t intervene in the affairs of another country. 不要干涉别的国家的事务。 2. It\'s time that men of good sense and good will to intervene. 这该是那些头脑清醒和心地善良的人们出面干预的时候了。 3. You\'d better not intervene in their dispute. 你最好还是不要介入他们的争端。 4. I am powerless to intervene in the matter. 我对调停此事无能为力。', '形容词: interventional 名词: intervenor 过去式: intervened 过去分词: intervened 现在分词: intervening 第三人称单数: intervenes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rail', '[reɪl]', 'n.栏杆；扶手；铁轨 v.抱怨；责骂；以横木围栏；铺铁轨', '1. A towel hung from the rail. 栏杆上搭著条毛巾。 2. We installed a stainless steel towel rail on the wall. 我们在墙上装了一个不锈钢的挂毛巾的横杆。 3. Nobody believes that he can jump over that rail. 没人相信他能越过那个栏杆。 4. Hold on to the rail or you\'ll slip! 抓住扶手，不然你会滑倒的。 5. It is better to fight for good than to rail at the ill 与其抱怨,不如积善', '名词: railer 过去式: railed 过去分词: railed 现在分词: railing 第三人称单数: rails');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('consecrate', '[\'kɑːnsɪkreɪt]', 'v.供神用；奉献；使神圣 adj.被献给神的；神圣的', '1. Who then is willing to consecrate himself this day to the Lord? 今日有谁乐意将自己献给耶和华呢。 2. A doctor\'s life is consecrated to curing sick people. 医生献身于医治病人。 3. I solemnly pledge myself to consecrate my life to the service of humanity. 我郑重地保证自己要奉献一切为人类服务。 4. Who then is willing to consecrate himself this day to the Lord? 今日有谁乐意将自己献给耶和华呢。', '形容词: consecrative 名词: consecrator 过去式: consecrated 过去分词: consecrated 现在分词: consecrating 第三人称单数: consecrates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('plough', '[plaʊ]', 'v.用犁耕田；耕犁；开(路) n.犁；耕地；铲雪机', '1. Peasants can only plough the land plot by plot. 农民犁田只能一块一块地犁。 2. The ground was ploughed and planted with corn. 地翻耕后种上了玉米。 3. We have to plough out the weeds. 我们得犁掉杂草。 4. The tractors will plough on throughout the night. 拖拉机整个晚上都在犁地。 5. The farmer is at the plough. 那个农民在种田。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dissection', '[daɪ\'sekʃn]', 'n.解剖；仔细分析', '1. According to the result of the dissection, the man died from heart attack. 根据解剖结果，此人死于心脏病发作。 2. Her first dissection made her change her mind about becoming a doctor. 她进行了首次解剖后就改变了要当医生的想法。 3. A dissection of your argument shows several inconsistencies. 对你论点作仔细分析后发现一些前后矛盾之处。 4. Your enjoyment of a novel can suffer from too much analysis and dissection. 对一部小说过多的剖析可能会影响你对它的欣赏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bereft', '[bɪ\'reft]', 'adj.失去……的；被剥夺的；失去亲人的 动词bereave的过去式和过去分词.', '1. He was bereft of all hope. 他失去了所有的希。 2. He was knocked down to the ground, bereft of sense. 他被击倒在地，失去了知觉。 3. They are bereft of their dignity. 他们被夺去了尊严。 4. The bereft girl keened her sorrow. 那个失去亲人的姑娘哭出自己的悲痛之情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('cessation', '[se\'seɪʃn]', 'n.终止；（短暂的）停止', '1. The bombardment continued without cessation. 轰炸持续不断地进行着。 2. Death is simply the cessation of the dream in total. 死亡只是全数梦想的停止。 3. Mexico called for an immediate cessation of hostilities. 墨西哥要求立即停止敌对行动。 4. The wise person does not deprecate life nor does he fear the cessation of life. 智者既不会藐视生命，也不会惧怕死亡。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('schism', '[\'skɪzəm]', 'n.分歧；分裂；分立；分派（教会）', '1. A schism appeared in this political party. 该政党内部出现分歧。 2. The Chinese-American schism poses a dilemma for the next president. 中美两国之间的分歧为下一任总统留下一个两难问题。 3. I shouldn\'t exaggerate the schism. 我不应该夸大这种分裂。 4. If another schism like that happen again, they will wind up in bankruptcy. 再发生一次那样的分裂，他们就将破产。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('motif', '[moʊ\'tiːf]', 'n.（音乐的）动机；主题；意念；装饰图案', '1. This simple motif runs throughout the entire score. 整个乐章自始至终都贯穿着这样一个简单的主题。 2. Love is an eternal motif in art and literature. 爱情是文学艺术中的永恒主题。 3. The motif of the picture is about peace. 这幅画的主题是和平。 4. This motif is concealed for a month or two. 他这个念头在头两个月还潜而不露。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('coven', '[\'kʌvn]', 'n.(尤指十三个) 女巫的集会；大聚会', '1. I think this is perfect for your weekly meetings at the coven. 我认为这件很适合你周末的聚会。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('prosecute', '[\'prɑːsɪkjuːt]', 'vt.起诉；告发；从事；彻底进行 vi.起诉；担任检察官', '1. Trespassers will be prosecuted. 闲人免进，违者必究。 2. He was prosecuted for exceeding the speed limit. 他被告发超速行驶。 3. He vowed that he would prosecute them for fraud. 他郑重宣布将起诉他们犯有欺诈罪。 4. We should never prosecute the innocent. 我们决不应控告无辜的人。 5. The police decided not to prosecute. 警方决定不予起诉。', '形容词: prosecutable 过去式: prosecuted 过去分词: prosecuted 现在分词: prosecuting 第三人称单数: prosecutes');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('insurgent', '[ɪn\'sɜːrdʒənt]', 'adj.叛乱的；起义的 n.叛乱分子；反对派', '1. The insurgent mob assembled at the gate of the city park. 叛变的暴徒聚在市立公园的门口。 2. Insurgent forces were reported advancing in the region. 据报导，起义军在个地区正向前推进。 3. The risk of insurgent attacks is only part of the problem. 害怕被游击队的攻击只是问题的一小部分。 4. After a prolonged siege, the town was rendered up to the insurgents. 经过长时间包围之后，这个小镇已被起义军攻克。', '副词: insurgently');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pucker', '[\'pʌkər]', 'v.使折叠；起皱 n.褶皱；<口>慌张', '1. The dress fitted badly and puckered at the waist. 这件连衣裙不合身，腰部很皱。 2. The child\'s face puckered up and he began to cry. 那孩子脸一皱哭了起来。 3. His morning-coat fits him without a pucker. 他的晨礼服非常合身,穿起来连一条皱纹也没有。 4. How late you come! You made me in a pucker. 你怎么来得这么晚，真把人急死啦!', '过去式: puckered 过去分词: puckered 现在分词: puckering 第三人称单数: puckers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('sawdust', '[\'sɔːdʌst]', 'n.锯屑', '1. Sawdust was scattered on the floor. 地板上撒上了锯木屑。 2. They had been sawing; that was why they were covered in the sawdust. 他们一直在锯木头，因此弄得满身都是锯末。', '形容词: sawdusty');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('polymath', '[\'pɑːlimæθ]', 'n.博学的人 adj.知识广博的', '1. Susan, pressed to define the word “polymath,“ was both sweet and solemn. 苏珊不甘示弱,说“博学者”是可爱的也是严肃的。 2. Tim Gowers has an interesting post on the problem of scaling up the Polymath project to involve more contributors. 总结此期的题目是什么声音让你抓狂以及你为什么抓狂。 3. Kennedy warrants praise for the breadth of these polymath ambitions,aided though he was by five research assistants. 尽管肯尼迪有五个助手帮助，他仍以其博大的志向而受到称赞。 4. If the British won Polymath half the time, this would be “more than expected”. 如果“博学者”奖半数情况下由英国人摘取，那才叫“多于预期”。', '形容词: polymathic 名词: polymathy');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('humdrum', '[\'hʌmdrʌm]', 'adj.单调的；乏味的 n.乏味的谈话；无聊', '1. After his years of adventure, he could not settle down to a humdrum life. 多年的冒险生涯使他无法安下心来过这种单调的生活。 2. The accountant said it was the most humdrum day that she had ever passed. 会计师说这是她所度过的最无聊的一天。 3. Imagination raises a man above the humdrum of life. 想象使人从单调无聊的生活中解脱出来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('melancholy', '[\'melənkɑːli]', 'n.忧郁；忧愁；悲伤 adj.忧沉的；使人悲伤的', '1. Melancholy is the preponderant mood of the poem. 忧郁的感情是该诗的基调。 2. The melancholy of Antonio is caused by the serious social background rather than his own personality. 剧中安东尼奥的忧郁不仅是个性使然,更具有沉重的社会背景 3. Her sweet words dispersed his melancholy. 她的温柔话语驱散了他的忧愁。 4. There in the melancholy, in the dreariness, Bertha found a bitter fascination. 在这里，在阴郁、倦怠之中，伯莎发现了一种刺痛人心的魅力。 5. You must rid yourself of this melancholy mood. 你一定要摆脱这种忧愁情绪。', '副词: melancholily 名词: melancholiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('panther', '[\'pænθər]', 'n.黑豹；美洲豹', '1. The panther is running in the jungle. 那只黑豹正在丛林中奔跑。 2. The panther pounced on the little rabbit,but missed it. 黑豹朝小兔子猛扑过去，不过没扑着。 3. A panther was killed. 一头美洲狮被杀了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('malapropism', '[\'mæləprɑːpɪzəm]', 'n.词语荒唐误用(指误用发音近似而意义不通的词语)', '1. This stirring appeal is spoilt by a malapropism in the last phrase, the word singularity. 译文：一番振奋人心的呼吁就绘羽最后荒唐的词语缪用--奇思异想。 2. Since malapropism is full of features of source language, it is difficult to translate it into target language. 由于飞白辞格极具源语言特色，在翻译成目的语时就增加了难度。 3. Without being a malapropism, a word may still fail to be the right word for the writer\'s purpose, the \"mot juste\". 译文：即使不为荒唐的词语缪用，遣词造句也难免不偏离作者本意，即“非中的之语。” 4. This paper tries to search translation strategies of malapropism from Chinese to English by analyzing samples. 本文试通过译法例析探寻飞白辞格的汉英翻译策略。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('incorporate', '[ɪn\'kɔːrpəreɪt]', 'v.合并；组成公司 adj.合并的；公司组织的', '1. I will incorporate the new findings in my report. 我要把新发现并入我的报告。 2. This company is about to incorporate with its parent company. 这公司将要与其母公司合并。 3. We had to incorporate for a company for tax reasons. 鉴于税务原因，我们得组成公司。', '形容词: incorporable 名词: incorporation 过去式: incorporated 过去分词: incorporated 现在分词: incorporating 第三人称单数: incorporates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('maneuver', '[mə\'nuːvər]', 'vt.巧妙地操纵；使演习；调遣 vi.演习；调遣；用计策 n.演习；策略；调遣', '1. The mouse had a quick wit and was able to maneuver his way out of danger. 老鼠有急智可以灵巧地脱离危险。 2. They have had to maneuver the ship to avoid unforeseen shoals and shallows. 他们必须设法避开无法预见的暗礁和浅滩。 3. The maneuver aims to strengthen special police forces\' emergency response and combat capabilities. 此次演习的目的在于提高特种警力的危机反应能力和战斗能力。 4. An anti-failure maneuver is very important for power system safety and stability in operation. 反事故演习是保证电网安全稳定运行的重要一环。 5. He must have considered the patrol as an effective maneuver. 他思想上一定还以为派兵侦察是条妙计。', '形容词: maneuverable 名词: maneuverability 过去式: maneuvered 过去分词: maneuvered 现在分词: maneuvering 第三人称单数: maneuvers');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('imperious', '[ɪm\'pɪriəs]', 'adj.傲慢的；专横的；迫切的', '1. His imperious look makes us angry. 他那飞扬跋扈的样子令我们生气。 2. We all dislike her for her imperious gesture. 因她那傲慢的样子，我们都不喜欢她。 3. All his imperious orders were obeyed. 他所有那些专横的命令都被服从了。 4. The doll is one of the most imperious needs and, at the same time, one of the most charming instincts of feminine childhood. 娃娃是女孩童年时代一种最迫切的需要，同时也是一种最动人的本能。', '副词: imperiously 名词: imperiousness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vendor', '[\'vendər]', 'n.自动售货机；小贩；卖方；供货商 =vender', '1. The vendor is out of order again. 这台自动售货机又坏了。 2. I bought an apple from the fruit vendor. 我从水果贩那买了一个苹果。 3. A few militant members of the crowd attacked the vendor. 人群中几个好斗的人攻击了那个小贩。 4. The vendor signs a contract with the purchaser. 卖方须与买方签订契约。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ancestor', '[\'ænsestər]', 'n.祖宗；祖先；原种', '1. During the festival the investor investigated his ancestor. 节日期间投资者调查了他的祖宗。 2. They said their ancestor was a famous hunter and a crack hunter. 他们说他们的祖宗是个有名的猎人，也是个神枪手。 3. People who share an ancestor are called relatives. 有同一个祖先的叫做亲戚。 4. She has worshipped her ancestor. 她已拜过她的祖先。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rite', '[raɪt]', 'n.仪式；典礼', '1. The rite is more than a transition into adulthood. 这个仪式不仅仅象征着变成成年人。 2. There is a rite, for example, among my hunters. 比如说，我的那些猎人就有一种仪式。 3. The mock spanking administered to a birthday boy or girl recalls a rite that has long been an integral feature of many initiation ceremonies. 孩子过生日时，假装打他们的屁股使人们回想起一种仪式，这种仪式是很多成人典礼中不可缺少的一个步骤。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('febrile', '[\'fiːbraɪl]', 'adj.发烧的；热病的', '1. Seasonal febrile disease is a general term for all acute febrile diseases resulting from various warm-heat pathogens in the four seasons. 温病是由四季中不同的温热之邪引起的所有急性热病的总称。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('parasite', '[\'pærəsaɪt]', 'n.寄生虫；寄生生物；食客', '1. Rupture of the parasite may result in anaphylaxis. 寄生虫的碎裂可能导致过敏反应。 2. These flies carry a dangerous parasite. 这些苍蝇携带一种危险的寄生虫。 3. The parasite\'s host could be any bird. 该寄生生物的宿主可以是任何鸟类。 4. The result is a repeated signal, and a new limb forms in addition to the one to which the parasite attached itself. 这样的结果将是一种持续的讯号，而一种被寄生生物附著在肢体上所产生的新的生长型态将应运而生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bulk', '[bʌlk]', 'n.体积；容积；大块；大部分；大批 adj.散装的；大量的 vt.使膨胀；使成堆 vi.膨胀；显得重要', '1. It\'s not their weight that makes these sacks hard to carry, it\'s their bulk. 这些袋子难以搬运,倒不是因为重而是体积太大。 2. He heaved his huge bulk out of the chair. 他挺起巨大的身躯，从椅子上站了起来。 3. The bulk of the work has already been done. 大部分工作已经完成。 4. The great bulk of necessary work can never be anything but painful. 大量必须做的工作真令人痛苦。 5. We can manage some bulk carrier within two week. 我们可在两周内安排一些散装船去。 6. A dozen petticoats bulked out her figure. 十几条衬裙把她的身体撑得圆鼓鼓的。 7. The cake bulked up. 蛋糕发起来了。', '过去式: bulked 过去分词: bulked 现在分词: bulking 第三人称单数: bulks');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('currish', '[\'kɜːɪʃ]', 'adj.易怒的；脾气坏的', '1. PETRUCHIO. A good swift simile, but something currish. 彼特鲁乔：应答虽然快，比方却有点狗臭气。 2. The court ask his parent for their nonage child to take responsible for the child\'s currish actions. 法庭要求父母对于其未成年孩子恶意破坏文物的行为负责。', '副词: currishly');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('perishing', '[\'perɪʃɪŋ]', 'adj.严寒的；不耐烦的 动词perish的现在分词形式.', '1. He\'s too perishing mean to pay his share. 他小气极了，连自己的那份钱也不付。 2. I can\'t get in I\'ve lost the perishing key! 我进不去－－我把该死的钥匙丢了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('palliative', '[\'pæliətɪv]', 'adj.减轻的；缓和的；治标的 n.缓和剂', '1. Treatment of electrical burns is palliative. 电烧伤的治疗只起治标作用。 2. Aspirin is a palliative (drug). 阿斯匹林是一种缓解剂。', '副词: palliatively');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('folly', '[\'fɑːli]', 'n.愚蠢；荒唐事 (复)follies: 轻松歌舞剧.', '1. Such a demand borders upon folly. 提出这种要求简直是愚蠢。 2. It is a great folly to try to persuade him. 试图说服他未免太愚蠢了。 3. Some amuse themselves in folly. 有些人以干荒唐事取乐。', '名词复数: follies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('raffish', '[\'ræfɪʃ]', 'adj.放荡的；名誉不好的；艳俗的', '1. He was drinking cheap champagne with a raffish air. 他喝著廉价的香槟酒，样子十分放荡。', '副词: raffishly 名词: raffishness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('coterminous', '[koʊ\'tɜːrmɪnəs]', 'adj.相连的；有共同边界的；（事物或看法）几乎一致的 =conterminous.', '1. No nation imagines itself coterminous with mankind. 没有一个民族把自己想像为等同于人类。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('maculated', '[\'mækjʊˌleɪt]', 'vt.弄脏 adj.有斑点的', '1. Seeds oblate, 6-9 mm in diam., with tawny maculate stripes. 扁球形的种子，直径6-9毫米，具褐黄色的具斑点的条纹。 2. Seeds numerous, ovoid, 3-4 mm, surface maculate, apex acute. 种子多数，卵球形，3-4毫米，表面具斑点，先端锐尖。 3. Capsule oblate, red, ca. 1.5 cm in diam., squarrulose maculate. 扁球形，红色的蒴果，长约直径1.;5厘米，具小糠秕状具斑点。 4. Capsule globose, 6-8 mm in diam., green-white, squarrulose maculate. 直径的蒴果球状，6-8毫米，绿色白色，具小糠秕状具斑点。', '过去式: maculated 过去分词: maculated 现在分词: maculating 第三人称单数: maculates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('flange', '[flændʒ]', 'n.凸缘；边缘；轮缘；【机械】法兰（使管子与管子及和阀门相互连接的零件，连接于管端） v.装凸缘', '1. Every lens has a mounting flange with which it is attached to the camera body. 每个透镜都有一个安装凸缘，依靠它才能把透镜安装到相机上。 2. The bottom flange and the diaphragms must be selected carefully to match the product. 为与产品匹配，需仔细选择底部边缘和隔膜。 3. Tnis measure method supplies reliable data for security analysis and designing installed flange of steam turbine\' s vane. 此项技术可为汽轮机叶片安装轮缘的设计和安全性分析提供可靠依据。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('squab', '[skwɒb]', 'adj.刚孵出的；羽毛未丰的；矮胖的 n.乳鸽；雏鸽；矮胖子；长沙发；垫子', '1. Both men said it takes a lot of food to raise squab. 但他们两人均认为养殖乳鸽需要耗费大量食物。 2. Squab from the United States is generally exported frozen. 美国的雏鸽一般冷冻出口。 3. After all, young pigeons, called squab, have been raised for centuries for food. 毕竟饲养雏鸽供人食用已有几百年的历史了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('down-to-earth', '[\'daʊnt\'ə\'ɜːθ]', 'adj.实际的；谦逊的', '1. This theory seems to have no basis in fact. 这一理论似乎没有实际的根据。 2. We have a lot of practical work to do every day. 我们每天都有许多实际的工作要做。 3. The grand master tapped with his hammer, all sat down in their places, and one began reading a sermon on the necessity of meekness. 分会会长敲了一下槌子，大家都各自入座，其中一人宣读有关谦逊的必要性的训词。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('liaison', '[li\'eɪzɑːn]', 'n.联络；(男女间)私通', '1. Please send us a technical liaison letter about it. 请给我们一份有关此事的技术联络单。 2. He provided a liaison with the guerrillas. 他为游击队提供了联络渠道。 3. He had already contracted a liaison with some girl. 他和某个姑娘私通。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('woe', '[woʊ]', 'n.悲哀；苦痛；不幸；困难 int.用来表达悲伤或惊慌', '1. He inclined his ear to her tale of woe. 他倾听她讲述悲哀的故事。 2. Our two peoples are brothers sharing weal and woe. 我们两国人民是患难与共的兄弟。 3. She was extremely agitated as she poured forth her tale of woe. 在倾吐自己的不幸遭遇时，她情绪非常激动。 4. So far there is no magic bullet for economic woe. 到目前为止还没有解决经济困难的妙法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('rhythmic', '[\'rɪðmɪk]', 'adj.有节奏的；有韵律的', '1. The rhythmic music can be hypnotic. 有节奏的音乐有催眠作用。 2. Rhythmic speech or writing is like waves of the sea. 有韵律的演讲或写作就像海里的波涛。 3. In the bottom of these people,the spirit dwells in rhythmic silence. 在这种人的心里', '副词: rhythmically 异体字: rhythmical');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('gauche', '[ɡoʊʃ]', 'adj.笨拙的；粗鲁的；不善交际的', '1. He now seems gauche and uninteresting. 他显得又笨拙又古板。 2. He\'s rather gauche; he hasn\'t found his feet socially yet. 他蛮笨拙的,到现在还找不到在这社会上的立足之地。 3. I find him terribly gauche. 我认为他太不圆通了。', '副词: gauchely 名词: gaucheness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('disfigure', '[dɪs\'fɪɡjər]', 'v.使丑陋；损毁(外貌等)', '1. The accident disfigured him for life. 那次事故使他毁容，终生无法恢复。 2. This landscape is disfigured by a power station. 风景被发电厂破坏了。', '名词: disfiguration 过去式: disfigured 过去分词: disfigured 现在分词: disfiguring 第三人称单数: disfigures');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('deficiency', '[dɪ\'fɪʃnsi]', 'n.缺乏；不足；缺陷；缺点', '1. I have a slight calcium deficiency. 我有点缺钙。 2. The result in either case is an energy deficiency. 不论哪种情况结果都会导致能量损失。 3. Things will go much better if people of the same trade make up the other\'s deficiency from their own surplus. 同行业之间互通有无，调剂余缺，事情就好办得多了。 4. The deficiency of this plan is very clear and it can\'t possibly succeed. 这项计划的缺陷是很明显的，它不可能成功。', '名词复数: deficiencies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('categorical', '[ˌkætə\'ɡɔːrɪkl]', 'adj.绝对的；分类的', '1. The judgement was harsh and categorical. 这个说法是够尖刻的，够干脆的。 2. He has gone wiggle-waggle and cannot be persuaded to categorical. 他犹豫不决，无法劝他持明确的态度。 3. A categorical arrangement of specimens is needed to show the visitors. 需要标本的分类排列展示给访问者看。', '副词: categorically 异体字: categoric 名词: categoricalness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('salient', '[\'seɪliənt]', 'adj.突出的；显著的；跳跃的 n.突出部分', '1. The salient point of his plan is summed up in this report. 他的计划的要点在这个报告中酌此概括。 2. Honesty is his most salient characteristic. 诚实是他最显著的特点。 3. She pointed out all the salient feature of the building. 她指出了该建筑物的全部显著特征。 4. The Germans withdrew to the partly prepared Hagen line at the base of the salient. 德国的部分军队已经撤到哈根防线。', '副词: saliently 名词: salientness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('amputate', '[\'æmpjuteɪt]', 'v.切断；截（肢）', '1. It may be necessary to amputate his foot. 切除他的脚是必要的。 2. Her arm is so badly injured they will have to amputate (it). 她的胳膊伤势严重，他们不得不锯掉(它). 3. Doctor had to amputate his arm to save his life. 医生必须将他的手臂截肢来保全他的生命。 4. Her leg was so badly damaged that the doctors had to amputate. 她的那条腿伤得很厉害，医师只得将其截除。', '名词: amputation 过去式: amputated 过去分词: amputated 现在分词: amputating 第三人称单数: amputates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('vintage', '[\'vɪntɪdʒ]', 'n.收获；年代(葡萄；葡萄酒);制造年代；一组具有共同特征的人或事情 adj.佳酿的；古典的；优质的', '1. The vintage was later than usual last year. 去年葡萄收获季节较平常晚。 2. What vintage is this wine? 这种酒是哪一年酿造的？ 3. He have some rare old vintage in his collection of wine. 在他的酒类收藏中有一些名贵的陈年葡萄酒。 4. We can infer from the device on the trademark that the wine is vintage. 从商标上的纹章我们可以推断出这瓶红酒是陈年佳酿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('exposure', '[ɪk\'spoʊʒər]', 'n.暴露；揭露；胶片；曝光时间；(在电视、报纸等媒体上的)亮相；挨冻', '1. Exposure of the body to strong sunlight can be harmful. 身体受烈日暴晒会造成伤害。 2. Her skin was dry after exposure to the wind. 经过风吹后她的皮肤很干。 3. His election toppled down due to the exposure of his bribery. 他的竞选因为受贿被揭露而失败了。 4. How many exposures have you left? 还剩多少底片没有照？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('irate', '[aɪ\'reɪt]', 'adj.发怒的；生气的', '1. He dragged the irate fellow to the door. 他把那个发怒的家伙拖到门口。 2. The irate animal made for us,coming at a full jump. 那头发怒的动物以最快的速度向我们冲过来。', '副词: irately 名词: irateness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('surmount', '[sər\'maʊnt]', 'vt.克服；越过；登上 ... 最高点', '1. I think most of these obstacles can be surmounted. 我认为这些障碍大多数都是可以克服的。 2. We had many problems to surmount before we could start the project 我们得克服许多困难才能著手做这项工作. 3. The true love, should surmount the life the length, the mind width, the soul depth. 真正的爱，应该超越生命的长度、心灵的宽度、灵魂的深度。 4. I want to prove that sense can surmount impulse. 我要证明理智是可以战胜冲动的.', '形容词: surmountable 名词: surmounter 过去式: surmounted 过去分词: surmounted 现在分词: surmounting 第三人称单数: surmounts');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lapse', '[læps]', 'n.过失；流逝；间隔；堕落；失效 vi.流逝；失效；堕落；停止 vt.使失效', '1. The man admitted driving over the speed limit and apologized for the lapse. 这名男子承认超速行驶,并且为自己的过失道歉。 2. I started to eat the peas with my hands, but I don\'t think anyone noticed my little lapse. 我开始用手吃豌豆，但我想没有人注意到我的小错误。 3. The lapse of time is irreversible. 时光流逝不可逆转。 4. The lapse of year will never efface that scene of ruin from my memory. 时光的流逝绝不会把那废墟的景象从我的记忆中冲淡。 5. The days lapsed away. 日子在不知不觉之中过去。', '名词: lapser 过去式: lapsed 过去分词: lapsed 现在分词: lapsing 第三人称单数: lapses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('glisten', '[\'ɡlɪsn]', 'v.闪光；闪耀 n.闪亮；闪耀', '1. The street glistened in the rain. 街道在雨水中闪光。 2. Her eyes glistened with tears. 她眼中的泪水在闪烁。 3. I watched the moonlight glisten on the waters of Laguna Beach. 我凝视着倒映在拉古纳湾水面上的月光。', '过去式: glistened 过去分词: glistened 现在分词: glistening 第三人称单数: glistens');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('ore', '[ɔːr]', 'n.矿石；矿', '1. We will make an assay of the ore that he brought. 我们将对他带来的矿石做实验鉴定。 2. The ore is smelted in this large factory. 这个大型工厂里熔炼矿石。 3. This is an area rich in ore. 这里是个矿产丰富的地区。 4. But few of them had actually dug up any ore. 然而他们中只有少数几个确实挖了矿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('colloquial', '[kə\'loʊkwiəl]', 'adj.口语的；会话的', '1. Colloquial expression is an important property of spoken English. 口语惯用语是英语口语的一个重要组成部分。', '副词: colloquially 名词: colloquialness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('suffrage', '[\'sʌfrɪdʒ]', 'n.投票；选举权；参政权', '1. The voters gave their suffrage to him. 投票人都投票选他。 2. They robbed thousands of voters of their suffrage. 他们剥夺了成千上万选民的选举权。 3. The question of woman suffrage sets them at variance. 妇女参政的问题使他们发生争执。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('fertilizer', '[\'fɜːrtəlaɪzər]', 'n.肥料', '1. The stalks will rot and make good fertilizer. 杆儿腐烂后会成为很好的肥料。 2. Crushed bones make one of the best fertilizers. 碎骨是最好的肥料之一。 3. Farmers bartered rice for fertilizer. 农民们用大米换肥料。 4. The tractor hauled the fertilizer away. 拖拉机把肥料拉走了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pertain', '[pər\'teɪn]', 'vi.关于；从属；适合', '1. This letter does not pertain to politics. 这封信的内容与政治无关。 2. Learning the specific set of vocabulary words that pertain to one\'s business becomes a simple task. 学习和自己行业有关的这组特殊字汇成为一件简单的工作。 3. They own the house and the land pertaining to it. 他们拥有这栋房子以及附属于它的土地。 4. It does not pertain to the young to instruct their elders. 年轻人不应该对老年人发号施令。', '过去式: pertained 过去分词: pertained 现在分词: pertaining 第三人称单数: pertains');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('conformity', '[kən\'fɔːmətɪ]', 'n.一致；符合；遵守', '1. His behavior was in conformity with his ideals. 他的行为与他的理想一致。 2. Houses have to be built in conformity with local codes. 房子一定要造的符合当地法规。 3. His conformity was only pretending. 他的遵从只是一种假像。 4. We should act in conformity with the rules. 我们应该依照规定行事。', '名词复数: conformities');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('piecemeal', '[\'piːsmiːl]', 'adj.零碎的；逐渐的 adv.逐个地；零碎地', '1. I\'ve only had a piecemeal account of what happened. 我对发生的事情只有支离破碎的了解。 2. The gradual and piecemeal change was welcomed by most people. 这种一点一点渐进的改变受到大多数人的欢迎。 3. We have to destroy it piecemeal. 要解决它，就要一个一个地来。 4. The building was assembled piecemeal. 那座建筑物是一块一块地组装起来的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('bravado', '[brə\'vɑːdoʊ]', 'n.作威；虚张声势', '1. His bravado cost him the job. 他的这种张狂气势令他丢了工作机会。 2. Their behaviour was just sheer bravado. 他们的行为完全是虚张声势。 3. He needs no bravado to mesmerize spectators. 他不需要虚张声势给观众催眠。', '名词复数: bravados');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('baffle', '[\'bæfl]', 'v.困惑；难倒；阻碍；受挫 n.挡板；隔音板；反射板；困惑', '1. Police are baffled as to the identity of the killer. 警方不解凶手是谁。 2. One of the exam questions baffled me completely. 有一道试题把我完全难住了。 3. She baffled all our attempts to find her. 她千方百计不让我们找到她。', '名词: bafflement 过去式: baffled 过去分词: baffled 现在分词: baffling 第三人称单数: baffles');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pulse', '[pʌls]', 'n.脉搏；脉冲；[植]豆类 v.搏动；跳动', '1. His pulse is not very regular. 他的脉搏不很规则。 2. The excitement quickened my pulse. 激动使我的心跳加快。 3. I could feel a fluttering pulse. 我感到脉搏跳动。 4. The machine emits sound pulses. 这台机器可发出声脉冲信号。 5. I could feel blood pulsing through my veins. 我感到浑身血液在沸腾。', '过去式: pulsed 过去分词: pulsed 现在分词: pulsing 第三人称单数: pulses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('deceit', '[dɪ\'siːt]', 'n.欺骗；诡计；不诚实', '1. She told him of his old mother\'s deceit. 她向他诉说了母后的欺骗行为。 2. Deceit is a gift, but vengeance is swift. 欺骗可能会获得短暂的利益，但报复也会迅速地随之而来。 3. He was enmeshed in a web of deceit and lies. 他陷入充满诡计和谎言的圈套。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('disquisition', '[ˌdɪskwɪ\'zɪʃn]', 'n.专题论文；学术演讲；研究', '1. Amanda launched into a disquisition about contracts. 阿曼达投入到一篇关于合约的专题论文的写作中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('intricacy', '[\'ɪntrɪkəsi]', 'n.纷乱；错综复杂 (复)intricacies：错综复杂的事物.', '1. The intricacy of software systems has increased significantly. 软件系统的错综复杂程度大大增加了。 2. There is no divine mind or plan behind the order and intricacy of the natural world. 在这么有秩序而精细复杂的自然界的背后,并没有神的智慧或计划。 3. He was lost in the intricacies of a new electric motor. 他全神贯注于一种新式电马达的复杂结构。 4. The teacher introduced his young pupils to the intricacies of geometry. 那教师把几何的复杂的原理教授给他年轻的学生。', '名词复数: intricacies');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('merited', '[\'merɪtɪd]', 'adj.该得的；理所当然的；应得的 动词merit的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. Harry Kewell was the match-winner early in the second half when he blasted a volley past Paul Robinson to deny Spurs the point their boss felt they merited. 科威尔用那个技惊四座的凌空抽射帮助红军奠定了胜局，而热刺教头也承认胜利是红军应得的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('peruse', '[pə\'ruːz]', 'v.攻读；精读；阅读', '1. He is determined to peruse the postgraduate study. 他已决心攻读硕士研究生。 2. Please peruse this report at your leisure. 请在空暇时细读这篇报道。 3. After breakfast he perused the newspapers. 早饭后，他读了各种报纸。', '形容词: perusable 名词: perusal 过去式: perused 过去分词: perused 现在分词: perusing 第三人称单数: peruses');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('coordinate', '[koʊ\'ɔːrdɪneɪt]', 'v.（使）协调；（使）一致；（使）同等 n.坐标；同等的人物；配套服装 adj.同等的；等位的；(大学)男女分院制的', '1. You must coordinate the movements of your arms and legs when swimming. 游泳时你必须使臂和腿的动作相协调。 2. If we coordinate our efforts we should be able to win the game. 如果我们同心协力,我们应该能够打赢这场比赛。 3. You must coordinate what you said with what you did. 你必须使你的言行一致。 4. The filter is defined as a box of coordinates. 过滤器定义的是一个方框的坐标。 5. This coordinate system is called the triad at the point. 这个坐标系叫做该点的三面形坐标系。', '形容词: coordinative 副词: coordinately 名词: coordinateness 过去式: coordinated 过去分词: coordinated 现在分词: coordinating 第三人称单数: coordinates');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('quip', '[kwɪp]', 'v.说俏皮话；托辞 n.妙语；讽刺', '1. The chairman quipped that he would rather sell his airline than his computer systems. 董事长风趣的说道，比起他的计算机系统，他宁愿卖掉他的航空公司。 2. He ended his speech with a merry quip. 他以十分风趣的话结束了演讲。', '形容词: quippy 过去式: quipped 过去分词: quipped 现在分词: quipping 第三人称单数: quips');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('pecuniary', '[pɪ\'kjuːnieri]', 'adj.金钱上的；金钱的', '1. She is so independent that she refused all pecuniary aid. 她很独立，所以拒绝一切金钱上的资助。 2. He received thanks but no pecuniary compensation for his services. 他的服务只得到了一句谢谢却并没有物质上的补偿。 3. The insurance company must compensate you for your pecuniary loss in the fire. 保险公司应赔偿你在火灾中所蒙受的经济损失。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('minaret', '[ˌmɪnə\'ret]', 'n.(伊斯兰教寺院的)尖塔', '1. There is a minaret dedicated to Jesus. 这里有一座献给耶稣的尖塔。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('mongrel', '[\'mʌŋɡrəl]', 'n.杂种狗；杂交动植物；混血儿 adj.杂种的；杂交的；混血的', '1. The little mongrel satisfied the boy\'s desire for a dog. 那只小杂种狗满足了那孩子想要只狗的欲望。 2. Some people call English a mongrel language because it is a mixture of old German and French. 一些人称英文为杂种语言，因为它是旧式德语和法语的混合物。', '副词: mongrelly 名词: mongrelism');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('missile', '[\'mɪsl]', 'n.导弹；投射物', '1. The missile deflected from its trajectory. 导弹已偏离轨道。 2. The smallest deflection of the missile could bring disaster. 导弹有极微小的偏斜也可能酿出大祸。 3. The missile had blown the battleship asunder. 炮弹把战舰炸碎了。 4. A missile was projected into space. 导弹被发射升空。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('guilty', '[\'ɡɪlti]', 'adj.有罪的；内疚的', '1. The court found him guilty. 法官判他有罪。 2. The man was proved guilty of murder. 这个男子被证实犯了杀人罪。 3. A man is accounted innocent until he is proven guilty. 一个人未被证明有罪前，被视为是清白的。 4. His answer evidenced a guilty conscience. 他的回答证明他良心有愧。', '副词: guiltily 比较级: guiltier 最高级: guiltiest 名词: guiltiness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('entourage', '[\'ɑːnturɑːʒ]', 'n.随行人员；周围的事物', '1. Among his entourage was a retired general. 他的随行人员中有一位退休的将军。 2. Eisenhower introduced his entourage to the Pope. 艾森豪威尔向教皇介绍了自己的随行人员。 3. The entourage is the same and the rhythm is the same. 周围的一切还是那样，节奏也一样。 4. How does your entourage support you? 你周围的人怎样支持你?', 'none');
