INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('impenetrable', '[ɪm\'penɪtrəbl]', 'adj.不能穿过的；不可理喻的', '1. Armor plate is impenetrable by ordinary bullets. 装甲板普通子弹打不穿。 2. Some wild pheasants love impenetrable jungles. 有些野雉喜欢生活在密密的丛林里。 3. The motive for the crime was impenetrable. 那起罪行的作案动机叫人捉摸不透。 4. This history book is completely impenetrable to me. 这本历史书我完全看不懂.', '副词: impenetrably 名词: impenetrableness');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('resin', '[\'rezn]', 'n.树脂；松香；树脂制品 vt.涂树脂', '1. Amber is the resin of pine trees that grew very very long ago. 琥珀是古老的松脂。 2. They are made of a common plastic resin. 它们是用一种普通的塑胶合成树脂做成的。 3. From three o\'clock onward they would be burning resin. 从3点钟以后，它们就燃烧着松香。 4. This shelf was made of synthetic resin. 这个架子是合成树脂做的。', '形容词: resinous 过去式: resined 过去分词: resined 现在分词: resining 第三人称单数: resines');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('wean', '[wiːn]', 'v.给(婴儿)断奶；戒掉；放弃', '1. She had her baby weaned a year later. 她在一年后才把孩子的奶断掉。 2. Police weaned him away from drugs. 警察让他逐渐戒毒。 3. The patch enables smokers to wean themselves off cigarettes very gradually. 这张贴片能使吸烟者很缓慢地把烟戒掉。 4. She tried to wean him from playing football. 她试图让他不再踢足球。', '过去式: weaned 过去分词: weaned 现在分词: weaning 第三人称单数: weans');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('forbid', '[fər\'bɪd]', 'vt.禁止；阻止；不许', '1. Smoking is forbidden in this office. 这间办公室禁止吸烟。 2. I forbid you to call me late at night. 我禁止你在深夜给我打电话。 3. Lack of time forbids any further discussion at the point. 由于时间不够，现在不能深入讨论这个问题。 4. Lack of space forbids listing the names of all those who contributed. 篇幅所限,不能一一列出所有贡献者的名字。', '名词: forbiddance 过去式: forbade/forbad 过去分词: forbidden/forbid 现在分词: forbidding 第三人称单数: forbids');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('contempt', '[kən\'tempt]', 'n.轻视；轻蔑', '1. Her gesture was indicative of contempt. 她的动作表示轻视。 2. Such behaviour is beneath contempt. 这种行为令人不齿。 3. They showed nothing but contempt for him. 他们对他轻蔑已极。 4. Her behavior underlined her contempt for him. 她的态度清楚地表示了对他的轻蔑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('context', '[\'kɒntekst]', 'n.上下文；环境；背景', '1. It is usually easier to pick out the meaning of a phrase in a given context. 在特定的上下文中理解一个短语的含意往往要更容易些。 2. In the context of the present economic crisis it seems unwise to lower taxes. 鉴於当前的经济危机，降低税率似乎不妥。 3. This speech needs to be set in the context of Britain in the 1960s. 这篇演说需要放到20世纪60年代的英国这一背景之下来看待。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('famine', '[\'fæmɪn]', 'n.饥荒；极度缺乏', '1. War, famine and flood are terrible evils. 战争、饥荒和洪水都是可怕的灾祸。 2. Famine is often the sequel to war or drought. 饥荒往往是战争或干旱造成的。 3. It\'s impossible to remain unmoved by her reports of the famine. 任何人对她报道的饥荒情况都不可能无动于衷。 4. We are collecting money for the famine victim. 我们在为遭受饥荒的灾民募捐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('snowdrift', '[\'snoʊdrɪft]', 'n.雪堆；被风刮在一起的雪堆', '1. The dad-blamed car got stuck in a snowdrift. 该死的汽车陷在雪堆里了。 2. The fence with the thickest boards created a tall, narrow snowdrift close to the fence that lasted a long time. 有最浓的板的闸极栏建立一种接近于持续长的时间的闸极栏的高，狭窄的雪堆。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('inexpiable', '[ɪn\'ekspɪəbəl]', 'adj.不能补偿的', '1. For this act he is pursued by the Furies, the demonic guardians of mother-right, according to which matricide is the gravest and most inexpiable crime. 为此，他受到母权制的凶恶维护者依理逆司神的追究，因为按照母权制，杀母是不可赎的大罪。 2. inexpiable crimes. 不可抵赎的罪行 3. inexpiable hate 难平息的恨 4. an inexpiable sin 不能赎补的罪过', '副词: inexpiably');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('agreeable', '[ə\'ɡriːəbl]', 'adj.愉快的；和蔼可亲的；欣然同意的；一致的', '1. I enjoyed an agreeable holiday this summer. 今年夏天我度过了一个愉快的假期。 2. We spent a most agreeable day together. 我们在一起度过了非常愉快的一天。 3. I find her a very agreeable woman. 我发现她是个和蔼可亲的女人。 4. To a more agreeable adviser, or one from whom he would be more likely to learn, Mr. Harthouse could never be recommended. 赫德豪士先生表示谁也不能给他介绍一位更和蔼可亲的顾问，或者他会更可能向之学习的顾问了。', '副词: agreeably 名词: agreeability');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('upheaval', '[ʌp\'hiːvl]', 'n.向上的运动；剧变；动乱', '1. The French Revolution was a volcanic upheaval in European history. 法国大革命是欧洲历史上的一次剧变。 2. It was a terrible upheaval when his father died. 他父亲去世时家里一团糟。 3. I can\'t face the upheaval of moving house again. 我无法忍受再次搬家的折腾。 4. Many years ago, Johnson faced a major upheaval in his life. 许多年前，约翰逊遭遇生命中的剧变。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('convoy', '[\'kɒnvɔɪ]', 'n.护航队；护送；护卫；警护 v.护航；护送', '1. Two fighters buzzed the convoy as it approached the coast. 当护航队接近海岸时,两架战斗机飞近示警。 2. In a few hours, the destroyer drew on the convoy. 几小时后，驱逐舰就赶上了护航舰队。 3. The supply ships sailed under convoy. 补给船在护送之下航行。 4. The missiles were moved under convoy. 导弹在护卫之下转移. 5. The troop ships were convoyed across the Atlantic. 运兵船被护送渡过大西洋。', '过去式: convoyed 过去分词: convoyed 现在分词: convoying 第三人称单数: convoys');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('slander', '[\'slændər]', 'n.中伤；诽谤 vt.中伤；诽谤', '1. In the last election, they spattered their rivals with slander 在上届选举中,他们用谣言中伤对手。 2. I gave my ear to what I now know was the malice of slander . 我过去听信了谣言，现在我知道那是恶意中伤。 3. It\'s a malignant slander to me. 这对我是恶意的诽谤。 4. Her company is suing her for slander because of her remarks about their safety record. 由于她发表了关于公司安全记录的言论，该公司正以诽谤罪起诉她。 5. Brothers, do not slander one another. 弟兄们，你们不可彼此批评。', '形容词: slanderous 副词: slanderously 名词: slanderer 过去式: slandered 过去分词: slandered 现在分词: slandering 第三人称单数: slanders');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('lance', '[læns]', 'n.枪矛；矛状器具；鱼叉；配矛骑兵 v.以枪矛攻击；投掷；用柳叶刀切开；快速向前', '1. The horseman aimed his lance at his quarry. 骑手把长矛对准了他的猎物。 2. He was so vain and reckless that he would break a lance or two with his general. 年轻的军官一心取胜，他并不害怕与自己的将军比试一下。 3. It doesn\'t like dragger, but likes lance. 看起来不像是匕首，更像矛。 4. I\'ll break a lance with you in argument. 我要和你辩论，一决胜负。', '过去式: lanced 过去分词: lanced 现在分词: lancing 第三人称单数: lances');
INSERT INTO `gre` VALUES ('dispassionate', '[dɪs\'pæʃənət]', 'adj.冷静的；不带感情的；平心静气的', '1. A journalist should be a dispassionate reporter of fact. 记者应当是对事实作冷静报导的人 2. First offers, no matter how lucrative, must be met with a dispassionate eye. 第一轮出价,不论多么有利可图,一定要冷静面对。 3. You should be dispassionate even if you get some success in the negotiation. 假使在谈判中取得一些成功，你还是保持冷静为好。 4. We all should take a dispassionate look at a problem. 我们都必须用客观的眼光来看待这个问题。', '副词: dispassionately 名词: dispassionateness');
